WEBVTT

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:11.279
...

00:00:11.279 --> 00:00:16.199
Scholastic audio presents...

00:00:16.199 --> 00:00:17.460
Wings of Fire.

00:00:17.519 --> 00:00:22.679
Book 13, The Poison Jungle, by 2ET

00:00:22.679 --> 00:00:26.100
Sutherland, read by Shannon McManus.

00:00:50.159 --> 00:00:55.320
The Lost Continent Prophecy.

00:00:55.380 --> 00:01:00.539
Turn your eyes, your wings, your fire, to

00:01:00.539 --> 00:01:03.479
the land across the sea, where dragons

00:01:03.479 --> 00:01:06.719
are poisoned, and dragons are dying, and

00:01:06.719 --> 00:01:07.980
no one can ever be free.

00:01:08.099 --> 00:01:11.579
A secret lurks inside their eggs.

00:01:11.640 --> 00:01:14.280
A secret hides within their book.

00:01:14.280 --> 00:01:18.659
A secret buried far below may save those

00:01:18.659 --> 00:01:19.620
brave enough to look.

00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:24.180
Open your hearts, your minds, your wings

00:01:24.180 --> 00:01:26.400
to the dragons who flee from the hive.

00:01:26.459 --> 00:01:31.260
Face a great evil with talons united, or

00:01:31.260 --> 00:01:32.879
none of the tribes will survive.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:47.819
Prologue.

00:01:47.879 --> 00:01:51.420
The hive wing city loomed out of the

00:01:51.420 --> 00:01:54.359
savannah, impossibly tall and imposing

00:01:54.359 --> 00:01:56.280
and indestructible looking.

00:01:56.340 --> 00:02:00.060
And honestly, it's big smug aura would

00:02:00.060 --> 00:02:01.500
have been enough reason to burn it down

00:02:01.500 --> 00:02:04.739
in Bryany's opinion, but it was also

00:02:04.739 --> 00:02:07.379
bonus full of their enemies.

00:02:07.439 --> 00:02:10.620
Not to mention that it was made from

00:02:10.620 --> 00:02:12.599
trees that had been stolen from her own

00:02:12.599 --> 00:02:15.659
tribe, the leaf wings, long before she

00:02:15.659 --> 00:02:16.139
hatched.

00:02:16.259 --> 00:02:18.960
She had never known those trees herself

00:02:18.960 --> 00:02:20.400
but she should have.

00:02:20.460 --> 00:02:23.580
They should have lived 100s of years

00:02:23.580 --> 00:02:26.400
whispering to their seedlings and slowly

00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:29.099
reaching toward the light instead.

00:02:29.159 --> 00:02:32.159
They had been murdered, ground up into

00:02:32.159 --> 00:02:34.800
splinters, and mixed into the mash hive

00:02:34.800 --> 00:02:36.419
wings called tree stuff.

00:02:36.479 --> 00:02:38.759
Every hive was made of it.

00:02:38.879 --> 00:02:42.060
Which is why every hive is going to

00:02:42.060 --> 00:02:42.360
burn.

00:02:42.419 --> 00:02:46.680
Eventually, this one was a bit of a trial

00:02:46.680 --> 00:02:47.099
run.

00:02:47.159 --> 00:02:49.259
Bloodworm hive.

00:02:49.319 --> 00:02:51.719
Even the name gave her the creeps.

00:02:51.780 --> 00:02:54.659
She was glad her leaders had chosen one

00:02:54.659 --> 00:02:55.919
so palpably horrible.

00:02:55.979 --> 00:02:58.620
She might have felt a tad less

00:02:58.620 --> 00:03:00.719
enthusiastic about burning the prettier

00:03:00.719 --> 00:03:02.520
jewel hive they'd flown past a few days

00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:02.699
ago.

00:03:02.759 --> 00:03:05.939
Then again, maybe not.

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:08.819
All she had to do was picture the dragons

00:03:08.819 --> 00:03:11.280
inside, and even the sparkly glitter

00:03:11.280 --> 00:03:13.259
bazaar became instantly more sinister.

00:03:13.319 --> 00:03:15.479
But it didn't matter.

00:03:15.539 --> 00:03:18.180
They were here, behind a greenhouse

00:03:18.180 --> 00:03:20.340
outside bloodworm hive in the middle of

00:03:20.340 --> 00:03:22.860
the night, moments away from executing

00:03:22.860 --> 00:03:23.759
their great mission.

00:03:23.819 --> 00:03:26.759
I think it's kind of funny that all the

00:03:26.759 --> 00:03:28.020
hives have greenhouses.

00:03:28.080 --> 00:03:31.080
She said to hemlock and pokeweed.

00:03:31.080 --> 00:03:34.319
It's like the hive wings wiped out all

00:03:34.319 --> 00:03:36.479
the trees, thinking they were so clever.

00:03:36.539 --> 00:03:39.000
And then after they were done, they

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:41.639
realized, oops, plants are kind of useful

00:03:41.639 --> 00:03:42.780
actually.

00:03:42.840 --> 00:03:44.219
Maybe we should make some little houses

00:03:44.219 --> 00:03:45.000
and grow a few.

00:03:45.060 --> 00:03:48.360
She brushed one of her leaf shaped wings

00:03:48.360 --> 00:03:49.680
across the panes of glass.

00:03:49.800 --> 00:03:53.280
Easy enough, once they also stole the

00:03:53.280 --> 00:03:55.500
silk wings fire, I guess, she added.

00:03:55.560 --> 00:03:59.280
Hemlock and pokeweed, as usual, were

00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:02.340
being stoic and boring and ignored her by

00:04:02.340 --> 00:04:05.099
staring grimly off into space, as if they

00:04:05.099 --> 00:04:06.960
were too busy envisioning heroic things

00:04:06.960 --> 00:04:08.460
to trouble with conversations.

00:04:08.520 --> 00:04:12.120
She rolled her eyes, crouched beside them

00:04:12.120 --> 00:04:14.460
and peeked into the jar Belladonna had

00:04:14.460 --> 00:04:14.759
left them.

00:04:14.819 --> 00:04:17.699
Bryany had seen fire before.

00:04:17.819 --> 00:04:20.399
Once when lightning hit a tree and burned

00:04:20.399 --> 00:04:21.480
it to charred ash.

00:04:21.540 --> 00:04:23.699
But she'd never seen it like this.

00:04:23.759 --> 00:04:27.720
A long thread curled quietly inside stone

00:04:27.720 --> 00:04:30.779
glowing, like a bit of captured sun.

00:04:30.839 --> 00:04:32.759
It was so small.

00:04:32.879 --> 00:04:36.540
Especially compared to the giant hive in

00:04:36.540 --> 00:04:36.899
front of them.

00:04:36.959 --> 00:04:39.540
How can this possibly work?

00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:41.040
She whispered.

00:04:41.100 --> 00:04:44.459
How can this tiny bit of fire bring down

00:04:44.459 --> 00:04:45.000
a whole city?

00:04:45.120 --> 00:04:47.639
We follow the plan.

00:04:47.699 --> 00:04:49.199
Hemlock said.

00:04:49.259 --> 00:04:52.319
He gestured the bags of detony and other

00:04:52.319 --> 00:04:54.120
flammable plants they'd brought with them

00:04:54.120 --> 00:04:54.720
from the jungle.

00:04:54.779 --> 00:04:58.079
This would be easier.

00:04:58.139 --> 00:05:00.300
If we had sun do with us.

00:05:00.420 --> 00:05:03.839
Pokweed pointed out, in his deep, slow

00:05:03.839 --> 00:05:07.620
voice, I don't understand why she isn't

00:05:07.620 --> 00:05:07.800
here.

00:05:07.920 --> 00:05:10.259
She's busy.

00:05:10.319 --> 00:05:12.060
Hemlock said curtly.

00:05:12.120 --> 00:05:13.560
Doing what?

00:05:13.620 --> 00:05:15.240
Bryony asked.

00:05:15.300 --> 00:05:17.699
Although she knew perfectly well, he

00:05:17.699 --> 00:05:19.740
would continue to not tell her anything

00:05:19.740 --> 00:05:22.019
about his daughter's mystery activities.

00:05:22.079 --> 00:05:25.379
I thought she was going to help.

00:05:25.439 --> 00:05:27.420
Pokweed said again.

00:05:27.480 --> 00:05:32.339
I thought the plan involved flaming ivy

00:05:32.339 --> 00:05:34.139
growing up the walls.

00:05:34.199 --> 00:05:38.579
It will, Hemlock said, lifting his claws

00:05:38.579 --> 00:05:40.079
and flexing them significantly.

00:05:40.139 --> 00:05:42.839
Pokweed gave him a dubious look.

00:05:42.899 --> 00:05:46.860
Maybe we should wait for her, he said.

00:05:46.920 --> 00:05:49.139
Maybe she'll come soon.

00:05:49.199 --> 00:05:52.019
Pokweed.

00:05:52.079 --> 00:05:55.199
Hemlock said, finally letting a bit of

00:05:55.199 --> 00:05:57.180
exasperation slip into his voice.

00:05:57.240 --> 00:05:58.740
Don't be annoying.

00:05:58.800 --> 00:06:00.660
Hmm.

00:06:00.720 --> 00:06:02.279
Pokweed grumbled.

00:06:02.339 --> 00:06:03.420
That's nice.

00:06:03.480 --> 00:06:05.699
The plan is fine.

00:06:05.759 --> 00:06:08.819
Hemlock picked up the jar and cupped it

00:06:08.819 --> 00:06:09.480
between his talons.

00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:12.240
The glow lit up his face from below

00:06:12.240 --> 00:06:14.100
casting his eyes into shadows.

00:06:14.160 --> 00:06:16.560
We have what we need.

00:06:16.620 --> 00:06:19.139
Not being annoying.

00:06:19.199 --> 00:06:21.060
Pokweed muttered.

00:06:21.120 --> 00:06:23.100
Being sensible.

00:06:23.160 --> 00:06:26.339
Another dragon appeared around the corner

00:06:26.339 --> 00:06:28.500
of the greenhouse, and for a moment

00:06:28.500 --> 00:06:30.540
Bryony tensed, ready to fight.

00:06:30.660 --> 00:06:33.180
But it wasn't a hive wing.

00:06:33.240 --> 00:06:36.540
This dragon had golden rod yellow spots

00:06:36.540 --> 00:06:38.939
on his wings, but the rest of his scales

00:06:38.939 --> 00:06:41.639
were shades of gray, pale and dark

00:06:41.639 --> 00:06:45.300
overlapping, like a chintilla, or a

00:06:45.300 --> 00:06:47.279
snuggled up pile of chintillas.

00:06:47.339 --> 00:06:50.339
She'd only known this silk wing for a

00:06:50.339 --> 00:06:50.459
day.

00:06:50.579 --> 00:06:53.399
But every time she saw him, she thought

00:06:53.399 --> 00:06:55.139
of small, adorable furry things.

00:06:55.199 --> 00:06:58.079
Grayling, she whispered.

00:06:58.139 --> 00:07:02.040
Hi, Briony, he whispered back, smiling.

00:07:02.100 --> 00:07:03.660
Is it done?

00:07:03.720 --> 00:07:05.339
Hemlock interrupted.

00:07:05.399 --> 00:07:08.819
We did the best we could, Grayling said.

00:07:08.939 --> 00:07:11.399
All the soak wings who sleep in the hive

00:07:11.399 --> 00:07:13.500
have been worn to stay near an exit, and

00:07:13.500 --> 00:07:15.180
keep their dragonettes with them so they

00:07:15.180 --> 00:07:16.079
can evacuate first.

00:07:16.139 --> 00:07:18.959
We have members of the chrysalis assigned

00:07:18.959 --> 00:07:21.540
to retrieve our eggs, and the dragonettes

00:07:21.540 --> 00:07:23.759
going through metamorphosis right now, and

00:07:23.759 --> 00:07:25.560
we've sent messages along the webs that

00:07:25.560 --> 00:07:27.839
connect this hive to Jewel Hive and

00:07:27.839 --> 00:07:29.339
Mantis Hive.

00:07:29.399 --> 00:07:30.420
He hesitated.

00:07:30.480 --> 00:07:35.879
If we had one more day, we don't, Hemlock

00:07:35.879 --> 00:07:39.480
said, not unkindly, but with absolute

00:07:39.480 --> 00:07:40.860
finality in his voice.

00:07:40.920 --> 00:07:44.160
Grayling's gaze went to the long bridge

00:07:44.160 --> 00:07:46.439
of silk overhead that stretched toward

00:07:46.439 --> 00:07:47.279
mantas hives.

00:07:47.339 --> 00:07:50.879
It glimmered a little, as if some of the

00:07:50.879 --> 00:07:52.620
starlight was caught in the silvery

00:07:52.620 --> 00:07:53.100
filaments.

00:07:53.160 --> 00:07:56.220
Do you really think the whole city will

00:07:56.220 --> 00:07:56.459
burn?

00:07:56.459 --> 00:07:57.420
he asked.

00:07:57.480 --> 00:07:59.339
And the webs along with it?

00:07:59.459 --> 00:08:02.339
We are not going to set the webs alight

00:08:02.339 --> 00:08:02.819
on purpose.

00:08:02.879 --> 00:08:04.439
Bryany answered.

00:08:04.500 --> 00:08:06.959
But if the hive burns down like we're

00:08:06.959 --> 00:08:07.740
hoping.

00:08:07.860 --> 00:08:10.199
She didn't have to finish the sentence.

00:08:10.259 --> 00:08:12.720
It was pretty clear what would happen to

00:08:12.720 --> 00:08:14.459
the webs that were woven to the top

00:08:14.459 --> 00:08:15.540
levels of the hive.

00:08:15.600 --> 00:08:18.720
When sundew had 1st told them about the

00:08:18.720 --> 00:08:20.879
underground movement of silk wings called

00:08:20.879 --> 00:08:21.959
the chrysalis.

00:08:22.019 --> 00:08:23.939
Briony had thought someone must have

00:08:23.939 --> 00:08:25.319
cracked her very hard on the head.

00:08:25.379 --> 00:08:28.620
She had grown up side by side with Sundoo

00:08:28.620 --> 00:08:30.779
who was only a year younger than her.

00:08:30.839 --> 00:08:33.120
They had both been raised with the

00:08:33.120 --> 00:08:35.700
absolutely certain knowledge that silk

00:08:35.700 --> 00:08:37.980
wings were weak and timid and never stood

00:08:37.980 --> 00:08:38.580
up to anyone.

00:08:38.639 --> 00:08:41.879
And then when Sundew said they needed to

00:08:41.879 --> 00:08:44.159
warn the chrysalis before burning

00:08:44.159 --> 00:08:46.139
bloodworm hive.

00:08:46.200 --> 00:08:49.019
Well, that was truly epic nonsense.

00:08:49.080 --> 00:08:51.419
Wouldn't someone go straight to tell the

00:08:51.419 --> 00:08:52.080
hive wings?

00:08:52.139 --> 00:08:54.419
Wouldn't that ruin the whole plan?

00:08:54.480 --> 00:08:58.139
But then they found grayling, and a few

00:08:58.139 --> 00:09:00.179
other dragons from the bloodworm hive

00:09:00.179 --> 00:09:01.500
chrysalis.

00:09:01.559 --> 00:09:03.179
And now Briny couldn't even think about

00:09:03.179 --> 00:09:04.919
what would have happened if they'd burned

00:09:04.919 --> 00:09:06.419
it without getting the silk wings out

00:09:06.419 --> 00:09:06.720
first.

00:09:06.779 --> 00:09:09.419
She'd never have known Greyling at all.

00:09:09.480 --> 00:09:10.919
He might have died.

00:09:10.980 --> 00:09:13.320
And she wouldn't have known she'd lost

00:09:13.320 --> 00:09:13.559
him.

00:09:13.620 --> 00:09:15.480
All right.

00:09:15.539 --> 00:09:18.120
Grayling said, shaking himself.

00:09:18.179 --> 00:09:20.820
Then how can the chrysalis help?

00:09:20.879 --> 00:09:22.740
You would do that?

00:09:22.799 --> 00:09:25.320
Bryony asked, surprised.

00:09:25.379 --> 00:09:28.620
A spark kindled in hemlock's eyes.

00:09:28.679 --> 00:09:31.139
You could burn it from the inside too.

00:09:31.200 --> 00:09:32.399
He said.

00:09:32.460 --> 00:09:34.019
That would be very helpful.

00:09:34.080 --> 00:09:37.259
Greyling looked up at the hive.

00:09:37.320 --> 00:09:41.639
No, not the hive, Bryany realized.

00:09:41.700 --> 00:09:43.980
He was looking at the webs where he and

00:09:43.980 --> 00:09:46.679
his family lived, the home they had spun

00:09:46.679 --> 00:09:49.139
for themselves, the only home they knew.

00:09:49.200 --> 00:09:53.159
This mission, if it succeeded, would

00:09:53.159 --> 00:09:55.799
leave them lost in the Savannah, with no

00:09:55.799 --> 00:09:56.940
idea where they'd end up.

00:09:57.000 --> 00:10:00.899
You don't have to do anything, she said

00:10:00.899 --> 00:10:03.539
earning herself a frown from hemlock.

00:10:03.659 --> 00:10:05.940
It will be massively dangerous.

00:10:06.059 --> 00:10:09.299
He met her eyes and tipped his head to

00:10:09.299 --> 00:10:09.720
the side.

00:10:09.779 --> 00:10:12.600
I've wanted to fight back against the

00:10:12.600 --> 00:10:15.000
hive wings almost since the day I hatched

00:10:15.000 --> 00:10:16.799
he said softly.

00:10:16.860 --> 00:10:20.759
They let my father die, and they sent my

00:10:20.759 --> 00:10:22.559
brother away to the Setsi hive.

00:10:22.620 --> 00:10:26.159
Lady Bloodworm, is one of the cruelest of

00:10:26.159 --> 00:10:27.120
wasps' sisters.

00:10:27.179 --> 00:10:30.059
That's why the chrysalis here has so many

00:10:30.059 --> 00:10:30.360
members.

00:10:30.419 --> 00:10:33.000
I'm ready to do something real.

00:10:33.120 --> 00:10:34.980
I think we all are.

00:10:35.039 --> 00:10:37.200
Excellent.

00:10:37.259 --> 00:10:38.639
Hemlock said.

00:10:38.700 --> 00:10:41.340
Let's choose locations and plan our

00:10:41.340 --> 00:10:41.639
timing.

00:10:41.759 --> 00:10:45.059
We all have to act fast and as

00:10:45.059 --> 00:10:46.139
synchronized as possible.

00:10:46.259 --> 00:10:50.700
Bryony said to Greyling, Queen Wasp will

00:10:50.700 --> 00:10:52.679
be inside all these dragons the moment

00:10:52.679 --> 00:10:54.059
she realizes what's happening.

00:10:54.120 --> 00:10:57.120
By then, it has to be too late for her to

00:10:57.120 --> 00:10:57.480
stop it.

00:10:57.539 --> 00:11:01.440
I'll show you the plans we have for

00:11:01.440 --> 00:11:01.980
burning.

00:11:02.100 --> 00:11:04.740
Pokweed said lugubriously.

00:11:04.799 --> 00:11:06.600
I can do that.

00:11:06.659 --> 00:11:08.279
Briony jumped in.

00:11:08.340 --> 00:11:11.039
You and Hemlock reviewed the interior map

00:11:11.039 --> 00:11:12.840
of the hive we got from the chrysalis.

00:11:12.899 --> 00:11:15.899
She brushed Grayling's wing with her own

00:11:15.899 --> 00:11:17.639
and beckoned him over to the supplies.

00:11:17.700 --> 00:11:22.019
As she described each plant, how quickly

00:11:22.019 --> 00:11:25.980
it would burn, which ones would spray

00:11:25.980 --> 00:11:28.799
burning oil, she caught Grayling watching

00:11:28.799 --> 00:11:30.419
her with a strange expression in his

00:11:30.419 --> 00:11:30.960
eyes.

00:11:30.960 --> 00:11:35.519
What, she said, putting down a bundle of

00:11:35.519 --> 00:11:37.379
dead palm fronds they had gathered that

00:11:37.379 --> 00:11:39.240
morning along the shore of Dragonfly

00:11:39.240 --> 00:11:39.480
Bay.

00:11:39.539 --> 00:11:43.440
It's just, he hesitated.

00:11:43.500 --> 00:11:46.440
I'm just amazed at how much trouble your

00:11:46.440 --> 00:11:47.279
tribe has gone to.

00:11:47.340 --> 00:11:51.059
All these plans and all this work, just

00:11:51.059 --> 00:11:51.659
to save us.

00:11:51.720 --> 00:11:55.200
Briny tried not to show how startled she

00:11:55.200 --> 00:11:55.500
was.

00:11:55.559 --> 00:11:57.299
To save you?

00:11:57.360 --> 00:11:58.620
She echoed.

00:11:58.679 --> 00:12:01.559
The silk wings, he said.

00:12:01.620 --> 00:12:04.259
You could have left us to rot in Queen

00:12:04.259 --> 00:12:07.200
Wasp's talent, after we abandoned you

00:12:07.200 --> 00:12:09.659
during the tree wars, but you didn't.

00:12:09.779 --> 00:12:11.460
You came back to set us free.

00:12:11.519 --> 00:12:14.100
Oh, the guilt.

00:12:14.159 --> 00:12:17.580
Bryney felt it stabbing all her internal

00:12:17.580 --> 00:12:18.299
organs at once.

00:12:18.360 --> 00:12:21.059
How could she tell him that she'd never

00:12:21.059 --> 00:12:22.980
once thought about the plight of the silk

00:12:22.980 --> 00:12:24.059
wings before she met him?

00:12:24.120 --> 00:12:27.720
That their mission was vengeance, not

00:12:27.720 --> 00:12:28.259
rescue.

00:12:28.320 --> 00:12:32.220
It's not, not, she stammered.

00:12:32.279 --> 00:12:35.340
I mean, we, we are doing it for

00:12:35.340 --> 00:12:35.879
ourselves.

00:12:35.940 --> 00:12:39.240
Honestly, please don't think of us like

00:12:39.240 --> 00:12:41.220
heroes or saviors or anything.

00:12:41.340 --> 00:12:45.299
He flicked his tail. nearly toppling a

00:12:45.299 --> 00:12:46.559
neat pile of dry grass.

00:12:46.620 --> 00:12:49.559
Maybe as friends then?

00:12:49.559 --> 00:12:50.460
he asked.

00:12:50.580 --> 00:12:53.519
That works for me, she said.

00:12:53.580 --> 00:12:56.340
I'm sorry we're burning down your home.

00:12:56.399 --> 00:12:58.919
It's more like a cage anyway.

00:12:59.039 --> 00:13:00.000
He said.

00:13:00.120 --> 00:13:02.759
Where are you going to go after it

00:13:02.759 --> 00:13:03.419
burns?

00:13:03.480 --> 00:13:06.720
We found some underground caves to hide

00:13:06.720 --> 00:13:08.519
in for a few days, she said.

00:13:08.580 --> 00:13:12.240
Belladonna said we had to lie low, so we

00:13:12.240 --> 00:13:13.679
wouldn't lead wasp back to everyone

00:13:13.679 --> 00:13:13.980
else.

00:13:14.039 --> 00:13:17.279
Oh, he said.

00:13:17.399 --> 00:13:20.039
Running his claws over one of the palm

00:13:20.039 --> 00:13:20.580
fronds.

00:13:20.639 --> 00:13:23.879
Any chance there's room in there for a

00:13:23.879 --> 00:13:25.919
small, friendly silk wing?

00:13:25.980 --> 00:13:29.639
She smiled at him, and he made a, sorry

00:13:29.639 --> 00:13:34.139
about this face, or a couple 100 of

00:13:34.139 --> 00:13:34.320
them.

00:13:34.379 --> 00:13:36.899
I'll talk to Hemlock about it.

00:13:36.960 --> 00:13:38.220
She promised.

00:13:38.279 --> 00:13:40.740
She could see the older leaf wing

00:13:40.740 --> 00:13:41.460
beckoning them.

00:13:41.519 --> 00:13:44.159
His talons holding down the scribbled map

00:13:44.159 --> 00:13:45.779
of the interior of the hive.

00:13:45.840 --> 00:13:48.539
Thank you, Grayling said.

00:13:48.600 --> 00:13:51.059
She twined her tail around his.

00:13:51.120 --> 00:13:53.759
Let's go set a fire.

00:13:53.820 --> 00:13:58.200
Part one.

00:13:58.259 --> 00:14:01.019
Roots and sprouts.

00:14:01.080 --> 00:14:03.120
Chapter one.

00:14:03.240 --> 00:14:07.080
Sundoo sometimes like to imagine that she

00:14:07.080 --> 00:14:08.759
could fly all the way around the world

00:14:08.759 --> 00:14:11.100
without stopping, using nothing but her

00:14:11.100 --> 00:14:12.539
fury to keep her going.

00:14:12.600 --> 00:14:16.379
When she got tired, she'd think about all

00:14:16.379 --> 00:14:17.399
the things that made her angry.

00:14:17.460 --> 00:14:24.659
Hive wings, hive wings, hive wings, Queen

00:14:24.659 --> 00:14:28.740
Wasp, the murder of the trees, the

00:14:28.740 --> 00:14:30.360
attempted murder of my entire tribe.

00:14:30.419 --> 00:14:37.799
Hive Wings, Mother and Father, No, those

00:14:37.799 --> 00:14:39.120
weren't allowed on this list.

00:14:39.179 --> 00:14:41.279
Hive wings.

00:14:41.340 --> 00:14:44.940
Sundu imagined stabbing her claws into

00:14:44.940 --> 00:14:47.220
their necks, ripping their smug

00:14:47.220 --> 00:14:50.100
expressions off their faces, choking them

00:14:50.100 --> 00:14:53.100
with strangler vines, releasing fire ants

00:14:53.100 --> 00:14:54.779
into their eyeballs.

00:14:54.840 --> 00:14:57.419
A flash of yellow and black caught her

00:14:57.419 --> 00:14:59.340
eye, and she whipped her head toward it

00:14:59.340 --> 00:14:59.820
with a hiss.

00:14:59.940 --> 00:15:01.679
Sorry.

00:15:01.740 --> 00:15:04.139
Cricket dropped to a different air

00:15:04.139 --> 00:15:05.100
current and called up.

00:15:05.159 --> 00:15:07.019
I didn't mean to startle you.

00:15:07.080 --> 00:15:09.059
You didn't.

00:15:09.179 --> 00:15:10.559
Sundew snapped.

00:15:10.620 --> 00:15:13.620
It was sort of difficult to rage fly on

00:15:13.620 --> 00:15:16.200
the power of hating hive wings when there

00:15:16.200 --> 00:15:18.120
were 2 hive wings flying right alongside

00:15:18.120 --> 00:15:21.000
her, being extremely noisy and

00:15:21.000 --> 00:15:21.659
distracting.

00:15:21.720 --> 00:15:24.960
Also, when one of those high wings was

00:15:24.960 --> 00:15:27.240
sort of practically almost a friend-ish

00:15:27.240 --> 00:15:30.419
kind of dragon, maybe, and the other was

00:15:30.419 --> 00:15:32.820
the size of a large mango, and madly in

00:15:32.820 --> 00:15:33.600
love with sundew.

00:15:33.720 --> 00:15:38.519
Snoodoo, cried the little dragonette, tied

00:15:38.519 --> 00:15:40.019
snugly to Cricket's chest.

00:15:40.139 --> 00:15:43.019
Bumblebee reached her tiny talons towards

00:15:43.019 --> 00:15:43.620
sundew.

00:15:43.679 --> 00:15:45.779
Marbles snoodoo.

00:15:45.840 --> 00:15:48.779
Is that tiny lizard trying to say my

00:15:48.779 --> 00:15:49.019
name?

00:15:49.080 --> 00:15:51.240
Sendu asked, alarmed.

00:15:51.299 --> 00:15:52.980
How did that happen?

00:15:53.039 --> 00:15:55.379
She is very smart.

00:15:55.500 --> 00:15:57.179
Cricket said proudly.

00:15:57.240 --> 00:16:00.480
Not if she thinks she wants my attention

00:16:00.480 --> 00:16:02.100
Sundew pointed out.

00:16:02.159 --> 00:16:04.679
She turned her head north again, beating

00:16:04.679 --> 00:16:05.519
her wings harder.

00:16:05.580 --> 00:16:08.159
There was a dark line on the horizon

00:16:08.159 --> 00:16:08.519
ahead.

00:16:08.580 --> 00:16:10.019
They were almost there.

00:16:10.080 --> 00:16:12.539
The poison jungle.

00:16:12.539 --> 00:16:13.860
Home.

00:16:13.919 --> 00:16:17.820
Or never home, as some of the leaf wings

00:16:17.820 --> 00:16:20.519
called it, but the only home sundew had

00:16:20.519 --> 00:16:20.820
ever known.

00:16:20.879 --> 00:16:24.360
Her tribe's true home, the rest of the

00:16:24.360 --> 00:16:26.879
continent, covered in vast ancient

00:16:26.879 --> 00:16:29.700
forests, only existed in stories of the

00:16:29.700 --> 00:16:31.559
old days and dreams for the future.

00:16:31.620 --> 00:16:34.620
Sundew breathed and flew.

00:16:34.679 --> 00:16:36.840
Each wing beat brought her closer.

00:16:36.899 --> 00:16:41.340
Closer to the thorn sharp, fangs bared

00:16:41.340 --> 00:16:43.620
twisted safety of the poison jungle.

00:16:43.679 --> 00:16:46.919
Closer to the dragon she wasn't allowed

00:16:46.919 --> 00:16:47.460
to think about.

00:16:47.580 --> 00:16:51.059
She felt the pout she kept over her heart

00:16:51.059 --> 00:16:55.320
thump once, twice, again in rhythm with

00:16:55.320 --> 00:16:55.679
her wings.

00:16:55.740 --> 00:16:58.919
It was the only pouch, out of the many

00:16:58.919 --> 00:17:00.960
wrapped around her, that didn't hold

00:17:00.960 --> 00:17:02.820
venomous insects or useful plants.

00:17:02.940 --> 00:17:07.079
Inside, it was nothing but a small jade

00:17:07.079 --> 00:17:07.680
frog.

00:17:07.740 --> 00:17:10.680
Which didn't help with the not thinking

00:17:10.680 --> 00:17:13.740
about, it served, in fact, the opposite

00:17:13.740 --> 00:17:14.160
purpose.

00:17:14.220 --> 00:17:16.920
But sundew still brought it with her

00:17:16.920 --> 00:17:17.220
everywhere.

00:17:17.279 --> 00:17:20.400
As long as her parents, Belladonna and

00:17:20.400 --> 00:17:22.200
Hemlock, didn't know what it meant.

00:17:22.259 --> 00:17:23.700
They couldn't do anything about it.

00:17:23.759 --> 00:17:27.240
Um, sundo?

00:17:27.299 --> 00:17:29.759
Blue asked nervously from her left.

00:17:29.819 --> 00:17:31.740
She tilted her head toward him.

00:17:31.799 --> 00:17:33.839
It was weird to know a silk wing.

00:17:33.900 --> 00:17:35.940
After years of scoffing about how

00:17:35.940 --> 00:17:38.339
beautiful and useless they were, even

00:17:38.339 --> 00:17:38.880
weirder.

00:17:38.940 --> 00:17:41.220
He'd turned out to not be useless at

00:17:41.220 --> 00:17:41.400
all.

00:17:41.460 --> 00:17:43.859
Flame silk.

00:17:43.920 --> 00:17:45.779
I should have been a flame silk.

00:17:45.839 --> 00:17:48.000
If I had the power of fire.

00:17:48.119 --> 00:17:52.079
Well, I sort of do, now that we have

00:17:52.079 --> 00:17:52.380
blue.

00:17:52.440 --> 00:17:55.680
That thought made her uncomfortable, and

00:17:55.680 --> 00:17:56.460
she wasn't sure why.

00:17:56.519 --> 00:17:59.640
She bared her teeth at a passing starling

00:17:59.640 --> 00:18:01.680
and it nearly fell out of the sky in

00:18:01.680 --> 00:18:02.039
fright.

00:18:02.099 --> 00:18:05.339
Blue's wings glimmered azure in the rays

00:18:05.339 --> 00:18:06.420
of the setting sun.

00:18:06.480 --> 00:18:10.680
Um, isn't the poison jungle really

00:18:10.680 --> 00:18:11.279
dangerous?

00:18:11.339 --> 00:18:13.559
Or is that a lie?

00:18:13.619 --> 00:18:15.900
Soretel asked from our other side.

00:18:15.960 --> 00:18:19.559
Like, maybe leaf wings spread stories

00:18:19.559 --> 00:18:22.140
exaggerating how dangerous it is, so that

00:18:22.140 --> 00:18:22.799
no one else would go there.

00:18:22.859 --> 00:18:24.000
That would make sense.

00:18:24.059 --> 00:18:25.079
I bet that's it.

00:18:25.140 --> 00:18:27.420
Sundu laughed.

00:18:27.480 --> 00:18:30.480
How could we spread stories?

00:18:30.480 --> 00:18:31.200
she said.

00:18:31.319 --> 00:18:33.779
We haven't communicated with any silk

00:18:33.779 --> 00:18:36.180
wings or hive wings since the end of the

00:18:36.180 --> 00:18:37.619
tree wars 50 years ago?

00:18:37.680 --> 00:18:39.779
We were supposed to be extinct.

00:18:39.839 --> 00:18:42.180
That was kind of your whole goal

00:18:42.180 --> 00:18:42.539
remember?

00:18:42.599 --> 00:18:45.299
Not our goal.

00:18:45.420 --> 00:18:47.160
Blue protested in distress.

00:18:47.279 --> 00:18:50.400
No, everything you've heard about the

00:18:50.400 --> 00:18:53.460
jungle is true, Sundew said to Sordail.

00:18:53.519 --> 00:18:56.460
Queen Wasp sent a few expeditions to the

00:18:56.460 --> 00:18:59.039
poison jungle looking for resources, and

00:18:59.039 --> 00:19:00.839
trying to make sure no dragons were

00:19:00.839 --> 00:19:01.559
hiding from her there.

00:19:01.680 --> 00:19:03.299
Almost all of them died.

00:19:03.359 --> 00:19:05.579
The rest are the ones who brought the

00:19:05.579 --> 00:19:06.299
stories back to you.

00:19:06.359 --> 00:19:08.579
She frowned.

00:19:08.640 --> 00:19:11.579
One of the expeditions was sent to burn

00:19:11.579 --> 00:19:14.339
down the jungle, because Wasp wanted no

00:19:14.339 --> 00:19:15.900
more trees anywhere.

00:19:15.960 --> 00:19:18.539
None of those dragons survived.

00:19:18.599 --> 00:19:20.400
She flicked her tail.

00:19:20.460 --> 00:19:22.799
We helped the jungle make sure of that.

00:19:22.859 --> 00:19:25.440
No one who comes for the trees again will

00:19:25.440 --> 00:19:26.160
be allowed to live.

00:19:26.220 --> 00:19:30.059
But then, how have you survived?

00:19:30.119 --> 00:19:33.000
Blue asked, how can there be a whole

00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:34.799
tribe living in a place that's so

00:19:34.799 --> 00:19:35.940
dangerous for dragons?

00:19:36.059 --> 00:19:39.900
We didn't have a choice, Sundu answered.

00:19:39.960 --> 00:19:42.539
It's easier when you grow up knowing what

00:19:42.539 --> 00:19:45.000
to avoid, and how to treat snake bites

00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:46.619
and where the quicksand is.

00:19:46.680 --> 00:19:49.500
Nowadays, we only lose a few dragons a

00:19:49.500 --> 00:19:50.880
year to the carnivorous plants.

00:19:50.940 --> 00:19:53.099
The what now?

00:19:53.220 --> 00:19:55.980
Sortell said, his voice rising in

00:19:55.980 --> 00:19:56.519
octave.

00:19:56.579 --> 00:19:58.319
Carnivorous what?

00:19:58.380 --> 00:20:03.779
Yeah, you will probably get eaten, Sundu

00:20:03.779 --> 00:20:04.500
said with a shrug.

00:20:04.559 --> 00:20:08.400
They always get the loud, flappy ones, and

00:20:08.400 --> 00:20:10.559
that hive wing dragonette is Cobra Lily

00:20:10.559 --> 00:20:11.220
food for sure.

00:20:11.279 --> 00:20:13.680
Zami!

00:20:13.740 --> 00:20:15.660
Bumblebee shouted from behind them.

00:20:15.720 --> 00:20:18.779
I am not enjoying this conversation

00:20:18.779 --> 00:20:20.400
Storytell observed.

00:20:20.460 --> 00:20:23.460
Do we have to go to the place with the

00:20:23.460 --> 00:20:25.019
certain death?

00:20:25.079 --> 00:20:25.920
Blue asked.

00:20:26.039 --> 00:20:30.420
Yes, because it's my home, Sundoo said.

00:20:30.480 --> 00:20:32.819
And also the only place you'll be safe

00:20:32.819 --> 00:20:34.980
from Queen Wasp after burning down her

00:20:34.980 --> 00:20:36.900
greenhouse of mind control plants.

00:20:37.019 --> 00:20:40.500
And also, because there's a dragon there

00:20:40.500 --> 00:20:42.960
who I'm definitely not thinking about, and

00:20:42.960 --> 00:20:44.700
certainly do not think about all the

00:20:44.700 --> 00:20:44.940
time.

00:20:45.000 --> 00:20:48.599
We'd be safe across the ocean, wouldn't

00:20:48.599 --> 00:20:48.779
we?

00:20:48.839 --> 00:20:51.960
Cricket offered, flying back into sundews

00:20:51.960 --> 00:20:54.240
line of sight, in the distant kingdoms.

00:20:54.359 --> 00:20:56.099
Sundew laughed.

00:20:56.160 --> 00:20:58.380
If you would all like to fly out to sea

00:20:58.380 --> 00:21:00.779
in search of an imaginary continent, go

00:21:00.779 --> 00:21:03.900
for it, she thought, but did not add

00:21:03.900 --> 00:21:05.880
except for you, Blue.

00:21:05.940 --> 00:21:08.160
You belong to the leaf wings now.

00:21:08.220 --> 00:21:11.819
The group fell silent as they drew closer

00:21:11.819 --> 00:21:13.380
to the edge of the poison jungle.

00:21:13.440 --> 00:21:16.980
The snarling river, dark and swift

00:21:16.980 --> 00:21:19.500
flowing, marked the boundary, but the

00:21:19.500 --> 00:21:21.480
jungle was always prowling across the

00:21:21.480 --> 00:21:25.140
line, pitcher plants and cobra lilies

00:21:25.140 --> 00:21:27.180
grew thick along the shores on both sides

00:21:27.180 --> 00:21:30.539
and every time sundew flew this way, she

00:21:30.539 --> 00:21:32.700
saw more plants extending their tendrils

00:21:32.700 --> 00:21:33.359
across the water.

00:21:33.420 --> 00:21:36.299
More twisted little thorn trees starting

00:21:36.299 --> 00:21:38.039
to muscle their way up on the wrong

00:21:38.039 --> 00:21:38.400
side.

00:21:38.460 --> 00:21:42.960
If we set it free, The poison jungle

00:21:42.960 --> 00:21:45.359
could devour the continent for us, and

00:21:45.359 --> 00:21:46.740
all the hive wings too.

00:21:46.799 --> 00:21:49.559
If I set it free.

00:21:49.619 --> 00:21:52.500
I could unleash the jungle and send it

00:21:52.500 --> 00:21:54.180
forth to strangle our enemies.

00:21:54.240 --> 00:21:55.859
I won't though.

00:21:55.920 --> 00:21:58.559
I don't want to pentala covered in

00:21:58.559 --> 00:22:00.359
poisonous dragon eating plants.

00:22:00.420 --> 00:22:03.180
I want the pentala of the old stories.

00:22:03.299 --> 00:22:06.059
The giant forests that stretched from

00:22:06.059 --> 00:22:06.900
shore to shore.

00:22:06.960 --> 00:22:10.559
She closed her talons into fists.

00:22:10.619 --> 00:22:14.279
But if I can't have that, beating all the

00:22:14.279 --> 00:22:16.559
hive wings to overgrown bladder wards is

00:22:16.559 --> 00:22:20.279
a solid plan B. Sundew was over the river

00:22:20.279 --> 00:22:22.440
when she realized the others had stopped

00:22:22.440 --> 00:22:24.900
hovering in midair to stare at the

00:22:24.900 --> 00:22:25.200
trees.

00:22:25.319 --> 00:22:27.960
She swung around and flew back to them.

00:22:28.019 --> 00:22:31.319
They're so big.

00:22:31.380 --> 00:22:34.319
Cricket said, in an awe struck voice.

00:22:34.440 --> 00:22:37.500
Her gold orange wings hummed like a cloud

00:22:37.500 --> 00:22:39.420
of dragonflies.

00:22:39.480 --> 00:22:41.279
The late afternoon sunlight caught in her

00:22:41.279 --> 00:22:43.619
glasses, reflecting the rippling water

00:22:43.619 --> 00:22:43.920
below.

00:22:43.980 --> 00:22:47.579
I didn't know trees grew so enormous.

00:22:47.640 --> 00:22:50.279
Some of them look as tall as the hives.

00:22:50.339 --> 00:22:51.599
How old are they?

00:22:51.660 --> 00:22:52.440
Can you tell?

00:22:52.500 --> 00:22:54.599
Would they all get that big if they lived

00:22:54.599 --> 00:22:55.140
that long?

00:22:55.200 --> 00:22:57.180
Are they all dangerous?

00:22:57.240 --> 00:23:00.119
Oh, please tell me you have books about

00:23:00.119 --> 00:23:00.900
all these plants.

00:23:00.960 --> 00:23:04.559
I want to know how you can fly in there

00:23:04.559 --> 00:23:06.480
when everything's so close together

00:23:06.480 --> 00:23:09.539
Swartell declared, squinting at the

00:23:09.539 --> 00:23:12.299
tangle of vines, fallen trees, giant

00:23:12.299 --> 00:23:14.880
spider webs, and thickets of plants that

00:23:14.880 --> 00:23:16.799
wove impassable barriers between the

00:23:16.799 --> 00:23:17.160
trees.

00:23:17.220 --> 00:23:21.660
It feels like one vast creature with a

00:23:21.660 --> 00:23:22.319
1000000 eyes.

00:23:22.440 --> 00:23:24.539
Blue added softly.

00:23:24.599 --> 00:23:27.240
I can almost hear it breathing.

00:23:27.299 --> 00:23:30.000
Like it's waiting for us.

00:23:30.059 --> 00:23:34.859
The others stared at him, and even Sundew

00:23:34.859 --> 00:23:36.960
who was used to the creepy aura of the

00:23:36.960 --> 00:23:39.720
poison jungle, felt a trickle of ice run

00:23:39.720 --> 00:23:40.680
through her veins.

00:23:40.859 --> 00:23:43.440
Arglar, flirt.

00:23:43.500 --> 00:23:46.680
Bumblebee announced, jabbing Cricket's

00:23:46.680 --> 00:23:48.359
chin with one of her claws and breaking

00:23:48.359 --> 00:23:48.779
the spell.

00:23:48.839 --> 00:23:51.480
E, pal, Snoodoo?

00:23:51.539 --> 00:23:54.000
She reached hopefully towards sundew.

00:23:54.119 --> 00:23:59.519
I think E-Pal means eat now, Cricket

00:23:59.519 --> 00:24:00.660
explained with a sigh.

00:24:00.720 --> 00:24:02.940
She's been yelling it for the last half a

00:24:02.940 --> 00:24:03.900
continent.

00:24:03.960 --> 00:24:05.940
E pow!

00:24:06.000 --> 00:24:08.940
Bumblebee demonstrated with expansive arm

00:24:08.940 --> 00:24:11.160
gestures, trying to wiggle out of her

00:24:11.160 --> 00:24:13.380
sling, eat, pal.

00:24:13.440 --> 00:24:16.440
You can wait until we get to the village

00:24:16.440 --> 00:24:18.059
Sundu said sternly.

00:24:18.119 --> 00:24:19.799
Don't make that face at me.

00:24:19.859 --> 00:24:22.079
No whining, or you can wait until

00:24:22.079 --> 00:24:23.099
tomorrow morning.

00:24:23.160 --> 00:24:27.119
Bumblebee flopped slowly over backward, so

00:24:27.119 --> 00:24:29.039
her head and wings drooped toward the

00:24:29.039 --> 00:24:29.579
river below.

00:24:29.700 --> 00:24:35.220
Never, she said, mournfully and

00:24:35.220 --> 00:24:35.759
distinctly.

00:24:35.819 --> 00:24:40.619
Aw, Cricket said, tucking the dragonette

00:24:40.619 --> 00:24:42.359
back into place and patting her head.

00:24:42.420 --> 00:24:44.579
She's such a quick learner.

00:24:44.700 --> 00:24:48.180
Bumblebee snuggled into her chest and

00:24:48.180 --> 00:24:50.099
gave a loud, dramatic sigh.

00:24:50.160 --> 00:24:53.099
Sundew turned to sword tail.

00:24:53.160 --> 00:24:56.160
We keep the outer layers of the jungle as

00:24:56.160 --> 00:24:58.799
wild and impenetrable as possible, she

00:24:58.799 --> 00:25:04.500
said, for obvious reasons, of, oh, she

00:25:04.500 --> 00:25:04.980
means you.

00:25:05.039 --> 00:25:06.599
He said to Cricket.

00:25:06.660 --> 00:25:09.180
The obvious reasons are your murdery

00:25:09.180 --> 00:25:10.440
tribe and your evil queen.

00:25:10.500 --> 00:25:12.720
Swordtail.

00:25:12.779 --> 00:25:15.900
Come on, Blue said, drawing closer to

00:25:15.900 --> 00:25:16.859
cricket.

00:25:16.920 --> 00:25:19.319
Your tribe isn't exactly welcome here

00:25:19.319 --> 00:25:20.460
either, Silkwing.

00:25:20.519 --> 00:25:21.779
Sundew pointed out.

00:25:21.839 --> 00:25:24.240
She had a feeling she was going to get a

00:25:24.240 --> 00:25:25.980
pretty strong reaction when they got to

00:25:25.980 --> 00:25:27.000
the Leaf Wing village.

00:25:27.059 --> 00:25:29.940
But it was Belladonna's fault for leaving

00:25:29.940 --> 00:25:32.819
and setting a hive on fire, instead of

00:25:32.819 --> 00:25:34.799
waiting for sundew to meet her as she'd

00:25:34.799 --> 00:25:35.220
promised.

00:25:36.059 --> 00:25:37.440
If she didn't want sundew bringing

00:25:37.440 --> 00:25:39.599
strangers into the jungle, she should

00:25:39.599 --> 00:25:41.039
have stayed in one place till they came.

00:25:41.160 --> 00:25:44.880
Sundew looked up at the press of jostling

00:25:44.880 --> 00:25:46.380
tree trunks that rose before them.

00:25:46.440 --> 00:25:49.680
Flying gets easier farther in, she

00:25:49.680 --> 00:25:52.259
explained, but for now, we climb.

00:25:52.319 --> 00:25:55.920
Follow me, stay close, and don't touch

00:25:55.920 --> 00:25:58.319
anything I haven't touched first.

00:25:58.380 --> 00:26:01.380
She arched her wings and caught an air

00:26:01.380 --> 00:26:03.720
current that smelled faintly of salt and

00:26:03.720 --> 00:26:04.619
distant whales.

00:26:04.680 --> 00:26:07.920
It lifted her up and up toward the

00:26:07.920 --> 00:26:09.000
swaying tops of the trees.

00:26:09.059 --> 00:26:13.559
Up here, the branches were like 1000s of

00:26:13.559 --> 00:26:15.299
long spider monkey arms.

00:26:15.359 --> 00:26:17.579
They reached and caught one another

00:26:17.579 --> 00:26:20.940
bending back and looping around, fuzzy

00:26:20.940 --> 00:26:23.579
with pale green moss, or marked with the

00:26:23.579 --> 00:26:26.759
scratches of dragon, jaguar, and tamarind

00:26:26.759 --> 00:26:27.180
claws.

00:26:27.299 --> 00:26:30.420
The spot where the Machahillas grew was

00:26:30.420 --> 00:26:31.319
well camouflaged.

00:26:31.380 --> 00:26:34.500
Other plants with similar leaves had been

00:26:34.500 --> 00:26:37.140
planted all around it, up and down in

00:26:37.140 --> 00:26:38.460
along the wall of foliage.

00:26:38.519 --> 00:26:41.039
The sundew never had any trouble finding

00:26:41.039 --> 00:26:41.400
it.

00:26:41.460 --> 00:26:43.319
She could have flown to it with her eyes

00:26:43.319 --> 00:26:43.740
closed.

00:26:43.799 --> 00:26:46.740
She could sense the vibrations of the

00:26:46.740 --> 00:26:49.559
Makahia leaves, like quiet music in her

00:26:49.559 --> 00:26:49.799
head.

00:26:49.859 --> 00:26:53.339
They were higher, and trembled more than

00:26:53.339 --> 00:26:54.839
the vibrations of other plants.

00:26:54.960 --> 00:26:58.859
Sunday slowed down and brushed her tail

00:26:58.859 --> 00:27:01.079
lightly across the center of the Makahia

00:27:01.079 --> 00:27:01.559
cluster.

00:27:01.619 --> 00:27:05.519
At once, the long, oval, fern like leaves

00:27:05.519 --> 00:27:06.660
began folding together.

00:27:06.720 --> 00:27:10.259
Pair after pair along the stems, like

00:27:10.259 --> 00:27:12.059
butterfly wings closing up.

00:27:12.119 --> 00:27:15.299
As they closed, they revealed a gap in

00:27:15.299 --> 00:27:17.519
the branches behind them, just large

00:27:17.519 --> 00:27:18.960
enough for a dragon to fit through.

00:27:19.019 --> 00:27:22.619
Whoa, Blue whispered.

00:27:22.680 --> 00:27:25.140
I've never seen a plan do that before.

00:27:25.200 --> 00:27:31.259
Oh, I think they're called touch me nots

00:27:31.259 --> 00:27:31.619
aren't they?

00:27:31.680 --> 00:27:33.420
Cricket asked Sundoo.

00:27:33.480 --> 00:27:36.480
That's one name for them, Sundu

00:27:36.480 --> 00:27:36.839
answered.

00:27:36.960 --> 00:27:40.259
Ooh. said Swordtail.

00:27:40.319 --> 00:27:42.539
That sounds super dangerous.

00:27:42.599 --> 00:27:44.940
Touch me not, or you will die.

00:27:45.059 --> 00:27:48.779
Sundew snickered, and Cricket covered her

00:27:48.779 --> 00:27:50.039
snout to hide her smile.

00:27:50.099 --> 00:27:53.400
Actually, Sundew said to SwordTail.

00:27:53.460 --> 00:27:55.619
This is probably the only plant up here

00:27:55.619 --> 00:27:56.759
that won't kill you.

00:27:56.819 --> 00:28:01.319
Hmm, he said skeptically, squinting at

00:28:01.319 --> 00:28:03.240
the folded leaves as he followed sundew

00:28:03.240 --> 00:28:03.720
through the hole.

00:28:03.779 --> 00:28:07.259
Stepping into the jungle always felt like

00:28:07.259 --> 00:28:08.579
plunging underwater.

00:28:08.640 --> 00:28:11.160
If that water was actually thick green

00:28:11.160 --> 00:28:14.940
soup in a cauldron, boiling, and full of

00:28:14.940 --> 00:28:18.180
insects, Sundu hissed at a mosquito the

00:28:18.180 --> 00:28:20.519
size of her ear, and it veered away in

00:28:20.519 --> 00:28:21.960
search of more docile prey.

00:28:22.019 --> 00:28:25.559
Behind her, Cricket let out a yelp, and

00:28:25.559 --> 00:28:27.960
lifted one talon to reveal a crushed mess

00:28:27.960 --> 00:28:30.839
of yellowy orange ooze that had probably

00:28:30.839 --> 00:28:31.980
been a tree slug.

00:28:32.039 --> 00:28:34.559
Mmm, yum?

00:28:34.619 --> 00:28:37.079
Bumblebee inquired, reaching for it.

00:28:37.140 --> 00:28:38.220
E?

00:28:38.279 --> 00:28:41.099
No, cricket said.

00:28:41.160 --> 00:28:42.839
Gross, bumblebee.

00:28:42.900 --> 00:28:44.579
Gross!

00:28:44.640 --> 00:28:48.119
Bumblebee cried, waking up in anaconda as

00:28:48.119 --> 00:28:50.039
thick as sundoo's tail in the next tree

00:28:50.039 --> 00:28:50.519
over.

00:28:50.579 --> 00:28:53.880
The snake raised its head slowly and

00:28:53.880 --> 00:28:55.380
narrowed its eyes at the little

00:28:55.380 --> 00:28:56.160
dragonette.

00:28:56.220 --> 00:28:57.900
Shh.

00:28:57.960 --> 00:28:58.799
Let's move.

00:28:58.859 --> 00:29:00.359
Sundu whispered.

00:29:00.420 --> 00:29:02.940
She ran lightly along the branch and

00:29:02.940 --> 00:29:05.400
leaped to another, then scrambled up to

00:29:05.400 --> 00:29:07.259
one that crisscrossed above them.

00:29:07.319 --> 00:29:09.420
The trees shook as the other dragons

00:29:09.420 --> 00:29:11.160
tried clumsily to follow her.

00:29:11.220 --> 00:29:14.460
Sundew could sense the message spreading

00:29:14.460 --> 00:29:15.119
through the trees.

00:29:15.180 --> 00:29:16.559
Something new.

00:29:16.619 --> 00:29:20.640
Leaves whispered to leaves, roots and

00:29:20.640 --> 00:29:22.380
networks of underground filaments

00:29:22.380 --> 00:29:24.720
flickered the news along like twigs in a

00:29:24.720 --> 00:29:25.079
current.

00:29:25.140 --> 00:29:28.200
Watch, listen, be safe.

00:29:28.259 --> 00:29:30.839
Caution, stand guard.

00:29:30.900 --> 00:29:34.259
She didn't have time to dig her talons

00:29:34.259 --> 00:29:35.819
into the dirt and shape the story.

00:29:35.880 --> 00:29:38.579
She had to hope she could get her dragons

00:29:38.579 --> 00:29:39.480
to the village quickly.

00:29:39.539 --> 00:29:41.819
And then she could take a moment to talk

00:29:41.819 --> 00:29:42.299
to the trees.

00:29:42.359 --> 00:29:44.940
You're like a monkey.

00:29:45.000 --> 00:29:48.119
Sortell panted, catching up to her when

00:29:48.119 --> 00:29:49.500
she stopped to wait for them.

00:29:49.559 --> 00:29:51.900
I mean, in a good way.

00:29:51.900 --> 00:29:57.240
Like, uh, very fast, jumps, good jumps

00:29:57.240 --> 00:29:58.079
not foodishly.

00:29:58.140 --> 00:30:00.299
I mean, not in a dinner way.

00:30:00.359 --> 00:30:02.819
Just so fast.

00:30:02.880 --> 00:30:05.519
He wheezed to a stop.

00:30:05.579 --> 00:30:08.880
Cricket balanced along the branch to a

00:30:08.880 --> 00:30:11.279
spot behind him, digging in her claws in

00:30:11.279 --> 00:30:13.019
a way that made sundew wince.

00:30:13.079 --> 00:30:14.880
The trees wouldn't like that.

00:30:14.940 --> 00:30:18.359
But Bumblebee kept lunging sideways

00:30:18.359 --> 00:30:21.000
nearly out of her sling, reaching for

00:30:21.000 --> 00:30:23.759
bright flowers or shining beetles, so

00:30:23.759 --> 00:30:25.500
Sundew could see why Cricket needed to

00:30:25.500 --> 00:30:26.099
hold on tight.

00:30:26.160 --> 00:30:29.880
Bringing up the rear behind her was Blue

00:30:29.880 --> 00:30:32.160
who looked as if he was trying to swallow

00:30:32.160 --> 00:30:33.180
the jungle with his eyes.

00:30:33.240 --> 00:30:35.579
It's scary.

00:30:35.640 --> 00:30:39.000
Like being high up in the webs, he said

00:30:39.000 --> 00:30:42.240
thoughtfully, but loud, like the inside

00:30:42.240 --> 00:30:45.539
of the hives, except the buzzing isn't in

00:30:45.539 --> 00:30:46.980
a language you can understand.

00:30:47.099 --> 00:30:49.859
And the smell is way worse.

00:30:49.920 --> 00:30:51.839
Swartell observed.

00:30:51.900 --> 00:30:53.519
Sundew bristled.

00:30:53.579 --> 00:30:54.960
No, it isn't.

00:30:55.019 --> 00:30:57.960
The smell of 100s of dragons trapped in

00:30:57.960 --> 00:30:59.400
one structure is much worse.

00:30:59.460 --> 00:31:02.640
This is what plants and fresh air and

00:31:02.640 --> 00:31:03.599
freedom smell like.

00:31:03.660 --> 00:31:07.619
Isn't it also what rotting plants smell

00:31:07.619 --> 00:31:07.980
like?

00:31:08.039 --> 00:31:08.880
he asked.

00:31:08.940 --> 00:31:13.500
And dead animals, and I don't know what

00:31:13.500 --> 00:31:13.859
else.

00:31:13.920 --> 00:31:15.299
Swamp gas?

00:31:15.359 --> 00:31:18.960
You smell like swamp gas, she said

00:31:18.960 --> 00:31:19.559
furiously.

00:31:19.619 --> 00:31:23.039
I'm sorry, Blue interjected.

00:31:23.099 --> 00:31:25.559
I only meant it's interesting.

00:31:25.619 --> 00:31:28.140
I'm trying to map it onto something I

00:31:28.140 --> 00:31:28.799
felt before.

00:31:28.859 --> 00:31:31.200
But it's so different from anywhere I've

00:31:31.200 --> 00:31:31.380
been.

00:31:31.500 --> 00:31:36.480
Yeah, sorry, so I tell agreed, giving

00:31:36.480 --> 00:31:38.039
Sandu an abashed look.

00:31:38.160 --> 00:31:39.720
It's not that bad.

00:31:39.779 --> 00:31:41.759
Some of it is kind of cool.

00:31:41.819 --> 00:31:44.220
Like that flower right below us.

00:31:44.279 --> 00:31:45.599
Look, Blue.

00:31:45.660 --> 00:31:48.059
It's like an enormous wild, pink, open

00:31:48.059 --> 00:31:48.660
book.

00:31:48.720 --> 00:31:51.359
I mean, so pink.

00:31:51.420 --> 00:31:53.819
And it actually smells kind of.

00:31:54.059 --> 00:31:57.900
Do not, Sundu shouted, as he leaned

00:31:57.900 --> 00:31:58.920
toward it sniffing.

00:31:58.980 --> 00:32:00.839
But it was too late.

00:32:00.900 --> 00:32:04.200
Sortail's nose brushed the pink surface

00:32:04.200 --> 00:32:06.720
and the plant's jaws snapped shut around

00:32:06.720 --> 00:32:09.180
him, yanking him off the branch and

00:32:09.180 --> 00:32:10.259
swallowing him whole.

00:32:10.319 --> 00:32:14.400
In an instant, Swordtail was gone.

00:32:14.460 --> 00:32:18.720
Chapter 2.

00:32:18.960 --> 00:32:22.619
Touch the Venus dragon trap.

00:32:22.680 --> 00:32:24.839
Sundew finished with a sigh.

00:32:24.960 --> 00:32:29.279
Cricket shrieked, and 8 more dragon traps

00:32:29.279 --> 00:32:31.980
snapped shut all around them, excited by

00:32:31.980 --> 00:32:32.400
the noise.

00:32:32.460 --> 00:32:35.279
The hive wing jumped back and crashed

00:32:35.279 --> 00:32:37.559
into blue, nearly knocking them both off

00:32:37.559 --> 00:32:38.460
the branch.

00:32:38.519 --> 00:32:40.079
Sore tail!

00:32:40.140 --> 00:32:41.099
Blue shouted.

00:32:41.160 --> 00:32:42.599
Swordtail.

00:32:42.660 --> 00:32:45.960
I was about to point those out, Sundew

00:32:45.960 --> 00:32:46.319
said.

00:32:46.440 --> 00:32:48.599
One of the most dangerous plants in

00:32:48.599 --> 00:32:48.900
here.

00:32:48.960 --> 00:32:50.519
Never touch those.

00:32:50.579 --> 00:32:52.799
Never, never.

00:32:52.859 --> 00:32:56.099
She gave Bumblebee a very stern look.

00:32:56.160 --> 00:32:59.220
Never, small dragon.

00:32:59.279 --> 00:33:00.000
Do you hear me?

00:33:00.059 --> 00:33:02.339
Snabble.

00:33:02.400 --> 00:33:03.359
Poof.

00:33:03.420 --> 00:33:06.359
Bumblebee said in an awe struck tone

00:33:06.359 --> 00:33:08.700
staring at the spot where Sortail had

00:33:08.700 --> 00:33:11.519
been, Blue scrambled around Cricket.

00:33:11.579 --> 00:33:14.099
Soretail, can you hear me?

00:33:14.160 --> 00:33:17.400
He reached toward the overstuffed plant

00:33:17.400 --> 00:33:20.099
below them, where SoraTail's long blue

00:33:20.099 --> 00:33:22.920
and orange tail dangled, flailing from

00:33:22.920 --> 00:33:24.539
between the trap's jaws.

00:33:24.599 --> 00:33:27.539
Sundew smacked Blue's knuckles.

00:33:27.599 --> 00:33:29.160
What did I just say?

00:33:29.220 --> 00:33:30.420
She barked.

00:33:30.480 --> 00:33:32.220
Never touch them.

00:33:32.279 --> 00:33:34.259
How do we get him out?

00:33:34.319 --> 00:33:36.299
Cricket asked frantically.

00:33:36.359 --> 00:33:38.940
Muffled yells were coming from inside the

00:33:38.940 --> 00:33:39.480
plant.

00:33:39.539 --> 00:33:42.599
The sides bulged as swordtail thrashed

00:33:42.599 --> 00:33:43.319
and struggled.

00:33:43.380 --> 00:33:45.960
But Sundu knew that there was no way for

00:33:45.960 --> 00:33:48.480
a dragon to escape on his own once he was

00:33:48.480 --> 00:33:48.720
inside.

00:33:48.779 --> 00:33:51.539
Swordtail!

00:33:51.599 --> 00:33:52.740
she shouted.

00:33:52.799 --> 00:33:53.940
Stop moving.

00:33:54.059 --> 00:33:56.819
Of course, he was yelling too loud to

00:33:56.819 --> 00:33:57.119
hear her.

00:33:57.180 --> 00:34:00.839
Basic carnivorous plant safety lesson

00:34:00.839 --> 00:34:01.680
number one.

00:34:01.740 --> 00:34:05.160
Sundew said to the others, but mostly to

00:34:05.160 --> 00:34:07.079
bumblebee's wide-eyed face.

00:34:07.200 --> 00:34:10.320
If you fall into a dragon trap, go as

00:34:10.320 --> 00:34:11.219
still as you can.

00:34:11.280 --> 00:34:14.519
If the plant thinks you're just a rock or

00:34:14.519 --> 00:34:16.500
tree branch that fell in by accident

00:34:16.500 --> 00:34:18.659
it'll open back up and drop you.

00:34:18.719 --> 00:34:23.880
But if you flail around like an idiot, She

00:34:23.880 --> 00:34:26.340
shouted at SwordTail, then it will.

00:34:26.400 --> 00:34:28.559
Know you're a delicious snack for sure.

00:34:28.619 --> 00:34:31.079
And then what?

00:34:31.139 --> 00:34:33.659
Cricket asked, wide-eyed.

00:34:33.719 --> 00:34:37.079
Then it releases its digestive juices and

00:34:37.079 --> 00:34:38.639
eats you, Sundew said.

00:34:38.699 --> 00:34:39.839
Obviously.

00:34:39.900 --> 00:34:43.019
She swatted it blue as he tried reaching

00:34:43.019 --> 00:34:44.099
for Sordell again.

00:34:44.159 --> 00:34:46.259
Swordtail!

00:34:46.380 --> 00:34:49.019
Cricket and Blue yelled in unison.

00:34:49.079 --> 00:34:51.360
It's pretty definitely figured out he's

00:34:51.360 --> 00:34:51.960
alive by now.

00:34:52.019 --> 00:34:53.579
Sundu said.

00:34:53.639 --> 00:34:56.039
She pointed to the long hairs along the

00:34:56.039 --> 00:34:58.079
edges of the plant's mouth, which were

00:34:58.079 --> 00:34:59.639
starting to lock firmly together.

00:34:59.699 --> 00:35:03.000
It won't drop him even if he does shut up

00:35:03.000 --> 00:35:03.960
long enough to hear us.

00:35:04.019 --> 00:35:05.820
But it's a slow process.

00:35:05.880 --> 00:35:08.760
It'll take at least half a day before it

00:35:08.760 --> 00:35:09.179
kills them.

00:35:09.239 --> 00:35:12.599
Can't we slice it open and cut him out?

00:35:12.719 --> 00:35:15.480
Cricket asked, raising one of her talons

00:35:15.480 --> 00:35:16.559
to flex her claws.

00:35:16.679 --> 00:35:19.199
Sundu shook her head.

00:35:19.260 --> 00:35:21.119
They've adapted for that.

00:35:21.179 --> 00:35:23.940
It takes forever to saw through the shell

00:35:23.940 --> 00:35:24.840
of a dragon trap.

00:35:24.900 --> 00:35:27.719
Plus, they grow in clusters like this on

00:35:27.719 --> 00:35:28.139
purpose.

00:35:28.199 --> 00:35:31.440
So if you try, another one will get you.

00:35:31.559 --> 00:35:34.679
She pointed to the gaping pink jaws

00:35:34.679 --> 00:35:36.539
hanging from the trees all around them

00:35:36.539 --> 00:35:39.539
particularly the one leaning over sword

00:35:39.539 --> 00:35:42.300
tail's plant, ready to swallow any dragon

00:35:42.300 --> 00:35:43.260
who tried to help him.

00:35:43.320 --> 00:35:46.619
Blue paced up and down the branch.

00:35:46.679 --> 00:35:49.079
Soretail, he called again.

00:35:49.139 --> 00:35:51.719
We'll get you out, I promise.

00:35:51.780 --> 00:35:55.199
So, what do you normally do?

00:35:55.260 --> 00:35:57.119
Cricket asked Sundo.

00:35:57.179 --> 00:35:59.159
Your tribe must have found a way to

00:35:59.159 --> 00:36:00.900
rescue dragons from being eaten.

00:36:00.960 --> 00:36:06.000
Sort of, if having me counts as finding a

00:36:06.000 --> 00:36:06.179
way.

00:36:06.300 --> 00:36:09.659
Sundu had been studying the nearest plant

00:36:09.659 --> 00:36:10.440
as they talked.

00:36:10.500 --> 00:36:14.400
There was a promising kudzu vine choking

00:36:14.400 --> 00:36:17.579
one of the trees below them, or a thorny

00:36:17.579 --> 00:36:19.980
greenbrier vine system tangled through

00:36:19.980 --> 00:36:22.199
the branches just behind the dragon trap

00:36:22.199 --> 00:36:22.679
cluster.

00:36:22.739 --> 00:36:25.739
The sharp, dark stems prickled in the

00:36:25.739 --> 00:36:28.019
corners of her mind, coiled and

00:36:28.019 --> 00:36:28.860
dangerous.

00:36:28.920 --> 00:36:30.480
If she could get to one of them.

00:36:30.539 --> 00:36:33.900
But then she'd have to reveal her secret

00:36:33.900 --> 00:36:36.119
abilities to blue and cricket.

00:36:36.179 --> 00:36:38.639
They're going to find out pretty soon

00:36:38.639 --> 00:36:39.119
anyway.

00:36:39.179 --> 00:36:41.940
And it's the only way to save sword

00:36:41.940 --> 00:36:42.239
tail.

00:36:42.300 --> 00:36:45.179
I can, she started.

00:36:45.239 --> 00:36:48.420
There was a flash of bright orange light

00:36:48.420 --> 00:36:51.360
and heat beside her, a long thread of

00:36:51.360 --> 00:36:53.820
flame silk flew out of Blue's wrist and

00:36:53.820 --> 00:36:56.099
slithered around the dragon traps, leaves

00:36:56.099 --> 00:36:56.460
and stem.

00:36:56.579 --> 00:36:59.400
Stop, Sundew yelled.

00:36:59.460 --> 00:37:01.800
She lunged across cricket and grabbed

00:37:01.800 --> 00:37:03.840
Blue's arm, slamming it down to the

00:37:03.840 --> 00:37:04.139
branch.

00:37:04.199 --> 00:37:07.380
Why are you all impossible?

00:37:07.500 --> 00:37:10.739
She whirled, and saw the fire already

00:37:10.739 --> 00:37:13.260
beginning to catch, and spread down the

00:37:13.260 --> 00:37:15.960
length of the dragon trap stem toward the

00:37:15.960 --> 00:37:16.980
tree where its roots were.

00:37:17.099 --> 00:37:21.059
As the stem burned through, the squirming

00:37:21.059 --> 00:37:23.219
bulb of the dragon trap drooped and

00:37:23.219 --> 00:37:26.099
lulled sideways, setting off 3 more

00:37:26.099 --> 00:37:27.480
plants as it knocked into them.

00:37:27.480 --> 00:37:31.380
Sundune leaped up to a higher branch and

00:37:31.380 --> 00:37:34.139
seized a cluster of giant bromeliads.

00:37:34.199 --> 00:37:36.420
A small blue tree frog jumped out of one

00:37:36.420 --> 00:37:38.760
of them, and gave her a reproachful look

00:37:38.760 --> 00:37:40.679
as she ripped the flowers free.

00:37:40.800 --> 00:37:44.280
Inside each cluster of leaves was a pool

00:37:44.280 --> 00:37:44.820
of water.

00:37:44.880 --> 00:37:48.360
Some the size of her cupped talons, some

00:37:48.360 --> 00:37:49.500
much bigger.

00:37:49.559 --> 00:37:51.840
She swooped down and poured them over the

00:37:51.840 --> 00:37:52.079
fire.

00:37:52.139 --> 00:37:55.440
It sizzled and hissed at her.

00:37:55.500 --> 00:37:58.440
Half the flames went out, but one end

00:37:58.440 --> 00:38:00.900
began sprinting faster toward the tree.

00:38:01.019 --> 00:38:03.480
The smoke was already thick and curling

00:38:03.480 --> 00:38:05.400
into our eyes, making them water.

00:38:05.460 --> 00:38:08.400
All the nearest dragon traps had drawn

00:38:08.400 --> 00:38:10.320
back as far as their stems would allow.

00:38:10.380 --> 00:38:13.380
Leaves all around her curled away from

00:38:13.380 --> 00:38:13.739
the fire.

00:38:13.800 --> 00:38:16.920
She could feel the trees screaming deep

00:38:16.920 --> 00:38:17.519
in her nerves.

00:38:17.579 --> 00:38:20.699
I need a fire resistant plant.

00:38:20.760 --> 00:38:24.360
Something full of water or sap, or giant

00:38:24.360 --> 00:38:26.219
leaves I can use to smother the flames.

00:38:26.280 --> 00:38:29.940
Sundew glanced desperately around, and

00:38:29.940 --> 00:38:32.159
spotted a choke cherry tree on the jungle

00:38:32.159 --> 00:38:33.780
floor, far below her.

00:38:33.840 --> 00:38:36.420
She leaped through the smoke to the trunk

00:38:36.420 --> 00:38:38.579
of the burning tree, and pressed her

00:38:38.579 --> 00:38:41.280
talons against the bark, sending her

00:38:41.280 --> 00:38:43.559
power down through the wood, through the

00:38:43.559 --> 00:38:46.139
roots, through the mycelium threads under

00:38:46.139 --> 00:38:48.599
the soil, into the choke cherry tree.

00:38:48.659 --> 00:38:52.320
The choke cherry tree burst upward

00:38:52.320 --> 00:38:54.539
growing at the speed of an erupting

00:38:54.539 --> 00:38:55.139
volcano.

00:38:55.199 --> 00:38:58.800
Its branches smacked other plants aside

00:38:58.800 --> 00:39:01.800
its roots burrowed deep and fast to keep

00:39:01.800 --> 00:39:02.460
it steady.

00:39:02.579 --> 00:39:04.320
In a matter of heartbeats.

00:39:04.380 --> 00:39:06.480
The top of the tree was level with

00:39:06.480 --> 00:39:08.820
Sunday's head, and the berries on it were

00:39:08.820 --> 00:39:11.340
enormous, the size of her fists.

00:39:11.460 --> 00:39:15.420
She grabbed talonfuls of berries and

00:39:15.420 --> 00:39:17.400
smashed them onto the branch below the

00:39:17.400 --> 00:39:19.920
fire, smearing the juice around and

00:39:19.920 --> 00:39:20.219
around.

00:39:20.340 --> 00:39:23.519
The flames reached the wet barrier and

00:39:23.519 --> 00:39:25.860
slowed, prodding the goop in a

00:39:25.860 --> 00:39:26.699
disgruntled manner.

00:39:26.760 --> 00:39:30.179
More water splashed down on the fire from

00:39:30.179 --> 00:39:30.599
above.

00:39:30.659 --> 00:39:33.960
Sundu looked up, and saw cricket, with

00:39:33.960 --> 00:39:35.699
her claws full of bromeliads.

00:39:35.760 --> 00:39:38.519
Bumblebee was buried deep in her sling

00:39:38.519 --> 00:39:41.159
her snout covered by the striped fabric.

00:39:41.219 --> 00:39:43.920
Cricket poured out the stored rainwater

00:39:43.920 --> 00:39:46.380
in the flowers, methodically covering all

00:39:46.380 --> 00:39:49.260
the flames until at last, they were

00:39:49.260 --> 00:39:49.860
extinguished.

00:39:49.980 --> 00:39:53.159
Sundew rested her forehead against the

00:39:53.159 --> 00:39:55.019
tree, checking it for damage.

00:39:55.079 --> 00:39:58.260
Apart from one burnt limb and the smoke

00:39:58.260 --> 00:40:01.019
clogging its leaves, the rest of it was

00:40:01.019 --> 00:40:02.519
shaken, but unharmed.

00:40:02.579 --> 00:40:05.460
The dragon trap, however, was definitely

00:40:05.460 --> 00:40:05.940
dead.

00:40:06.000 --> 00:40:09.840
She turned toward it and realized that

00:40:09.840 --> 00:40:12.000
Blue was holding up the head and trying

00:40:12.000 --> 00:40:14.039
to pry open the jaws at the same time

00:40:14.039 --> 00:40:16.320
mostly unsuccessfully.

00:40:16.380 --> 00:40:19.559
Cricket hovered beside him, supporting

00:40:19.559 --> 00:40:21.719
the weight of the plant and sword tail.

00:40:21.780 --> 00:40:24.780
The other dragon traps, which had been

00:40:24.780 --> 00:40:27.420
scared back by the fire, were slowly

00:40:27.420 --> 00:40:28.559
inching toward them again.

00:40:28.619 --> 00:40:31.260
Sundew flew over to blue.

00:40:31.320 --> 00:40:33.659
She could hear Swordtail coughing inside

00:40:33.659 --> 00:40:34.619
the plant.

00:40:34.679 --> 00:40:37.019
That was incredibly stupid.

00:40:37.139 --> 00:40:39.780
She snapped her tail back and forth.

00:40:39.840 --> 00:40:42.119
Her insides felt as though they were

00:40:42.119 --> 00:40:44.639
boiling with anger, as though the flame

00:40:44.639 --> 00:40:46.559
silk had gone straight into her veins as

00:40:46.559 --> 00:40:46.739
well.

00:40:46.860 --> 00:40:49.440
You could have set this whole jungle on

00:40:49.440 --> 00:40:49.980
fire.

00:40:50.039 --> 00:40:52.860
I'm sorry, Blue said.

00:40:52.920 --> 00:40:55.380
And at least he looked like he meant it

00:40:55.380 --> 00:40:57.900
unless the tears in his eyes came from

00:40:57.900 --> 00:40:58.679
the smoke in the air.

00:40:58.739 --> 00:41:00.719
I panicked.

00:41:00.780 --> 00:41:02.940
I only wanted to save Swordtail.

00:41:03.059 --> 00:41:05.340
I had no idea it would spread like that.

00:41:05.400 --> 00:41:07.440
You should have thought about it.

00:41:07.500 --> 00:41:10.559
You just saw a wasp's greenhouse go up in

00:41:10.559 --> 00:41:10.980
flames.

00:41:11.039 --> 00:41:14.460
A fellow leaf wing would have roared back

00:41:14.460 --> 00:41:17.699
at sundew, a dragon from her tribe would

00:41:17.699 --> 00:41:20.940
have bristled, defended himself, argued

00:41:20.940 --> 00:41:23.699
stormed around, pointed out all the ways

00:41:23.699 --> 00:41:24.599
she was wrong.

00:41:24.719 --> 00:41:27.900
Most conversations in her village ended

00:41:27.900 --> 00:41:31.800
in fights or started with a fight, or at

00:41:31.800 --> 00:41:33.119
least involved some shouting.

00:41:33.179 --> 00:41:37.260
But Blue nodded, and wiped his eyes, and

00:41:37.260 --> 00:41:38.579
apologized again.

00:41:38.639 --> 00:41:40.380
You're right.

00:41:40.440 --> 00:41:43.199
I'm really, really sorry, Sundo.

00:41:43.260 --> 00:41:46.679
Which made it kind of impossible to keep

00:41:46.679 --> 00:41:47.579
yelling at him.

00:41:47.639 --> 00:41:50.280
The ball of sundew's anger bounced back

00:41:50.280 --> 00:41:52.739
inside her. and started mutating into

00:41:52.739 --> 00:41:55.260
something useless and distracting, like

00:41:55.260 --> 00:41:57.360
guilt or pity or something.

00:41:57.420 --> 00:42:01.199
She scowled down at the dragon trap, which

00:42:01.199 --> 00:42:03.119
was starting to crack open where Blue was

00:42:03.119 --> 00:42:03.599
pulling on it.

00:42:03.659 --> 00:42:06.900
I bet your flame silk is hard to control

00:42:06.900 --> 00:42:07.260
isn't it?

00:42:07.380 --> 00:42:10.199
Cricket asked breathlessly, trying to

00:42:10.199 --> 00:42:11.760
hold up the still smoking plant.

00:42:11.820 --> 00:42:14.400
Yeah, Blue said.

00:42:14.460 --> 00:42:17.159
So, it was extra stupid of me.

00:42:17.219 --> 00:42:20.639
We'll help you practice with it, Sundew

00:42:20.639 --> 00:42:22.559
said, wondering if she could really offer

00:42:22.559 --> 00:42:23.280
something like that.

00:42:23.340 --> 00:42:26.280
There wasn't a leaf wing alive who knew

00:42:26.280 --> 00:42:28.079
anything about managing plame silk.

00:42:28.199 --> 00:42:31.800
But for now, promise me you won't use it

00:42:31.800 --> 00:42:33.840
in the jungle unless I tell you to.

00:42:33.900 --> 00:42:37.019
I promise, he said.

00:42:37.079 --> 00:42:38.519
I really promise.

00:42:38.579 --> 00:42:40.739
Can you help me get sore tail out?

00:42:40.800 --> 00:42:42.179
He must be so scared.

00:42:42.300 --> 00:42:45.780
No, not scared.

00:42:45.900 --> 00:42:48.900
Sortell half yelled, half sputtered

00:42:48.900 --> 00:42:50.519
through the crack in the plant's jaws.

00:42:50.579 --> 00:42:53.039
This plant is in big trouble.

00:42:53.099 --> 00:42:54.840
I'm going to slice it up from the

00:42:54.840 --> 00:42:55.199
inside.

00:42:55.260 --> 00:42:57.420
I'm going to give it such a stomach

00:42:57.420 --> 00:42:57.900
ache.

00:42:57.960 --> 00:43:00.539
It'll seriously regret trying to eat me.

00:43:00.599 --> 00:43:02.519
You deserved it.

00:43:02.579 --> 00:43:04.500
Sundu barked at him.

00:43:04.559 --> 00:43:06.960
It was a relief to have someone she could

00:43:06.960 --> 00:43:08.460
be mad at without feeling bad.

00:43:08.519 --> 00:43:11.340
She hooked her claws around the top edge

00:43:11.340 --> 00:43:13.500
of the plant's mouth, and motioned for

00:43:13.500 --> 00:43:14.820
Blue to take the bottom edge.

00:43:14.880 --> 00:43:17.159
You basically fed yourself to it.

00:43:17.219 --> 00:43:19.199
I did not.

00:43:19.260 --> 00:43:23.159
That is, it, I was just smelling it.

00:43:23.219 --> 00:43:24.960
Sortail growled.

00:43:25.019 --> 00:43:28.739
Sundew flapped her wings, pushing herself

00:43:28.739 --> 00:43:30.059
backward as hard as she could.

00:43:30.119 --> 00:43:34.019
The smell is designed to attract dragons

00:43:34.019 --> 00:43:35.219
she conceded.

00:43:35.280 --> 00:43:37.920
But only dragons with no brains in their

00:43:37.920 --> 00:43:40.440
heads, who like constantly causing

00:43:40.440 --> 00:43:42.780
trouble for their traveling companions.

00:43:42.840 --> 00:43:45.119
I said you would get eaten right away, and

00:43:45.119 --> 00:43:45.599
I was right.

00:43:45.659 --> 00:43:48.840
With a ripping, crackling sound.

00:43:48.900 --> 00:43:50.820
The jaws finally parted.

00:43:50.880 --> 00:43:53.519
Swordtail hauled himself out and back

00:43:53.519 --> 00:43:55.800
onto the 1st branch, coughing and

00:43:55.800 --> 00:43:56.639
blinking rapidly.

00:43:56.699 --> 00:43:59.820
The others let go of the dragon trap, and

00:43:59.820 --> 00:44:01.679
the head broke off from the blackened

00:44:01.679 --> 00:44:04.079
stem, tumbling away to the forest floor.

00:44:04.139 --> 00:44:07.440
Sundew could sense the hunger of the

00:44:07.440 --> 00:44:09.659
surrounding dragon traps.

00:44:09.659 --> 00:44:11.820
As the smoke faded into the air, they

00:44:11.820 --> 00:44:14.400
were getting bolder, wrestling closer in

00:44:14.400 --> 00:44:15.239
their stealthy way.

00:44:15.300 --> 00:44:18.719
She shoved cricket and bumblebee back

00:44:18.719 --> 00:44:21.179
onto the branch, and Blue clambered after

00:44:21.179 --> 00:44:21.360
them.

00:44:21.420 --> 00:44:25.440
I've never seen such a pile of idiocy, she

00:44:25.440 --> 00:44:25.739
said.

00:44:25.800 --> 00:44:28.980
Now really stay close to me and really

00:44:28.980 --> 00:44:29.880
don't touch anything.

00:44:29.940 --> 00:44:33.119
I feel like we could have gotten a bit

00:44:33.119 --> 00:44:34.019
more of a warning.

00:44:34.079 --> 00:44:37.019
Swortail objected with a cough as they

00:44:37.019 --> 00:44:37.800
started walking again.

00:44:37.860 --> 00:44:40.980
Like, it'd be pretty helpful if you'd

00:44:40.980 --> 00:44:44.400
point out, that's a carnivorous plant, and

00:44:44.400 --> 00:44:47.340
that one is super flammable, and that one

00:44:47.340 --> 00:44:48.119
can kill you.

00:44:48.179 --> 00:44:52.260
All right, Sunday said, waving at the

00:44:52.260 --> 00:44:53.280
entire jungle around them.

00:44:53.340 --> 00:44:56.880
These are dangerous plants, and most of

00:44:56.880 --> 00:44:59.579
them are carnivorous, and all of them can

00:44:59.579 --> 00:44:59.820
kill you.

00:44:59.880 --> 00:45:04.679
Do not sniff, touch, eat, poke, lick, or

00:45:04.679 --> 00:45:08.340
set fire to any of them, or you will

00:45:08.340 --> 00:45:08.880
probably die.

00:45:08.940 --> 00:45:11.280
And next time, I will let you.

00:45:11.340 --> 00:45:13.380
She doesn't mean that.

00:45:13.440 --> 00:45:16.800
Cricket whispered to bumblebee, who

00:45:16.800 --> 00:45:18.420
chirped sleepily back at her.

00:45:18.480 --> 00:45:21.719
It must have been pretty awful when your

00:45:21.719 --> 00:45:24.119
tribe 1st got here, Blue said.

00:45:24.179 --> 00:45:27.300
Sundew did not dignify that with an

00:45:27.300 --> 00:45:29.880
answer, since she was pretty sure it

00:45:29.880 --> 00:45:32.219
would involve more yelling at him, and

00:45:32.219 --> 00:45:33.719
apparently she didn't really enjoy

00:45:33.719 --> 00:45:34.679
yelling at Blue.

00:45:34.800 --> 00:45:38.039
Yelling at sore tail on the other hand

00:45:38.039 --> 00:45:39.420
was always satisfying.

00:45:39.480 --> 00:45:42.420
They climbed in silence for a little

00:45:42.420 --> 00:45:45.659
while, hopping from branch to branch as

00:45:45.659 --> 00:45:46.739
they descended through the jungle.

00:45:46.800 --> 00:45:49.800
It was a prickly silence, though.

00:45:49.860 --> 00:45:53.340
Blue had an aura of guilt around him.

00:45:53.400 --> 00:45:55.500
Swordtail kept muttering under his breath

00:45:55.500 --> 00:45:58.260
and Sundew could feel Cricket's eyes on

00:45:58.260 --> 00:45:58.380
her.

00:45:58.500 --> 00:46:01.559
She knew her well enough by now to guess

00:46:01.559 --> 00:46:03.780
that cricket was trying really hard to

00:46:03.780 --> 00:46:06.119
hold back a question, and that pretty

00:46:06.119 --> 00:46:07.199
soon she would fail.

00:46:07.260 --> 00:46:09.599
Sundoo?

00:46:09.659 --> 00:46:12.179
Cricket burst out as they passed a

00:46:12.179 --> 00:46:14.579
cluster of glowering giant hogweeds.

00:46:14.639 --> 00:46:19.559
Ah, what, Sundew said, casting a glance

00:46:19.559 --> 00:46:21.239
over her shoulder at the hive wing

00:46:21.239 --> 00:46:24.239
Crickets glasses were fogged up from the

00:46:24.239 --> 00:46:26.400
humidity, and she kept swiping at them

00:46:26.400 --> 00:46:27.900
with bumblebee's sling.

00:46:27.960 --> 00:46:29.639
It's just...

00:46:29.639 --> 00:46:31.559
Cricket hesitated.

00:46:31.619 --> 00:46:33.840
And Sundu realized what she was going to

00:46:33.840 --> 00:46:34.139
ask.

00:46:34.199 --> 00:46:36.960
Even in the midst of fighting the fire

00:46:36.960 --> 00:46:38.579
with Bromeliad pools?

00:46:38.639 --> 00:46:40.559
Of course, cricket would notice what

00:46:40.559 --> 00:46:42.059
every dragon around her was doing.

00:46:42.179 --> 00:46:44.880
Especially if it was something weird and

00:46:44.880 --> 00:46:45.840
unscientific.

00:46:45.900 --> 00:46:49.079
Cricket tilted her head at sundew.

00:46:49.139 --> 00:46:53.039
Did you make a tree grow?

00:46:53.099 --> 00:46:57.420
Chapter 3.

00:46:57.599 --> 00:47:00.480
Sundew winced.

00:47:00.539 --> 00:47:04.019
Her gift was no secret inside the tribe

00:47:04.019 --> 00:47:06.599
but Belladonna had been very clear that

00:47:06.599 --> 00:47:09.059
she wasn't supposed to let any hive wings

00:47:09.059 --> 00:47:10.860
or silk wings find out about it.

00:47:10.920 --> 00:47:14.159
Sundew had already risked exposing it

00:47:14.159 --> 00:47:14.400
twice.

00:47:14.460 --> 00:47:17.820
Once, when she grew the vines that helped

00:47:17.820 --> 00:47:19.860
Blue and Luna escape the flame silk

00:47:19.860 --> 00:47:20.280
cavern.

00:47:20.400 --> 00:47:23.639
Once, when she used seaweed to help her

00:47:23.639 --> 00:47:25.800
transport an unconscious sword tail

00:47:25.800 --> 00:47:28.619
across Dragonfly Bay, she had gotten away

00:47:28.619 --> 00:47:31.500
with it both times, she'd even managed to

00:47:31.500 --> 00:47:33.000
avoid cricket's questions.

00:47:33.179 --> 00:47:35.940
But there was no way to get around the

00:47:35.940 --> 00:47:37.739
poison jungle without using her power.

00:47:37.860 --> 00:47:40.619
She couldn't even walk through the leaf

00:47:40.619 --> 00:47:42.840
wing village without dragons asking her

00:47:42.840 --> 00:47:43.920
for help with their plants.

00:47:43.980 --> 00:47:46.440
Cricket and the others would know

00:47:46.440 --> 00:47:47.699
everything soon anyway.

00:47:47.760 --> 00:47:50.940
Yeah, she said to Cricket.

00:47:51.000 --> 00:47:52.559
I do that sometimes.

00:47:52.619 --> 00:47:55.679
Grow trees?

00:47:55.739 --> 00:48:00.179
Cricket asked, like, really tall trees

00:48:00.179 --> 00:48:02.099
out of nowhere before anyone can blink.

00:48:02.219 --> 00:48:06.599
Not out of nowhere, Sandu said.

00:48:06.659 --> 00:48:09.300
I can only help along whatever plant is

00:48:09.300 --> 00:48:09.780
already there.

00:48:09.840 --> 00:48:13.199
I can't make plants or seeds appear.

00:48:13.260 --> 00:48:14.400
If I could.

00:48:14.460 --> 00:48:16.860
I'd have been throwing down oak trees and

00:48:16.860 --> 00:48:19.440
beech groves and pine forests all over

00:48:19.440 --> 00:48:20.340
Pantala by now.

00:48:20.400 --> 00:48:24.480
But that's amazing, Blue said.

00:48:24.539 --> 00:48:25.920
Why didn't you tell us?

00:48:25.980 --> 00:48:28.860
Because you didn't know if you could

00:48:28.860 --> 00:48:29.400
trust us.

00:48:29.460 --> 00:48:31.739
He answered himself immediately.

00:48:31.800 --> 00:48:34.920
Because you wouldn't want Queen Wasp to

00:48:34.920 --> 00:48:35.219
find out.

00:48:35.280 --> 00:48:39.119
As if we would ever tell Queen Wasp

00:48:39.119 --> 00:48:40.619
Sortell objected.

00:48:40.679 --> 00:48:43.440
Oh, Blue said.

00:48:43.500 --> 00:48:46.199
I remember reading something about this.

00:48:46.320 --> 00:48:49.199
Leaf Wings who could control plants.

00:48:49.260 --> 00:48:52.019
I remember thinking that sounded like

00:48:52.019 --> 00:48:54.480
magic, and wondering what I would grow

00:48:54.480 --> 00:48:55.320
with it if I could.

00:48:55.380 --> 00:48:58.860
Can all leaf wings do this?

00:48:58.920 --> 00:49:00.059
Cricket asked.

00:49:00.119 --> 00:49:03.539
Sundew shook her head, but she was

00:49:03.539 --> 00:49:05.760
rescued from any further questions by an

00:49:05.760 --> 00:49:07.860
eruption of roars from the jungle below.

00:49:07.920 --> 00:49:11.820
The others jumped, and Bumblebee woke up

00:49:11.820 --> 00:49:13.800
and poked her head out of the sling.

00:49:13.920 --> 00:49:15.780
R?

00:49:15.780 --> 00:49:16.920
she inquired.

00:49:16.980 --> 00:49:19.380
Bamo slamoee now?

00:49:19.440 --> 00:49:23.820
Everyone, shush, Sundu said, crouching

00:49:23.820 --> 00:49:24.719
low to the branch.

00:49:24.780 --> 00:49:28.079
Especially you, she whispered to

00:49:28.079 --> 00:49:28.739
Bumblebee.

00:49:28.800 --> 00:49:32.519
You sha, hush, shush.

00:49:32.579 --> 00:49:34.019
Bumblebee declared proudly.

00:49:34.079 --> 00:49:36.960
Cricket produced a berry from somewhere

00:49:36.960 --> 00:49:39.420
and the little dragonette seized it and

00:49:39.420 --> 00:49:41.820
stuffed it whole into her mouth, which

00:49:41.820 --> 00:49:43.860
would keep her quiet for most 10

00:49:43.860 --> 00:49:44.159
seconds.

00:49:44.219 --> 00:49:47.280
Thick leaves hid them from what was

00:49:47.280 --> 00:49:47.880
happening below.

00:49:47.940 --> 00:49:51.000
But Sundew could clearly hear at least 3

00:49:51.000 --> 00:49:54.179
dragons bellowing, and a 4th roar that

00:49:54.179 --> 00:49:55.739
didn't sound like a dragon to her.

00:49:55.800 --> 00:49:58.380
She rested her ear against the bark of

00:49:58.380 --> 00:50:00.599
the tree, and tried to get the tree's

00:50:00.599 --> 00:50:01.739
sense of what was going on.

00:50:01.800 --> 00:50:04.800
But whatever it was, the tree was

00:50:04.800 --> 00:50:07.139
apparently not threatened, and therefore

00:50:07.139 --> 00:50:07.679
not interested.

00:50:07.739 --> 00:50:11.880
Come on, Mandrake, one of the dragons

00:50:11.880 --> 00:50:12.480
bellowed.

00:50:12.539 --> 00:50:14.460
Strangle it or something.

00:50:14.519 --> 00:50:16.440
It's moving too fast.

00:50:16.559 --> 00:50:18.960
Mandrake's voice shouted back.

00:50:19.019 --> 00:50:22.500
If it would just, can we back it over to

00:50:22.500 --> 00:50:23.159
or next to that?

00:50:23.280 --> 00:50:26.400
Can't I please just kill it?

00:50:26.460 --> 00:50:28.260
yelled that there a dragon.

00:50:28.320 --> 00:50:30.539
We could be home and cooking it by now.

00:50:30.599 --> 00:50:33.480
This panther will die of old age before

00:50:33.480 --> 00:50:36.179
mandrake finds the perfect vine in the

00:50:36.179 --> 00:50:38.219
perfect place and figures out what to do

00:50:38.219 --> 00:50:38.519
with it.

00:50:38.579 --> 00:50:42.000
Oh, poor mandrake.

00:50:42.059 --> 00:50:45.239
Sundew could guess exactly what was

00:50:45.239 --> 00:50:45.659
happening now.

00:50:45.719 --> 00:50:48.599
She'd seen enough of the hunt this

00:50:48.599 --> 00:50:50.519
hapless dragon had been dragged into by

00:50:50.519 --> 00:50:51.360
his father and sister.

00:50:51.420 --> 00:50:55.380
Stay here, she whispered to the others.

00:50:55.440 --> 00:50:58.199
Sundew swung lightly down through the

00:50:58.199 --> 00:51:00.480
branches, slipping carefully through the

00:51:00.480 --> 00:51:02.519
leaves and avoiding the spider webs as

00:51:02.519 --> 00:51:03.179
well as she could.

00:51:03.179 --> 00:51:06.360
In a moment, she found a spot near the

00:51:06.360 --> 00:51:08.280
trunk with a view of the jungle floor

00:51:08.280 --> 00:51:11.940
where, if she kept still, the clusters of

00:51:11.940 --> 00:51:14.280
giant rattling seed pods should keep her

00:51:14.280 --> 00:51:14.639
hidden.

00:51:14.699 --> 00:51:18.420
Now she could see mandrake, darting

00:51:18.420 --> 00:51:20.639
helplessly around the clearing, grabbing

00:51:20.639 --> 00:51:22.139
at plants, but letting them go without

00:51:22.139 --> 00:51:22.800
using them.

00:51:22.800 --> 00:51:25.619
His father and sister watched from the

00:51:25.619 --> 00:51:28.380
low branches of the nearest trees, with

00:51:28.380 --> 00:51:30.000
matching critical expressions on their

00:51:30.000 --> 00:51:30.480
faces.

00:51:30.480 --> 00:51:34.199
The panther slunk after him, snarling.

00:51:34.260 --> 00:51:37.440
Its teeth bigger than mandrake's claws.

00:51:37.500 --> 00:51:40.920
Its black fur rippled over huge muscles.

00:51:40.980 --> 00:51:44.579
Only the biggest, strongest, scariest

00:51:44.579 --> 00:51:46.619
mammals could survive in the poison

00:51:46.619 --> 00:51:48.900
jungle, so all their panthers were

00:51:48.900 --> 00:51:51.480
unnecessarily gigantic and terrifying.

00:51:51.539 --> 00:51:55.199
Terrifying to dragons like mandrake, that

00:51:55.199 --> 00:51:58.559
is, not at all terrifying to sundo, who

00:51:58.559 --> 00:52:00.179
was in charge of hunting their prey for

00:52:00.179 --> 00:52:01.800
every big tribe feast.

00:52:01.980 --> 00:52:04.800
How dare they have mandrake do it

00:52:04.800 --> 00:52:05.159
instead?

00:52:05.219 --> 00:52:07.440
She thought with a flare of anger.

00:52:07.500 --> 00:52:09.840
Are they having a feast without me?

00:52:09.900 --> 00:52:11.760
Don't they care where I am?

00:52:11.820 --> 00:52:14.699
Aren't I their precious savior of the

00:52:14.699 --> 00:52:15.300
world or something?

00:52:15.360 --> 00:52:18.719
Then again, her last fight with

00:52:18.719 --> 00:52:20.460
Belladonna had been quite dramatic.

00:52:20.519 --> 00:52:23.639
It would be just like her mother to spite

00:52:23.639 --> 00:52:25.800
her by burning down a hive and

00:52:25.800 --> 00:52:28.199
celebrating with an all tribe panther

00:52:28.199 --> 00:52:30.420
feast, while pretending she didn't care

00:52:30.420 --> 00:52:31.920
whether sundew was there or not.

00:52:31.980 --> 00:52:34.380
She knew Sundew would have to come back

00:52:34.380 --> 00:52:34.920
eventually.

00:52:34.980 --> 00:52:37.380
Sundew had nowhere else to go.

00:52:37.440 --> 00:52:41.699
But if I did, if I could just fly away.

00:52:41.760 --> 00:52:43.139
Would I?

00:52:43.199 --> 00:52:46.800
Sunday's talons went to the pout with a

00:52:46.800 --> 00:52:48.059
little jade frog in it.

00:52:48.119 --> 00:52:49.980
I could have left.

00:52:50.039 --> 00:52:52.619
Belladonna doesn't even know I could have

00:52:52.619 --> 00:52:53.039
left them.

00:52:53.099 --> 00:52:54.780
But I didn't.

00:52:54.840 --> 00:52:58.260
Because I have a purpose, and that

00:52:58.260 --> 00:53:00.119
purpose is vengeance.

00:53:00.179 --> 00:53:02.579
I hatched for one reason.

00:53:02.639 --> 00:53:04.739
To destroy our enemies.

00:53:04.800 --> 00:53:09.239
That's why I will always come back, not

00:53:09.239 --> 00:53:11.340
for Belladonna, or Hemlock.

00:53:11.400 --> 00:53:14.940
I come back, so that one day I can be the

00:53:14.940 --> 00:53:16.619
one who wipes out the hive wings

00:53:16.619 --> 00:53:16.920
forever.

00:53:17.039 --> 00:53:22.739
A tiny face clamoring, Snoodoo, poked its

00:53:22.739 --> 00:53:24.840
way into her thoughts, and she scowled.

00:53:24.900 --> 00:53:28.199
Or, oh, the high wings except two, I

00:53:28.199 --> 00:53:28.440
guess.

00:53:28.500 --> 00:53:31.739
Below her, the panther pounced

00:53:31.739 --> 00:53:33.360
experimentally toward mandrake.

00:53:33.420 --> 00:53:37.019
Mandrake shrieked and threw a seed pod at

00:53:37.019 --> 00:53:38.579
it before running off to the other side

00:53:38.579 --> 00:53:39.420
of the clearing.

00:53:39.420 --> 00:53:42.480
Nettle sighed loudly and rolled her

00:53:42.480 --> 00:53:42.659
eyes.

00:53:42.719 --> 00:53:45.840
He has to learn how to do this.

00:53:45.960 --> 00:53:47.579
Wolf Spain said to her.

00:53:47.639 --> 00:53:49.199
Why?

00:53:49.260 --> 00:53:50.519
She complained.

00:53:50.579 --> 00:53:53.400
I could do it so much faster without any

00:53:53.400 --> 00:53:54.239
magical powers.

00:53:54.300 --> 00:53:56.880
And if we need the magic, We have

00:53:56.880 --> 00:53:57.480
sundew.

00:53:57.539 --> 00:54:00.599
We don't have sundew right now.

00:54:00.659 --> 00:54:02.579
Her father pointed out.

00:54:02.639 --> 00:54:05.159
She might have to go on another mission

00:54:05.159 --> 00:54:05.760
like this one.

00:54:05.820 --> 00:54:08.400
And what if we're attacked and Mandrake

00:54:08.400 --> 00:54:09.239
has to step up.

00:54:09.300 --> 00:54:11.940
Then we're all going to die.

00:54:12.059 --> 00:54:13.860
Nettle said flatly.

00:54:13.920 --> 00:54:18.539
I can hear you, Mandrake protested, and

00:54:18.539 --> 00:54:20.219
it is not helping.

00:54:20.280 --> 00:54:23.280
He dug his talons into the leaf mulch

00:54:23.280 --> 00:54:24.719
underneath him and closed his eyes.

00:54:24.780 --> 00:54:28.679
By all the trees, Sundew thought.

00:54:28.800 --> 00:54:30.900
Don't close your eyes, mandrake.

00:54:30.960 --> 00:54:33.059
Not when there's a panther stalking you.

00:54:33.119 --> 00:54:36.539
This was why mandrake was never assigned

00:54:36.539 --> 00:54:38.099
to offensive plant magic.

00:54:38.159 --> 00:54:42.480
He always had to focus and breathe, even

00:54:42.480 --> 00:54:43.980
in the middle of an actual emergency.

00:54:44.039 --> 00:54:48.059
Well, sundew couldn't let him get mauled

00:54:48.059 --> 00:54:50.460
by a panther, even if that might make her

00:54:50.460 --> 00:54:51.360
life a little easier.

00:54:51.420 --> 00:54:54.840
She sent her magic down through the trunk

00:54:54.840 --> 00:54:57.179
and into the ground and through the roots

00:54:57.179 --> 00:55:00.059
and the mosses and ferns to the thicket

00:55:00.059 --> 00:55:01.920
of thorn tangles behind the panther.

00:55:02.039 --> 00:55:05.880
As it crouched, growling, ready to spring

00:55:05.880 --> 00:55:08.219
at mandrake, she felt into the root

00:55:08.219 --> 00:55:10.679
system that extended below the panther's

00:55:10.679 --> 00:55:10.980
paws.

00:55:11.099 --> 00:55:14.400
Just before the giant cat leaped.

00:55:14.460 --> 00:55:17.099
A new thorn bush burst out of the ground

00:55:17.099 --> 00:55:19.139
and slammed into the panther's

00:55:19.139 --> 00:55:19.679
underbelly.

00:55:19.739 --> 00:55:22.920
Thorns stabbed and tangled the panther's

00:55:22.920 --> 00:55:25.139
fur as they sprouted, trapping the animal

00:55:25.139 --> 00:55:28.380
in place, with a furious yowl it tried to

00:55:28.380 --> 00:55:28.739
struggle.

00:55:28.800 --> 00:55:30.960
But its movements only ensnared it

00:55:30.960 --> 00:55:31.260
further.

00:55:31.320 --> 00:55:35.579
Across the clearing, Wolfsbane and Nettle

00:55:35.579 --> 00:55:37.619
goggled at the panther in bewilderment

00:55:37.619 --> 00:55:40.139
Sundew had to cover her snout to keep

00:55:40.139 --> 00:55:40.860
from laughing.

00:55:40.920 --> 00:55:45.179
Mandrake cracked one eyelid, then opened

00:55:45.179 --> 00:55:48.539
them both, looking startled and pleased.

00:55:48.599 --> 00:55:50.159
Whoa.

00:55:50.219 --> 00:55:51.119
Did I do that?

00:55:51.179 --> 00:55:52.440
He asked.

00:55:52.500 --> 00:55:54.239
Son.

00:55:54.300 --> 00:55:55.679
Wolfsbang crowed.

00:55:55.739 --> 00:55:57.179
Look at you.

00:55:57.239 --> 00:55:58.619
That was incredible.

00:55:58.679 --> 00:56:03.300
Uh-uh, Nettles said, resettling her face

00:56:03.300 --> 00:56:04.679
into its usual sneer.

00:56:04.739 --> 00:56:06.000
No way.

00:56:06.059 --> 00:56:07.980
Send do.

00:56:08.039 --> 00:56:09.300
Send you.

00:56:09.360 --> 00:56:11.039
You can't fool me.

00:56:11.099 --> 00:56:13.199
I know you're here somewhere.

00:56:13.260 --> 00:56:17.639
Sundew held her breath, wondering if she

00:56:17.639 --> 00:56:19.260
could brazen it out.

00:56:19.320 --> 00:56:22.139
Wolfsbane and mandrake squinted up into

00:56:22.139 --> 00:56:25.079
the trees, and of course, right into that

00:56:25.079 --> 00:56:27.960
moment of silence, a very loud, high

00:56:27.960 --> 00:56:31.980
pitched voice howled, Snoo doo.

00:56:32.099 --> 00:56:34.679
What was that?

00:56:34.800 --> 00:56:37.619
Mandrake asked, looking spooked?

00:56:37.679 --> 00:56:41.460
Sounded like a dragonette, said his

00:56:41.460 --> 00:56:41.699
father.

00:56:41.760 --> 00:56:44.699
Sounded like proof that I am right.

00:56:44.760 --> 00:56:48.119
Nettle barked, come on out, sundew.

00:56:48.179 --> 00:56:50.219
Sundew sighed.

00:56:50.280 --> 00:56:52.500
There was no hiding the wrestling and

00:56:52.500 --> 00:56:55.500
shushing noises coming from above, or the

00:56:55.500 --> 00:57:00.420
e, e, now. wail that followed.

00:57:00.539 --> 00:57:05.340
Dragonettes, 100% the worst.

00:57:05.400 --> 00:57:08.579
She swung down from the tree and thumped

00:57:08.579 --> 00:57:11.159
to the ground in a cloud of damp leaf

00:57:11.159 --> 00:57:11.760
fragments.

00:57:11.820 --> 00:57:15.360
Hey, mandrake, she said with a nod.

00:57:15.480 --> 00:57:19.800
Oh, he said, his wings drooping.

00:57:19.860 --> 00:57:21.300
It was you.

00:57:21.360 --> 00:57:24.780
Pardon me for making sure you didn't

00:57:24.780 --> 00:57:26.639
become her feast instead of the other way

00:57:26.639 --> 00:57:30.000
around, Sandu growled, flicking her tail

00:57:30.000 --> 00:57:30.719
of the panther.

00:57:30.780 --> 00:57:34.679
I knew it, Nettle said.

00:57:34.739 --> 00:57:39.719
Sorry, I mean, thank you, said Mandrake.

00:57:39.780 --> 00:57:41.880
I was just excited for a moment.

00:57:42.000 --> 00:57:46.320
I know, Sundoo said, but you have to

00:57:46.320 --> 00:57:48.179
learn to feel the plants, with your eyes

00:57:48.179 --> 00:57:48.599
open.

00:57:48.659 --> 00:57:51.539
She glared at wolf's vein.

00:57:51.599 --> 00:57:54.119
Especially if your irresponsible family

00:57:54.119 --> 00:57:55.800
is going to keep trying to get you

00:57:55.800 --> 00:57:56.039
killed.

00:57:56.099 --> 00:57:59.159
I was watching him.

00:57:59.219 --> 00:58:01.320
Wolf Spain said dismissively.

00:58:01.380 --> 00:58:02.940
Sundo.

00:58:03.000 --> 00:58:05.519
What is that cacophony up there?

00:58:05.579 --> 00:58:08.880
He pointed out with his eyebrows raised

00:58:08.880 --> 00:58:11.159
as though there was anything unfamiliar

00:58:11.159 --> 00:58:13.079
about the sound of a hungry dragonette

00:58:13.079 --> 00:58:14.519
throwing a temper tantrum.

00:58:14.579 --> 00:58:16.739
You can come down.

00:58:16.860 --> 00:58:19.019
Sunday's shouted to her friends.

00:58:19.079 --> 00:58:22.139
Go to the trunk and work your way down

00:58:22.139 --> 00:58:22.619
slowly.

00:58:22.739 --> 00:58:25.380
Don't touch anything but the tree.

00:58:25.440 --> 00:58:28.380
Metal's mouth dropped open again.

00:58:28.440 --> 00:58:30.239
Who is that?

00:58:30.300 --> 00:58:31.260
She demanded.

00:58:31.320 --> 00:58:33.599
Someone who doesn't know our jungle?

00:58:33.659 --> 00:58:37.619
Did you bring strangers into our trees?

00:58:37.739 --> 00:58:40.199
Don't be a drama queen.

00:58:40.260 --> 00:58:42.179
Sundew said sharply.

00:58:42.239 --> 00:58:43.199
They can help us.

00:58:43.260 --> 00:58:46.440
Do your parents know about this?

00:58:46.500 --> 00:58:50.280
Wolfsbane asked, which was only the most

00:58:50.280 --> 00:58:53.400
irritating question in the universe, and

00:58:53.400 --> 00:58:55.320
one Sunday was very sick of hearing.

00:58:55.380 --> 00:58:58.739
Belladonna and Hemlock had gone ahead and

00:58:58.739 --> 00:59:00.960
burned down a hive without asking her

00:59:00.960 --> 00:59:01.320
first.

00:59:01.380 --> 00:59:03.960
So it served them right for her to bring

00:59:03.960 --> 00:59:06.420
hive wings and silk wings into the jungle

00:59:06.420 --> 00:59:07.619
without their permission.

00:59:07.679 --> 00:59:10.440
Sortell hid the ground first.

00:59:10.500 --> 00:59:13.260
His talons sinking into the layers of

00:59:13.260 --> 00:59:15.300
moss and dead leaves with a squelch.

00:59:15.360 --> 00:59:17.639
He looked a little the worse for wear

00:59:17.639 --> 00:59:20.460
after his tussle with a dragon trap, but

00:59:20.460 --> 00:59:22.320
still very clearly a silk wing.

00:59:22.380 --> 00:59:25.199
Nettle was about to snap something

00:59:25.199 --> 00:59:25.980
furious.

00:59:26.039 --> 00:59:29.579
When Blue climbed down behind Swordtail

00:59:29.579 --> 00:59:32.820
and she lost her powers of speech, There

00:59:32.820 --> 00:59:35.820
was nothing that color blue in the poison

00:59:35.820 --> 00:59:36.300
jungle.

00:59:36.360 --> 00:59:39.659
He was a kind of shiny that sundew's

00:59:39.659 --> 00:59:40.559
tribe wasn't used to.

00:59:40.619 --> 00:59:44.340
But even blue's beautiful wings couldn't

00:59:44.340 --> 00:59:45.900
distract the leaf wings from the

00:59:45.900 --> 00:59:48.059
appearance of cricket, cradling

00:59:48.059 --> 00:59:48.840
bumblebee.

00:59:48.900 --> 00:59:52.079
Nettle flared her wings with a violent

00:59:52.079 --> 00:59:52.559
hiss.

00:59:52.619 --> 00:59:55.920
Wolfsbane whipped a long, thorny vine off

00:59:55.920 --> 00:59:58.199
his tail and held it ready to fight.

00:59:58.260 --> 01:00:01.500
Even mandrake growled softly under his

01:00:01.500 --> 01:00:02.039
breath.

01:00:02.099 --> 01:00:06.360
It's all right, calm down, Sundu said.

01:00:06.480 --> 01:00:07.199
They're with me.

01:00:07.320 --> 01:00:10.920
That doesn't make it all right, Nettle

01:00:10.920 --> 01:00:11.400
cried.

01:00:11.460 --> 01:00:13.500
Hive wings in here?

01:00:13.559 --> 01:00:14.280
What is wrong with you?

01:00:14.340 --> 01:00:16.559
Queen Wasp will be right behind them.

01:00:16.619 --> 01:00:18.900
No, she won't.

01:00:19.019 --> 01:00:20.460
Sundew snapped.

01:00:20.519 --> 01:00:22.920
She can't mind control these two.

01:00:23.039 --> 01:00:25.500
She doesn't know where they are or where

01:00:25.500 --> 01:00:25.980
we are.

01:00:26.039 --> 01:00:30.360
Nothing has changed, except now we have a

01:00:30.360 --> 01:00:31.079
flame silk.

01:00:31.139 --> 01:00:34.260
Wolfsbane let out a little huff of

01:00:34.260 --> 01:00:36.360
surprise and pointed at Blue.

01:00:36.420 --> 01:00:37.559
That one.

01:00:37.619 --> 01:00:41.460
Sundew hesitated. and was furious at

01:00:41.460 --> 01:00:42.840
herself for hesitating.

01:00:42.900 --> 01:00:45.059
Why did she feel weird about this?

01:00:45.119 --> 01:00:47.940
Yes, she said.

01:00:48.000 --> 01:00:51.000
She felt a twinge of that weird feeling

01:00:51.000 --> 01:00:52.980
at the nervous look on Blue's face.

01:00:53.099 --> 01:00:55.800
But he doesn't have anything to worry

01:00:55.800 --> 01:00:57.480
about, she told herself.

01:00:57.539 --> 01:01:00.840
He can be useful to us, and will protect

01:01:00.840 --> 01:01:01.619
him from wasp.

01:01:01.739 --> 01:01:02.760
Win-win.

01:01:02.820 --> 01:01:06.960
I wouldn't say you have a flame silk.

01:01:07.019 --> 01:01:09.000
Swartell said pointedly.

01:01:09.059 --> 01:01:12.659
I mean, he is a flame silk, and he's here

01:01:12.659 --> 01:01:14.940
but he has himself.

01:01:15.000 --> 01:01:16.019
No one else has him.

01:01:16.079 --> 01:01:18.119
I mean, he is not for having.

01:01:18.179 --> 01:01:19.500
He's his own dragon.

01:01:19.559 --> 01:01:21.599
Hmm.

01:01:21.659 --> 01:01:24.900
Wolf Spain said, ignoring him and

01:01:24.900 --> 01:01:27.179
studying blue with fathomless brown

01:01:27.179 --> 01:01:27.480
eyes.

01:01:27.539 --> 01:01:30.840
So why not kill the others and just keep

01:01:30.840 --> 01:01:31.980
this one sundo?

01:01:32.039 --> 01:01:36.119
Because they're all useful, Sundew said

01:01:36.119 --> 01:01:36.480
quickly.

01:01:36.539 --> 01:01:38.940
She tried to make her voice sound as

01:01:38.940 --> 01:01:41.519
aggressive and no nonsense as she could

01:01:41.519 --> 01:01:43.380
especially the hive wing.

01:01:43.440 --> 01:01:46.380
She's immune to the mind control, and we

01:01:46.380 --> 01:01:48.300
think she's figured out how WASP does

01:01:48.300 --> 01:01:48.480
it.

01:01:48.599 --> 01:01:50.940
What about him?

01:01:51.000 --> 01:01:54.000
Metal asked, pointing its sword tail.

01:01:54.059 --> 01:01:55.679
He looks unnecessary.

01:01:55.739 --> 01:01:59.400
All right, maybe useful is the wrong

01:01:59.400 --> 01:01:59.760
word.

01:01:59.820 --> 01:02:03.239
Sendu amended, earning an offended look

01:02:03.239 --> 01:02:05.159
from the blue orange white dragon.

01:02:05.219 --> 01:02:07.559
But we can't kill him without upsetting

01:02:07.559 --> 01:02:09.119
the flame silk, not worth it.

01:02:09.179 --> 01:02:13.199
Blue blinked, and sidled a step closer to

01:02:13.199 --> 01:02:13.860
SwordTail.

01:02:13.920 --> 01:02:17.280
His antennae had unfurled into thin

01:02:17.280 --> 01:02:19.800
trembling stems over his head, like

01:02:19.800 --> 01:02:22.019
tentacles of ivy looking for a place to

01:02:22.019 --> 01:02:22.800
land safely.

01:02:22.920 --> 01:02:28.440
I am useful, Swartel protested, I have

01:02:28.440 --> 01:02:29.159
many uses.

01:02:29.219 --> 01:02:32.460
I am smart, and I know things, and I can

01:02:32.460 --> 01:02:35.280
fight hive wings, and I am in the

01:02:35.280 --> 01:02:36.300
chrysalis.

01:02:36.360 --> 01:02:39.420
Hello, which everyone seems to forget

01:02:39.480 --> 01:02:41.099
secret revolutionary over here.

01:02:41.159 --> 01:02:45.059
And I am also, by the way, extremely good

01:02:45.059 --> 01:02:45.480
company.

01:02:45.539 --> 01:02:50.099
And the dragonette, Wolfbane asked

01:02:50.099 --> 01:02:50.940
Sundew.

01:02:51.000 --> 01:02:53.579
An experiment, she said.

01:02:53.639 --> 01:02:55.860
We think she's immune to the mind control

01:02:55.860 --> 01:02:56.280
too.

01:02:56.340 --> 01:02:59.039
Youth think?

01:02:59.099 --> 01:03:00.420
Nettle demanded.

01:03:00.480 --> 01:03:03.179
That's quite a risky experiment, you

01:03:03.179 --> 01:03:03.659
idiots.

01:03:03.780 --> 01:03:08.159
It's going great so far, Sundew flared.

01:03:08.219 --> 01:03:10.679
You get away with everything, because

01:03:10.679 --> 01:03:13.019
you're Belladonna's daughter, and you're

01:03:13.019 --> 01:03:14.039
so special.

01:03:14.159 --> 01:03:17.039
Nettle shouted, but you've gone too far

01:03:17.039 --> 01:03:18.420
this time sundew.

01:03:18.480 --> 01:03:19.800
No one will stand for this.

01:03:19.860 --> 01:03:23.579
Let's go ask Belladonna what to do

01:03:23.579 --> 01:03:27.000
Wolfsbane said, resting one talon on

01:03:27.000 --> 01:03:27.840
Nettle's shoulder.

01:03:27.900 --> 01:03:29.340
Fine.

01:03:29.460 --> 01:03:32.099
Nettles shook him off, but I know what

01:03:32.099 --> 01:03:32.579
she'll say.

01:03:32.639 --> 01:03:35.280
We'll be back soon to execute your new

01:03:35.280 --> 01:03:35.820
pets.

01:03:35.880 --> 01:03:39.420
She folded her wings and hissed at sundew

01:03:39.420 --> 01:03:41.820
one more time before turning and marching

01:03:41.820 --> 01:03:42.000
away.

01:03:42.059 --> 01:03:46.139
Wait for us here, Wolf Spain said.

01:03:46.199 --> 01:03:48.119
I'll stay with them.

01:03:48.239 --> 01:03:49.679
Mandrake offered.

01:03:49.800 --> 01:03:53.039
Wolfbane gave a faint shrug and followed

01:03:53.039 --> 01:03:54.300
Nettle into the undergrowth.

01:03:54.360 --> 01:03:58.199
Sundew sat down with a snort of disgust.

01:03:58.260 --> 01:04:01.440
This wasn't how she'd planned to arrive.

01:04:01.500 --> 01:04:03.960
She was supposed to be the one who

01:04:03.960 --> 01:04:05.579
explained all this to Belladonna.

01:04:05.639 --> 01:04:08.760
Not that she wanted to, but she didn't

01:04:08.760 --> 01:04:10.500
want stupid wolfsbane to do it.

01:04:10.559 --> 01:04:12.000
He'd get it all wrong.

01:04:12.059 --> 01:04:13.860
But it didn't matter.

01:04:13.920 --> 01:04:16.739
Belladonna wasn't the boss of Sundew

01:04:16.739 --> 01:04:19.980
except in the literal, she ran the whole

01:04:19.980 --> 01:04:22.860
tribe sense, but Sundew was going to save

01:04:22.860 --> 01:04:25.739
the world, and wreak furious vengeance on

01:04:25.739 --> 01:04:26.940
those who deserved it.

01:04:27.000 --> 01:04:29.579
So there wasn't anything Belladonna could

01:04:29.579 --> 01:04:32.400
do to her or her friends, not if she

01:04:32.400 --> 01:04:33.659
wanted a part in a vengeance.

01:04:33.780 --> 01:04:36.360
Just try me, mother.

01:04:36.420 --> 01:04:42.900
Oh, Blue said, that didn't sound like it

01:04:42.900 --> 01:04:43.679
went very well.

01:04:43.739 --> 01:04:45.420
Really?

01:04:45.480 --> 01:04:47.519
That was a pretty average conversation

01:04:47.519 --> 01:04:49.980
with Nettle, Sundew said.

01:04:50.039 --> 01:04:52.920
She took a breath, searching the greenery

01:04:52.920 --> 01:04:53.820
with her mind.

01:04:53.880 --> 01:04:54.780
There.

01:04:54.840 --> 01:04:58.079
A bush covered in small pale globules.

01:04:58.139 --> 01:05:00.659
Her power slipped through the roots and

01:05:00.659 --> 01:05:03.119
stems to grow just one of the branches

01:05:03.119 --> 01:05:04.440
out until she could reach it.

01:05:04.500 --> 01:05:07.139
She took one of the sticky white berries

01:05:07.139 --> 01:05:08.280
and threw it at the panther.

01:05:08.340 --> 01:05:11.460
It snarled and snapped the berry out of

01:05:11.460 --> 01:05:11.760
the air.

01:05:11.820 --> 01:05:14.940
A moment later, the panther keeled over

01:05:14.940 --> 01:05:15.780
dead.

01:05:15.840 --> 01:05:20.280
Oh, cool, Mandrake said with a flick of

01:05:20.280 --> 01:05:22.739
his wings, which were dark green with

01:05:22.739 --> 01:05:25.739
thin gold stripes on top and mahogany

01:05:25.739 --> 01:05:26.460
brown underneath.

01:05:26.519 --> 01:05:30.360
But everyone can still eat the panther

01:05:30.360 --> 01:05:30.539
right?

01:05:30.599 --> 01:05:34.139
Yeah, I use these on prey all the time

01:05:34.139 --> 01:05:36.659
she said, tossing one to him.

01:05:36.719 --> 01:05:40.260
Harmless to dragons, deadly to mammals.

01:05:40.320 --> 01:05:41.159
No idea why.

01:05:41.280 --> 01:05:42.900
Really?

01:05:42.960 --> 01:05:44.159
Cricket said.

01:05:44.219 --> 01:05:46.980
Mandrake handed her the berry, and she

01:05:46.980 --> 01:05:48.119
gave it a fascinated look.

01:05:48.179 --> 01:05:50.519
E?

01:05:50.579 --> 01:05:53.880
Bumblebee asked, leaning out of her sling

01:05:53.880 --> 01:05:54.239
hopefully.

01:05:54.300 --> 01:05:58.260
Maybe not this, Cricket said to her, just

01:05:58.260 --> 01:05:58.980
to be safe.

01:05:59.099 --> 01:06:02.639
Here, these are all right to eat, Sundew

01:06:02.639 --> 01:06:04.920
said, unearthing a tuber from the dark

01:06:04.920 --> 01:06:06.780
earth and flinging it to cricket.

01:06:06.840 --> 01:06:09.239
Snoodoo.

01:06:09.300 --> 01:06:12.659
Bumblebee cooed, with a worshipful look.

01:06:12.719 --> 01:06:16.380
Maybe she thinks Snoodoo means food

01:06:16.380 --> 01:06:17.699
Sundoo guest.

01:06:17.760 --> 01:06:20.400
Pretty sure she knows it's you.

01:06:20.519 --> 01:06:23.219
The hero who provides all the best food

01:06:23.219 --> 01:06:26.219
cricket said, tucking the root into

01:06:26.219 --> 01:06:29.460
bumblebee's tiny talons, the dragonette

01:06:29.460 --> 01:06:31.320
wrapped her little arms around the tuber

01:06:31.320 --> 01:06:33.239
and began gnawing on it with great

01:06:33.239 --> 01:06:34.019
determination.

01:06:34.139 --> 01:06:36.360
Excuse me.

01:06:36.420 --> 01:06:37.980
Should we be running away?

01:06:38.039 --> 01:06:41.340
Swartell asked, maybe hiding?

01:06:41.400 --> 01:06:42.300
Boss?

01:06:42.360 --> 01:06:44.460
Don't you think hiding us might be a good

01:06:44.460 --> 01:06:45.179
idea?

01:06:45.239 --> 01:06:47.820
No, you nitwit?

01:06:47.880 --> 01:06:49.860
We're trying to get to the village, not

01:06:49.860 --> 01:06:50.579
hide from it.

01:06:50.639 --> 01:06:52.559
Getting there was the whole point.

01:06:52.619 --> 01:06:54.900
Nobody's going to execute you.

01:06:55.019 --> 01:06:57.179
Sundew said impatiently.

01:06:57.239 --> 01:06:59.340
Not until I tell them to anyway.

01:06:59.400 --> 01:07:00.719
They need me.

01:07:00.780 --> 01:07:04.500
Because of your power, cricket guest.

01:07:04.559 --> 01:07:06.360
They need yours too.

01:07:06.420 --> 01:07:08.760
Sundew pointed out to Blue.

01:07:08.820 --> 01:07:11.099
So tell them exactly what you want.

01:07:11.159 --> 01:07:12.840
Don't let them walk all over you.

01:07:12.900 --> 01:07:17.519
Oh, but all right.

01:07:17.579 --> 01:07:21.840
But mild dragons are hard to deal with, he

01:07:21.840 --> 01:07:22.139
said.

01:07:22.199 --> 01:07:27.179
Are all leaf wings that, um, shouty?

01:07:27.239 --> 01:07:29.280
Everyone but me.

01:07:29.340 --> 01:07:32.099
Mandrake answered with a nervous laugh.

01:07:32.159 --> 01:07:34.139
That's not true.

01:07:34.199 --> 01:07:37.679
Sundew thought, touching her jade frog

01:07:37.679 --> 01:07:40.380
lightly through the pouch, but he's never

01:07:40.380 --> 01:07:40.920
met the others.

01:07:40.980 --> 01:07:46.619
The one nice leaf wing, Swartail said

01:07:46.619 --> 01:07:48.000
sounds like a good dragon to know.

01:07:48.059 --> 01:07:50.460
I'm Cricket.

01:07:50.519 --> 01:07:51.719
This is Bumblebee.

01:07:51.780 --> 01:07:55.380
That's Blue, and that's Swordtail, cricket

01:07:55.380 --> 01:07:55.860
said.

01:07:55.920 --> 01:07:58.260
She tilted her head at Mandrake.

01:07:58.320 --> 01:07:59.519
Who are you?

01:07:59.579 --> 01:08:05.219
I'm Mandrake, he said, smiling his non

01:08:04.199 --> 01:08:06.360
threatening, crooked smile at all of

01:08:06.360 --> 01:08:06.539
them.

01:08:06.599 --> 01:08:08.639
Sundu's fiance.

01:08:08.699 --> 01:08:12.659
Chapter 4.

01:08:12.960 --> 01:08:16.680
Cricket world to stare at sundew.

01:08:16.739 --> 01:08:18.899
Her what?

01:08:18.960 --> 01:08:21.300
Sword tail echoed.

01:08:21.359 --> 01:08:24.179
I thought we agreed not to use that

01:08:24.179 --> 01:08:24.479
word.

01:08:24.600 --> 01:08:26.819
Sundu grumbled at Mandrake.

01:08:26.880 --> 01:08:31.079
Well, future husband sounds weird, he

01:08:31.079 --> 01:08:31.619
pointed out.

01:08:31.680 --> 01:08:35.279
So does fiance, super weird.

01:08:35.340 --> 01:08:37.920
She snapped a dying branch off the

01:08:37.920 --> 01:08:40.380
nearest bush and broke it in her talons

01:08:40.380 --> 01:08:42.359
over and over until it was a pile of

01:08:42.359 --> 01:08:42.899
splinters.

01:08:42.960 --> 01:08:47.699
But you, this dragon?

01:08:47.760 --> 01:08:49.739
Blue said, bewildered.

01:08:49.859 --> 01:08:54.419
I just Didn't picture your one true love

01:08:54.419 --> 01:08:55.859
being someone like this.

01:08:55.920 --> 01:08:57.659
Cricket finished for him.

01:08:57.720 --> 01:09:01.079
Nobody said anything about true love.

01:09:01.199 --> 01:09:03.420
Sundew yelped.

01:09:03.479 --> 01:09:06.479
At the same time as Mandrake stammered, no

01:09:06.479 --> 01:09:07.979
no, that's not at all.

01:09:08.039 --> 01:09:10.020
No, we are not that, no.

01:09:10.079 --> 01:09:13.500
Cricket and Blue exchanged puzzled

01:09:13.500 --> 01:09:16.020
glances, which made Sundo want to poke

01:09:16.020 --> 01:09:17.579
them quite hard with her claws.

01:09:17.640 --> 01:09:20.100
Just because they were all melty and

01:09:20.100 --> 01:09:21.899
silly over each other didn't mean

01:09:21.899 --> 01:09:23.520
everyone else in the world got to be that

01:09:23.520 --> 01:09:23.760
way.

01:09:23.819 --> 01:09:29.279
But, I thought, cricket started, and

01:09:29.279 --> 01:09:31.139
Sundew suddenly had a horrible flash of

01:09:31.139 --> 01:09:31.499
memory.

01:09:31.560 --> 01:09:33.479
Oh no.

01:09:33.539 --> 01:09:36.840
She'd said something to the nosy hive

01:09:36.840 --> 01:09:39.060
wing a few days ago about how she

01:09:39.060 --> 01:09:41.399
understood Sordail's obsession with Luna

01:09:41.399 --> 01:09:44.340
because she had a one true love too.

01:09:44.399 --> 01:09:47.939
A thing she hadn't even thought about

01:09:47.939 --> 01:09:50.039
blurting out, because she'd never

01:09:50.039 --> 01:09:52.739
expected to see cricket standing here, in

01:09:52.739 --> 01:09:54.839
the poison jungle, right in front of

01:09:54.839 --> 01:09:56.939
Mandrake, about to spill the biggest

01:09:56.939 --> 01:09:59.279
secret was keeping from her tribe.

01:09:59.340 --> 01:10:03.479
Nope, she shouted, before Cricket could

01:10:03.479 --> 01:10:06.600
finish her sentence, wrong, bad, no

01:10:06.600 --> 01:10:07.079
thinking.

01:10:07.140 --> 01:10:09.119
Whatever you thought, stuff it back in

01:10:09.119 --> 01:10:09.300
there.

01:10:09.359 --> 01:10:12.779
She bumped Mandrake's side, and did a

01:10:12.779 --> 01:10:14.760
weird hopping sidestep that was

01:10:14.760 --> 01:10:16.800
definitely not going to convince anyone

01:10:16.800 --> 01:10:17.579
of her sanity.

01:10:17.640 --> 01:10:20.220
We're just betrothed.

01:10:20.279 --> 01:10:20.819
It's not weird.

01:10:20.880 --> 01:10:21.720
It's normal fine.

01:10:21.779 --> 01:10:24.239
Oh my goodness.

01:10:24.359 --> 01:10:26.520
Blue said, blinking.

01:10:26.579 --> 01:10:29.159
What is happening right now?

01:10:29.279 --> 01:10:30.899
Swordell asked.

01:10:31.020 --> 01:10:34.920
All right, I'm sorry, Cricket said.

01:10:34.979 --> 01:10:38.159
She took a step back from sundew, tilting

01:10:38.159 --> 01:10:39.539
her wings calmingly.

01:10:39.600 --> 01:10:41.880
I totally misunderstood.

01:10:41.939 --> 01:10:46.380
She hadn't, and she didn't, and she knew

01:10:46.380 --> 01:10:46.619
it.

01:10:46.680 --> 01:10:49.680
Sandu couldn't read other dragons the way

01:10:49.680 --> 01:10:52.079
she could read plants, but cricket was

01:10:52.079 --> 01:10:54.659
like a wide open encyclopedia, and at the

01:10:54.659 --> 01:10:58.199
moment, her pages were turned to mystery

01:10:58.199 --> 01:11:00.420
I am biting my tongue about for now, but

01:11:00.420 --> 01:11:02.100
will definitely solve eventually.

01:11:02.220 --> 01:11:05.520
Which did not bode well for sundew's

01:11:05.520 --> 01:11:06.300
secret.

01:11:06.359 --> 01:11:10.500
So, how can you have a fiance?

01:11:10.560 --> 01:11:13.260
Cricket asked. aren't you the same age as

01:11:13.260 --> 01:11:13.560
I am?

01:11:13.680 --> 01:11:16.800
I'm six, Sundew said.

01:11:16.859 --> 01:11:19.680
But ever since we hatched, the plan has

01:11:19.680 --> 01:11:20.880
always been for us to get married

01:11:20.880 --> 01:11:21.720
eventually.

01:11:21.779 --> 01:11:24.720
We both have the strongest leaf speak in

01:11:24.720 --> 01:11:27.539
the tribe, which means our dragonettes

01:11:27.539 --> 01:11:29.819
should be even more powerful, and that's

01:11:29.819 --> 01:11:31.560
what the tribe needs to defeat the hive

01:11:31.560 --> 01:11:33.180
wings and restore the trees.

01:11:33.239 --> 01:11:35.520
Unless I can do it all myself.

01:11:35.640 --> 01:11:38.699
Then I could be with a dragon I choose.

01:11:38.760 --> 01:11:41.100
Mandrake was nodding.

01:11:41.159 --> 01:11:44.340
Sundube's leaf speak is much stronger

01:11:44.340 --> 01:11:45.899
than mine, though, he said.

01:11:45.960 --> 01:11:48.659
The strongest our tribe is seen in

01:11:48.659 --> 01:11:49.079
centuries.

01:11:49.140 --> 01:11:52.560
That's why Belladonna and Hemlock got

01:11:52.560 --> 01:11:54.720
together to have me, Sundu said.

01:11:54.840 --> 01:11:57.539
They had the strongest leaf speak in the

01:11:57.539 --> 01:11:58.199
last generation.

01:11:58.260 --> 01:12:01.319
The tribe has been working toward having

01:12:01.319 --> 01:12:03.899
a dragon like sundew ever since the tree

01:12:03.899 --> 01:12:05.819
wars, Mandrake added.

01:12:05.880 --> 01:12:10.199
Oh, Cricket said, as though several

01:12:10.199 --> 01:12:12.300
answers were finally clicking together in

01:12:12.300 --> 01:12:12.600
her head.

01:12:12.659 --> 01:12:15.479
When did my parents get back?

01:12:15.539 --> 01:12:17.460
Sundew asked Mandrake.

01:12:17.520 --> 01:12:20.939
She wanted to know, and she also very

01:12:20.939 --> 01:12:22.800
much wanted to get off the subject of her

01:12:22.800 --> 01:12:23.460
future marriage.

01:12:23.520 --> 01:12:26.640
Not long before you, he said.

01:12:26.819 --> 01:12:28.140
Maybe half a day?

01:12:28.199 --> 01:12:30.779
And only Belladonna and Odalum.

01:12:30.840 --> 01:12:32.760
Hemlock and the other 2 were going to

01:12:32.760 --> 01:12:36.000
ground near the, uh, the target.

01:12:36.119 --> 01:12:38.640
He cast a nervous glance of the other

01:12:38.640 --> 01:12:39.119
dragons.

01:12:39.180 --> 01:12:41.399
They know, she said.

01:12:41.520 --> 01:12:44.039
We saw the fire, from a distance, I

01:12:44.039 --> 01:12:44.279
mean.

01:12:44.340 --> 01:12:46.380
His eyes lit up.

01:12:46.439 --> 01:12:47.939
Oh, wow.

01:12:48.000 --> 01:12:49.619
Was it amazing?

01:12:49.680 --> 01:12:51.899
Billadonna said they torched the whole

01:12:51.899 --> 01:12:52.140
thing.

01:12:52.199 --> 01:12:56.159
Flames brushing the clouds, hive wings

01:12:56.159 --> 01:12:57.779
screaming with rage.

01:12:57.899 --> 01:13:00.479
We weren't that close.

01:13:00.539 --> 01:13:03.239
Sundu said, we just saw the smoke.

01:13:03.300 --> 01:13:05.939
I don't know if the whole hive burned

01:13:05.939 --> 01:13:06.180
down.

01:13:06.239 --> 01:13:09.600
And I wouldn't trust Belladonna's

01:13:09.600 --> 01:13:09.779
report.

01:13:09.840 --> 01:13:13.199
Her mother had a tendency to exaggerate

01:13:13.199 --> 01:13:15.659
especially when it came to grand plans

01:13:15.659 --> 01:13:17.279
against Queen Wasp.

01:13:17.340 --> 01:13:19.739
The whole hive.

01:13:19.800 --> 01:13:23.159
Blue echoed, gazing up into the trees.

01:13:23.220 --> 01:13:26.460
And all the webs connected to it.

01:13:26.520 --> 01:13:29.819
Mandrake had the grace to look a little

01:13:29.819 --> 01:13:30.539
abashed.

01:13:30.659 --> 01:13:33.119
Was that your hive?

01:13:33.239 --> 01:13:33.840
He asked.

01:13:33.960 --> 01:13:36.779
No, Swordtail answered.

01:13:36.840 --> 01:13:39.300
You guys burned down bloodworm hive.

01:13:39.359 --> 01:13:40.680
And good riddance.

01:13:40.739 --> 01:13:42.119
Good riddance to all of them.

01:13:42.180 --> 01:13:45.960
Sundew saw cricket flinch, and Blue

01:13:45.960 --> 01:13:47.819
gently rest his tail on hers.

01:13:47.939 --> 01:13:50.100
Blah!

01:13:50.159 --> 01:13:52.079
Bumblebee announced suddenly.

01:13:52.140 --> 01:13:55.260
She threw the tuber at Sortail's head

01:13:55.260 --> 01:13:56.220
bonking him on the snout.

01:13:56.279 --> 01:13:58.020
No, blah.

01:13:58.079 --> 01:13:59.460
Gimme go.

01:13:59.520 --> 01:14:00.720
Give me go.

01:14:00.779 --> 01:14:05.279
Hey, ow, you violent little larva, sword

01:14:05.279 --> 01:14:06.000
tell yelped.

01:14:06.060 --> 01:14:10.260
Bumblebee, calm down, Cricket said, trying

01:14:10.260 --> 01:14:12.060
to wrestle the dragonette back into the

01:14:12.060 --> 01:14:14.520
sling, but the little hive wing was too

01:14:14.520 --> 01:14:15.539
furious to be handled.

01:14:15.600 --> 01:14:18.359
She yowled and threw out her yellow and

01:14:18.359 --> 01:14:20.520
black striped wings, and flung herself

01:14:20.520 --> 01:14:23.159
around, wailing, until she managed to

01:14:23.159 --> 01:14:25.079
topple out of Cricket's arms onto the

01:14:25.079 --> 01:14:25.979
leaf mulch.

01:14:26.039 --> 01:14:29.159
Immediately she popped up and sprinted

01:14:29.159 --> 01:14:31.500
over to sundew, as well as she could

01:14:31.500 --> 01:14:31.920
sprint.

01:14:31.979 --> 01:14:34.380
It was more of a wattle, if one were

01:14:34.380 --> 01:14:35.579
going to be strictly accurate.

01:14:35.640 --> 01:14:38.699
Bumblebee collapsed on top of Sundew's

01:14:38.699 --> 01:14:41.760
foot, and batted her woebegone amber eyes

01:14:41.760 --> 01:14:43.619
up in Sundew's general direction.

01:14:43.680 --> 01:14:47.279
Snoodoo, she sniffled.

01:14:47.340 --> 01:14:49.500
Snoop, blimy.

01:14:49.560 --> 01:14:51.960
Whatever is snoobly me is?

01:14:52.020 --> 01:14:53.100
It's not my problem.

01:14:53.220 --> 01:14:54.899
Sundu informed her.

01:14:54.960 --> 01:14:57.960
Bumblebee clutched her ankle as Sundew

01:14:57.960 --> 01:14:58.619
tried to pull away.

01:14:58.680 --> 01:15:02.399
Hubble, snowble, boo, she said

01:15:02.399 --> 01:15:03.119
piteously.

01:15:03.180 --> 01:15:05.520
Eee, Snorf.

01:15:05.579 --> 01:15:08.039
How starving can you be?

01:15:08.100 --> 01:15:09.420
Sundu demanded.

01:15:09.539 --> 01:15:11.699
We'll be in the village soon, and there's

01:15:11.699 --> 01:15:12.420
plenty of food there.

01:15:12.539 --> 01:15:16.319
Bumblebee's pinprick claws dug into

01:15:16.319 --> 01:15:18.960
sundew's scales as she clambered up onto

01:15:18.960 --> 01:15:21.359
the leaf wing's shoulder and snuggled

01:15:21.359 --> 01:15:22.979
into the curve between her wing and

01:15:22.979 --> 01:15:23.579
neck.

01:15:23.640 --> 01:15:26.579
Penny foo, she said confidently.

01:15:26.640 --> 01:15:32.460
Sundew had never held a dragonette, or

01:15:32.460 --> 01:15:35.220
ever had anything climb on her, apart

01:15:35.220 --> 01:15:37.560
from unpleasant insects, as far as she

01:15:37.560 --> 01:15:38.039
could remember.

01:15:38.100 --> 01:15:40.619
Her mother had outlawed pets in the

01:15:40.619 --> 01:15:42.840
village, because they wasted resources

01:15:42.840 --> 01:15:44.520
and distracted dragons from their

01:15:44.520 --> 01:15:44.819
mission.

01:15:44.880 --> 01:15:47.939
Dragonettes were strictly supervised and

01:15:47.939 --> 01:15:50.520
kept to their own area for their safety

01:15:50.520 --> 01:15:53.220
and also probably because Belladonna

01:15:53.220 --> 01:15:54.899
didn't like them anymore than Sundew

01:15:54.899 --> 01:15:55.140
did.

01:15:55.199 --> 01:15:58.619
All her front of brain thought, told her

01:15:58.619 --> 01:16:00.659
to peel off the baby hive wing and give

01:16:00.659 --> 01:16:01.680
it back to cricket.

01:16:01.979 --> 01:16:04.199
She did not need to walk into her tribe

01:16:04.199 --> 01:16:06.840
with a tiny enemy plastered to her neck

01:16:06.840 --> 01:16:08.220
burbling cheerfully.

01:16:08.279 --> 01:16:11.460
Also, she shouldn't let bumblebee get any

01:16:11.460 --> 01:16:12.600
more attached to her.

01:16:12.600 --> 01:16:16.439
Also, also, what if Queen Wasp did jump

01:16:16.439 --> 01:16:18.119
into bumblebee all of a sudden?

01:16:18.180 --> 01:16:20.220
Then the dragonette would be in the

01:16:20.220 --> 01:16:22.260
perfect position to strangle sundew.

01:16:22.319 --> 01:16:25.140
I'm not scared of wasp.

01:16:25.199 --> 01:16:26.520
She scolded herself.

01:16:26.579 --> 01:16:29.399
I can protect myself from a dragonette

01:16:29.399 --> 01:16:31.739
and I don't have to prove anything to

01:16:31.739 --> 01:16:32.939
anyone in my tribe.

01:16:33.000 --> 01:16:35.640
So what if they don't like that I've got

01:16:35.640 --> 01:16:36.840
a hive wing on my shoulder.

01:16:36.899 --> 01:16:39.239
I am going to let her stay there.

01:16:39.300 --> 01:16:41.640
Just to show them I don't care.

01:16:41.699 --> 01:16:44.220
This is stupid.

01:16:44.279 --> 01:16:46.199
We don't have to sit here and wait for

01:16:46.199 --> 01:16:49.739
Wolfsbane, she said, resettling her wings

01:16:49.739 --> 01:16:51.239
to keep Bumblebee in place.

01:16:51.300 --> 01:16:53.640
I don't need permission to go into my own

01:16:53.640 --> 01:16:54.060
village.

01:16:54.119 --> 01:16:55.140
Come on.

01:16:55.199 --> 01:16:57.359
She marched toward the trees.

01:16:57.420 --> 01:17:02.399
But sundo, Mandrake protested, it'll only

01:17:02.399 --> 01:17:03.119
be a moment.

01:17:03.180 --> 01:17:04.199
Don't make them mad.

01:17:04.260 --> 01:17:07.500
They're already mad, she retorted.

01:17:07.560 --> 01:17:09.779
They're going to be mad no matter what we

01:17:09.779 --> 01:17:10.020
do.

01:17:10.079 --> 01:17:12.119
And it's not like we're going to spend

01:17:12.119 --> 01:17:13.199
the night in the jungle.

01:17:13.260 --> 01:17:14.279
We're going in.

01:17:14.399 --> 01:17:18.479
Follow me and don't ask questions, she

01:17:18.479 --> 01:17:20.699
said, giving Cricket a stern look.

01:17:20.819 --> 01:17:25.800
Even, I mean, yes, and do, Cricket said.

01:17:25.859 --> 01:17:29.279
Bring the panther, Sundoo said to

01:17:29.279 --> 01:17:30.300
Mandrake.

01:17:30.359 --> 01:17:33.119
She sent a message to the Thorn Bines, and

01:17:33.119 --> 01:17:35.640
they relaxed, releasing the big cat's

01:17:35.640 --> 01:17:37.859
body enough that Mandrake could haul it

01:17:37.859 --> 01:17:39.960
over one shoulder and stagger along

01:17:39.960 --> 01:17:40.380
behind them.

01:17:40.439 --> 01:17:43.739
The outer perimeter of the village was a

01:17:43.739 --> 01:17:44.460
short walk away.

01:17:44.520 --> 01:17:47.939
It looked like an upside down nest, a

01:17:47.939 --> 01:17:50.460
huge emerald and chocolate colored living

01:17:50.460 --> 01:17:53.340
dome made of interlocking vines and

01:17:53.340 --> 01:17:56.159
shrubs that soared up and up between the

01:17:56.159 --> 01:17:56.880
trees.

01:17:57.239 --> 01:17:59.819
The barrier enclosed the entire village

01:17:59.819 --> 01:18:02.699
protecting the dragons inside from all

01:18:02.699 --> 01:18:05.039
the ways the jungle might try to sneak in

01:18:05.039 --> 01:18:08.279
to kill them, hemlock, belladonna, and

01:18:08.279 --> 01:18:10.739
sundew's grandmother had started it with

01:18:10.739 --> 01:18:13.560
their limited leaf speak, but sundew had

01:18:13.560 --> 01:18:14.100
perfected it.

01:18:14.159 --> 01:18:18.060
She tested it as they approached, sending

01:18:18.060 --> 01:18:19.920
her senses along the roots under her

01:18:19.920 --> 01:18:21.899
talons and out through the weaving

01:18:21.899 --> 01:18:24.060
branches to search for any holes or

01:18:24.060 --> 01:18:24.479
weaknesses.

01:18:24.539 --> 01:18:26.760
There was a patch where the leaves were

01:18:26.760 --> 01:18:27.119
thin.

01:18:27.180 --> 01:18:29.520
After a moment of pressing the edges with

01:18:29.520 --> 01:18:32.039
her mind, she found an infestation of

01:18:32.039 --> 01:18:33.840
caterpillars that were nibbling their way

01:18:33.840 --> 01:18:34.380
through the roof.

01:18:34.439 --> 01:18:36.539
Oh no, you don't.

01:18:36.600 --> 01:18:38.399
Nobody eats my work.

01:18:38.460 --> 01:18:40.920
You will die for this caterpillars.

01:18:40.979 --> 01:18:44.399
She summoned another vine to coil across

01:18:44.399 --> 01:18:46.680
the thin spot, blending in with the other

01:18:46.680 --> 01:18:49.800
leaves, except this one was full of toxic

01:18:49.800 --> 01:18:50.220
sap.

01:18:50.279 --> 01:18:52.619
When the caterpillars tried to eat it

01:18:52.619 --> 01:18:53.819
they would be poisoned.

01:18:53.939 --> 01:18:57.000
Or they would see their friends dying

01:18:57.000 --> 01:18:59.819
wise up, and go find a different plant to

01:18:59.819 --> 01:19:00.239
invest.

01:19:00.300 --> 01:19:02.939
It was very satisfying.

01:19:03.000 --> 01:19:06.060
If only all sundew's problems could be

01:19:06.060 --> 01:19:07.020
solved that easily.

01:19:07.079 --> 01:19:09.000
Wow.

01:19:09.060 --> 01:19:12.300
Cricket said as the whole barrier came

01:19:12.300 --> 01:19:14.699
into view, rising far over their heads.

01:19:14.760 --> 01:19:20.159
How did you, er, I mean, I really wonder

01:19:20.159 --> 01:19:21.960
how dragons could build something like

01:19:21.960 --> 01:19:23.760
this and how long it would take.

01:19:23.880 --> 01:19:26.460
And which plants were used and how it

01:19:26.460 --> 01:19:29.340
survives, but notice how I am totally not

01:19:29.340 --> 01:19:31.260
asking, although I am definitely

01:19:31.260 --> 01:19:33.600
listening, should anyone around here

01:19:33.600 --> 01:19:35.579
maybe feel like talking about it?

01:19:35.640 --> 01:19:39.840
I'll give you a tour later, Sundew said

01:19:39.840 --> 01:19:41.159
hiding her amusement.

01:19:41.220 --> 01:19:44.520
Of course, sundew could go in and out of

01:19:44.520 --> 01:19:47.100
the barrier anywhere she wished, just by

01:19:47.100 --> 01:19:49.500
communicating with the plants, but for

01:19:49.500 --> 01:19:51.779
the sake of appearances, when anyone was

01:19:51.779 --> 01:19:53.399
watching, she went through the main

01:19:53.399 --> 01:19:53.760
gate.

01:19:53.819 --> 01:19:56.579
Unless it was super annoying, and that

01:19:56.579 --> 01:19:58.260
depended on who the guard on duty was.

01:19:58.319 --> 01:20:02.579
A long, elegant dragon sat in coiled

01:20:02.579 --> 01:20:05.760
stillness by the entrance, as poised as a

01:20:05.760 --> 01:20:08.279
carnivorous plant waiting for her prey to

01:20:08.279 --> 01:20:08.699
pass by.

01:20:08.760 --> 01:20:12.420
Sundew squinted at her, and saw streaks

01:20:12.420 --> 01:20:14.819
of pinkish red along her horns, and the

01:20:14.819 --> 01:20:16.560
veins of her summer green wings.

01:20:16.619 --> 01:20:19.739
She exhaled with relief, they were in

01:20:19.739 --> 01:20:19.920
luck.

01:20:19.979 --> 01:20:23.159
It was Cobra Lily, one of sundew's

01:20:23.159 --> 01:20:23.760
favorite dragons.

01:20:23.880 --> 01:20:27.300
Cobra Lily was the opposite of Nettle.

01:20:27.359 --> 01:20:30.479
She was never annoying or judgmental, and

01:20:30.479 --> 01:20:31.500
she rarely shouted.

01:20:31.560 --> 01:20:33.659
When Cobra Lily got angry?

01:20:33.720 --> 01:20:38.039
It was a deep, cold, icy anger that she

01:20:38.039 --> 01:20:40.680
held on to for the rest of her life, and

01:20:40.680 --> 01:20:42.479
only friends like Sundew knew it was

01:20:42.479 --> 01:20:42.659
there.

01:20:42.720 --> 01:20:46.319
Sundew had once seen her slip a deadly

01:20:46.319 --> 01:20:48.539
mantineal fruit into another dragon's

01:20:48.539 --> 01:20:50.880
lunch as payback for insulting her sister

01:20:50.880 --> 01:20:52.079
2 years earlier.

01:20:52.140 --> 01:20:55.380
He'd survived, but only barely.

01:20:55.439 --> 01:20:58.199
Cobra Lily was kind of awesome.

01:20:58.260 --> 01:21:00.600
Hello, beautiful.

01:21:00.659 --> 01:21:03.960
Cobra Lily said languidly, as they came

01:21:03.960 --> 01:21:04.199
up.

01:21:04.260 --> 01:21:06.659
You've got a little monster on your

01:21:06.659 --> 01:21:06.960
neck.

01:21:07.020 --> 01:21:10.979
You have no idea, Sundu agreed.

01:21:11.039 --> 01:21:12.239
How's the village?

01:21:12.300 --> 01:21:13.260
Did I miss anything?

01:21:13.319 --> 01:21:15.840
Boring without you?

01:21:15.899 --> 01:21:19.920
Cobra Lily leaned down to nudge sundew

01:21:19.920 --> 01:21:20.640
with her snout.

01:21:20.699 --> 01:21:23.039
You were gone forever.

01:21:23.100 --> 01:21:26.159
I nearly murdered Nettle just to make

01:21:26.159 --> 01:21:27.539
something interesting happen.

01:21:27.600 --> 01:21:30.539
I can't imagine anyone objecting to

01:21:30.539 --> 01:21:30.720
that.

01:21:30.779 --> 01:21:34.260
Anyway, I know, but wait till you see

01:21:34.260 --> 01:21:34.859
what I brought back.

01:21:34.920 --> 01:21:38.520
Sundew moved Bumblebee to her back so she

01:21:38.520 --> 01:21:39.840
could sort through her pouches.

01:21:39.899 --> 01:21:44.819
Spies and slugs by the look of it, Cobra

01:21:44.819 --> 01:21:47.579
Lily guest, eyeing the other dragons over

01:21:47.579 --> 01:21:48.359
Sundew's shoulder.

01:21:48.479 --> 01:21:51.300
The book of Clearsight.

01:21:51.359 --> 01:21:54.420
Sundew said, as she hauled it out and put

01:21:54.420 --> 01:21:56.100
it in Cobra Lily's talons.

01:21:56.159 --> 01:21:59.880
And the secret of wasp's mind control, we

01:21:59.880 --> 01:22:00.180
think.

01:22:00.239 --> 01:22:03.180
She brought out the length of vine she'd

01:22:03.180 --> 01:22:05.100
cut off the plant in Wasp's greenhouse.

01:22:05.159 --> 01:22:07.260
Any idea what this is?

01:22:07.380 --> 01:22:10.859
Cobra Lily studied it for a moment. before

01:22:10.859 --> 01:22:12.239
turning her eyes back to the book.

01:22:12.300 --> 01:22:15.479
Never seen it before, she said.

01:22:15.539 --> 01:22:17.819
That was disappointing.

01:22:17.880 --> 01:22:20.699
Cobra Lily was always top of the class.

01:22:20.819 --> 01:22:23.579
Sundew had hoped she'd be able to solve

01:22:23.579 --> 01:22:26.100
the mystery quickly, but there were other

01:22:26.100 --> 01:22:27.720
leaf wings Sundew could ask.

01:22:27.779 --> 01:22:31.500
Thump went the little jade frog over her

01:22:31.500 --> 01:22:33.899
heart as she tucked the vine away again.

01:22:33.960 --> 01:22:38.460
Belladonna said this was useless, Cobra

01:22:38.460 --> 01:22:39.840
Lily flipped through the pages of the

01:22:39.840 --> 01:22:42.600
book, scanning Clearsight's prophecies.

01:22:42.659 --> 01:22:46.739
It's not, no way, Cricket burst out

01:22:46.739 --> 01:22:49.020
because now we know the truth.

01:22:49.079 --> 01:22:51.180
Did she tell you what's in there and how

01:22:51.180 --> 01:22:52.859
it changes everything?

01:22:52.920 --> 01:22:55.680
Cobra Lily leveled her cool gaze on

01:22:55.680 --> 01:22:56.100
cricket.

01:22:56.159 --> 01:22:59.100
Why is your prisoner talking to me?

01:22:59.159 --> 01:23:01.260
She asked Sundu.

01:23:01.319 --> 01:23:03.060
She's not my prisoner.

01:23:03.119 --> 01:23:07.260
She's, I don't know, an ally, I guess, and

01:23:07.260 --> 01:23:07.739
she's right.

01:23:07.800 --> 01:23:11.039
I mean, we nearly got killed stealing it

01:23:11.039 --> 01:23:12.539
so it better not be useless.

01:23:12.600 --> 01:23:15.119
I can't believe Belladon has said that.

01:23:15.180 --> 01:23:17.760
Sundu growled softly.

01:23:17.819 --> 01:23:21.000
Was Belladonna trying to downplay Sundu's

01:23:21.000 --> 01:23:21.720
successful mission?

01:23:21.779 --> 01:23:24.300
Cobra Lily handed back the book.

01:23:24.359 --> 01:23:25.739
Cool.

01:23:25.800 --> 01:23:28.319
Good luck explaining them to everyone

01:23:28.319 --> 01:23:28.619
else.

01:23:28.680 --> 01:23:32.699
A moment later, they were inside, or at

01:23:32.699 --> 01:23:35.220
least into the detoxification chamber.

01:23:35.279 --> 01:23:37.920
Cricket looked around in puzzlement at

01:23:37.920 --> 01:23:39.359
the tightly woven branches that

01:23:39.359 --> 01:23:39.960
surrounded them.

01:23:40.020 --> 01:23:42.779
The space where they stood was barely big

01:23:42.779 --> 01:23:45.720
enough to fit 4 dragons, and one tiny

01:23:45.720 --> 01:23:47.760
dragonette, squeezed in together.

01:23:47.819 --> 01:23:51.000
It was meant for three, but of course

01:23:51.000 --> 01:23:52.739
SwordTail squashed himself in as well.

01:23:52.800 --> 01:23:55.920
Mandrake, on the other talon, was

01:23:55.920 --> 01:23:57.960
politely waiting outside for his turn.

01:23:58.140 --> 01:24:01.859
Get off my tail, Sundu said.

01:24:01.920 --> 01:24:03.420
Shoving sword tail away.

01:24:03.479 --> 01:24:05.819
Bumblebee, close your eyes.

01:24:05.880 --> 01:24:07.920
The dragonette tilted her head

01:24:07.920 --> 01:24:10.199
quizzically, and send Drew reached out to

01:24:10.199 --> 01:24:11.939
cover the little high wings face with one

01:24:11.939 --> 01:24:12.539
of her talons.

01:24:12.600 --> 01:24:19.560
Why are we all, Blue shrieked, as a

01:24:19.560 --> 01:24:21.300
cascade of water poured over them.

01:24:21.359 --> 01:24:24.420
Cricket threw her wings over her head, and

01:24:24.420 --> 01:24:27.119
Soritel blundered back onto Sunday's tail

01:24:27.119 --> 01:24:28.859
so she had to push him off again.

01:24:28.920 --> 01:24:32.039
As quickly as it had come, the water was

01:24:32.039 --> 01:24:34.079
gone. sluicing away through a channel

01:24:34.079 --> 01:24:35.640
that led outside the barrier.

01:24:35.699 --> 01:24:38.880
That's to wash away any seeds that might

01:24:38.880 --> 01:24:40.140
have been trying to sneak in.

01:24:40.260 --> 01:24:41.819
Sundew explained.

01:24:41.939 --> 01:24:44.399
She pointed at the clusters of thorn

01:24:44.399 --> 01:24:47.520
balls and tiny winged seed pods that were

01:24:47.520 --> 01:24:49.140
spinning away on the surface of the dirty

01:24:49.140 --> 01:24:49.500
water.

01:24:49.560 --> 01:24:52.920
The poison jungle is always trying to get

01:24:52.920 --> 01:24:56.100
through, and it has many tricks, but so

01:24:56.100 --> 01:24:56.460
do we.

01:24:56.520 --> 01:24:59.939
But you feel stupid now, seeds, she

01:24:59.939 --> 01:25:00.600
shouted at them.

01:25:00.659 --> 01:25:04.439
The seeds feel stupid.

01:25:04.500 --> 01:25:06.300
Blue asked, blinking.

01:25:06.359 --> 01:25:09.720
Well, they should, Sundew said.

01:25:09.779 --> 01:25:12.659
I've told them a 1000000 times to stay

01:25:12.659 --> 01:25:15.300
out of here, but it's the one order they

01:25:15.300 --> 01:25:16.560
can't seem to get through their thick

01:25:16.560 --> 01:25:16.979
heads.

01:25:17.039 --> 01:25:19.979
Pods, bark, arr.

01:25:20.039 --> 01:25:21.960
There isn't a dragon speak word for it.

01:25:22.020 --> 01:25:25.560
Maybe the instinct to spread is too

01:25:25.560 --> 01:25:27.720
strong, Cricket said thoughtfully.

01:25:27.779 --> 01:25:31.020
It's survival to them, sticking to

01:25:31.020 --> 01:25:32.579
whatever will carry them the farthest

01:25:32.579 --> 01:25:34.920
trying to plant themselves wherever they

01:25:34.920 --> 01:25:35.159
can.

01:25:35.220 --> 01:25:38.819
I mean, is it disobedience if they can't

01:25:38.819 --> 01:25:39.119
help it?

01:25:39.180 --> 01:25:42.000
How would a plant teach its seeds to fall

01:25:42.000 --> 01:25:43.680
off our feet before we enter the

01:25:43.680 --> 01:25:44.039
village?

01:25:44.100 --> 01:25:46.920
That would be so amazing if it could

01:25:46.920 --> 01:25:47.100
though.

01:25:47.159 --> 01:25:49.500
Some kind of warning system maybe?

01:25:49.560 --> 01:25:51.359
But it would have to know that going

01:25:51.359 --> 01:25:52.979
inside the village would kill it

01:25:52.979 --> 01:25:53.640
somehow.

01:25:53.699 --> 01:25:57.720
She trailed off, as Sundu pushed open the

01:25:57.720 --> 01:25:59.640
chamber door, and they all stepped

01:25:59.640 --> 01:26:01.560
through into the murky green light under

01:26:01.560 --> 01:26:01.979
the dome.

01:26:02.100 --> 01:26:06.359
This was the village, Sundew's home.

01:26:06.420 --> 01:26:09.359
The safest place in the poison jungle.

01:26:09.479 --> 01:26:12.359
A circle cleared of all the deadliest

01:26:12.359 --> 01:26:15.180
plants, so that leaf wing dragonettes had

01:26:15.180 --> 01:26:17.159
half a chance of surviving to adulthood.

01:26:17.220 --> 01:26:20.399
Instead of menacing Strangler vines

01:26:20.399 --> 01:26:23.640
dragon traps, or deadly sandbox trees

01:26:23.640 --> 01:26:24.600
looming overhead.

01:26:24.659 --> 01:26:27.359
There was open air all the way to the

01:26:27.359 --> 01:26:30.180
roof of the dome, as high above them as

01:26:30.180 --> 01:26:31.199
the tree canopy.

01:26:31.260 --> 01:26:34.800
It was high enough for dragons to fly, and

01:26:34.800 --> 01:26:37.439
for dragonettes to learn to fly, without

01:26:37.439 --> 01:26:39.239
the danger of anything snaring their

01:26:39.239 --> 01:26:41.520
wings, or dripping poison on their

01:26:41.520 --> 01:26:41.880
scales.

01:26:41.939 --> 01:26:45.779
Sundew was kind of unreasonably proud of

01:26:45.779 --> 01:26:46.319
this feature.

01:26:46.380 --> 01:26:49.800
Belladonna had started the walls, but

01:26:49.800 --> 01:26:51.479
she'd never managed to complete the

01:26:51.479 --> 01:26:54.420
overhead enclosure on her own, so it had

01:26:54.420 --> 01:26:56.699
only become truly safe in here once

01:26:56.699 --> 01:26:57.960
sundew came along.

01:26:58.020 --> 01:27:00.899
Fatalities, especially among the

01:27:00.899 --> 01:27:03.239
Dragonettes, had dropped significantly.

01:27:03.300 --> 01:27:06.479
But of course, we can't talk about that.

01:27:06.539 --> 01:27:10.380
We can't take a moment to say, hey, things

01:27:10.380 --> 01:27:11.520
are a little better, aren't they?

01:27:11.640 --> 01:27:15.060
We can only talk about the hive wings, and

01:27:15.060 --> 01:27:17.460
our fury, and all the things we're going

01:27:17.460 --> 01:27:18.060
to do to them.

01:27:18.180 --> 01:27:21.060
No time to pat you on the head or say

01:27:21.060 --> 01:27:22.739
thank you, Sundo.

01:27:22.800 --> 01:27:25.020
She took a deep breath.

01:27:25.079 --> 01:27:27.960
Stepping into the village always made her

01:27:27.960 --> 01:27:30.899
heart beat faster. and her ears lie flat

01:27:30.899 --> 01:27:33.239
as though she was preparing for battle.

01:27:33.300 --> 01:27:34.800
It should have been the other way

01:27:34.800 --> 01:27:35.100
around.

01:27:35.159 --> 01:27:37.739
It should have been the jungle that set

01:27:37.739 --> 01:27:40.680
off her danger sensors, but in here

01:27:40.680 --> 01:27:43.680
Sundew knew that her mother was always a

01:27:43.680 --> 01:27:46.079
few steps away, that they were always

01:27:46.079 --> 01:27:47.819
only moments from a fight.

01:27:47.880 --> 01:27:50.220
Sundew.

01:27:50.279 --> 01:27:52.680
Case in point.

01:27:52.739 --> 01:27:55.619
Belladonna came thundering out of the

01:27:55.619 --> 01:27:57.960
meeting house, her wings billowing like

01:27:57.960 --> 01:27:58.920
storm clouds.

01:27:58.979 --> 01:28:01.680
She flew down the steps and landed with

01:28:01.680 --> 01:28:04.020
one claw already in sundew's face.

01:28:04.079 --> 01:28:07.319
How dare you bring enemies into our

01:28:07.319 --> 01:28:07.800
village?

01:28:07.920 --> 01:28:10.380
I told her to wait outside.

01:28:10.439 --> 01:28:13.380
Wolvesbang cried, aggrieved.

01:28:13.439 --> 01:28:16.260
Hey, I told you to wait outside.

01:28:16.319 --> 01:28:19.800
Yeah, not share where you got the idea

01:28:19.800 --> 01:28:21.539
that you can tell me to do anything.

01:28:21.600 --> 01:28:23.640
Sundew said to him.

01:28:23.699 --> 01:28:26.340
She batted her mother's claw aside.

01:28:26.399 --> 01:28:29.819
And you might remember, mother, that

01:28:29.819 --> 01:28:31.560
working with these dragons was your idea

01:28:31.560 --> 01:28:32.399
in the 1st place.

01:28:32.520 --> 01:28:37.199
Out there, Belladonna yelled, pointing

01:28:37.199 --> 01:28:39.840
vaguely out of the jungle, not in here.

01:28:39.899 --> 01:28:43.020
What is that on your neck?

01:28:43.079 --> 01:28:46.680
This is Bumblebee.

01:28:46.739 --> 01:28:48.180
Sundew said.

01:28:48.239 --> 01:28:50.279
She had to admit, she was kind of

01:28:50.279 --> 01:28:52.199
enjoying how much she'd thrown her mother

01:28:52.199 --> 01:28:52.800
for a loop.

01:28:52.859 --> 01:28:54.600
Isn't she cute?

01:28:54.720 --> 01:28:57.420
Me, mommy.

01:28:57.479 --> 01:29:00.359
The dragonette said, curling her tail

01:29:00.359 --> 01:29:02.460
around sundew's neck and edging a little

01:29:02.460 --> 01:29:02.819
closer.

01:29:02.880 --> 01:29:05.939
Other leaf wings were gathering

01:29:05.939 --> 01:29:09.239
whispering, arguing in hushed tones all

01:29:09.239 --> 01:29:09.600
around them.

01:29:09.659 --> 01:29:12.720
One of them pointed at cricket, and there

01:29:12.720 --> 01:29:14.760
was a ripple of scowls across all the

01:29:14.760 --> 01:29:15.840
green and brown faces.

01:29:15.960 --> 01:29:21.119
These are our allies, Sun to announce, in

01:29:21.119 --> 01:29:21.840
a raised voice.

01:29:21.840 --> 01:29:25.140
Anyone who hurts a scale on their bodies

01:29:25.140 --> 01:29:27.899
will find his or her eyeballs on the

01:29:27.899 --> 01:29:29.939
wrong end of a bombardier beetle.

01:29:30.000 --> 01:29:32.340
She turned back to Belladonna.

01:29:32.399 --> 01:29:36.180
Cricket, as you know, is immune to wasps

01:29:36.180 --> 01:29:39.000
mind control, and blue is a flame silk.

01:29:39.060 --> 01:29:41.880
They helped us get the book of Clearsight

01:29:41.880 --> 01:29:45.119
as you requested, and now they need a

01:29:45.119 --> 01:29:46.439
place to hide from WASP.

01:29:46.500 --> 01:29:49.140
Seems like the least we could do, right?

01:29:49.199 --> 01:29:52.859
A flame silk, one of the leaf wings

01:29:52.859 --> 01:29:53.399
called.

01:29:53.399 --> 01:29:56.100
Prove it. called another.

01:29:56.159 --> 01:29:59.399
Sundew grabbed Blue's wrist to stop him

01:29:59.399 --> 01:30:01.979
but he'd remembered her lecture and was

01:30:01.979 --> 01:30:03.060
already shaking his head.

01:30:03.119 --> 01:30:06.600
Not in here, you bees for brains.

01:30:06.659 --> 01:30:09.119
She spat at the offending leaf wing.

01:30:09.180 --> 01:30:13.079
He doesn't have to prove it, Belladonna

01:30:13.079 --> 01:30:13.920
said regally.

01:30:13.979 --> 01:30:15.359
We know what he is.

01:30:15.479 --> 01:30:18.479
It was his flame silk we use to burn down

01:30:18.479 --> 01:30:19.619
bloodworm hive.

01:30:19.680 --> 01:30:23.520
Blue gasped. and pulled away from sundew

01:30:23.520 --> 01:30:28.020
as the dragons around them went, Oh, in

01:30:28.020 --> 01:30:29.939
hushed, pleased tones.

01:30:30.000 --> 01:30:31.979
Wait, what?

01:30:32.100 --> 01:30:35.880
Cricket said, blues, flame, silk, but

01:30:35.880 --> 01:30:37.500
how?

01:30:37.560 --> 01:30:39.000
They didn't know.

01:30:39.060 --> 01:30:40.979
They never put it together.

01:30:41.039 --> 01:30:43.800
It hadn't occurred to Sundew that this

01:30:43.800 --> 01:30:45.180
would be a surprise to them.

01:30:45.239 --> 01:30:48.539
Maybe an unforgivable surprise.

01:30:48.600 --> 01:30:50.520
Judging by the looks on their faces.

01:30:50.579 --> 01:30:52.859
Is that true?

01:30:52.979 --> 01:30:54.000
Blue asked.

01:30:54.060 --> 01:30:56.760
Send you, Cricket said.

01:30:56.819 --> 01:30:59.159
How did your parents get their claws on

01:30:59.159 --> 01:31:00.539
Blue's flame silk?

01:31:00.600 --> 01:31:04.500
Chapter 5.

01:31:04.800 --> 01:31:07.319
I gave it to them.

01:31:07.380 --> 01:31:09.239
Sundu said defiantly.

01:31:09.300 --> 01:31:10.680
Of course I did.

01:31:10.739 --> 01:31:11.699
So what?

01:31:11.760 --> 01:31:14.579
Blue sat down and clutched his head.

01:31:14.699 --> 01:31:16.439
When?

01:31:16.439 --> 01:31:17.279
he cried.

01:31:17.340 --> 01:31:19.380
How did you even have any?

01:31:19.439 --> 01:31:22.920
I gathered some when you 1st came out of

01:31:22.920 --> 01:31:24.779
your cocoon, Sundu said.

01:31:24.899 --> 01:31:26.039
Don't you remember?

01:31:26.100 --> 01:31:27.960
I put it in a stone jar.

01:31:28.020 --> 01:31:29.939
I wasn't sneaky about it.

01:31:30.000 --> 01:31:33.779
But you were with us from then until we

01:31:33.779 --> 01:31:36.239
escaped Jewel Hive, Cricket said.

01:31:36.300 --> 01:31:37.319
Weren't you?

01:31:37.380 --> 01:31:39.600
I thought you didn't see your parents in

01:31:39.600 --> 01:31:40.199
all that time.

01:31:40.319 --> 01:31:44.100
I saw them the night after I got Blue's

01:31:44.100 --> 01:31:46.020
Flame Silk, Sundu said.

01:31:46.079 --> 01:31:48.659
While you were all asleep in the carpet

01:31:48.659 --> 01:31:51.359
stall outside the glitter bazaar, I got

01:31:51.359 --> 01:31:52.979
up early and met them to give them my

01:31:52.979 --> 01:31:55.859
report, and the flame silk as they had

01:31:55.859 --> 01:31:56.340
requested.

01:31:56.399 --> 01:31:59.579
And to ask for more time, as you

01:31:59.579 --> 01:32:02.399
requested, which they said no to again

01:32:02.399 --> 01:32:04.560
and then came back and rejoined you

01:32:04.560 --> 01:32:05.399
before you woke up.

01:32:05.399 --> 01:32:07.979
Why didn't you tell us?

01:32:08.039 --> 01:32:09.659
Swartell demanded.

01:32:09.720 --> 01:32:13.619
I don't report to you, Sundew pointed

01:32:13.619 --> 01:32:13.859
out.

01:32:13.920 --> 01:32:16.260
Belladonna was my mission commander.

01:32:16.319 --> 01:32:19.439
Not that you follow my orders very well

01:32:19.439 --> 01:32:19.800
either.

01:32:19.859 --> 01:32:21.960
Belladon observed.

01:32:22.020 --> 01:32:24.600
I can't believe this.

01:32:24.720 --> 01:32:26.340
Cricket said to Sundo.

01:32:26.460 --> 01:32:30.119
I keep thinking you, but then I keep

01:32:30.119 --> 01:32:30.720
being wrong.

01:32:30.779 --> 01:32:34.800
Their expressions gave Sundew a squiggly

01:32:34.800 --> 01:32:37.199
feeling that she wanted to stab and stab

01:32:37.199 --> 01:32:38.880
and stab until it was dead.

01:32:38.939 --> 01:32:42.000
How can you possibly be surprised?

01:32:42.060 --> 01:32:43.020
she asked.

01:32:43.079 --> 01:32:46.079
Where did you think they got the fire to

01:32:46.079 --> 01:32:47.880
burn down bloodworm hive?

01:32:47.939 --> 01:32:50.760
I didn't think it was from me.

01:32:50.819 --> 01:32:52.319
Blue said.

01:32:52.380 --> 01:32:54.960
He buried his face in his talons.

01:32:55.020 --> 01:32:58.079
Cricket sat down next to him and spread

01:32:58.079 --> 01:32:59.579
one of her wings over him.

01:32:59.640 --> 01:33:01.979
You took such a little bit.

01:33:02.039 --> 01:33:05.399
You only need a little bit of flame silk

01:33:05.399 --> 01:33:06.960
if you have the right materials.

01:33:07.020 --> 01:33:10.140
Belladonna said briskly, although, of

01:33:10.140 --> 01:33:12.659
course, more is better, which is why

01:33:12.659 --> 01:33:14.520
you're going to be so useful for the rest

01:33:14.520 --> 01:33:15.060
of the war.

01:33:15.180 --> 01:33:16.859
Blue shuddered.

01:33:16.920 --> 01:33:18.539
No way.

01:33:18.659 --> 01:33:19.800
He said.

01:33:19.859 --> 01:33:22.020
I don't want to be useful for killing

01:33:22.020 --> 01:33:22.619
anyone.

01:33:22.680 --> 01:33:25.979
Billadonna's look was almost pitying.

01:33:26.100 --> 01:33:29.579
Sundew could almost see a dragon in there

01:33:29.579 --> 01:33:31.380
who felt guilty about what she wanted to

01:33:31.380 --> 01:33:34.319
do, and who maybe understood why Blue

01:33:34.319 --> 01:33:35.100
didn't want to do it.

01:33:35.159 --> 01:33:38.039
But that dragon was never going to be the

01:33:38.039 --> 01:33:39.000
one everyone else saw.

01:33:39.119 --> 01:33:43.619
You can't imagine we'd let a weapon like

01:33:43.619 --> 01:33:46.439
yours fall into our talons and not use it

01:33:46.439 --> 01:33:48.420
Sundu's mother said.

01:33:48.479 --> 01:33:50.939
Try to think of what we're doing as

01:33:50.939 --> 01:33:54.659
freeing your tribe, rather than killing

01:33:54.659 --> 01:33:55.140
the other one.

01:33:55.199 --> 01:33:56.640
Does that help?

01:33:56.699 --> 01:33:59.640
No, Blue cried.

01:33:59.760 --> 01:34:03.479
If you want his cooperation, Sandu

01:34:03.479 --> 01:34:04.079
interjected.

01:34:04.140 --> 01:34:06.000
You're going to have to take care of his

01:34:06.000 --> 01:34:06.420
friends.

01:34:06.479 --> 01:34:09.600
Safe harbor for both silk wings and both

01:34:09.600 --> 01:34:12.239
hive wings, and I do mean safe.

01:34:12.239 --> 01:34:15.600
No mysterious leaves in their food, no

01:34:15.600 --> 01:34:17.100
fire ants in their beds.

01:34:17.159 --> 01:34:20.220
If you want the flame silk to help you

01:34:20.220 --> 01:34:22.079
you have to take care of them just as

01:34:22.079 --> 01:34:23.220
well as you take care of him.

01:34:23.279 --> 01:34:27.060
But Sun do, Blue started.

01:34:27.119 --> 01:34:30.060
Then yelped as Swordell trod on his

01:34:30.060 --> 01:34:30.300
foot.

01:34:30.359 --> 01:34:34.680
What she said, Swartell talked over him

01:34:34.680 --> 01:34:37.800
exactly that, especially the no fire

01:34:37.800 --> 01:34:38.460
ants.

01:34:38.520 --> 01:34:39.359
Please.

01:34:39.479 --> 01:34:42.960
Belladonna sat back on her haunches, and

01:34:42.960 --> 01:34:45.000
regarded them with narrowed eyes for a

01:34:45.000 --> 01:34:45.600
long moment.

01:34:45.720 --> 01:34:48.659
Hmm, she said.

01:34:48.720 --> 01:34:51.239
Very clever, sundew.

01:34:51.300 --> 01:34:55.079
Sundew managed by the skin of her teeth

01:34:55.079 --> 01:34:56.939
not to say, really?

01:34:57.000 --> 01:34:59.760
In an excited little dragonette voice

01:34:59.760 --> 01:35:02.460
she'd outwitted her mother.

01:35:02.520 --> 01:35:04.619
It was just like she'd said to Blue.

01:35:04.680 --> 01:35:07.319
He had to realize he had the power here

01:35:07.319 --> 01:35:09.060
and together they could use it.

01:35:09.119 --> 01:35:12.840
They just had to be smart, and maybe he

01:35:12.840 --> 01:35:14.699
wouldn't want to use his flame silk at

01:35:14.699 --> 01:35:17.159
first, but she could convince him, or

01:35:17.159 --> 01:35:19.560
figure out a way to use it that he

01:35:19.560 --> 01:35:20.699
wouldn't have a problem with.

01:35:20.819 --> 01:35:24.720
Yes, Belladonna said.

01:35:24.779 --> 01:35:27.539
Flicking her tail and shooting sundew and

01:35:27.539 --> 01:35:28.260
approving look.

01:35:28.380 --> 01:35:31.859
Bringing us hostages to leverage in case

01:35:31.859 --> 01:35:33.659
the flame silk was reluctant.

01:35:33.720 --> 01:35:36.479
Very, very clever.

01:35:36.539 --> 01:35:39.539
I knew we'd raised a smart little

01:35:39.539 --> 01:35:40.020
warrior.

01:35:40.079 --> 01:35:42.840
Sundew's jaw dropped.

01:35:42.899 --> 01:35:47.100
That wasn't, she hadn't, That was not how

01:35:47.100 --> 01:35:48.539
this was supposed to go.

01:35:48.600 --> 01:35:51.539
Cricket and bumblebee weren't leverage.

01:35:51.600 --> 01:35:54.180
There were even minutes when she liked

01:35:54.180 --> 01:35:55.199
swordtail.

01:35:55.260 --> 01:35:56.640
Every once in a while.

01:35:56.699 --> 01:35:58.739
She certainly hadn't meant to turn them

01:35:58.739 --> 01:36:00.539
over to her mother as hostages.

01:36:00.600 --> 01:36:04.260
And maybe Belladonna knew that.

01:36:04.319 --> 01:36:07.739
Maybe the betrayed look on cricket's face

01:36:07.739 --> 01:36:10.140
was exactly the reaction she'd been

01:36:10.140 --> 01:36:10.619
hoping for.

01:36:10.680 --> 01:36:13.439
Or maybe her mother really did think

01:36:13.439 --> 01:36:15.779
Sundew had tricked all these dragons into

01:36:15.779 --> 01:36:16.920
walking into her claws.

01:36:16.979 --> 01:36:21.119
Either way, Belladonna saw them as her

01:36:21.119 --> 01:36:21.840
prisoners now.

01:36:21.899 --> 01:36:25.920
Sundew's rage pulsed under her scales.

01:36:25.979 --> 01:36:28.079
She wanted to flay something.

01:36:28.140 --> 01:36:31.199
She wanted to upend all her pouches over

01:36:31.199 --> 01:36:33.720
Belladonna's head and let the insects

01:36:33.720 --> 01:36:34.680
devour her.

01:36:34.739 --> 01:36:37.739
She wanted to scream and tear down the

01:36:37.739 --> 01:36:40.079
barrier. and let the jungle come surging

01:36:40.079 --> 01:36:40.319
in.

01:36:40.439 --> 01:36:44.760
I meant what I said, she hissed.

01:36:44.819 --> 01:36:48.239
Anyone who harms these dragons will

01:36:48.239 --> 01:36:49.319
answer to me.

01:36:49.380 --> 01:36:52.439
That includes you, Belladonna.

01:36:52.500 --> 01:36:55.680
All right, dear, her mother said

01:36:55.680 --> 01:36:56.399
dismissively.

01:36:56.460 --> 01:36:59.340
Which was the worst.

01:36:59.399 --> 01:37:03.840
Sundew was going to straight up stab her

01:37:03.840 --> 01:37:05.760
just for that tone of voice.

01:37:05.819 --> 01:37:07.319
Never mind everything else.

01:37:07.380 --> 01:37:11.220
Belladonna turned and waved one talon at

01:37:11.220 --> 01:37:11.939
Wolfsbane.

01:37:12.000 --> 01:37:15.239
Let's put them all in poke weed's nest.

01:37:15.300 --> 01:37:17.460
He'll be hiding out with hemlock for who

01:37:17.460 --> 01:37:17.939
knows how long.

01:37:18.060 --> 01:37:21.960
We'll take Bryonies too, Sundoo said.

01:37:22.020 --> 01:37:24.539
She knew which nests were free.

01:37:24.600 --> 01:37:27.239
She knew which dragons had been sent to

01:37:27.239 --> 01:37:28.079
burn the hive.

01:37:28.140 --> 01:37:30.420
And she wasn't going to let Belladonna

01:37:30.420 --> 01:37:32.760
pen up Cricket and the others in one tiny

01:37:32.760 --> 01:37:33.119
place.

01:37:33.180 --> 01:37:36.720
It didn't have to feel like prison, even

01:37:36.720 --> 01:37:37.619
if it kind of was.

01:37:37.680 --> 01:37:41.279
Even if this whole place feels like a

01:37:41.279 --> 01:37:42.300
prison to me sometimes.

01:37:42.359 --> 01:37:45.899
From the moment she'd stepped back into

01:37:45.899 --> 01:37:48.479
the village, Sundew's claws had been

01:37:48.479 --> 01:37:48.899
twitching.

01:37:48.960 --> 01:37:51.720
She was so close to where she really

01:37:51.720 --> 01:37:52.439
wanted to be.

01:37:52.500 --> 01:37:56.279
She'd been gone for so long, and she'd

01:37:56.279 --> 01:37:58.260
managed to focus on the mission for all

01:37:58.260 --> 01:37:59.100
that time.

01:37:59.159 --> 01:38:02.939
But now, all she wanted to do was blast a

01:38:02.939 --> 01:38:04.800
hole in the barrier and run to her

01:38:04.800 --> 01:38:05.220
dragon.

01:38:05.340 --> 01:38:09.060
She touched the pout with a jade frog in

01:38:09.060 --> 01:38:09.239
it.

01:38:09.300 --> 01:38:11.159
Not much longer.

01:38:11.220 --> 01:38:14.460
Don't make a stupid mistake now, with

01:38:14.460 --> 01:38:14.939
everyone watching.

01:38:15.000 --> 01:38:18.779
Get them settled and come report to me.

01:38:18.899 --> 01:38:21.060
Belladonna said to send you.

01:38:21.119 --> 01:38:24.899
I particularly want a full explanation of

01:38:24.899 --> 01:38:26.340
that. thing.

01:38:26.460 --> 01:38:29.159
She flicked one claw at Bumblebee.

01:38:29.279 --> 01:38:33.600
We'll get the feast ready, Wolfsbane said

01:38:33.600 --> 01:38:35.760
hurrying to where mandrake had dropped

01:38:35.760 --> 01:38:36.539
the panther.

01:38:36.600 --> 01:38:39.420
Bumblebee grabbed Sundew's ear and

01:38:39.420 --> 01:38:42.960
whispered, he into it.

01:38:43.079 --> 01:38:45.600
Yes, come on.

01:38:45.659 --> 01:38:46.739
We'll find you something.

01:38:46.859 --> 01:38:49.619
Sundew turned toward the food stores.

01:38:49.680 --> 01:38:53.579
Wait, Swordell said, jumping forward.

01:38:53.640 --> 01:38:56.460
Sundu, ask about Luna.

01:38:56.520 --> 01:39:00.060
Sundew was pretty sure her tribe hadn't

01:39:00.060 --> 01:39:00.840
found Luna.

01:39:00.899 --> 01:39:03.960
If they had captured another more willing

01:39:03.960 --> 01:39:05.939
flame silk already, They wouldn't be

01:39:05.939 --> 01:39:07.140
reacting this way to blue.

01:39:07.199 --> 01:39:09.300
But she had promised to ask.

01:39:09.359 --> 01:39:12.239
She lifted her chin and looked up into

01:39:12.239 --> 01:39:13.739
her mother's sharp green eyes.

01:39:13.800 --> 01:39:17.039
Has anyone seen another silk wing?

01:39:17.100 --> 01:39:19.319
She was blown out to sea several days

01:39:19.319 --> 01:39:19.739
ago?

01:39:19.800 --> 01:39:22.260
We wondered if she came ashore in the

01:39:22.260 --> 01:39:22.619
jungle?

01:39:22.680 --> 01:39:25.800
Belladonna turned to look at one of her

01:39:25.800 --> 01:39:27.659
lieutenants, who shook her head.

01:39:27.720 --> 01:39:30.479
Those are the 1st silk wings I've ever

01:39:30.479 --> 01:39:30.720
seen.

01:39:30.779 --> 01:39:34.079
Biblus said, pointing at blue and sword

01:39:34.079 --> 01:39:36.479
tail, we haven't run into any strange

01:39:36.479 --> 01:39:37.979
dragons in our territory.

01:39:38.100 --> 01:39:40.560
She started to say something else

01:39:40.560 --> 01:39:43.260
hesitated, and then shook her head

01:39:43.260 --> 01:39:43.560
again.

01:39:43.619 --> 01:39:47.819
No, we haven't brought anyone unusual

01:39:47.819 --> 01:39:48.899
into our village.

01:39:48.960 --> 01:39:52.560
There was a very slight, barely

01:39:52.560 --> 01:39:54.899
perceptible emphasis on our.

01:39:55.020 --> 01:39:58.140
Sundu heard it, and she knew what that

01:39:58.140 --> 01:40:00.119
meant, and that the smart thing to do

01:40:00.119 --> 01:40:02.159
would be to wait and get answers her own

01:40:02.159 --> 01:40:02.640
way later.

01:40:02.699 --> 01:40:06.359
But unfortunately, cricket heard it too

01:40:06.359 --> 01:40:07.920
and she pounced.

01:40:08.039 --> 01:40:10.680
Did you say our village?

01:40:10.739 --> 01:40:12.119
What does that mean?

01:40:12.180 --> 01:40:13.500
She asked.

01:40:13.560 --> 01:40:14.640
What were you going to say?

01:40:14.699 --> 01:40:18.840
Biblus shifted on her talons, stirring

01:40:18.840 --> 01:40:22.199
the leaf mulch under her claws, Nothing

01:40:22.199 --> 01:40:23.100
she said.

01:40:23.220 --> 01:40:27.300
No confirmed reports, only rumors.

01:40:27.359 --> 01:40:30.359
I don't bring every silly rumor back to

01:40:30.359 --> 01:40:31.079
our commander.

01:40:31.140 --> 01:40:33.960
She bowed her head toward Belladonna.

01:40:34.020 --> 01:40:35.640
Rumors of what?

01:40:35.699 --> 01:40:38.640
Soratell nudged Sundee's side.

01:40:38.699 --> 01:40:40.800
Make them tell us, Sundu.

01:40:40.859 --> 01:40:43.859
I must admit, I'm curious as well.

01:40:43.920 --> 01:40:46.260
Belladonna said archly.

01:40:46.319 --> 01:40:49.260
I give you permission to share, Biblus.

01:40:49.319 --> 01:40:52.140
Well, all right.

01:40:52.260 --> 01:40:54.659
The other leaf wing looked very

01:40:54.659 --> 01:40:55.560
uncomfortable.

01:40:55.619 --> 01:40:58.500
Biblus was one of Belladonna's most loyal

01:40:58.500 --> 01:40:59.159
dragons.

01:40:59.220 --> 01:41:02.279
She was in Sundew's earliest memories

01:41:02.279 --> 01:41:04.859
following her mother's orders, watching

01:41:04.859 --> 01:41:07.560
over Sundew, making sure all the rules

01:41:07.560 --> 01:41:08.159
were followed.

01:41:08.220 --> 01:41:11.100
Biblus needed rules.

01:41:11.159 --> 01:41:12.600
She liked everything to fit into

01:41:12.600 --> 01:41:13.199
squares.

01:41:13.260 --> 01:41:16.020
She never set foot outside the barrier

01:41:16.020 --> 01:41:18.779
unless she was on a specific mission, and

01:41:18.779 --> 01:41:19.619
then she came right back.

01:41:19.680 --> 01:41:23.279
Sharing an unsubstantiated rumor without

01:41:23.279 --> 01:41:25.739
evidence to back it up, must have felt

01:41:25.739 --> 01:41:27.600
like rubbing nettles on her palms to

01:41:27.600 --> 01:41:27.840
her.

01:41:27.899 --> 01:41:31.859
A few of the guards on patrol mentioned

01:41:31.859 --> 01:41:36.539
that there was increased activity over

01:41:36.539 --> 01:41:36.899
there.

01:41:36.960 --> 01:41:38.340
She said.

01:41:38.399 --> 01:41:41.579
More noise, voices raised.

01:41:41.699 --> 01:41:43.380
Agitated trees.

01:41:43.439 --> 01:41:46.560
The ones with leaf speak said there was a

01:41:46.560 --> 01:41:47.579
whisper of something new.

01:41:47.640 --> 01:41:50.100
But you know how plans can be.

01:41:50.220 --> 01:41:52.619
They often don't know what they don't

01:41:52.619 --> 01:41:53.340
know.

01:41:53.399 --> 01:41:56.220
We believe we noted slightly more prey

01:41:56.220 --> 01:41:56.880
being caught.

01:41:56.939 --> 01:41:58.859
Nothing definite, mind you.

01:41:58.920 --> 01:42:03.180
But potentially consistent with the

01:42:03.180 --> 01:42:05.579
possibility of one or more strange

01:42:05.579 --> 01:42:08.699
dragons perhaps having arrived.

01:42:08.760 --> 01:42:09.840
There.

01:42:09.899 --> 01:42:11.880
Where?

01:42:11.939 --> 01:42:13.380
Thordell cried.

01:42:13.439 --> 01:42:14.460
What are you talking about?

01:42:14.520 --> 01:42:17.939
Are you saying there's another village in

01:42:17.939 --> 01:42:18.479
the jungle?

01:42:18.539 --> 01:42:21.359
Cricket said, glancing at sundew.

01:42:21.420 --> 01:42:23.039
Who lives there?

01:42:23.100 --> 01:42:24.659
More leaf wings?

01:42:24.720 --> 01:42:26.819
Billadonna snorted.

01:42:26.880 --> 01:42:29.760
They don't deserve to be called leaf

01:42:29.760 --> 01:42:30.239
wings.

01:42:30.359 --> 01:42:32.699
We are the leaf wings.

01:42:32.760 --> 01:42:34.739
We're the ones who are still fighting for

01:42:34.739 --> 01:42:35.460
our future.

01:42:35.579 --> 01:42:37.920
We're not giving up on our tribe and

01:42:37.920 --> 01:42:41.039
rolling over like pill bugs, leaf wings.

01:42:41.100 --> 01:42:41.939
Pah.

01:42:42.060 --> 01:42:44.699
She stabbed her claws into the ground

01:42:44.699 --> 01:42:47.460
dragged out a flailing earthworm, and

01:42:47.460 --> 01:42:48.479
sliced it into pieces.

01:42:48.539 --> 01:42:52.739
Mother has a bit of a complex about the

01:42:52.739 --> 01:42:53.460
other tribe.

01:42:53.520 --> 01:42:55.140
Sundu explained.

01:42:55.199 --> 01:42:58.500
We call them sap wings.

01:42:58.560 --> 01:43:01.920
Biblis added, by order of the commander.

01:43:01.979 --> 01:43:06.539
My order was to never speak of them.

01:43:06.600 --> 01:43:08.699
Belladonna hissed.

01:43:08.819 --> 01:43:12.180
They might as well not exist for all the

01:43:12.180 --> 01:43:13.020
use they are to us.

01:43:13.079 --> 01:43:16.500
She scrabbled up the dirt and reburied

01:43:16.500 --> 01:43:18.180
the carved up earthworm bits.

01:43:18.239 --> 01:43:22.500
But Luna might be there, Swartel asked.

01:43:22.560 --> 01:43:23.699
We should go ask.

01:43:23.760 --> 01:43:25.079
Sundu.

01:43:25.140 --> 01:43:25.800
Can we go ask?

01:43:25.859 --> 01:43:28.859
No one is going anywhere.

01:43:28.920 --> 01:43:31.020
Belladonna commanded.

01:43:31.079 --> 01:43:33.060
Sundew frowned at her.

01:43:33.119 --> 01:43:35.220
And perhaps something in her look got

01:43:35.220 --> 01:43:35.520
through.

01:43:35.579 --> 01:43:40.859
Tonight, I mean, Belladonna added, a

01:43:40.859 --> 01:43:41.579
little reluctantly.

01:43:41.640 --> 01:43:44.880
It's too dark for anyone to wander around

01:43:44.880 --> 01:43:47.340
in the jungle, especially brainless

01:43:47.340 --> 01:43:49.199
outsiders who can't wait to get eaten.

01:43:49.260 --> 01:43:52.800
I will consider sending them a message in

01:43:52.800 --> 01:43:56.579
the morning if everyone behaves.

01:43:56.640 --> 01:43:58.739
For some reason.

01:43:58.800 --> 01:44:00.359
She looked at sundew.

01:44:00.420 --> 01:44:02.699
Sundew gave her a matching glare.

01:44:02.819 --> 01:44:07.140
Moon is a flame silk too, Sortell said

01:44:07.140 --> 01:44:07.619
quickly.

01:44:07.680 --> 01:44:09.840
She's way more likely to help you than

01:44:09.840 --> 01:44:10.439
Blue is.

01:44:10.500 --> 01:44:12.720
If the sab wings have her, you should

01:44:12.720 --> 01:44:14.039
definitely try to get her back here.

01:44:14.159 --> 01:44:16.979
Belladonna rubbed her chin.

01:44:17.039 --> 01:44:19.319
Hmm, she said.

01:44:19.439 --> 01:44:22.800
An interesting point, butterfly dragon.

01:44:22.859 --> 01:44:24.300
I will include that in my

01:44:24.300 --> 01:44:25.020
considerations.

01:44:25.079 --> 01:44:27.659
She turned to go back into the meeting

01:44:27.659 --> 01:44:30.779
house in a definitive this conversation

01:44:30.779 --> 01:44:31.920
is over kind of way.

01:44:32.039 --> 01:44:35.939
As soon as she was gone, Bumblebee tugged

01:44:35.939 --> 01:44:40.500
on Sundu's ear again. she said

01:44:40.500 --> 01:44:41.159
vehemently.

01:44:41.220 --> 01:44:44.460
The food nets were full to overflowing

01:44:44.460 --> 01:44:46.920
most likely in preparation for the feast

01:44:46.920 --> 01:44:50.279
Sundew walked bumblebee over to them, and

01:44:50.279 --> 01:44:51.539
let her pick out a mango.

01:44:51.659 --> 01:44:54.960
Then a piece of dried capybara, then a

01:44:54.960 --> 01:44:57.479
bowl of river snails, which bumblebee

01:44:57.479 --> 01:44:59.460
took one bite of and promptly flung its

01:44:59.460 --> 01:45:00.300
sundew's face.

01:45:00.359 --> 01:45:03.300
And then another mango, and then she had

01:45:03.300 --> 01:45:05.220
to wrestle the dragonette away from the

01:45:05.220 --> 01:45:06.840
food and drag her back to the others.

01:45:06.899 --> 01:45:11.399
Bumblebee growled.

01:45:11.460 --> 01:45:14.460
She flopped onto Sundu's shoulder and set

01:45:14.460 --> 01:45:16.859
her tiny teeth into a piece of capybara.

01:45:16.920 --> 01:45:20.340
Which Sundew suspected was a 2nd strip

01:45:20.340 --> 01:45:22.260
the dragonette had smuggled away

01:45:22.260 --> 01:45:22.739
somehow.

01:45:22.800 --> 01:45:26.279
Blue and Cricket and Sword Tail had

01:45:26.279 --> 01:45:28.380
fallen silent as she came up to them.

01:45:28.439 --> 01:45:30.180
They were all looking at her as if they

01:45:30.180 --> 01:45:32.520
weren't quite sure whether she was sundew

01:45:32.520 --> 01:45:34.619
the dragon who'd been helping them and

01:45:34.619 --> 01:45:36.779
protecting them and saving their butts

01:45:36.779 --> 01:45:39.359
for the last several days, or a

01:45:39.359 --> 01:45:41.340
dragonette eating crocodile instead.

01:45:41.399 --> 01:45:45.659
The nests are this way, Sundoo said

01:45:45.659 --> 01:45:47.579
stomping past them.

01:45:47.640 --> 01:45:49.199
She didn't have to explain herself.

01:45:49.260 --> 01:45:51.239
She was a leaf wing.

01:45:51.300 --> 01:45:54.239
Besides, they were her prisoners when she

01:45:54.239 --> 01:45:54.659
met them.

01:45:54.720 --> 01:45:56.880
They should be grateful that now at least

01:45:56.880 --> 01:45:58.319
they were valuable prisoners.

01:45:58.380 --> 01:46:01.800
And she'd helped with their problems too

01:46:01.800 --> 01:46:02.340
hadn't she?

01:46:02.399 --> 01:46:05.699
She'd helped save Blue's sister, even

01:46:05.699 --> 01:46:07.380
though it made Belladonna grumpy.

01:46:07.500 --> 01:46:09.659
It certainly wasn't Sundoo's fault that

01:46:09.659 --> 01:46:11.279
Blue had immediately lost her again.

01:46:11.340 --> 01:46:14.819
Sundew had also helped swordtail find the

01:46:14.819 --> 01:46:16.920
chrysalis, and she'd helped with

01:46:16.920 --> 01:46:19.380
cricket's starry eyed, let's save the

01:46:19.380 --> 01:46:22.260
tribes with truth, and flyers plan.

01:46:22.319 --> 01:46:24.659
She'd done all kinds of dangerous

01:46:24.659 --> 01:46:26.340
nonsense for these outsiders.

01:46:26.399 --> 01:46:29.340
How dare they be all aghast that she was

01:46:29.340 --> 01:46:32.220
still a leaf wing, loyal to her tribe at

01:46:32.220 --> 01:46:32.520
heart.

01:46:32.579 --> 01:46:35.220
I don't need them to like me.

01:46:35.279 --> 01:46:38.579
I don't need anyone to like me except one

01:46:38.579 --> 01:46:39.119
dragon.

01:46:39.180 --> 01:46:43.859
Here, she said, stopping at Pokweeds

01:46:43.859 --> 01:46:44.340
Nest.

01:46:44.399 --> 01:46:46.680
It was a ramshackle assortment of

01:46:46.680 --> 01:46:49.020
branches woven into a sort of egg shape.

01:46:49.079 --> 01:46:51.300
Sundew wasn't even sure if it would keep

01:46:51.300 --> 01:46:51.960
out the rain.

01:46:52.020 --> 01:46:55.319
Pokweed was a big dragon who didn't care

01:46:55.319 --> 01:46:56.880
much about his own physical comfort.

01:46:56.939 --> 01:47:00.899
He lived to destroy hive wings. was all.

01:47:00.960 --> 01:47:03.420
But at least his nest was big enough to

01:47:03.420 --> 01:47:05.159
fit 2 sleeping dragons comfortably.

01:47:05.220 --> 01:47:08.460
Blue and sore towel can take this one

01:47:08.460 --> 01:47:09.659
Sundoo said.

01:47:09.779 --> 01:47:12.060
Cricket and bumblebee in that one.

01:47:12.119 --> 01:47:15.180
She pointed to Bryony's nest, which was

01:47:15.180 --> 01:47:17.340
close by and much tidier than poke

01:47:17.340 --> 01:47:17.760
weeds.

01:47:17.819 --> 01:47:20.159
The 2 of them were near the outer edges

01:47:20.159 --> 01:47:20.640
of the village.

01:47:20.699 --> 01:47:24.060
Along a path lined with nests that led to

01:47:24.060 --> 01:47:24.600
the meeting house.

01:47:24.659 --> 01:47:26.520
What about you?

01:47:26.579 --> 01:47:27.840
Blue asked.

01:47:27.960 --> 01:47:29.579
Aren't you going to stay with us?

01:47:29.640 --> 01:47:32.039
Sunday squinted at him.

01:47:32.100 --> 01:47:35.220
Hadn't he just been giving her an oh

01:47:35.220 --> 01:47:36.180
you're a monster face?

01:47:36.300 --> 01:47:38.819
Maybe I misread it.

01:47:38.939 --> 01:47:40.560
That was cricket's expression.

01:47:40.619 --> 01:47:44.699
But maybe blues was just sad face, and I

01:47:44.699 --> 01:47:46.619
mistook it for hating me face.

01:47:46.680 --> 01:47:51.359
I have my own nest, she said, flicking

01:47:51.359 --> 01:47:53.159
her tail toward the woven sphere where

01:47:53.159 --> 01:47:54.000
she slept.

01:47:54.000 --> 01:47:56.340
She'd been so thrilled when she turned

01:47:56.340 --> 01:47:59.340
too, and Belladonna and Hemlock had given

01:47:59.340 --> 01:48:01.380
her permission to move out of theirs and

01:48:01.380 --> 01:48:02.159
build her own.

01:48:02.220 --> 01:48:04.979
It had taken her a while to notice that

01:48:04.979 --> 01:48:07.319
no other dragonettes left their families

01:48:07.319 --> 01:48:08.399
before the age of five.

01:48:08.520 --> 01:48:10.439
But she didn't dwell on that.

01:48:10.500 --> 01:48:13.619
After all, she saw plenty of her parents

01:48:13.619 --> 01:48:15.420
all day long during training and

01:48:15.420 --> 01:48:15.779
lessons.

01:48:15.840 --> 01:48:18.600
She liked the peace and quiet of being

01:48:18.600 --> 01:48:19.680
completely alone at night.

01:48:19.739 --> 01:48:22.140
I do like it.

01:48:22.199 --> 01:48:25.619
Besides, it's much easier to sneak out of

01:48:25.619 --> 01:48:26.279
the village this way.

01:48:26.399 --> 01:48:30.180
Oh, of course, Blue said.

01:48:30.239 --> 01:48:33.539
How will we remember which ones are for

01:48:33.539 --> 01:48:33.960
us?

01:48:34.020 --> 01:48:36.960
Cricket asked, pacing around the cluster

01:48:36.960 --> 01:48:37.500
of nets.

01:48:37.560 --> 01:48:39.359
They all look the same.

01:48:39.420 --> 01:48:42.359
Sundew grunched her eyebrows

01:48:42.359 --> 01:48:42.960
quizzically.

01:48:43.020 --> 01:48:45.359
They looked nothing the same.

01:48:45.420 --> 01:48:48.239
The branches came from different plans or

01:48:48.239 --> 01:48:52.380
were woven in different ways and She took

01:48:52.380 --> 01:48:55.859
a deep breath, help one more time, and

01:48:55.859 --> 01:48:57.840
then I can leave them to Belladonna if I

01:48:57.840 --> 01:48:58.079
want to.

01:48:58.140 --> 01:49:01.380
Sundoo reached into the ground with her

01:49:01.380 --> 01:49:02.100
leaf speak.

01:49:02.159 --> 01:49:05.039
She found a tendril and followed it back

01:49:05.039 --> 01:49:08.460
calling roots to her, until a vine curled

01:49:08.460 --> 01:49:10.680
through the soft, dark earth and climbed

01:49:10.680 --> 01:49:12.720
up, weaving around the doorway of

01:49:12.720 --> 01:49:13.739
Bryony's nest.

01:49:13.800 --> 01:49:16.260
Purple morning glories burst from the

01:49:16.260 --> 01:49:17.760
buds as it settled in place.

01:49:17.880 --> 01:49:20.159
There, she said.

01:49:20.220 --> 01:49:21.899
Think you can figure it out now?

01:49:21.960 --> 01:49:24.600
Thank you, Blue said.

01:49:24.659 --> 01:49:29.220
So cool, so tell breathed.

01:49:29.279 --> 01:49:31.979
Sundo, cricket started.

01:49:32.100 --> 01:49:34.859
I have to go report to Belladonna.

01:49:34.979 --> 01:49:37.979
Sundew disentangled Bumblebee from her

01:49:37.979 --> 01:49:41.220
neck and pastor into cricket's talons, the

01:49:41.220 --> 01:49:43.920
dragonette protested sleepily, breathing

01:49:43.920 --> 01:49:47.039
capybara breath into sundew's snout, but

01:49:47.039 --> 01:49:48.779
it didn't take long before she was curled

01:49:48.779 --> 01:49:50.279
up in cricket's arms with her eyes

01:49:50.279 --> 01:49:50.760
closed.

01:49:50.819 --> 01:49:55.020
It's just Aren't you our friend?

01:49:55.079 --> 01:49:56.340
Cricket asked.

01:49:56.399 --> 01:49:59.699
There's so much you didn't tell us, like

01:49:59.699 --> 01:50:02.340
about the flame silk or the other village

01:50:02.340 --> 01:50:06.000
or the secret plans to burn the hives, or

01:50:06.000 --> 01:50:07.560
the dragon you're going to marry.

01:50:07.680 --> 01:50:11.039
Maybe not everything is your business

01:50:11.039 --> 01:50:12.659
Sundew Flair.

01:50:12.720 --> 01:50:15.779
Maybe you don't need the answer to every

01:50:15.779 --> 01:50:16.859
question in the world.

01:50:16.979 --> 01:50:19.979
Maybe I was a little busy helping you

01:50:19.979 --> 01:50:22.500
investigate Queen Wasp and burning down

01:50:22.500 --> 01:50:24.239
greenhouses and keeping you alive.

01:50:24.300 --> 01:50:27.119
It's not her fault, cricket.

01:50:27.180 --> 01:50:30.539
Blue said, leaning against the hive wing

01:50:30.539 --> 01:50:31.020
side.

01:50:31.079 --> 01:50:33.779
His shimmering blue purple scales were

01:50:33.779 --> 01:50:35.760
dimmer in the green light that filtered

01:50:35.760 --> 01:50:37.979
through the dome, but his flame silk

01:50:37.979 --> 01:50:40.319
glowed like fireflies under the scales on

01:50:40.319 --> 01:50:40.739
his wrists.

01:50:40.800 --> 01:50:44.039
She was trying to help by bringing us

01:50:44.039 --> 01:50:44.220
here.

01:50:44.279 --> 01:50:47.100
She's been working on her tribe's plan

01:50:47.100 --> 01:50:47.520
her whole life.

01:50:47.579 --> 01:50:50.039
She's only known us for a few days.

01:50:50.100 --> 01:50:52.560
It makes sense that she didn't tell us

01:50:52.560 --> 01:50:52.920
everything.

01:50:52.979 --> 01:50:55.739
And you know she didn't want them to burn

01:50:55.739 --> 01:50:56.819
bloodworm hive.

01:50:56.880 --> 01:50:58.800
Do I know that?

01:50:58.920 --> 01:51:00.119
Cricket asked.

01:51:00.180 --> 01:51:01.500
Send do.

01:51:01.560 --> 01:51:04.260
Can you protect Blue if he doesn't want

01:51:04.260 --> 01:51:06.300
them to use his flame silk anymore?

01:51:06.359 --> 01:51:10.020
Of course I can, Sandu shouted.

01:51:10.079 --> 01:51:11.460
And they all jumped back.

01:51:11.520 --> 01:51:13.979
By all the trees.

01:51:14.039 --> 01:51:15.840
It's like you cannot keep straight in

01:51:15.840 --> 01:51:17.880
your heads who are the good guys and who

01:51:17.880 --> 01:51:20.039
are the bad guys here, when it is very

01:51:20.039 --> 01:51:20.520
obvious.

01:51:20.579 --> 01:51:22.380
R at you.

01:51:22.439 --> 01:51:25.260
She whirled and flung herself with a path

01:51:25.260 --> 01:51:26.220
toward the meeting house.

01:51:26.279 --> 01:51:28.680
As she stormed off.

01:51:28.739 --> 01:51:32.039
She heard Swordtails say, She's right.

01:51:32.100 --> 01:51:34.739
I have no idea if her mom is the good guy

01:51:34.739 --> 01:51:36.539
or the bad guy or what right now.

01:51:36.600 --> 01:51:40.079
Sundew did not let herself think.

01:51:40.199 --> 01:51:43.859
Neither do I. She did not.

01:51:43.920 --> 01:51:45.960
Let herself worry about who was honest

01:51:45.960 --> 01:51:48.659
with her, and whom she would rescue from

01:51:48.659 --> 01:51:50.880
a burning hive, and whether being

01:51:50.880 --> 01:51:53.159
manipulative was normal for a mom and a

01:51:53.159 --> 01:51:53.520
leader.

01:51:53.579 --> 01:51:55.859
And what was going to happen next to blue

01:51:55.859 --> 01:51:56.520
and his friends.

01:51:56.579 --> 01:51:58.920
She gave her report.

01:51:58.979 --> 01:52:02.159
She showed Belladonna the length of vine

01:52:02.159 --> 01:52:03.720
from Wasp's greenhouse.

01:52:03.960 --> 01:52:06.119
Belladonna recognized it from the days

01:52:06.119 --> 01:52:08.699
they'd spent hiding there, but neither

01:52:08.699 --> 01:52:10.859
she nor any of the dragons she summoned

01:52:10.859 --> 01:52:11.760
knew what it was either.

01:52:11.819 --> 01:52:15.300
Sundew also explained what they'd learned

01:52:15.300 --> 01:52:18.300
about wasps' mind control, just as she'd

01:52:18.300 --> 01:52:19.619
promised cricket she would.

01:52:19.680 --> 01:52:23.039
And as she'd predicted, Belladonna didn't

01:52:23.039 --> 01:52:23.220
care.

01:52:23.279 --> 01:52:25.979
The entire hive wing tribe was still

01:52:25.979 --> 01:52:27.479
trapped in wasp's power.

01:52:27.539 --> 01:52:29.399
It didn't matter how they got that way.

01:52:29.520 --> 01:52:32.819
They still had to be defeated, every last

01:52:32.819 --> 01:52:35.399
one of them, and the only decision left

01:52:35.399 --> 01:52:38.520
to make, according to Belladonna, was

01:52:38.520 --> 01:52:39.600
which hive to burn next.

01:52:39.659 --> 01:52:43.500
After giving her report, Sundew stopped

01:52:43.500 --> 01:52:46.739
by the weapons storehouse, where mandrake

01:52:46.739 --> 01:52:49.319
as usual, was sorting and taking care of

01:52:49.319 --> 01:52:50.880
the hazardous insect collection.

01:52:50.939 --> 01:52:54.359
He was always happiest in here, tending

01:52:54.359 --> 01:52:56.039
to the bullet ants and venomous

01:52:56.039 --> 01:52:56.760
centipedes.

01:52:56.880 --> 01:53:00.420
Sundew took off her empty pouches, and

01:53:00.420 --> 01:53:02.460
reorganized her weaponry and supplies

01:53:02.460 --> 01:53:05.159
between the rest of the leafy bags, then

01:53:05.159 --> 01:53:06.359
resettled them around herself.

01:53:06.420 --> 01:53:09.239
Do you want to restock?

01:53:09.300 --> 01:53:10.380
Mandrake asked.

01:53:10.439 --> 01:53:13.199
He gestured the wall of neatly labeled

01:53:13.199 --> 01:53:13.619
boxes.

01:53:13.680 --> 01:53:17.100
More sleep lilies, or smoke leaves?

01:53:17.220 --> 01:53:19.680
Not tonight, sundew said.

01:53:19.739 --> 01:53:21.119
Maybe tomorrow.

01:53:21.239 --> 01:53:24.300
She was too tired to plan a new set of

01:53:24.300 --> 01:53:26.279
weapons, and she didn't know what the

01:53:26.279 --> 01:53:27.720
next threat would be anyway.

01:53:27.779 --> 01:53:31.319
Sundew sat through the feast, but she

01:53:31.319 --> 01:53:33.359
didn't feel like eating Panther, or

01:53:33.359 --> 01:53:36.300
dancing with Mandrake, or smiling at any

01:53:36.300 --> 01:53:38.100
of the dragons who came to congratulate

01:53:38.100 --> 01:53:39.720
her on a successful mission.

01:53:39.899 --> 01:53:42.479
As glowing night blooms at the village

01:53:42.479 --> 01:53:45.359
she watched her fellow leaf wings sidle

01:53:45.359 --> 01:53:48.000
up to blue and sore tail, testing out

01:53:48.000 --> 01:53:50.340
questions, slowly letting them in.

01:53:50.399 --> 01:53:52.739
She saw cricket try to join the

01:53:52.739 --> 01:53:55.380
conversations, and she saw all the leaf

01:53:55.380 --> 01:53:57.119
wings turn away from her with their wings

01:53:57.119 --> 01:53:59.100
curled and teeth clenched.

01:53:59.159 --> 01:54:02.340
She saw the looks they gave bumblebee as

01:54:02.340 --> 01:54:04.319
the little hive wing dragonette ate

01:54:04.319 --> 01:54:06.479
everything she could reach, and she saw

01:54:06.479 --> 01:54:08.939
how bumblebee seemed to sense it and grow

01:54:08.939 --> 01:54:11.460
smaller, staying close to the shelter of

01:54:11.460 --> 01:54:12.300
Cricket's wings.

01:54:12.359 --> 01:54:15.840
Don't make every problem your problem

01:54:15.840 --> 01:54:16.439
Sandu.

01:54:16.500 --> 01:54:17.579
Not right now.

01:54:17.640 --> 01:54:20.760
Just get to midnight and deal with

01:54:20.760 --> 01:54:21.779
everything else tomorrow.

01:54:21.840 --> 01:54:26.520
And then finally, finally, the feast

01:54:26.520 --> 01:54:26.880
ended.

01:54:26.939 --> 01:54:29.100
The leaf wings started crawling into

01:54:29.100 --> 01:54:29.880
their nests.

01:54:29.939 --> 01:54:32.340
Two dragons took up their posts outside

01:54:32.340 --> 01:54:33.659
the village entrance.

01:54:33.720 --> 01:54:36.239
Blue paused in front of sundew as they

01:54:36.239 --> 01:54:37.739
headed down the path to the nests.

01:54:37.800 --> 01:54:40.380
Are you sure you don't want to stay with

01:54:40.380 --> 01:54:40.979
us denied?

01:54:41.100 --> 01:54:42.060
He asked.

01:54:42.119 --> 01:54:44.220
She shook her head.

01:54:44.279 --> 01:54:46.619
She wanted to be with someone who made

01:54:46.619 --> 01:54:49.439
her feel more like herself, not dragons

01:54:49.439 --> 01:54:51.300
who made her feel like an untrustworthy

01:54:51.300 --> 01:54:51.720
snake.

01:54:51.779 --> 01:54:55.079
Sortell waved from the doorway of

01:54:55.079 --> 01:54:57.420
Pokweed's nest, and she nodded back.

01:54:57.479 --> 01:55:00.960
She climbed into her own nest. and

01:55:00.960 --> 01:55:02.579
watched through the branches as the

01:55:02.579 --> 01:55:03.539
village went quiet.

01:55:03.600 --> 01:55:08.880
Finally, finally, the time came.

01:55:08.939 --> 01:55:10.979
Almost midnight.

01:55:11.039 --> 01:55:12.479
Time to go.

01:55:12.539 --> 01:55:15.960
Sundew slipped out of her nest, and

01:55:15.960 --> 01:55:18.000
padded stealthily to the far side of the

01:55:18.000 --> 01:55:19.140
barrier from the entrance.

01:55:19.140 --> 01:55:21.539
The plants here knew her very well.

01:55:21.600 --> 01:55:24.479
They'd been trained to grow in a way that

01:55:24.479 --> 01:55:27.000
looked impenetrable to anyone else, but

01:55:27.000 --> 01:55:29.579
as she approached, they sensed her and

01:55:29.579 --> 01:55:32.279
leaned away from one another, bending and

01:55:32.279 --> 01:55:34.680
twining, until there was a hole in the

01:55:34.680 --> 01:55:36.899
barrier just big enough for a small leaf

01:55:36.899 --> 01:55:37.260
wing.

01:55:37.319 --> 01:55:40.199
She hopped through and let it close

01:55:40.199 --> 01:55:40.739
behind her.

01:55:40.800 --> 01:55:44.159
The jungle night was noisier than the day

01:55:44.159 --> 01:55:47.159
between the insects and night prowling

01:55:47.159 --> 01:55:50.460
predators, the declarations of the frogs

01:55:50.460 --> 01:55:52.079
and the skittering clouds of bats

01:55:52.079 --> 01:55:52.560
overhead.

01:55:52.619 --> 01:55:55.800
She used her leaf speak to clear the way

01:55:55.800 --> 01:55:58.140
warning off the dragon traps and

01:55:58.140 --> 01:55:58.800
sundews.

01:55:58.859 --> 01:56:00.659
She knew this route by heart.

01:56:00.720 --> 01:56:03.000
Better even than she knew the names of

01:56:03.000 --> 01:56:04.140
her fellow leaf wings.

01:56:04.199 --> 01:56:06.899
Soon she was at the pond.

01:56:06.960 --> 01:56:09.720
Dark water ribald in front of her

01:56:09.720 --> 01:56:12.119
reflecting slivers of light from the 3

01:56:12.119 --> 01:56:12.720
moons.

01:56:12.720 --> 01:56:16.680
Sundew set the small jade frog on the

01:56:16.680 --> 01:56:19.439
boulder in the center of the pond, climbed

01:56:19.439 --> 01:56:22.319
the nearest safe tree, took a deep breath

01:56:22.319 --> 01:56:25.199
and curled herself on a branch to wait

01:56:25.199 --> 01:56:25.859
for Willow.

01:56:25.920 --> 01:56:30.479
Chapter 6.

01:56:30.539 --> 01:56:34.380
It was the frog's fault, really, that

01:56:34.380 --> 01:56:36.539
Sundew had discovered the sap wings when

01:56:36.539 --> 01:56:37.680
she was only 2 years old.

01:56:37.739 --> 01:56:40.380
Not the jade frog.

01:56:40.439 --> 01:56:42.119
This was an actual frog.

01:56:42.180 --> 01:56:45.060
Small and brownish green, with orange

01:56:45.060 --> 01:56:46.979
flecks across its knobbly back.

01:56:47.100 --> 01:56:50.100
A frog that hopped into sundew's bowl of

01:56:50.100 --> 01:56:52.800
tarot, snarfed up the sugar sprinkled

01:56:52.800 --> 01:56:54.840
grasshoppers she'd been saving for

01:56:54.840 --> 01:56:57.960
dessert, stuck out its tongue at her, and

01:56:57.960 --> 01:57:00.239
then jaunted off into the jungle, as if

01:57:00.239 --> 01:57:02.760
it aggravated dragons every day with no

01:57:02.760 --> 01:57:03.779
consequences.

01:57:03.840 --> 01:57:07.439
Well, that was not going to stand.

01:57:07.500 --> 01:57:09.239
No, sir.

01:57:09.300 --> 01:57:12.539
This time, there would most definitely be

01:57:12.539 --> 01:57:14.939
consequences, frog.

01:57:15.000 --> 01:57:17.399
She chased the frog to the thorn vine

01:57:17.399 --> 01:57:17.939
fence.

01:57:18.000 --> 01:57:20.100
Belladonna's original version of the

01:57:20.100 --> 01:57:22.920
barrier, where it popped through a gap in

01:57:22.920 --> 01:57:24.720
the leaves and vanished into the jungle.

01:57:24.779 --> 01:57:28.560
Now, dragonettes under 4 years old were

01:57:28.560 --> 01:57:30.659
not technically allowed outside the

01:57:30.659 --> 01:57:32.460
safety perimeter of the village on their

01:57:32.460 --> 01:57:35.159
own, but sundew was not like the other

01:57:35.159 --> 01:57:38.279
leaf wing dragonettes, and really, she

01:57:38.279 --> 01:57:41.279
was almost three, which was practically

01:57:41.279 --> 01:57:41.939
four.

01:57:42.060 --> 01:57:44.880
And plus also, what was she supposed to

01:57:44.880 --> 01:57:45.659
do?

01:57:45.720 --> 01:57:48.300
Just let the frog taunt her like that?

01:57:48.359 --> 01:57:52.199
Besides, she knew the jungle better than

01:57:52.199 --> 01:57:53.640
any of the other dragonettes.

01:57:53.699 --> 01:57:57.000
She was a Venus dragon trap slayer.

01:57:57.180 --> 01:58:00.359
She had battled cobra lilies and thundoos

01:58:00.359 --> 01:58:02.760
and pitcher plans and beaten them all.

01:58:02.819 --> 01:58:05.399
She had mighty superpowers.

01:58:05.460 --> 01:58:08.939
No one could stop sundew, chosen one

01:58:08.939 --> 01:58:11.460
daughter of the leaders of the leaf wings

01:58:11.460 --> 01:58:15.180
especially not on a quest for vengeance.

01:58:15.300 --> 01:58:17.939
This frog was going down.

01:58:18.000 --> 01:58:21.420
Sundew glanced around to make sure no one

01:58:21.420 --> 01:58:21.840
was watching.

01:58:21.899 --> 01:58:24.300
Most of the adult dragons were in a

01:58:24.300 --> 01:58:26.579
council meeting, so it seemed fairly safe

01:58:26.579 --> 01:58:28.739
and then hurtled over the fence.

01:58:28.859 --> 01:58:32.039
The jungle on the other side of the

01:58:32.039 --> 01:58:34.199
thorns looked a lot like the jungle on

01:58:34.199 --> 01:58:36.600
her own side, except maybe the plants

01:58:36.600 --> 01:58:38.640
were bigger, and grew more thickly

01:58:38.640 --> 01:58:39.420
entwined.

01:58:39.479 --> 01:58:41.819
She spotted the miscreant frog right

01:58:41.819 --> 01:58:42.060
away.

01:58:42.119 --> 01:58:44.819
It was squatting in a patch of wet leaf

01:58:44.819 --> 01:58:48.060
mulch, chewing in a very self satisfied

01:58:48.060 --> 01:58:51.300
way, chewing her grasshopper.

01:58:51.359 --> 01:58:53.279
Aha!

01:58:53.340 --> 01:58:55.859
Sundew roared, pouncing on it.

01:58:55.920 --> 01:58:58.439
Her claws squished into the

01:58:58.439 --> 01:59:00.779
disintegrating leaves and mud, but

01:59:00.779 --> 01:59:03.300
somehow missed the frog, which leaved

01:59:03.300 --> 01:59:05.460
several feet into the air and bounded off

01:59:05.460 --> 01:59:06.479
through the undergrowth.

01:59:06.539 --> 01:59:09.000
No, Sundew shouted.

01:59:09.060 --> 01:59:10.500
You will pay for this.

01:59:10.619 --> 01:59:14.640
She shot after the frog. ducking under

01:59:14.640 --> 01:59:17.520
snapping plant teeth, and weaving through

01:59:17.520 --> 01:59:19.739
thickets of Strangler vines that tried to

01:59:19.739 --> 01:59:21.000
tighten and ensnare her.

01:59:21.060 --> 01:59:24.239
She was moving too fast for them, but not

01:59:24.239 --> 01:59:26.579
fast enough to catch the frog, who could

01:59:26.579 --> 01:59:28.500
bound to right over quicksand that she

01:59:28.500 --> 01:59:29.340
had to go around.

01:59:29.399 --> 01:59:32.640
At one point, she lost the frog and had

01:59:32.640 --> 01:59:33.600
to freeze for a moment.

01:59:33.659 --> 01:59:36.180
And then it made the mistake of leaping

01:59:36.180 --> 01:59:38.159
away again, and she was after it at

01:59:38.159 --> 01:59:38.340
once.

01:59:38.399 --> 01:59:41.760
Sundew was surprised when they broke

01:59:41.760 --> 01:59:44.100
through into a clearing, and she realized

01:59:44.100 --> 01:59:45.600
the sky was turning purple.

01:59:45.659 --> 01:59:48.239
She didn't think she'd been chasing the

01:59:48.239 --> 01:59:50.939
frog for that long, but she hadn't been

01:59:50.939 --> 01:59:52.739
paying attention to anything except the

01:59:52.739 --> 01:59:54.239
flicker of its legs up ahead.

01:59:54.300 --> 01:59:57.119
One of the moons was already climbing the

01:59:57.119 --> 01:59:57.359
sky.

01:59:57.420 --> 02:00:00.899
Belladonna and hemlock were going to be

02:00:00.899 --> 02:00:01.380
furious.

02:00:01.439 --> 02:00:06.180
Not as furious as I am, she thought, with

02:00:06.180 --> 02:00:09.420
this frog, who caused all this trouble in

02:00:09.420 --> 02:00:12.720
the 1st place, and must feel my wrath.

02:00:12.779 --> 02:00:16.199
She slowed down as she slipped out of the

02:00:16.199 --> 02:00:18.779
trees, realizing there was a pond in the

02:00:18.779 --> 02:00:21.539
clearing, fed on the far side by a small

02:00:21.539 --> 02:00:25.199
silvery stream, a boulder as smooth as

02:00:25.199 --> 02:00:27.840
obsidian stuck up out of the water, near

02:00:27.840 --> 02:00:30.300
the middle of the pond, and some of the

02:00:30.300 --> 02:00:32.939
far trees leaned down toward it, like

02:00:32.939 --> 02:00:34.800
parent dragons feeding their little

02:00:34.800 --> 02:00:35.159
ones.

02:00:35.220 --> 02:00:38.699
Not particularly like Sundu's parents

02:00:38.699 --> 02:00:41.340
that is, but like a few other parents she

02:00:41.340 --> 02:00:42.479
had seen among the tribe.

02:00:42.539 --> 02:00:45.359
The frog had paused by the edge of the

02:00:45.359 --> 02:00:47.340
pond. half buried in the mud.

02:00:47.399 --> 02:00:50.279
Sundew could see its eyes rolling back

02:00:50.279 --> 02:00:52.260
toward her and its throat pulsing

02:00:52.260 --> 02:00:52.739
rapidly.

02:00:52.800 --> 02:00:56.640
She crept forward on stealthy talons

02:00:56.640 --> 02:00:59.699
placing each claw silently, crouching

02:00:59.699 --> 02:01:01.979
close to the ground, and holding her

02:01:01.979 --> 02:01:03.119
wings perfectly still.

02:01:03.180 --> 02:01:05.939
Here I come, frog.

02:01:06.000 --> 02:01:07.859
Prepare to die.

02:01:07.920 --> 02:01:15.840
One step, another, closer, and pounce.

02:01:15.960 --> 02:01:19.500
Her claws closed on mud and thin air.

02:01:19.560 --> 02:01:22.079
The frog disappeared into the pond with a

02:01:22.079 --> 02:01:23.279
smug plop.

02:01:23.340 --> 02:01:28.500
Sundew roared, shaking the leaves on the

02:01:28.500 --> 02:01:30.960
trees overhead, and making several dragon

02:01:30.960 --> 02:01:32.699
traps snap shut on nothing.

02:01:32.760 --> 02:01:37.859
You slippery, flea brained, smirking, bug

02:01:36.899 --> 02:01:38.880
eyed son of a hive wing.

02:01:38.939 --> 02:01:40.680
I am going to destroy you.

02:01:40.800 --> 02:01:43.800
Even in her rage.

02:01:43.859 --> 02:01:45.720
She knew better than to leap into an

02:01:45.720 --> 02:01:47.819
unfamiliar body of water without checking

02:01:47.819 --> 02:01:49.979
for water wheels and bladder warts

02:01:49.979 --> 02:01:50.279
first.

02:01:50.340 --> 02:01:53.579
She whipped around, wrenched a large

02:01:53.579 --> 02:01:56.100
branch out of the nearest tree, and

02:01:56.100 --> 02:01:57.899
started furiously stabbing the water with

02:01:57.899 --> 02:01:58.140
it.

02:01:58.199 --> 02:02:01.140
Droplets flew up and drenched her face

02:02:01.140 --> 02:02:03.600
and wings, and the underbrush rippled

02:02:03.600 --> 02:02:06.239
with tiny animals scurrying away from the

02:02:06.239 --> 02:02:08.100
enormous splashes she was making.

02:02:08.159 --> 02:02:11.579
She checked the sharp end of the branch.

02:02:11.640 --> 02:02:15.659
No impaled frog, no tangles of deadly

02:02:15.659 --> 02:02:18.119
underwater plants either, but that didn't

02:02:18.119 --> 02:02:18.960
mean there weren't any.

02:02:19.020 --> 02:02:21.539
If she went into the water, and got

02:02:21.539 --> 02:02:24.300
drowned by a hungry water wheel, instead

02:02:24.300 --> 02:02:26.579
of fulfilling her great stupid destiny.

02:02:26.640 --> 02:02:29.220
Her parents would strongly disapprove.

02:02:29.279 --> 02:02:33.000
But the frog, it couldn't get away with

02:02:33.000 --> 02:02:33.659
this.

02:02:33.720 --> 02:02:36.659
Come out and face me like a reptile

02:02:36.659 --> 02:02:38.159
Sundew shouted.

02:02:38.220 --> 02:02:40.619
I'm going to bite off your legs and feed

02:02:40.619 --> 02:02:41.819
them to a tarantula.

02:02:41.880 --> 02:02:44.520
I'm going to pour piranhas into this pond

02:02:44.520 --> 02:02:47.100
and tell them all to eat you slowly.

02:02:47.159 --> 02:02:51.300
By all the trees, said a voice above

02:02:51.300 --> 02:02:51.600
her.

02:02:51.659 --> 02:02:53.819
Who are you talking to?

02:02:53.939 --> 02:02:57.060
Sundu jumped back, startled.

02:02:57.119 --> 02:03:00.359
A pale green dragon sat on the boulder

02:03:00.420 --> 02:03:01.800
blinking down at her.

02:03:01.859 --> 02:03:04.380
She had definitely not been there a

02:03:04.380 --> 02:03:04.739
moment earlier.

02:03:04.800 --> 02:03:08.100
Also, she was a dragonette.

02:03:08.159 --> 02:03:10.859
Out beyond the safety perimeter, just

02:03:10.859 --> 02:03:11.880
like sundew.

02:03:12.119 --> 02:03:15.119
Also, Sundew had never seen her before.

02:03:15.180 --> 02:03:17.880
Which didn't seem possible in a group as

02:03:17.880 --> 02:03:19.739
small as the leaf wings.

02:03:19.800 --> 02:03:22.859
Also, she had the deepest brown eyes

02:03:22.859 --> 02:03:24.180
sundew had ever seen.

02:03:24.239 --> 02:03:27.420
My arch nemesis.

02:03:27.479 --> 02:03:30.060
Sundu growled in response to her question

02:03:30.060 --> 02:03:33.239
who is hiding in this pond, but not for

02:03:33.239 --> 02:03:37.199
long because I am going to destroy him or

02:03:37.199 --> 02:03:38.699
her, whatever it is.

02:03:38.699 --> 02:03:41.640
The new dragon tilted her head to study

02:03:41.640 --> 02:03:42.180
the water.

02:03:42.239 --> 02:03:43.920
Wow.

02:03:43.979 --> 02:03:47.640
What did this terrible, extremely doomed

02:03:47.640 --> 02:03:48.779
fiend do to you?

02:03:48.840 --> 02:03:53.699
It stole my grasshopper, which I was, you

02:03:53.699 --> 02:03:54.060
know what?

02:03:54.119 --> 02:03:56.460
It doesn't matter, Sundew said.

02:03:56.520 --> 02:03:59.520
Noticing the amusement that was sneaking

02:03:59.520 --> 02:04:00.659
onto the stranger's face.

02:04:00.720 --> 02:04:03.840
What it did is not the point.

02:04:03.899 --> 02:04:07.199
What I'm going to do to it is completely

02:04:07.199 --> 02:04:10.739
justified, trust me, I just have to catch

02:04:10.739 --> 02:04:11.220
it first.

02:04:11.279 --> 02:04:13.500
Are we?

02:04:13.560 --> 02:04:16.500
We're not talking about a dragon.

02:04:16.560 --> 02:04:17.640
Are we?

02:04:17.699 --> 02:04:18.899
The stranger asked.

02:04:18.960 --> 02:04:23.340
No, send do admit it.

02:04:23.399 --> 02:04:25.739
The other dragon wrinkled her snout

02:04:25.739 --> 02:04:26.340
thoughtfully.

02:04:26.399 --> 02:04:28.140
A crocodile?

02:04:28.260 --> 02:04:30.119
A monitor lizard?

02:04:30.180 --> 02:04:32.760
Oh, a Gila monster.

02:04:32.819 --> 02:04:34.979
Those things are cranky.

02:04:35.039 --> 02:04:38.399
I nearly got in a fight with one last 2

02:04:38.399 --> 02:04:40.920
moons night because I stepped on its tail

02:04:40.920 --> 02:04:42.720
but I obviously didn't mean to.

02:04:42.779 --> 02:04:45.180
Hey, maybe it's the same one.

02:04:45.239 --> 02:04:46.979
It's not.

02:04:47.039 --> 02:04:48.600
Sundew snapped.

02:04:48.659 --> 02:04:50.279
She scowled the water.

02:04:50.340 --> 02:04:56.039
It's a frog, she said at last, but a very

02:04:56.039 --> 02:04:59.399
bad frog who deserves stamping on.

02:04:59.399 --> 02:05:01.079
Oh no.

02:05:01.140 --> 02:05:04.140
That's, oh, dear.

02:05:04.199 --> 02:05:07.439
The stranger covered her face, as though

02:05:07.439 --> 02:05:09.720
she was overcome with sympathy, but

02:05:09.720 --> 02:05:11.760
Sundew could see her shoulders shaking.

02:05:11.819 --> 02:05:13.920
Don't you laugh at me.

02:05:13.979 --> 02:05:15.239
She yelped.

02:05:15.300 --> 02:05:17.159
You would understand if you'd seen its

02:05:17.159 --> 02:05:18.539
stupid smug face.

02:05:18.600 --> 02:05:21.180
I can't stand smug faces.

02:05:21.239 --> 02:05:23.699
I just want to smush them all flat.

02:05:23.760 --> 02:05:26.220
You should have been here 5 heartbeats

02:05:26.220 --> 02:05:28.020
sooner, then you could have seen it

02:05:28.020 --> 02:05:30.479
smirkety smirking its way into the pond.

02:05:30.539 --> 02:05:33.420
Sundew glanced around at the dimming

02:05:33.420 --> 02:05:33.960
sunlight.

02:05:34.020 --> 02:05:37.500
Where did you come from anyway?

02:05:37.560 --> 02:05:40.739
The stranger waved one of her wings of

02:05:40.739 --> 02:05:41.640
the trees behind her.

02:05:41.819 --> 02:05:44.340
From the village, of course, silly.

02:05:44.460 --> 02:05:47.460
But the village wasn't behind her.

02:05:47.520 --> 02:05:50.399
It was quite a long way in the opposite

02:05:50.399 --> 02:05:50.760
direction.

02:05:50.819 --> 02:05:53.819
Um, what?

02:05:53.939 --> 02:05:56.939
Sundu asked, which wasn't exactly the

02:05:56.939 --> 02:05:58.920
incisive line of questioning she'd been

02:05:58.920 --> 02:05:59.460
planning on.

02:05:59.520 --> 02:06:01.619
Who are you?

02:06:01.680 --> 02:06:03.420
The other dragon asked.

02:06:03.539 --> 02:06:06.239
I feel like I should really know you

02:06:06.239 --> 02:06:06.659
already.

02:06:06.720 --> 02:06:10.020
Sundew drew herself up and made her

02:06:10.020 --> 02:06:10.979
fiercest face.

02:06:11.039 --> 02:06:13.619
It was one thing for sundew to not know

02:06:13.619 --> 02:06:16.260
this stranger, but it was inconceivable

02:06:16.260 --> 02:06:18.239
for this stranger to not know her.

02:06:18.300 --> 02:06:20.699
Yes, you should.

02:06:20.760 --> 02:06:22.800
I am sundoo.

02:06:22.859 --> 02:06:24.239
Who are you?

02:06:24.300 --> 02:06:26.819
The dragon tilted her head.

02:06:26.880 --> 02:06:30.180
Her scales were dappled with darker green

02:06:30.180 --> 02:06:32.760
leaf shapes, like the shadows of long

02:06:32.760 --> 02:06:33.779
oval leaves.

02:06:33.840 --> 02:06:36.119
Her eyes looked like they were smiling.

02:06:36.180 --> 02:06:39.840
Her whole face was doing a weird, crinkly

02:06:39.840 --> 02:06:42.420
sparkly thing that made sundew's face

02:06:42.420 --> 02:06:43.500
want to do the same thing.

02:06:43.560 --> 02:06:46.140
Crinkling and sparkling.

02:06:46.260 --> 02:06:49.140
What kind of weird brain magic was this?

02:06:49.199 --> 02:06:51.840
Sundew, really?

02:06:51.899 --> 02:06:54.000
That's an unusual name.

02:06:54.119 --> 02:06:55.140
She said.

02:06:55.199 --> 02:06:58.619
No, it's not, Sundu snapped.

02:06:58.680 --> 02:07:01.680
I mean, it is, technically, because I'm

02:07:01.680 --> 02:07:04.020
the only one who has it, but everyone's

02:07:04.020 --> 02:07:07.199
heard it, so it's very well known, which

02:07:07.199 --> 02:07:09.060
means it can't be unusual by that

02:07:09.060 --> 02:07:11.880
definition, I mean, is my point.

02:07:11.939 --> 02:07:14.880
And besides, your name is the weird one.

02:07:14.939 --> 02:07:18.359
It's just so weird.

02:07:18.420 --> 02:07:21.180
The brain magic was doing something to

02:07:21.180 --> 02:07:22.020
her words too.

02:07:22.140 --> 02:07:25.260
She frowned as severely as she could.

02:07:25.260 --> 02:07:27.479
Stop crinkling face.

02:07:27.539 --> 02:07:31.979
I haven't told you my name yet, said the

02:07:31.979 --> 02:07:34.020
other dragon, sparkling even more.

02:07:34.140 --> 02:07:38.100
Well, I bet it's weirder than sundew.

02:07:38.220 --> 02:07:40.560
Sundew fluffed out her wings.

02:07:40.680 --> 02:07:44.699
I'm Willow, said the dappled green dragon

02:07:44.699 --> 02:07:45.539
with a perfect face.

02:07:45.600 --> 02:07:48.000
There, see?

02:07:48.060 --> 02:07:50.340
I was right, sundew said.

02:07:50.460 --> 02:07:53.340
Like, whoever knew anyone named Willow.

02:07:53.399 --> 02:07:54.420
Not me.

02:07:54.479 --> 02:07:57.239
Willow tilted her head, looking

02:07:57.239 --> 02:07:57.840
confused.

02:07:57.899 --> 02:08:01.920
What do you mean by well known?

02:08:02.039 --> 02:08:05.039
I've never heard of you.

02:08:05.100 --> 02:08:06.779
Should I have?

02:08:06.840 --> 02:08:10.079
Sundew flicked her tail and accidentally

02:08:10.079 --> 02:08:12.300
knocked a startled lizard into the pond.

02:08:12.359 --> 02:08:15.239
I'm the daughter of Belladonna and

02:08:15.239 --> 02:08:16.619
Hemlock, she said.

02:08:16.680 --> 02:08:19.140
You know, the whole plan.

02:08:19.260 --> 02:08:21.539
I'm the one who has to save Pantala.

02:08:21.659 --> 02:08:24.659
Save Pantala from what?

02:08:24.720 --> 02:08:26.039
Willow asked.

02:08:26.100 --> 02:08:28.140
Sundew's jaw dropped.

02:08:28.199 --> 02:08:31.380
From the hive wings?

02:08:31.439 --> 02:08:32.520
she cried.

02:08:32.579 --> 02:08:34.619
Don't you know anything?

02:08:34.680 --> 02:08:35.460
Where have you been?

02:08:35.520 --> 02:08:36.600
Who are you?

02:08:36.659 --> 02:08:38.699
Oh.

02:08:38.760 --> 02:08:42.300
Willow's front talon flew to her face.

02:08:42.359 --> 02:08:44.760
She stared at Sundew, as though a

02:08:44.760 --> 02:08:46.560
lightning bolt had dropped out of the sky

02:08:46.560 --> 02:08:47.880
and asked for directions.

02:08:47.939 --> 02:08:50.640
I know why your names are weird.

02:08:50.699 --> 02:08:52.739
You're a poison wing.

02:08:52.800 --> 02:08:54.600
A what?

02:08:54.659 --> 02:08:57.479
Sundew barked, but Willow had already

02:08:57.479 --> 02:08:59.460
flown off the boulder to land beside

02:08:59.460 --> 02:08:59.699
her.

02:08:59.760 --> 02:09:03.539
She circled sundew, studying her wings

02:09:03.539 --> 02:09:05.340
and tail with wide eyes.

02:09:05.399 --> 02:09:06.720
Up close.

02:09:06.840 --> 02:09:09.479
She carried a scent of mint and chocolate

02:09:09.479 --> 02:09:10.979
and new rain.

02:09:11.039 --> 02:09:13.260
But how can you be?

02:09:13.319 --> 02:09:15.659
You look just like us?

02:09:15.779 --> 02:09:17.039
Willow said.

02:09:17.100 --> 02:09:18.840
Maybe a little prettier.

02:09:18.960 --> 02:09:22.260
She met Sundew's eyes, and ducked her

02:09:22.260 --> 02:09:25.319
head, doing that full face smile crinkle

02:09:25.319 --> 02:09:27.300
thing, and trying to hide it at the same

02:09:27.300 --> 02:09:29.399
time, maybe a lot.

02:09:29.460 --> 02:09:32.640
Which was a weird and wrong observation

02:09:32.640 --> 02:09:35.399
because Willow was the one with the river

02:09:35.399 --> 02:09:39.119
deep eyes, and the sparkle face, and that

02:09:39.119 --> 02:09:40.739
wasn't the point, Sundew.

02:09:40.859 --> 02:09:44.699
I'm not a poison anything, Sandu said.

02:09:44.760 --> 02:09:46.140
I'm a leaf wing.

02:09:46.199 --> 02:09:49.020
But you're one of the offshoots, aren't

02:09:49.020 --> 02:09:49.199
you?

02:09:49.260 --> 02:09:50.520
Willow asked.

02:09:50.579 --> 02:09:53.279
She stopped circling and sat down

02:09:53.279 --> 02:09:55.439
checking the ground below her for

02:09:55.439 --> 02:09:56.640
anything thorny first.

02:09:56.699 --> 02:10:00.239
The scary dragons with all the dangerous

02:10:00.239 --> 02:10:01.020
plant names.

02:10:01.079 --> 02:10:03.600
Sundew stared at her.

02:10:03.659 --> 02:10:05.520
Offshoots?

02:10:05.579 --> 02:10:06.420
She echoed.

02:10:06.479 --> 02:10:11.340
I thought, we were the only ones, the

02:10:11.340 --> 02:10:12.600
only leaf wings left.

02:10:12.720 --> 02:10:17.340
Willow's sparkly look dimmed a little, as

02:10:17.340 --> 02:10:19.140
though someone had thrown cobwebs over

02:10:19.140 --> 02:10:19.920
her starlight.

02:10:19.979 --> 02:10:25.319
Oh, no, she said, there's us.

02:10:25.380 --> 02:10:26.699
The rest of us.

02:10:26.760 --> 02:10:31.500
The, um, sorry, I'm not sure how else to

02:10:31.500 --> 02:10:31.920
say this.

02:10:31.979 --> 02:10:36.899
The real leaf wings, the ones who stayed

02:10:36.899 --> 02:10:39.180
with Queen Sequoia and are still loyal to

02:10:39.180 --> 02:10:39.359
her.

02:10:39.420 --> 02:10:42.659
Queen Sequoia is still alive?

02:10:42.779 --> 02:10:45.359
Sundu said, startled.

02:10:45.420 --> 02:10:50.640
Wow, Willow said, her wide eyed look was

02:10:50.640 --> 02:10:52.380
sort of unreasonably adorable.

02:10:52.439 --> 02:10:55.380
I can't believe they keep us a secret

02:10:55.380 --> 02:10:55.920
from you.

02:10:55.979 --> 02:10:59.159
We learn all about the poison wings in

02:10:59.159 --> 02:10:59.399
school.

02:10:59.460 --> 02:11:01.380
What do you learn?

02:11:01.439 --> 02:11:02.880
Sandu asked.

02:11:02.939 --> 02:11:05.159
Curiosity warring with anger.

02:11:05.220 --> 02:11:06.899
Did mother know about this?

02:11:06.960 --> 02:11:10.979
If so, how dare she hide anything from

02:11:10.979 --> 02:11:11.699
sundew?

02:11:11.760 --> 02:11:13.739
What do they tell you about us?

02:11:13.800 --> 02:11:19.319
Oh, you know, how some dragons wanted to

02:11:19.319 --> 02:11:21.659
keep fighting the tree wars, so they

02:11:21.659 --> 02:11:24.000
split off from the rest of the tribe when

02:11:24.000 --> 02:11:26.699
we reached the poison jungle, and then

02:11:26.699 --> 02:11:28.619
they started naming their dragonettes

02:11:28.619 --> 02:11:31.319
after deadly plants, instead of giving

02:11:31.319 --> 02:11:34.199
them tree names, like leaf wings always

02:11:34.199 --> 02:11:36.779
have, and how they've been plotting

02:11:36.779 --> 02:11:38.579
revenge on the hive wings all these

02:11:38.579 --> 02:11:39.000
years.

02:11:39.119 --> 02:11:42.060
Queen Sequoia met with their leader last

02:11:42.060 --> 02:11:42.960
moon cycle.

02:11:43.020 --> 02:11:45.359
She's always trying to convince her that

02:11:45.359 --> 02:11:48.600
it's safer to stay here and lie low until

02:11:48.600 --> 02:11:50.100
Queen Wasp dies.

02:11:50.520 --> 02:11:52.439
Met with their leader.

02:11:52.500 --> 02:11:56.039
There was only one dragon that could be.

02:11:56.039 --> 02:11:59.579
Belladonna, Sundu's mother.

02:11:59.640 --> 02:12:03.060
Sundu wondered which hunting expedition

02:12:03.060 --> 02:12:05.880
or council meeting had been the lie

02:12:05.880 --> 02:12:08.279
Belladonna had tossed her way to hide her

02:12:08.279 --> 02:12:10.380
secret meeting with a leaf winged queen.

02:12:10.439 --> 02:12:12.420
The queen who was still alive.

02:12:12.479 --> 02:12:14.880
Even though Sundew and the other

02:12:14.880 --> 02:12:17.340
dragonettes had been taught that she died

02:12:17.340 --> 02:12:18.420
during the tree wars.

02:12:18.539 --> 02:12:21.180
Willow was still talking.

02:12:21.239 --> 02:12:24.840
I mean, can you imagine how dumb it would

02:12:24.840 --> 02:12:26.699
be to go poke one of the hives?

02:12:26.819 --> 02:12:29.340
As long as they think we're extinct.

02:12:29.399 --> 02:12:30.479
We're safe.

02:12:30.539 --> 02:12:33.359
But if we let them know we're still out

02:12:33.359 --> 02:12:35.340
here, she shuddered.

02:12:35.460 --> 02:12:39.720
Excuse me, Sundew said, bristling.

02:12:39.779 --> 02:12:42.779
So your suggestion is we let them win.

02:12:42.840 --> 02:12:46.079
We let them steal our continent and revel

02:12:46.079 --> 02:12:48.060
in our extermination.

02:12:48.119 --> 02:12:50.819
We just accept living here.

02:12:50.880 --> 02:12:53.880
She waved her wings at the Venus dragon

02:12:53.880 --> 02:12:56.640
traps overhead, which had been slowly

02:12:56.640 --> 02:12:59.220
leaning down toward them, closer and

02:12:59.220 --> 02:13:00.899
closer as the conversation went on.

02:13:01.020 --> 02:13:04.140
Sundew dug a rock out of the mud and

02:13:04.140 --> 02:13:05.399
threw it at the nearest plant.

02:13:05.460 --> 02:13:09.180
It snapped shut and drew back, and the

02:13:09.180 --> 02:13:10.380
others around it bristled.

02:13:10.439 --> 02:13:14.279
It's not that bad here, Willow said.

02:13:14.340 --> 02:13:15.300
Right?

02:13:15.359 --> 02:13:19.560
I mean, I think it's better with, um

02:13:19.560 --> 02:13:21.359
interesting company.

02:13:21.420 --> 02:13:24.840
She gave Sundew that crinkle, sparkle

02:13:24.840 --> 02:13:27.239
smile face, that made all the words in

02:13:27.239 --> 02:13:29.520
Sundew's head run around bumping into one

02:13:29.520 --> 02:13:31.739
another, like disoriented moths.

02:13:31.859 --> 02:13:35.340
Do not smile back at her son do.

02:13:35.399 --> 02:13:37.979
She is fundamentally wrong about your

02:13:37.979 --> 02:13:38.939
entire life purpose.

02:13:39.000 --> 02:13:42.420
What is your face doing, Sundew?

02:13:42.539 --> 02:13:46.979
We deserve to be out there, Sundu said

02:13:46.979 --> 02:13:49.680
trying to focus on everything she'd been

02:13:49.680 --> 02:13:49.920
taught.

02:13:49.979 --> 02:13:52.979
Belladonna had trained her to summon her

02:13:52.979 --> 02:13:54.239
anger at a moment's notice.

02:13:54.300 --> 02:13:57.720
That was a safe place to go when sundew's

02:13:57.720 --> 02:13:59.399
other emotions got too complicated.

02:13:59.520 --> 02:14:03.539
Wasp could live for another 100 years, or

02:14:03.539 --> 02:14:05.399
she could be replaced by someone equally

02:14:05.399 --> 02:14:05.699
bad.

02:14:05.760 --> 02:14:08.340
We can't just sit around and wait for

02:14:08.340 --> 02:14:09.720
history to sort itself out.

02:14:09.779 --> 02:14:11.220
We have to fight.

02:14:11.279 --> 02:14:13.680
We have to make things better with our

02:14:13.680 --> 02:14:14.460
own claws.

02:14:14.520 --> 02:14:18.060
Willow blinked at the fist Sundew was

02:14:18.060 --> 02:14:20.579
making, and then she reached out and took

02:14:20.579 --> 02:14:22.439
it between her own front talons.

02:14:22.500 --> 02:14:26.039
She smoothed out the tension and laid one

02:14:26.039 --> 02:14:27.539
palm over sundews.

02:14:27.600 --> 02:14:30.420
Her scales warm and light as a fern

02:14:30.420 --> 02:14:30.960
frond.

02:14:31.020 --> 02:14:34.020
Sundew could feel Willow's heartbeat

02:14:34.020 --> 02:14:36.420
going only about half as fast as

02:14:36.420 --> 02:14:37.140
sundews.

02:14:37.199 --> 02:14:40.439
Willow said softly.

02:14:40.500 --> 02:14:43.260
You don't have to do anything right this

02:14:43.260 --> 02:14:43.500
second.

02:14:43.560 --> 02:14:45.060
Just be here.

02:14:45.180 --> 02:14:47.100
Breathe.

02:14:47.159 --> 02:14:51.720
No one had ever told Sun do to breathe

02:14:51.720 --> 02:14:52.140
before.

02:14:52.199 --> 02:14:55.680
Her 1st instinct was to scoff, that she

02:14:55.680 --> 02:14:58.439
already was breathing, and she did it

02:14:58.439 --> 02:15:00.420
rather often and was quite good at it

02:15:00.420 --> 02:15:01.079
thanks very much.

02:15:01.140 --> 02:15:03.840
But there was something in Willow's face

02:15:03.840 --> 02:15:07.079
in her eyes as she gazed down at sundew's

02:15:07.079 --> 02:15:09.659
talons, that made her impossible to scoff

02:15:09.659 --> 02:15:10.140
at.

02:15:10.199 --> 02:15:12.479
They stood like that for a moment.

02:15:12.600 --> 02:15:15.659
One of Willow's graceful wings was a

02:15:15.659 --> 02:15:18.600
breath away from brushing sundews, like a

02:15:18.600 --> 02:15:20.699
butterfly hovering just over a leaf.

02:15:20.699 --> 02:15:24.000
Sundoo wondered if the butterfly was as

02:15:24.000 --> 02:15:26.279
aware of it, as the leaf was.

02:15:26.340 --> 02:15:28.859
She wasn't sure if her heartbeat was

02:15:28.859 --> 02:15:31.319
slowing down, or Willows was speeding

02:15:31.319 --> 02:15:31.500
up.

02:15:31.560 --> 02:15:34.680
But at some point, she realized they had

02:15:34.680 --> 02:15:35.159
synced.

02:15:35.220 --> 02:15:37.439
Don't you think?

02:15:37.439 --> 02:15:40.140
Bump is a terrible word.

02:15:40.199 --> 02:15:42.060
Willow said thoughtfully.

02:15:42.119 --> 02:15:45.659
I mean, that's what most dragons would

02:15:45.659 --> 02:15:48.300
say our hearts are doing, but it doesn't

02:15:48.300 --> 02:15:49.739
feel thumpy to me.

02:15:49.800 --> 02:15:52.619
Pulse doesn't seem right either.

02:15:52.680 --> 02:15:55.199
Beat sounds too violent.

02:15:55.319 --> 02:15:57.600
It's not quite tapping.

02:15:57.659 --> 02:16:00.359
There should be a better word for this.

02:16:00.479 --> 02:16:05.340
For 2 heartbeat finding each other, Sundew

02:16:05.340 --> 02:16:08.640
said, as quietly as she could, trying not

02:16:08.640 --> 02:16:09.359
to break the spell.

02:16:09.420 --> 02:16:13.020
Willow gave her a shy, sideways smile.

02:16:13.079 --> 02:16:15.420
I hope so.

02:16:15.479 --> 02:16:17.939
Sundew didn't know what to say.

02:16:18.000 --> 02:16:20.939
Belladonna would have told her to push

02:16:20.939 --> 02:16:23.399
the other leaf wing into the pond, and

02:16:23.399 --> 02:16:25.739
yell at her about the tree wars, and how

02:16:25.739 --> 02:16:27.539
important it was to go kill wasp.

02:16:27.659 --> 02:16:30.359
She would have pointed out that sundew

02:16:30.359 --> 02:16:33.120
had a duty to marry mandrake and raise

02:16:33.120 --> 02:16:35.940
superpowered danger babies to destroy

02:16:35.940 --> 02:16:36.600
their enemies.

02:16:36.659 --> 02:16:39.899
Belladonna would have said, there was

02:16:39.899 --> 02:16:41.280
nothing more important than their

02:16:41.280 --> 02:16:43.559
vengeance, and that Willow was not worth

02:16:43.559 --> 02:16:44.100
talking to.

02:16:44.159 --> 02:16:47.040
But Belladonna was a liar.

02:16:47.159 --> 02:16:50.280
And Willow was the only dragon who'd ever

02:16:50.280 --> 02:16:52.620
given sundew this all over inside

02:16:52.620 --> 02:16:53.819
sparkles feeling.

02:16:53.879 --> 02:16:56.699
She let her wing brush willows lightly.

02:16:56.760 --> 02:16:58.260
Guess what?

02:16:58.319 --> 02:17:00.180
I've made a decision.

02:17:00.239 --> 02:17:01.860
You have?

02:17:01.920 --> 02:17:03.239
Yes.

02:17:03.299 --> 02:17:06.359
Sendu cleared her throat and made a

02:17:06.359 --> 02:17:07.139
portentous face.

02:17:07.200 --> 02:17:10.200
I have decided to spare that odious

02:17:10.200 --> 02:17:11.639
frog's life in your honor.

02:17:11.700 --> 02:17:15.000
Oh, Willow laughed.

02:17:15.120 --> 02:17:16.079
That's too bad.

02:17:16.139 --> 02:17:19.559
I had just decided to camp out by this

02:17:19.559 --> 02:17:22.319
pond until it emerges so I could murder

02:17:22.319 --> 02:17:22.739
it for you.

02:17:22.799 --> 02:17:24.539
What?

02:17:24.600 --> 02:17:26.639
Sundew couldn't stop herself from

02:17:26.639 --> 02:17:27.180
laughing too.

02:17:27.239 --> 02:17:30.180
No one has ever offered to murder a frog

02:17:30.180 --> 02:17:30.719
for me before.

02:17:30.780 --> 02:17:34.319
Well, no one has ever offered to not

02:17:34.319 --> 02:17:35.879
murder a frog for me before.

02:17:35.940 --> 02:17:37.139
Willow said.

02:17:37.200 --> 02:17:39.360
It's very magnanimous of you.

02:17:39.420 --> 02:17:43.500
That's me, said Sundew, ever so magna

02:17:43.500 --> 02:17:44.100
ganimus.

02:17:44.159 --> 02:17:46.319
Can you come live with us?

02:17:46.440 --> 02:17:48.059
Willow burst out.

02:17:48.120 --> 02:17:50.879
Come be a leaf wing, and meet Queen

02:17:50.879 --> 02:17:53.639
Sequoia, and forget about fighting, and

02:17:53.639 --> 02:17:54.600
see me every day?

02:17:54.719 --> 02:17:58.559
That was the 1st time she had asked, but

02:17:58.559 --> 02:17:59.339
it wasn't the last.

02:17:59.399 --> 02:18:01.920
Nearly every time they met.

02:18:01.979 --> 02:18:04.680
Willow offered again to bring Sundew into

02:18:04.680 --> 02:18:07.559
the other village, to give her a home, and

02:18:07.559 --> 02:18:09.540
teach her how to be a peace loving sap

02:18:09.540 --> 02:18:12.780
wing, a name Willow never used and quite

02:18:12.780 --> 02:18:13.620
disliked.

02:18:13.680 --> 02:18:16.799
But every time, sundew had had to say

02:18:16.799 --> 02:18:17.159
no.

02:18:17.219 --> 02:18:20.159
No, I have a purpose.

02:18:20.219 --> 02:18:23.099
No, my tribe needs me.

02:18:23.159 --> 02:18:26.459
Your tribe needs me to do this too, even

02:18:26.459 --> 02:18:27.600
if none of you realize it.

02:18:27.659 --> 02:18:31.139
No, I have to save the world first.

02:18:31.200 --> 02:18:33.420
I'm sorry.

02:18:33.479 --> 02:18:35.459
She'd said that 1st time.

02:18:35.520 --> 02:18:37.500
I can't.

02:18:37.620 --> 02:18:39.659
Willow had looked away.

02:18:39.719 --> 02:18:43.559
Wings sliding slowly down, but Sundew had

02:18:43.559 --> 02:18:45.179
caught her talons before she could pull

02:18:45.179 --> 02:18:45.719
away entirely.

02:18:45.840 --> 02:18:48.120
But can I see you again?

02:18:48.180 --> 02:18:49.440
She'd asked.

02:18:49.500 --> 02:18:50.639
Tomorrow night?

02:18:50.700 --> 02:18:52.079
And the night after that?

02:18:52.139 --> 02:18:54.419
Maybe also the one after that.

02:18:54.419 --> 02:18:56.879
And the one after that, and the one after

02:18:56.879 --> 02:18:58.379
that, I can sneak out.

02:18:58.440 --> 02:18:59.100
It's easy.

02:18:59.219 --> 02:19:02.699
Willow had laughed again, and the next

02:19:02.699 --> 02:19:05.099
night she'd given sundew the jade frog.

02:19:05.159 --> 02:19:09.059
Our signal, she'd said, so I know if

02:19:09.059 --> 02:19:09.479
you're there.

02:19:09.540 --> 02:19:11.280
Leave it on the rock.

02:19:11.340 --> 02:19:12.899
And I'll come find you.

02:19:12.959 --> 02:19:17.219
In the ensuing 4 years, Sundew had

02:19:17.219 --> 02:19:18.780
convinced her mother that even the

02:19:18.780 --> 02:19:20.700
youngest dragonettes needed to know about

02:19:20.700 --> 02:19:23.159
the sapwings, instead of only learning

02:19:23.159 --> 02:19:24.600
about them when they turned four.

02:19:24.659 --> 02:19:27.299
But Belladonna never took her to her

02:19:27.299 --> 02:19:29.940
meetings with Queen Sequoia, nor did she

02:19:29.940 --> 02:19:31.379
ever tell the council what they talked

02:19:31.379 --> 02:19:31.620
about.

02:19:31.680 --> 02:19:34.559
She'd forbidden sundew to go to their

02:19:34.559 --> 02:19:36.959
village, or try talking to any of them.

02:19:37.020 --> 02:19:40.440
She seemed to find Sundew's interest in

02:19:40.440 --> 02:19:42.959
them suspicious, and she hated hearing

02:19:42.959 --> 02:19:43.799
about them in any case.

02:19:43.860 --> 02:19:46.799
So Sunduke kept Willow a secret.

02:19:46.920 --> 02:19:48.239
Her secret.

02:19:48.299 --> 02:19:51.659
This was the longest they'd gone without

02:19:51.659 --> 02:19:52.319
seeing each other.

02:19:52.379 --> 02:19:56.219
She'd told Willow it might be a while, but

02:19:56.219 --> 02:19:57.899
she'd been gone even longer than she

02:19:57.899 --> 02:20:00.719
expected, and she hadn't told Willow why

02:20:00.719 --> 02:20:02.159
or where she was going.

02:20:02.219 --> 02:20:05.219
A light rain started to fall.

02:20:05.280 --> 02:20:07.799
Misting through the leaves above sundew.

02:20:07.920 --> 02:20:10.260
She wasn't sure how much time had

02:20:10.260 --> 02:20:10.680
passed.

02:20:10.739 --> 02:20:13.680
Only one of the moons was visible through

02:20:13.680 --> 02:20:14.399
the canopy now.

02:20:14.459 --> 02:20:16.739
Will she still come?

02:20:16.799 --> 02:20:19.200
What if she's given up watching for the

02:20:19.200 --> 02:20:19.620
frog?

02:20:19.680 --> 02:20:22.920
But at last the shadows around the pond

02:20:22.920 --> 02:20:26.100
rippled, and one glided up to the boulder

02:20:26.100 --> 02:20:28.020
and then down to the moonlight in front

02:20:28.020 --> 02:20:30.719
of her, becoming the silhouette of the

02:20:30.719 --> 02:20:33.000
only dragon Sundu ever looked forward to

02:20:33.000 --> 02:20:33.239
seeing.

02:20:33.299 --> 02:20:37.799
Sundew leaped out of the tree and bounded

02:20:37.799 --> 02:20:40.020
over the grass into Willow's wings.

02:20:40.020 --> 02:20:44.579
Chapter 7.

02:20:44.639 --> 02:20:47.520
You were gone forever.

02:20:47.579 --> 02:20:50.819
Willow said, clasping sundew's front

02:20:50.819 --> 02:20:52.079
talons and hers.

02:20:52.139 --> 02:20:54.000
I have so much to tell you.

02:20:54.059 --> 02:20:56.879
I've been waiting and waiting, and

02:20:56.879 --> 02:20:59.159
checking the boulder every night, and it

02:20:59.159 --> 02:21:01.559
was dreadful, and I didn't like it, and

02:21:01.559 --> 02:21:02.520
let's never do that again.

02:21:02.639 --> 02:21:05.819
I was half afraid Belladonna must have

02:21:05.819 --> 02:21:06.600
found out about us.

02:21:06.659 --> 02:21:09.360
I started to wonder whether I needed to

02:21:09.360 --> 02:21:11.340
mount a daring rescue operation.

02:21:11.399 --> 02:21:13.500
Blast through the barrier.

02:21:13.559 --> 02:21:17.100
Knock the other poison wings aside, tear

02:21:17.100 --> 02:21:19.020
down your prison and sweep you away to

02:21:19.020 --> 02:21:19.319
safety.

02:21:19.379 --> 02:21:21.840
Wouldn't that have been so heroic?

02:21:21.959 --> 02:21:25.440
Sundew twined her tail around Willows.

02:21:25.559 --> 02:21:29.579
The most heroic, romantic thing ever, but

02:21:29.579 --> 02:21:30.659
totally unnecessary.

02:21:30.719 --> 02:21:32.760
You know, Belladonna couldn't keep me

02:21:32.760 --> 02:21:34.680
locked up, even if she wanted to.

02:21:34.739 --> 02:21:38.219
She reached her leaf speak into the earth

02:21:38.219 --> 02:21:40.440
sending her power along their roots until

02:21:40.440 --> 02:21:43.079
she found what she wanted, and summoned a

02:21:43.079 --> 02:21:44.340
spray of violets from the ground.

02:21:44.399 --> 02:21:47.940
They sprang up, small and beautiful and

02:21:47.940 --> 02:21:50.579
purple, right beside Willow's claws.

02:21:50.639 --> 02:21:52.319
Show off.

02:21:52.379 --> 02:21:54.360
Willow said affectionately.

02:21:54.420 --> 02:21:57.239
This particular clearing was probably the

02:21:57.239 --> 02:21:59.579
most colorful spot in the jungle, thanks

02:21:59.579 --> 02:22:01.620
to the clusters of flowers scattered all

02:22:01.620 --> 02:22:04.020
over it, which sundew had grown for

02:22:04.020 --> 02:22:05.280
willow in the last 3 years.

02:22:05.340 --> 02:22:08.819
So what have you really been so busy

02:22:08.819 --> 02:22:09.059
with?

02:22:09.120 --> 02:22:12.239
I had this awful nightmare that you left

02:22:12.239 --> 02:22:14.579
the poison jungle and ran into WASP.

02:22:14.700 --> 02:22:16.440
It felt so real.

02:22:16.559 --> 02:22:19.319
I almost told Queen Sequoia about it.

02:22:19.379 --> 02:22:21.840
But she's always reassuring us that

02:22:21.840 --> 02:22:24.120
Belladonna wouldn't endanger the rest of

02:22:24.120 --> 02:22:27.899
us by, that she'd at least to tell

02:22:27.899 --> 02:22:29.520
Sundu.

02:22:29.639 --> 02:22:30.780
She said.

02:22:30.840 --> 02:22:33.360
Her voice faltering at the expression on

02:22:33.360 --> 02:22:34.200
sundew's face.

02:22:34.260 --> 02:22:36.239
What is it?

02:22:36.299 --> 02:22:39.600
She let go of Sunday's talons and covered

02:22:39.600 --> 02:22:39.899
her mouth.

02:22:39.959 --> 02:22:41.520
Oh no.

02:22:41.579 --> 02:22:45.659
I did leave the jungle, Sandu said.

02:22:45.719 --> 02:22:47.100
Don't freak out.

02:22:47.159 --> 02:22:50.340
But you weren't seen, Willow said.

02:22:50.399 --> 02:22:54.360
Nobody saw you because you were careful

02:22:54.360 --> 02:22:54.780
right?

02:22:54.840 --> 02:22:58.379
We were careful.

02:22:58.500 --> 02:23:00.239
Sundu said slowly.

02:23:00.299 --> 02:23:03.600
I mean, we were careful.

02:23:03.659 --> 02:23:05.700
Who's we?

02:23:05.760 --> 02:23:06.840
Willow asked.

02:23:06.899 --> 02:23:07.920
What does that mean?

02:23:07.979 --> 02:23:11.819
Belladonna, Hemlock, and I made it to

02:23:11.819 --> 02:23:14.579
Wasp Hive without any trouble, Sandu

02:23:14.579 --> 02:23:14.879
said.

02:23:14.940 --> 02:23:17.399
But we couldn't get inside at first.

02:23:17.459 --> 02:23:20.700
And then we ran into these other

02:23:20.700 --> 02:23:21.479
dragons.

02:23:21.479 --> 02:23:22.799
Oh no.

02:23:22.860 --> 02:23:25.680
Oh no, Willow whispered.

02:23:25.739 --> 02:23:28.319
But it was all right, Sundew said

02:23:28.319 --> 02:23:28.680
quickly.

02:23:28.739 --> 02:23:31.440
Two of them were silk wings, and the

02:23:31.440 --> 02:23:33.239
other is a hive wing who can't be mind

02:23:33.239 --> 02:23:34.920
controlled, and she's on our side.

02:23:34.979 --> 02:23:38.819
Now, I mean, we kind of dragged her onto

02:23:38.819 --> 02:23:40.920
our side, but I think she was heading

02:23:40.920 --> 02:23:41.700
that way anyhow.

02:23:41.760 --> 02:23:44.280
Technically, she's really on this one

02:23:44.280 --> 02:23:47.520
particular Silkwings side, but he might

02:23:47.520 --> 02:23:50.340
be with us, unless Belladonna has ruined

02:23:50.340 --> 02:23:50.520
it.

02:23:50.579 --> 02:23:53.040
But the point is, they were fine and

02:23:53.040 --> 02:23:53.639
wanted to help.

02:23:53.700 --> 02:23:56.280
Well, agreed to help.

02:23:56.340 --> 02:23:59.159
And couldn't say no, but basically

02:23:59.159 --> 02:24:01.920
agreeable-ish sort of way.

02:24:01.979 --> 02:24:05.579
I'm going to have a heart attack, Willow

02:24:05.579 --> 02:24:05.879
said.

02:24:05.940 --> 02:24:08.579
So you met some allies and came straight

02:24:08.579 --> 02:24:11.579
home safely, without being seen.

02:24:11.639 --> 02:24:13.260
Well?

02:24:13.440 --> 02:24:16.260
No, Sandu admitted.

02:24:16.319 --> 02:24:17.520
We...

02:24:17.520 --> 02:24:20.040
Kind of stole the book of Clear Sight.

02:24:20.159 --> 02:24:21.479
What?

02:24:21.540 --> 02:24:24.840
Willow shrieked, sending an explosion of

02:24:24.840 --> 02:24:26.940
sleeping birds catapulting into the night

02:24:26.940 --> 02:24:27.299
sky.

02:24:27.360 --> 02:24:32.219
Sandu said. reaching to cover Willow's

02:24:32.219 --> 02:24:32.639
snout.

02:24:32.700 --> 02:24:34.620
We had to have it.

02:24:34.680 --> 02:24:37.379
We needed to take away Wasp's secret

02:24:37.379 --> 02:24:40.379
knowledge of the future, or at least we

02:24:40.379 --> 02:24:42.719
needed to know what it says too, right?

02:24:42.780 --> 02:24:45.479
Isn't that one of Sequoia's eternal

02:24:45.479 --> 02:24:47.639
arguments that we can't do anything

02:24:47.639 --> 02:24:50.520
against WASP because she has this all

02:24:50.520 --> 02:24:52.559
knowing book to warn her of our every

02:24:52.559 --> 02:24:52.979
move?

02:24:52.979 --> 02:24:57.719
Yes, but that's insane, Willow said.

02:24:57.780 --> 02:25:00.000
That book must have been the most heavily

02:25:00.000 --> 02:25:01.920
guarded object in the most heavily

02:25:01.920 --> 02:25:03.479
guarded hive in Pentala.

02:25:03.540 --> 02:25:08.040
It was, Sundew said, but not anymore.

02:25:08.100 --> 02:25:09.420
Ha ha.

02:25:09.479 --> 02:25:10.799
Now it is mine.

02:25:10.860 --> 02:25:14.340
No way, Willow said.

02:25:14.459 --> 02:25:15.719
You really did it?

02:25:15.780 --> 02:25:17.219
Did you read it?

02:25:17.280 --> 02:25:20.219
Are you now the most all knowing dragon

02:25:20.219 --> 02:25:21.059
in all the land?

02:25:21.120 --> 02:25:23.459
The future is spread out before you?

02:25:23.520 --> 02:25:25.860
All the secrets of what's to come?

02:25:25.920 --> 02:25:29.219
So, said Sundew.

02:25:29.280 --> 02:25:30.180
No.

02:25:30.239 --> 02:25:31.620
No.

02:25:31.680 --> 02:25:35.760
Turns out, the whole book Mystique was an

02:25:35.760 --> 02:25:36.479
enormous lie.

02:25:36.540 --> 02:25:40.020
Clearsight did leave a few prophecies, but

02:25:40.020 --> 02:25:42.000
they petered out over a 1000 years ago.

02:25:42.059 --> 02:25:46.079
Nothing WASP told us was true.

02:25:46.139 --> 02:25:49.139
Willow stared at her in the moonlight.

02:25:49.200 --> 02:25:50.579
Wow.

02:25:50.639 --> 02:25:52.139
She said softly.

02:25:52.200 --> 02:25:54.479
Didn't you once guess that?

02:25:54.540 --> 02:25:56.100
A couple years ago?

02:25:56.159 --> 02:25:59.100
You said, what if none of it is real?

02:25:59.159 --> 02:26:01.799
What if there never was a clear sight?

02:26:01.860 --> 02:26:04.139
And everything we've been told about the

02:26:04.139 --> 02:26:07.260
book was made up by a sinister hive wing

02:26:07.260 --> 02:26:08.159
somewhere along the way?

02:26:08.219 --> 02:26:10.319
Did I say that?

02:26:10.379 --> 02:26:13.559
Sundew flicked her wings, pleased with

02:26:13.559 --> 02:26:14.159
herself?

02:26:14.219 --> 02:26:16.440
Well, I was half right.

02:26:16.500 --> 02:26:19.739
It looks like clear sight was real, but

02:26:19.739 --> 02:26:22.260
so were the lies, and the sinister hive

02:26:22.260 --> 02:26:24.120
wings all over the last 1000 years.

02:26:24.180 --> 02:26:27.059
Willow took a deep breath.

02:26:27.120 --> 02:26:29.760
Okay, she said.

02:26:29.819 --> 02:26:31.559
So that's amazing.

02:26:31.620 --> 02:26:35.100
You snuck into the hive, into the temple

02:26:35.100 --> 02:26:38.879
stole the book, got back out again, and

02:26:38.879 --> 02:26:41.340
came straight home without being seen

02:26:41.340 --> 02:26:42.420
right?

02:26:42.479 --> 02:26:45.600
Um, said Zundoo.

02:26:45.659 --> 02:26:46.559
No.

02:26:46.620 --> 02:26:48.180
No?

02:26:48.239 --> 02:26:49.559
Sundoo.

02:26:49.620 --> 02:26:51.000
Not exactly.

02:26:51.059 --> 02:26:53.879
I mean, we did sneak into the hive

02:26:53.879 --> 02:26:56.459
without being seen, and the temple.

02:26:56.459 --> 02:26:59.520
The actual stealing and running away went

02:26:59.520 --> 02:27:01.440
Less well.

02:27:01.500 --> 02:27:05.639
By all the trees, Willow said, you were

02:27:05.639 --> 02:27:07.440
seen, sundew.

02:27:07.500 --> 02:27:09.180
Tell me you weren't seen.

02:27:09.299 --> 02:27:11.340
Her wings were shaking.

02:27:11.399 --> 02:27:13.680
Sundu grabbed her front talons again.

02:27:13.739 --> 02:27:15.299
It's all right.

02:27:15.360 --> 02:27:16.860
I'm here, aren't I?

02:27:16.920 --> 02:27:18.540
I made it back safely.

02:27:18.600 --> 02:27:21.719
I even brought our new allies with us.

02:27:21.780 --> 02:27:23.879
One of them can shoot fire.

02:27:23.940 --> 02:27:27.059
A fire blasting dragon and the book of

02:27:27.059 --> 02:27:27.780
Clearsight.

02:27:27.840 --> 02:27:30.239
That's a pretty successful mission, don't

02:27:30.239 --> 02:27:30.540
you think?

02:27:30.600 --> 02:27:33.719
But Hive Wings saw you.

02:27:33.780 --> 02:27:36.000
So they know we're not extinct.

02:27:36.059 --> 02:27:40.260
Oh, maybe no one will believe them, Willow

02:27:40.260 --> 02:27:40.559
said.

02:27:40.620 --> 02:27:44.639
It'll be like seeing ghosts or scavengers

02:27:44.639 --> 02:27:47.700
a dramatic story to tell at parties, but

02:27:47.700 --> 02:27:50.399
no one takes it seriously, right?

02:27:50.459 --> 02:27:52.559
Maybe the others will think they were

02:27:52.559 --> 02:27:53.340
hallucinating.

02:27:53.399 --> 02:27:58.200
Having wild visions, imagination run amok

02:27:58.200 --> 02:27:59.879
and everyone will laugh at them and say

02:27:59.879 --> 02:28:00.959
ha ha.

02:28:01.020 --> 02:28:01.979
Leaf Wings.

02:28:02.040 --> 02:28:04.200
They're all dead, you goof.

02:28:04.260 --> 02:28:07.139
We scoff at your hilarious story, and

02:28:07.139 --> 02:28:09.059
definitely are not even remotely

02:28:09.059 --> 02:28:11.159
considering going out with an army to

02:28:11.159 --> 02:28:13.799
hunt down and kill the rest of the tribe

02:28:13.799 --> 02:28:15.420
because there aren't any left.

02:28:15.479 --> 02:28:17.340
Leaf wings.

02:28:17.399 --> 02:28:17.879
How amusing.

02:28:17.940 --> 02:28:19.079
This could happen.

02:28:19.139 --> 02:28:21.180
That's probably how it will be.

02:28:21.239 --> 02:28:24.600
I mean, how many hive wings saw you after

02:28:24.600 --> 02:28:25.020
all.

02:28:25.079 --> 02:28:27.000
One, two?

02:28:27.059 --> 02:28:29.760
Sundews grunched up her face.

02:28:29.819 --> 02:28:31.260
Three?

02:28:31.319 --> 02:28:33.120
Willow said nervously.

02:28:33.180 --> 02:28:37.020
More like, All of them?

02:28:37.079 --> 02:28:38.459
Sundu admitted.

02:28:38.520 --> 02:28:39.959
All of them?

02:28:40.079 --> 02:28:44.639
You have got to stop shouting, Sundu

02:28:44.639 --> 02:28:44.940
said.

02:28:45.000 --> 02:28:47.819
Your village isn't that far away, and I'm

02:28:47.819 --> 02:28:49.440
not up to dealing with any dragons who

02:28:49.440 --> 02:28:50.280
aren't you tonight.

02:28:50.340 --> 02:28:53.819
You can't possibly mean all of them

02:28:53.819 --> 02:28:55.079
Willow said.

02:28:55.139 --> 02:28:59.700
Well, Sundoo said, in the sense that

02:28:59.700 --> 02:29:01.559
Queen Wasp possessed the entire

02:29:01.559 --> 02:29:04.920
population of Wasp Pive, summoned them to

02:29:04.920 --> 02:29:07.860
the temple, had them all attack us, and

02:29:07.860 --> 02:29:10.260
then watched me escape, I think

02:29:10.260 --> 02:29:12.659
technically, yes, all of them is pretty

02:29:12.659 --> 02:29:13.319
accurate.

02:29:13.379 --> 02:29:14.940
Oh wait.

02:29:15.000 --> 02:29:18.600
Actually, only all of the ones in Wasp

02:29:18.600 --> 02:29:20.219
Hive, not the other hives.

02:29:20.340 --> 02:29:23.879
So that's only one out of 9 hives, like

02:29:23.879 --> 02:29:27.420
so really, only one ninth of the hive

02:29:27.420 --> 02:29:28.200
wing population.

02:29:28.260 --> 02:29:29.159
See?

02:29:29.219 --> 02:29:29.879
You were right.

02:29:29.940 --> 02:29:31.680
Not all of them after all.

02:29:31.739 --> 02:29:36.059
All the dragons in Wasp Hive.

02:29:36.180 --> 02:29:38.040
Willow said faintly.

02:29:38.100 --> 02:29:42.180
With the queen in their heads. attacked

02:29:42.180 --> 02:29:45.479
you and saw you, and watched you escape

02:29:45.479 --> 02:29:47.399
with the book of Clear sight.

02:29:47.520 --> 02:29:50.520
Yes, Sundew said.

02:29:50.579 --> 02:29:51.659
Now you've got it?

02:29:51.719 --> 02:29:54.780
It was a very impressive escape if I do

02:29:54.780 --> 02:29:55.500
say so myself.

02:29:55.559 --> 02:30:01.500
So, Willow said, basically, we are all

02:30:01.500 --> 02:30:01.979
going to die.

02:30:02.100 --> 02:30:05.340
No, Sandu cried.

02:30:05.399 --> 02:30:07.860
She reached up and brushed her claws

02:30:07.860 --> 02:30:09.420
gently along Willow's face.

02:30:09.479 --> 02:30:11.639
No, we're not Willow.

02:30:11.700 --> 02:30:13.260
We're going to win this time.

02:30:13.319 --> 02:30:16.500
How can you possibly think that?

02:30:16.559 --> 02:30:18.899
Even if we could win eventually?

02:30:18.959 --> 02:30:23.219
War means dead leaf wings, especially war

02:30:23.219 --> 02:30:26.159
against Queen Wasp, and we can't win

02:30:26.159 --> 02:30:28.559
because nothing is different from last

02:30:28.559 --> 02:30:31.079
time except there are fewer leaf wings to

02:30:31.079 --> 02:30:31.739
start with.

02:30:31.799 --> 02:30:35.219
That's not true, Sundoo said.

02:30:35.280 --> 02:30:37.139
Things are completely different.

02:30:37.200 --> 02:30:40.260
She started counting off on her talons.

02:30:40.379 --> 02:30:42.360
We have a flame silk.

02:30:42.420 --> 02:30:45.059
We have the book of Clearsight, and know

02:30:45.059 --> 02:30:45.780
the truth about it.

02:30:45.840 --> 02:30:48.899
Our half of the tribe has been preparing

02:30:48.899 --> 02:30:51.719
for war for 50 years, and have lots of

02:30:51.719 --> 02:30:52.319
new weapons.

02:30:52.379 --> 02:30:55.260
The silk wings are restless and depressed

02:30:55.260 --> 02:30:56.040
and unhappy.

02:30:56.100 --> 02:30:59.760
I mean, not all of them, I think, but

02:30:59.760 --> 02:31:02.639
enough to have formed an underground anti

02:31:01.440 --> 02:31:04.620
hive wing movement, so they won't just

02:31:04.620 --> 02:31:06.899
blindly go along with a wasp this time.

02:31:06.959 --> 02:31:10.260
Also, the hive wings will be too scared

02:31:10.260 --> 02:31:12.180
to come fight us in the poison jungle.

02:31:12.239 --> 02:31:16.260
And we know the secret of Queen Wasp's

02:31:16.260 --> 02:31:16.979
mind control.

02:31:17.040 --> 02:31:20.399
She let go of Willow and tugged the vine

02:31:20.399 --> 02:31:21.479
out of its pouch.

02:31:21.719 --> 02:31:22.799
It's a plant.

02:31:22.860 --> 02:31:24.239
This plant.

02:31:24.299 --> 02:31:27.719
She must eat it or something, and she

02:31:27.719 --> 02:31:30.000
injects it into hive wing eggs to put the

02:31:30.000 --> 02:31:31.920
dragons inside under her power.

02:31:31.979 --> 02:31:36.059
She held it out, and Willow sniffed the

02:31:36.059 --> 02:31:38.879
leaves, then ran one claw lightly along

02:31:38.879 --> 02:31:40.020
the prickled stem.

02:31:40.020 --> 02:31:43.440
I don't know it, she said.

02:31:43.500 --> 02:31:46.620
If it grew here, surely you'd be able to

02:31:46.620 --> 02:31:48.239
sense it, wouldn't you?

02:31:48.299 --> 02:31:49.920
I tried.

02:31:50.040 --> 02:31:52.559
Sundew had been trying.

02:31:52.620 --> 02:31:54.360
From the moment they stepped into the

02:31:54.360 --> 02:31:54.780
jungle.

02:31:54.840 --> 02:31:57.479
She'd been sending her leaf speak out

02:31:57.479 --> 02:32:00.059
into the jungle, tracing along route

02:32:00.059 --> 02:32:02.159
pathways and tangles of underground

02:32:02.159 --> 02:32:03.959
Mycelia as far as she could go.

02:32:04.020 --> 02:32:08.399
A couple of the oldest trees did that, hmm

02:32:08.399 --> 02:32:10.079
thing they do when something seems

02:32:10.079 --> 02:32:10.680
familiar.

02:32:10.739 --> 02:32:13.500
And once I thought I heard a relative of

02:32:13.500 --> 02:32:15.780
this plant echo back from somewhere far

02:32:15.780 --> 02:32:16.139
away.

02:32:16.200 --> 02:32:17.579
But I lost it.

02:32:17.639 --> 02:32:19.979
And none of the trees could tell me where

02:32:19.979 --> 02:32:20.399
it might be.

02:32:20.459 --> 02:32:24.059
There are dragons we could ask in my

02:32:24.059 --> 02:32:25.920
village, Willow said.

02:32:25.979 --> 02:32:29.280
She hesitated, then touched her forehead

02:32:29.280 --> 02:32:31.200
to sundews for the length of 5

02:32:31.200 --> 02:32:31.860
heartbeats.

02:32:31.920 --> 02:32:35.040
I think you need to come to my village

02:32:35.040 --> 02:32:35.520
Sundew.

02:32:35.579 --> 02:32:37.260
I think it's time.

02:32:37.319 --> 02:32:40.620
Time to meet the Sapwings.

02:32:40.620 --> 02:32:42.899
To see how the other tribe lives.

02:32:43.020 --> 02:32:45.420
What it's like to be a village of

02:32:45.420 --> 02:32:47.940
cowardly dragons instead of warriors for

02:32:47.940 --> 02:32:48.420
justice.

02:32:48.479 --> 02:32:51.719
Time to finally see Willow's home.

02:32:51.780 --> 02:32:53.819
I can't.

02:32:53.879 --> 02:32:56.040
Sundu let go and stepped back.

02:32:56.159 --> 02:32:58.860
I'd be betraying my tribe.

02:32:58.920 --> 02:33:01.200
Belladonna would be furious.

02:33:01.260 --> 02:33:03.540
And wouldn't you get in trouble?

02:33:03.600 --> 02:33:07.079
Not as much as you will, Willow said.

02:33:07.139 --> 02:33:11.879
I mean, a lot of dragons will be mad, but

02:33:11.879 --> 02:33:13.979
we have to tell Queen Sequoia about all

02:33:13.979 --> 02:33:14.219
this.

02:33:14.280 --> 02:33:15.540
Don't you see?

02:33:15.600 --> 02:33:18.840
She needs to know about the book, and the

02:33:18.840 --> 02:33:19.620
flame silk.

02:33:19.739 --> 02:33:23.100
Sundew started to interrupt, then stopped

02:33:23.100 --> 02:33:25.799
herself, but Willow knew her too well to

02:33:25.799 --> 02:33:26.159
miss that.

02:33:26.219 --> 02:33:27.840
What?

02:33:27.899 --> 02:33:29.700
Is there something else?

02:33:29.700 --> 02:33:30.719
she asked.

02:33:30.780 --> 02:33:36.120
Maybe, one more thing, Sandu said.

02:33:36.180 --> 02:33:38.760
She'll probably want to know about the

02:33:38.760 --> 02:33:40.200
hive we burned down.

02:33:40.260 --> 02:33:44.040
Willow opened her mouth, then closed it

02:33:44.040 --> 02:33:47.100
again, then opened it again, like a

02:33:47.100 --> 02:33:49.620
really adorable but totally flabbergasted

02:33:49.620 --> 02:33:51.059
dragon trap in the rain.

02:33:51.479 --> 02:33:54.299
Sorry, I didn't get to that part.

02:33:54.360 --> 02:33:55.680
Sundew said.

02:33:55.739 --> 02:33:58.379
Hemlock took a few other dragons to burn

02:33:58.379 --> 02:33:59.520
down one of the hives.

02:33:59.579 --> 02:34:02.459
I only saw it from a distance, but there

02:34:02.459 --> 02:34:03.420
was a lot of smoke.

02:34:03.479 --> 02:34:05.700
So, I think it must have worked.

02:34:05.760 --> 02:34:09.780
She decided not to mention burning wasps

02:34:09.780 --> 02:34:10.799
greenhouses as well.

02:34:10.860 --> 02:34:13.139
She'd let that come up later.

02:34:13.200 --> 02:34:16.020
At a more natural and hopefully less

02:34:16.020 --> 02:34:18.120
tense point in the conversation.

02:34:18.360 --> 02:34:21.840
Then we don't have any time, Willow said

02:34:21.899 --> 02:34:23.940
taking a step back toward her village.

02:34:24.000 --> 02:34:27.840
I thought we'd have a moment to plan, but

02:34:27.840 --> 02:34:29.700
that's an act of war, Sandu.

02:34:29.819 --> 02:34:32.459
WASP is probably on her way here right

02:34:32.459 --> 02:34:35.459
now, with the whole brain washed hive

02:34:35.459 --> 02:34:36.540
wing army behind her.

02:34:36.600 --> 02:34:40.559
Doubtful, Sandu scoffed, and I still

02:34:40.559 --> 02:34:41.340
can't.

02:34:41.459 --> 02:34:45.659
I agree with Willow. interjected a new

02:34:45.659 --> 02:34:45.899
voice.

02:34:46.020 --> 02:34:49.920
An enormous, long necked leaf wing

02:34:49.920 --> 02:34:52.860
emerged from the trees behind Willow

02:34:52.860 --> 02:34:54.360
ducking her head to avoid the lower

02:34:54.360 --> 02:34:57.180
branches, and dangling dragon traps.

02:34:57.239 --> 02:35:00.840
Her tail was scarred with claw marks, and

02:35:00.840 --> 02:35:02.700
dragged in the pond as she came toward

02:35:02.700 --> 02:35:02.879
them.

02:35:02.940 --> 02:35:07.079
Sundew saw, with horrified fascination

02:35:07.079 --> 02:35:10.260
that she was missing an ear and half of

02:35:10.260 --> 02:35:11.280
one of her horns.

02:35:11.280 --> 02:35:14.040
This was a dragon who had been in battle

02:35:14.040 --> 02:35:15.120
and fought hard.

02:35:15.180 --> 02:35:18.180
This was also a dragon who had been alive

02:35:18.180 --> 02:35:19.860
for a very long time.

02:35:19.920 --> 02:35:22.799
A dragon who could still remember the

02:35:22.799 --> 02:35:25.319
ancient forests before the tree wars.

02:35:25.379 --> 02:35:28.979
And from the way she walked, and the way

02:35:28.979 --> 02:35:31.319
she tilted her head to look down at them

02:35:31.319 --> 02:35:33.180
and the way she held her wings like

02:35:33.180 --> 02:35:36.479
majestic jewels, this was a royal

02:35:36.479 --> 02:35:37.020
dragon.

02:35:37.079 --> 02:35:40.020
The Royal Dragon.

02:35:40.079 --> 02:35:44.219
Hello, Belladonna's daughter, said Queen

02:35:44.219 --> 02:35:45.000
Sequoia.

02:35:45.059 --> 02:35:47.879
Willow is correct that I need to know

02:35:47.879 --> 02:35:48.360
everything.

02:35:48.420 --> 02:35:52.440
I think, it is high time you joined the

02:35:52.440 --> 02:35:53.700
real Leaf Wings.

02:35:53.760 --> 02:35:58.200
Chapter 8.

02:35:58.260 --> 02:36:02.219
Your majesty, willow gasped.

02:36:02.280 --> 02:36:04.979
Sundew found herself bowing her head

02:36:04.979 --> 02:36:07.260
instinctively, and she quickly jerked it

02:36:07.260 --> 02:36:07.680
back up again.

02:36:07.739 --> 02:36:11.459
She was a true leaf wing, or a poison

02:36:11.459 --> 02:36:14.040
wing, as the Sapwings called them, and

02:36:14.040 --> 02:36:16.680
more important, she was sundew, and she

02:36:16.680 --> 02:36:17.639
bowed to nobody.

02:36:17.700 --> 02:36:21.000
Queen Sequoia smiled faintly.

02:36:21.059 --> 02:36:24.059
You have exactly your grandmother's

02:36:24.059 --> 02:36:25.139
stubborn expression.

02:36:25.200 --> 02:36:27.360
I saw it many times during the tree

02:36:27.360 --> 02:36:27.840
wars.

02:36:27.899 --> 02:36:29.879
My grandmother?

02:36:29.940 --> 02:36:32.700
Sundew echoed, surprised.

02:36:32.760 --> 02:36:34.559
She'd heard of her, of course, all the

02:36:34.559 --> 02:36:37.260
time, but she'd died before sundew

02:36:37.260 --> 02:36:37.680
hatched.

02:36:37.739 --> 02:36:40.799
She was my best general.

02:36:40.920 --> 02:36:42.659
Sequoia side.

02:36:42.719 --> 02:36:46.500
And my most loyal, until I finally gave

02:36:46.500 --> 02:36:48.059
her an order she couldn't follow.

02:36:48.180 --> 02:36:49.860
Give up and run away.

02:36:49.920 --> 02:36:52.979
That's when she left me and started your

02:36:52.979 --> 02:36:53.639
group instead.

02:36:53.700 --> 02:36:57.780
She turned, offhandedly sweeping a noisy

02:36:57.780 --> 02:37:00.239
toad into the pond with one talon, where

02:37:00.239 --> 02:37:01.920
it sank with a startled glorp.

02:37:01.979 --> 02:37:05.340
Come, we will be safer in the village.

02:37:05.399 --> 02:37:07.379
I shouldn't.

02:37:07.440 --> 02:37:09.000
I should turn and run home.

02:37:09.059 --> 02:37:13.079
Belladonna will lose her mind if she

02:37:13.079 --> 02:37:15.059
discovers I've run to the sapwings to

02:37:15.059 --> 02:37:15.899
tell tales on her.

02:37:15.959 --> 02:37:19.079
She wasn't sure whether it was the idea

02:37:19.079 --> 02:37:22.079
of Belladonna's apoplectic face, or the

02:37:22.079 --> 02:37:24.959
air of authority around Queen Sequoia, but

02:37:24.959 --> 02:37:26.579
she found herself following the queen

02:37:26.579 --> 02:37:27.659
with Willow by her side.

02:37:27.719 --> 02:37:30.299
Did you tell her about me?

02:37:30.360 --> 02:37:32.159
Sundu hissed at Willow.

02:37:32.219 --> 02:37:33.299
Did you bring her here?

02:37:33.360 --> 02:37:37.979
Sundew, Willow said patiently, in the

02:37:37.979 --> 02:37:39.600
tone of a teacher reminding her students

02:37:39.600 --> 02:37:42.360
that 3+3 always equals 6.

02:37:42.479 --> 02:37:45.420
I wouldn't do that, and you know it.

02:37:45.479 --> 02:37:48.000
She did sort of know it.

02:37:48.059 --> 02:37:49.979
But there was a part of her that was

02:37:49.979 --> 02:37:51.479
still mad that she'd been caught like

02:37:51.479 --> 02:37:53.700
this, and she wanted someone to blame.

02:37:53.760 --> 02:37:55.500
Sundu scowled.

02:37:55.559 --> 02:37:58.139
I can blame Queen Sequoia.

02:37:58.200 --> 02:38:01.020
What was she doing spying on us?

02:38:01.079 --> 02:38:01.680
How dare she?

02:38:01.739 --> 02:38:04.379
I will definitely tell her how I feel

02:38:04.379 --> 02:38:06.719
about that in as mad a voice as I like.

02:38:06.780 --> 02:38:09.180
I don't have to treat her like a queen.

02:38:09.239 --> 02:38:11.159
I can yell at her if I want to.

02:38:11.219 --> 02:38:12.360
Maybe not.

02:38:12.479 --> 02:38:14.639
Right this 2nd, maybe later.

02:38:14.700 --> 02:38:16.680
When I feel like it.

02:38:16.739 --> 02:38:18.899
Don't be scared.

02:38:18.959 --> 02:38:20.579
Willow whispered.

02:38:20.639 --> 02:38:21.899
I'm not scared.

02:38:21.959 --> 02:38:25.319
Sundew snapped. loud enough for the queen

02:38:25.319 --> 02:38:26.700
to glance over her shoulder at them.

02:38:26.760 --> 02:38:28.680
She lowered her voice.

02:38:28.739 --> 02:38:31.079
When am I ever scared?

02:38:31.139 --> 02:38:33.000
What do I have to be scared of?

02:38:33.059 --> 02:38:35.579
She's just a big dragon.

02:38:35.639 --> 02:38:36.600
She doesn't even have an army.

02:38:36.659 --> 02:38:37.920
I'm not scared.

02:38:37.979 --> 02:38:41.520
Willow stopped and took one of Sundew's

02:38:41.520 --> 02:38:42.000
talons.

02:38:42.000 --> 02:38:44.760
In the dark, Sundew felt the smooth

02:38:44.760 --> 02:38:47.159
familiar weight of the jade frog come to

02:38:47.159 --> 02:38:47.940
rest in her palm.

02:38:48.000 --> 02:38:51.239
She tucked it back into her pouch, brushed

02:38:51.239 --> 02:38:53.280
her wing along willows, and felt her

02:38:53.280 --> 02:38:54.780
heart rate start to calm down.

02:38:54.840 --> 02:38:57.239
I'm sorry she followed me.

02:38:57.299 --> 02:38:59.459
But I'm not sorry you're coming to the

02:38:59.459 --> 02:39:02.159
village, Willow said, starting to walk

02:39:02.159 --> 02:39:02.579
again.

02:39:02.639 --> 02:39:04.979
There's something I can't wait to show

02:39:04.979 --> 02:39:05.219
you.

02:39:05.340 --> 02:39:08.760
You did say you had something to tell me

02:39:08.760 --> 02:39:10.920
Sundu remembered it sheepishly.

02:39:10.979 --> 02:39:11.940
What is it?

02:39:12.000 --> 02:39:16.079
I mean, I think it's exciting, Willow

02:39:16.079 --> 02:39:16.379
said.

02:39:16.440 --> 02:39:19.860
Maybe not as much to you, after all you

02:39:19.860 --> 02:39:21.959
are almost dying and war starting.

02:39:22.020 --> 02:39:23.040
But guess what?

02:39:23.100 --> 02:39:25.920
There are strangers in our village, 3 of

02:39:25.920 --> 02:39:28.260
them, and you'll never believe where 2 of

02:39:28.260 --> 02:39:29.340
them come from.

02:39:29.399 --> 02:39:30.180
It's amazing.

02:39:30.239 --> 02:39:31.799
Wait until you see them.

02:39:31.860 --> 02:39:34.799
Is one of them a silkwing?

02:39:34.860 --> 02:39:35.819
Sundu asked.

02:39:35.879 --> 02:39:37.979
One of the silk wings I brought to the

02:39:37.979 --> 02:39:39.479
rainforest is looking for a sister.

02:39:39.540 --> 02:39:42.299
She stopped herself just in time from

02:39:42.299 --> 02:39:45.180
adding, and our spies thought you might

02:39:45.180 --> 02:39:45.540
have her.

02:39:45.600 --> 02:39:48.840
She was quite sure that Queen Sequoia was

02:39:48.840 --> 02:39:50.579
listening to them, even though she was

02:39:50.579 --> 02:39:51.479
several steps ahead.

02:39:51.540 --> 02:39:55.440
Actually, yes, the 3rd one is a silk wing

02:39:55.440 --> 02:39:56.340
Willow said.

02:39:56.399 --> 02:39:59.040
Aw, I hope we can reunite them.

02:39:59.100 --> 02:40:03.120
Sundu flicked her wings, surprised and

02:40:03.120 --> 02:40:03.780
pleased.

02:40:03.959 --> 02:40:05.760
What were the chances that Luna would

02:40:05.760 --> 02:40:08.340
have blown ashore here, and survived and

02:40:08.340 --> 02:40:10.559
been rescued by the sapwings, before

02:40:10.559 --> 02:40:13.139
sundew's tribe mates or the dragon traps

02:40:13.139 --> 02:40:15.719
or the cobra lilies or the snakes got

02:40:15.719 --> 02:40:15.959
her?

02:40:16.020 --> 02:40:18.479
That would solve a few problems.

02:40:18.540 --> 02:40:20.940
If we could give Luna to Belladonna

02:40:20.940 --> 02:40:23.879
instead of blue, a willing flame silk

02:40:23.879 --> 02:40:25.920
ally would be a much better bargain than

02:40:25.920 --> 02:40:28.200
hostages who have to be coerced into

02:40:28.200 --> 02:40:28.680
helping us.

02:40:28.739 --> 02:40:31.200
Then blue and cricket could do whatever

02:40:31.200 --> 02:40:32.159
they want to do next.

02:40:32.219 --> 02:40:34.620
And if they don't want to be my friends

02:40:34.620 --> 02:40:36.239
anymore, that's just fine.

02:40:36.299 --> 02:40:39.659
But first, Sequoia would have to agree to

02:40:39.659 --> 02:40:40.440
give up Luna.

02:40:40.500 --> 02:40:43.079
What if she has her own plans for using

02:40:43.079 --> 02:40:43.979
flame silk?

02:40:44.100 --> 02:40:45.780
And the other two?

02:40:45.840 --> 02:40:46.739
she asked.

02:40:46.799 --> 02:40:48.479
You'll see.

02:40:48.540 --> 02:40:51.780
Willow flashed her an unmistakable grin

02:40:51.780 --> 02:40:54.059
sparkling even in the darkness under the

02:40:54.059 --> 02:40:54.420
trees.

02:40:54.479 --> 02:40:57.659
Sundew felt a funny shiver in her chest

02:40:57.659 --> 02:40:59.819
as though her heart had shaken raindrops

02:40:59.819 --> 02:41:00.360
off its wings.

02:41:00.420 --> 02:41:04.079
Even after everything I just told her

02:41:04.079 --> 02:41:06.719
even though she thinks I've endangered

02:41:06.719 --> 02:41:09.239
her tribe, and restarted a war she

02:41:09.239 --> 02:41:09.719
doesn't want.

02:41:09.780 --> 02:41:11.579
She still loves me.

02:41:11.639 --> 02:41:15.840
In Zendu's life, love mostly came in the

02:41:15.840 --> 02:41:17.760
form of yelling and criticism and

02:41:17.760 --> 02:41:18.239
judgment.

02:41:18.299 --> 02:41:21.780
Her parents loved her and showed it by

02:41:21.780 --> 02:41:23.399
telling her everything she did wrong

02:41:23.399 --> 02:41:25.799
correcting her mistakes, and starting

02:41:25.799 --> 02:41:27.479
shouting matches whenever they were the

02:41:27.479 --> 02:41:28.799
slightest bit aggravated.

02:41:28.860 --> 02:41:31.739
It still confused her sometimes when

02:41:31.739 --> 02:41:32.819
Willow did none of that.

02:41:32.879 --> 02:41:35.040
It was confusing her right now.

02:41:35.100 --> 02:41:37.379
Wasn't Willow angry at her?

02:41:37.440 --> 02:41:40.379
She'd never seen Willow get angry.

02:41:40.440 --> 02:41:42.840
It was kind of unsettling, honestly.

02:41:42.959 --> 02:41:46.260
Sundew had thought about it for years, and

02:41:46.260 --> 02:41:47.819
eventually came to the conclusion that

02:41:47.819 --> 02:41:49.920
Willow must just hide her anger really

02:41:49.920 --> 02:41:50.219
well.

02:41:50.280 --> 02:41:53.040
But did that mean it would erupt one day

02:41:53.040 --> 02:41:55.620
all of a sudden, and burn down their

02:41:55.620 --> 02:41:56.040
relationship.

02:41:56.100 --> 02:41:58.979
These were the things Sundew worried

02:41:58.979 --> 02:41:59.459
about at night.

02:41:59.520 --> 02:42:03.479
She'd expected to find a wall or barrier

02:42:03.479 --> 02:42:06.120
or fence, like the one she'd built around

02:42:06.120 --> 02:42:09.120
her own village, but instead, the sapwing

02:42:09.120 --> 02:42:11.040
village crept up around them, like

02:42:11.040 --> 02:42:11.760
termites.

02:42:11.819 --> 02:42:14.520
The 1st sign was that all the dragon

02:42:14.520 --> 02:42:15.299
traps disappeared.

02:42:15.360 --> 02:42:18.000
Sundew had never walked through a stretch

02:42:18.000 --> 02:42:19.979
of jungle with no dragon traps in it.

02:42:20.040 --> 02:42:23.760
Nor, she realized, were there any sundews

02:42:23.760 --> 02:42:27.000
or pitcher plants, or anything else that

02:42:27.000 --> 02:42:27.780
ate dragons.

02:42:27.840 --> 02:42:30.780
Sundew was looking so carefully for

02:42:30.780 --> 02:42:33.180
carnivorous plants that she missed the

02:42:33.180 --> 02:42:36.000
1st few leaf houses, but then they were

02:42:36.000 --> 02:42:37.620
overhead, and it was dark.

02:42:37.680 --> 02:42:40.680
Suddenly she noticed a cluster of

02:42:40.680 --> 02:42:42.780
phosphorescent moss in a tree up ahead

02:42:42.780 --> 02:42:45.780
and as they approached, she realized it

02:42:45.780 --> 02:42:47.819
lit up the interior of a kind of leaf

02:42:47.819 --> 02:42:50.159
globe tree house perched in the higher

02:42:50.159 --> 02:42:50.579
branches.

02:42:50.639 --> 02:42:54.780
Whoa, she said, stopping without

02:42:54.780 --> 02:42:55.500
realizing it.

02:42:55.559 --> 02:42:58.559
Willow nudged her forward again, and then

02:42:58.559 --> 02:43:00.540
Sundew spotted more and more of them.

02:43:00.600 --> 02:43:02.940
The trees were full of the leaf houses

02:43:02.940 --> 02:43:05.819
not so different from the nests in her

02:43:05.819 --> 02:43:08.459
village, except that they were in the sky

02:43:08.459 --> 02:43:11.100
covered in leaves, and much bigger than

02:43:11.100 --> 02:43:11.760
her own.

02:43:12.059 --> 02:43:14.280
She guessed each would fit at least 6

02:43:14.280 --> 02:43:15.239
dragons comfortably.

02:43:15.360 --> 02:43:17.459
At least of the ones she saw.

02:43:17.520 --> 02:43:20.280
Now she heard voices too.

02:43:20.340 --> 02:43:22.799
Here and there the murmur of dragons

02:43:22.799 --> 02:43:25.319
talking, and not far away, someone

02:43:25.319 --> 02:43:26.700
singing a lullaby.

02:43:26.760 --> 02:43:29.520
She heard a dragonette chirping, and his

02:43:29.520 --> 02:43:31.200
parents sending him back to bed.

02:43:31.260 --> 02:43:33.540
She heard the soft rustle of dragons

02:43:33.540 --> 02:43:36.180
leaping from tree to tree, possibly

02:43:36.180 --> 02:43:37.559
tracking the queen's movements.

02:43:37.680 --> 02:43:42.000
And mine, she guessed, her claws curling

02:43:42.000 --> 02:43:42.719
into the dirt.

02:43:42.780 --> 02:43:45.479
Willow and Sequoia spread their wings at

02:43:45.479 --> 02:43:47.879
the same time, and Sundew followed suit.

02:43:47.940 --> 02:43:50.579
They leaped into the air and led her to

02:43:50.579 --> 02:43:52.799
the largest tree house of all, a

02:43:52.799 --> 02:43:54.600
structure that spiraled all the way

02:43:54.600 --> 02:43:57.420
around an enormous baobab, with several

02:43:57.420 --> 02:44:00.299
levels, balconies, and rooms built out

02:44:00.299 --> 02:44:01.979
along the massive branches.

02:44:02.040 --> 02:44:04.079
Sundew couldn't see all of it in the dark

02:44:04.079 --> 02:44:06.180
but from the night blooms that were lit

02:44:06.180 --> 02:44:08.700
up in a few rooms, she was able to see

02:44:08.700 --> 02:44:11.280
dark, purple, and white clematis vines

02:44:11.280 --> 02:44:13.620
twining all around the columns and bright

02:44:13.620 --> 02:44:15.780
red trumpet creepers dangling from the

02:44:15.780 --> 02:44:16.200
ceilings.

02:44:16.260 --> 02:44:19.620
They landed in a room on the top level

02:44:19.620 --> 02:44:22.319
with a smooth, polished wood floor that

02:44:22.319 --> 02:44:24.180
must have taken a lot of work to make so

02:44:24.180 --> 02:44:25.260
slippery and shiny.

02:44:25.319 --> 02:44:28.860
A young leaf wing was waiting for them

02:44:28.860 --> 02:44:31.260
curled on a mahogany throne, sewing

02:44:31.260 --> 02:44:33.000
sheets of speckled paper together to make

02:44:33.000 --> 02:44:33.239
a book.

02:44:33.360 --> 02:44:36.659
She looked a little older than Sundo, with

02:44:36.659 --> 02:44:38.760
large brown eyes and deft, dark green

02:44:38.760 --> 02:44:39.360
claws.

02:44:39.420 --> 02:44:43.620
Hazel, Queen Sequoia said reprovingly, as

02:44:43.620 --> 02:44:44.639
the dragon looked up.

02:44:44.700 --> 02:44:47.219
What have I told you about bookmaking at

02:44:47.219 --> 02:44:47.520
night?

02:44:47.579 --> 02:44:51.479
It's an efficient use of my time.

02:44:51.540 --> 02:44:54.180
Hazel guessed, with a mischievous grin.

02:44:54.299 --> 02:44:56.459
You will ruin your eyes.

02:44:56.579 --> 02:44:59.219
The queen tugged the pages out of her

02:44:59.219 --> 02:45:02.280
talons as Hazel protested, and then we'll

02:45:02.280 --> 02:45:03.899
either have to steal glasses from the

02:45:03.899 --> 02:45:06.959
hive wings or have a blind queen, and I

02:45:06.959 --> 02:45:08.159
don't like either of those plans.

02:45:08.219 --> 02:45:11.700
Sundew gave Willow a startled look.

02:45:11.819 --> 02:45:14.879
That's the queen's great granddaughter.

02:45:15.000 --> 02:45:18.299
Willow whispered, Princess Hazel, next in

02:45:18.299 --> 02:45:19.139
line for the throne.

02:45:19.200 --> 02:45:21.059
Oh, right.

02:45:21.120 --> 02:45:23.700
Willow had mentioned Hazel a few times

02:45:23.700 --> 02:45:26.100
mostly in the context of why Queen

02:45:26.100 --> 02:45:28.799
Sequoia refused to restart the train wars

02:45:28.799 --> 02:45:31.020
something about not wanting to lose any

02:45:31.020 --> 02:45:31.739
more dragons.

02:45:31.799 --> 02:45:35.399
I think glasses are cute, Hazel said

02:45:35.399 --> 02:45:37.979
breezily, and we won't have to steal them

02:45:37.979 --> 02:45:39.540
if the scouts are right about the poison

02:45:39.540 --> 02:45:41.819
wings capturing a real flame silk today.

02:45:41.879 --> 02:45:45.840
Hazel, the queen said in a warning tone.

02:45:45.899 --> 02:45:47.819
This is sundoo.

02:45:47.879 --> 02:45:49.559
Belladonna's daughter.

02:45:49.620 --> 02:45:51.420
Hazel's jaw dropped.

02:45:51.479 --> 02:45:54.479
She stared at Sundew for a long, awestruck

02:45:54.479 --> 02:45:54.780
moment.

02:45:54.840 --> 02:45:57.600
That's how you were supposed to react

02:45:57.600 --> 02:45:59.940
when you met me, Sundu whispered to

02:45:59.940 --> 02:46:00.299
Willow.

02:46:00.360 --> 02:46:02.520
These sundew?

02:46:02.579 --> 02:46:04.860
Willow gasped, widening her eyes

02:46:04.860 --> 02:46:05.639
theatrically.

02:46:05.700 --> 02:46:08.940
The one and only sundew, the one who

02:46:08.940 --> 02:46:11.100
almost slew the great and terrible

02:46:11.100 --> 02:46:13.319
grasshopper stealing frog menace of the

02:46:13.319 --> 02:46:13.739
jungle?

02:46:13.799 --> 02:46:16.500
Sundew bopped her on the nose with her

02:46:16.500 --> 02:46:18.719
tail, and Willow dissolved in giggles.

02:46:18.780 --> 02:46:20.819
Am I allowed to say hi?

02:46:20.879 --> 02:46:22.860
Hazel asked her great grandmother.

02:46:22.920 --> 02:46:27.000
Yes, of course, Queen Sequoia said, a

02:46:27.000 --> 02:46:29.520
little impatiently, especially if it gets

02:46:29.520 --> 02:46:30.420
you off my throne.

02:46:30.479 --> 02:46:31.739
Go on.

02:46:31.799 --> 02:46:34.799
Chairs are for old dragon bones.

02:46:34.860 --> 02:46:36.959
Not bendy little saplings like you.

02:46:37.079 --> 02:46:40.620
Hazel bounded off the throne and skidded

02:46:40.620 --> 02:46:42.120
across the floor to Sunday's feet.

02:46:42.180 --> 02:46:44.280
Hello, I'm Hazel.

02:46:44.340 --> 02:46:45.540
Sorry, you know that.

02:46:45.600 --> 02:46:47.520
I hear about you all the time.

02:46:47.579 --> 02:46:49.860
Belladonna thinks you should be queen

02:46:49.860 --> 02:46:50.940
instead of me.

02:46:51.000 --> 02:46:51.540
Do you think so too?

02:46:51.600 --> 02:46:53.579
She's so scary.

02:46:53.639 --> 02:46:55.920
Sorry, I know she's your mom.

02:46:55.979 --> 02:46:58.620
Ah, I'm saying all the wrong things.

02:46:58.680 --> 02:47:01.139
She drew herself up and did a rather

02:47:01.139 --> 02:47:03.659
impressive imitation of Queen Sequoia's

02:47:03.659 --> 02:47:04.379
regal expression.

02:47:04.440 --> 02:47:07.139
Even her voice went hilariously fancy.

02:47:07.200 --> 02:47:10.319
Welcome to the Leaf Wing Village.

02:47:10.379 --> 02:47:12.420
We are delighted you could join us.

02:47:12.479 --> 02:47:13.860
T?

02:47:13.860 --> 02:47:17.219
Oh, you don't have to be queen face hazel

02:47:17.219 --> 02:47:18.840
for Sundu, Willow said.

02:47:18.899 --> 02:47:20.879
Yes, she does.

02:47:20.940 --> 02:47:24.239
Queen Sequoia called, just as Hazel was

02:47:24.239 --> 02:47:25.559
starting to relax her wings.

02:47:25.620 --> 02:47:28.200
She snapped them back into elegant arches

02:47:28.200 --> 02:47:28.799
immediately.

02:47:28.860 --> 02:47:32.399
It's good practice, and none of us know

02:47:32.399 --> 02:47:34.440
Belladonna's daughter as well as you

02:47:34.440 --> 02:47:35.639
apparently do, Willow.

02:47:35.700 --> 02:47:41.639
Oh, I, we met um, Willow stammered.

02:47:41.700 --> 02:47:45.120
By accident, Sundew said, it was my

02:47:45.120 --> 02:47:45.420
fault.

02:47:45.479 --> 02:47:47.639
Not that we have anything to apologize

02:47:47.639 --> 02:47:48.059
for.

02:47:48.120 --> 02:47:49.920
Whoever said we couldn't know each

02:47:49.920 --> 02:47:50.159
other.

02:47:50.219 --> 02:47:52.620
I mean, that would be a stupid rule.

02:47:52.680 --> 02:47:56.040
I believe that is Belladonna's rule.

02:47:56.100 --> 02:47:59.579
Sequoia said, rubbing her forehead, isn't

02:47:59.579 --> 02:47:59.700
it?

02:47:59.760 --> 02:48:02.700
No fraternizing between poison wings and

02:48:02.700 --> 02:48:03.479
leaf wings.

02:48:03.540 --> 02:48:05.940
We are not poison wings.

02:48:05.940 --> 02:48:07.200
Sundew snapped.

02:48:07.260 --> 02:48:09.659
And even if it is her rule, it's still

02:48:09.659 --> 02:48:11.940
stupid, and she didn't even make it until

02:48:11.940 --> 02:48:14.459
after I met Willow, and she can't tell me

02:48:14.459 --> 02:48:16.440
what to do or who to like anyway.

02:48:16.500 --> 02:48:17.700
It's none of her business.

02:48:17.760 --> 02:48:21.780
It's a little bit of her business, Sequoia

02:48:21.780 --> 02:48:24.299
pointed out, as both your mother and your

02:48:24.299 --> 02:48:24.840
commander.

02:48:24.899 --> 02:48:27.239
But I'm not actually remotely interested

02:48:27.239 --> 02:48:30.479
in you and Willow or how you met, or why

02:48:30.479 --> 02:48:32.399
she's been sneaking out and staring

02:48:32.399 --> 02:48:34.620
wistfully at an empty pond for the last

02:48:34.620 --> 02:48:35.280
several nights.

02:48:35.340 --> 02:48:38.819
She pointed one long claw at sundew.

02:48:38.879 --> 02:48:41.579
I heard you say something about a book.

02:48:41.639 --> 02:48:46.440
A flame silk, and a burned hive, the full

02:48:46.440 --> 02:48:46.920
story.

02:48:47.040 --> 02:48:48.000
Now.

02:48:48.059 --> 02:48:51.059
Sundew didn't have to tell her

02:48:51.059 --> 02:48:54.600
technically, this wasn't her queen, if

02:48:54.600 --> 02:48:57.360
the tribe had officially split in two, but

02:48:57.360 --> 02:48:59.579
then again, if she had to choose between

02:48:59.579 --> 02:49:02.040
obeying this queen or following her

02:49:02.040 --> 02:49:04.439
mother's orders, she kind of liked the

02:49:04.439 --> 02:49:06.659
idea of choosing this one, and she did

02:49:06.659 --> 02:49:08.280
need help identifying the vine.

02:49:08.399 --> 02:49:10.860
If she was still following Cricket's daft

02:49:10.860 --> 02:49:13.260
plan of trying to unbrainwash the hive

02:49:13.260 --> 02:49:13.559
wings.

02:49:13.680 --> 02:49:18.299
Plus, it would make Belladonna so mad, and

02:49:18.299 --> 02:49:19.319
she fully deserved it.

02:49:19.379 --> 02:49:22.559
So Sundu told the queen everything.

02:49:22.620 --> 02:49:25.440
The whole story about leaving the jungle

02:49:25.440 --> 02:49:27.840
hiding in the greenhouse, meeting blue

02:49:27.840 --> 02:49:30.780
and cricket, stealing the book, rescuing

02:49:30.780 --> 02:49:33.780
blue, sneaking into jewel hive, finding

02:49:33.780 --> 02:49:36.239
the chrysalis, spreading the truth about

02:49:36.239 --> 02:49:39.059
the mind control and the book, cricket

02:49:39.059 --> 02:49:40.559
kidnapping and egg for some reason

02:49:40.559 --> 02:49:43.319
escaping, figuring out that the mind

02:49:43.319 --> 02:49:46.020
control was connected to a plant, watching

02:49:46.020 --> 02:49:48.959
bloodworm hive burn from a distance, and

02:49:48.959 --> 02:49:50.760
then taking advantage of the tribe's

02:49:50.760 --> 02:49:52.860
distraction to burn down wasp's

02:49:52.860 --> 02:49:54.540
greenhouse of mind control plants.

02:49:54.600 --> 02:49:59.280
And then we came home, she finished, and

02:49:59.280 --> 02:50:00.840
nobody followed us and everything is

02:50:00.840 --> 02:50:01.079
fine.

02:50:01.139 --> 02:50:02.940
Mission accomplished.

02:50:03.000 --> 02:50:03.719
All good.

02:50:03.780 --> 02:50:04.979
Vengeance on track.

02:50:05.040 --> 02:50:07.979
The queen leaned back into her throne

02:50:07.979 --> 02:50:09.180
with a weary expression.

02:50:09.239 --> 02:50:12.840
Sundew wondered how old she was, as old

02:50:12.840 --> 02:50:13.620
as she looked.

02:50:13.680 --> 02:50:17.219
The tree wars were only 50 years ago, and

02:50:17.219 --> 02:50:19.379
she'd been a young queen when Wasp tried

02:50:19.379 --> 02:50:22.379
to steal her power and usurp her tribe, if

02:50:22.379 --> 02:50:24.299
Sundew remembered her history correctly.

02:50:24.360 --> 02:50:28.260
I can't believe Belladonna did it.

02:50:28.319 --> 02:50:32.459
Queen Sequoia said in a thin voice, after

02:50:32.459 --> 02:50:35.040
all our conversations, after everything

02:50:35.040 --> 02:50:38.340
I've said to her, her mother was so loyal

02:50:38.340 --> 02:50:41.579
but that viper, she snapped her jaw shut

02:50:41.579 --> 02:50:43.620
suddenly and took a deep breath through

02:50:43.620 --> 02:50:45.180
her nostrils.

02:50:45.239 --> 02:50:46.379
Great grandmother?

02:50:46.440 --> 02:50:47.399
Hazel said.

02:50:47.520 --> 02:50:49.440
Do not talk to me.

02:50:49.500 --> 02:50:52.079
I am calming down, Sequoia barked.

02:50:52.139 --> 02:50:54.840
The 3 younger leaf wings looked at one

02:50:54.840 --> 02:50:56.760
another, then back to the queen.

02:50:56.819 --> 02:50:59.940
Sequoia was staring so hard at a knot on

02:50:59.940 --> 02:51:02.040
the end of her throne, that Sundu thought

02:51:02.040 --> 02:51:03.180
it might burst into flames.

02:51:03.239 --> 02:51:07.260
She kept breathing in and out, extremely

02:51:07.260 --> 02:51:08.760
loudly. through her nose.

02:51:08.819 --> 02:51:10.799
Are you?

02:51:10.860 --> 02:51:12.180
Hazel started.

02:51:12.239 --> 02:51:14.760
No, I am not.

02:51:14.879 --> 02:51:16.739
Sequoia growled.

02:51:16.799 --> 02:51:17.760
Shush.

02:51:17.819 --> 02:51:20.100
Hazel sighed.

02:51:20.159 --> 02:51:22.860
This could take a minute, she whispered

02:51:22.860 --> 02:51:23.639
to Sundu.

02:51:23.700 --> 02:51:25.440
Does this happen a lot?

02:51:25.500 --> 02:51:27.239
Sundu whispered back.

02:51:27.299 --> 02:51:29.760
Only when she's really mad.

02:51:29.819 --> 02:51:32.760
Usually she can squash it pretty well

02:51:32.760 --> 02:51:35.219
without this whole theatrical interlude.

02:51:35.280 --> 02:51:37.559
I can still hear you.

02:51:37.620 --> 02:51:40.260
Sequoia thumbed to the side of her throne

02:51:40.260 --> 02:51:40.799
with her tail.

02:51:40.860 --> 02:51:45.360
I am trying to count until I feel calmer

02:51:45.360 --> 02:51:47.399
and less like murdering everyone.

02:51:47.459 --> 02:51:50.819
Sendu tilted her head at the queen.

02:51:50.879 --> 02:51:52.319
Count?

02:51:52.440 --> 02:51:54.719
she echoed, glancing at Willow.

02:51:54.780 --> 02:51:56.879
That's why all her meetings with

02:51:56.879 --> 02:51:58.319
Belladonna takes so long.

02:51:58.440 --> 02:51:59.700
Hazel joked.

02:51:59.760 --> 02:52:02.819
Because she has to take deep breaths and

02:52:02.819 --> 02:52:04.620
count to calm herself down after

02:52:04.620 --> 02:52:07.020
everything her mom says, or else she

02:52:07.020 --> 02:52:08.219
might end up strangling her.

02:52:08.280 --> 02:52:11.700
She should try, Sundoo said.

02:52:11.760 --> 02:52:13.739
Why doesn't she just yell at her?

02:52:13.739 --> 02:52:15.059
Or us?

02:52:15.120 --> 02:52:17.760
Willow gave her an alarmed look.

02:52:17.819 --> 02:52:19.799
I don't want her to yell at us.

02:52:19.860 --> 02:52:23.280
But then maybe she'll feel better, Sundew

02:52:23.280 --> 02:52:23.760
pointed out.

02:52:23.819 --> 02:52:27.120
Well, I wouldn't, Willow said.

02:52:27.239 --> 02:52:30.000
I'd feel awful, and I bet she would too.

02:52:30.059 --> 02:52:32.340
Does yelling make you feel better?

02:52:32.399 --> 02:52:34.379
It's only ever made me feel worse.

02:52:34.440 --> 02:52:38.879
Oh my goodness, Sandu said, I must hear

02:52:38.879 --> 02:52:40.739
every story about you yelling at someone

02:52:40.739 --> 02:52:41.459
right this minute.

02:52:41.520 --> 02:52:44.520
Willow grunged your nose at her.

02:52:44.579 --> 02:52:46.139
I was very little.

02:52:46.260 --> 02:52:49.200
It was only once, and I still feel guilty

02:52:49.200 --> 02:52:49.500
about it.

02:52:49.620 --> 02:52:54.000
Well, I'm sure they deserved it, Sundoo

02:52:54.000 --> 02:52:54.719
said loyally.

02:52:54.780 --> 02:52:57.600
Great grandmother tries very hard not to

02:52:57.600 --> 02:52:58.739
yell at her subjects.

02:52:58.860 --> 02:53:01.799
Hazel said, in her queen face voice.

02:53:01.860 --> 02:53:05.459
She was a more impulsive, angry dragon

02:53:05.459 --> 02:53:07.920
back during the tree wars, and she has

02:53:07.920 --> 02:53:09.600
come to believe it got several of her

02:53:09.600 --> 02:53:10.559
subjects killed.

02:53:10.559 --> 02:53:14.100
She has made an effort to become a wiser

02:53:14.100 --> 02:53:17.280
calmer ruler, thanks in large part to the

02:53:17.280 --> 02:53:19.260
implementation of this counting to 10

02:53:19.260 --> 02:53:19.799
strategy.

02:53:19.860 --> 02:53:24.420
She must be past 10 by now, Sundu said.

02:53:24.479 --> 02:53:26.879
I could have counted to 900 in this

02:53:26.879 --> 02:53:27.059
time.

02:53:27.120 --> 02:53:31.079
Not with a trio of aggravating twigs

02:53:31.079 --> 02:53:33.180
chattering like magpies in the

02:53:33.180 --> 02:53:33.719
background.

02:53:33.719 --> 02:53:36.420
Queen Sequoia interjected sternly.

02:53:36.479 --> 02:53:38.280
She took another deep breath.

02:53:38.340 --> 02:53:40.500
I am calm.

02:53:40.559 --> 02:53:42.000
Everything is fine.

02:53:42.059 --> 02:53:46.799
I just want to say, Sandu blurted, that I

02:53:46.799 --> 02:53:48.600
for one, am very glad you were an angry

02:53:48.600 --> 02:53:50.940
dragon when the tree war started, because

02:53:50.940 --> 02:53:53.219
it meant you fought back against wasps

02:53:53.219 --> 02:53:55.799
power grab, and didn't just roll over for

02:53:55.799 --> 02:53:57.299
her like monarch did.

02:53:57.360 --> 02:53:59.879
I'm glad you fought for our tribe and

02:53:59.879 --> 02:54:01.020
protected us from her.

02:54:01.079 --> 02:54:03.600
I would hate for the leaf wings to be

02:54:03.600 --> 02:54:05.760
stuck where the spineless silk wings are

02:54:05.760 --> 02:54:06.120
right now.

02:54:06.180 --> 02:54:08.819
So thank you for being a mad dragon, and

02:54:08.819 --> 02:54:10.860
I say keep it up, and let's go fight some

02:54:10.860 --> 02:54:11.159
more.

02:54:11.219 --> 02:54:14.219
The queen gazed down at her for a long

02:54:14.219 --> 02:54:16.559
moment, and then a flicker of a smile

02:54:16.559 --> 02:54:17.280
crossed her face.

02:54:17.340 --> 02:54:21.059
I think Belladonna made a mistake leaving

02:54:21.059 --> 02:54:22.739
you out of our meetings for all this

02:54:22.739 --> 02:54:22.979
time.

02:54:23.040 --> 02:54:24.360
She said.

02:54:24.420 --> 02:54:27.120
You're considerably more persuasive than

02:54:27.120 --> 02:54:27.899
she is.

02:54:27.959 --> 02:54:31.200
Sendu fluffed up the frill along her

02:54:31.200 --> 02:54:32.280
spine and beamed.

02:54:32.340 --> 02:54:34.260
Take that, Belladonna.

02:54:34.319 --> 02:54:36.899
I knew I should have been invited, just

02:54:36.899 --> 02:54:37.739
like I've been saying.

02:54:37.799 --> 02:54:42.659
But no, said Queen Sequoia.

02:54:42.719 --> 02:54:44.940
Sundew deflated as she went on.

02:54:45.000 --> 02:54:48.360
My leaf wings are not getting involved in

02:54:48.360 --> 02:54:48.899
another war.

02:54:48.959 --> 02:54:51.239
Do we have a choice?

02:54:51.360 --> 02:54:52.500
Willow asked.

02:54:52.559 --> 02:54:55.920
Won't wasp come after all of us now, after

02:54:55.920 --> 02:54:57.600
what happened to bloodworm hive?

02:54:57.659 --> 02:55:01.139
I suspect she'll be even angrier about

02:55:01.139 --> 02:55:04.079
her greenhouse than the hive, Sequoia

02:55:04.079 --> 02:55:06.600
said thoughtfully, especially if that was

02:55:06.600 --> 02:55:10.139
her only supply of this mystery plant, and

02:55:10.139 --> 02:55:11.579
she needs it to control her tribe.

02:55:11.639 --> 02:55:13.979
Let me see that vine.

02:55:14.040 --> 02:55:17.100
Sundu pulled out the cutting, which was

02:55:17.100 --> 02:55:18.719
looking a little the worse for wear after

02:55:18.719 --> 02:55:20.459
going in and out of her pouch several

02:55:20.459 --> 02:55:20.940
times.

02:55:20.940 --> 02:55:23.459
She stepped forward and draped it over

02:55:23.459 --> 02:55:25.680
Sequoia's outstretched talons.

02:55:25.739 --> 02:55:28.379
Something happened to the Queen's face.

02:55:28.440 --> 02:55:31.620
It was fast and hard to catch in the dim

02:55:31.620 --> 02:55:34.500
phosphorescent light, but Sundew thought

02:55:34.500 --> 02:55:37.139
she saw recognition and horror flashed

02:55:37.139 --> 02:55:37.920
through the queen's eyes.

02:55:37.979 --> 02:55:40.139
Her claws closed around the vine

02:55:40.139 --> 02:55:43.020
compulsively, crushing it slightly, and

02:55:43.020 --> 02:55:44.399
then she released it again and took

02:55:44.399 --> 02:55:45.420
another deep breath.

02:55:45.479 --> 02:55:48.899
You know it, Sundu said.

02:55:48.959 --> 02:55:50.459
You've seen this vine before.

02:55:50.520 --> 02:55:52.920
I'm...

02:55:52.920 --> 02:55:56.159
Not sure, Sequoia said.

02:55:56.219 --> 02:55:58.079
She rose abruptly to her feet.

02:55:58.139 --> 02:56:00.479
I need to consult my books.

02:56:00.540 --> 02:56:03.299
Go away and come back after dawn.

02:56:03.360 --> 02:56:06.780
All 3 of you, she added with a stern look

02:56:06.780 --> 02:56:07.379
at Hazel.

02:56:07.440 --> 02:56:10.620
Sundew kind of wanted to ask for the vine

02:56:10.620 --> 02:56:12.659
back, but she had a pretty strong feeling

02:56:12.659 --> 02:56:15.180
the queen would say no, and then what was

02:56:15.180 --> 02:56:15.540
she do?

02:56:15.600 --> 02:56:17.700
Try to wrestle it out of the massive

02:56:17.700 --> 02:56:18.959
dragon's talons?

02:56:19.020 --> 02:56:21.540
I'll get the truth out of her when we

02:56:21.540 --> 02:56:22.200
come back, though.

02:56:22.260 --> 02:56:25.020
She thought, as they all took a step back

02:56:25.020 --> 02:56:26.399
toward the edge of the balcony.

02:56:26.459 --> 02:56:28.739
She definitely knows that plant.

02:56:28.799 --> 02:56:31.680
Can I take Sundu to meet the new

02:56:31.680 --> 02:56:32.280
dragons?

02:56:32.340 --> 02:56:33.360
Willow asked.

02:56:33.420 --> 02:56:37.500
Yes, yes, the Queen answered, waving them

02:56:37.500 --> 02:56:37.680
off.

02:56:37.739 --> 02:56:40.200
They're asleep, you nut?

02:56:40.260 --> 02:56:42.540
Hazel pointed out with a granite willow

02:56:42.540 --> 02:56:45.000
that made son do absolutely wild with

02:56:45.000 --> 02:56:45.659
jealousy.

02:56:45.659 --> 02:56:49.020
Then we'll just peek at them, Willow

02:56:49.020 --> 02:56:49.319
said.

02:56:49.440 --> 02:56:50.639
Come on, Sundoo.

02:56:50.700 --> 02:56:53.219
The new dragons, it turned out.

02:56:53.280 --> 02:56:55.020
We're only a few levels down the same

02:56:55.020 --> 02:56:58.260
tree, in 2 side by side interior rooms

02:56:58.260 --> 02:57:00.420
that Sundew noticed were not prison

02:57:00.420 --> 02:57:01.500
cells.

02:57:01.559 --> 02:57:01.920
Exactly.

02:57:01.979 --> 02:57:04.500
But we're not exactly wide open to the

02:57:04.500 --> 02:57:05.520
rest of the village either.

02:57:05.579 --> 02:57:08.100
She also couldn't help but notice the

02:57:08.100 --> 02:57:10.680
vines of thorns and toxic sap that wound

02:57:10.680 --> 02:57:13.620
around the doorways, or the 4 leaf wings

02:57:13.620 --> 02:57:16.860
stationed nearby. casually playing pick

02:57:16.860 --> 02:57:18.840
up twigs in the hall in the middle of the

02:57:18.840 --> 02:57:19.079
night.

02:57:19.200 --> 02:57:22.139
They gave Willow and Sundew suspicious

02:57:22.139 --> 02:57:24.540
looks, but went back to their game with a

02:57:24.540 --> 02:57:26.040
shrug when they saw Hazel with them.

02:57:26.100 --> 02:57:30.000
The silk wing is in there, Willow

02:57:30.000 --> 02:57:32.280
whispered, pointing to the 1st doorway.

02:57:32.340 --> 02:57:34.979
Sundew peered inside, her heart

02:57:34.979 --> 02:57:36.059
thumping.

02:57:36.120 --> 02:57:38.040
This whole time, she'd felt confident

02:57:38.040 --> 02:57:39.059
that Luna was all right.

02:57:39.120 --> 02:57:41.819
Her sense of Luna, from the short time

02:57:41.819 --> 02:57:44.219
they'd been together, was that Luna could

02:57:44.219 --> 02:57:45.540
absolutely take care of herself.

02:57:45.659 --> 02:57:48.600
But Blue and Swordtail had worried so

02:57:48.600 --> 02:57:51.420
much and so incessantly, that it must

02:57:51.420 --> 02:57:53.280
have rubbed off on her a little, because

02:57:53.280 --> 02:57:55.620
now she felt a tremor of weird excitement

02:57:55.620 --> 02:57:57.120
as she peered into the dark room.

02:57:57.239 --> 02:58:01.739
Luna, at last, safe and sound, so

02:58:01.739 --> 02:58:03.360
everyone could shut up about her and

02:58:03.360 --> 02:58:06.719
focus on the mission, except it wasn't

02:58:06.719 --> 02:58:07.020
Luna.

02:58:07.139 --> 02:58:09.899
She couldn't see the sleeping silk wing

02:58:09.899 --> 02:58:12.120
very clearly, but she could see that the

02:58:12.120 --> 02:58:14.760
wings were a dark color, maybe blue or

02:58:14.760 --> 02:58:17.520
purple, not the pale pearly green that

02:58:17.520 --> 02:58:20.280
Luna's were, and there was no flame silk

02:58:20.280 --> 02:58:22.379
glow from this silk wings wrists.

02:58:22.440 --> 02:58:24.059
What's wrong?

02:58:24.120 --> 02:58:25.979
Willow said softly.

02:58:26.040 --> 02:58:28.440
Not the dragon we're looking for.

02:58:28.500 --> 02:58:31.139
Sundew shook her head with a sigh.

02:58:31.200 --> 02:58:33.479
Blue was going to be disappointed.

02:58:33.540 --> 02:58:35.340
Sortell was going to be worse.

02:58:35.399 --> 02:58:38.280
He was going to be super annoying about

02:58:38.280 --> 02:58:38.459
it.

02:58:38.579 --> 02:58:40.920
But Luna had to be all right.

02:58:40.979 --> 02:58:42.899
She must have just landed.

02:58:43.139 --> 02:58:44.639
Somewhere else.

02:58:44.700 --> 02:58:46.620
Where did you find her?

02:58:46.739 --> 02:58:50.159
Trapped in Origula, not far from the

02:58:50.159 --> 02:58:51.719
border, Willow said.

02:58:51.780 --> 02:58:54.000
She's lucky we got there before it ate

02:58:54.000 --> 02:58:54.180
her.

02:58:54.239 --> 02:58:57.059
I wonder what a silk wing was doing

02:58:57.059 --> 02:58:58.799
inside the poison jungle.

02:58:58.920 --> 02:59:00.840
Sundew said thoughtfully.

02:59:00.899 --> 02:59:03.420
Escaping from hive wings, I think.

02:59:03.479 --> 02:59:04.620
Willow said.

02:59:04.680 --> 02:59:06.659
Now, come see the others.

02:59:06.780 --> 02:59:09.959
She tugged on Sunday's elbow and led her

02:59:09.959 --> 02:59:10.860
to the 2nd doorway.

02:59:10.920 --> 02:59:13.559
Sundew found herself holding her breath

02:59:13.559 --> 02:59:14.520
as she looked inside.

02:59:14.639 --> 02:59:17.940
For a moment, she didn't know what she

02:59:17.940 --> 02:59:18.239
was saying.

02:59:18.299 --> 02:59:22.319
There were 2 dragons, asleep back to back

02:59:22.319 --> 02:59:24.540
with the bigger one's wing tented over

02:59:24.540 --> 02:59:25.200
the smaller one.

02:59:25.260 --> 02:59:28.079
The smaller ones seemed to be greenish

02:59:28.079 --> 02:59:30.659
like a leaf wing, but the wing she could

02:59:30.659 --> 02:59:33.540
see was an odd shape, not leaf like at

02:59:33.540 --> 02:59:36.959
all, and the other dragon was, not

02:59:36.959 --> 02:59:37.440
green.

02:59:37.500 --> 02:59:39.000
Maybe blue?

02:59:39.059 --> 02:59:40.739
Like a silk wing.

02:59:40.799 --> 02:59:43.260
But with only 2 wings?

02:59:43.319 --> 02:59:47.219
Strangest of all, they were both kind of

02:59:47.219 --> 02:59:47.879
glowing.

02:59:47.940 --> 02:59:49.920
She squinted at them.

02:59:49.979 --> 02:59:51.659
Yep.

02:59:51.719 --> 02:59:54.299
Little patterns in their scales had a

02:59:54.299 --> 02:59:56.819
faint glow to them, all along their wings

02:59:56.819 --> 02:59:58.739
and across their snouts and down their

02:59:58.739 --> 03:00:01.020
tails, as though they had rolled in

03:00:01.020 --> 03:00:03.840
phosphorescent moss, except it seemed to

03:00:03.840 --> 03:00:04.799
be really part of them.

03:00:04.860 --> 03:00:07.379
What are they?

03:00:07.440 --> 03:00:10.139
She breathed, awestruck.

03:00:10.200 --> 03:00:14.459
They call themselves sea wings, Willow

03:00:14.459 --> 03:00:14.940
whispered.

03:00:15.000 --> 03:00:17.639
And they come from the distant kingdoms.

03:00:17.700 --> 03:00:22.200
Chapter 9.

03:00:22.260 --> 03:00:25.739
Willow and Sundew spent the rest of the

03:00:25.739 --> 03:00:27.840
night in a pile of leaves in Hazel's

03:00:27.840 --> 03:00:28.860
room.

03:00:28.920 --> 03:00:30.659
Willow offered to take Sundew back to her

03:00:30.659 --> 03:00:33.000
own home, but she was clearly nervous

03:00:33.000 --> 03:00:35.159
about waking her dad, and explaining

03:00:35.159 --> 03:00:36.780
sundew to him in the middle of the

03:00:36.780 --> 03:00:37.020
night.

03:00:37.079 --> 03:00:39.780
So they decided it would be easier to

03:00:39.780 --> 03:00:42.000
sleep in the queen's tree house and deal

03:00:42.000 --> 03:00:43.559
with grown ups in the morning instead.

03:00:43.620 --> 03:00:46.739
With daylight to help, and after the

03:00:46.739 --> 03:00:48.059
queen spoke to them.

03:00:48.120 --> 03:00:51.059
Sundu fell asleep almost as soon as she

03:00:51.059 --> 03:00:53.760
lay down next to Willow, the long days of

03:00:53.760 --> 03:00:55.979
flying and stress catching up to her all

03:00:55.979 --> 03:00:56.280
at once.

03:00:56.340 --> 03:00:58.680
She had a moment to breathe.

03:00:58.739 --> 03:01:01.680
A moment of feeling Willow's tranquil

03:01:01.680 --> 03:01:04.079
heartbeat through their scales, a moment

03:01:04.079 --> 03:01:06.299
to think, Stay on guard.

03:01:06.420 --> 03:01:07.860
I don't know this village.

03:01:07.979 --> 03:01:11.159
There are strangers all around me, except

03:01:11.159 --> 03:01:11.639
Willow.

03:01:11.700 --> 03:01:14.579
I have Willow, right beside me.

03:01:14.639 --> 03:01:17.520
And then she was out, in a darkness

03:01:17.520 --> 03:01:18.780
beyond dreams.

03:01:18.840 --> 03:01:21.600
She slept well past dawn.

03:01:21.659 --> 03:01:24.299
As she realized when she finally awoke to

03:01:24.299 --> 03:01:26.879
find the sun shining cheerfully, already

03:01:26.879 --> 03:01:28.500
ambling up the curve of the sky.

03:01:28.559 --> 03:01:32.219
She sat up quickly and blinked at Hazel

03:01:32.219 --> 03:01:34.379
who was perched in her hammock, reading a

03:01:34.379 --> 03:01:34.559
book.

03:01:34.620 --> 03:01:38.760
Hazel's room was bright and airy, studded

03:01:38.760 --> 03:01:40.979
with open windows and balconies so the

03:01:40.979 --> 03:01:43.260
breeze flew through it, but sheltered

03:01:43.260 --> 03:01:45.180
from the rain by an overhanging roof of

03:01:45.180 --> 03:01:46.379
large, round leaves.

03:01:46.440 --> 03:01:50.040
Three desks took up half the room, even

03:01:50.040 --> 03:01:51.600
when they were shoved into the corner to

03:01:51.600 --> 03:01:53.700
make space for the leaf pile sundew had

03:01:53.700 --> 03:01:54.000
slept in.

03:01:54.059 --> 03:01:56.700
Each desk was covered in a mess of

03:01:56.700 --> 03:01:58.680
bookbinding supplies made from jungle

03:01:58.680 --> 03:02:01.319
ingredients, some kind of sap glue

03:02:01.319 --> 03:02:03.540
dripping over the sides of its pot, tree

03:02:03.540 --> 03:02:06.479
fiber threads draped everywhere, and bark

03:02:06.479 --> 03:02:09.180
for the covers scattered about, dyed in

03:02:09.180 --> 03:02:11.819
colors from deep berry red to summery

03:02:11.819 --> 03:02:14.340
daisy yellow, to a swirl of purple and

03:02:14.340 --> 03:02:15.180
pearl white.

03:02:15.239 --> 03:02:18.840
Bright red trumpet creeper flowers poked

03:02:18.840 --> 03:02:20.879
through the roof, and Hazel had hung

03:02:20.879 --> 03:02:23.040
small paper dragons and clouds from every

03:02:23.040 --> 03:02:25.620
leaf stem, so there was a little blizzard

03:02:25.620 --> 03:02:26.579
of them flying overhead.

03:02:26.639 --> 03:02:30.120
Sundew blinked again, and looked over her

03:02:30.120 --> 03:02:31.860
shoulder to see Willow still asleep

03:02:31.860 --> 03:02:32.399
beside her.

03:02:32.459 --> 03:02:35.579
Willow had one wing flung out to the side

03:02:35.579 --> 03:02:38.399
the way a baby dragonette might sleep, and

03:02:38.399 --> 03:02:39.899
her cheek was pillowed on her front

03:02:39.899 --> 03:02:41.879
talons in a cute smushy way.

03:02:41.940 --> 03:02:44.340
Focus, undo.

03:02:44.459 --> 03:02:47.340
Or pause for a moment to be happy.

03:02:47.399 --> 03:02:49.440
That's what Willow would say to do.

03:02:49.500 --> 03:02:52.500
After all the craziness with silk wings

03:02:52.500 --> 03:02:55.079
and sneaking through hives, and dealing

03:02:55.079 --> 03:02:57.000
with strangers, I am back with her at

03:02:57.000 --> 03:02:59.100
last, where I can just be myself.

03:02:59.159 --> 03:03:01.379
She sighed.

03:03:01.440 --> 03:03:03.719
All right, moment over.

03:03:03.780 --> 03:03:07.979
Hazel, she said, and the princess finally

03:03:07.979 --> 03:03:08.940
looked up from her book.

03:03:09.000 --> 03:03:11.280
Aren't we late to meet your great

03:03:11.280 --> 03:03:11.879
grandmother?

03:03:11.940 --> 03:03:13.979
Weren't we supposed to be there at dawn?

03:03:14.040 --> 03:03:16.559
Hazel's wings lifted and bell in a

03:03:16.559 --> 03:03:16.920
shrug.

03:03:16.979 --> 03:03:19.559
She sent a messenger that she wasn't

03:03:19.559 --> 03:03:19.920
ready yet.

03:03:19.979 --> 03:03:22.020
She'll call us when she wants us.

03:03:22.079 --> 03:03:22.739
Don't worry.

03:03:22.799 --> 03:03:24.899
Sundew frowned at her.

03:03:24.959 --> 03:03:27.540
And what am I supposed to do until then?

03:03:27.600 --> 03:03:30.059
Just sit around this village like an

03:03:30.059 --> 03:03:31.620
orchid waiting to be stomped?

03:03:31.680 --> 03:03:33.479
Dragons will be looking for me.

03:03:33.540 --> 03:03:35.280
Also, I have things to do.

03:03:35.340 --> 03:03:38.700
She thought of blue and cricket, and a

03:03:38.700 --> 03:03:41.219
bumblebee and swordtail, would they worry

03:03:41.219 --> 03:03:41.520
about her?

03:03:41.579 --> 03:03:44.700
Or would they think she'd abandoned them

03:03:44.700 --> 03:03:46.860
as would be typical of her according to

03:03:46.860 --> 03:03:47.579
them, apparently.

03:03:47.639 --> 03:03:50.879
I hope someone feeds bumblebee.

03:03:50.940 --> 03:03:53.520
She caught herself thinking, and then she

03:03:53.520 --> 03:03:54.600
wanted to smack herself.

03:03:54.659 --> 03:03:58.139
That dragonette would 1000% make sure

03:03:58.139 --> 03:03:58.979
someone fed her.

03:03:59.040 --> 03:04:02.579
She didn't need sundew for that. of them

03:04:02.579 --> 03:04:03.059
needed her.

03:04:03.120 --> 03:04:06.420
You're doing the most important thing.

03:04:06.479 --> 03:04:08.579
Willow said sleepily.

03:04:08.639 --> 03:04:11.159
You're investigating the mind control

03:04:11.159 --> 03:04:14.159
plant and warning us that the hive wings

03:04:14.159 --> 03:04:14.879
know we're here.

03:04:14.940 --> 03:04:17.340
That's pretty important if you ask me.

03:04:17.399 --> 03:04:21.180
The hive wings don't know we're here

03:04:21.180 --> 03:04:22.920
Sundew pointed out.

03:04:22.979 --> 03:04:25.079
They know we're still alive, but they

03:04:25.079 --> 03:04:25.559
don't know where.

03:04:25.620 --> 03:04:28.979
Willow propped her chin on one talon and

03:04:28.979 --> 03:04:30.780
gave sundew a skeptical look.

03:04:30.840 --> 03:04:32.760
You don't think they'll guess pretty

03:04:32.760 --> 03:04:33.180
quickly?

03:04:33.239 --> 03:04:36.780
Hmm, where could those dragons who like

03:04:36.780 --> 03:04:38.459
trees possibly be?

03:04:38.520 --> 03:04:41.399
Oh, perhaps in the only bit of forest

03:04:41.399 --> 03:04:43.799
left on the whole continent, which also

03:04:43.799 --> 03:04:46.200
happens to be the only place we haven't

03:04:46.200 --> 03:04:48.000
been able to go for the last 50 years?

03:04:48.059 --> 03:04:50.219
What a coincidence.

03:04:50.280 --> 03:04:53.819
Sundew felt unease ripple under her

03:04:53.819 --> 03:04:54.120
scales.

03:04:54.180 --> 03:04:55.860
Was Willow right?

03:04:55.920 --> 03:04:58.500
Would it be that easy for Wasp to find

03:04:58.500 --> 03:04:58.680
them?

03:04:58.799 --> 03:05:01.559
She'd assumed Wasp would come after them

03:05:01.559 --> 03:05:04.139
eventually, but also that she'd waste

03:05:04.139 --> 03:05:05.700
some resources searching the whole

03:05:05.700 --> 03:05:06.239
continent first?

03:05:06.299 --> 03:05:10.020
It doesn't matter if they guess right, she

03:05:10.020 --> 03:05:10.559
huffed.

03:05:10.620 --> 03:05:12.540
The poison jungle will fight them off.

03:05:12.600 --> 03:05:14.940
Even if they arrived at the snarling

03:05:14.940 --> 03:05:17.100
river today, they couldn't get through to

03:05:17.100 --> 03:05:18.059
either of our villages.

03:05:18.120 --> 03:05:19.860
The jungle will eat them alive.

03:05:19.920 --> 03:05:23.579
I hope you're right, Willow said.

03:05:23.639 --> 03:05:26.940
Hey, while we wait, let's go talk to

03:05:26.940 --> 03:05:27.780
those sea wings.

03:05:27.840 --> 03:05:29.159
Don't you want to meet them?

03:05:29.280 --> 03:05:32.340
Sundew scales prickled with excitement

03:05:32.340 --> 03:05:32.819
and nerves.

03:05:32.940 --> 03:05:35.340
She'd nearly forgotten about them while

03:05:35.340 --> 03:05:36.180
she slept.

03:05:36.239 --> 03:05:38.459
Dragons from the distant kingdoms.

03:05:38.579 --> 03:05:41.459
She couldn't believe it, but Cricket was

03:05:41.459 --> 03:05:41.700
right.

03:05:41.760 --> 03:05:44.579
It was a real place where dragons really

03:05:44.579 --> 03:05:44.940
lived.

03:05:45.000 --> 03:05:47.579
Yes, she said.

03:05:47.639 --> 03:05:48.899
Let's do that right now.

03:05:48.959 --> 03:05:53.040
We can take them some breakfast, Willow

03:05:53.040 --> 03:05:55.260
said, sitting up and stretching.

03:05:55.319 --> 03:05:57.120
Hazel, want to come too?

03:05:57.239 --> 03:05:59.219
The princess shook her head.

03:05:59.280 --> 03:06:01.319
I met a really good part.

03:06:01.440 --> 03:06:04.079
She said apologetically, holding up her

03:06:04.079 --> 03:06:04.319
book.

03:06:04.379 --> 03:06:06.899
You know, great grandma usually never

03:06:06.899 --> 03:06:09.239
leaves me alone for this long, so I want

03:06:09.239 --> 03:06:10.739
to take advantage of it while I can.

03:06:10.799 --> 03:06:13.799
I get that, Willow said.

03:06:13.860 --> 03:06:14.819
See you later.

03:06:14.879 --> 03:06:19.260
Bye, Sundew mumbled. following Willow out

03:06:19.260 --> 03:06:19.559
of the room.

03:06:19.680 --> 03:06:22.620
They flew down to the kitchen level, where

03:06:22.620 --> 03:06:25.379
2 busy dragons waved at Willow, and made

03:06:25.379 --> 03:06:28.020
puzzled faces at sundew, but didn't stop

03:06:28.020 --> 03:06:30.120
their whirl of chopping and peeling and

03:06:30.120 --> 03:06:30.540
preparing.

03:06:30.600 --> 03:06:33.719
Willow scooped up 2 halves of a coconut

03:06:33.719 --> 03:06:36.360
gave one to Sundew, and filled them both

03:06:36.360 --> 03:06:38.459
with strips of dried mango and raw fish.

03:06:38.520 --> 03:06:41.760
It seems like most of the dragons in the

03:06:41.760 --> 03:06:43.920
palace know you, Sundu observed.

03:06:43.979 --> 03:06:47.940
I guess, Willow said, glancing around at

03:06:47.940 --> 03:06:49.020
the chefs.

03:06:49.079 --> 03:06:51.299
I mean, everyone kind of knows everyone.

03:06:51.360 --> 03:06:53.459
There aren't that many of us in the tribe

03:06:53.459 --> 03:06:53.940
after all.

03:06:54.000 --> 03:06:57.479
Because the hive wings tried to wipe us

03:06:57.479 --> 03:07:00.540
out, and then half of us left to form our

03:07:00.540 --> 03:07:02.579
own tribe, Sunday thought.

03:07:02.639 --> 03:07:05.100
With an odd twist of guilt under her

03:07:05.100 --> 03:07:05.819
usual anger.

03:07:05.879 --> 03:07:08.639
Do you come here a lot, though?

03:07:08.700 --> 03:07:09.899
Sundew asked.

03:07:09.959 --> 03:07:12.600
Watching Willow dig out and open a barrel

03:07:12.600 --> 03:07:13.620
of macadamia nuts?

03:07:13.739 --> 03:07:15.600
To the palace, I mean?

03:07:15.659 --> 03:07:17.639
Maybe to see Hazel?

03:07:17.700 --> 03:07:20.940
Willow crinkled her snout at sundew.

03:07:21.000 --> 03:07:25.020
Hazel is a friend of mine, she said.

03:07:25.079 --> 03:07:27.719
Like all the dragonets, our age in the

03:07:27.719 --> 03:07:28.020
village.

03:07:28.079 --> 03:07:31.379
But if what you're really asking is, hey

03:07:31.379 --> 03:07:33.600
Willow, have you by any chance fallen in

03:07:33.600 --> 03:07:35.399
love with some other dragon while I

03:07:35.399 --> 03:07:37.319
abandoned you to go start a war and

03:07:37.319 --> 03:07:38.940
frolic with silk wings?

03:07:39.000 --> 03:07:40.979
And there is no, I haven't.

03:07:41.040 --> 03:07:44.159
You're still the only dragon for me, even

03:07:44.159 --> 03:07:46.620
when you ask silly veiled questions.

03:07:46.680 --> 03:07:49.979
She tossed a nut at Sundew, which bounced

03:07:49.979 --> 03:07:51.180
off her nose before she caught it.

03:07:51.239 --> 03:07:54.299
Oh, Sundu said.

03:07:54.360 --> 03:07:56.340
Well, then, good.

03:07:56.399 --> 03:07:57.059
Fine.

03:07:57.120 --> 03:07:59.879
I mean, that wasn't what I was asking, but

03:07:59.879 --> 03:08:01.559
since you brought it up.

03:08:01.680 --> 03:08:03.899
That's great and good and fine with me.

03:08:03.959 --> 03:08:06.899
And Willow prompted.

03:08:06.959 --> 03:08:11.280
And thank you for the macadamia nut, send

03:08:11.280 --> 03:08:11.940
you guest.

03:08:12.000 --> 03:08:15.120
And you're still the only dragon for me

03:08:15.120 --> 03:08:17.399
too, Willow, light of my life.

03:08:17.520 --> 03:08:19.860
I promise I will never fall for beautiful

03:08:19.860 --> 03:08:21.420
silk wing and leave you.

03:08:21.479 --> 03:08:24.299
Willow put one talon dramatically to her

03:08:24.299 --> 03:08:24.719
forehead.

03:08:24.780 --> 03:08:28.860
By all the trees, Sundew said.

03:08:28.920 --> 03:08:30.479
Of course, that's obvious.

03:08:30.540 --> 03:08:32.159
That's so obvious.

03:08:32.219 --> 03:08:34.559
I don't need to say that, do I?

03:08:34.620 --> 03:08:35.760
You know all that.

03:08:35.819 --> 03:08:40.020
I mean, obviously, as if, leave you for a

03:08:40.020 --> 03:08:40.739
silk wing?

03:08:40.860 --> 03:08:41.399
Bleh.

03:08:41.459 --> 03:08:43.260
Willow giggled.

03:08:43.319 --> 03:08:46.379
I know, she said, but you should say it

03:08:46.379 --> 03:08:47.159
all the time anyway.

03:08:47.219 --> 03:08:49.799
I can't imagine you would take me

03:08:49.799 --> 03:08:52.379
seriously if I said things like light of

03:08:52.379 --> 03:08:55.079
my life all the time, sundew said

03:08:55.079 --> 03:08:57.420
balancing the coconut and its contents

03:08:57.420 --> 03:08:59.399
carefully as she spread her wings and

03:08:59.399 --> 03:09:00.840
flew off the balcony with Willow.

03:09:00.899 --> 03:09:04.020
I will always take you exactly as

03:09:04.020 --> 03:09:05.159
seriously as you deserve.

03:09:05.219 --> 03:09:07.620
Willow said, grinning.

03:09:07.680 --> 03:09:10.739
That is not a comforting answer, light of

03:09:10.739 --> 03:09:12.420
my life, sundew said.

03:09:12.540 --> 03:09:14.940
Willow started laughing so hard.

03:09:15.000 --> 03:09:16.440
She nearly dropped her coconut.

03:09:16.559 --> 03:09:19.379
A different set of not quite exactly

03:09:19.379 --> 03:09:21.659
guards were gathered outside the strange

03:09:21.659 --> 03:09:22.739
dragon's rooms.

03:09:22.799 --> 03:09:25.379
These 4 were bent over a map of the

03:09:25.379 --> 03:09:27.719
jungle around the village, pointing out

03:09:27.719 --> 03:09:29.399
spots where unwanted plants were trying

03:09:29.399 --> 03:09:31.799
to get in, and comparing stories of their

03:09:31.799 --> 03:09:33.719
valiant battles with dragon traps.

03:09:33.719 --> 03:09:37.319
They glanced up at Willow and Sundew, but

03:09:37.319 --> 03:09:39.360
didn't move to stop them, or even ask

03:09:39.360 --> 03:09:40.680
what they were doing there as they

03:09:40.680 --> 03:09:40.979
landed.

03:09:41.100 --> 03:09:45.059
Can anyone in the village just stop by to

03:09:45.059 --> 03:09:46.319
see the weird dragons?

03:09:46.319 --> 03:09:47.280
Sundew asked.

03:09:47.340 --> 03:09:51.840
I suppose so, Willow said, but I probably

03:09:51.840 --> 03:09:53.940
visit them the most, because I'm the one

03:09:53.940 --> 03:09:54.360
who found them.

03:09:54.420 --> 03:09:56.579
You are?

03:09:56.639 --> 03:09:58.680
Sundu blinked at her in surprise.

03:09:58.739 --> 03:10:01.079
Didn't I mention that?

03:10:01.139 --> 03:10:02.159
Willow said.

03:10:02.219 --> 03:10:04.620
She flicked her wings back and batted her

03:10:04.620 --> 03:10:05.219
eyelashes.

03:10:05.280 --> 03:10:10.200
I rescued them from a giant anaconda.

03:10:10.260 --> 03:10:11.819
If it weren't for me?

03:10:11.879 --> 03:10:13.260
They'd be super dead.

03:10:13.319 --> 03:10:15.239
And then we'd have nothing but the

03:10:15.239 --> 03:10:17.159
remains of 2 interesting corpses to

03:10:17.159 --> 03:10:17.399
study.

03:10:17.459 --> 03:10:18.840
She sighed.

03:10:18.899 --> 03:10:22.079
The Bluer dragon poked her head out of a

03:10:22.079 --> 03:10:22.319
room.

03:10:22.379 --> 03:10:25.680
In the daylight, it was a little harder

03:10:25.680 --> 03:10:28.020
to see the dots of phosphorescent scales

03:10:28.020 --> 03:10:30.059
around her eyes, and along her snout

03:10:30.059 --> 03:10:33.360
bones, but her deep blue color, unusual

03:10:33.360 --> 03:10:36.059
wing shape, and sundew noticed for the

03:10:36.059 --> 03:10:38.879
1st time webbed talons were much more

03:10:38.879 --> 03:10:39.479
obvious.

03:10:39.540 --> 03:10:43.260
Willow, she said brightly.

03:10:43.319 --> 03:10:44.520
I always know it's you when I hear

03:10:44.520 --> 03:10:46.500
someone talking loudly about heroic

03:10:46.500 --> 03:10:47.639
anaconda rescues.

03:10:47.700 --> 03:10:50.219
I will forgive you for the corpse comment

03:10:50.219 --> 03:10:51.239
because you come with food.

03:10:51.299 --> 03:10:55.559
Hi, tsunami, Willow said, passing her one

03:10:55.559 --> 03:10:56.280
of the coconuts.

03:10:56.340 --> 03:10:59.280
This is sundew, my girlfriend.

03:10:59.340 --> 03:11:03.299
Unexpected tiny starbursts of joy

03:11:03.299 --> 03:11:06.000
exploded all through sundew's body from

03:11:06.000 --> 03:11:07.620
her toes to her wingtips.

03:11:07.680 --> 03:11:10.139
They had never told anyone that before.

03:11:10.200 --> 03:11:13.860
Hearing Willow say it out loud, casually

03:11:13.860 --> 03:11:16.500
to a totally random dragon, was probably

03:11:16.500 --> 03:11:18.899
the 2nd greatest moment of sundew's life

03:11:18.899 --> 03:11:20.819
right after meeting Willow.

03:11:20.879 --> 03:11:23.219
She wondered what the blue dragon must

03:11:23.219 --> 03:11:25.139
think of meeting a leaf wing wearing

03:11:25.139 --> 03:11:27.479
whatever incredibly giddy expression she

03:11:27.479 --> 03:11:28.680
probably had on her face.

03:11:28.680 --> 03:11:30.959
Hello, Sundoo.

03:11:31.020 --> 03:11:32.879
What kind of tree is that?

03:11:33.000 --> 03:11:35.760
Tsunami asked, backing into the room so

03:11:35.760 --> 03:11:36.360
they could enter.

03:11:36.420 --> 03:11:38.700
The other dragon lay on his side by the

03:11:38.700 --> 03:11:38.940
wall.

03:11:39.000 --> 03:11:42.120
He looked slightly ill, but he lifted his

03:11:42.120 --> 03:11:43.139
head curiously to see them.

03:11:43.260 --> 03:11:45.780
It's not a tree.

03:11:45.840 --> 03:11:48.299
It's a plant that eats dragons and other

03:11:48.299 --> 03:11:50.219
animals, Willow explained.

03:11:50.280 --> 03:11:52.860
She's one of the poison wings I told you

03:11:52.860 --> 03:11:53.040
about.

03:11:53.159 --> 03:11:56.819
That's not what we call ourselves, Sundoo

03:11:56.819 --> 03:11:57.360
said quickly.

03:11:57.420 --> 03:12:00.719
We're leaf wings, real leaf wings.

03:12:00.780 --> 03:12:03.540
She might be able to answer some of your

03:12:03.540 --> 03:12:06.000
questions, Willow said to the dark blue

03:12:06.000 --> 03:12:06.600
dragon.

03:12:06.659 --> 03:12:09.180
Because she's just been to the hives.

03:12:09.239 --> 03:12:13.680
Oh, tsunami said, looking at sundew more

03:12:13.680 --> 03:12:14.159
intently.

03:12:14.219 --> 03:12:18.000
Hi, croaked the other Sea Wing.

03:12:18.059 --> 03:12:19.739
I'm turtle.

03:12:19.799 --> 03:12:21.719
Sorry I'm not getting up.

03:12:21.780 --> 03:12:23.819
I don't feel very well.

03:12:23.879 --> 03:12:27.840
He swallowed a lot more of the Gullet

03:12:27.840 --> 03:12:30.239
River than I would recommend, Willow

03:12:30.239 --> 03:12:30.780
explained.

03:12:30.840 --> 03:12:33.120
I'm sure he'll be all right in another

03:12:33.120 --> 03:12:33.659
day or two.

03:12:33.780 --> 03:12:37.079
The ginger tea has been helping, hasn't

03:12:37.079 --> 03:12:37.559
it, turtle?

03:12:37.620 --> 03:12:41.819
He more or less agreed, flopping his head

03:12:41.819 --> 03:12:42.299
down again.

03:12:42.360 --> 03:12:45.420
Poor dragon, Willow said.

03:12:45.540 --> 03:12:47.940
You know, I told them to turn around and

03:12:47.940 --> 03:12:50.100
go straight back to their continent, but

03:12:50.100 --> 03:12:51.120
it's a good thing they didn't.

03:12:51.180 --> 03:12:53.040
I don't think turtle would have made it.

03:12:53.159 --> 03:12:56.760
Groom, broom, he groaned.

03:12:56.819 --> 03:12:59.579
You really came all the way from the

03:12:59.579 --> 03:13:00.600
distant kingdoms?

03:13:00.659 --> 03:13:01.979
How did you get here?

03:13:02.040 --> 03:13:04.200
Sundu asked tsunami.

03:13:04.260 --> 03:13:06.059
She could practically hear cricket

03:13:06.059 --> 03:13:07.920
banging off the walls of her brain

03:13:07.920 --> 03:13:09.299
yelping questions.

03:13:09.360 --> 03:13:12.000
These dragons from the distant kingdoms

03:13:12.000 --> 03:13:14.040
would absolutely make her lose her mind.

03:13:14.159 --> 03:13:16.920
She'd probably be even worse about them

03:13:16.920 --> 03:13:19.200
than she was about her beloved mysterious

03:13:19.200 --> 03:13:20.159
reading monkeys.

03:13:20.159 --> 03:13:23.399
We swam, tsunami said.

03:13:23.459 --> 03:13:26.399
She held up one of her webbed talons, then

03:13:26.399 --> 03:13:28.440
pointed to what looked like gills along

03:13:28.440 --> 03:13:28.799
her neck.

03:13:28.860 --> 03:13:32.340
Sea wings can breathe underwater, so we'd

03:13:32.340 --> 03:13:34.680
swim until we got tired, take a nap at

03:13:34.680 --> 03:13:36.780
the bottom of the sea, ate some fish, and

03:13:36.780 --> 03:13:37.319
then keep going.

03:13:37.379 --> 03:13:39.899
It felt like heading off the edge of the

03:13:39.899 --> 03:13:40.139
world.

03:13:40.200 --> 03:13:43.319
For most of the trip, we couldn't see any

03:13:43.319 --> 03:13:44.399
land in any direction.

03:13:44.459 --> 03:13:47.819
Maybe an island in the distance, unless

03:13:47.819 --> 03:13:50.219
we were hallucinating those, but we were

03:13:50.219 --> 03:13:51.959
trying to stay on a course due west

03:13:51.959 --> 03:13:54.780
following the stars if my brother has any

03:13:54.780 --> 03:13:55.920
idea what he's talking about.

03:13:55.979 --> 03:14:00.239
It took us about 4 days of almost nonstop

03:14:00.239 --> 03:14:00.659
swimming.

03:14:00.719 --> 03:14:03.239
But I bet I could have done it in 3 by

03:14:03.239 --> 03:14:03.479
myself.

03:14:03.540 --> 03:14:06.899
I'm not sure if Turtle is really sick or

03:14:06.899 --> 03:14:08.399
just still recovering from all that

03:14:08.399 --> 03:14:09.059
exercise.

03:14:09.120 --> 03:14:13.260
Oi, turtle protested weakly.

03:14:13.319 --> 03:14:16.500
Right here, and really sick.

03:14:16.559 --> 03:14:19.139
That's a long time to swim without

03:14:19.139 --> 03:14:21.659
knowing anything was out there, Sundew

03:14:21.659 --> 03:14:22.139
said.

03:14:22.200 --> 03:14:24.239
They must be out of their minds.

03:14:24.299 --> 03:14:27.000
What kind of lunatics would swim off the

03:14:27.000 --> 03:14:28.379
edge of the world for no reason?

03:14:28.440 --> 03:14:31.860
But we did know this continent was out

03:14:31.860 --> 03:14:34.319
here, tsunami said, surprised.

03:14:34.379 --> 03:14:36.120
Didn't you tell her, Willow?

03:14:36.180 --> 03:14:39.600
I thought you should, Willow said.

03:14:39.659 --> 03:14:42.780
A Pantalan dragon washed ashore on our

03:14:42.780 --> 03:14:45.420
coast several days ago, Tsunami said.

03:14:45.479 --> 03:14:47.639
She got caught in a storm and blown over

03:14:47.639 --> 03:14:48.299
the sea to us.

03:14:48.360 --> 03:14:50.100
In a storm?

03:14:50.219 --> 03:14:52.979
Sandu echoed, her ears perking up.

03:14:53.040 --> 03:14:55.020
Does she have pale green wings and

03:14:55.020 --> 03:14:55.799
glowing wrists?

03:14:55.860 --> 03:14:57.600
Whoa.

03:14:57.659 --> 03:14:59.520
You know Luna?

03:14:59.579 --> 03:15:01.319
Turtles said from the corner.

03:15:01.379 --> 03:15:04.500
I thought leaf wings and silk wings

03:15:04.500 --> 03:15:06.780
didn't talk to each other, tsunami said

03:15:06.780 --> 03:15:07.260
to Willow.

03:15:07.319 --> 03:15:10.139
For example, Luna didn't say anything

03:15:10.139 --> 03:15:11.340
about this jungle.

03:15:11.399 --> 03:15:15.899
Or about dragon eating plants, or dragon

03:15:15.899 --> 03:15:19.440
eating giant snakes, or dragon poisoning

03:15:19.440 --> 03:15:21.479
rivers, turtle mumbled.

03:15:21.540 --> 03:15:25.620
I only met Luna briefly, Sundu said, when

03:15:25.620 --> 03:15:27.540
we rescued her from the Flame Silk

03:15:27.540 --> 03:15:27.840
Cavern.

03:15:27.899 --> 03:15:31.559
Turtle and tsunami exchanged significant

03:15:31.559 --> 03:15:31.920
glances.

03:15:31.979 --> 03:15:35.100
So that part of her story was true

03:15:35.100 --> 03:15:36.600
tsunami murmured.

03:15:36.659 --> 03:15:39.239
Willow had never heard of a flame silk

03:15:39.239 --> 03:15:39.600
cavern.

03:15:39.659 --> 03:15:41.639
I'm sure it was all true.

03:15:41.700 --> 03:15:43.139
Sundew said.

03:15:43.200 --> 03:15:45.899
Luna's feisty for a silkwing, but she's

03:15:45.899 --> 03:15:47.579
still a silkwing, and they're a pretty

03:15:47.579 --> 03:15:48.299
simple tribe.

03:15:48.360 --> 03:15:50.579
Whatever she told you, you should believe

03:15:50.579 --> 03:15:50.819
it.

03:15:50.879 --> 03:15:52.440
Really?

03:15:52.559 --> 03:15:53.879
tsunami said.

03:15:53.940 --> 03:15:56.399
She was very worked up about the plight

03:15:56.399 --> 03:15:57.420
of the silk wings.

03:15:57.479 --> 03:15:59.700
She wanted us to gather an army and

03:15:59.700 --> 03:16:01.620
charge across the ocean and destroy the

03:16:01.620 --> 03:16:02.879
hive wings to save her tribe.

03:16:02.940 --> 03:16:06.239
Sundew leaped to her feet, her eyes

03:16:06.239 --> 03:16:06.719
shining.

03:16:06.780 --> 03:16:09.959
Uh-oh, said tsunami.

03:16:10.020 --> 03:16:12.120
Yes, Sundu cried.

03:16:12.180 --> 03:16:12.899
Do that.

03:16:12.959 --> 03:16:13.860
Do that.

03:16:13.979 --> 03:16:17.040
Hang on, said Turtle.

03:16:17.100 --> 03:16:18.899
How big is your army?

03:16:18.959 --> 03:16:21.180
What kinds of weapons do you have?

03:16:21.239 --> 03:16:22.260
How soon can they be here?

03:16:22.319 --> 03:16:23.639
Are they on their way?

03:16:23.700 --> 03:16:25.559
Are you the advanced scouts?

03:16:25.680 --> 03:16:27.239
Send do.

03:16:27.299 --> 03:16:29.879
Don't get too excited, Willow said

03:16:29.879 --> 03:16:32.280
reaching out to touch one of sundew's

03:16:32.280 --> 03:16:33.420
shaking wings with hers.

03:16:33.540 --> 03:16:35.819
They are not sure they should get

03:16:35.819 --> 03:16:36.540
involved.

03:16:36.600 --> 03:16:38.280
Why wouldn't you?

03:16:38.340 --> 03:16:39.780
Sundew yelped.

03:16:39.840 --> 03:16:42.000
Don't you care about fighting injustice

03:16:42.000 --> 03:16:44.940
and and evil?

03:16:45.000 --> 03:16:48.239
Evil, you could stop evil.

03:16:48.299 --> 03:16:48.899
Did you think of that?

03:16:48.959 --> 03:16:52.500
Hey, tsunami protested.

03:16:52.559 --> 03:16:55.620
I've stopped plenty of evil, and so has

03:16:55.620 --> 03:16:55.979
turtle.

03:16:56.100 --> 03:16:59.639
Sendu gave him a skeptical look, but

03:16:59.639 --> 03:17:01.379
decided to refrain from asking how that

03:17:01.379 --> 03:17:01.799
was possible.

03:17:01.860 --> 03:17:06.000
Then stop this one, she said to tsunami.

03:17:06.059 --> 03:17:08.520
The hive wings are the worst, and they

03:17:08.520 --> 03:17:09.719
deserve to be wiped out.

03:17:09.780 --> 03:17:14.040
Tsunami's face closed down suddenly, like

03:17:14.040 --> 03:17:15.719
a dragon trap slamming shut.

03:17:15.780 --> 03:17:19.979
We don't wipe out entire tribes, she said

03:17:19.979 --> 03:17:22.799
firmly, and we will never help anyone

03:17:22.799 --> 03:17:24.000
who'd be willing to do that.

03:17:24.059 --> 03:17:27.659
But you don't know what they did, Sandu

03:17:27.659 --> 03:17:28.020
cried.

03:17:28.079 --> 03:17:30.420
She felt like all her hope was slipping

03:17:30.420 --> 03:17:33.719
away, like chocolate in a dream, melting

03:17:33.719 --> 03:17:35.100
through her claws before she could eat

03:17:35.100 --> 03:17:35.340
it.

03:17:35.399 --> 03:17:39.600
At that exact wrong moment, Hazel poked

03:17:39.600 --> 03:17:40.139
her head in the door.

03:17:40.200 --> 03:17:43.319
Wow, she said.

03:17:43.379 --> 03:17:44.940
Can't you all hear that?

03:17:45.000 --> 03:17:47.520
She jerked one claw over her shoulder.

03:17:47.520 --> 03:17:51.059
In the pause that followed, Sundew heard

03:17:51.059 --> 03:17:53.340
the unmistakable roars of a horribly

03:17:53.340 --> 03:17:55.620
familiar voice somewhere on the jungle

03:17:55.620 --> 03:17:56.340
floor outside.

03:17:56.399 --> 03:18:00.780
Oh no, she said, looking at Willow.

03:18:00.840 --> 03:18:03.420
She didn't even realize she'd held out

03:18:03.420 --> 03:18:05.520
one of her talons until Willow took it

03:18:05.520 --> 03:18:07.139
and squeezed it reassuringly.

03:18:07.200 --> 03:18:09.420
What is that?

03:18:09.540 --> 03:18:10.739
Tsunami asked.

03:18:10.799 --> 03:18:12.540
Sundew sighed.

03:18:12.659 --> 03:18:14.100
My mother is here.

03:18:14.159 --> 03:18:18.479
Chapter 10.

03:18:18.780 --> 03:18:22.379
Willow, Sundew, and Hazel reached

03:18:22.379 --> 03:18:24.059
Sequoia's throne room first.

03:18:24.120 --> 03:18:26.280
The leaf winged queen was sitting on her

03:18:26.280 --> 03:18:28.500
throne with her eyes closed and her

03:18:28.500 --> 03:18:30.659
forehead furrowed, as though she had a

03:18:30.659 --> 03:18:31.680
massive headache.

03:18:31.739 --> 03:18:34.440
That's only going to get worse.

03:18:34.500 --> 03:18:36.479
Sundoo thought grimly.

03:18:36.540 --> 03:18:39.420
Your majesty, Willow said.

03:18:39.479 --> 03:18:41.760
We heard Belladonna outside.

03:18:41.819 --> 03:18:43.500
Sundu finished for her.

03:18:43.559 --> 03:18:45.840
I don't know how she guessed I was here.

03:18:45.899 --> 03:18:48.659
I often leave the village at night or in

03:18:48.659 --> 03:18:49.799
the early morning to hunt.

03:18:49.860 --> 03:18:52.020
I didn't think she'd come looking for me

03:18:52.020 --> 03:18:54.420
so quickly, or that she'd ever think to

03:18:54.420 --> 03:18:55.739
check among the sap wings.

03:18:55.799 --> 03:19:00.479
Ah, Queen Sequoia said, opening her

03:19:00.479 --> 03:19:00.719
eyes.

03:19:00.780 --> 03:19:02.700
She didn't think of it.

03:19:02.760 --> 03:19:04.200
I summoned her.

03:19:04.260 --> 03:19:07.200
Summoned her?

03:19:07.260 --> 03:19:10.260
Sundew said, flabbergasted.

03:19:10.319 --> 03:19:12.899
Nobody summoned Belladonna.

03:19:12.959 --> 03:19:15.299
Also, how dare the queen?

03:19:15.360 --> 03:19:17.459
Why didn't you ask me?

03:19:17.520 --> 03:19:19.079
Or at least warn me?

03:19:19.139 --> 03:19:20.520
I don't want to see her.

03:19:20.579 --> 03:19:23.819
I mean, here, now, like this.

03:19:23.940 --> 03:19:26.819
She forced herself not to glance at

03:19:26.819 --> 03:19:29.399
Willow, not to give away too much with a

03:19:29.399 --> 03:19:29.579
look.

03:19:29.639 --> 03:19:31.680
She wasn't ready to tell her mother

03:19:31.680 --> 03:19:32.459
everything yet.

03:19:32.520 --> 03:19:35.159
She didn't want Belladonna to ruin this

03:19:35.159 --> 03:19:37.079
the way she definitely would.

03:19:37.139 --> 03:19:39.840
Queen Sequoia looked faintly

03:19:39.840 --> 03:19:40.500
incredulous.

03:19:40.559 --> 03:19:44.219
I don't want to see her either, but we

03:19:44.219 --> 03:19:46.260
don't have time for my peace of mind or

03:19:46.260 --> 03:19:47.520
your family drama.

03:19:47.579 --> 03:19:50.879
Wasp is about to throw her entire brute

03:19:50.879 --> 03:19:54.000
force at us, every claw and tooth and

03:19:54.000 --> 03:19:55.139
venomous stinger.

03:19:55.200 --> 03:19:58.559
We need a plan, and we need all talons

03:19:58.559 --> 03:19:58.920
ready.

03:19:58.979 --> 03:20:02.639
All leaf wings, no matter what our

03:20:02.639 --> 03:20:04.020
differences have been in the past.

03:20:04.079 --> 03:20:08.040
Well, talking to her isn't going to help

03:20:08.040 --> 03:20:09.420
Sandu grumbled.

03:20:09.540 --> 03:20:13.260
I don't exactly have a choice, Sequoia

03:20:13.260 --> 03:20:13.500
said.

03:20:13.559 --> 03:20:16.860
I need to know what else she's done and

03:20:16.860 --> 03:20:18.000
what she's going to do next.

03:20:18.059 --> 03:20:21.239
I told her to bring your captives, or

03:20:21.239 --> 03:20:23.879
else I wouldn't release my hostage, the

03:20:23.879 --> 03:20:24.420
queen added.

03:20:24.479 --> 03:20:25.620
That's you.

03:20:25.680 --> 03:20:29.040
She let out a snort of laughter, as if

03:20:29.040 --> 03:20:30.840
she was picturing Belladonna's reaction

03:20:30.840 --> 03:20:33.420
to that threat, and Sundu had to admit to

03:20:33.420 --> 03:20:35.219
herself that it was kind of hilarious to

03:20:35.219 --> 03:20:35.459
imagine.

03:20:35.579 --> 03:20:39.299
It was slightly less hilarious when

03:20:39.299 --> 03:20:41.579
Belladonna swooped in, though, in her

03:20:41.579 --> 03:20:42.959
towering cloud of rage.

03:20:43.020 --> 03:20:45.120
She came straight through one of the

03:20:45.120 --> 03:20:47.280
balconies and slammed her talons on the

03:20:47.280 --> 03:20:49.860
polished wood floor, scattering raindrops

03:20:49.860 --> 03:20:50.159
everywhere.

03:20:50.219 --> 03:20:52.799
She was only wearing a few of her pouches

03:20:52.799 --> 03:20:54.840
as though she'd thrown them on in a

03:20:54.840 --> 03:20:55.200
hurry.

03:20:55.260 --> 03:20:58.020
But Sundew could hear ominous hissing and

03:20:58.020 --> 03:20:59.579
clicking coming from a couple of them.

03:20:59.639 --> 03:21:02.100
It sounded as though Belladonna had

03:21:02.100 --> 03:21:03.840
packed a few of her nastier insect

03:21:03.840 --> 03:21:04.379
weapons.

03:21:04.440 --> 03:21:06.299
What are you doing here?

03:21:06.360 --> 03:21:08.459
She roared at sundu.

03:21:08.520 --> 03:21:10.260
You know you're not allowed to talk to

03:21:10.260 --> 03:21:12.360
sap wings, and you're definitely not

03:21:12.360 --> 03:21:13.379
allowed in their village.

03:21:13.500 --> 03:21:16.920
Sundew spread her wings and shrugged

03:21:16.920 --> 03:21:18.840
hoping no one could hear her pounding

03:21:18.840 --> 03:21:19.079
heart.

03:21:19.200 --> 03:21:21.000
What could I do?

03:21:21.059 --> 03:21:22.139
They caught me.

03:21:22.200 --> 03:21:24.420
Caught, you?

03:21:24.479 --> 03:21:26.040
Belladonna snarled.

03:21:26.159 --> 03:21:30.180
And, um, dragged me back here, Sundew

03:21:30.180 --> 03:21:32.219
said, kicking and fighting the whole

03:21:32.219 --> 03:21:32.399
way.

03:21:32.459 --> 03:21:35.280
These dragons.

03:21:35.340 --> 03:21:37.860
Belladonna scoffed disbelievingly.

03:21:37.920 --> 03:21:40.379
Sapwings did that?

03:21:40.440 --> 03:21:44.040
Yes, and then they forced me to tell them

03:21:44.040 --> 03:21:46.020
everything, Sundew said.

03:21:46.079 --> 03:21:47.940
It was barbaric, really.

03:21:48.000 --> 03:21:49.200
You should be mad at her.

03:21:49.260 --> 03:21:52.200
She pointed at the queen. who rolled her

03:21:52.200 --> 03:21:52.440
eyes.

03:21:52.500 --> 03:21:55.680
Something about this feels highly

03:21:55.680 --> 03:21:58.139
unlikely, Belladonna growled.

03:21:58.200 --> 03:22:02.159
It doesn't matter, Queen Sequoia said

03:22:02.159 --> 03:22:02.940
standing up.

03:22:03.000 --> 03:22:05.520
Belladonna, I should arrest you for

03:22:05.520 --> 03:22:05.940
treason.

03:22:06.000 --> 03:22:09.059
You did everything I told you not to do.

03:22:09.120 --> 03:22:11.399
You were seen by hive wings.

03:22:11.459 --> 03:22:14.459
You stole their sacred property, and you

03:22:14.459 --> 03:22:15.899
said one of their hives on fire.

03:22:15.959 --> 03:22:19.559
Beladan lifted her chin and narrowed her

03:22:19.559 --> 03:22:19.799
eyes.

03:22:19.860 --> 03:22:23.340
I see you really did tell them everything

03:22:23.340 --> 03:22:25.079
she said to Sundo.

03:22:25.200 --> 03:22:27.780
Did you bring her captives?

03:22:27.840 --> 03:22:29.100
The queen asked.

03:22:29.159 --> 03:22:30.899
The flame silk and the others.

03:22:31.020 --> 03:22:32.879
I brought the others.

03:22:32.940 --> 03:22:35.819
Belladonna said, flicking her tail at the

03:22:35.819 --> 03:22:36.120
window.

03:22:36.180 --> 03:22:38.940
Outside, Sandu caught a glimpse of

03:22:38.940 --> 03:22:41.340
Wolfsbane and Biblus, hovering on either

03:22:41.340 --> 03:22:42.059
side of cricket.

03:22:42.120 --> 03:22:44.579
No wonder the trees were starting to fill

03:22:44.579 --> 03:22:47.219
up with curious dragons, gathering to

03:22:47.219 --> 03:22:49.139
stare at the hive wing in their midst.

03:22:49.200 --> 03:22:51.000
But not the flame silk.

03:22:51.059 --> 03:22:54.120
You cannot have my flame silk, Belladonna

03:22:54.120 --> 03:22:54.479
added.

03:22:54.540 --> 03:22:57.360
Even in exchange for your daughter.

03:22:57.420 --> 03:23:01.379
Sequoia asked lightly, almost as though

03:23:01.379 --> 03:23:02.340
she was just curious.

03:23:02.399 --> 03:23:05.940
My daughter could escape and kill you all

03:23:05.940 --> 03:23:07.200
any time she wanted to.

03:23:07.260 --> 03:23:10.260
Belladonna said, with a stern look at

03:23:10.260 --> 03:23:10.799
Sundew.

03:23:10.920 --> 03:23:13.799
The only reason she hasn't yet is she's

03:23:13.799 --> 03:23:15.299
trying to infuriate me.

03:23:15.420 --> 03:23:19.860
That's right, mother, Sundu said, with a

03:23:19.860 --> 03:23:20.760
theatrical yawn.

03:23:20.819 --> 03:23:22.319
It's all about you.

03:23:22.379 --> 03:23:24.659
You're the only reason I do anything.

03:23:24.719 --> 03:23:27.600
I think about you all day long.

03:23:27.659 --> 03:23:30.000
Stop it, you two.

03:23:30.059 --> 03:23:31.680
The queen ordered.

03:23:31.739 --> 03:23:34.500
Belladonna, bring the other captives

03:23:34.500 --> 03:23:35.159
inside.

03:23:35.219 --> 03:23:38.280
Hazel, please go retrieve our strange

03:23:38.280 --> 03:23:39.120
guests.

03:23:39.180 --> 03:23:41.579
Hazel nodded and hurried out of the

03:23:41.579 --> 03:23:41.700
room.

03:23:41.819 --> 03:23:44.159
What if I don't?

03:23:44.280 --> 03:23:45.899
Belladonna started.

03:23:45.959 --> 03:23:49.260
I don't care what you don't want to do.

03:23:49.379 --> 03:23:52.500
I am not going to let your dragons die.

03:23:52.620 --> 03:23:55.200
Queen Sequoia said fiercely.

03:23:55.260 --> 03:23:58.139
You may have been apart from us for 50

03:23:58.139 --> 03:24:01.139
years, but you're still my tribe.

03:24:01.260 --> 03:24:04.500
If we don't work together now, we don't

03:24:04.500 --> 03:24:05.159
stand a chance.

03:24:05.219 --> 03:24:08.760
She closed her eyes and muttered, one.

03:24:08.940 --> 03:24:10.739
Two.

03:24:10.739 --> 03:24:12.420
Three.

03:24:12.719 --> 03:24:15.239
Belladonna huffed her way over to the

03:24:15.239 --> 03:24:17.340
window and signaled to Wolf's Bane.

03:24:17.399 --> 03:24:19.860
Are you going to tell us the truth about

03:24:19.860 --> 03:24:21.360
that mind control plant?

03:24:21.420 --> 03:24:22.920
Sundew asked the queen.

03:24:22.979 --> 03:24:26.399
Sequoia opened her eyes, gave her a

03:24:26.399 --> 03:24:29.579
strange, clouded look, and hesitated, but

03:24:29.579 --> 03:24:30.180
only for a moment.

03:24:30.239 --> 03:24:34.200
Yes, she said, I have to.

03:24:34.260 --> 03:24:38.040
Sandu wanted to press her further, but

03:24:38.040 --> 03:24:40.260
just then Hazel came back in with tsunami

03:24:40.260 --> 03:24:42.540
and the unfamiliar silk wing behind her.

03:24:42.600 --> 03:24:45.899
The silk wing was very tall, with huge

03:24:45.899 --> 03:24:48.059
indigo wings dotted here and there with

03:24:48.059 --> 03:24:48.959
iridescent green.

03:24:49.020 --> 03:24:52.260
She had an alert, defiant expression on

03:24:52.260 --> 03:24:54.659
her face, but she didn't seem worried to

03:24:54.659 --> 03:24:56.639
be surrounded by so many leaf wings.

03:24:56.700 --> 03:24:59.280
Oh, thank goodness.

03:24:59.399 --> 03:25:02.219
Swordell's voice came loudly through the

03:25:02.219 --> 03:25:02.520
window.

03:25:02.579 --> 03:25:05.219
I was wondering how long we'd have to

03:25:05.219 --> 03:25:06.180
wait out here in the rain.

03:25:06.239 --> 03:25:08.940
I am completely soggy.

03:25:09.000 --> 03:25:12.479
Ah, he said, as he landed on the balcony

03:25:12.479 --> 03:25:13.739
and squelched inside.

03:25:13.860 --> 03:25:16.440
I'm so sorry about your floors.

03:25:16.500 --> 03:25:19.379
Oh man, look at these footprints.

03:25:19.440 --> 03:25:21.600
I didn't even know I had this much mud on

03:25:21.600 --> 03:25:21.780
me.

03:25:21.840 --> 03:25:24.180
I mean, how did that even happen?

03:25:24.239 --> 03:25:26.040
We were flying, right?

03:25:26.100 --> 03:25:28.799
And yet, Soretail?

03:25:28.860 --> 03:25:31.079
The purple silk wing gasped.

03:25:31.139 --> 03:25:35.040
He looked up, and his jaw dropped, and he

03:25:35.040 --> 03:25:36.780
stared at her for an astonished moment.

03:25:36.840 --> 03:25:38.700
Aio!

03:25:38.760 --> 03:25:41.520
He finally shouted, bounding across the

03:25:41.520 --> 03:25:42.180
room toward her.

03:25:42.239 --> 03:25:44.879
All thoughts of his wetness seemed to fly

03:25:44.879 --> 03:25:47.399
out of his head, much like the shower of

03:25:47.399 --> 03:25:49.079
droplets that covered everyone in the

03:25:49.079 --> 03:25:51.180
room as he threw his wings around the

03:25:51.180 --> 03:25:51.719
other dragon.

03:25:51.840 --> 03:25:56.100
Sore tailed by all the trees, Sundew

03:25:56.100 --> 03:25:57.719
huffed, shaking herself off.

03:25:57.780 --> 03:26:00.059
She glanced to the balcony and saw

03:26:00.059 --> 03:26:02.459
Cricket coming in, carrying Bumblebee.

03:26:02.520 --> 03:26:05.399
Their eyes met, and cricket gave her a

03:26:05.399 --> 03:26:06.540
tentative, worried smile.

03:26:06.659 --> 03:26:11.040
This is my sister, sword tail crowed.

03:26:11.100 --> 03:26:14.280
Sundu, cricket, this is Io, my sister.

03:26:14.340 --> 03:26:16.440
How did you get here?

03:26:16.500 --> 03:26:17.760
Io cried.

03:26:17.819 --> 03:26:20.159
That's the longest story ever.

03:26:20.219 --> 03:26:21.299
How did you get here?

03:26:21.360 --> 03:26:22.559
He asked.

03:26:22.620 --> 03:26:25.079
As cricket sidled across the room to

03:26:25.079 --> 03:26:25.979
sundew's side.

03:26:26.100 --> 03:26:29.040
Sundew noticed that Bumblebee was asleep

03:26:29.040 --> 03:26:31.139
and then noticed that she found that

03:26:31.139 --> 03:26:33.120
disappointing for some completely

03:26:33.120 --> 03:26:34.379
inexplicable reason.

03:26:34.440 --> 03:26:38.040
Well, my plan was to hide with some

03:26:38.040 --> 03:26:39.659
friend in the yellow jacket hive

03:26:39.659 --> 03:26:42.840
chrysalis, Io said to Swordtail, but when

03:26:42.840 --> 03:26:45.420
I got there, I was spotted by guards, who

03:26:45.420 --> 03:26:47.340
chased me pretty much all the way to the

03:26:47.340 --> 03:26:50.760
jungle, I flew inside to escape them, and

03:26:50.760 --> 03:26:52.559
almost immediately got caught by this

03:26:52.559 --> 03:26:55.620
enormous, horrifying, insanely sticky

03:26:55.620 --> 03:26:56.159
plant.

03:26:56.219 --> 03:26:59.579
It was going to eat me, sore tail, with

03:26:59.579 --> 03:27:01.379
like, it's goo or something.

03:27:01.440 --> 03:27:02.940
How wild is that?

03:27:03.059 --> 03:27:05.100
But these dragons rescued me?

03:27:05.159 --> 03:27:07.020
And they said I could lie low here for a

03:27:07.020 --> 03:27:07.200
while.

03:27:07.260 --> 03:27:11.280
That is bogkers, Sortell said.

03:27:11.340 --> 03:27:14.399
I got eaten too, by giant mouth plant.

03:27:14.459 --> 03:27:16.860
Another sword tail.

03:27:16.920 --> 03:27:20.340
Sundew whispered to Cricket, just what we

03:27:20.340 --> 03:27:20.579
need.

03:27:20.639 --> 03:27:24.479
IO seized SwordTail's front talons.

03:27:24.540 --> 03:27:26.579
Have you heard anything about blue?

03:27:26.639 --> 03:27:27.600
She asked.

03:27:27.659 --> 03:27:30.120
Did the hive wings catch him, or did he

03:27:30.120 --> 03:27:30.959
find a chrysalis?

03:27:31.020 --> 03:27:32.579
Neither.

03:27:32.700 --> 03:27:33.840
Swartell said.

03:27:33.899 --> 03:27:35.040
He found her.

03:27:35.100 --> 03:27:37.079
He pointed at Cricket.

03:27:37.139 --> 03:27:40.680
Io saw the hive wing for the 1st time, and

03:27:40.680 --> 03:27:42.540
her face underwent an extraordinary

03:27:42.540 --> 03:27:45.959
transformation from excitement to fury in

03:27:45.959 --> 03:27:46.379
seconds.

03:27:46.440 --> 03:27:49.079
She took a step forward, her ears

03:27:49.079 --> 03:27:51.719
flattened to her head, but Swordtail

03:27:51.719 --> 03:27:53.700
bundled himself into her path and shook

03:27:53.700 --> 03:27:54.360
her by the shoulders.

03:27:54.479 --> 03:27:57.360
No, no, calm down.

03:27:57.420 --> 03:28:00.059
Crickets on our side, he said.

03:28:00.120 --> 03:28:03.479
She saved blue, like more than once.

03:28:03.540 --> 03:28:06.000
He's here, in fact, in the other leaf

03:28:06.000 --> 03:28:06.899
wing village right now.

03:28:06.959 --> 03:28:09.959
Oh, Io said.

03:28:10.020 --> 03:28:14.159
But, what about, she flicked her tail at

03:28:14.159 --> 03:28:16.860
cricket, pointed to her head, and rolled

03:28:16.860 --> 03:28:18.840
her eyes back until almost only the

03:28:18.840 --> 03:28:21.540
whites were showing. doesn't work on her

03:28:21.540 --> 03:28:22.620
he said.

03:28:22.680 --> 03:28:25.440
No evil queen in her head, not ever.

03:28:25.500 --> 03:28:29.159
Oh, well, great.

03:28:29.219 --> 03:28:31.920
IO waved politely at Cricket.

03:28:31.979 --> 03:28:33.239
Nice to meet you.

03:28:33.299 --> 03:28:35.100
Thanks for saving Blue.

03:28:35.159 --> 03:28:38.760
Excuse me, tsunami interjected.

03:28:38.819 --> 03:28:40.079
Did you say blue?

03:28:40.200 --> 03:28:43.979
It's just, we were told to find a, oh my

03:28:43.979 --> 03:28:46.139
gosh, cricket gasped.

03:28:46.200 --> 03:28:48.360
She gripped Sundu's arm and pointed at

03:28:48.360 --> 03:28:49.020
tsunami.

03:28:49.079 --> 03:28:51.659
Oh, oh my gosh.

03:28:51.719 --> 03:28:52.620
Do you see that?

03:28:52.680 --> 03:28:54.120
What is happening?

03:28:54.180 --> 03:28:54.959
Who is that?

03:28:55.020 --> 03:28:57.479
Why is she amazing and blue?

03:28:57.540 --> 03:28:59.579
And look at her wings, and are those

03:28:59.579 --> 03:29:00.899
webbed talons?

03:29:00.959 --> 03:29:02.459
Are they for swimming?

03:29:02.579 --> 03:29:04.260
Is she a water dragon?

03:29:04.319 --> 03:29:05.819
What is she?

03:29:05.879 --> 03:29:07.260
And where did she come from?

03:29:07.319 --> 03:29:10.440
Oh my gosh, she's from the distant

03:29:10.440 --> 03:29:11.579
kingdoms, isn't she?

03:29:11.639 --> 03:29:14.819
If you're going to faint, hand me

03:29:14.819 --> 03:29:17.100
Bumblebee 1st so you don't squash her by

03:29:17.100 --> 03:29:19.079
accident, Sundew suggested.

03:29:19.139 --> 03:29:22.319
I should visit new continents more often

03:29:22.319 --> 03:29:25.020
tsunami said, with a pleased expression.

03:29:25.079 --> 03:29:27.180
I wish everyone was that excited to see

03:29:27.180 --> 03:29:27.420
me.

03:29:27.540 --> 03:29:30.479
Wait until you tell Sortell that you met

03:29:30.479 --> 03:29:31.079
Luna.

03:29:31.200 --> 03:29:32.639
Cindu said.

03:29:32.700 --> 03:29:36.420
Soretail whirled toward tsunami, his face

03:29:36.420 --> 03:29:37.680
incandescent with hope.

03:29:37.799 --> 03:29:41.760
Yes, she's all right, tsunami said.

03:29:41.819 --> 03:29:44.040
She washed ashore on our continent.

03:29:44.100 --> 03:29:45.540
She's the reason we're here.

03:29:45.600 --> 03:29:47.700
She says you all need help.

03:29:47.760 --> 03:29:50.520
She asked us to look for sore tail and

03:29:50.520 --> 03:29:52.079
blue to tell them she's okay.

03:29:52.139 --> 03:29:56.399
IO put one wing around her brother, as he

03:29:56.399 --> 03:29:58.559
buried his face in his talons and burst

03:29:58.559 --> 03:29:59.280
into tears.

03:29:59.340 --> 03:30:03.000
Ah, sore tail, she said.

03:30:03.059 --> 03:30:04.500
She'll find a way back here.

03:30:04.559 --> 03:30:06.959
You'll always find your way back to each

03:30:06.959 --> 03:30:07.200
other.

03:30:07.260 --> 03:30:09.899
Sappy.

03:30:09.959 --> 03:30:12.239
Tsunami commented, but that's basically

03:30:12.239 --> 03:30:13.319
what Luna said too.

03:30:13.379 --> 03:30:16.920
How does she speak our language?

03:30:16.979 --> 03:30:18.600
Cricket breathed.

03:30:18.659 --> 03:30:21.659
Is it magic that we understand her?

03:30:21.719 --> 03:30:25.079
Is she a magic superpowered dragon like

03:30:25.079 --> 03:30:26.100
clear sight?

03:30:26.219 --> 03:30:27.420
Oh my gosh.

03:30:27.479 --> 03:30:28.920
Can you see the future?

03:30:28.979 --> 03:30:33.540
I can see a future, tsunami answered.

03:30:33.600 --> 03:30:36.479
One where it takes me the next 3 years to

03:30:36.479 --> 03:30:37.620
answer all your questions.

03:30:37.680 --> 03:30:39.059
Really?

03:30:39.120 --> 03:30:40.620
Cricket gasped.

03:30:40.680 --> 03:30:43.739
Calm down, Cricket, Sandoo said.

03:30:43.799 --> 03:30:46.559
If this dragon could see the future, she

03:30:46.559 --> 03:30:48.059
wouldn't have almost been eaten by an

03:30:48.059 --> 03:30:49.020
anaconda.

03:30:49.139 --> 03:30:53.159
True, tsunami said, I also wouldn't have

03:30:53.159 --> 03:30:54.899
eaten that thing this morning that looked

03:30:54.899 --> 03:30:57.299
like a slug and turned out to be a slug.

03:30:57.420 --> 03:31:00.719
The queen clapped her talons together, and

03:31:00.719 --> 03:31:02.639
everyone fell silent, turning toward

03:31:02.639 --> 03:31:02.879
her.

03:31:02.940 --> 03:31:07.319
Listen, there's a lot to cover, she

03:31:07.319 --> 03:31:07.620
said.

03:31:07.680 --> 03:31:10.680
And we don't have much time, so we must

03:31:10.680 --> 03:31:13.200
save the introductions, reunions, and

03:31:13.200 --> 03:31:15.600
questions until after our urgent

03:31:15.600 --> 03:31:16.139
business.

03:31:16.200 --> 03:31:19.020
As I understand it, 2 days ago.

03:31:19.079 --> 03:31:22.079
Belladonna and the Poison Wings committed

03:31:22.079 --> 03:31:23.100
an act of war.

03:31:23.159 --> 03:31:26.219
By burning one of the hive wings cities.

03:31:26.280 --> 03:31:29.219
During the course of that mission, leaf

03:31:29.219 --> 03:31:30.059
wings were seen.

03:31:30.180 --> 03:31:33.600
So there will be no doubt in Queen Wasp's

03:31:33.600 --> 03:31:36.299
mind that our tribe is still alive, and

03:31:36.299 --> 03:31:37.739
that we are the ones who started the

03:31:37.739 --> 03:31:38.040
fire.

03:31:38.100 --> 03:31:41.399
Can't we tell her it was them and not

03:31:41.399 --> 03:31:42.000
us?

03:31:42.000 --> 03:31:44.879
Hazel asked, jabbing one of her claws at

03:31:44.879 --> 03:31:45.659
Belladonna.

03:31:45.719 --> 03:31:50.100
Yeah, give that a try, said Wolf's bang

03:31:50.100 --> 03:31:50.579
darkly.

03:31:50.639 --> 03:31:52.799
I hear she's quite reasonable.

03:31:52.860 --> 03:31:56.159
Sorry, Hazel, said the Queen.

03:31:56.219 --> 03:31:59.100
She hates all leaf wings equally, and

03:31:59.100 --> 03:32:00.780
she'll be even more furious when she

03:32:00.780 --> 03:32:02.280
discovers I'm not dead.

03:32:02.340 --> 03:32:05.459
There's no chance she'd let half of us

03:32:05.459 --> 03:32:07.500
just carry on living quietly in the

03:32:07.500 --> 03:32:07.860
jungle.

03:32:07.920 --> 03:32:10.739
She flared her wings and looked over at

03:32:10.739 --> 03:32:12.239
Wolf's Bane and Belladonna.

03:32:12.299 --> 03:32:15.299
There's also no chance I'd let her kill

03:32:15.299 --> 03:32:17.040
the other half of our tribe.

03:32:17.100 --> 03:32:19.379
Even if she did promise the rest of us

03:32:19.379 --> 03:32:20.040
our safety.

03:32:20.100 --> 03:32:22.559
Those are our dragons too.

03:32:22.620 --> 03:32:26.399
We don't bow to you, Belladonna snapped.

03:32:26.459 --> 03:32:27.719
We don't have a queen.

03:32:27.780 --> 03:32:31.079
Sequoia narrowed her eyes, and took

03:32:31.079 --> 03:32:33.180
several long, deep breaths without saying

03:32:33.180 --> 03:32:33.540
anything.

03:32:33.600 --> 03:32:37.260
Finally, she spat, but you do have a

03:32:37.260 --> 03:32:40.319
problem, an incoming army problem.

03:32:40.379 --> 03:32:42.420
And you won't be able to fight them with

03:32:42.420 --> 03:32:43.559
only half the tribe.

03:32:43.620 --> 03:32:46.620
Even a full leaf wing tribe wasn't able

03:32:46.620 --> 03:32:48.120
to stand against them last time.

03:32:48.180 --> 03:32:51.000
And our numbers are much smaller now.

03:32:51.059 --> 03:32:54.659
How do you know we have an incoming army

03:32:54.659 --> 03:32:55.139
problem?

03:32:55.200 --> 03:32:57.000
Belladonna scoffed.

03:32:57.059 --> 03:32:58.739
Maybe we scared them.

03:32:58.799 --> 03:33:01.079
Maybe they're licking their wounds and

03:33:01.079 --> 03:33:03.239
wondering if we're vengeful ghosts.

03:33:03.479 --> 03:33:05.159
The queen shook her head.

03:33:05.219 --> 03:33:07.319
I know wasp.

03:33:07.379 --> 03:33:09.840
She strikes back the moment she's

03:33:09.840 --> 03:33:10.319
struck.

03:33:10.379 --> 03:33:13.559
I estimate we have a day, maybe two.

03:33:13.620 --> 03:33:16.379
While they put out the fire, tend to

03:33:16.379 --> 03:33:18.479
their wounded, and relocate their eggs

03:33:18.479 --> 03:33:19.500
and dragonettes.

03:33:19.559 --> 03:33:22.440
Then perhaps a day to gather her hoard

03:33:22.440 --> 03:33:23.040
and travel here.

03:33:23.159 --> 03:33:24.899
More likely less.

03:33:24.959 --> 03:33:27.180
If they're not on the border of the

03:33:27.180 --> 03:33:29.579
poison jungle by tonight, they will be by

03:33:29.579 --> 03:33:30.360
tomorrow morning.

03:33:30.420 --> 03:33:32.040
Tonight?

03:33:32.100 --> 03:33:33.299
Willow gasped.

03:33:33.420 --> 03:33:35.520
That's ridiculous.

03:33:35.579 --> 03:33:37.620
Belladonna growled.

03:33:37.680 --> 03:33:40.440
She can't organize her army or get war

03:33:40.440 --> 03:33:41.819
ready that quickly.

03:33:41.879 --> 03:33:44.879
Yes, she can.

03:33:44.940 --> 03:33:46.260
Cricket said.

03:33:46.319 --> 03:33:48.899
She doesn't need to waste time sending

03:33:48.899 --> 03:33:51.780
messengers, or waiting for dragons to say

03:33:51.780 --> 03:33:53.399
their goodbyes or any of that.

03:33:53.459 --> 03:33:56.219
She'll just slither into all their heads

03:33:56.219 --> 03:33:59.219
and make them come to her, whether they

03:33:59.219 --> 03:34:00.180
want to or not.

03:34:00.239 --> 03:34:03.899
I told you about the mind control.

03:34:03.959 --> 03:34:06.420
Queen Sequoia said with a sigh.

03:34:06.479 --> 03:34:09.360
But you never quite believed me.

03:34:09.479 --> 03:34:13.020
She stood up, lifted the vine off the

03:34:13.020 --> 03:34:14.940
back of her throne, and held it out for

03:34:14.940 --> 03:34:15.600
everyone to see.

03:34:15.659 --> 03:34:19.319
This is the other reason she won't waste

03:34:19.319 --> 03:34:20.100
any time.

03:34:20.219 --> 03:34:23.040
She needs this plant to keep her hold on

03:34:23.040 --> 03:34:25.620
her tribe, but Sundu and her friends

03:34:25.620 --> 03:34:26.760
burned up her supply.

03:34:26.819 --> 03:34:31.979
Which was a good idea, Swartell objected

03:34:31.979 --> 03:34:33.239
just so we're clear.

03:34:33.299 --> 03:34:35.700
It was very heroic, and a blow for

03:34:35.700 --> 03:34:37.680
justice and freedom, and I was definitely

03:34:37.680 --> 03:34:38.280
involved.

03:34:38.340 --> 03:34:42.059
She might have more of the plant, Cricket

03:34:42.059 --> 03:34:42.479
said.

03:34:42.540 --> 03:34:45.239
We burned one greenhouse, but she could

03:34:45.239 --> 03:34:46.379
have a backup somewhere.

03:34:46.440 --> 03:34:47.340
Couldn't she?

03:34:47.399 --> 03:34:49.799
Maybe, said the queen.

03:34:49.860 --> 03:34:52.799
But she also knows where to find as much

03:34:52.799 --> 03:34:53.579
as she needs.

03:34:53.639 --> 03:34:55.739
She pointed out the window.

03:34:55.799 --> 03:34:57.299
Right here.

03:34:57.360 --> 03:35:00.120
And the poison jungle, where it came

03:35:00.120 --> 03:35:00.420
from.

03:35:00.479 --> 03:35:02.700
It came from here?

03:35:02.760 --> 03:35:03.780
Sundu said.

03:35:03.840 --> 03:35:04.860
Are you sure?

03:35:04.979 --> 03:35:06.780
I haven't been able to sense it

03:35:06.780 --> 03:35:07.200
anywhere.

03:35:07.260 --> 03:35:10.620
That's because it's quarantined.

03:35:10.680 --> 03:35:14.159
Queen Sequoia frowned at the vine. as

03:35:14.159 --> 03:35:15.239
though it didn't deserve to live.

03:35:15.299 --> 03:35:18.959
It only grows in one particular corner of

03:35:18.959 --> 03:35:21.719
the jungle, guarded by a dragon named

03:35:21.719 --> 03:35:23.940
Hawthorne, who is forbidden to let it

03:35:23.940 --> 03:35:24.239
escape.

03:35:24.360 --> 03:35:26.159
Really?

03:35:26.219 --> 03:35:29.340
Hazel breathed, her eyes wide.

03:35:29.399 --> 03:35:31.079
You've never told me about this.

03:35:31.139 --> 03:35:34.799
I've never heard of it either, growled

03:35:34.799 --> 03:35:35.579
Belladonna.

03:35:35.639 --> 03:35:38.879
It's not a secret we want anyone to know

03:35:38.879 --> 03:35:40.200
said the Queen.

03:35:40.260 --> 03:35:43.200
It's the most dangerous plant in the

03:35:43.200 --> 03:35:44.399
whole poison jungle.

03:35:44.459 --> 03:35:46.739
She plucked one of the wilting flowers

03:35:46.739 --> 03:35:49.020
off the vine, and held it before her

03:35:49.020 --> 03:35:49.260
eyes.

03:35:49.319 --> 03:35:52.200
The pale white of the petals was starting

03:35:52.200 --> 03:35:53.280
to fade to brown.

03:35:53.340 --> 03:35:56.219
But at the heart of the wilting flower

03:35:56.219 --> 03:35:59.399
was a glistening dark red seed, so dark.

03:35:59.459 --> 03:36:00.719
It was almost black.

03:36:00.780 --> 03:36:03.180
Have any of you?

03:36:03.299 --> 03:36:04.680
asked the queen.

03:36:04.739 --> 03:36:07.860
Heard of the legend of the hive.

03:36:07.920 --> 03:36:12.000
Part two.

03:36:12.059 --> 03:36:14.280
Tendrils and teeth.

03:36:14.340 --> 03:36:16.559
Chapter 11.

03:36:16.920 --> 03:36:19.079
The what?

03:36:19.139 --> 03:36:20.819
Belladonna barked.

03:36:20.879 --> 03:36:21.780
Legend?

03:36:21.840 --> 03:36:23.639
Is it story hour now?

03:36:23.700 --> 03:36:25.260
I don't care about an old legend.

03:36:25.319 --> 03:36:29.879
This is important, said Queen Sequoia.

03:36:29.940 --> 03:36:32.700
She held out one talent to Hazel, who

03:36:32.700 --> 03:36:33.659
went forward to take it.

03:36:33.719 --> 03:36:36.059
Do any of you know it?

03:36:36.120 --> 03:36:39.540
Sundu glanced around, but all the other

03:36:39.540 --> 03:36:41.159
dragons in the room were shaking their

03:36:41.159 --> 03:36:41.639
heads too.

03:36:41.700 --> 03:36:43.799
The queen sighed again.

03:36:43.860 --> 03:36:46.500
Sundew kind of wanted to poke her in the

03:36:46.500 --> 03:36:49.020
snout with her sharpest claw, once for

03:36:49.020 --> 03:36:49.979
every sigh.

03:36:50.040 --> 03:36:52.139
What did she have to be so tired about?

03:36:52.260 --> 03:36:55.379
After 50 years of cowering in the jungle

03:36:55.379 --> 03:36:57.659
and not fighting the bad guys.

03:36:57.719 --> 03:37:01.260
It was a story from long before Clear

03:37:01.260 --> 03:37:02.100
Side's time.

03:37:02.159 --> 03:37:06.000
Queen Sequoia began, guiding Hazel to sit

03:37:06.000 --> 03:37:06.420
at her feet.

03:37:06.479 --> 03:37:08.760
The princess looked up at her great

03:37:08.760 --> 03:37:10.680
grandmother with wide eyed awe.

03:37:10.739 --> 03:37:13.500
Sundoo wondered if bumblebee would look

03:37:13.500 --> 03:37:14.520
like that when she could understand

03:37:14.520 --> 03:37:15.299
stories.

03:37:15.360 --> 03:37:17.459
Not that I care.

03:37:17.520 --> 03:37:19.139
I certainly won't be the one telling

03:37:19.139 --> 03:37:19.440
them.

03:37:19.500 --> 03:37:23.040
The legend begins with the earliest days

03:37:23.040 --> 03:37:25.379
of dragons arriving on this continent

03:37:25.379 --> 03:37:26.520
said the queen.

03:37:26.639 --> 03:37:30.120
Back when the Leaf Wing tribe and the

03:37:30.120 --> 03:37:32.940
Beetle Wing tribe were new, and they came

03:37:32.940 --> 03:37:34.979
to these shores to escape trouble in the

03:37:34.979 --> 03:37:36.120
distant kingdoms.

03:37:36.180 --> 03:37:37.620
The what?

03:37:37.680 --> 03:37:39.180
Swartell broke in.

03:37:39.299 --> 03:37:40.739
What's a beetle wing?

03:37:40.860 --> 03:37:43.979
That's what silk wings and hive wings

03:37:43.979 --> 03:37:46.799
used to be, before Clearside came along

03:37:46.799 --> 03:37:48.959
and her ancestors split them into 2

03:37:48.959 --> 03:37:49.379
tribes.

03:37:49.500 --> 03:37:52.680
The beetle wings were more like silk

03:37:52.680 --> 03:37:55.680
wings, according to the stories. except

03:37:55.680 --> 03:37:58.379
that some of them had deadly weapons, like

03:37:58.379 --> 03:38:00.180
the ones you now find among the hive

03:38:00.180 --> 03:38:02.819
wings, shooting deadly venom from their

03:38:02.819 --> 03:38:05.459
fangs, in particular, according to the

03:38:05.459 --> 03:38:06.059
old stories.

03:38:06.120 --> 03:38:10.200
Tsunami gave a little jump, as if she'd

03:38:10.200 --> 03:38:11.040
been startled by something.

03:38:11.100 --> 03:38:13.200
Whoa.

03:38:13.319 --> 03:38:16.860
Sortell looked at his claws, as if he was

03:38:16.860 --> 03:38:18.659
hoping venomous stingers might suddenly

03:38:18.659 --> 03:38:19.260
pop out of them.

03:38:19.319 --> 03:38:22.379
What was the trouble that they had to

03:38:22.379 --> 03:38:23.040
escape from?

03:38:23.100 --> 03:38:24.360
Cricket asked.

03:38:24.420 --> 03:38:27.780
Probably the same trouble there always is

03:38:27.780 --> 03:38:29.100
Io said.

03:38:29.219 --> 03:38:31.559
Dragons being cruel to other dragons

03:38:31.559 --> 03:38:33.719
because they don't look or act exactly

03:38:33.719 --> 03:38:34.319
like themselves.

03:38:34.379 --> 03:38:37.500
The legend doesn't say.

03:38:37.620 --> 03:38:40.860
What it does say, the queen went on.

03:38:40.920 --> 03:38:43.920
Is that the 1st dragons who landed on

03:38:43.920 --> 03:38:45.959
Pentala encountered something...

03:38:45.959 --> 03:38:47.879
Very strange.

03:38:47.940 --> 03:38:52.079
Her voice dropped so low, sundew could

03:38:52.079 --> 03:38:53.639
barely hear her over the sound of the

03:38:53.639 --> 03:38:54.299
rain outside.

03:38:54.360 --> 03:38:58.559
The night they arrived, as they all

03:38:58.559 --> 03:38:59.159
slept.

03:38:59.219 --> 03:39:02.280
The earth below them began to seethe with

03:39:02.280 --> 03:39:02.700
motion.

03:39:02.760 --> 03:39:07.379
Tiny legs crawled across their scales, and

03:39:07.379 --> 03:39:09.540
then more, and then more of them.

03:39:09.600 --> 03:39:12.959
The dragons awoke suddenly from their

03:39:12.959 --> 03:39:14.700
dreams into a true nightmare.

03:39:14.760 --> 03:39:17.159
They were covered in fire ants.

03:39:17.280 --> 03:39:21.540
Their shrieks rose up to the 3 moons, and

03:39:21.540 --> 03:39:24.059
they ran to the ocean, but even as they

03:39:24.059 --> 03:39:27.120
ran, more colonies of ants boiled up out

03:39:27.120 --> 03:39:28.319
of the ground and attacked.

03:39:28.379 --> 03:39:31.739
They marched up the dragon's legs and

03:39:31.739 --> 03:39:34.500
burrowed between their scales and dug

03:39:34.500 --> 03:39:35.940
their mandibles into their skin.

03:39:36.000 --> 03:39:39.479
The ants didn't let go as the dragons

03:39:39.479 --> 03:39:40.379
plunged into the sea.

03:39:40.500 --> 03:39:42.959
They didn't try to save themselves.

03:39:43.020 --> 03:39:44.459
They held on.

03:39:44.579 --> 03:39:48.959
Like grim death, until at last the ants

03:39:48.959 --> 03:39:49.440
drowned.

03:39:49.559 --> 03:39:52.260
Yeesh.

03:39:52.319 --> 03:39:55.319
Sortell said, with a theatrical shudder.

03:39:55.379 --> 03:40:00.479
But the ends were only the beginning, said

03:40:00.479 --> 03:40:01.440
Queen Sequoia.

03:40:01.559 --> 03:40:05.280
The next morning, as the dragons were

03:40:05.280 --> 03:40:07.379
limping back to their campsite, they

03:40:07.379 --> 03:40:09.899
heard buzzing in the air, getting closer

03:40:09.899 --> 03:40:10.979
and closer.

03:40:11.100 --> 03:40:14.340
When they looked up, the sky was dark

03:40:14.340 --> 03:40:15.180
with bees.

03:40:15.239 --> 03:40:18.120
So many bees, they blotted out the sun.

03:40:18.180 --> 03:40:21.299
The bees descended and attacked all at

03:40:21.299 --> 03:40:23.459
once, just as the ants had done.

03:40:23.579 --> 03:40:26.760
And again, the dragons were forced to

03:40:26.760 --> 03:40:28.680
flee into the bay and hide below the

03:40:28.680 --> 03:40:28.920
water.

03:40:28.979 --> 03:40:32.399
The legend says they were saved by their

03:40:32.399 --> 03:40:35.159
flame silks, who burned the bees out of

03:40:35.159 --> 03:40:35.459
the sky.

03:40:35.520 --> 03:40:39.600
So the legend of the hive is about creepy

03:40:39.600 --> 03:40:40.620
ants and bees?

03:40:40.680 --> 03:40:41.879
Io asked.

03:40:41.940 --> 03:40:43.559
The queen shook her head.

03:40:43.620 --> 03:40:45.180
It got worse.

03:40:45.239 --> 03:40:47.879
And stranger.

03:40:48.000 --> 03:40:50.639
The swarms of insects kept coming.

03:40:50.700 --> 03:40:54.000
And the next attacks came from insects

03:40:54.000 --> 03:40:55.920
that normally don't work in groups.

03:40:55.979 --> 03:40:59.100
Imagine armies of venomous centipedes.

03:40:59.219 --> 03:41:02.700
Battalions of setse flies, swarms of

03:41:02.700 --> 03:41:03.899
bombardier beetles.

03:41:03.959 --> 03:41:07.319
They killed dragon after dragon with

03:41:07.319 --> 03:41:09.360
mindless, unwavering ferocity.

03:41:09.420 --> 03:41:12.780
Some of the dragons vanish to the night

03:41:12.780 --> 03:41:14.159
never to be seen again.

03:41:14.219 --> 03:41:16.799
Others went down right in front of their

03:41:16.799 --> 03:41:19.559
friends, suddenly covered in assassin

03:41:19.559 --> 03:41:19.920
bugs.

03:41:20.040 --> 03:41:23.219
Of course the dragons fought back.

03:41:23.280 --> 03:41:26.579
They'd come too far to run away, and

03:41:26.579 --> 03:41:28.379
according to the story, they were

03:41:28.379 --> 03:41:30.420
refugees who could never return to the

03:41:30.420 --> 03:41:31.139
distant kingdoms.

03:41:31.260 --> 03:41:33.479
So they fought to stay.

03:41:33.540 --> 03:41:36.360
But it seemed that whenever they struck

03:41:36.360 --> 03:41:38.639
down one group of attackers, another

03:41:38.639 --> 03:41:40.319
would instantly appear in its place.

03:41:40.379 --> 03:41:43.260
The insects were followed by coils of

03:41:43.260 --> 03:41:46.260
rattlesnakes, a vast pride of lions

03:41:46.260 --> 03:41:48.180
murders of crows.

03:41:48.299 --> 03:41:52.200
The queen lowered her voice again, staring

03:41:52.200 --> 03:41:53.760
into the heart of the pale flower.

03:41:53.819 --> 03:41:56.520
These were not ordinary attacks.

03:41:56.639 --> 03:41:58.739
The animals moved like a single

03:41:58.739 --> 03:41:59.399
organism.

03:41:59.459 --> 03:42:02.219
If a crow was struck on one end of the

03:42:02.219 --> 03:42:04.500
battlefield, the crows at the far end

03:42:04.500 --> 03:42:05.760
somehow knew instantly.

03:42:05.819 --> 03:42:09.299
The snakes attacked simultaneously

03:42:09.299 --> 03:42:11.700
targeting their victims with coordinated

03:42:11.700 --> 03:42:12.540
precision.

03:42:12.600 --> 03:42:14.399
But how?

03:42:14.520 --> 03:42:15.540
Cricket asked.

03:42:15.600 --> 03:42:18.180
This sounds like a myth that's gotten a

03:42:18.180 --> 03:42:19.139
little warped over time.

03:42:19.200 --> 03:42:21.600
Are you saying this plant works on

03:42:21.600 --> 03:42:22.260
anything?

03:42:22.319 --> 03:42:26.219
Reptiles, birds, insects, and mammals?

03:42:26.280 --> 03:42:28.620
How is that possible scientifically?

03:42:28.680 --> 03:42:32.340
Um, I have a more important question

03:42:32.340 --> 03:42:33.840
Sandu interjected.

03:42:33.899 --> 03:42:35.879
Who was controlling them?

03:42:35.940 --> 03:42:39.659
She realized she'd twined her tail around

03:42:39.659 --> 03:42:41.520
Willows at some point during the story.

03:42:41.579 --> 03:42:44.280
Probably while the ice was trickling down

03:42:44.280 --> 03:42:44.819
her spine.

03:42:44.879 --> 03:42:48.120
But Belladonna's eyes were riveted on the

03:42:48.120 --> 03:42:50.579
queen, and Sundu couldn't make herself

03:42:50.579 --> 03:42:52.319
pull away from Willow's comforting

03:42:52.319 --> 03:42:52.739
warmth.

03:42:52.799 --> 03:42:55.860
Queen Sequoia closed her front talons

03:42:55.860 --> 03:42:58.139
around the flower, and looked straight at

03:42:58.139 --> 03:42:58.860
sundew.

03:42:58.920 --> 03:43:00.299
Nobody knows.

03:43:00.360 --> 03:43:02.219
What?

03:43:02.340 --> 03:43:03.840
said Swordtail.

03:43:03.899 --> 03:43:06.299
Three moons.

03:43:06.360 --> 03:43:09.059
I think my chills have chills, tsunami

03:43:09.059 --> 03:43:11.340
said, shaking her wings out as though she

03:43:11.340 --> 03:43:12.180
couldn't feel them anymore.

03:43:12.239 --> 03:43:15.239
How could nobody know?

03:43:15.299 --> 03:43:16.440
Cricket asked.

03:43:16.500 --> 03:43:18.600
Didn't they find the dragon behind all

03:43:18.600 --> 03:43:19.020
the attacks?

03:43:19.079 --> 03:43:22.920
The tribes never found anyone, said the

03:43:22.920 --> 03:43:23.219
queen.

03:43:23.280 --> 03:43:26.700
They searched far and wide for years, but

03:43:26.700 --> 03:43:28.079
there were no other dragons on the

03:43:28.079 --> 03:43:29.760
continent, as far as they could tell.

03:43:29.819 --> 03:43:33.899
But Hazel started, then trailed off.

03:43:33.959 --> 03:43:35.819
What they found.

03:43:35.940 --> 03:43:37.079
Was this?

03:43:37.200 --> 03:43:40.440
Queen Sequoia opened her talons to reveal

03:43:40.440 --> 03:43:41.159
the flower again.

03:43:41.219 --> 03:43:44.459
The seed inside it glistened, like a

03:43:44.459 --> 03:43:46.079
wicked little eye, watching them.

03:43:46.200 --> 03:43:49.020
We call it the breath of evil.

03:43:49.139 --> 03:43:52.739
Seems a little dramatic, Belladonna

03:43:52.739 --> 03:43:53.159
muttered.

03:43:53.219 --> 03:43:56.219
This vine covered everything, said the

03:43:56.219 --> 03:43:56.459
Queen.

03:43:56.520 --> 03:43:58.920
The legend described it exactly.

03:43:58.979 --> 03:44:01.319
It is the part of the story that has

03:44:01.319 --> 03:44:02.819
survived the most intact.

03:44:02.940 --> 03:44:05.520
As though the storytellers knew how

03:44:05.520 --> 03:44:07.260
important it would be for us to recognize

03:44:07.260 --> 03:44:09.059
it, if it ever appeared again.

03:44:09.120 --> 03:44:12.360
This plant was wound around every tree

03:44:12.360 --> 03:44:15.899
through every meadow, in every marsh, no

03:44:15.899 --> 03:44:16.860
matter the landscape.

03:44:16.920 --> 03:44:19.500
It derived across all of Pentala.

03:44:19.559 --> 03:44:22.379
But the dragons from the distant kingdom

03:44:22.379 --> 03:44:24.719
soon discovered, that when they destroyed

03:44:24.719 --> 03:44:27.059
this plant, the attacks waned.

03:44:27.120 --> 03:44:29.579
When they cleared all the vine from an

03:44:29.579 --> 03:44:32.159
area, that area gradually became safe to

03:44:32.159 --> 03:44:34.620
live in, no more attacks.

03:44:34.680 --> 03:44:37.319
The animals began to behave like normal

03:44:37.319 --> 03:44:38.280
animals.

03:44:38.340 --> 03:44:40.139
So long as they lived within the

03:44:40.139 --> 03:44:42.719
perimeter the dragons made. where there

03:44:42.719 --> 03:44:43.620
was no breath of evil.

03:44:43.680 --> 03:44:45.780
I don't like this name.

03:44:45.840 --> 03:44:48.659
Swartell said, or this plant.

03:44:48.719 --> 03:44:50.280
I just want that on the record.

03:44:50.340 --> 03:44:51.780
I don't like it at all.

03:44:51.840 --> 03:44:55.379
I can see why Queen Wasp doesn't let us

03:44:55.379 --> 03:44:57.659
hear that story, IO said.

03:44:57.719 --> 03:45:00.479
It might ring a few bells, even inside a

03:45:00.479 --> 03:45:01.799
dense hive wing skull.

03:45:01.860 --> 03:45:05.700
Sundew saw cricket wince, and tuck the

03:45:05.700 --> 03:45:07.680
sling a little tighter around Bumblebee.

03:45:07.739 --> 03:45:10.799
But how does it end?

03:45:10.860 --> 03:45:11.879
Willow asked.

03:45:11.940 --> 03:45:15.479
The legend of the hive, I mean, there's

03:45:15.479 --> 03:45:16.139
not much more.

03:45:16.200 --> 03:45:19.139
Queen Sequoia said, spreading her front

03:45:19.139 --> 03:45:19.799
talons.

03:45:19.860 --> 03:45:23.100
It's all garbled, from millennia of being

03:45:23.100 --> 03:45:23.760
passed down.

03:45:23.879 --> 03:45:26.040
This is how I understand it.

03:45:26.100 --> 03:45:28.920
Something here tried to kill us when our

03:45:28.920 --> 03:45:32.219
ancestors arrived, using mind control to

03:45:32.219 --> 03:45:34.860
turn the wildlife into weapons, but

03:45:34.860 --> 03:45:36.600
destroying the breath of evil took away

03:45:36.600 --> 03:45:37.079
its power.

03:45:37.139 --> 03:45:40.379
Once they realized that, the tribes

03:45:40.379 --> 03:45:42.540
organized expeditions to uproot the plant

03:45:42.540 --> 03:45:43.979
across the whole continent.

03:45:44.040 --> 03:45:45.840
Hang on.

03:45:45.899 --> 03:45:48.180
Can we go back to the thing breathing the

03:45:48.180 --> 03:45:48.600
evil?

03:45:48.659 --> 03:45:49.739
Sundu said.

03:45:49.860 --> 03:45:53.100
The dragon, or dragons, that controlled

03:45:53.100 --> 03:45:53.459
everything?

03:45:53.520 --> 03:45:56.639
Even though the tribes never found it, it

03:45:56.639 --> 03:45:58.079
must have died too, right?

03:45:58.139 --> 03:46:00.600
Once the plants were destroyed and it

03:46:00.600 --> 03:46:03.479
realized it had lost, she paused and

03:46:03.479 --> 03:46:05.159
looked around at the range of frightened

03:46:05.159 --> 03:46:05.760
expressions.

03:46:05.819 --> 03:46:07.260
Right?

03:46:07.379 --> 03:46:10.319
Of course, said the queen.

03:46:10.379 --> 03:46:13.860
This was a very long time ago, 1000s of

03:46:13.860 --> 03:46:14.459
years.

03:46:14.520 --> 03:46:17.100
But I guess the plants weren't all

03:46:17.100 --> 03:46:20.399
destroyed after all, said Cricket, lifting

03:46:20.399 --> 03:46:22.139
her head to face Queen Sequoia.

03:46:22.200 --> 03:46:25.440
The queen rested one talent on Hazel's

03:46:25.440 --> 03:46:26.280
head and sighed.

03:46:26.340 --> 03:46:27.420
No.

03:46:27.479 --> 03:46:29.219
Some of it survived.

03:46:29.340 --> 03:46:31.620
Hidden deep in the poison jungle.

03:46:31.739 --> 03:46:36.360
Where wasp found it, Cricket said slowly

03:46:36.360 --> 03:46:38.700
she must know the legend.

03:46:38.760 --> 03:46:41.639
She must have gone looking for it, hoping

03:46:41.639 --> 03:46:42.540
she could use it herself.

03:46:42.600 --> 03:46:45.239
I wondered how she figured out what to do

03:46:45.239 --> 03:46:45.540
with it.

03:46:45.600 --> 03:46:49.139
And if it once worked on any animal, why

03:46:49.139 --> 03:46:50.940
did she only use it on hive wings?

03:46:51.000 --> 03:46:53.399
Why bother with the tree wars?

03:46:53.399 --> 03:46:55.920
If she could also mind control the leaf

03:46:55.920 --> 03:46:57.299
wings and silk wings?

03:46:57.360 --> 03:46:59.520
Queen Sequoia shuttered?

03:46:59.579 --> 03:47:01.500
I'm sure she tried.

03:47:01.559 --> 03:47:03.239
Belladonna spat.

03:47:03.299 --> 03:47:05.399
Probably doesn't work on a superior

03:47:05.399 --> 03:47:06.840
species like leaf wings.

03:47:06.899 --> 03:47:09.719
Sundew caught IO rolling her eyes.

03:47:09.840 --> 03:47:13.139
The point is, this is where she got it

03:47:13.139 --> 03:47:16.200
from, Sundew said, so this is where

03:47:16.200 --> 03:47:17.520
she'll come to get more of it.

03:47:17.579 --> 03:47:20.219
If we really burned up her whole supply.

03:47:20.280 --> 03:47:24.479
Not if we strike her first. snarled

03:47:24.479 --> 03:47:25.260
Belladonna.

03:47:25.319 --> 03:47:27.659
We're going to burn all their hives.

03:47:27.719 --> 03:47:29.399
I'm planning our next attack now.

03:47:29.520 --> 03:47:32.579
We just need a little more flame silk, and

03:47:32.579 --> 03:47:35.159
Yellow Jacket Hive will be a pile of ash

03:47:35.159 --> 03:47:36.120
before you can blink.

03:47:36.180 --> 03:47:39.719
Wasp isn't going to wait for you to do

03:47:39.719 --> 03:47:41.159
that, Cricket said.

03:47:41.219 --> 03:47:43.200
Queen Sequoia is right.

03:47:43.260 --> 03:47:45.299
She's gathering her army right now.

03:47:45.360 --> 03:47:47.760
She'll be here before you can convince

03:47:47.760 --> 03:47:49.739
Blue to give you any more flame silk

03:47:49.739 --> 03:47:52.200
before you could even get to Yellowjacket

03:47:52.200 --> 03:47:53.639
Hive if you already had it.

03:47:53.700 --> 03:47:56.280
We must act quickly.

03:47:56.399 --> 03:47:59.700
Queen Sequoia rose from her throne with a

03:47:59.700 --> 03:48:02.219
commanding expression, and Sandu could

03:48:02.219 --> 03:48:03.959
suddenly see why a whole tribe would have

03:48:03.959 --> 03:48:06.600
followed her into battle over and over, no

03:48:06.600 --> 03:48:07.739
matter how often they lost.

03:48:07.799 --> 03:48:11.520
Belladonna, wolf's bane, and the silk

03:48:11.520 --> 03:48:14.700
wings, the queen said, pointing to Io and

03:48:14.700 --> 03:48:15.360
sword tail.

03:48:15.420 --> 03:48:18.000
Wolf's bane looked slightly startled that

03:48:18.000 --> 03:48:18.600
she knew his name.

03:48:18.659 --> 03:48:21.180
You 4 will come with me.

03:48:21.239 --> 03:48:23.459
We will gather our strongest warriors

03:48:23.459 --> 03:48:26.459
from both villages, and fly to the

03:48:26.459 --> 03:48:29.219
snarling river, to prepare for wasps

03:48:29.219 --> 03:48:29.520
attack.

03:48:29.579 --> 03:48:31.860
We need to strengthen the jungle's

03:48:31.860 --> 03:48:33.899
defenses and hold them off as long as

03:48:33.899 --> 03:48:34.200
possible.

03:48:34.260 --> 03:48:38.879
Um, Swartell said, I mean, that sounds

03:48:38.879 --> 03:48:43.079
awesome, but how exactly are we going to

03:48:43.079 --> 03:48:43.319
help?

03:48:43.379 --> 03:48:45.600
He pointed to himself and IO.

03:48:45.719 --> 03:48:49.260
By talking to the flame silk, Sequoia

03:48:49.260 --> 03:48:49.500
said.

03:48:49.559 --> 03:48:52.500
I understand his reluctance to burn down

03:48:52.500 --> 03:48:53.159
hives.

03:48:53.219 --> 03:48:56.100
But I hope you can convince him how much

03:48:56.100 --> 03:48:58.260
we'll need him in battle when wasp

03:48:58.260 --> 03:48:58.739
attacks.

03:48:58.799 --> 03:49:01.799
Also, one of you must contact the

03:49:01.799 --> 03:49:02.579
chrysalis.

03:49:02.639 --> 03:49:05.219
If they want to rise up and overthrow

03:49:05.219 --> 03:49:07.680
Queen Wasp, now is the time.

03:49:07.739 --> 03:49:10.319
They must bring their dragons to fight

03:49:10.319 --> 03:49:14.399
alongside us, or WASP will win, and they

03:49:14.399 --> 03:49:15.719
will never have a chance to be free.

03:49:15.840 --> 03:49:17.940
What about me?

03:49:18.000 --> 03:49:20.700
Hazel asked. shouldn't I go with you?

03:49:20.760 --> 03:49:23.819
The queen's face softened, looking down

03:49:23.819 --> 03:49:25.020
at her great granddaughter.

03:49:25.079 --> 03:49:29.520
No, she said, I won't be able to think

03:49:29.520 --> 03:49:30.659
clearly with you there.

03:49:30.719 --> 03:49:33.959
I need to know you're safe here, and that

03:49:33.959 --> 03:49:36.360
the rest of the tribe is safe too, because

03:49:36.360 --> 03:49:37.799
you'll be in charge of them.

03:49:38.040 --> 03:49:40.979
If Wasp gets past us, you'll need to

03:49:40.979 --> 03:49:41.879
decide what to do.

03:49:41.940 --> 03:49:44.159
Fight her or run.

03:49:44.219 --> 03:49:46.559
Run where?

03:49:46.620 --> 03:49:47.579
Cricket asked.

03:49:47.639 --> 03:49:51.239
Deeper into the jungle, answered the

03:49:51.239 --> 03:49:51.540
queen.

03:49:51.600 --> 03:49:55.260
Or perhaps farther.

03:49:55.319 --> 03:49:57.840
She turned her gaze to tsunami.

03:49:57.899 --> 03:50:01.139
That's what I've been saying, Cricket

03:50:01.139 --> 03:50:01.620
yelped.

03:50:01.680 --> 03:50:02.879
Right, Sundu?

03:50:02.940 --> 03:50:04.920
I said we should escape to the distant

03:50:04.920 --> 03:50:05.340
kingdoms.

03:50:05.399 --> 03:50:09.959
Hey, whoa, tsunami said, spreading her

03:50:09.959 --> 03:50:11.280
wings and looking alarmed.

03:50:11.340 --> 03:50:12.899
It's not that easy.

03:50:13.020 --> 03:50:14.879
Can any of you swim?

03:50:15.000 --> 03:50:16.860
Or breathe underwater?

03:50:16.979 --> 03:50:21.299
We can swim, Willow said, in the river.

03:50:21.360 --> 03:50:23.399
Maybe not like you swim, though.

03:50:23.399 --> 03:50:25.860
All right, probably nothing like you.

03:50:25.920 --> 03:50:29.280
Not like, swim across an entire ocean for

03:50:29.280 --> 03:50:31.739
days and days kind of swimming, no.

03:50:31.799 --> 03:50:35.040
Sundoo realized that her mother was

03:50:35.040 --> 03:50:37.620
glaring narrowly at willow, and also

03:50:37.620 --> 03:50:40.319
realized, a half 2nd later, that she

03:50:40.319 --> 03:50:42.479
still had her tail twined with willows

03:50:42.479 --> 03:50:46.079
and, oh dear, that probably had something

03:50:46.079 --> 03:50:48.059
to do with the look on Belladonna's

03:50:48.059 --> 03:50:48.179
face.

03:50:48.239 --> 03:50:52.440
Well, too bad, she thought defiantly.

03:50:52.500 --> 03:50:54.059
I'm not letting go now.

03:50:54.120 --> 03:50:56.579
I'm not ever letting go of her again.

03:50:56.700 --> 03:51:00.659
If this is it, all our truth spilled over

03:51:00.659 --> 03:51:03.000
the table, then this is my truth.

03:51:03.059 --> 03:51:05.100
I choose Willow.

03:51:05.159 --> 03:51:08.819
Even if she is a sapwing and not mandrake

03:51:08.819 --> 03:51:10.260
mom.

03:51:10.379 --> 03:51:14.819
Right, tsunami said to Willow, so how

03:51:14.819 --> 03:51:15.600
would you all get there?

03:51:15.659 --> 03:51:19.079
Sorry, it just, it seems unlikely.

03:51:19.139 --> 03:51:22.020
I've been trying to think about how we

03:51:22.020 --> 03:51:23.940
could bring other dragons over here to

03:51:23.940 --> 03:51:28.079
help you, if we decided to do that, she

03:51:28.079 --> 03:51:30.420
added quickly, glancing at Sundew.

03:51:30.479 --> 03:51:32.399
And I can't think of anything.

03:51:32.459 --> 03:51:35.399
Maybe if my friend Starflight were here

03:51:35.399 --> 03:51:36.899
or Kibli.

03:51:37.020 --> 03:51:39.719
Hmm, she crinkled her snout.

03:51:39.780 --> 03:51:42.180
I might have a way to ask them though.

03:51:42.239 --> 03:51:43.620
What?

03:51:43.680 --> 03:51:45.659
Sword Tell asked, how?

03:51:45.719 --> 03:51:46.739
How would you do that?

03:51:46.799 --> 03:51:50.399
Distant kingdom super dragon magic

03:51:50.399 --> 03:51:53.280
Cricket whispered, her eyes shining.

03:51:53.340 --> 03:51:55.200
Ahem.

03:51:55.260 --> 03:51:57.540
The queen said, taking over the

03:51:57.540 --> 03:51:58.319
conversation again.

03:51:58.379 --> 03:52:02.459
So, Hazel and Tsunami, you'll stay here

03:52:02.459 --> 03:52:05.219
and try to formulate a plan, a way to get

03:52:05.219 --> 03:52:07.500
to the distant kingdoms if we need to.

03:52:07.559 --> 03:52:10.799
Or another solution in case Queen Wasp

03:52:10.799 --> 03:52:11.700
reaches the village.

03:52:11.760 --> 03:52:14.579
Belladonna, you may send a few of your

03:52:14.579 --> 03:52:15.659
dragons to work with them.

03:52:15.719 --> 03:52:17.459
Biblus, perhaps.

03:52:17.520 --> 03:52:19.500
I understand she's quite clever.

03:52:19.559 --> 03:52:23.159
Yes, I see how much information your

03:52:23.159 --> 03:52:24.120
scouts have gathered.

03:52:24.180 --> 03:52:25.500
No need to rub it in.

03:52:25.559 --> 03:52:27.540
Belladonna snapped.

03:52:27.600 --> 03:52:30.840
Queen Sequoia closed her eyes, lifted her

03:52:30.840 --> 03:52:33.299
chin, paused for about the amount of time

03:52:33.299 --> 03:52:35.639
it took to count to 10, and then turned

03:52:35.639 --> 03:52:37.319
her gaze directly on sundew.

03:52:37.440 --> 03:52:40.139
The rest of you, she said.

03:52:40.200 --> 03:52:43.079
Sundo, willow, hive wing.

03:52:43.139 --> 03:52:45.180
You must seek the guardian of the breath

03:52:45.180 --> 03:52:46.260
of evil vine.

03:52:46.379 --> 03:52:48.600
Hawthorne has had 50 years to work.

03:52:48.659 --> 03:52:51.840
It's a long shot, but maybe he finally

03:52:51.840 --> 03:52:53.879
found the one thing that could truly save

03:52:53.879 --> 03:52:54.120
us.

03:52:54.180 --> 03:52:56.340
An antidote?

03:52:56.399 --> 03:52:57.540
Cricket blurted.

03:52:57.600 --> 03:53:00.360
Sequoia arched an eyebrow at her.

03:53:00.479 --> 03:53:02.579
Yes, she said.

03:53:02.639 --> 03:53:06.059
That was my dramatic line, young dragon

03:53:06.059 --> 03:53:07.319
an antidote.

03:53:07.440 --> 03:53:09.600
Something that can break the mind

03:53:09.600 --> 03:53:10.200
control?

03:53:10.260 --> 03:53:13.440
Cricket said, too excited to be chastised

03:53:13.440 --> 03:53:15.780
a way to free the rest of my tribe.

03:53:15.899 --> 03:53:20.520
That was our hope, and his quest, said

03:53:20.520 --> 03:53:20.940
the queen.

03:53:21.000 --> 03:53:22.860
But he never returned.

03:53:22.920 --> 03:53:25.620
I have heard nothing in all these years

03:53:25.620 --> 03:53:28.559
so perhaps it was impossible.

03:53:28.620 --> 03:53:30.840
Or perhaps he is dead.

03:53:30.899 --> 03:53:34.020
Or perhaps we'll find him and save

03:53:34.020 --> 03:53:34.739
everybody.

03:53:34.799 --> 03:53:37.260
Cricket bounced on her talons so

03:53:37.260 --> 03:53:39.719
enthusiastically that Bumblebee woke up

03:53:39.719 --> 03:53:40.319
with a snort.

03:53:40.379 --> 03:53:42.899
Don't get your hopes up too high.

03:53:43.020 --> 03:53:44.520
The queen warned.

03:53:44.579 --> 03:53:46.440
After all this time on his own.

03:53:46.500 --> 03:53:49.200
I'm not sure he could possibly still be

03:53:49.200 --> 03:53:49.500
alive.

03:53:49.559 --> 03:53:53.639
Not to mention, said Io, that even if you

03:53:53.639 --> 03:53:55.979
do cure all the hive wings, they might

03:53:55.979 --> 03:53:58.079
still decide to fight for wasp with their

03:53:58.079 --> 03:53:59.100
own free will.

03:53:59.159 --> 03:54:02.459
This finally did make crickets wings

03:54:02.459 --> 03:54:03.059
sink.

03:54:03.180 --> 03:54:05.579
They won't, she protested.

03:54:05.639 --> 03:54:07.200
I'm sure they won't.

03:54:07.260 --> 03:54:09.719
Some of them won't, anyway.

03:54:09.780 --> 03:54:12.780
She trailed off, worrying one of her

03:54:12.780 --> 03:54:13.319
claws.

03:54:13.379 --> 03:54:15.719
Where is this dragon?

03:54:15.780 --> 03:54:17.219
Sundew asked the queen.

03:54:17.280 --> 03:54:21.120
In the eye of the jungle, Sequoia

03:54:21.120 --> 03:54:22.979
answered, I'll give you a map.

03:54:23.040 --> 03:54:25.799
It'll be a dangerous journey, but I think

03:54:25.799 --> 03:54:27.360
you're the right dragons to undertake

03:54:27.360 --> 03:54:27.540
it.

03:54:27.600 --> 03:54:30.479
You might want to leave the dragonette

03:54:30.479 --> 03:54:32.399
with us, though, Hazel offered.

03:54:32.459 --> 03:54:35.459
Cricket closed her wings protectively

03:54:35.459 --> 03:54:38.040
around Bumblebee, who shoved them aside

03:54:38.040 --> 03:54:38.700
to peek out again.

03:54:38.819 --> 03:54:41.819
Her eyes were enormous, and she was

03:54:41.819 --> 03:54:43.559
quieter than Sundew had ever seen her.

03:54:43.620 --> 03:54:47.159
I'd rather keep her with me, Cricket

03:54:47.159 --> 03:54:47.520
said.

03:54:47.579 --> 03:54:50.399
She'll be fine, Sandu agreed.

03:54:50.459 --> 03:54:51.540
We'll keep her safe.

03:54:51.600 --> 03:54:54.180
Just a moment.

03:54:54.180 --> 03:54:56.340
Belladonna hissed.

03:54:56.399 --> 03:54:59.399
I'm not letting my daughter stroll off on

03:54:59.399 --> 03:55:03.120
a suicide mission with only these 2 these

03:55:03.120 --> 03:55:05.100
2 strangers alongside her.

03:55:05.159 --> 03:55:08.340
She cast a vicious look at cricket and

03:55:08.340 --> 03:55:11.100
Willow, especially Willow, Sundew

03:55:11.100 --> 03:55:11.399
thought.

03:55:11.459 --> 03:55:14.459
I insist they take 2 of my dragons with

03:55:14.459 --> 03:55:14.700
them.

03:55:14.760 --> 03:55:18.360
Sundew guessed immediately where this was

03:55:18.360 --> 03:55:18.719
going.

03:55:18.780 --> 03:55:22.979
Ah, no, mother, why?

03:55:23.040 --> 03:55:24.120
She protested.

03:55:24.180 --> 03:55:27.719
Either you don't go, Belladonna said

03:55:27.719 --> 03:55:30.600
firmly, or you take mandrake and Nettle

03:55:30.600 --> 03:55:30.959
with you.

03:55:31.020 --> 03:55:35.280
Chapter 12.

03:55:35.639 --> 03:55:39.959
I think I should be in charge, Nettle

03:55:39.959 --> 03:55:42.180
announced, as Sundew spread the map out

03:55:42.180 --> 03:55:43.920
on a tree stump in the center of the

03:55:43.920 --> 03:55:44.760
sapwing village.

03:55:44.819 --> 03:55:47.700
The rain had finally stopped, so the

03:55:47.700 --> 03:55:49.979
stump was slightly damp, but the map was

03:55:49.979 --> 03:55:51.840
drawn on a large waterproof leaf.

03:55:51.959 --> 03:55:55.379
It was also, in Sundu's opinion, not the

03:55:55.379 --> 03:55:57.659
most helpful map she'd ever seen, but

03:55:57.659 --> 03:55:59.399
Queen Sequoia said this was all the

03:55:59.399 --> 03:56:00.360
information she had.

03:56:00.420 --> 03:56:04.020
Ha, Sendu said, without looking up at

03:56:04.020 --> 03:56:04.620
Nettle.

03:56:04.680 --> 03:56:08.040
No, but I'm the oldest.

03:56:08.040 --> 03:56:09.899
Metal hissed.

03:56:09.959 --> 03:56:12.360
So I have the most experience in the

03:56:12.360 --> 03:56:14.520
jungle, and I have been training for a

03:56:14.520 --> 03:56:17.399
mission like this my whole life, and I am

03:56:17.399 --> 03:56:18.180
a natural leader.

03:56:18.239 --> 03:56:19.680
Ha.

03:56:19.739 --> 03:56:23.700
Ha, Sundew snorted, outvoted 4 to one.

03:56:23.819 --> 03:56:26.100
You didn't even ask them.

03:56:26.159 --> 03:56:27.360
They might vote for me.

03:56:27.420 --> 03:56:29.879
Nope, said Willow.

03:56:29.940 --> 03:56:32.700
Sorry, no, said Cricket.

03:56:32.760 --> 03:56:34.200
Me boo.

03:56:34.260 --> 03:56:34.920
Bop.

03:56:35.040 --> 03:56:37.739
Bumblebee chimed in enthusiastically from

03:56:37.739 --> 03:56:38.159
her sling.

03:56:38.219 --> 03:56:42.780
Oh, whoops, 5 to one, Sendu said.

03:56:42.840 --> 03:56:45.420
Maybe she is smarter than she looks, she

03:56:45.420 --> 03:56:46.260
added to Cricket.

03:56:46.319 --> 03:56:48.659
She held out her palm and the dragonette

03:56:48.659 --> 03:56:49.559
whacked it delightedly.

03:56:49.620 --> 03:56:52.079
Man Drake!

03:56:52.139 --> 03:56:54.360
Nettle demanded, swelling up with

03:56:54.360 --> 03:56:55.739
indignation.

03:56:55.799 --> 03:56:57.000
Tell her I should be the leader.

03:56:57.120 --> 03:56:58.979
Sundo.

03:56:59.040 --> 03:57:00.659
Why would you do this to me?

03:57:00.719 --> 03:57:03.420
Mandrake asked plaintively.

03:57:03.540 --> 03:57:06.719
Because if she's mad at you, maybe she'll

03:57:06.719 --> 03:57:08.700
stop harassing me for a nanosecond.

03:57:08.819 --> 03:57:10.200
Sundew pointed out.

03:57:10.260 --> 03:57:13.079
Willow, what's the farthest you've been

03:57:13.079 --> 03:57:13.500
on this map?

03:57:13.620 --> 03:57:16.920
Willow pointed to a cluster of squiggles

03:57:16.920 --> 03:57:20.219
northeast of the village, the Mantineal

03:57:20.219 --> 03:57:20.579
Grove.

03:57:20.639 --> 03:57:23.639
I got too close to it once on a hunt, and

03:57:23.639 --> 03:57:25.500
my father dragged me back here and

03:57:25.500 --> 03:57:26.879
lectured me for a week about it.

03:57:26.940 --> 03:57:30.299
Willow's father had turned out to be a

03:57:30.299 --> 03:57:33.000
kind eyed, pale green dragon, with a lot

03:57:33.000 --> 03:57:34.139
of nervous energy.

03:57:34.200 --> 03:57:37.200
Sundew had only met him for a moment, as

03:57:37.200 --> 03:57:39.360
the queen swept him into her entourage

03:57:39.360 --> 03:57:41.819
and he paused to wish Willow good luck.

03:57:41.879 --> 03:57:43.979
Sundew had noticed, with a twinge of

03:57:43.979 --> 03:57:46.440
disappointment, that Willow hadn't said

03:57:46.440 --> 03:57:49.200
my girlfriend, in that introduction.

03:57:49.500 --> 03:57:52.020
Of course, that probably required a

03:57:52.020 --> 03:57:54.659
slightly longer conversation involving

03:57:54.659 --> 03:57:56.579
some confessions about sneaking off into

03:57:56.579 --> 03:57:57.540
the jungle at night.

03:57:57.600 --> 03:58:00.899
Sundew needed to have a similar, slightly

03:58:00.899 --> 03:58:03.659
longer conversation with Mandrake, but

03:58:03.659 --> 03:58:06.180
not in front of Nettle, and not when they

03:58:06.180 --> 03:58:08.340
only had a day to find the antidote, and

03:58:08.340 --> 03:58:10.139
bring it back to stop Queen Wasp.

03:58:10.200 --> 03:58:12.540
Priorities sundo.

03:58:12.600 --> 03:58:13.920
Focus on the mission.

03:58:13.979 --> 03:58:17.219
Totally not just avoiding something

03:58:17.219 --> 03:58:18.780
enormously awkward.

03:58:18.840 --> 03:58:19.500
No.

03:58:19.559 --> 03:58:22.799
There's not a lot of detail in this map.

03:58:22.860 --> 03:58:24.420
Sunu observed.

03:58:24.479 --> 03:58:27.000
She wished she'd had time to restock her

03:58:27.000 --> 03:58:29.579
pouches, they felt unfortunately light

03:58:29.579 --> 03:58:32.340
for such a dangerous expedition, she

03:58:32.340 --> 03:58:34.799
rechecked her list in her mind, hoping

03:58:34.799 --> 03:58:36.299
what she did have would be useful.

03:58:36.360 --> 03:58:39.420
Most of us haven't gone past the

03:58:39.420 --> 03:58:41.040
manchineels, Willow said.

03:58:41.100 --> 03:58:43.379
They are scary death trees.

03:58:43.500 --> 03:58:46.500
I've read about them, but I've never seen

03:58:46.500 --> 03:58:49.260
one, Cricket said, pushing up her

03:58:49.260 --> 03:58:49.620
glasses.

03:58:49.680 --> 03:58:52.920
Her tail was doing it, so curious, I can

03:58:52.920 --> 03:58:54.899
hardly stand it, twitch dance.

03:58:54.959 --> 03:58:58.260
Don't even think about it, Sundu said.

03:58:58.319 --> 03:59:01.020
No time for research today, Miss Brainy.

03:59:01.079 --> 03:59:02.459
We'll go around them.

03:59:02.520 --> 03:59:04.799
She rolled up the leaf again and glanced

03:59:04.799 --> 03:59:05.459
up at the trees.

03:59:05.520 --> 03:59:07.979
The sapwings were frantically busy

03:59:07.979 --> 03:59:10.500
hopping from tree to tree, shouting

03:59:10.500 --> 03:59:12.780
suggestions at one another, and gathering

03:59:12.780 --> 03:59:14.760
in small worried groups to whisper before

03:59:14.760 --> 03:59:15.540
splitting up again.

03:59:15.659 --> 03:59:17.879
But there were still a few of them who

03:59:17.879 --> 03:59:19.680
had stopped to peer down curiously at

03:59:19.680 --> 03:59:21.000
cricket and bumblebee.

03:59:21.059 --> 03:59:23.399
The 1st hive wings most of them had ever

03:59:23.399 --> 03:59:23.579
seen.

03:59:23.700 --> 03:59:27.959
Which is, thanks to us, the real leaf

03:59:27.959 --> 03:59:30.000
wings who scared off all of WASP's

03:59:30.000 --> 03:59:32.579
raiding parties, or tricked them into

03:59:32.579 --> 03:59:33.360
getting eaten.

03:59:33.420 --> 03:59:36.420
Find something more productive and less

03:59:36.420 --> 03:59:39.000
nosy to do, she shouted at the closest

03:59:39.000 --> 03:59:42.120
peeping leaf wing, he jumped and scurried

03:59:42.120 --> 03:59:44.040
away up the tree, like a startled

03:59:44.040 --> 03:59:44.700
squirrel.

03:59:44.760 --> 03:59:48.540
Oh my goodness, Willow said, must you be

03:59:48.540 --> 03:59:49.260
so terrifying?

03:59:49.319 --> 03:59:53.399
It's my special skill, Sandu said, and he

03:59:53.399 --> 03:59:53.879
deserved it.

03:59:53.940 --> 03:59:55.620
Did he though?

03:59:55.739 --> 03:59:57.299
Willow said thoughtfully.

03:59:57.360 --> 03:59:59.760
Could you please keep being the one

03:59:59.760 --> 04:00:00.360
dragon?

04:00:00.479 --> 04:00:01.799
I am not furious at right now?

04:00:01.860 --> 04:00:03.180
Sundu said.

04:00:03.239 --> 04:00:05.159
Come on, everyone, let's go.

04:00:05.219 --> 04:00:08.340
Willow, you lead the way for now, since

04:00:08.340 --> 04:00:09.959
you're the most familiar with the jungle

04:00:09.959 --> 04:00:10.620
around your village.

04:00:10.680 --> 04:00:14.459
Willow hesitated for a moment, as though

04:00:14.459 --> 04:00:16.020
she was thinking about pressing her point

04:00:16.020 --> 04:00:19.260
a bit more, but instead, she nodded and

04:00:19.260 --> 04:00:21.420
headed into the trees, to Sundu's

04:00:21.420 --> 04:00:21.719
relief.

04:00:21.780 --> 04:00:25.020
Sundu followed, with cricket a half step

04:00:25.020 --> 04:00:25.500
behind her.

04:00:25.559 --> 04:00:28.559
The hive wing was like a shadow, staying

04:00:28.559 --> 04:00:31.079
as close to sundew as she could, although

04:00:31.079 --> 04:00:32.819
she kept twisting her head to stare at

04:00:32.819 --> 04:00:34.620
weird plants as they went by.

04:00:34.680 --> 04:00:37.379
I'm familiar with this area too.

04:00:37.440 --> 04:00:39.600
Nettle complained from the rear.

04:00:39.719 --> 04:00:42.540
I've been scouting in sapwing territory

04:00:42.540 --> 04:00:43.979
since before Mandrake was born.

04:00:44.040 --> 04:00:46.739
I know every kind of tree around here.

04:00:46.799 --> 04:00:52.379
Me, me, me, me, me, Bumblebee said, in a

04:00:52.379 --> 04:00:54.059
hilariously similar tone of voice.

04:00:54.120 --> 04:00:57.479
Sundu smothered a laugh and glanced over

04:00:57.479 --> 04:00:59.459
her shoulder for the joy of catching

04:00:59.459 --> 04:01:01.020
Nettle's furious gowl.

04:01:01.079 --> 04:01:05.340
Excuse me, Nettle demanded.

04:01:05.399 --> 04:01:07.559
Why are we taking a hatchling with us?

04:01:07.620 --> 04:01:10.620
A nasty hive wing hatchling no less.

04:01:10.680 --> 04:01:13.319
Oh, is it because we're hoping something

04:01:13.319 --> 04:01:13.979
will eat her?

04:01:14.040 --> 04:01:16.799
A snack for the dragon traps?

04:01:16.920 --> 04:01:17.399
What a good idea.

04:01:17.459 --> 04:01:21.479
Maybe you should shut your trap, Sundew

04:01:21.479 --> 04:01:21.899
suggested.

04:01:21.959 --> 04:01:24.899
Brr, brr, brr.

04:01:24.959 --> 04:01:26.700
Bumblebee agreed.

04:01:26.819 --> 04:01:29.520
She seemed to be feeling saucier now that

04:01:29.520 --> 04:01:31.079
they were heading away from the villages

04:01:31.079 --> 04:01:32.879
full of staring dragons.

04:01:33.000 --> 04:01:34.979
Mandrake.

04:01:35.100 --> 04:01:36.120
Nettle cried.

04:01:36.180 --> 04:01:37.860
Are you going to let her talk like that?

04:01:37.920 --> 04:01:40.559
If you don't stand up to her now, she's

04:01:40.559 --> 04:01:42.120
going to walk all over you when you're

04:01:42.120 --> 04:01:42.239
married.

04:01:42.299 --> 04:01:46.379
Oh, I have no idea what that feels like

04:01:46.379 --> 04:01:47.940
he grumbled.

04:01:48.000 --> 04:01:50.700
Willow turned to arch her eyebrows at

04:01:50.700 --> 04:01:51.420
sundew.

04:01:51.479 --> 04:01:53.579
Don't panic, sundo.

04:01:53.639 --> 04:01:55.620
Don't blurt out something idiotic.

04:01:55.680 --> 04:01:57.659
This was not the end of the world.

04:01:57.719 --> 04:02:00.000
Willow knew about mandrake.

04:02:00.059 --> 04:02:02.280
She knew Sundew was supposed to marry him

04:02:02.280 --> 04:02:03.479
in some distant future.

04:02:03.540 --> 04:02:06.659
She knew Sundu didn't want to and didn't

04:02:06.659 --> 04:02:09.780
plan to and wasn't going to, and she knew

04:02:09.780 --> 04:02:11.639
that Sundu had been figuring out how to

04:02:11.639 --> 04:02:12.899
explain that to him for years.

04:02:13.020 --> 04:02:17.219
Willow did think years was a bit of a

04:02:17.219 --> 04:02:19.200
long time for Sundew to hang on to that

04:02:19.200 --> 04:02:19.860
explanation.

04:02:19.920 --> 04:02:22.979
But she also thought sundew would

04:02:22.979 --> 04:02:25.379
eventually leave the offshoot tribe and

04:02:25.379 --> 04:02:26.700
come live with the sapwings.

04:02:26.760 --> 04:02:29.459
She'd always hoped that one day sundew

04:02:29.459 --> 04:02:32.159
would magically stop feeling so angry, and

04:02:32.159 --> 04:02:34.440
that she'd give up the vengeful life of a

04:02:34.440 --> 04:02:35.760
poison wing on her own.

04:02:35.879 --> 04:02:38.219
Willow had expected that to be the

04:02:38.219 --> 04:02:40.440
inevitable end of any marriage plans with

04:02:40.440 --> 04:02:41.280
Mandrake.

04:02:41.340 --> 04:02:44.760
Sundew had a different endgame in mind

04:02:44.760 --> 04:02:45.180
however.

04:02:45.239 --> 04:02:49.020
In her plan, she'd fulfill her destiny

04:02:49.020 --> 04:02:51.299
destroy the hive wings, prove to her

04:02:51.299 --> 04:02:53.459
mother that she could do it herself, and

04:02:53.459 --> 04:02:54.420
return a hero.

04:02:54.479 --> 04:02:56.819
Then she'd be able to choose her own

04:02:56.819 --> 04:02:57.180
future.

04:02:57.239 --> 04:02:59.459
She'd be able to do anything she wanted

04:02:59.459 --> 04:03:01.020
once that was done.

04:03:01.079 --> 04:03:04.440
She hadn't expected her destiny to be

04:03:04.440 --> 04:03:05.760
quite this awkward.

04:03:05.819 --> 04:03:09.840
They walked and climbed, and whacked

04:03:09.840 --> 04:03:11.340
their way through the undergrowth for a

04:03:11.340 --> 04:03:14.639
long time, mostly in silence, apart from

04:03:14.639 --> 04:03:16.920
Nettle complaining, and bumblebee

04:03:16.920 --> 04:03:17.520
chirping at things.

04:03:17.639 --> 04:03:21.059
Willow moved confidently, pointing out

04:03:21.059 --> 04:03:24.299
things to avoid, like snake nests and low

04:03:24.299 --> 04:03:25.739
hanging strangler vines.

04:03:25.799 --> 04:03:28.500
Dense clouds of moss covered the tree

04:03:28.500 --> 04:03:30.840
roots all around them, dotted with

04:03:30.840 --> 04:03:33.120
sprouts of deadly mushrooms that looked

04:03:33.120 --> 04:03:35.219
like eyeballs growing out of the earth

04:03:35.219 --> 04:03:36.840
ate me.

04:03:36.899 --> 04:03:38.940
The mushrooms chortled.

04:03:39.000 --> 04:03:40.139
Just try.

04:03:40.200 --> 04:03:43.440
Ferns brushed their scales and whispered

04:03:43.440 --> 04:03:44.579
back along their stems.

04:03:44.639 --> 04:03:46.799
Strange, strange.

04:03:46.860 --> 04:03:47.280
Why?

04:03:47.280 --> 04:03:47.700
Why?

04:03:47.760 --> 04:03:50.159
Beware, beware, creatures out of place.

04:03:50.280 --> 04:03:52.860
In their vague, feathery fern way.

04:03:52.920 --> 04:03:56.340
Nettle was on a rant about how she'd have

04:03:56.340 --> 04:03:57.840
found a better route by now.

04:03:57.899 --> 04:03:59.940
When they reached a slope that slanted

04:03:59.940 --> 04:04:02.399
sharply down ahead of them, riddled with

04:04:02.399 --> 04:04:05.219
the lumpy roots and pricker bushes, a

04:04:05.219 --> 04:04:07.139
slick layer of rotting leaves made it

04:04:07.139 --> 04:04:10.079
tricky to stay upright, sundew found a

04:04:10.079 --> 04:04:12.059
branch that wasn't covered in thorns or

04:04:12.059 --> 04:04:15.059
toxic sap, held onto it with one talon

04:04:15.059 --> 04:04:17.040
and reached out to support cricket with

04:04:17.040 --> 04:04:17.399
the other.

04:04:17.459 --> 04:04:20.819
You know, you can go ahead and ask all

04:04:20.819 --> 04:04:22.799
the annoying questions buzzing around in

04:04:22.799 --> 04:04:25.680
your head, she said, as the hive wing

04:04:25.680 --> 04:04:28.079
slipped and slid past her, clinging to

04:04:28.079 --> 04:04:28.860
her arm.

04:04:28.920 --> 04:04:31.319
Bumblebee leaned out of her sling to gawk

04:04:31.319 --> 04:04:33.239
at the fuzzy orange monkeys in the tree

04:04:33.239 --> 04:04:33.659
overhead.

04:04:33.719 --> 04:04:36.299
Sundew wasn't sure how cricket could

04:04:36.299 --> 04:04:38.520
balance it all, with the dragonette

04:04:38.520 --> 04:04:39.479
wriggling around like that.

04:04:39.540 --> 04:04:42.299
I'd rather listen to you than Nettle.

04:04:42.360 --> 04:04:44.219
Oh, really?

04:04:44.280 --> 04:04:45.600
Nettle spat.

04:04:45.659 --> 04:04:47.399
Leave the jungle once.

04:04:47.459 --> 04:04:49.620
And suddenly you're a hive wing loving

04:04:49.620 --> 04:04:50.579
traitor to the tribe.

04:04:50.700 --> 04:04:52.139
I should have seen this coming.

04:04:52.200 --> 04:04:53.280
I always.

04:04:53.579 --> 04:04:57.420
Her diatribe turned into a shriek as she

04:04:57.420 --> 04:05:00.239
took a wrong step, lost her balance, and

04:05:00.239 --> 04:05:01.860
plummeted down the steep hill.

04:05:01.920 --> 04:05:05.579
Sundew yanked cricket out of the way, and

04:05:05.579 --> 04:05:08.579
Nettle hurtled past, plowing a canyon

04:05:08.579 --> 04:05:09.540
through the wet leaves.

04:05:09.600 --> 04:05:12.420
Willow managed to leap into the air and

04:05:12.420 --> 04:05:14.940
hover before she got knocked over.

04:05:15.000 --> 04:05:16.979
She tried to catch Nettle, but the dragon

04:05:16.979 --> 04:05:18.239
was sliding too fast.

04:05:18.299 --> 04:05:21.479
Wait, come back and tell us again about

04:05:21.479 --> 04:05:23.520
how you're the smartest dragon in the

04:05:23.520 --> 04:05:25.739
jungle, Sundu called after her.

04:05:25.799 --> 04:05:28.799
Nettle screamed back something about

04:05:28.799 --> 04:05:29.879
killing sundew.

04:05:29.940 --> 04:05:33.059
And then her voice abruptly cut off as

04:05:33.059 --> 04:05:34.920
she vanished over the bottom edge of the

04:05:34.920 --> 04:05:35.159
hill.

04:05:35.219 --> 04:05:36.719
Uh-oh.

04:05:36.780 --> 04:05:38.159
Mandrake said.

04:05:38.219 --> 04:05:41.340
It was difficult to fly between the low

04:05:41.340 --> 04:05:44.219
tangled branches, the hungry dragon traps

04:05:44.219 --> 04:05:46.379
and the surprise cobwebs full of

04:05:46.379 --> 04:05:48.659
poisonous spiders, but they finally

04:05:48.659 --> 04:05:51.120
managed to hop, hover, skip down the

04:05:51.120 --> 04:05:53.639
slope to a flat spot at the bottom, which

04:05:53.639 --> 04:05:55.920
turned out to overlook a large brackish

04:05:55.920 --> 04:05:56.219
lake.

04:05:56.280 --> 04:05:58.500
Cricket peered over the edge.

04:05:58.559 --> 04:06:02.760
It's not that far down, she reported, but

04:06:02.760 --> 04:06:04.020
I don't see Nettle anywhere.

04:06:04.079 --> 04:06:07.079
Wow, said Sundew.

04:06:07.139 --> 04:06:09.719
I was hoping we'd lose her, but I didn't

04:06:09.719 --> 04:06:10.920
think it would happen quite that fast.

04:06:10.979 --> 04:06:14.159
Mandrake gave her a look, and she rolled

04:06:14.159 --> 04:06:14.579
her eyes.

04:06:14.639 --> 04:06:16.319
I'm kidding.

04:06:16.440 --> 04:06:17.159
I sure she's fine.

04:06:17.219 --> 04:06:19.200
She can handle anything, remember?

04:06:19.260 --> 04:06:22.139
What if she fell in the pond and

04:06:22.139 --> 04:06:22.680
drowned?

04:06:22.739 --> 04:06:24.840
Willow asked anxiously.

04:06:24.899 --> 04:06:26.760
Get me out of here.

04:06:26.819 --> 04:06:29.940
Nettle's muffled voice screamed from

04:06:29.940 --> 04:06:30.659
somewhere below them.

04:06:30.780 --> 04:06:34.559
That doesn't sound like drowning, Sundu

04:06:34.559 --> 04:06:34.860
said.

04:06:34.920 --> 04:06:36.719
She fell on the spot where she could

04:06:36.719 --> 04:06:38.819
spread her wings to their full length and

04:06:38.819 --> 04:06:41.280
hopped over the edge, floating down to

04:06:41.280 --> 04:06:42.540
the muddy banks of the lake.

04:06:42.540 --> 04:06:47.100
Her talons squelched into slimy black mud

04:06:47.100 --> 04:06:49.200
and nearly flattened a squashy looking

04:06:49.200 --> 04:06:52.680
toad, who let out an alarmed blart and

04:06:52.680 --> 04:06:53.399
scooted away.

04:06:53.459 --> 04:06:56.639
Sharp hollow reeds poked out of the marsh

04:06:56.639 --> 04:06:57.360
all around her.

04:06:57.420 --> 04:06:59.940
Some of them were broken near the bottom

04:06:59.940 --> 04:07:02.760
and nearly hidden by the mud, stabbing

04:07:02.760 --> 04:07:04.620
her feet as she picked her way closer to

04:07:04.620 --> 04:07:04.920
the water.

04:07:04.979 --> 04:07:08.639
From down here, it was obvious what had

04:07:08.639 --> 04:07:10.139
happened to Nettle.

04:07:10.200 --> 04:07:12.600
A huge cluster of pitcher plants was

04:07:12.600 --> 04:07:15.120
gathered right below the hill, gaping

04:07:15.120 --> 04:07:17.399
maws, ready to swallow any animal that

04:07:17.399 --> 04:07:18.360
tumbled down it.

04:07:18.420 --> 04:07:21.659
Each one looked like a long green sack

04:07:21.659 --> 04:07:24.000
tipped with stripes of dark pink around

04:07:24.000 --> 04:07:25.559
the open mouth at the top.

04:07:25.620 --> 04:07:28.739
Sundu had a collection of much smaller

04:07:28.739 --> 04:07:30.600
pitcher plants growing outside her nest

04:07:30.600 --> 04:07:33.540
to catch flies before they buzzed in and

04:07:33.540 --> 04:07:34.020
bothered her.

04:07:34.079 --> 04:07:37.079
She really didn't like this big kind

04:07:37.079 --> 04:07:37.200
though.

04:07:37.260 --> 04:07:40.739
It was super creepy to look at a giant

04:07:40.739 --> 04:07:43.139
pitcher plant and wonder whether there

04:07:43.139 --> 04:07:45.479
might be a dragon corpse decomposing

04:07:45.479 --> 04:07:45.959
inside it.

04:07:46.020 --> 04:07:49.799
Or, in this case, a dragon that was still

04:07:49.799 --> 04:07:51.899
very much alive and spitting mad.

04:07:51.899 --> 04:07:53.760
Get me out.

04:07:53.819 --> 04:07:55.440
Get me out of this thing.

04:07:55.500 --> 04:07:57.360
Nettle shrieked.

04:07:57.420 --> 04:08:00.180
One of the plants wobbled as she slammed

04:08:00.180 --> 04:08:00.959
herself into the side.

04:08:01.020 --> 04:08:02.879
Whoa.

04:08:02.940 --> 04:08:05.819
Cricket said, landing beside sundew.

04:08:05.879 --> 04:08:08.700
She's in there?

04:08:08.760 --> 04:08:11.280
Why doesn't she just fly out?

04:08:11.340 --> 04:08:13.739
Me, bum more.

04:08:13.860 --> 04:08:16.319
Bumblebee added, wide eyed.

04:08:16.379 --> 04:08:19.680
The inside walls are covered in slime

04:08:19.680 --> 04:08:22.260
Willow answered, as she and Mandrake

04:08:22.260 --> 04:08:23.100
joined them.

04:08:23.159 --> 04:08:25.440
It coats the wings of its prey as it

04:08:25.440 --> 04:08:28.319
falls in, making it harder to fly and

04:08:28.319 --> 04:08:29.639
impossible to climb out.

04:08:29.700 --> 04:08:32.700
There are also sharp hairs lining the

04:08:32.700 --> 04:08:35.520
walls, pointing down, so anything that

04:08:35.520 --> 04:08:37.680
tries to fly or climb up will get

04:08:37.680 --> 04:08:38.459
stabbed.

04:08:38.520 --> 04:08:40.620
And if we don't get her out soon.

04:08:40.680 --> 04:08:44.520
Mandrake said, she'll either drown or get

04:08:44.520 --> 04:08:46.680
digested by the acid pool at the bottom

04:08:46.680 --> 04:08:49.139
of the pitcher, which would be bad.

04:08:49.200 --> 04:08:52.139
He added, almost as though reminding

04:08:52.139 --> 04:08:52.500
himself.

04:08:52.559 --> 04:08:56.340
I wish Blue were here, Cricket said

04:08:56.340 --> 04:08:58.260
pressing her talons to her forehead.

04:08:58.319 --> 04:09:01.260
I'm not sure setting it on fire would

04:09:01.260 --> 04:09:03.600
improve Nettle's situation, Sundew

04:09:03.600 --> 04:09:04.079
pointed out.

04:09:04.139 --> 04:09:08.040
Oh, I didn't mean for his flame silk

04:09:08.040 --> 04:09:09.000
Cricket said.

04:09:09.059 --> 04:09:12.000
It would just make me feel better.

04:09:12.059 --> 04:09:15.239
She glanced down, looking embarrassed.

04:09:15.299 --> 04:09:17.819
Sundew understood that.

04:09:17.879 --> 04:09:20.459
She had wished for Willow's company a

04:09:20.459 --> 04:09:22.139
1000000 times during her mission to the

04:09:22.139 --> 04:09:22.620
hives.

04:09:22.680 --> 04:09:25.680
She stole a glance at Willow, caught her

04:09:25.680 --> 04:09:27.600
looking back, and had to smother a

04:09:27.600 --> 04:09:27.899
smile.

04:09:27.959 --> 04:09:31.260
We'll have to cut her out, Sundew said

04:09:31.260 --> 04:09:31.920
briskly.

04:09:31.979 --> 04:09:34.200
Willow and I will start with our claws.

04:09:34.260 --> 04:09:36.059
Mandrake and Cricket?

04:09:36.120 --> 04:09:37.620
Look for anything else around here that

04:09:37.620 --> 04:09:38.700
might be even sharper.

04:09:38.760 --> 04:09:41.940
They had to wade into the thicket of

04:09:41.940 --> 04:09:44.280
pitcher plants to get to nettles, which

04:09:44.280 --> 04:09:46.979
was extra creepy, because Sundew could

04:09:46.979 --> 04:09:49.379
sense them all thinking, in essence.

04:09:49.440 --> 04:09:51.180
Hmm, yeah.

04:09:51.239 --> 04:09:54.120
Come in yum, delicious.

04:09:54.180 --> 04:09:57.360
Wanted, mmm, mine.

04:09:57.420 --> 04:10:00.780
Like a creepy background chorus of hungry

04:10:00.780 --> 04:10:01.500
ghosts.

04:10:01.620 --> 04:10:05.459
Their stems were cold and clammy, and the

04:10:05.459 --> 04:10:07.739
pitchers bumped against them, some of

04:10:07.739 --> 04:10:09.899
them skin crawlingly heavier than

04:10:09.899 --> 04:10:10.620
others.

04:10:10.680 --> 04:10:12.959
Don't think about what might be in

04:10:12.959 --> 04:10:13.260
there.

04:10:13.319 --> 04:10:15.540
Do not think about it.

04:10:15.600 --> 04:10:19.020
The plant nettle was in had a

04:10:19.020 --> 04:10:21.840
particularly smug, plummy vibe to it.

04:10:21.959 --> 04:10:24.180
As though it wanted all its neighbors to

04:10:24.180 --> 04:10:26.639
notice that it had caught the best prey

04:10:26.639 --> 04:10:28.200
and no one else could have it.

04:10:28.260 --> 04:10:29.639
Ha.

04:10:29.760 --> 04:10:31.079
Ha, ha, hmm.

04:10:31.139 --> 04:10:33.000
Look at my yums.

04:10:33.059 --> 04:10:35.579
All mine, my yums.

04:10:35.700 --> 04:10:37.440
It smirked.

04:10:37.500 --> 04:10:40.139
Well, it wasn't going to be so pleased

04:10:40.139 --> 04:10:41.340
for much longer.

04:10:41.399 --> 04:10:44.520
Willow stabbed her claws into its side

04:10:44.520 --> 04:10:47.219
and Sundew felt the plant snarl with

04:10:47.219 --> 04:10:47.700
fury.

04:10:47.760 --> 04:10:50.879
Chili vibrations echoed through the roots

04:10:50.879 --> 04:10:53.159
and leaves all around her, and she

04:10:53.159 --> 04:10:54.959
thought some of the plants were leaning

04:10:54.959 --> 04:10:55.379
closer.

04:10:55.440 --> 04:10:58.379
Mmm, yum.

04:10:58.440 --> 04:11:01.200
Climb in here, little yums.

04:11:01.260 --> 04:11:05.159
Dangerous, delicious, eat before it hurts

04:11:05.159 --> 04:11:05.459
us.

04:11:05.520 --> 04:11:08.219
Eat it now, yum.

04:11:08.280 --> 04:11:11.940
She added her claws to the grooves Willow

04:11:11.940 --> 04:11:14.100
was making, dragging them up and down

04:11:14.100 --> 04:11:15.959
digging deeper each time.

04:11:16.020 --> 04:11:18.899
They carved a square in the side of the

04:11:18.899 --> 04:11:19.260
picture.

04:11:19.379 --> 04:11:22.379
Big enough, she hoped, for Nettle to

04:11:22.379 --> 04:11:22.860
crawl through.

04:11:22.920 --> 04:11:25.379
But the walls of the pitcher were thick

04:11:25.379 --> 04:11:28.260
and rubbery, and oozed with slime that

04:11:28.260 --> 04:11:30.059
made their talons sting and stick

04:11:30.059 --> 04:11:30.540
together.

04:11:30.600 --> 04:11:32.940
It felt like their progress was too slow

04:11:32.940 --> 04:11:35.579
as though they might look up any moment

04:11:35.579 --> 04:11:37.139
and find that night had fallen.

04:11:37.200 --> 04:11:40.139
Also, it was incredibly hard to focus

04:11:40.139 --> 04:11:42.420
with Nettle's shrieking bloody murder the

04:11:42.420 --> 04:11:42.959
entire time.

04:11:43.020 --> 04:11:46.319
Sundew took a step back and shook her

04:11:46.319 --> 04:11:47.280
aching talons.

04:11:47.340 --> 04:11:50.520
I can't believe I'm doing this for nettle

04:11:50.520 --> 04:11:51.180
of all dragons.

04:11:51.239 --> 04:11:54.719
Here, Cricket gasped behind them.

04:11:54.780 --> 04:11:57.780
She leaned between 2 pitchers, and passed

04:11:57.780 --> 04:12:00.540
them a wickedly sharp thorn almost as

04:12:00.540 --> 04:12:01.979
tall as Willow.

04:12:02.040 --> 04:12:04.979
Ah, watch it, Sundu cried.

04:12:05.040 --> 04:12:06.600
You nearly stabbed Willow.

04:12:06.659 --> 04:12:08.940
Not that nearly.

04:12:09.000 --> 04:12:10.139
Willow said.

04:12:10.200 --> 04:12:11.819
This is perfect cricket.

04:12:11.879 --> 04:12:12.540
Thank you.

04:12:12.659 --> 04:12:15.719
She wrapped her arms around the wider end

04:12:15.719 --> 04:12:18.120
and thrust the thorn at the plant like a

04:12:18.120 --> 04:12:18.420
spear.

04:12:18.479 --> 04:12:22.559
To sundew's surprise, it appears to write

04:12:22.559 --> 04:12:23.940
through one of the lines they had

04:12:23.940 --> 04:12:25.020
carved.

04:12:25.079 --> 04:12:27.780
Nettle's shriek instantly went up an

04:12:27.780 --> 04:12:28.860
octave.

04:12:28.920 --> 04:12:30.239
What are you doing?

04:12:30.299 --> 04:12:31.799
She screeched.

04:12:31.860 --> 04:12:33.299
Are you trying to kill me?

04:12:33.360 --> 04:12:35.639
We're getting you out.

04:12:35.760 --> 04:12:38.579
Sandu yelled back, like you've been

04:12:38.579 --> 04:12:40.379
screaming about this whole time?

04:12:40.440 --> 04:12:41.340
Just get out of the way.

04:12:41.459 --> 04:12:45.780
As if there's anywhere to go, Nettle

04:12:45.780 --> 04:12:46.319
bellowed.

04:12:46.379 --> 04:12:49.020
It's crammed and dark, and things are

04:12:49.020 --> 04:12:51.479
stabbing me, and this goo on my tail

04:12:51.479 --> 04:12:53.280
really hurts and...

04:12:54.180 --> 04:12:56.459
But while she was shouting, Willow had

04:12:56.459 --> 04:12:58.260
been dragging the thorn along the outline

04:12:58.260 --> 04:13:00.780
of the square, and suddenly, a whole

04:13:00.780 --> 04:13:03.479
piece of the pitcher wall fell off, and

04:13:03.479 --> 04:13:04.920
Nettle came tumbling out after it.

04:13:04.979 --> 04:13:06.959
Ew.

04:13:07.020 --> 04:13:10.200
Bumblebee declared, and perhaps her most

04:13:10.200 --> 04:13:11.760
accurate observation so far.

04:13:11.819 --> 04:13:15.000
Nettle was dripping with pinkish green

04:13:15.000 --> 04:13:18.780
slime from horns to tail, and the acidic

04:13:18.780 --> 04:13:21.299
rotting smell coming from her, and the

04:13:21.299 --> 04:13:24.000
sliced up plant was nearly as bad as a

04:13:24.000 --> 04:13:25.620
corpse flower in full bloom.

04:13:25.680 --> 04:13:29.520
That took you long enough, she yelped

04:13:29.520 --> 04:13:30.719
struggling to her feet.

04:13:30.780 --> 04:13:33.120
Her wings were plastered to her side.

04:13:33.180 --> 04:13:36.780
You're welcome, Mandrake called from

04:13:36.780 --> 04:13:38.520
outside the pitcher plant cluster.

04:13:38.579 --> 04:13:41.040
I cannot believe this.

04:13:41.100 --> 04:13:44.639
Nettle stamp squelched past sundew and

04:13:44.639 --> 04:13:47.219
willow, shoving pitcher plant viciously

04:13:47.219 --> 04:13:49.620
as she went by, and marched to over to

04:13:49.620 --> 04:13:50.280
the edge of the lake.

04:13:50.340 --> 04:13:53.340
The muddy water made the slime look even

04:13:53.340 --> 04:13:53.879
more dreadful.

04:13:53.940 --> 04:13:56.340
But as she scrubbed it all over herself

04:13:56.340 --> 04:13:59.219
hints of her own green scales started to

04:13:59.219 --> 04:13:59.940
peek through again.

04:14:00.000 --> 04:14:02.280
Are you all right?

04:14:02.340 --> 04:14:03.420
Cricket asked.

04:14:03.479 --> 04:14:06.899
As if you care, Nettle spat.

04:14:06.959 --> 04:14:09.059
Do not talk to me right now.

04:14:09.120 --> 04:14:10.920
I don't want anybody talking to me.

04:14:10.979 --> 04:14:14.520
That sounded like an entirely fine plan

04:14:14.520 --> 04:14:15.420
to send do.

04:14:15.479 --> 04:14:17.700
She pulled out the map and held it up

04:14:17.700 --> 04:14:19.920
squinting at the lines in the semi

04:14:19.920 --> 04:14:20.459
darkness.

04:14:20.520 --> 04:14:23.579
She knew the sun was high in the sky, but

04:14:23.579 --> 04:14:25.440
only a little of its light filtered down

04:14:25.440 --> 04:14:26.579
to them here at the bottom of the

04:14:26.579 --> 04:14:27.000
jungle.

04:14:27.059 --> 04:14:30.059
It looks like we need to cross this lake

04:14:30.059 --> 04:14:32.639
to avoid dimangineals, Sundu said.

04:14:32.700 --> 04:14:35.340
Nettle, while you're there, could you

04:14:35.340 --> 04:14:37.020
poke your nose in the water and see if a

04:14:37.020 --> 04:14:38.159
bladder wort tries to eat you?

04:14:38.280 --> 04:14:41.639
I'll feed you and your stupid little

04:14:41.639 --> 04:14:43.920
striped monster to the bladder warts

04:14:43.920 --> 04:14:45.180
Nettle snarled.

04:14:45.239 --> 04:14:47.219
Ta-da!

04:14:47.340 --> 04:14:50.100
Bumblebee declared, working 2 of her

04:14:50.100 --> 04:14:51.959
wings free and flinging them out to

04:14:51.959 --> 04:14:52.440
either side.

04:14:52.500 --> 04:14:55.920
Could YouTube please stop yelling at each

04:14:55.920 --> 04:14:56.159
other?

04:14:56.219 --> 04:14:57.600
Willow asked.

04:14:57.659 --> 04:14:59.819
She was standing at the edge of the water

04:14:59.819 --> 04:15:02.100
squinting at the cloudy surface that

04:15:02.100 --> 04:15:03.000
stretched ahead of them.

04:15:03.059 --> 04:15:05.280
It's only making this harder.

04:15:05.340 --> 04:15:08.399
Sundew blinked at her in surprise.

04:15:08.459 --> 04:15:10.620
It didn't feel harder to her.

04:15:10.680 --> 04:15:13.680
In fact, yelling at Nettle gave her

04:15:13.680 --> 04:15:15.840
energy, and it stopped her from worrying

04:15:15.840 --> 04:15:18.000
about all the really big things she had

04:15:18.000 --> 04:15:18.420
to worry about.

04:15:18.479 --> 04:15:22.200
Moreover, couldn't Willow see the

04:15:22.200 --> 04:15:23.760
difference between nettles yelling

04:15:23.760 --> 04:15:27.479
unproductive, vicious, out of control, and

04:15:27.479 --> 04:15:30.719
sundoes, hilarious, and morale boosting?

04:15:30.780 --> 04:15:33.479
Look, Willow said.

04:15:33.540 --> 04:15:35.760
There are plants floating right below the

04:15:35.760 --> 04:15:37.559
surface all the way across the pond.

04:15:37.620 --> 04:15:40.739
Bet you anything, there are water wheels

04:15:40.739 --> 04:15:41.280
everywhere.

04:15:41.340 --> 04:15:46.260
Yeesh, Mandrake said with a shudder, and

04:15:46.260 --> 04:15:47.639
even Nettle took a step back.

04:15:47.700 --> 04:15:49.920
Water wheels?

04:15:49.979 --> 04:15:51.420
Cricket asked Willow.

04:15:51.479 --> 04:15:55.920
They're like aquatic dragon traps, Willow

04:15:55.920 --> 04:15:56.340
said.

04:15:56.399 --> 04:16:00.239
Same idea. touch one, and it closes

04:16:00.239 --> 04:16:03.180
around you, drags you under, drowns you

04:16:03.180 --> 04:16:04.379
and digests you.

04:16:04.440 --> 04:16:08.399
Ew. said Bumblebee.

04:16:08.459 --> 04:16:11.040
No, bumblebee.

04:16:11.100 --> 04:16:12.540
Cricket said sternly.

04:16:12.600 --> 04:16:16.739
Not ooh, more like, yikes, terrifying.

04:16:16.799 --> 04:16:19.920
Although, speaking purely scientifically

04:16:19.920 --> 04:16:21.540
that is pretty amazing.

04:16:21.659 --> 04:16:25.500
Plants that can drown you, plants that

04:16:25.500 --> 04:16:26.940
slime you and eat you?

04:16:27.000 --> 04:16:29.340
I can't believe they didn't teach us any

04:16:29.340 --> 04:16:31.139
of this at Terrarium Academy.

04:16:31.200 --> 04:16:33.840
This is way more interesting than how to

04:16:33.840 --> 04:16:34.799
grow radishes.

04:16:34.860 --> 04:16:37.739
I'm glad you're so fascinated.

04:16:37.799 --> 04:16:40.559
Nettle said in an icy voice.

04:16:40.620 --> 04:16:43.559
Perhaps we could switch to places, and

04:16:43.559 --> 04:16:45.360
your tribe could try growing up in a

04:16:45.360 --> 04:16:46.979
habitat where everything is trying to

04:16:46.979 --> 04:16:47.340
kill you.

04:16:47.459 --> 04:16:50.579
Can't I yell at her when she's being mean

04:16:50.579 --> 04:16:51.180
to cricket?

04:16:51.239 --> 04:16:54.059
Sundew wondered, glancing at Willow

04:16:54.059 --> 04:16:54.299
again.

04:16:54.360 --> 04:16:57.059
She was studying the trees overhead now.

04:16:57.120 --> 04:17:00.659
Although, I guess I've said things almost

04:17:00.659 --> 04:17:02.520
exactly like that to Cricket 2.

04:17:02.700 --> 04:17:06.000
She nudged cricket, who was looking

04:17:06.000 --> 04:17:06.840
pretty deflated.

04:17:06.899 --> 04:17:09.719
I bet you're dying to ask about the

04:17:09.719 --> 04:17:11.399
mansion eels, she said.

04:17:11.520 --> 04:17:13.680
The hive wing wrinkled her snout.

04:17:13.739 --> 04:17:16.979
I've been restraining myself, she

04:17:16.979 --> 04:17:17.399
whispered.

04:17:17.459 --> 04:17:20.459
You can see them over there, Sandu said

04:17:20.520 --> 04:17:22.559
pointing to the grove of trees that

04:17:22.559 --> 04:17:24.540
crowded all the way up against the left

04:17:24.540 --> 04:17:25.200
bank of the lake.

04:17:25.260 --> 04:17:28.200
The fruit looks edible, but will make you

04:17:28.200 --> 04:17:29.520
insane and then kill you.

04:17:29.579 --> 04:17:32.399
Also, the sap is poisonous.

04:17:32.459 --> 04:17:35.219
If you stand under one while it's raining

04:17:35.219 --> 04:17:37.680
poisonous sap will drip on you and you

04:17:37.680 --> 04:17:38.100
will die.

04:17:38.159 --> 04:17:41.159
Also, they are covered in wicked thorns.

04:17:41.280 --> 04:17:45.719
Like I said, willow chimed in, scary

04:17:45.719 --> 04:17:48.180
death trees, she pointed up.

04:17:48.239 --> 04:17:51.000
I think we have enough room to fly over

04:17:51.000 --> 04:17:51.479
the lake.

04:17:51.600 --> 04:17:55.379
If we're careful, go one at a time, and

04:17:55.379 --> 04:17:57.959
avoid the dragon traps, trumpet flowers

04:17:57.959 --> 04:17:59.520
and were rigelas.

04:17:59.579 --> 04:18:01.319
Roar Ridgelas?

04:18:01.319 --> 04:18:02.940
Crickets said alertly.

04:18:03.000 --> 04:18:05.459
Do you know anything?

04:18:05.520 --> 04:18:07.260
Nettle demanded.

04:18:07.379 --> 04:18:09.719
Nettle, stop it.

04:18:09.780 --> 04:18:13.079
Willow said, in her most extremely very

04:18:13.079 --> 04:18:16.260
stern voice, where Ridgulas are like

04:18:16.260 --> 04:18:19.319
sticky death shrubs, she said to

04:18:19.319 --> 04:18:19.860
Cricket.

04:18:19.920 --> 04:18:22.920
If you brush up against one, you'll be

04:18:22.920 --> 04:18:25.079
stuck there until assassin bugs come and

04:18:25.079 --> 04:18:25.559
eat you.

04:18:25.620 --> 04:18:29.159
Urgh, Mandrake said faintly.

04:18:29.219 --> 04:18:31.979
You know, I'm really not sure why

04:18:31.979 --> 04:18:33.840
Belladonna wanted me to be on this

04:18:33.840 --> 04:18:34.139
mission.

04:18:34.260 --> 04:18:37.559
So you could keep an eye on send you, of

04:18:37.559 --> 04:18:39.360
course, Nettles snapped.

04:18:39.420 --> 04:18:40.979
Sundew bristled.

04:18:41.040 --> 04:18:43.860
Nobody needs to keep any eyes on me.

04:18:43.920 --> 04:18:45.299
Gross.

04:18:45.360 --> 04:18:46.079
How dare you?

04:18:46.200 --> 04:18:48.000
Sundo.

04:18:48.059 --> 04:18:51.540
Stop, Willow said, resting her tail

04:18:51.540 --> 04:18:53.159
gently on sundew's shoulder.

04:18:53.219 --> 04:18:54.899
Just let it go.

04:18:54.959 --> 04:18:57.239
We have more important things to worry

04:18:57.239 --> 04:18:57.540
about.

04:18:57.600 --> 04:19:00.840
Sundew scowled at Nettle.

04:19:00.899 --> 04:19:02.639
It was bad enough when Nettle was just

04:19:02.639 --> 04:19:03.360
irritating.

04:19:03.420 --> 04:19:06.420
But there would be justifiable murder

04:19:06.420 --> 04:19:08.579
involved if Nettle kept making Willow

04:19:08.579 --> 04:19:09.780
talk to Sundew like that.

04:19:09.840 --> 04:19:13.979
I'll fly across first, Willow said, to

04:19:13.979 --> 04:19:15.899
make sure there's a safe path.

04:19:15.959 --> 04:19:18.840
No, I'll fly across first.

04:19:18.899 --> 04:19:21.780
Nettle said, I'm not scared if that's

04:19:21.780 --> 04:19:22.260
what you think.

04:19:22.319 --> 04:19:25.799
Willow held out her talons, palms up.

04:19:25.860 --> 04:19:27.780
I do not think that.

04:19:27.840 --> 04:19:30.180
Of course you can go 1st if you want to.

04:19:30.239 --> 04:19:34.500
That's right, Nettle muttered, shaking

04:19:34.500 --> 04:19:36.540
the last bits of slime off her wings.

04:19:36.600 --> 04:19:39.000
There was mud caked between her scales

04:19:39.000 --> 04:19:41.639
and trails of dried slime along her neck

04:19:41.639 --> 04:19:43.860
and tail, but at least she was able to

04:19:43.860 --> 04:19:44.280
fly again.

04:19:44.340 --> 04:19:46.920
She stamped her feet a few times and then

04:19:46.920 --> 04:19:47.340
took off.

04:19:47.399 --> 04:19:51.360
They all squinted after her, watching her

04:19:51.360 --> 04:19:53.639
path as she zigzagged and maneuvered

04:19:53.639 --> 04:19:55.200
around the obstacles that hung over the

04:19:55.200 --> 04:19:55.440
lake.

04:19:55.500 --> 04:19:59.100
It must be exhausting to be that angry

04:19:59.100 --> 04:20:01.979
all the time, Willow commented.

04:20:02.040 --> 04:20:04.260
I'm not, though, Sundew said.

04:20:04.379 --> 04:20:05.520
You know that, right?

04:20:05.579 --> 04:20:08.040
That I'm not like that.

04:20:08.159 --> 04:20:12.659
I know, Willow said, but her smile seemed

04:20:12.659 --> 04:20:13.739
a little hesitant.

04:20:13.799 --> 04:20:16.739
Sundew thought for a moment, and then

04:20:16.739 --> 04:20:17.700
said carefully.

04:20:17.819 --> 04:20:21.239
But it's not bad to be angry.

04:20:21.299 --> 04:20:23.700
Sometimes there are things a dragon

04:20:23.700 --> 04:20:25.079
should be angry about.

04:20:25.139 --> 04:20:29.700
I guess, Willow said. looking down at her

04:20:29.700 --> 04:20:30.180
claws.

04:20:30.239 --> 04:20:33.719
It's just not usually my 1st reaction to

04:20:33.719 --> 04:20:34.020
anything.

04:20:34.139 --> 04:20:37.200
Like everything about the hive wings and

04:20:37.200 --> 04:20:37.680
what they did.

04:20:37.739 --> 04:20:41.159
It makes me really, really sad.

04:20:41.219 --> 04:20:43.559
If I think about it too much.

04:20:43.620 --> 04:20:46.680
I want to curl up in a pile of leaves and

04:20:46.680 --> 04:20:47.040
cry.

04:20:47.100 --> 04:20:49.979
But what good would it do to be mad

04:20:49.979 --> 04:20:50.700
instead?

04:20:50.819 --> 04:20:54.420
I mean, whenever I do get mad, I usually

04:20:54.420 --> 04:20:57.840
end up feeling guilty or really tired or

04:20:57.840 --> 04:20:58.079
both.

04:20:58.200 --> 04:21:02.280
It's not like that for me, Sundu said.

04:21:02.340 --> 04:21:05.879
Maybe the guilty part sometimes, but

04:21:05.879 --> 04:21:07.739
being mad makes me want to get up and do

04:21:07.739 --> 04:21:08.159
something.

04:21:08.219 --> 04:21:11.100
It makes me want to fix the bad things.

04:21:11.159 --> 04:21:13.739
Isn't that better than curling up under a

04:21:13.739 --> 04:21:15.780
pile of leaves and hoping the bad things

04:21:15.780 --> 04:21:16.260
go away?

04:21:16.319 --> 04:21:19.319
Willow looked into her eyes for a long

04:21:19.319 --> 04:21:21.659
moment, as if she was really thinking

04:21:21.659 --> 04:21:23.040
about sundew's point.

04:21:23.100 --> 04:21:25.680
Yes, she said finally.

04:21:25.739 --> 04:21:27.299
That makes sense.

04:21:27.420 --> 04:21:29.219
It does?

04:21:29.280 --> 04:21:31.440
Sundew said, startled.

04:21:31.500 --> 04:21:34.379
In her tribe, arguments went all day.

04:21:34.440 --> 04:21:37.500
And nobody ever admitted that the other

04:21:37.500 --> 04:21:39.120
dragon had said something sensible.

04:21:39.180 --> 04:21:42.479
Willow glanced sideways at cricket and

04:21:42.479 --> 04:21:45.120
mandrake, but their gazes were riveted on

04:21:45.120 --> 04:21:47.639
Nettle as she negotiated a tricky spiral

04:21:47.639 --> 04:21:48.899
under a Strangler vine.

04:21:49.020 --> 04:21:51.899
I like that you want to fix the bad

04:21:51.899 --> 04:21:52.260
things.

04:21:52.379 --> 04:21:55.680
Willows said softly, touching one of

04:21:55.680 --> 04:21:57.239
sundew's talons with her own.

04:21:57.360 --> 04:22:00.540
But are you only mad at the bad things?

04:22:00.600 --> 04:22:03.540
Or are you mad at everybody all the

04:22:03.540 --> 04:22:03.780
time?

04:22:03.840 --> 04:22:07.200
Sundew bit back a snappy retort.

04:22:07.260 --> 04:22:08.879
That wasn't fair.

04:22:08.940 --> 04:22:12.059
She wasn't mad all the time, and when she

04:22:12.059 --> 04:22:14.399
was mad, the other dragon clearly

04:22:14.399 --> 04:22:15.000
deserved it.

04:22:15.059 --> 04:22:17.159
She made it.

04:22:17.280 --> 04:22:18.780
Mandrake shouted.

04:22:18.840 --> 04:22:20.760
He jumped up and down, flapping his

04:22:20.760 --> 04:22:21.120
wings.

04:22:21.180 --> 04:22:22.379
We can do this.

04:22:22.440 --> 04:22:24.959
Do you want to go next?

04:22:25.020 --> 04:22:26.340
Cricket asked him.

04:22:26.399 --> 04:22:29.459
I'd rather watch someone else one more

04:22:29.459 --> 04:22:32.340
time, he said, if that's all right.

04:22:32.399 --> 04:22:35.459
I'll go, Willow said.

04:22:35.520 --> 04:22:38.280
She brushed Sundew's wing lightly, with

04:22:38.280 --> 04:22:40.739
an expression that might have meant, sorry

04:22:40.739 --> 04:22:44.459
don't be mad, or we'll be all right, or

04:22:44.459 --> 04:22:46.799
I'm totally falling out of love with you

04:22:46.799 --> 04:22:47.219
right now.

04:22:47.280 --> 04:22:51.360
Sundew wasn't sure, but she wished she

04:22:51.360 --> 04:22:53.040
had something to stab to make herself

04:22:53.040 --> 04:22:53.879
feel a little better.

04:22:53.940 --> 04:22:57.299
Willow's crossing was smoother and more

04:22:57.299 --> 04:22:58.620
graceful than nettles.

04:22:58.680 --> 04:23:00.180
Objectively true.

04:23:00.239 --> 04:23:02.700
Not at all, sundew's biased opinion.

04:23:02.760 --> 04:23:06.479
Mandrake went after her, swerving wildly

04:23:06.479 --> 04:23:08.819
around Origula, and swooping low enough

04:23:08.819 --> 04:23:10.680
that he nearly fell in the lake a couple

04:23:10.680 --> 04:23:11.040
of times.

04:23:11.100 --> 04:23:13.739
But at last he made it safely to the

04:23:13.739 --> 04:23:14.100
other side.

04:23:14.159 --> 04:23:18.479
All right, Cricket said. taking a deep

04:23:18.479 --> 04:23:18.840
breath.

04:23:18.899 --> 04:23:20.280
I can do this.

04:23:20.340 --> 04:23:23.940
Let me take Bumblebee, Sundoo said.

04:23:24.000 --> 04:23:26.100
I'm more used to this kind of flying than

04:23:26.100 --> 04:23:27.719
you are, and she might throw you off.

04:23:27.780 --> 04:23:29.940
Snoodoo!

04:23:30.059 --> 04:23:31.440
Bumblebee cheered.

04:23:31.500 --> 04:23:33.959
She lifted her little talons up and did a

04:23:33.959 --> 04:23:35.459
very good impression of something cute.

04:23:35.520 --> 04:23:38.219
Something more like a tamarind and

04:23:38.219 --> 04:23:39.840
definitely not like a hive wing.

04:23:39.959 --> 04:23:41.760
Are you sure?

04:23:41.819 --> 04:23:42.780
Cricket asked.

04:23:42.840 --> 04:23:44.579
I thought you didn't want her getting

04:23:44.579 --> 04:23:45.420
attached to you.

04:23:45.479 --> 04:23:48.959
Well, I'm not planning to glue her to me

04:23:48.959 --> 04:23:50.040
Sundu said.

04:23:50.100 --> 04:23:52.620
I just figured I'd marginally increase

04:23:52.620 --> 04:23:53.940
both your odds for survival.

04:23:54.000 --> 04:23:58.860
I do like that goal, Cricket said, smiling

04:23:58.860 --> 04:24:00.360
as she untied the sling.

04:24:00.420 --> 04:24:02.940
She passed bumblebee into sundew's arms

04:24:02.940 --> 04:24:05.340
and started rewrapping the scarves around

04:24:05.340 --> 04:24:07.920
sundew's shoulders, readjusting her

04:24:07.920 --> 04:24:08.700
pouches as she did.

04:24:08.760 --> 04:24:12.059
Bumblebee was lighter than sundew had

04:24:12.059 --> 04:24:12.360
expected.

04:24:12.420 --> 04:24:15.659
A warm little ball of scales with lots of

04:24:15.659 --> 04:24:16.440
spiky bits.

04:24:16.500 --> 04:24:19.379
Her elbows and wings and horns and tail

04:24:19.379 --> 04:24:22.020
all seemed to poke sundew at once, as the

04:24:22.020 --> 04:24:24.420
dragonette wriggled around, burbling with

04:24:24.420 --> 04:24:24.719
joy.

04:24:24.780 --> 04:24:27.659
But after a moment, she settled with her

04:24:27.659 --> 04:24:30.120
wings tucked in and nudged her nose under

04:24:30.120 --> 04:24:31.200
sundew's chin.

04:24:31.260 --> 04:24:33.899
One of her tiny talons wrapped around the

04:24:33.899 --> 04:24:35.459
pouch with a jade frog in it.

04:24:35.520 --> 04:24:39.059
It felt weirdly comfortable and mildly

04:24:39.059 --> 04:24:40.020
alarming at the same time.

04:24:40.079 --> 04:24:43.079
This was definitely a small living thing

04:24:43.079 --> 04:24:45.059
that might die if sundew did anything

04:24:45.059 --> 04:24:45.659
wrong.

04:24:45.719 --> 04:24:48.420
But it was also a small living thing that

04:24:48.420 --> 04:24:50.159
apparently completely trusted her.

04:24:50.219 --> 04:24:53.940
Plants did that sometimes, but plants

04:24:53.940 --> 04:24:55.079
weren't exactly cuddly.

04:24:55.139 --> 04:24:57.000
We're fine.

04:24:57.059 --> 04:24:59.819
Sundu said to Cricket, stop fussing and

04:24:59.819 --> 04:25:00.239
get flying.

04:25:00.299 --> 04:25:03.600
She watched cricket dart and hover

04:25:03.600 --> 04:25:04.620
through the obstacles.

04:25:04.680 --> 04:25:06.959
Pausing now and then to peer at a plant

04:25:06.959 --> 04:25:07.979
she didn't recognize.

04:25:08.040 --> 04:25:10.139
One of them turned out to be an

04:25:10.139 --> 04:25:12.299
iridescent pink beetle instead of a

04:25:12.299 --> 04:25:15.299
flower, and it shot a blast of acid at

04:25:15.299 --> 04:25:18.299
her, that she just managed to duck before

04:25:18.299 --> 04:25:20.100
heading down to land on the opposite

04:25:20.100 --> 04:25:20.700
shore.

04:25:20.760 --> 04:25:23.879
Sundew tugged the scarf a little higher

04:25:23.879 --> 04:25:25.200
up Bumblebee's neck.

04:25:25.260 --> 04:25:29.579
Our turn, little bug, stay very still, and

04:25:29.579 --> 04:25:31.319
do not distract me.

04:25:31.379 --> 04:25:32.219
Understand?

04:25:32.280 --> 04:25:34.739
Oobi, goo.

04:25:34.799 --> 04:25:36.659
Bumblebee said sternly.

04:25:36.719 --> 04:25:38.520
She patted Sundu's face.

04:25:38.579 --> 04:25:41.579
Do knobby, splam flamp.

04:25:41.639 --> 04:25:44.639
I wasn't planning on being splam flam

04:25:44.639 --> 04:25:46.500
Sundu retorted, whatever that is.

04:25:46.559 --> 04:25:50.340
She lifted off, wobbling a little as she

04:25:50.340 --> 04:25:51.899
adjusted to Bumblebee's weight.

04:25:52.020 --> 04:25:54.780
Her claws skimmed the lake's surface as

04:25:54.780 --> 04:25:57.000
she flew under a crisscrossing tangle of

04:25:57.000 --> 04:25:59.760
vines, and below her, she saw blurry

04:25:59.760 --> 04:26:01.979
water wheels, snapping shut on the

04:26:01.979 --> 04:26:02.940
ripples.

04:26:03.000 --> 04:26:06.059
A knobbly reptilian head rose from the

04:26:06.059 --> 04:26:08.159
depths to stare at her with yellow eyes

04:26:08.159 --> 04:26:10.319
but she didn't stop to figure out what it

04:26:10.319 --> 04:26:10.620
was.

04:26:10.680 --> 04:26:14.579
Up a little higher, over a knot of dragon

04:26:14.579 --> 04:26:17.700
traps, wings tucked to fit between a loop

04:26:17.700 --> 04:26:20.340
of dangling snakes, and a glittering web

04:26:20.340 --> 04:26:22.139
of poisonous sap.

04:26:22.200 --> 04:26:24.360
Now she had a straight line of sight to

04:26:24.360 --> 04:26:26.280
the 4 dragons waiting on the far side.

04:26:26.340 --> 04:26:28.440
Nettle was twitching her tail

04:26:28.440 --> 04:26:29.159
impatiently.

04:26:29.219 --> 04:26:30.959
Willow looked anxious.

04:26:31.020 --> 04:26:32.819
Not much farther.

04:26:32.879 --> 04:26:34.500
She said to Bumblebee.

04:26:34.559 --> 04:26:37.500
She beat her wings once and turned into a

04:26:37.500 --> 04:26:37.799
dive.

04:26:37.860 --> 04:26:41.340
And then suddenly Bumblebee shrieked, be

04:26:41.340 --> 04:26:44.399
bluff, and flung herself upward, grabbing

04:26:44.399 --> 04:26:47.159
sundew's horns, pulling them down, and

04:26:47.159 --> 04:26:49.319
smacking her little body over sundew's

04:26:49.319 --> 04:26:49.680
entire face.

04:26:49.739 --> 04:26:53.520
Sundew yelped and fell. momentarily

04:26:53.520 --> 04:26:54.120
blinded.

04:26:54.180 --> 04:26:56.760
Her wings flailed to catch the air.

04:26:56.819 --> 04:27:00.120
And instead, she felt one of them catch

04:27:00.120 --> 04:27:00.899
on something else.

04:27:00.959 --> 04:27:04.920
Something sticky and prickling that

04:27:04.920 --> 04:27:07.620
caught and held her wing fast, slamming

04:27:07.620 --> 04:27:08.340
her to a stop.

04:27:08.399 --> 04:27:10.979
Her momentum spun her toward the caught

04:27:10.979 --> 04:27:13.739
wing, she flung out a talon to stop

04:27:13.739 --> 04:27:16.379
herself, and felt it smack straight into

04:27:16.379 --> 04:27:18.239
the same gluey ooze.

04:27:18.299 --> 04:27:22.500
She was trapped, and so was Bumblebee, and

04:27:22.500 --> 04:27:24.600
she could already feel the other tendrils

04:27:24.600 --> 04:27:25.200
closing in.

04:27:25.260 --> 04:27:30.000
Whispered the plant.

04:27:30.059 --> 04:27:33.959
So delicious.

04:27:34.020 --> 04:27:38.399
Chapter 13.

04:27:38.579 --> 04:27:41.040
Sundoo.

04:27:41.100 --> 04:27:42.299
Willow screamed.

04:27:42.420 --> 04:27:45.239
Sundew couldn't see around the black and

04:27:45.239 --> 04:27:47.219
yellow scales draped over her snout.

04:27:47.280 --> 04:27:49.559
She didn't even know exactly which kind

04:27:49.559 --> 04:27:51.180
of sticky plant had caught them.

04:27:51.239 --> 04:27:55.079
Bumblebee, she said, trying to keep the

04:27:55.079 --> 04:27:55.979
panic out of her voice.

04:27:56.040 --> 04:27:57.540
Are you all right?

04:27:57.600 --> 04:28:01.200
Bumblebee said in a small voice.

04:28:01.260 --> 04:28:03.719
Good, said Sundew.

04:28:03.780 --> 04:28:06.000
Then what in the name of all the trees

04:28:06.000 --> 04:28:06.540
was that?

04:28:06.659 --> 04:28:08.459
Eep?

04:28:08.579 --> 04:28:11.040
Bumblebee said in an even smaller voice.

04:28:11.100 --> 04:28:12.600
Bebuff.

04:28:12.659 --> 04:28:16.079
Get off my face, Sundew snapped.

04:28:16.139 --> 04:28:17.280
Carefully.

04:28:17.340 --> 04:28:19.379
I am really mad at you.

04:28:19.440 --> 04:28:22.920
Beep, beep, beep, beep, beep.

04:28:22.979 --> 04:28:26.219
Bumblebee protested. wiggling down until

04:28:26.219 --> 04:28:28.500
she was hanging from Sundew's snout with

04:28:28.500 --> 04:28:29.879
her tail around Sunday's neck.

04:28:29.940 --> 04:28:32.700
She managed to scoot herself back into

04:28:32.700 --> 04:28:34.860
the sling and leaned into Sundew's chest

04:28:34.860 --> 04:28:37.260
patting her heart under the jade frog.

04:28:37.319 --> 04:28:39.600
Miss Snoogoo.

04:28:39.719 --> 04:28:44.340
Goo is right, Sundoo said, studying their

04:28:44.340 --> 04:28:44.940
abductor.

04:28:45.000 --> 04:28:47.579
She was stuck on one of the towering

04:28:47.579 --> 04:28:49.739
leaves of a plant that sprawled across a

04:28:49.739 --> 04:28:51.600
small island in the lake below her.

04:28:51.899 --> 04:28:55.319
The leaf was bright lime green, with 100s

04:28:55.319 --> 04:28:57.959
of thin red stalks poking out of it that

04:28:57.959 --> 04:29:00.059
made the entire plant look fuzzily

04:29:00.059 --> 04:29:01.079
scarlet from afar.

04:29:01.139 --> 04:29:03.959
At the tip of each stalk was a glistening

04:29:03.959 --> 04:29:06.600
drop, like a translucent murder pearl.

04:29:06.659 --> 04:29:09.780
Oh, no, Sundu muttered.

04:29:09.840 --> 04:29:15.000
Isn't this amazing, Nettle called, with

04:29:15.000 --> 04:29:16.920
an undeniable note of triumph in her

04:29:16.920 --> 04:29:17.159
voice.

04:29:17.219 --> 04:29:20.639
The great and wonderful sundew trapped by

04:29:20.639 --> 04:29:22.559
an actual sundew.

04:29:22.680 --> 04:29:24.899
That's a sundew?

04:29:25.020 --> 04:29:26.399
Cricket said.

04:29:26.459 --> 04:29:26.879
Huh.

04:29:26.940 --> 04:29:28.440
I thought they'd be prettier.

04:29:28.500 --> 04:29:31.200
That thing looks like a giant spider got

04:29:31.200 --> 04:29:33.659
turned into a plant and sprouted weird

04:29:33.659 --> 04:29:35.040
red hairs all over it.

04:29:35.100 --> 04:29:37.979
But you can get away from it.

04:29:38.040 --> 04:29:38.700
Right, Sundoo?

04:29:38.760 --> 04:29:40.620
Sundo?

04:29:40.680 --> 04:29:41.940
Willow cried.

04:29:42.000 --> 04:29:42.959
Don't move.

04:29:43.020 --> 04:29:46.680
That was an unhelpfully obvious piece of

04:29:46.680 --> 04:29:47.040
advice.

04:29:47.100 --> 04:29:49.860
Sundu knew that struggling would only

04:29:49.860 --> 04:29:52.200
trap her worse, but she didn't exactly

04:29:52.200 --> 04:29:53.760
have many options at the moment.

04:29:53.819 --> 04:29:57.180
Three of the sticky dewdrops, had snagged

04:29:57.180 --> 04:29:58.680
Sundew's left wing tip.

04:29:58.739 --> 04:30:01.319
Her right front talon was caught on

04:30:01.319 --> 04:30:03.899
another 2, and her back talons were

04:30:03.899 --> 04:30:05.760
snared and still more below her.

04:30:05.819 --> 04:30:08.520
As she tried to brace the rest of her

04:30:08.520 --> 04:30:09.959
body away from the plant.

04:30:10.020 --> 04:30:13.860
Huddled in her sling, Bumblebee was

04:30:13.860 --> 04:30:16.979
trapped between Sundew and the sundew, but

04:30:16.979 --> 04:30:18.780
she hadn't touched the sticky substance

04:30:18.780 --> 04:30:19.020
yet.

04:30:19.079 --> 04:30:22.379
She peeked at it with wide eyes, more

04:30:22.379 --> 04:30:25.139
still than sundew had ever seen her, as

04:30:25.139 --> 04:30:26.760
though she understood the danger of

04:30:26.760 --> 04:30:27.000
moving.

04:30:27.120 --> 04:30:30.180
The other tentacles on the leaf were

04:30:30.180 --> 04:30:33.360
creeping toward them, leaning, drooping

04:30:33.360 --> 04:30:34.860
closer and closer.

04:30:34.860 --> 04:30:38.219
In a few moments, new beads would reach

04:30:38.219 --> 04:30:40.680
her scales, latching on with gummy

04:30:40.680 --> 04:30:41.399
ferocity.

04:30:41.459 --> 04:30:44.520
Soon after that, the tentacles would wrap

04:30:44.520 --> 04:30:47.459
tighter, drawing her inescapably into

04:30:47.459 --> 04:30:50.100
their embrace, until they held her and

04:30:50.100 --> 04:30:53.579
Bumblebee as close as they could, until

04:30:53.579 --> 04:30:56.280
they suffocated and died, and were

04:30:56.280 --> 04:30:57.360
consumed by the plant.

04:30:57.420 --> 04:31:00.959
She summoned all the power of her leaf

04:31:00.959 --> 04:31:01.500
speak.

04:31:01.559 --> 04:31:02.760
Stop.

04:31:02.819 --> 04:31:04.920
She screamed at the tentacles.

04:31:04.979 --> 04:31:07.139
The sundew froze.

04:31:07.200 --> 04:31:10.559
Each red stalk tentacle paused where it

04:31:10.559 --> 04:31:13.079
was, as though the plant was staring at

04:31:13.079 --> 04:31:15.299
her with a 100 glistening beady eyes.

04:31:15.360 --> 04:31:18.000
Let us go.

04:31:18.059 --> 04:31:19.260
She ordered it.

04:31:19.319 --> 04:31:23.520
A long pause as confused messages fired

04:31:23.520 --> 04:31:25.920
up and down the sundew's synapses.

04:31:25.979 --> 04:31:29.700
Can't, it finally whispered back.

04:31:29.819 --> 04:31:32.819
Not so much a response as an observation

04:31:32.819 --> 04:31:35.940
echoing through the leaves. hungry.

04:31:36.000 --> 04:31:39.600
Want this, mine.

04:31:39.659 --> 04:31:43.559
One of the tentacles reached for her face

04:31:43.559 --> 04:31:46.260
and she roared, stop again.

04:31:46.319 --> 04:31:50.280
It froze once more, but it was so close

04:31:50.280 --> 04:31:52.920
to her eye now that she couldn't stop the

04:31:52.920 --> 04:31:54.600
panic thundering through her heart.

04:31:54.719 --> 04:31:58.020
The plant sensed it, and flickered

04:31:58.020 --> 04:32:00.360
something curious and malevolent back at

04:32:00.360 --> 04:32:00.540
her.

04:32:00.600 --> 04:32:03.899
Her fear tasted delicious to it.

04:32:03.959 --> 04:32:05.700
I'm not scared.

04:32:05.760 --> 04:32:07.920
She snarled out loud.

04:32:07.979 --> 04:32:10.440
I want to rip you out by your roots and

04:32:10.440 --> 04:32:11.760
burn you to ashes.

04:32:11.879 --> 04:32:13.979
Malevolent flicker.

04:32:14.040 --> 04:32:15.899
More.

04:32:15.959 --> 04:32:19.319
It liked the taste of her anger too.

04:32:19.379 --> 04:32:23.159
She shuddered despite herself, and felt a

04:32:23.159 --> 04:32:24.360
tentacle snag on her tail.

04:32:24.479 --> 04:32:27.780
She had to stay calm, especially for

04:32:27.780 --> 04:32:28.500
bumblebee.

04:32:28.559 --> 04:32:31.139
The rotten little bugface had gotten her

04:32:31.139 --> 04:32:33.000
into this mess, but she didn't have to

04:32:33.000 --> 04:32:33.479
die for it.

04:32:33.540 --> 04:32:36.719
You do not want this prey.

04:32:36.719 --> 04:32:39.780
She thought forcefully and leaf speak.

04:32:39.840 --> 04:32:41.340
It will sicken you.

04:32:41.399 --> 04:32:43.680
Hmm.

04:32:43.680 --> 04:32:47.219
The sundew responded with skepticism.

04:32:47.280 --> 04:32:49.139
Sundoo?

04:32:49.200 --> 04:32:51.719
I'm coming to get you, Willow called.

04:32:51.780 --> 04:32:54.479
No, Sundu shouted back.

04:32:54.540 --> 04:32:56.040
You'll only get stuck too.

04:32:56.100 --> 04:32:57.719
I can get out of this.

04:32:57.780 --> 04:32:58.440
Stay there.

04:32:58.500 --> 04:33:00.659
Mafib?

04:33:00.780 --> 04:33:03.479
Bumblebee asked, wiggling her head up

04:33:03.479 --> 04:33:05.340
closer to sundoos.

04:33:05.400 --> 04:33:07.560
She poked the jade frog pout with one of

04:33:07.560 --> 04:33:08.159
her claws.

04:33:08.220 --> 04:33:09.840
Sme buff?

04:33:09.959 --> 04:33:13.020
Sme buff, sundew echoed.

04:33:13.080 --> 04:33:15.060
Are you trying to annoy me to death

04:33:15.060 --> 04:33:16.619
before the plant eats me?

04:33:16.680 --> 04:33:18.060
you wretched little lizard?

04:33:18.119 --> 04:33:19.619
Boof.

04:33:19.680 --> 04:33:22.020
Bumblebee insisted indignantly.

04:33:22.080 --> 04:33:24.720
She leaned under Sundu's left arm and

04:33:24.720 --> 04:33:25.680
jabbed another pouch.

04:33:25.740 --> 04:33:27.659
Boof, boof, boof.

04:33:27.720 --> 04:33:30.299
Sundew was about to yell at her to shut

04:33:30.299 --> 04:33:30.540
up.

04:33:30.599 --> 04:33:33.059
When a realization hit her like a falling

04:33:33.059 --> 04:33:33.419
tree.

04:33:33.479 --> 04:33:37.139
Wait, she said, are you trying to say

04:33:37.139 --> 04:33:37.740
bug?

04:33:37.799 --> 04:33:40.740
Does a mi Zacco?

04:33:40.860 --> 04:33:43.380
Bumblebee shouted, as though she couldn't

04:33:43.380 --> 04:33:45.060
believe how thick Sundew's head was.

04:33:45.119 --> 04:33:46.379
Bluff.

04:33:46.439 --> 04:33:49.139
I do have a couple of bugs in there

04:33:49.139 --> 04:33:50.399
Sundew said.

04:33:50.459 --> 04:33:51.659
That might.

04:33:51.659 --> 04:33:53.639
Shush, and let me think.

04:33:53.759 --> 04:33:56.759
Shmasham, is-mush.

04:33:56.880 --> 04:33:58.259
Bumblebee grumbled.

04:33:58.319 --> 04:34:00.900
She draped herself around Sundu's free

04:34:00.900 --> 04:34:02.939
arm and glared at the tentacles.

04:34:03.000 --> 04:34:05.639
Most of them were still hovering as the

04:34:05.639 --> 04:34:08.159
plant decided what to do, but a few were

04:34:08.159 --> 04:34:11.279
stealing closer at a snail's pace, as if

04:34:11.279 --> 04:34:12.900
hoping no one would notice until too

04:34:12.900 --> 04:34:13.139
late.

04:34:13.200 --> 04:34:15.060
Bugs.

04:34:15.119 --> 04:34:16.379
Boof.

04:34:16.439 --> 04:34:17.219
Wait.

04:34:17.340 --> 04:34:18.720
Be buff.

04:34:18.779 --> 04:34:21.059
What if that actually meant something?

04:34:21.119 --> 04:34:24.179
Willow, Sundew called.

04:34:24.240 --> 04:34:26.580
Did you see why Bumblebee freaked out?

04:34:26.639 --> 04:34:27.720
Did she see something?

04:34:27.779 --> 04:34:30.899
Yes, Willow called back.

04:34:30.959 --> 04:34:32.459
Didn't you see it too?

04:34:32.520 --> 04:34:34.560
Obviously not.

04:34:34.619 --> 04:34:35.339
What was it?

04:34:35.400 --> 04:34:38.400
It was the biggest set sea fly I've ever

04:34:38.400 --> 04:34:40.200
seen, Cricket exclaimed.

04:34:40.259 --> 04:34:42.479
It was like 3 times the size of

04:34:42.479 --> 04:34:43.139
bumblebee.

04:34:43.200 --> 04:34:46.200
All the insects are oversized here

04:34:46.200 --> 04:34:47.520
Mandrake said.

04:34:47.580 --> 04:34:49.619
At least, that's what my father says.

04:34:49.680 --> 04:34:53.159
Now Sundu had a vague memory of something

04:34:53.159 --> 04:34:54.119
buzzing nearby.

04:34:54.180 --> 04:34:56.759
Right before Bumblebee grabbed her face.

04:34:56.819 --> 04:34:59.759
She hated setsy flies.

04:34:59.819 --> 04:35:02.159
One of her favorite teachers had been

04:35:02.159 --> 04:35:04.380
killed by a setsy flybite.

04:35:04.439 --> 04:35:06.719
After that, she'd made it her personal

04:35:06.719 --> 04:35:08.939
mission to tell every carnivorous plant

04:35:08.939 --> 04:35:11.699
near the village to eat as many set sea

04:35:11.699 --> 04:35:13.919
flies as possible, and they hadn't been

04:35:13.919 --> 04:35:15.479
seen in her part of the jungle ever

04:35:15.479 --> 04:35:15.899
since.

04:35:15.959 --> 04:35:18.419
But this wasn't her part of the jungle.

04:35:18.540 --> 04:35:21.479
Willow, where did it go?

04:35:21.540 --> 04:35:22.500
Can you still see it?

04:35:22.560 --> 04:35:25.259
No, Willow said.

04:35:25.319 --> 04:35:26.279
Nothing.

04:35:26.340 --> 04:35:28.560
Maybe there?

04:35:28.619 --> 04:35:30.779
Mandrake's voice said nervously.

04:35:30.840 --> 04:35:33.959
Oh, yes, I think so.

04:35:34.020 --> 04:35:37.860
Sundu, to your right and above you, on

04:35:37.860 --> 04:35:38.400
the vine.

04:35:38.459 --> 04:35:41.159
Sundu carefully inched her head around

04:35:41.159 --> 04:35:41.819
and looked up.

04:35:41.880 --> 04:35:45.180
She glimpsed the shimmer of wings and a

04:35:45.180 --> 04:35:47.819
huge blackish brown body, nearly hidden

04:35:47.819 --> 04:35:48.299
by leaves.

04:35:48.360 --> 04:35:51.840
She tried to think, but it had been a

04:35:51.840 --> 04:35:53.639
long time since she'd studied them.

04:35:53.759 --> 04:35:57.539
What attracts setsi flies, she yelled to

04:35:57.539 --> 04:35:58.139
her friends.

04:35:58.200 --> 04:35:59.819
Attracts them?

04:35:59.880 --> 04:36:00.900
Nettle shouted.

04:36:00.959 --> 04:36:02.340
Why would he want to do that?

04:36:02.400 --> 04:36:05.520
Maybe the smell of blood?

04:36:05.880 --> 04:36:06.479
Willow guessed.

04:36:06.540 --> 04:36:08.400
Bright colors.

04:36:08.459 --> 04:36:10.979
Cricket shouted, especially blue.

04:36:11.040 --> 04:36:12.540
Really?

04:36:12.599 --> 04:36:13.799
Mandrake said.

04:36:13.860 --> 04:36:14.639
How do you know that?

04:36:14.700 --> 04:36:16.740
I read a study.

04:36:16.799 --> 04:36:19.439
Cricket said, from a while ago, way

04:36:19.439 --> 04:36:20.639
before the tree wars.

04:36:20.700 --> 04:36:23.340
I kind of like reading studies.

04:36:23.459 --> 04:36:27.060
Worth a try, Sundew said, thinking

04:36:27.060 --> 04:36:28.560
quickly through the items in her

04:36:28.560 --> 04:36:29.159
pouches.

04:36:29.220 --> 04:36:31.319
The only problem was that she couldn't

04:36:31.319 --> 04:36:32.939
reach most of them with her only free

04:36:32.939 --> 04:36:35.520
talent, at least not without probably

04:36:35.520 --> 04:36:36.659
getting more stuck.

04:36:36.720 --> 04:36:38.159
She took a breath.

04:36:38.220 --> 04:36:39.720
Bumblebee.

04:36:39.779 --> 04:36:40.679
She said.

04:36:40.740 --> 04:36:41.639
Are you listening?

04:36:41.700 --> 04:36:43.979
Can you do something important for me?

04:36:44.040 --> 04:36:48.540
EM, Bumblebee said, in her most solemn

04:36:48.540 --> 04:36:51.479
voice, patches of black scales circled

04:36:51.479 --> 04:36:53.939
her yellow gold eyes, making her look a

04:36:53.939 --> 04:36:56.459
little like a tragic panda as she gazed

04:36:56.459 --> 04:36:57.720
up into Sundew's face.

04:36:57.779 --> 04:37:01.139
I need you to climb onto my back, Sundew

04:37:01.139 --> 04:37:01.379
said.

04:37:01.500 --> 04:37:02.459
Really?

04:37:02.520 --> 04:37:03.779
Carefully.

04:37:03.840 --> 04:37:07.319
Hold on tight, and find the leaf pouch

04:37:07.319 --> 04:37:10.020
under my left wing that's a darker green

04:37:10.020 --> 04:37:11.159
than the others.

04:37:11.220 --> 04:37:13.259
Do not open it yet.

04:37:13.380 --> 04:37:17.700
B Mish, Bumblebee said grandly.

04:37:17.759 --> 04:37:20.759
She crawled up onto Sundu's shoulder and

04:37:20.759 --> 04:37:23.039
started inching her way down Sundu's back

04:37:23.039 --> 04:37:25.379
clinging to the pouch straps and the

04:37:25.379 --> 04:37:26.999
other side of the slang as she went.

04:37:27.060 --> 04:37:29.700
Sandu could hear her singing softly to

04:37:29.700 --> 04:37:30.360
herself.

04:37:30.419 --> 04:37:32.699
Beamish, Snoo, do.

04:37:32.699 --> 04:37:34.979
Bump, bump, Snabble, eh?

04:37:35.040 --> 04:37:38.279
B, miss, new, do, bump, bump, snay, all

04:37:38.279 --> 04:37:38.520
day.

04:37:38.580 --> 04:37:41.520
The dragonette tugged at the fiber ropes

04:37:41.520 --> 04:37:44.459
wound around sundew's left wing, and one

04:37:44.459 --> 04:37:46.319
of the tentacles above them curled

04:37:46.319 --> 04:37:48.959
forward and glommed onto sundew's wing

04:37:48.959 --> 04:37:50.459
scales next to the others.

04:37:50.520 --> 04:37:54.959
Yuck, dragon, Sundew thought frantically

04:37:54.959 --> 04:37:55.560
at the plant.

04:37:55.619 --> 04:37:57.959
Dragons so very yuck.

04:37:58.020 --> 04:38:00.900
Sick, the plant that eats the dragons.

04:38:01.080 --> 04:38:07.080
The sun do thought, but then, shivering

04:38:07.080 --> 04:38:09.360
along its leaves from the central core

04:38:09.360 --> 04:38:11.099
sick.

04:38:11.159 --> 04:38:13.799
Sick.

04:38:13.860 --> 04:38:18.000
Poisonous yuck dragons, sundew tried.

04:38:18.060 --> 04:38:20.040
Maybe kill the sundew.

04:38:20.040 --> 04:38:22.560
Mind the meal.

04:38:22.619 --> 04:38:26.999
The plant whispered to itself, Danger.

04:38:27.060 --> 04:38:30.659
But, hunger.

04:38:30.720 --> 04:38:33.540
But danger.

04:38:33.599 --> 04:38:36.119
But hunger.

04:38:36.240 --> 04:38:38.459
Zob.

04:38:38.520 --> 04:38:40.979
Bumblebee announced, holding up the dark

04:38:40.979 --> 04:38:41.819
green pouch.

04:38:41.880 --> 04:38:45.240
In the inner fold, you'll find butterfly

04:38:45.240 --> 04:38:48.180
wings, Sundew said, pick out the blue

04:38:48.180 --> 04:38:50.279
ones, and throw them at the tentacles

04:38:50.279 --> 04:38:51.060
right above us.

04:38:51.119 --> 04:38:53.999
The dragonette hesitated, and Sunday

04:38:53.999 --> 04:38:56.279
realized that was too many instructions

04:38:56.279 --> 04:38:56.759
at once.

04:38:56.819 --> 04:38:59.279
Do you know the color blue?

04:38:59.340 --> 04:39:00.479
Sundu asked.

04:39:00.540 --> 04:39:03.900
Bumblebee glanced around nervously, then

04:39:03.900 --> 04:39:07.200
pointed it up with a, maybe, expression

04:39:07.200 --> 04:39:10.680
except up could be the sky, which was, in

04:39:10.680 --> 04:39:13.080
fact, blue, or the tree canopy that

04:39:13.080 --> 04:39:15.900
mostly hid it from view, which was not, or

04:39:15.900 --> 04:39:17.880
any of the various bright flowers and

04:39:17.880 --> 04:39:19.560
curious monkey faces watching them.

04:39:19.619 --> 04:39:22.859
Find a blue wing in there and show it to

04:39:22.859 --> 04:39:24.539
me, Sundu ordered.

04:39:24.599 --> 04:39:27.419
Her arms and back ached from the strain

04:39:27.419 --> 04:39:29.819
of pressing herself away from the sundew

04:39:29.819 --> 04:39:32.159
and her mind was getting very tired from

04:39:32.159 --> 04:39:34.139
trying to keep the leaf speak orders

04:39:34.139 --> 04:39:34.979
going at the same time.

04:39:35.040 --> 04:39:38.400
The little hive wing dug into the pouch

04:39:38.400 --> 04:39:41.040
for what felt like an age, and finally

04:39:41.040 --> 04:39:43.380
emerged with a talon full of bright blue

04:39:43.380 --> 04:39:44.700
morpho wings.

04:39:44.759 --> 04:39:48.240
That's right, Sundew said, twitching more

04:39:48.240 --> 04:39:49.979
than she meant to in her excitement.

04:39:50.040 --> 04:39:52.680
Another tentacle latched itself to her

04:39:52.680 --> 04:39:52.919
tail.

04:39:53.040 --> 04:39:54.180
Now.

04:39:54.419 --> 04:39:57.119
But Bumblebee wasn't waiting for more

04:39:57.119 --> 04:39:57.599
directions.

04:39:57.659 --> 04:40:00.360
She threw the morpho wings up at the

04:40:00.360 --> 04:40:02.099
stalk of the sundew that was slowly

04:40:02.099 --> 04:40:03.900
curving down toward them.

04:40:03.959 --> 04:40:06.659
The blues stuck where it landed, covering

04:40:06.659 --> 04:40:08.520
the scarlet and green with a small window

04:40:08.520 --> 04:40:11.459
of bright azure beauty, like Blue's

04:40:11.459 --> 04:40:11.759
wings.

04:40:11.819 --> 04:40:14.520
Bumblebee squeaked with delight at

04:40:14.520 --> 04:40:16.560
herself. and immediately pulled out

04:40:16.560 --> 04:40:17.520
another talon full.

04:40:17.580 --> 04:40:20.580
This one, when she threw it, turned out

04:40:20.580 --> 04:40:23.279
to have a few other colors mixed in, but

04:40:23.279 --> 04:40:25.200
it still looked like a shining mosaic

04:40:25.200 --> 04:40:27.900
most of it a blue that shone in the dark

04:40:27.900 --> 04:40:28.680
green jungle.

04:40:28.799 --> 04:40:31.439
The plant twitched around the scattered

04:40:31.439 --> 04:40:34.200
wings, bewildered by the new sensation

04:40:34.200 --> 04:40:35.400
that didn't match the others.

04:40:35.459 --> 04:40:40.439
The Setsy fly was moving.

04:40:40.500 --> 04:40:43.740
Only a little at first, hopping to a

04:40:43.740 --> 04:40:46.740
closer leaf, turning in a circle, glaring

04:40:46.740 --> 04:40:48.599
its wings and zipping them closed again

04:40:48.599 --> 04:40:50.459
Bumblebee?

04:40:50.520 --> 04:40:53.400
Sundew whispered, get back in the sling.

04:40:53.459 --> 04:40:57.000
Bumblebee clambered rapidly over Sundew's

04:40:57.000 --> 04:40:57.659
shoulder again.

04:40:57.720 --> 04:40:59.880
No singing or burbling this time.

04:40:59.939 --> 04:41:02.639
She crawled into the sling and wrapped it

04:41:02.639 --> 04:41:04.500
around herself with a little shiver.

04:41:04.560 --> 04:41:10.500
The Setsy zoomed past, close enough for

04:41:10.500 --> 04:41:12.599
Sundu to feel the wind of its passing

04:41:12.599 --> 04:41:13.680
against her free wing.

04:41:13.799 --> 04:41:17.099
She held still as it circled and dove

04:41:17.099 --> 04:41:17.340
again.

04:41:17.400 --> 04:41:20.459
It was studying the blue shapes with its

04:41:20.459 --> 04:41:21.599
huge horrible eyes.

04:41:21.659 --> 04:41:24.720
Come on, sundue prayed.

04:41:24.779 --> 04:41:26.099
Please let this work.

04:41:26.159 --> 04:41:30.360
With a final decisive buzz, the set sea

04:41:30.360 --> 04:41:32.759
fly swooped down and landed squarely on

04:41:32.759 --> 04:41:35.580
top of the blue wings just above sundew's

04:41:35.580 --> 04:41:35.939
head.

04:41:36.060 --> 04:41:38.639
She lunged forward and slammed her free

04:41:38.639 --> 04:41:41.279
talon into its back, smashing the fly

04:41:41.279 --> 04:41:42.840
into the sticky tentacles.

04:41:42.900 --> 04:41:46.080
It jerked and spasmed, but the sundew

04:41:46.080 --> 04:41:46.680
held it tight.

04:41:46.740 --> 04:41:50.040
More tentacles closed in, faster, the

04:41:50.040 --> 04:41:51.419
more the fly fought.

04:41:51.479 --> 04:41:52.799
Yes.

04:41:52.919 --> 04:41:55.560
The sundews leaves hissed.

04:41:55.680 --> 04:41:57.779
Take the fly.

04:41:57.840 --> 04:42:01.259
Sundew commanded, matching her leaf speak

04:42:01.259 --> 04:42:03.540
to the sundew's sly, curling tone.

04:42:03.599 --> 04:42:05.700
Delicious, yes.

04:42:05.759 --> 04:42:07.799
Dragons, yuck.

04:42:07.919 --> 04:42:10.799
Two of the stalks touching her wing

04:42:10.799 --> 04:42:12.840
pulled away, and reached for the fly

04:42:12.840 --> 04:42:13.380
instead.

04:42:13.439 --> 04:42:14.819
Then another.

04:42:14.880 --> 04:42:17.700
Then the ones trapping her talon let go.

04:42:17.759 --> 04:42:20.520
And gradually she felt the sun do

04:42:20.520 --> 04:42:23.159
releasing her, choosing the simpler, less

04:42:23.159 --> 04:42:24.779
argumentative prey instead.

04:42:24.900 --> 04:42:27.900
As soon as she could, she threw herself

04:42:27.900 --> 04:42:30.720
back into the air to freedom, she dove

04:42:30.720 --> 04:42:33.000
toward the lake shore, where Willow was

04:42:33.000 --> 04:42:35.279
waiting with outstretched arms and landed

04:42:35.279 --> 04:42:35.819
with a crash.

04:42:35.939 --> 04:42:37.979
Ha, ha!

04:42:38.040 --> 04:42:40.139
Bumblebee declared triumphantly.

04:42:40.200 --> 04:42:42.720
She rolled herself out of the sling and

04:42:42.720 --> 04:42:45.180
did a little shimmy dance in the mud.

04:42:45.240 --> 04:42:47.880
Her wings whisked around her, iridescent

04:42:47.880 --> 04:42:49.680
and sparkling like a dragonflies.

04:42:49.740 --> 04:42:51.240
Be buff.

04:42:51.299 --> 04:42:52.740
I say what, eh?

04:42:52.740 --> 04:42:54.779
Me, miss, yim, yim, yim.

04:42:54.840 --> 04:42:57.900
You wouldn't have had to save the day if

04:42:57.900 --> 04:42:59.520
you hadn't gotten us stuck in the 1st

04:42:59.520 --> 04:43:01.500
place, Sundew pointed out.

04:43:01.560 --> 04:43:04.500
She stretched her cramped wings and tail

04:43:04.500 --> 04:43:07.380
and neck and arms, and tried to shake the

04:43:07.380 --> 04:43:08.700
feeling back into her toes.

04:43:08.759 --> 04:43:10.979
Her muscles were so confused.

04:43:11.040 --> 04:43:13.860
She decided to lie down in the mud for a

04:43:13.860 --> 04:43:15.000
moment and let them recover.

04:43:15.060 --> 04:43:17.939
Good work, bumblebee.

04:43:18.000 --> 04:43:19.259
Cricket cooed.

04:43:19.319 --> 04:43:20.880
You helped so much.

04:43:20.939 --> 04:43:23.459
You're such a smart dragon?

04:43:23.580 --> 04:43:24.479
What a good listener.

04:43:24.540 --> 04:43:27.119
For tree's sake, cricket.

04:43:27.180 --> 04:43:28.200
Sundew said.

04:43:28.259 --> 04:43:30.720
Belladonna had never given her that many

04:43:30.720 --> 04:43:33.479
compliments in her life, let alone all at

04:43:33.479 --> 04:43:33.659
once.

04:43:33.720 --> 04:43:36.599
If my mother talked to me like that, I'd

04:43:36.599 --> 04:43:40.979
be, well adjusted, Willow guessed, with a

04:43:40.979 --> 04:43:43.020
crinkly eyed smile that made it very hard

04:43:43.020 --> 04:43:43.979
to scowl at her.

04:43:44.040 --> 04:43:48.060
As soft as a sap wing, sundew finished

04:43:48.060 --> 04:43:49.740
sticking her tongue out at willow.

04:43:49.799 --> 04:43:54.119
Ah, you can be soft, Cricket said to

04:43:54.119 --> 04:43:56.400
bumblebee, still in her googly voice.

04:43:56.459 --> 04:43:59.279
The dragonette was curled in her arms now

04:43:59.279 --> 04:44:02.340
preening and purring like a baby jaguar.

04:44:02.400 --> 04:44:05.520
You don't have to be mean and scary.

04:44:05.580 --> 04:44:07.020
No, you don't.

04:44:07.080 --> 04:44:09.659
You won't be like the other hive wings.

04:44:09.720 --> 04:44:12.119
You're too cute, and you have your own

04:44:12.119 --> 04:44:12.779
brain.

04:44:12.840 --> 04:44:13.799
Don't you?

04:44:13.860 --> 04:44:15.659
Snubble, flump.

04:44:15.779 --> 04:44:17.279
Bubblebee agreed.

04:44:17.340 --> 04:44:20.220
Let out an enormous yawn, and drooped

04:44:20.220 --> 04:44:21.720
into cricket's shoulder with her eyes

04:44:21.720 --> 04:44:22.200
closing.

04:44:22.259 --> 04:44:25.439
Blech, nettle grumbled.

04:44:25.500 --> 04:44:26.639
I'm going to be sick.

04:44:26.700 --> 04:44:30.180
So sorry, I didn't manage to die for you

04:44:30.180 --> 04:44:31.380
Sundu said.

04:44:31.439 --> 04:44:34.020
She realized that Willow was lying down

04:44:34.020 --> 04:44:36.240
beside her, twining her tail around

04:44:36.240 --> 04:44:38.639
sundews and resting her wing across

04:44:38.639 --> 04:44:39.540
sundew's back.

04:44:39.599 --> 04:44:41.880
You scared me half to death.

04:44:42.000 --> 04:44:44.880
Willow said softly in Sundu's ear.

04:44:44.939 --> 04:44:46.680
Are you all right?

04:44:46.740 --> 04:44:49.619
Can you please promise me you'll never

04:44:49.619 --> 04:44:49.919
die?

04:44:49.979 --> 04:44:54.419
Yes, Sandu said, nudging her with her

04:44:54.419 --> 04:44:54.900
snout.

04:44:54.959 --> 04:44:56.279
I promise.

04:44:56.340 --> 04:44:59.400
She was relieved to see that Willow

04:44:59.400 --> 04:45:01.259
wasn't still upset about their arguments

04:45:01.259 --> 04:45:02.520
on the other side of the lake.

04:45:02.639 --> 04:45:05.520
It was scarier than a setsu fly to think

04:45:05.520 --> 04:45:07.680
that Willow might see sundew differently

04:45:07.680 --> 04:45:10.500
once they were around other dragons, that

04:45:10.500 --> 04:45:12.119
she might think sundew was just another

04:45:12.119 --> 04:45:12.840
nettle.

04:45:12.900 --> 04:45:15.599
But that wasn't what she saw in Willow's

04:45:15.599 --> 04:45:15.779
eyes.

04:45:15.840 --> 04:45:19.680
She saw herself, loved, just the way she

04:45:19.680 --> 04:45:19.979
was.

04:45:20.040 --> 04:45:23.819
Metal frowned down at sundew and willow

04:45:23.819 --> 04:45:26.400
then turned and kicked Mandrake's ankle.

04:45:26.459 --> 04:45:28.439
Oh, he protested.

04:45:28.500 --> 04:45:32.279
I mean, ah, I'm glad you're alive, Sundu.

04:45:32.340 --> 04:45:33.779
Thanks.

04:45:33.840 --> 04:45:35.099
Sundew mumbled.

04:45:35.159 --> 04:45:37.200
Just going to rest for a moment.

04:45:37.259 --> 04:45:39.720
She closed her eyes and took a deep

04:45:39.720 --> 04:45:42.419
breath, filling her lungs with Willow's

04:45:42.419 --> 04:45:44.819
scent, and her mind with the murmurs of

04:45:44.819 --> 04:45:46.560
plants who weren't trying to murder her

04:45:46.560 --> 04:45:48.900
at least not right that second.

04:45:48.900 --> 04:45:52.380
There were orchids nearby, each vying to

04:45:52.380 --> 04:45:53.340
be the most beautiful.

04:45:53.400 --> 04:45:56.040
She found the roots of sun lilies not far

04:45:56.040 --> 04:45:58.979
below the soil, and quietly sang one up

04:45:58.979 --> 04:46:01.319
to the surface, so it would peek through

04:46:01.319 --> 04:46:03.180
right between Willow's front claws.

04:46:03.240 --> 04:46:06.240
Sundew didn't have to open her eyes to

04:46:06.240 --> 04:46:07.500
feel Willow smiling.

04:46:07.560 --> 04:46:11.880
I nearly got eaten too, Nettle complained

04:46:11.880 --> 04:46:14.159
and I didn't require a nap afterward.

04:46:14.220 --> 04:46:18.119
With a sigh, Sundoo pushed herself to her

04:46:18.119 --> 04:46:21.479
feet, Nettle was the worst, but it was

04:46:21.479 --> 04:46:22.979
true that they didn't have time to rest

04:46:22.979 --> 04:46:23.939
any longer.

04:46:24.060 --> 04:46:26.459
The sun had passed the midway point of

04:46:26.459 --> 04:46:29.520
the sky, and if cricket and Queen Sequoia

04:46:29.520 --> 04:46:31.799
were right, the hive wing army was almost

04:46:31.799 --> 04:46:32.819
certainly on its way.

04:46:32.880 --> 04:46:36.419
Willow leaned over her shoulder as

04:46:36.419 --> 04:46:38.099
Thundew unrolled the map again.

04:46:38.159 --> 04:46:41.159
Nettles shoved mandrake, so he stumbled

04:46:41.159 --> 04:46:42.360
into Sundew's other side.

04:46:42.419 --> 04:46:45.599
This is where the map gets extra

04:46:45.599 --> 04:46:46.500
unhelpful.

04:46:46.560 --> 04:46:49.560
Sundu said, reaching out her wing to help

04:46:49.560 --> 04:46:50.939
him catch his balance.

04:46:51.000 --> 04:46:53.040
I mean, what are all these small

04:46:53.040 --> 04:46:55.080
squiggling lines from here to the eye.

04:46:55.139 --> 04:46:57.419
They look like snakes.

04:46:57.479 --> 04:46:58.979
Mandrake offered.

04:46:59.040 --> 04:47:01.560
Um, someone tell me I'm wrong.

04:47:01.619 --> 04:47:06.060
They do look like snakes, Willow said.

04:47:06.119 --> 04:47:09.000
That's fine, Nettles scoffed.

04:47:09.060 --> 04:47:11.340
I've killed 100s of snakes.

04:47:11.400 --> 04:47:12.180
No problem.

04:47:12.240 --> 04:47:16.500
But, all at once, Mandrake asked.

04:47:16.619 --> 04:47:19.799
I mean, this whole section of the map is

04:47:19.799 --> 04:47:21.720
just snakes.

04:47:21.779 --> 04:47:23.459
If those are snakes.

04:47:23.520 --> 04:47:24.959
Maybe they're not.

04:47:25.020 --> 04:47:26.580
Maybe they're very tiny rivers.

04:47:26.639 --> 04:47:29.459
It looks like there are words here

04:47:29.459 --> 04:47:32.099
Cricket said, crouching closer to the

04:47:32.099 --> 04:47:33.419
leap and squinting at it.

04:47:33.479 --> 04:47:35.099
You're right.

04:47:35.159 --> 04:47:37.919
Willow held the leaf up to the faint

04:47:37.919 --> 04:47:40.500
sunlight, and they all tried to read the

04:47:40.500 --> 04:47:42.360
miniature letters carved between the

04:47:42.360 --> 04:47:43.259
squiggles' shapes.

04:47:43.319 --> 04:47:46.139
Does it say tiny rivers?

04:47:46.259 --> 04:47:48.540
Mandrake asked hopefully.

04:47:48.599 --> 04:47:50.159
Den?

04:47:50.159 --> 04:47:51.240
Cricket guessed.

04:47:51.299 --> 04:47:57.479
Den of Vipers, Sundew said.

04:47:57.540 --> 04:48:00.900
A shiver ran down her spine that felt

04:48:00.900 --> 04:48:03.060
like the sinister glee of a plant about

04:48:03.060 --> 04:48:03.900
to feast.

04:48:04.020 --> 04:48:06.720
The last section of the jungle standing

04:48:06.720 --> 04:48:09.779
between us and the eye, is called the den

04:48:09.779 --> 04:48:10.560
of vipers.

04:48:10.619 --> 04:48:15.180
Chapter 14.

04:48:15.419 --> 04:48:18.900
Sundu couldn't tell whether the jungle

04:48:18.900 --> 04:48:20.819
had gotten darker because the sun was

04:48:20.819 --> 04:48:23.220
starting to go down, or because the tree

04:48:23.220 --> 04:48:25.500
canopy was denser here, and there was

04:48:25.500 --> 04:48:27.959
less room to maneuver, or because it felt

04:48:27.959 --> 04:48:30.060
like beady eyes were watching them from

04:48:30.060 --> 04:48:30.840
every tree.

04:48:30.900 --> 04:48:34.020
They had been walking, clambering

04:48:34.020 --> 04:48:36.900
squelching, slogging, for a long time

04:48:36.900 --> 04:48:39.419
since crossing the lake, and still hadn't

04:48:39.419 --> 04:48:40.139
run into any snakes.

04:48:40.200 --> 04:48:44.340
You are all ridiculous, Nettle declared

04:48:44.340 --> 04:48:46.680
shoving her way past sundew as they

04:48:46.680 --> 04:48:47.880
climbed over a fallen tree.

04:48:47.939 --> 04:48:50.159
Snakes are not scary.

04:48:50.220 --> 04:48:51.900
Metal.

04:48:51.959 --> 04:48:53.880
You are very welcome to kill all the

04:48:53.880 --> 04:48:54.779
viper's forests.

04:48:54.900 --> 04:48:57.419
Mandrake said in exasperation.

04:48:57.540 --> 04:48:59.939
Do you think they are dragon bite

04:48:59.939 --> 04:49:00.479
vipers?

04:49:00.540 --> 04:49:02.099
Cricket asked anxiously.

04:49:02.159 --> 04:49:05.220
I read that those can kill one of us with

04:49:05.220 --> 04:49:06.060
a single bite.

04:49:06.119 --> 04:49:07.919
Have any of you ever seen one?

04:49:07.979 --> 04:49:09.419
I've never seen one.

04:49:09.479 --> 04:49:11.639
We don't exactly get a lot of snakes in

04:49:11.639 --> 04:49:12.240
the hives.

04:49:12.299 --> 04:49:14.159
Not even in the greenhouses.

04:49:14.220 --> 04:49:17.099
I saw some little snakes in a pet shop in

04:49:17.099 --> 04:49:17.400
the market.

04:49:17.459 --> 04:49:19.500
Do leaf wings have pets?

04:49:19.560 --> 04:49:23.159
Yes, said Willow, at the same time as

04:49:23.159 --> 04:49:24.779
Sundew said, no.

04:49:24.840 --> 04:49:26.400
They glanced at each other.

04:49:26.459 --> 04:49:30.180
Sap wings do, Sandu added with a shrug.

04:49:30.299 --> 04:49:33.540
Poison wings don't, Willow agreed.

04:49:33.599 --> 04:49:37.500
We are not poison wings, Sundoo objected

04:49:37.500 --> 04:49:40.080
for the 1000000th time, that really makes

04:49:40.080 --> 04:49:41.279
us sound like a bad guys.

04:49:41.400 --> 04:49:45.060
I'll stop if you stop, Willow offered.

04:49:45.119 --> 04:49:48.299
I mean, sap wings sounds like a tribe

04:49:48.299 --> 04:49:50.040
that drips around sticking to

04:49:50.040 --> 04:49:50.340
everything.

04:49:50.400 --> 04:49:53.939
Cricket giggled, and Sundew smothered her

04:49:53.939 --> 04:49:54.540
own laugh.

04:49:54.599 --> 04:49:57.360
All right, truce, she said.

04:49:57.419 --> 04:50:00.540
Leaf Wings, said Willow.

04:50:00.599 --> 04:50:02.700
We're both leaf wings.

04:50:02.700 --> 04:50:05.580
But only the drippy, sticky half of us

04:50:05.580 --> 04:50:07.680
have pets, Sundew pointed out.

04:50:07.740 --> 04:50:10.319
She ducked away from Willow swatting at

04:50:10.319 --> 04:50:12.360
her, and thought she saw something dart

04:50:12.360 --> 04:50:15.240
by under the leaves, something long and

04:50:15.240 --> 04:50:16.680
gold and black and green.

04:50:16.740 --> 04:50:20.759
She froze, staring at the ground as the

04:50:20.759 --> 04:50:21.599
others kept walking.

04:50:21.659 --> 04:50:24.060
But now the leaves were still.

04:50:24.119 --> 04:50:26.700
She didn't see any sign of whatever had

04:50:26.700 --> 04:50:26.939
moved.

04:50:27.060 --> 04:50:30.540
Maybe she had imagined it. as nervous as

04:50:30.540 --> 04:50:30.779
she was.

04:50:30.840 --> 04:50:34.020
She hurried to catch up to her friends.

04:50:34.080 --> 04:50:36.720
I have a cockatoo.

04:50:36.779 --> 04:50:38.520
Willow was saying to cricket.

04:50:38.580 --> 04:50:41.759
Her name is Takatu, and she's the

04:50:41.759 --> 04:50:43.020
smartest bird in the world.

04:50:43.080 --> 04:50:45.299
Sundu stop laughing at me.

04:50:45.360 --> 04:50:47.700
She shoved Sundu's shoulder

04:50:47.700 --> 04:50:48.299
affectionately.

04:50:48.360 --> 04:50:51.299
I was only a little older than Bumblebee

04:50:51.299 --> 04:50:51.900
when I named her.

04:50:51.959 --> 04:50:54.119
I'd like to see you come up with a better

04:50:54.119 --> 04:50:54.840
name at that age.

04:50:54.959 --> 04:51:00.119
Word a bird, Bumblebee said sleepily from

04:51:00.119 --> 04:51:02.099
her sling, and Cricket laughed again.

04:51:02.159 --> 04:51:04.500
Could you keep the racket down back

04:51:04.500 --> 04:51:04.799
there?

04:51:04.860 --> 04:51:06.900
Nettles shouted from up ahead.

04:51:07.020 --> 04:51:10.860
They fell silent for a moment, navigating

04:51:10.860 --> 04:51:13.439
an uphill slope covered in ferns and moss

04:51:13.439 --> 04:51:16.200
covered rocks, and death cap mushrooms.

04:51:16.259 --> 04:51:19.740
Sundew glanced up at the looming trees.

04:51:19.799 --> 04:51:22.139
She'd never felt trees loom like this

04:51:22.139 --> 04:51:22.380
before.

04:51:22.500 --> 04:51:25.680
Even with her leaf speak, she couldn't

04:51:25.680 --> 04:51:26.520
connect well with them.

04:51:26.580 --> 04:51:29.520
These trees grumbled and muttered.

04:51:29.580 --> 04:51:31.740
They were unhappy about something that

04:51:31.740 --> 04:51:33.900
had gone on long enough to register even

04:51:33.900 --> 04:51:34.319
with them.

04:51:34.380 --> 04:51:36.479
But they couldn't articulate it.

04:51:36.540 --> 04:51:37.979
Of course they couldn't.

04:51:38.099 --> 04:51:39.840
Trees almost never could.

04:51:39.900 --> 04:51:42.779
They could only radiate discontent and

04:51:42.779 --> 04:51:43.020
gloom.

04:51:43.080 --> 04:51:45.119
Is it me?

04:51:45.180 --> 04:51:46.619
Cricket whispered.

04:51:46.680 --> 04:51:49.200
Or is it a lot quieter all of a sudden?

04:51:49.259 --> 04:51:52.740
Willow and Sundu both stopped beside her

04:51:52.740 --> 04:51:53.279
and listened.

04:51:53.400 --> 04:51:55.439
Cricket was right.

04:51:55.560 --> 04:51:58.259
The constant chirping of cicadas and

04:51:58.259 --> 04:51:59.819
grasshoppers had fallen silent.

04:51:59.880 --> 04:52:03.060
There was no sound of monkeys swinging

04:52:03.060 --> 04:52:05.040
above them or calling across the jungle.

04:52:05.099 --> 04:52:07.500
Sundew couldn't even hear any birds.

04:52:07.619 --> 04:52:10.619
The wind rustled the branches overhead.

04:52:10.680 --> 04:52:11.819
That was all.

04:52:11.880 --> 04:52:15.299
Sundew was searching the treetops for any

04:52:15.299 --> 04:52:18.299
birds, when she saw the 1st dragon bite

04:52:18.299 --> 04:52:19.080
viper's head.

04:52:19.139 --> 04:52:22.619
She looked past it twice at 1st, because

04:52:22.619 --> 04:52:25.619
it was perfectly still, but the 3rd time

04:52:25.619 --> 04:52:28.500
something about the smooth serpentine

04:52:28.500 --> 04:52:29.520
shape caught her eye.

04:52:29.580 --> 04:52:32.880
The head was poking up out of a cluster

04:52:32.880 --> 04:52:35.520
of green weeds, only a few steps from

04:52:35.520 --> 04:52:36.540
willow.

04:52:36.599 --> 04:52:39.840
It was, most definitely the head of a

04:52:39.840 --> 04:52:42.540
viper. attached to the rest of the body

04:52:42.540 --> 04:52:45.240
of a viper, as far as sundew could see.

04:52:45.299 --> 04:52:46.680
But it was not moving.

04:52:46.740 --> 04:52:50.459
It seemed frozen there, like a statue of

04:52:50.459 --> 04:52:50.880
a snake.

04:52:51.000 --> 04:52:54.779
She noticed that Mandrake and Nettle had

04:52:54.779 --> 04:52:57.240
fallen silent too, and stopped where they

04:52:57.240 --> 04:52:59.099
were, at the top of the slope.

04:52:59.099 --> 04:53:01.560
They both had their eyes fixed on

04:53:01.560 --> 04:53:04.020
something near their feet, and Mandrake

04:53:04.020 --> 04:53:04.979
looked close to fainting.

04:53:05.040 --> 04:53:09.659
That is really weird, Willow said

04:53:09.659 --> 04:53:11.580
answering cricket's question.

04:53:11.639 --> 04:53:13.560
She clearly hadn't seen the snake.

04:53:13.680 --> 04:53:16.979
With a shrug, she stepped forward, and

04:53:16.979 --> 04:53:18.900
Sundu reached to pull her away from the

04:53:18.900 --> 04:53:20.819
viper, but it still didn't move.

04:53:20.880 --> 04:53:25.919
Willow, she whispered, poking her tail, to

04:53:25.919 --> 04:53:26.520
your left.

04:53:26.639 --> 04:53:28.979
Ominous paralyzed viper or something?

04:53:29.040 --> 04:53:32.340
Willow saw it and started back in alarm

04:53:32.340 --> 04:53:34.439
but it still didn't move.

04:53:34.500 --> 04:53:36.599
What's wrong with it?

04:53:36.659 --> 04:53:38.159
Cricket whispered.

04:53:38.220 --> 04:53:39.720
Can't it see us?

04:53:39.840 --> 04:53:41.520
Is it dead?

04:53:41.580 --> 04:53:44.700
No, Sundu whispered.

04:53:44.759 --> 04:53:47.759
As the snake's tongue slithered out

04:53:47.759 --> 04:53:50.459
tasted the air, and slithered back in.

04:53:50.520 --> 04:53:54.119
Its lidless, bright yellow eyes seemed to

04:53:54.119 --> 04:53:55.080
be staring right at them.

04:53:55.139 --> 04:53:58.500
But when they edged forward together, its

04:53:58.500 --> 04:53:59.340
eyes didn't follow.

04:53:59.400 --> 04:54:02.759
It stared directly into space, head

04:54:02.759 --> 04:54:05.759
raised, completely still, except for its

04:54:05.759 --> 04:54:06.119
tongue.

04:54:06.180 --> 04:54:08.459
Should we try to kill it?

04:54:08.459 --> 04:54:11.580
Sandu asked quietly as they stepped

04:54:11.580 --> 04:54:13.439
forward, keeping their gaze on it.

04:54:13.500 --> 04:54:15.779
That might wake it up.

04:54:15.840 --> 04:54:17.220
Willow whispered.

04:54:17.279 --> 04:54:20.639
I say as long as it's not moving, don't

04:54:20.639 --> 04:54:20.939
touch it.

04:54:21.000 --> 04:54:22.979
Let's just get away from it.

04:54:23.040 --> 04:54:26.700
They moved softly but quickly up the hill

04:54:26.700 --> 04:54:29.400
staying on the rocks, and away from the

04:54:29.400 --> 04:54:30.720
long weeds as much as they could.

04:54:30.779 --> 04:54:34.439
Another snake was poised near the top

04:54:34.439 --> 04:54:36.720
staring at nettle and mandrake.

04:54:36.840 --> 04:54:39.840
This one was coiled around a thorny shrub

04:54:39.840 --> 04:54:42.240
its green and black head jutting out into

04:54:42.240 --> 04:54:44.639
the air, like an extra creepy branch.

04:54:44.700 --> 04:54:46.560
Has it moved?

04:54:46.619 --> 04:54:48.900
Sundu whispered from a boulder behind

04:54:48.900 --> 04:54:49.139
them?

04:54:49.200 --> 04:54:51.119
Not yet.

04:54:51.180 --> 04:54:53.580
Mandrake answered through his teeth.

04:54:53.639 --> 04:54:55.680
But neither have we.

04:54:55.799 --> 04:54:59.759
See if you can slide away, Sundew

04:54:59.759 --> 04:55:00.299
suggested.

04:55:00.360 --> 04:55:02.759
We saw one below that stared at us but

04:55:02.759 --> 04:55:03.299
didn't attack.

04:55:03.419 --> 04:55:06.299
Maybe this one is frozen in place too.

04:55:06.360 --> 04:55:09.000
I should wring its neck.

04:55:09.060 --> 04:55:12.060
Nettle growled, but she didn't make a

04:55:12.060 --> 04:55:14.340
move toward it, and after another moment

04:55:14.340 --> 04:55:17.520
Mandrake cautiously sidled a step away

04:55:17.520 --> 04:55:18.659
and then another.

04:55:18.720 --> 04:55:22.139
The snake's tongue flickered in and out

04:55:22.139 --> 04:55:25.380
but it stayed poised in place, enormous

04:55:25.380 --> 04:55:26.580
yellow eyes glaring.

04:55:26.700 --> 04:55:30.180
Sundu guessed it was as long as a dragon

04:55:30.180 --> 04:55:32.040
if you straightened out all its coils.

04:55:32.099 --> 04:55:35.279
Let's go, Willow whispered.

04:55:35.340 --> 04:55:37.080
Watch where you step.

04:55:37.139 --> 04:55:41.040
She led the way as they paced single file

04:55:41.040 --> 04:55:43.439
with careful steps along the ridge of the

04:55:43.439 --> 04:55:44.759
hill and down the other side.

04:55:44.819 --> 04:55:48.599
Sundew kept her wings tucked in close and

04:55:48.599 --> 04:55:49.860
her tail lifted off the ground.

04:55:49.919 --> 04:55:53.340
Each time her talons came down on a slick

04:55:53.340 --> 04:55:55.979
of wet leaves, she expected to see a blur

04:55:55.979 --> 04:55:58.740
of motion and feel fangs sinking into her

04:55:58.740 --> 04:55:59.040
ankle.

04:55:59.099 --> 04:56:03.360
There, Cricket breathed, inclining her

04:56:03.360 --> 04:56:03.959
head to the left.

04:56:04.020 --> 04:56:06.540
Two more snakes were looped around the

04:56:06.540 --> 04:56:08.400
branches of a tree, with their heads

04:56:08.400 --> 04:56:11.400
reaching toward the path, staring, and

04:56:11.400 --> 04:56:13.799
still, over here too.

04:56:13.919 --> 04:56:16.619
Mandrake flicked his tail slightly.

04:56:16.680 --> 04:56:19.500
They were passing a patch of tangled ivy

04:56:19.500 --> 04:56:22.380
vines and long grass that appeared to

04:56:22.380 --> 04:56:24.180
have strange plants growing up from the

04:56:24.180 --> 04:56:27.060
center of it, but they weren't plants.

04:56:27.119 --> 04:56:30.599
They were more snakes. 6 or more.

04:56:30.659 --> 04:56:33.599
Smooth heads curled up like cobra lilies

04:56:33.599 --> 04:56:35.880
with their menacing dandelion eyes

04:56:35.880 --> 04:56:36.599
glittering.

04:56:36.659 --> 04:56:39.540
Why aren't they moving?

04:56:39.599 --> 04:56:41.040
Cricket asked.

04:56:41.099 --> 04:56:43.860
She hesitated at a large tree root

04:56:43.860 --> 04:56:46.380
inspected the shadows around it, then

04:56:46.380 --> 04:56:47.520
gingerly stepped over it.

04:56:47.580 --> 04:56:49.979
Stupid question.

04:56:50.040 --> 04:56:52.740
We obviously don't know, Nettle

04:56:52.740 --> 04:56:53.099
muttered.

04:56:53.220 --> 04:56:55.619
Never seen snakes act like this.

04:56:55.680 --> 04:56:58.979
Maybe they're watching for better prey

04:56:58.979 --> 04:57:01.139
than us, Willow whispered.

04:57:01.200 --> 04:57:03.720
Sundu could hardly stand it.

04:57:03.779 --> 04:57:06.840
Her sore muscles protested at the slow

04:57:06.840 --> 04:57:07.619
tense pace.

04:57:07.680 --> 04:57:09.479
She wanted to scream.

04:57:09.540 --> 04:57:12.180
She wanted to seize a tree and shove it

04:57:12.180 --> 04:57:13.439
over on top of the snakes.

04:57:13.560 --> 04:57:16.380
She wanted to throw exploding seed pods

04:57:16.380 --> 04:57:16.860
at them.

04:57:16.919 --> 04:57:19.139
She would rather fight than deal with

04:57:19.139 --> 04:57:19.380
this.

04:57:19.439 --> 04:57:22.979
This awful creeping, this prickling

04:57:22.979 --> 04:57:24.720
feeling of waiting for something to

04:57:24.720 --> 04:57:25.020
attack.

04:57:25.080 --> 04:57:28.439
They reached the bottom of the slope and

04:57:28.439 --> 04:57:31.200
found a stream, its muddy water trickling

04:57:31.200 --> 04:57:32.459
slowly over stones.

04:57:32.520 --> 04:57:34.919
Willow began to pick her way across

04:57:34.919 --> 04:57:37.439
silently pointing to branches that were

04:57:37.439 --> 04:57:40.259
actually snakes, rocks that were actually

04:57:40.259 --> 04:57:42.900
snakes, and glimmers of fish that were

04:57:42.900 --> 04:57:44.520
actually underwater snakes.

04:57:44.639 --> 04:57:48.000
There were a lot of snakes in the

04:57:48.000 --> 04:57:48.180
stream.

04:57:48.240 --> 04:57:50.759
Maybe we should fly.

04:57:50.880 --> 04:57:53.700
Mandrake suggested, halfway across.

04:57:53.759 --> 04:57:56.819
We could go over the whole den of vipers

04:57:56.819 --> 04:57:57.360
couldn't we?

04:57:57.419 --> 04:58:01.259
Nettles snorted and jabbed one claw the

04:58:01.259 --> 04:58:02.099
trees overhead.

04:58:02.159 --> 04:58:03.479
Sundew looked up.

04:58:03.540 --> 04:58:06.599
The branches above them were dripping

04:58:06.599 --> 04:58:07.200
with snakes.

04:58:07.319 --> 04:58:10.619
Scales gleamed between the leaves.

04:58:10.680 --> 04:58:12.900
Hundreds of yellow eyes watched them

04:58:12.900 --> 04:58:14.220
unblinking.

04:58:14.220 --> 04:58:16.560
There were so many coils wound around

04:58:16.560 --> 04:58:18.840
each branch, that it was impossible to

04:58:18.840 --> 04:58:20.939
tell where one snake ended and another

04:58:20.939 --> 04:58:21.360
began.

04:58:21.419 --> 04:58:25.380
Sundu glanced back at bumblebee, asleep

04:58:25.380 --> 04:58:26.099
in her sling.

04:58:26.159 --> 04:58:28.319
Maybe we shouldn't have brought her out

04:58:28.319 --> 04:58:28.979
here after all.

04:58:29.040 --> 04:58:33.659
The water was very cold around her talons

04:58:33.659 --> 04:58:34.919
colder than she thought it should be.

04:58:35.040 --> 04:58:38.220
I wish we knew how much farther we have

04:58:38.220 --> 04:58:38.520
to go.

04:58:38.580 --> 04:58:41.819
They waited out of the stream on the

04:58:41.819 --> 04:58:44.459
other side and kept going between trees

04:58:44.459 --> 04:58:47.340
that pressed closer and closer, below

04:58:47.340 --> 04:58:50.099
more and more frozen, watchful snakes.

04:58:50.159 --> 04:58:53.459
Sundew reached out tentatively with her

04:58:53.459 --> 04:58:55.860
leaf speak, and felt the presence of

04:58:55.860 --> 04:58:57.119
plants so dangerous.

04:58:57.240 --> 04:58:59.279
Her tribe had cleared them out of the

04:58:59.279 --> 04:59:00.540
area around the village.

04:59:00.599 --> 04:59:04.020
Malicious blistering hogweeds chuckled

04:59:04.020 --> 04:59:06.419
nearby, spiking through the murmur of the

04:59:06.419 --> 04:59:06.959
other plants.

04:59:07.080 --> 04:59:10.259
A hungry, gurgling hum underneath

04:59:10.259 --> 04:59:13.020
everything, told her that Kudzu vines

04:59:13.020 --> 04:59:15.720
were wound throughout this area, devouring

04:59:15.720 --> 04:59:17.220
and choking the quieter trees.

04:59:17.279 --> 04:59:19.740
But there was something worse.

04:59:19.799 --> 04:59:23.580
Something much creepier, something that

04:59:23.580 --> 04:59:25.319
reached out to her mind with cold

04:59:25.319 --> 04:59:26.400
tendrils.

04:59:26.459 --> 04:59:28.919
She hissed softly.

04:59:28.979 --> 04:59:31.680
Willow paused to look back at her.

04:59:31.740 --> 04:59:33.659
The breath of evil.

04:59:33.779 --> 04:59:36.299
Sundu whispered, it's here.

04:59:36.360 --> 04:59:37.680
I can feel it.

04:59:37.740 --> 04:59:40.380
She could smell it now too.

04:59:40.439 --> 04:59:43.560
The same peppery rotting smell that she'd

04:59:43.560 --> 04:59:45.900
encountered in Queen Wasp's greenhouse.

04:59:45.959 --> 04:59:48.599
She had examined that vine while they hid

04:59:48.599 --> 04:59:48.840
there.

04:59:48.900 --> 04:59:51.180
But it hadn't spoken to her at all.

04:59:51.240 --> 04:59:53.639
Nothing like what was currently reaching

04:59:53.639 --> 04:59:55.860
back toward her, as though it was trying

04:59:55.860 --> 04:59:58.560
to plant little seeds in her brain, and

04:59:58.560 --> 05:00:00.000
slither through the cracks in her

05:00:00.000 --> 05:00:00.360
scales.

05:00:00.419 --> 05:00:04.560
Look, Mandrake said, pointing.

05:00:04.619 --> 05:00:07.799
There was a light up ahead, a break in

05:00:07.799 --> 05:00:09.360
the trees where a full sunlight was

05:00:09.360 --> 05:00:10.799
shining through to the forest floor.

05:00:10.860 --> 05:00:15.119
Maybe that's the eye, Cricket whispered.

05:00:15.240 --> 05:00:17.159
Where Hawthorne lives?

05:00:17.220 --> 05:00:19.380
How can he live here?

05:00:19.439 --> 05:00:22.979
Willow whispered back, surrounded by all

05:00:22.979 --> 05:00:25.560
these vipers, and the breath of evil.

05:00:25.619 --> 05:00:29.099
Maybe he doesn't, Nettle said.

05:00:29.159 --> 05:00:30.180
Maybe he's dead.

05:00:30.240 --> 05:00:33.659
That's the spirit nettle, Sundu said.

05:00:33.720 --> 05:00:34.979
Let's go check it out.

05:00:35.040 --> 05:00:38.520
They headed toward the light, and as the

05:00:38.520 --> 05:00:40.380
jungle became easier to see all around

05:00:40.380 --> 05:00:43.259
them, Sundew spotted the scarlet and

05:00:43.259 --> 05:00:44.580
green vines overhead.

05:00:44.639 --> 05:00:49.139
It was here, growing freely, hardly a

05:00:49.139 --> 05:00:51.599
day's walk from Queen Sequoia's village

05:00:51.599 --> 05:00:52.740
she shuddered.

05:00:52.799 --> 05:00:55.740
Why hadn't any scouts encountered it?

05:00:55.799 --> 05:00:57.299
Why didn't everyone know about it?

05:00:57.360 --> 05:01:00.180
Was it too well hidden behind the vipers

05:01:00.180 --> 05:01:03.119
and the Mantineel trees, so no one ever

05:01:03.119 --> 05:01:03.659
came this way?

05:01:03.720 --> 05:01:06.419
They were almost at the edge of the

05:01:06.419 --> 05:01:08.520
clearing. when the snakes suddenly

05:01:08.520 --> 05:01:08.819
moved.

05:01:08.880 --> 05:01:12.720
An enormous one dropped straight out of

05:01:12.720 --> 05:01:14.819
the tree in front of them, blocking their

05:01:14.819 --> 05:01:15.180
path.

05:01:15.240 --> 05:01:18.299
Five more glided out of the bushes behind

05:01:18.299 --> 05:01:20.939
them. others slithered down from the

05:01:20.939 --> 05:01:21.419
branches.

05:01:21.479 --> 05:01:24.360
They were surrounded, and the vipers

05:01:24.360 --> 05:01:25.200
began to hiss.

05:01:25.259 --> 05:01:27.240
Sundew?

05:01:27.299 --> 05:01:29.939
Willow said, taking a step closer to the

05:01:29.939 --> 05:01:30.419
group.

05:01:30.479 --> 05:01:31.740
Any ideas?

05:01:31.860 --> 05:01:34.380
Why bother asking her?

05:01:34.439 --> 05:01:35.700
Nettle demanded.

05:01:35.759 --> 05:01:37.319
I have a great idea.

05:01:37.439 --> 05:01:38.520
Let's kill them.

05:01:38.639 --> 05:01:41.099
She lunged toward the one in front of

05:01:41.099 --> 05:01:41.459
them.

05:01:41.520 --> 05:01:44.759
It bared its fangs and darted at her, fast

05:01:44.759 --> 05:01:48.000
as lightning, and mandrake screamed, and

05:01:48.000 --> 05:01:50.400
Sundew felt willow grab one of her talons

05:01:50.400 --> 05:01:52.619
as they threw their wings out to form a

05:01:52.619 --> 05:01:54.360
shield around cricket and bumblebee.

05:01:54.419 --> 05:01:57.779
A gust of wind billowed from the clearing

05:01:57.779 --> 05:02:01.319
as something gigantic swooped down, and

05:02:01.319 --> 05:02:03.599
then wings blocked the sunlight, and

05:02:03.599 --> 05:02:05.939
giant claws stabbed into the snake

05:02:05.939 --> 05:02:08.819
stopping it barely a heartbeat away from

05:02:08.819 --> 05:02:10.979
sinking its fangs into Nettle's throat.

05:02:11.040 --> 05:02:15.299
The snake writhed in its death throes, and

05:02:15.299 --> 05:02:18.000
as one, all the vipers around them rose

05:02:18.000 --> 05:02:20.880
up like cobras about to strike, glaring

05:02:20.880 --> 05:02:21.840
with their yellow eyes.

05:02:21.900 --> 05:02:25.560
Begone, shouted the new dragon.

05:02:25.619 --> 05:02:28.020
Leave these travelers in peace.

05:02:28.080 --> 05:02:31.259
The hissing intensified, slipping along

05:02:31.259 --> 05:02:33.659
sundew's nerves and all through her bones

05:02:33.659 --> 05:02:36.299
but after a horrible heart pounding

05:02:36.299 --> 05:02:38.700
moment of stillness, all the snakes

05:02:38.700 --> 05:02:40.979
dropped to the ground and slithered away

05:02:40.979 --> 05:02:41.939
into the underbrush.

05:02:42.000 --> 05:02:45.959
Well, you very nearly just died.

05:02:46.020 --> 05:02:49.319
The giant leaf wing said, smiling down at

05:02:49.319 --> 05:02:49.560
them.

05:02:49.619 --> 05:02:51.959
He shook the snake's corpse to make sure

05:02:51.959 --> 05:02:54.840
it was dead, then tossed it away, like a

05:02:54.840 --> 05:02:56.819
weed he'd just yanked out of the dirt.

05:02:56.880 --> 05:02:59.880
What kind of idiots come to a place like

05:02:59.880 --> 05:03:00.959
the den of vipers?

05:03:01.020 --> 05:03:04.380
Desperate ones, Sundew admitted.

05:03:04.439 --> 05:03:06.360
We were looking for a dragon named

05:03:06.360 --> 05:03:07.020
Hawthorne.

05:03:07.080 --> 05:03:09.299
Thank you for saving my sister.

05:03:09.419 --> 05:03:11.279
Mandrake interjected.

05:03:11.340 --> 05:03:14.520
I didn't need saving, Nettle barked.

05:03:14.580 --> 05:03:15.779
I was about to kill it myself.

05:03:15.840 --> 05:03:19.560
If you had, then the others would have

05:03:19.560 --> 05:03:20.639
immediately killed all of you.

05:03:20.759 --> 05:03:22.680
The stranger pointed out.

05:03:22.740 --> 05:03:25.860
I mean, only reasonable, right?

05:03:25.919 --> 05:03:28.200
You did come into our territory.

05:03:28.259 --> 05:03:30.060
No one ever does that.

05:03:30.119 --> 05:03:32.459
So, they tend to be a bit

05:03:32.459 --> 05:03:33.720
overprotective.

05:03:33.779 --> 05:03:35.400
They?

05:03:35.880 --> 05:03:37.080
I'm sorry, who?

05:03:37.139 --> 05:03:38.040
The Vipers?

05:03:38.159 --> 05:03:41.040
They're protecting you?

05:03:41.099 --> 05:03:42.240
Cricket asked.

05:03:42.299 --> 05:03:44.700
They are protecting you.

05:03:44.759 --> 05:03:45.599
What?

05:03:45.720 --> 05:03:48.720
Oh, yes, he answered.

05:03:48.779 --> 05:03:51.599
I'm Hawthorne, and those were my vibers.

05:03:51.659 --> 05:03:52.919
Who wants tea?

05:03:52.979 --> 05:03:57.240
Chapter 15.

05:03:57.659 --> 05:04:01.319
Hawthorne turned and sauntered cheerfully

05:04:01.319 --> 05:04:02.400
off into the sunlight.

05:04:02.459 --> 05:04:05.099
Mandrake followed him, blinking in

05:04:05.099 --> 05:04:05.580
confusion.

05:04:05.639 --> 05:04:08.459
Willow stopped sundew with her wing as

05:04:08.459 --> 05:04:09.060
she stepped forward.

05:04:09.119 --> 05:04:12.720
I feel like we should be really careful

05:04:12.720 --> 05:04:14.340
she said softly.

05:04:14.400 --> 05:04:17.279
Me too, Sandu agreed.

05:04:17.340 --> 05:04:21.060
Same here, Nettle said unexpectedly.

05:04:21.180 --> 05:04:24.599
But this is the dragon we're looking for

05:04:24.599 --> 05:04:24.840
right?

05:04:24.900 --> 05:04:26.939
Cricket asked.

05:04:27.000 --> 05:04:27.900
She adjusted her glasses.

05:04:27.959 --> 05:04:29.880
The one with all the answers.

05:04:30.000 --> 05:04:32.520
Who knows everything about this vine and

05:04:32.520 --> 05:04:33.360
the mind control?

05:04:33.419 --> 05:04:36.060
Her tail was twitching with nervous

05:04:36.060 --> 05:04:36.479
excitement.

05:04:36.540 --> 05:04:39.479
Yes, Willow said.

05:04:39.540 --> 05:04:41.459
And he seems nice enough.

05:04:41.520 --> 05:04:43.979
It's just everything else.

05:04:44.040 --> 05:04:48.060
We'll go with him, Sundoo said to Cricket

05:04:48.060 --> 05:04:49.200
but carefully.

05:04:49.259 --> 05:04:52.380
Cricket nodded and they edged out into

05:04:52.380 --> 05:04:54.360
the clearing, squinting in the much

05:04:54.360 --> 05:04:55.139
brighter light here.

05:04:55.200 --> 05:04:58.319
All the low hanging vines had been cut

05:04:58.319 --> 05:05:00.360
back, along with sections of the canopy

05:05:00.360 --> 05:05:03.000
overhead, leaving space for grass to grow

05:05:03.000 --> 05:05:04.139
in the patches of sun.

05:05:04.200 --> 05:05:07.080
A small vegetable garden covered a

05:05:07.080 --> 05:05:08.759
quarter of the clearing, with the

05:05:08.759 --> 05:05:10.500
undergrowth cleared away all around it.

05:05:10.560 --> 05:05:13.020
And in the center of the clearing was a

05:05:13.020 --> 05:05:16.500
house, shaped like a cell in a hive, not

05:05:16.500 --> 05:05:19.259
a nest or a hammock, or a platform in a

05:05:19.259 --> 05:05:19.560
tree.

05:05:19.619 --> 05:05:23.159
Someone, presumably Hawthorne, had taken

05:05:23.159 --> 05:05:25.560
the time to turn tree trunks into smooth

05:05:25.560 --> 05:05:26.220
flat boards.

05:05:26.340 --> 05:05:29.340
Someone had fitted them together, and

05:05:29.340 --> 05:05:31.380
someone had woven flax curtains for the

05:05:31.380 --> 05:05:33.900
door and windows, then dyed them pale

05:05:33.900 --> 05:05:34.139
red.

05:05:34.200 --> 05:05:37.860
Sundu pivoted to study the entire space

05:05:37.860 --> 05:05:40.799
but she saw no sign of the breath of evil

05:05:40.799 --> 05:05:42.360
within the perimeter of the clearing.

05:05:42.479 --> 05:05:45.419
She could still hear it though, and feel

05:05:45.419 --> 05:05:47.639
it, curling around the edges of her

05:05:47.639 --> 05:05:47.759
mind.

05:05:47.880 --> 05:05:49.860
Come on in.

05:05:49.919 --> 05:05:51.959
Hawthorne called from the doorway.

05:05:52.080 --> 05:05:55.319
They stepped up onto a covered porch that

05:05:55.319 --> 05:05:56.340
ran along the front of the house.

05:05:56.400 --> 05:05:59.220
One end of it seemed to be a small

05:05:59.220 --> 05:06:01.860
woodworking studio, where a little half

05:06:01.860 --> 05:06:03.900
carved dragon sat on a stump.

05:06:03.959 --> 05:06:06.959
Honeysuckle vines adorned the roof of the

05:06:06.959 --> 05:06:09.599
porch, adding a sweet smell to the air

05:06:09.599 --> 05:06:12.180
and a tranquil murmur to the chorus in

05:06:12.180 --> 05:06:12.959
sundew's head.

05:06:13.080 --> 05:06:18.299
Inside, Hawthorne's house was breezy, warm

05:06:18.299 --> 05:06:20.340
and full of a rose colored light from the

05:06:20.340 --> 05:06:22.139
sun filtering through the curtains.

05:06:22.200 --> 05:06:24.959
It was all one room, but with a high

05:06:24.959 --> 05:06:28.200
ceiling and lots of space, carved wooden

05:06:28.200 --> 05:06:31.799
dragons, snakes, trees, and orangutans

05:06:31.799 --> 05:06:33.840
perched atop the shelves on every wall.

05:06:33.900 --> 05:06:36.419
Sundew looked closely at one of the

05:06:36.419 --> 05:06:38.520
dragon heads, and thought it looked a lot

05:06:38.520 --> 05:06:39.659
like Queen Sequoia.

05:06:39.720 --> 05:06:42.000
Did you make all of these?

05:06:42.060 --> 05:06:44.459
Cricket asked, gazing around the room.

05:06:44.520 --> 05:06:47.700
Ah, yes, Hawthorne answered.

05:06:47.819 --> 05:06:50.040
Lots of time on my talent, you know.

05:06:50.099 --> 05:06:51.779
No one else to talk to.

05:06:51.840 --> 05:06:53.880
So I thought I'd make some friends for

05:06:53.880 --> 05:06:54.180
myself.

05:06:54.299 --> 05:06:55.740
This one's my favorite.

05:06:55.799 --> 05:06:58.860
He padded a smooth egg shape made of

05:06:58.860 --> 05:07:01.020
honey colored wood, with a delicate

05:07:01.020 --> 05:07:02.700
filigree of leaves carved around the

05:07:02.700 --> 05:07:02.939
top.

05:07:03.000 --> 05:07:05.759
It sat on a stand on a little table by

05:07:05.759 --> 05:07:07.319
itself, next to the window.

05:07:07.380 --> 05:07:09.959
They're better company than you'd think.

05:07:10.020 --> 05:07:12.240
Thank goodness I have you, right?

05:07:12.299 --> 05:07:13.799
He said to the ag.

05:07:13.860 --> 05:07:17.639
Poor lonely dragon, Sundew thought.

05:07:17.700 --> 05:07:20.880
But then carving little figures to be

05:07:20.880 --> 05:07:22.200
your only friends is one thing.

05:07:22.259 --> 05:07:25.439
Organizing a nest of snakes to be your

05:07:25.439 --> 05:07:26.880
bodyguards is quite another.

05:07:27.000 --> 05:07:30.360
I can't help but notice that you're a

05:07:30.360 --> 05:07:33.779
hive wing, Hawthorne said, wagging one

05:07:33.779 --> 05:07:34.860
claw at cricket.

05:07:34.860 --> 05:07:37.619
I hope you being here means peace has

05:07:37.619 --> 05:07:39.180
finally been achieved between the

05:07:39.180 --> 05:07:39.599
tribes.

05:07:39.659 --> 05:07:42.900
So, maybe I can go home?

05:07:43.080 --> 05:07:44.639
He added hopefully.

05:07:44.700 --> 05:07:46.380
Nettle snorted.

05:07:46.439 --> 05:07:47.580
Peace?

05:07:47.639 --> 05:07:49.560
Not even close, she said.

05:07:49.619 --> 05:07:52.500
This one's a bit of an ex-hive wing.

05:07:52.560 --> 05:07:54.959
At least according to the morons who

05:07:54.959 --> 05:07:55.319
believe her.

05:07:55.380 --> 05:08:00.840
Ah, hmm, Hawthorne said, crouching to dig

05:08:00.840 --> 05:08:01.740
in a cabinet.

05:08:01.740 --> 05:08:03.900
Traitor to her tribe, eh?

05:08:03.959 --> 05:08:06.779
No, Cricket said.

05:08:06.840 --> 05:08:08.040
The opposite.

05:08:08.099 --> 05:08:09.659
I want to save them.

05:08:09.720 --> 05:08:10.979
Oh, right.

05:08:11.099 --> 05:08:13.139
His muffled voice responded.

05:08:13.200 --> 05:08:14.580
I know that feeling.

05:08:14.639 --> 05:08:17.520
He emerged again, smiling.

05:08:17.580 --> 05:08:20.880
I must say, if I'd known so many visitors

05:08:20.880 --> 05:08:22.560
were coming, I would have carved more

05:08:22.560 --> 05:08:24.900
cups, but these are all I have.

05:08:24.959 --> 05:08:28.259
He produced 3 ebony cups and a stone jar

05:08:28.259 --> 05:08:29.400
full of tea leaves.

05:08:29.459 --> 05:08:31.979
Sundew could smell the chamomile from

05:08:31.979 --> 05:08:32.700
across the room.

05:08:32.759 --> 05:08:35.340
We'll just have to share, won't we?

05:08:35.459 --> 05:08:38.159
Yes, we can manage that.

05:08:38.220 --> 05:08:42.720
Oh, no, thank you, Willow said politely.

05:08:42.779 --> 05:08:44.939
I'm afraid we don't have time for tea.

05:08:45.000 --> 05:08:46.919
We don't?

05:08:47.040 --> 05:08:49.319
Mandrake said, with a wistful look.

05:08:49.380 --> 05:08:51.900
Nettles stepped on his talon, and he

05:08:51.900 --> 05:08:52.259
yelped.

05:08:52.319 --> 05:08:55.560
It won't take long, Hawthorne said.

05:08:55.619 --> 05:08:57.959
There's a hot spring out bag where I can

05:08:57.959 --> 05:08:58.560
get the water.

05:08:58.619 --> 05:08:59.939
Not even have honey.

05:09:00.060 --> 05:09:01.680
He started toward the door.

05:09:01.740 --> 05:09:05.700
Really, no, Sundu said, putting one

05:09:05.700 --> 05:09:07.259
talent over the tea jar.

05:09:07.319 --> 05:09:09.000
The tribe is in danger.

05:09:09.060 --> 05:09:11.819
We must get back before Queen Wasp

05:09:11.819 --> 05:09:13.799
attacks, which might be as soon as

05:09:13.799 --> 05:09:14.099
tonight.

05:09:14.159 --> 05:09:19.020
Oh, Hawthorne said, looking startled.

05:09:19.080 --> 05:09:21.299
That does sound serious.

05:09:21.360 --> 05:09:24.000
Really worth mentioning, I must say.

05:09:24.060 --> 05:09:27.060
Yes, I call that relevant news.

05:09:27.119 --> 05:09:28.979
How do you know that?

05:09:29.099 --> 05:09:32.459
Someone is quite clever, I see.

05:09:32.580 --> 05:09:35.759
He put one talon on his wooden egg and

05:09:35.759 --> 05:09:37.979
frowned down at it thoughtfully.

05:09:38.040 --> 05:09:41.220
Ah, he said, after a moment.

05:09:41.279 --> 05:09:44.220
He looked up at them, his brow clearing.

05:09:44.340 --> 05:09:47.819
You know about the breath of evil.

05:09:47.880 --> 05:09:51.419
We know it's linked to WASP's mind

05:09:51.419 --> 05:09:53.220
control, Sendu said.

05:09:53.340 --> 05:09:56.340
We were hoping, did Queen Sequoia send

05:09:56.340 --> 05:09:56.520
you?

05:09:56.639 --> 05:09:58.439
He interrupted eagerly.

05:09:58.500 --> 05:10:00.959
Does she want me back at last?

05:10:01.080 --> 05:10:02.220
He hesitated.

05:10:02.340 --> 05:10:03.479
That is.

05:10:03.959 --> 05:10:06.479
Is Sequoia still queen?

05:10:06.540 --> 05:10:09.779
She is, Willow answered.

05:10:09.840 --> 05:10:13.860
She is, he said, clasping his front

05:10:13.860 --> 05:10:14.880
talons together.

05:10:14.939 --> 05:10:18.419
That's that's wonderful news.

05:10:18.540 --> 05:10:23.700
After all this time, still alive, I can

05:10:23.700 --> 05:10:24.419
hardly believe it.

05:10:24.540 --> 05:10:26.279
And she did send you.

05:10:26.340 --> 05:10:28.439
What did she say about me?

05:10:28.500 --> 05:10:31.139
That you've been working on a cure for

05:10:31.139 --> 05:10:32.459
wasps' mind control?

05:10:32.580 --> 05:10:33.659
Sundu said.

05:10:33.720 --> 05:10:35.939
She said, you know more about it than any

05:10:35.939 --> 05:10:36.840
other dragon alive.

05:10:36.900 --> 05:10:39.959
Ah, he said.

05:10:40.020 --> 05:10:42.840
His long green wings dipped and folded

05:10:42.840 --> 05:10:43.259
back.

05:10:43.319 --> 05:10:45.659
That is certainly true, isn't it?

05:10:45.720 --> 05:10:49.200
I mean, that was her intention sending me

05:10:49.200 --> 05:10:49.439
here.

05:10:49.500 --> 05:10:52.919
Quite a long time it's been for me to be

05:10:52.919 --> 05:10:55.259
here studying it all alone.

05:10:55.319 --> 05:10:58.139
I really should be an expert by now.

05:10:58.200 --> 05:10:59.340
He laughed.

05:10:59.459 --> 05:11:02.459
Are you using it on the snakes?

05:11:02.520 --> 05:11:03.659
Cricket burst out.

05:11:03.779 --> 05:11:05.580
Is that why they listen to you?

05:11:05.639 --> 05:11:09.060
Well, of course, he said.

05:11:09.119 --> 05:11:11.159
Rather hard to study something without

05:11:11.159 --> 05:11:12.419
doing a few experiments.

05:11:12.479 --> 05:11:15.119
So, they obey you?

05:11:15.240 --> 05:11:16.860
Nettle said curiously.

05:11:16.919 --> 05:11:19.500
You can just order them around.

05:11:19.560 --> 05:11:23.880
Are you in their heads, like WASP, when

05:11:23.880 --> 05:11:25.500
she controls her subjects?

05:11:25.560 --> 05:11:26.459
Cricket asked.

05:11:26.520 --> 05:11:29.340
So many questions.

05:11:29.400 --> 05:11:30.540
I really don't know if I can do this

05:11:30.540 --> 05:11:31.139
without tea.

05:11:31.200 --> 05:11:34.619
Hawthorne said, grabbing a teapot and

05:11:34.619 --> 05:11:35.580
bustling out the back door.

05:11:35.700 --> 05:11:39.000
Willow and Sundew exchanged glances while

05:11:39.000 --> 05:11:41.880
he was gone, but for once, Sundew

05:11:41.880 --> 05:11:43.020
couldn't guess what she was thinking.

05:11:43.080 --> 05:11:46.139
Sundew wasn't even sure what she thought

05:11:46.139 --> 05:11:47.700
of the eccentric old dragon.

05:11:47.759 --> 05:11:51.599
Hawthorne scooted back inside, steam

05:11:51.599 --> 05:11:53.279
rising from the water in the teapot.

05:11:53.340 --> 05:11:55.919
He shook out a pile of tea leaves into

05:11:55.919 --> 05:11:58.139
each cup and poured the water over top of

05:11:58.139 --> 05:11:58.319
them.

05:11:58.380 --> 05:12:00.180
See?

05:12:00.240 --> 05:12:02.040
Already, he said.

05:12:02.099 --> 05:12:03.900
Please do have some.

05:12:03.959 --> 05:12:05.400
I'm quite proud of this tea.

05:12:05.459 --> 05:12:08.159
He set a jar of honey on the table as

05:12:08.159 --> 05:12:10.020
well, with a pleased expression.

05:12:10.139 --> 05:12:12.479
No visitors in decade.

05:12:12.540 --> 05:12:14.459
This is so splendid.

05:12:14.520 --> 05:12:18.060
Hawthorne, Willow said gently.

05:12:18.180 --> 05:12:20.340
We really are short on time.

05:12:20.400 --> 05:12:22.500
Of course.

05:12:22.619 --> 05:12:25.319
He said, his expression clouding.

05:12:25.380 --> 05:12:28.680
I am surprised it took Sequoia so long to

05:12:28.680 --> 05:12:29.040
send you.

05:12:29.099 --> 05:12:31.500
I was beginning to think none of my

05:12:31.500 --> 05:12:32.459
messages got through.

05:12:32.580 --> 05:12:34.740
Messages?

05:12:34.799 --> 05:12:35.939
Mandrake asked.

05:12:36.000 --> 05:12:39.779
Well, Hawthorne said, he took a sip of

05:12:39.779 --> 05:12:40.080
his tea.

05:12:40.139 --> 05:12:42.900
I was forbidden to return to the village

05:12:42.900 --> 05:12:44.099
myself, wasn't I?

05:12:44.159 --> 05:12:47.220
Sundew gave Willow a puzzled look.

05:12:47.279 --> 05:12:48.599
You were?

05:12:48.720 --> 05:12:52.740
So I sent messages, however I could, he

05:12:52.740 --> 05:12:56.520
said, in coconuts down the river, tied to

05:12:56.520 --> 05:12:58.259
the legs of monkeys and birds.

05:12:58.319 --> 05:13:01.560
I even sent a few of my vipers, but they

05:13:01.560 --> 05:13:02.639
were killed before they could reach the

05:13:02.639 --> 05:13:03.000
village.

05:13:03.060 --> 05:13:04.619
Such a shame.

05:13:04.680 --> 05:13:07.680
They were smart little snakes, just doing

05:13:07.680 --> 05:13:08.580
what I'd asked.

05:13:08.639 --> 05:13:12.000
I don't think she got any of those

05:13:12.000 --> 05:13:12.900
messages.

05:13:13.080 --> 05:13:14.099
Willow confessed.

05:13:14.159 --> 05:13:15.959
What did they say?

05:13:16.020 --> 05:13:18.299
Sandu asked, leaning forward.

05:13:18.360 --> 05:13:20.459
Did you find an antidote?

05:13:20.520 --> 05:13:23.340
I did, he said.

05:13:23.400 --> 05:13:26.159
His eyes suddenly glistened with unshed

05:13:26.159 --> 05:13:26.639
tears.

05:13:26.700 --> 05:13:29.279
That is, I believe so.

05:13:29.340 --> 05:13:32.759
But that's amazing, Cricket said.

05:13:32.819 --> 05:13:34.080
Why are you sad?

05:13:34.200 --> 05:13:36.659
Hawthorne rubbed his eyes with his

05:13:36.659 --> 05:13:37.139
knuckles.

05:13:37.200 --> 05:13:42.180
Oh, it's only, you know, a time I've

05:13:42.180 --> 05:13:42.540
lost.

05:13:42.540 --> 05:13:45.180
All these years I could have spent with

05:13:45.180 --> 05:13:45.900
Sequoia.

05:13:45.959 --> 05:13:49.380
Cricket sat down beside him and put one

05:13:49.380 --> 05:13:51.720
talon over his, where it rested on the

05:13:51.720 --> 05:13:51.900
table.

05:13:51.959 --> 05:13:55.439
He twitched slightly, as though his

05:13:55.439 --> 05:13:57.180
instinct was to pull away from a hive

05:13:57.180 --> 05:13:59.759
wing, but he left his talon in hers.

05:13:59.819 --> 05:14:02.580
I'm sorry for what you've been through

05:14:02.639 --> 05:14:03.599
she said.

05:14:03.659 --> 05:14:06.000
I can't imagine what it was like to be

05:14:06.000 --> 05:14:06.959
alone for so long.

05:14:07.020 --> 05:14:09.779
But what you were doing is so important.

05:14:09.900 --> 05:14:12.479
You're going to save so many dragons

05:14:12.479 --> 05:14:13.080
Hawthorne.

05:14:13.139 --> 05:14:15.779
When all the hive wings are freed, you're

05:14:15.779 --> 05:14:16.619
going to be a hero.

05:14:16.680 --> 05:14:19.500
The leaf wing who devoted his life to

05:14:19.500 --> 05:14:20.099
freeing them.

05:14:20.220 --> 05:14:23.459
Your antidote will save my sis, my

05:14:23.459 --> 05:14:23.759
mother.

05:14:23.819 --> 05:14:25.799
It means everything to me.

05:14:25.860 --> 05:14:28.259
Not to mention it'll stop another war.

05:14:28.319 --> 05:14:32.220
He sniffed and pulled his talon away to

05:14:32.220 --> 05:14:33.419
swipe at his eyes again.

05:14:33.419 --> 05:14:36.240
That is something, he said.

05:14:36.299 --> 05:14:39.959
If it works, I'm glad to know this wasn't

05:14:39.959 --> 05:14:40.439
all for nothing.

05:14:40.560 --> 05:14:44.099
And don't get me wrong, I know I deserved

05:14:44.099 --> 05:14:44.400
this.

05:14:44.459 --> 05:14:47.340
I told the queen I understood and I meant

05:14:47.340 --> 05:14:47.580
it.

05:14:47.639 --> 05:14:50.279
This was the right punishment for me.

05:14:50.340 --> 05:14:52.319
The only punishment.

05:14:52.380 --> 05:14:54.060
What?

05:14:54.119 --> 05:14:55.080
Cricket said.

05:14:55.200 --> 05:14:57.479
Glancing at the other leaf wings as

05:14:57.479 --> 05:14:58.680
though they might have the answers.

05:14:58.740 --> 05:15:01.740
Willow spread her wings, equally

05:15:01.740 --> 05:15:02.340
puzzled.

05:15:02.400 --> 05:15:04.139
What do you mean?

05:15:04.200 --> 05:15:05.580
She said to Hawthorne.

05:15:05.639 --> 05:15:08.220
I thought you volunteered for this?

05:15:08.279 --> 05:15:10.080
How could you deserve it?

05:15:10.139 --> 05:15:13.139
What were you being punished for?

05:15:13.200 --> 05:15:14.459
Sundu asked.

05:15:14.580 --> 05:15:16.200
He blinked at them.

05:15:16.259 --> 05:15:18.299
Surprise written in every crease of his

05:15:18.299 --> 05:15:18.599
face.

05:15:18.659 --> 05:15:22.080
Didn't she tell you why I'm here?

05:15:22.200 --> 05:15:23.580
He asked.

05:15:23.639 --> 05:15:25.680
Sundu shook her head.

05:15:25.740 --> 05:15:28.319
She didn't know why she suddenly felt so

05:15:28.319 --> 05:15:30.779
full of dread, as though the earth was

05:15:30.779 --> 05:15:32.099
about to collapse underneath her.

05:15:32.159 --> 05:15:35.759
Because I'm the one who found the breath

05:15:35.759 --> 05:15:36.299
of evil.

05:15:36.360 --> 05:15:39.119
After everyone thought it had been wiped

05:15:39.119 --> 05:15:41.099
out centuries ago, he said.

05:15:41.159 --> 05:15:44.040
And I'm the one who gave it to Queen

05:15:44.040 --> 05:15:44.700
Wasp.

05:15:44.819 --> 05:15:49.139
Chapter 16.

05:15:49.319 --> 05:15:51.419
What?

05:15:51.479 --> 05:15:52.860
Willow cried.

05:15:52.919 --> 05:15:55.619
She staggered back a step, and Sundew

05:15:55.619 --> 05:15:58.020
reached to catch her, their wings sliding

05:15:58.020 --> 05:15:59.520
together like falling petals.

05:15:59.580 --> 05:16:02.580
Hawthorne's words didn't seem to fit

05:16:02.580 --> 05:16:04.080
inside Sundew's brain.

05:16:04.139 --> 05:16:06.119
She couldn't link them properly to

05:16:06.119 --> 05:16:06.479
reality.

05:16:06.540 --> 05:16:08.939
They just didn't make sense.

05:16:09.000 --> 05:16:11.220
You?

05:16:11.220 --> 05:16:12.659
Gave it to her?

05:16:12.720 --> 05:16:13.979
Cricket said.

05:16:14.040 --> 05:16:15.720
The breath of evil?

05:16:15.779 --> 05:16:17.340
What do you mean?

05:16:17.400 --> 05:16:18.000
When?

05:16:18.060 --> 05:16:19.439
You didn't really.

05:16:19.500 --> 05:16:21.240
Why would you do that?

05:16:21.299 --> 05:16:23.220
Why would you make her more powerful?

05:16:23.279 --> 05:16:26.580
Why would you give anyone the power to

05:16:26.580 --> 05:16:28.020
control other dragons like that?

05:16:28.080 --> 05:16:31.259
I don't understand, said Willow.

05:16:31.319 --> 05:16:34.680
Me neither, echoed Mandrake.

05:16:34.740 --> 05:16:37.619
I understand that someone's been lying to

05:16:37.619 --> 05:16:40.139
us, and keeping things from us.

05:16:40.200 --> 05:16:41.520
Metal snarled.

05:16:41.580 --> 05:16:43.680
I may not understand what those exact

05:16:43.680 --> 05:16:45.779
things are, but I know that I'm angry

05:16:45.779 --> 05:16:46.259
about it.

05:16:46.319 --> 05:16:50.340
Hawthorne held up his front talons, palms

05:16:50.340 --> 05:16:50.639
out.

05:16:50.759 --> 05:16:53.040
I'm sorry, I thought you knew.

05:16:53.099 --> 05:16:55.380
I thought Queen Sequoia would have told

05:16:55.380 --> 05:16:55.680
you.

05:16:55.740 --> 05:16:57.840
Wouldn't you think she would share the

05:16:57.840 --> 05:16:59.880
whole story before sending someone on a

05:16:59.880 --> 05:17:00.840
quest this dangerous?

05:17:00.959 --> 05:17:05.159
I would thank that, Nettle snapped.

05:17:05.220 --> 05:17:06.360
She should have.

05:17:06.419 --> 05:17:09.479
Maybe she thought Hawthorne was dead.

05:17:09.540 --> 05:17:12.119
And if he was, then no one would ever

05:17:12.119 --> 05:17:13.139
have to know the whole truth.

05:17:13.200 --> 05:17:15.240
Mandrake suggested.

05:17:15.299 --> 05:17:18.360
That is not better, Nettle cried.

05:17:18.419 --> 05:17:19.319
That is worse.

05:17:19.380 --> 05:17:20.639
Talk about cowardly.

05:17:20.759 --> 05:17:24.840
Sundew was angry too, but she mostly felt

05:17:24.840 --> 05:17:26.639
as if she'd been walking along a strong

05:17:26.639 --> 05:17:29.099
branch, and it had suddenly snapped off

05:17:29.099 --> 05:17:31.979
and sent her plummeting to the ground, and

05:17:31.979 --> 05:17:34.319
the ground was extraordinarily far away

05:17:34.319 --> 05:17:36.720
and her wings weren't working, and it was

05:17:36.720 --> 05:17:38.520
difficult to focus on being mad and

05:17:38.520 --> 05:17:40.319
trying not to plummet at the same time.

05:17:40.380 --> 05:17:43.860
I think you need to tell us the whole

05:17:43.860 --> 05:17:46.380
story, Sundew said to Hawthorne.

05:17:46.439 --> 05:17:48.779
I must have misunderstood something.

05:17:48.840 --> 05:17:51.720
He didn't mean he went looking for the

05:17:51.720 --> 05:17:52.439
breath of evil.

05:17:52.500 --> 05:17:55.259
He can't possibly mean that we did this

05:17:55.259 --> 05:17:56.220
to the hive wings.

05:17:56.279 --> 05:17:59.819
Hawthorne looked down at his tea, and

05:17:59.819 --> 05:18:01.319
fiddled with a handle on his cup.

05:18:01.439 --> 05:18:03.900
All right, he said.

05:18:03.959 --> 05:18:06.900
But can I please start by saying, I know

05:18:06.900 --> 05:18:08.099
you'll hate me at the end of it.

05:18:08.159 --> 05:18:09.419
That's all right.

05:18:09.479 --> 05:18:12.119
If you could hold back a little bit

05:18:12.119 --> 05:18:12.540
though.

05:18:12.599 --> 05:18:16.020
I'd appreciate it. 50 years of carrying

05:18:16.020 --> 05:18:19.259
this guilt has really been a lot, if you

05:18:19.259 --> 05:18:19.740
can imagine.

05:18:19.799 --> 05:18:24.840
More explaining, less self pity, nettle

05:18:24.840 --> 05:18:25.200
hissed.

05:18:25.319 --> 05:18:27.240
He nodded again.

05:18:27.299 --> 05:18:28.680
Yes.

05:18:28.740 --> 05:18:31.200
Well, let's see.

05:18:31.259 --> 05:18:34.860
Queen Wasp was dangerous from the moment

05:18:34.860 --> 05:18:36.240
she inherited her crown.

05:18:36.299 --> 05:18:40.439
Her mother, Queen Cocineal, was deceitful

05:18:40.439 --> 05:18:42.900
and power hungry, but at least she

05:18:42.900 --> 05:18:45.000
respected the separate tribe monarchies.

05:18:45.060 --> 05:18:47.099
Wasp, though.

05:18:47.159 --> 05:18:50.279
She looked at silk wings and leaf wings

05:18:50.279 --> 05:18:52.919
and only saw more dragons to crush under

05:18:52.919 --> 05:18:53.580
her talons.

05:18:53.639 --> 05:18:56.580
She wanted everyone to bow to her.

05:18:56.639 --> 05:18:59.099
That became clear very early on.

05:18:59.159 --> 05:19:01.860
But that wasn't the worst of it.

05:19:01.919 --> 05:19:04.919
She thought our power came from the

05:19:04.919 --> 05:19:05.400
trees.

05:19:05.520 --> 05:19:08.099
And she thought that if she cut them down

05:19:08.099 --> 05:19:09.479
we'd become weak.

05:19:09.540 --> 05:19:12.240
She did it stealthily at first.

05:19:12.299 --> 05:19:15.180
Stretches of forest cleared and faraway

05:19:15.180 --> 05:19:16.979
corners where we might not notice.

05:19:17.040 --> 05:19:21.360
Accidental forest fires that wiped out

05:19:21.360 --> 05:19:22.200
100s of trees.

05:19:22.319 --> 05:19:25.560
Another 100 cut down to build her 1st

05:19:25.560 --> 05:19:28.439
hive, and a dramatic performance art

05:19:28.439 --> 05:19:29.939
piece when we tried to object.

05:19:30.000 --> 05:19:33.419
Oh, are leaf wings the only ones allowed

05:19:33.419 --> 05:19:35.220
to use pentalin resources now?

05:19:35.279 --> 05:19:38.340
Why shouldn't I build my tribe a city to

05:19:38.340 --> 05:19:38.700
live in?

05:19:38.759 --> 05:19:40.080
And so on?

05:19:40.139 --> 05:19:43.380
He paused to sip his tea again.

05:19:43.439 --> 05:19:45.840
Then nudged one of the other cups toward

05:19:45.840 --> 05:19:47.459
Nettle and Mandrake with a hopeful

05:19:47.459 --> 05:19:50.400
expression, Nettle scowled at him, and he

05:19:50.400 --> 05:19:52.380
sighed and returned it to his story.

05:19:52.439 --> 05:19:54.900
By the time we figured out what she was

05:19:54.900 --> 05:19:55.139
doing.

05:19:55.200 --> 05:19:57.720
It was too late for countless trees.

05:19:57.840 --> 05:20:00.240
We tried to stop her in all the

05:20:00.240 --> 05:20:02.459
diplomatic ways, but she would lie to our

05:20:02.459 --> 05:20:05.639
faces, promise to stop, and then turn

05:20:05.639 --> 05:20:06.659
around and keep doing it.

05:20:06.720 --> 05:20:09.419
Or she'd have her guards throw us out.

05:20:09.479 --> 05:20:13.439
The queen of the leaf wings, tossed out

05:20:13.439 --> 05:20:16.139
of wasp hive, like a spider that crawled

05:20:16.139 --> 05:20:16.979
in the wrong window.

05:20:17.040 --> 05:20:19.319
Can you imagine?

05:20:19.380 --> 05:20:22.439
I can imagine tossing you out a window?

05:20:22.500 --> 05:20:23.880
Nettle offered.

05:20:24.000 --> 05:20:26.639
And then she became even worse.

05:20:26.700 --> 05:20:28.380
He continued hurriedly.

05:20:28.439 --> 05:20:30.900
She announced that according to the book

05:20:30.900 --> 05:20:33.299
of Clearsight, the time had come for us

05:20:33.299 --> 05:20:35.580
to consolidate the 3 tribes under one

05:20:35.580 --> 05:20:36.060
queen.

05:20:36.180 --> 05:20:37.680
Her.

05:20:37.740 --> 05:20:41.939
She sent Queen Monarch and Queen Sequoia

05:20:41.939 --> 05:20:44.520
instructions for formally stepping down

05:20:44.520 --> 05:20:47.520
and handing their subjects over to her

05:20:47.520 --> 05:20:48.000
control.

05:20:48.060 --> 05:20:51.720
We know this part, Sundu said.

05:20:51.840 --> 05:20:54.479
Queen Monarch said yes, Queen Sequoia

05:20:54.479 --> 05:20:56.400
said no, and the tree wars began.

05:20:56.459 --> 05:21:00.060
Not immediately, said Hawthorne.

05:21:00.119 --> 05:21:02.040
First we tried to talk her down.

05:21:02.099 --> 05:21:05.700
And second, we tried something else.

05:21:05.759 --> 05:21:09.240
He cupped his claws around the teacup and

05:21:09.240 --> 05:21:09.900
closed his eyes.

05:21:09.959 --> 05:21:12.419
I thought we could stop her.

05:21:12.540 --> 05:21:15.060
I thought we could save everyone.

05:21:15.119 --> 05:21:18.779
By giving Wasp the most powerful weapon

05:21:18.779 --> 05:21:20.819
in the world, Cricket asked.

05:21:20.880 --> 05:21:24.360
Yes, please do explain the logic there?

05:21:24.419 --> 05:21:25.319
Sundew said.

05:21:25.380 --> 05:21:28.680
It wasn't supposed to make her powerful.

05:21:28.740 --> 05:21:32.220
Hawthorne looked down at his talons.

05:21:32.279 --> 05:21:35.700
I thought, if I found the plant and we

05:21:35.700 --> 05:21:36.419
used it on her.

05:21:36.479 --> 05:21:39.959
That we'd be able to control her.

05:21:40.080 --> 05:21:42.840
Willow turned her face in towards

05:21:42.840 --> 05:21:45.299
Sundew's shoulder, hiding it for a moment

05:21:45.299 --> 05:21:48.119
as she breathed in a small, hiccuping

05:21:48.119 --> 05:21:48.299
way.

05:21:48.360 --> 05:21:51.419
Sundew wound her tail around willows and

05:21:51.419 --> 05:21:52.020
tried to think straight.

05:21:52.080 --> 05:21:55.619
We were trying to turn the hive wing

05:21:55.619 --> 05:21:57.959
queen into our mind controlled zombie.

05:21:58.020 --> 05:22:00.119
We would have done that to her.

05:22:00.180 --> 05:22:03.060
The same terrible things she's done to

05:22:03.060 --> 05:22:03.540
her subjects.

05:22:03.599 --> 05:22:05.159
Instead.

05:22:05.220 --> 05:22:07.560
We made her stronger than any other

05:22:07.560 --> 05:22:08.099
dragon.

05:22:08.159 --> 05:22:10.919
We gave her a way to keep her claws on

05:22:10.919 --> 05:22:13.500
her tribe's necks and the power to use

05:22:13.500 --> 05:22:14.520
them against us.

05:22:14.580 --> 05:22:17.639
She glanced over a cricket, who was

05:22:17.639 --> 05:22:19.020
staring at Hawthorne in horror.

05:22:19.080 --> 05:22:21.659
I thought we were the good tribe.

05:22:21.659 --> 05:22:23.880
How could we do something like this?

05:22:23.939 --> 05:22:26.520
When did this happen?

05:22:26.580 --> 05:22:27.779
Cricket asked.

05:22:27.840 --> 05:22:30.119
Questions that suddenly exploding out of

05:22:30.119 --> 05:22:32.939
her, like flame silk erupting from Blue's

05:22:32.939 --> 05:22:33.659
wrists.

05:22:33.720 --> 05:22:35.459
And how did you give it to her?

05:22:35.520 --> 05:22:38.099
How did she get her talent on more of the

05:22:38.099 --> 05:22:38.400
plant?

05:22:38.459 --> 05:22:40.439
How did she figure out what to do with

05:22:40.439 --> 05:22:40.619
it?

05:22:40.680 --> 05:22:44.040
She stopped, pressing her talons to her

05:22:44.040 --> 05:22:44.459
temples.

05:22:44.520 --> 05:22:46.860
Why would you do this?

05:22:46.919 --> 05:22:50.939
She threatened our trees, hive wing

05:22:50.939 --> 05:22:52.200
Hawthorne said.

05:22:52.200 --> 05:22:54.299
With a hard note in his voice that told

05:22:54.299 --> 05:22:56.400
Sundew, he still thought his actions were

05:22:56.400 --> 05:22:56.939
justified.

05:22:57.000 --> 05:22:59.159
The trees we loved.

05:22:59.220 --> 05:23:01.680
Our homes and souls.

05:23:01.740 --> 05:23:04.380
We saw the war that was coming.

05:23:04.439 --> 05:23:07.500
We knew how dangerous she was, and we

05:23:07.500 --> 05:23:08.819
knew we couldn't give her the leaf

05:23:08.819 --> 05:23:09.180
wings.

05:23:09.299 --> 05:23:13.979
So we held a peace summit, and I, I put

05:23:13.979 --> 05:23:15.060
it in her food that night.

05:23:15.119 --> 05:23:18.419
Willow took one of Sunday's clenched

05:23:18.419 --> 05:23:21.360
talons, smoothed it flat, and looked up

05:23:21.360 --> 05:23:22.200
at Hawthorn again.

05:23:22.259 --> 05:23:25.200
Did the queen know what you were doing?

05:23:25.259 --> 05:23:27.959
He made an inscrutable face.

05:23:28.020 --> 05:23:31.259
I told her what I wanted to do.

05:23:31.319 --> 05:23:33.659
She didn't stop me.

05:23:33.720 --> 05:23:36.779
But I can't say she exactly told me to do

05:23:36.779 --> 05:23:37.020
it.

05:23:37.080 --> 05:23:39.659
She could have stopped me, though.

05:23:39.720 --> 05:23:41.520
I was so loyal.

05:23:41.580 --> 05:23:43.680
I always listened to her.

05:23:43.740 --> 05:23:46.200
If she had told me not to do it.

05:23:46.259 --> 05:23:46.979
I wouldn't have.

05:23:47.040 --> 05:23:48.599
She never said no.

05:23:48.659 --> 05:23:50.700
This is really...

05:23:51.659 --> 05:23:54.060
Hawthorne stopped himself, lashing his

05:23:54.060 --> 05:23:54.720
tail for a moment.

05:23:54.779 --> 05:23:58.979
I mean, he continued in a calmer voice.

05:23:59.099 --> 05:24:01.259
Of course it was my fault.

05:24:01.380 --> 05:24:03.240
I found the plant.

05:24:03.299 --> 05:24:05.580
I slipped it into wasp's food.

05:24:05.639 --> 05:24:06.720
That was me.

05:24:06.840 --> 05:24:09.779
Even if I did it with the noblest of

05:24:09.779 --> 05:24:10.200
intentions.

05:24:10.259 --> 05:24:13.680
He really does still think he did the

05:24:13.680 --> 05:24:15.479
right thing, Sundoo thought.

05:24:15.540 --> 05:24:18.540
And that it just went wrong.

05:24:18.599 --> 05:24:22.139
At 1st it seemed like nothing happened.

05:24:22.200 --> 05:24:24.060
It clearly didn't work.

05:24:24.119 --> 05:24:25.740
Hawthorne said.

05:24:25.799 --> 05:24:28.919
He put one talon on the wooden egg again

05:24:28.919 --> 05:24:31.139
tracing the leaves with one claw.

05:24:31.200 --> 05:24:33.840
Wasp behaved exactly the same.

05:24:33.900 --> 05:24:36.060
Both that night at dinner.

05:24:36.119 --> 05:24:37.799
And the following morning during

05:24:37.799 --> 05:24:38.639
negotiations.

05:24:38.700 --> 05:24:41.459
We tried to steer her onto a peaceful

05:24:41.459 --> 05:24:45.119
path, we tried subtle suggestions, and

05:24:45.119 --> 05:24:47.459
when those didn't work, we tried to order

05:24:47.459 --> 05:24:48.419
her to back down.

05:24:48.479 --> 05:24:52.860
She hissed at us and promised war, just

05:24:52.860 --> 05:24:53.639
as she always did.

05:24:53.700 --> 05:24:55.919
So we thought we had failed.

05:24:55.979 --> 05:24:57.779
No harm done.

05:24:57.840 --> 05:25:00.479
A long shot attempt at salvation that

05:25:00.479 --> 05:25:00.959
didn't work.

05:25:01.020 --> 05:25:03.779
It wasn't until later.

05:25:03.840 --> 05:25:07.560
When I saw her mind control, that I

05:25:07.560 --> 05:25:09.000
realized we must have caused it.

05:25:09.060 --> 05:25:11.819
I don't know how she figured out what to

05:25:11.819 --> 05:25:13.919
do, or where she got the plant.

05:25:14.040 --> 05:25:16.860
He tapped his claws on the top of the

05:25:16.860 --> 05:25:17.220
egg.

05:25:17.279 --> 05:25:20.880
That's what you get for sneaking and half

05:25:20.880 --> 05:25:23.279
measures, Nettle growled.

05:25:23.340 --> 05:25:25.259
It should have been poison in her food

05:25:25.259 --> 05:25:26.099
instead.

05:25:26.159 --> 05:25:28.439
That would have saved 100s of dragons.

05:25:28.500 --> 05:25:32.520
Nobody argued with her, but Sundew could

05:25:32.520 --> 05:25:34.380
see the consternation written all over

05:25:34.380 --> 05:25:35.939
Willows and Crickets' faces.

05:25:36.000 --> 05:25:37.259
She's right.

05:25:37.319 --> 05:25:40.740
But she's also wrong, Sundew thought.

05:25:40.799 --> 05:25:43.439
Even I don't think anyone should poison

05:25:43.439 --> 05:25:44.880
dragons at a peace summit.

05:25:44.939 --> 05:25:49.740
The good news, Hawthorne broke in, slicing

05:25:49.740 --> 05:25:50.279
through the tension.

05:25:50.400 --> 05:25:53.400
Is the now I know what we did wrong.

05:25:53.459 --> 05:25:56.759
We needed to ingest the plant ourselves.

05:25:56.819 --> 05:25:59.819
Otherwise, there was no connection

05:25:59.819 --> 05:26:01.500
between our minds and hers.

05:26:01.560 --> 05:26:05.700
But if you both ate it, Cricket asked

05:26:05.700 --> 05:26:06.299
doubtfully.

05:26:06.419 --> 05:26:08.700
Who would control who?

05:26:08.759 --> 05:26:10.979
Why wouldn't she be the one controlling

05:26:10.979 --> 05:26:11.759
you instead?

05:26:11.819 --> 05:26:15.000
Ah, said Hawthorne.

05:26:15.060 --> 05:26:16.680
His expression lightening.

05:26:16.740 --> 05:26:19.080
Those are mysteries I solved with

05:26:19.080 --> 05:26:19.799
science.

05:26:19.860 --> 05:26:24.240
Experimentation, research, investigation.

05:26:24.299 --> 05:26:27.479
All the careful procedures I wish I'd had

05:26:27.479 --> 05:26:28.259
time for back then.

05:26:28.319 --> 05:26:31.200
It's amazing what you can discover when

05:26:31.200 --> 05:26:33.180
you're alone for 50 years with nothing

05:26:33.180 --> 05:26:33.779
else to do.

05:26:33.840 --> 05:26:37.979
Yes, I know, not completely alone.

05:26:38.040 --> 05:26:40.860
Sundew tilted her head at him.

05:26:40.979 --> 05:26:43.319
Not completely alone?

05:26:43.380 --> 05:26:44.159
she echoed.

05:26:44.220 --> 05:26:45.840
Do you mean the snakes?

05:26:45.959 --> 05:26:50.279
The snakes, the foliage, my wooden

05:26:50.279 --> 05:26:53.400
friends, he answered, waving his claws

05:26:53.400 --> 05:26:54.479
around the little house.

05:26:54.479 --> 05:26:58.259
I have extremely strong leaf speak, so I

05:26:58.259 --> 05:26:59.939
can always chat with the jungle if I get

05:26:59.939 --> 05:27:00.299
lonely.

05:27:00.360 --> 05:27:03.779
So, you've been experimenting on the

05:27:03.779 --> 05:27:06.959
snakes, Cricket said, and you figured out

05:27:06.959 --> 05:27:08.099
how to mind control them?

05:27:08.159 --> 05:27:10.680
Is that also how you found the antidote?

05:27:10.740 --> 05:27:12.840
Yes, exactly.

05:27:12.959 --> 05:27:14.459
Hawthorne said.

05:27:14.520 --> 05:27:16.020
I tried everything.

05:27:16.080 --> 05:27:18.540
And I finally found this.

05:27:18.599 --> 05:27:21.840
He darted across the room to a wooden

05:27:21.840 --> 05:27:24.959
chest, ornately carved with 100s of tiny

05:27:24.959 --> 05:27:25.619
leaves.

05:27:25.680 --> 05:27:28.259
Sundew couldn't even imagine how long it

05:27:28.259 --> 05:27:29.459
had taken him to carve it.

05:27:29.520 --> 05:27:32.700
He lifted off the lid, grunting slightly

05:27:32.700 --> 05:27:34.799
at the weight of it, and laid it on the

05:27:34.799 --> 05:27:37.020
floor beside him, then beckoned cricket

05:27:37.020 --> 05:27:37.560
to look inside.

05:27:37.680 --> 05:27:41.459
Sundew edged closer so she could see as

05:27:41.459 --> 05:27:41.639
well.

05:27:41.700 --> 05:27:44.700
The chest seemed to be full of tiny

05:27:44.700 --> 05:27:45.779
gnarled bits of roots.

05:27:45.840 --> 05:27:49.020
They looked like ginger root, but smelled

05:27:49.020 --> 05:27:50.099
more like old oranges.

05:27:50.159 --> 05:27:52.799
From the look on cricket's face, though

05:27:52.799 --> 05:27:54.119
they might have been made of gold.

05:27:54.180 --> 05:27:57.360
This is the antidote?

05:27:57.479 --> 05:28:00.299
She said to Hawthorne in a hushed voice.

05:28:00.360 --> 05:28:02.759
She reached in and lifted out one of the

05:28:02.759 --> 05:28:05.040
roots, turning it between her claws.

05:28:05.099 --> 05:28:06.900
What is it?

05:28:06.959 --> 05:28:10.200
It's another plant I found growing in the

05:28:10.200 --> 05:28:11.580
jungle, he said.

05:28:11.639 --> 05:28:14.520
I call it heart of salvation.

05:28:14.639 --> 05:28:17.759
Nettle snorted, and he shot her a half

05:28:17.759 --> 05:28:18.119
smile.

05:28:18.180 --> 05:28:20.819
I figure if we're going to be all

05:28:20.819 --> 05:28:23.400
dramatic with our plant names, I might as

05:28:23.400 --> 05:28:23.880
well join in.

05:28:23.939 --> 05:28:25.680
Wow.

05:28:25.740 --> 05:28:27.659
Cricket said reverently.

05:28:27.720 --> 05:28:29.340
And it really works.

05:28:29.400 --> 05:28:31.380
It breaks the mind control?

05:28:31.439 --> 05:28:34.319
As far as I can tell, he said.

05:28:34.380 --> 05:28:37.740
It works on snakes, but who knows about

05:28:37.740 --> 05:28:38.520
dragons?

05:28:38.580 --> 05:28:41.340
I haven't exactly had any test subjects

05:28:41.340 --> 05:28:42.360
for that, have I?

05:28:42.419 --> 05:28:45.360
Oh, maybe you could eat one, and we'll

05:28:45.360 --> 05:28:46.200
see if it works on you.

05:28:46.259 --> 05:28:48.659
She shook her head ruefully.

05:28:48.720 --> 05:28:51.540
I am not susceptible to the mind control

05:28:51.540 --> 05:28:52.380
she said.

05:28:52.500 --> 05:28:56.040
Queen Wasp never injected my egg, so it

05:28:56.040 --> 05:28:58.560
doesn't work on me, which means we

05:28:58.560 --> 05:28:59.939
wouldn't learn anything from me eating

05:28:59.939 --> 05:29:00.240
this.

05:29:00.299 --> 05:29:02.939
She sighed and put it back in the chest.

05:29:03.000 --> 05:29:05.700
Hawthorne watched the movements of her

05:29:05.700 --> 05:29:07.919
claw intently, as if he was trying to

05:29:07.919 --> 05:29:09.479
think of a way she could still be useful

05:29:09.479 --> 05:29:10.259
to the experiment.

05:29:10.319 --> 05:29:14.880
So to test it out, Sundu said, we'll have

05:29:14.880 --> 05:29:17.279
to find a hive wing who is all zombie

05:29:17.279 --> 05:29:19.500
brained, force them to eat it, and see

05:29:19.500 --> 05:29:19.979
what happens.

05:29:20.040 --> 05:29:24.840
I'm afraid so, he said, ringing his claws

05:29:24.840 --> 05:29:25.080
together.

05:29:25.139 --> 05:29:28.860
Well, luckily for us, there is probably

05:29:28.860 --> 05:29:30.599
about a 1000 of them heading this way

05:29:30.599 --> 05:29:31.139
right now.

05:29:31.200 --> 05:29:32.759
Sundew said.

05:29:32.819 --> 05:29:35.340
Peck all the weird nobbly salvation

05:29:35.340 --> 05:29:37.020
routes you have, and let's go.

05:29:37.080 --> 05:29:41.700
Chapter 17.

05:29:41.939 --> 05:29:45.240
It took a while to convince Hawthorne

05:29:45.240 --> 05:29:47.580
that, yes, they really meant it.

05:29:47.639 --> 05:29:49.200
He should come back to the village with

05:29:49.200 --> 05:29:52.799
them, that, yes, Queen Sequoia would be

05:29:52.799 --> 05:29:54.779
happy to see him, now that he'd found the

05:29:54.779 --> 05:29:57.840
antidote, that, no, nobody would yell at

05:29:57.840 --> 05:30:00.720
him, probably, and in fact, nobody had

05:30:00.720 --> 05:30:03.000
any idea what he'd done except for the

05:30:03.000 --> 05:30:04.500
queen, as far as they knew.

05:30:04.560 --> 05:30:07.200
Then they had to deal with him being

05:30:07.200 --> 05:30:08.580
miffed about everyone completely

05:30:08.580 --> 05:30:11.759
forgetting him, and then they had to talk

05:30:11.759 --> 05:30:13.860
him out of packing every single one of

05:30:13.860 --> 05:30:14.700
his carvings.

05:30:14.759 --> 05:30:18.419
There's no time, Sundu cried, as

05:30:18.419 --> 05:30:20.220
Hawthorne scooped up an armful of little

05:30:20.220 --> 05:30:22.439
wooden sequoias and glanced around

05:30:22.439 --> 05:30:23.340
frantically for a box.

05:30:23.400 --> 05:30:26.580
Hawthorne, you can come back and get them

05:30:26.580 --> 05:30:26.819
later.

05:30:26.880 --> 05:30:29.819
Right now, the only thing we can bring is

05:30:29.819 --> 05:30:30.479
the antidote.

05:30:30.599 --> 05:30:33.419
We need to move as quickly as we can, not

05:30:33.419 --> 05:30:35.400
card a house full of nonsense all over

05:30:35.400 --> 05:30:35.880
the jungle.

05:30:35.939 --> 05:30:38.700
They're beautiful carvings.

05:30:38.819 --> 05:30:41.159
Willow interjected soothingly.

05:30:41.220 --> 05:30:43.439
Maybe just bring one for now.

05:30:43.560 --> 05:30:47.279
Hawthorne's expression relaxed, and he

05:30:47.279 --> 05:30:49.380
dropped all the others, reaching for his

05:30:49.380 --> 05:30:50.520
egg like favorite.

05:30:50.580 --> 05:30:53.880
Yes, we can do that, he said.

05:30:53.939 --> 05:30:56.700
As long as I have this friend.

05:30:56.759 --> 05:30:57.360
I will be all right.

05:30:57.419 --> 05:31:01.439
Wonderful, Nettle said, rolling her

05:31:01.439 --> 05:31:01.680
eyes.

05:31:01.740 --> 05:31:03.119
You carry that?

05:31:03.180 --> 05:31:04.979
Mandrake and I will carry this.

05:31:05.099 --> 05:31:07.919
She waved one wing over the chest full of

05:31:07.919 --> 05:31:08.400
roots.

05:31:08.459 --> 05:31:11.459
Sundew had misgivings about that plan.

05:31:11.520 --> 05:31:14.040
Leaving the antidote and the talons of

05:31:14.040 --> 05:31:16.560
those two, but cricket was carrying

05:31:16.560 --> 05:31:19.139
bumblebee, and Sundu wanted a chance to

05:31:19.139 --> 05:31:20.700
talk to Willow out of everyone's

05:31:20.700 --> 05:31:21.180
earshot.

05:31:21.240 --> 05:31:22.799
It'll be fine.

05:31:22.919 --> 05:31:25.200
They'll be careful with it, I'm sure.

05:31:25.319 --> 05:31:27.900
What about my vipers?

05:31:28.020 --> 05:31:30.479
Hawthorne asked, as they stepped out the

05:31:30.479 --> 05:31:30.779
door.

05:31:30.840 --> 05:31:33.299
Sundew cast a glance at the sky.

05:31:33.360 --> 05:31:35.220
She guessed it was late afternoon.

05:31:35.279 --> 05:31:38.939
Ah, what about your vipers?

05:31:39.000 --> 05:31:40.380
Mandrake echoed.

05:31:40.439 --> 05:31:43.200
They started across the clearing. back

05:31:43.200 --> 05:31:44.759
into the snake spangled jungle.

05:31:44.819 --> 05:31:46.799
Should I bring them?

05:31:46.860 --> 05:31:48.540
Hawthorne said brightly.

05:31:48.599 --> 05:31:50.340
I should bring them, shouldn't I?

05:31:50.400 --> 05:31:53.400
Your army of poisonous snakes?

05:31:53.459 --> 05:31:55.680
To a village full of dragonettes?

05:31:55.740 --> 05:31:56.639
Willow said.

05:31:56.700 --> 05:31:59.400
I vote, definitely no.

05:31:59.459 --> 05:32:02.880
But they might be useful, Hawthorne

05:32:02.880 --> 05:32:04.259
argued, his face falling.

05:32:04.380 --> 05:32:06.540
Aren't we about to go to war?

05:32:06.659 --> 05:32:08.639
Yes, so I hear.

05:32:08.700 --> 05:32:11.220
So maybe Queen Sequoia would like a few

05:32:11.220 --> 05:32:13.439
zombie vipers on her side this time.

05:32:13.560 --> 05:32:16.380
Please don't, Cricket said.

05:32:16.439 --> 05:32:18.659
We don't want to make killing dragons

05:32:18.659 --> 05:32:19.200
easier.

05:32:19.259 --> 05:32:21.360
We don't want to kill anyone.

05:32:21.419 --> 05:32:23.400
We're going to free them all with the

05:32:23.400 --> 05:32:25.259
antidote, and then there won't be any

05:32:25.259 --> 05:32:25.500
war.

05:32:25.560 --> 05:32:27.720
Nettle snorted.

05:32:27.779 --> 05:32:29.220
Extremely pointedly.

05:32:29.340 --> 05:32:33.840
If it works, Hawthorne said sadly, and if

05:32:33.840 --> 05:32:35.580
we can figure out how to give it to all

05:32:35.580 --> 05:32:35.939
of them.

05:32:36.000 --> 05:32:39.000
Ooh, Vipers might help with that.

05:32:39.060 --> 05:32:41.880
Sounds like a decent backup plan to me.

05:32:41.939 --> 05:32:43.439
That old chimed in.

05:32:43.500 --> 05:32:46.080
She'd wound vines around the trunk, and

05:32:46.080 --> 05:32:48.479
looped one end over her shoulder, and one

05:32:48.479 --> 05:32:50.520
over mandrakes, so it hung between them.

05:32:50.580 --> 05:32:52.979
They were both already huffing from the

05:32:52.979 --> 05:32:53.459
weight of it.

05:32:53.520 --> 05:32:56.340
I mean, no harm done having an extra

05:32:56.340 --> 05:32:57.659
secret weapon around, right?

05:32:57.720 --> 05:33:01.740
Exactly, Hawthorne said, beaming.

05:33:01.799 --> 05:33:04.139
He flapped his wings once and gazed

05:33:04.139 --> 05:33:06.779
through the trees, his eyes going weirdly

05:33:06.779 --> 05:33:07.259
still.

05:33:07.319 --> 05:33:10.080
I'll just have a few of them follow us.

05:33:10.139 --> 05:33:13.139
Willow, Sandu whispered.

05:33:13.200 --> 05:33:14.279
Should we stop him?

05:33:14.340 --> 05:33:15.840
I don't know.

05:33:15.959 --> 05:33:17.639
Willow whispered back.

05:33:17.700 --> 05:33:20.099
She furrowed her brow at the rustlings

05:33:20.099 --> 05:33:20.700
and the leaves.

05:33:20.759 --> 05:33:24.599
It feels wrong, but then I'm not even

05:33:24.599 --> 05:33:26.340
sure I know what's right and wrong

05:33:26.340 --> 05:33:26.700
anymore.

05:33:26.759 --> 05:33:29.819
Queen Sequoia was always my moral

05:33:29.819 --> 05:33:30.419
compass.

05:33:30.479 --> 05:33:32.459
I thought she'd always do the right

05:33:32.459 --> 05:33:32.700
thing.

05:33:32.819 --> 05:33:35.459
And I wanted to be like her so much.

05:33:35.520 --> 05:33:38.400
But what she was going to do to wasp.

05:33:38.459 --> 05:33:40.860
And the fact that she lied to us about

05:33:40.860 --> 05:33:41.819
it.

05:33:41.880 --> 05:33:43.439
I don't know how to feel right now.

05:33:43.500 --> 05:33:45.360
Mad?

05:33:45.479 --> 05:33:46.919
Sandu suggested.

05:33:46.979 --> 05:33:47.880
Really mad?

05:33:47.939 --> 05:33:49.860
You're allowed to be angry about this

05:33:49.860 --> 05:33:50.400
willow.

05:33:50.459 --> 05:33:52.799
She brushed Willow's wing lightly.

05:33:52.860 --> 05:33:55.979
I don't want to be mad, Willow

05:33:55.979 --> 05:33:56.520
protested.

05:33:56.580 --> 05:33:58.020
What good would that do?

05:33:58.080 --> 05:34:00.900
If I let myself be really angry?

05:34:01.080 --> 05:34:04.200
I might do something terrible, like yell

05:34:04.200 --> 05:34:05.400
at Queen Sequoia.

05:34:05.459 --> 05:34:08.400
Maybe she should be yelled at.

05:34:08.459 --> 05:34:09.840
Sundew pointed out.

05:34:09.900 --> 05:34:12.000
But how would that help?

05:34:12.119 --> 05:34:14.819
Then she'd feel awful, and I'd feel

05:34:14.819 --> 05:34:17.220
guilty, and we'd be distracted from more

05:34:17.220 --> 05:34:17.759
important things.

05:34:17.819 --> 05:34:21.360
The point is to make sure she knows she

05:34:21.360 --> 05:34:23.939
did something wrong, so she won't do it

05:34:23.939 --> 05:34:24.240
again.

05:34:24.299 --> 05:34:26.819
And maybe she'll try harder to fix it.

05:34:26.880 --> 05:34:30.479
I'm sure she already knows it was wrong

05:34:30.479 --> 05:34:31.740
Willow said.

05:34:31.799 --> 05:34:36.119
I'm not sure he does, Sundew said, nodding

05:34:36.119 --> 05:34:36.900
toward Hawthorne.

05:34:36.959 --> 05:34:39.180
He was walking at the front of the group

05:34:39.180 --> 05:34:40.500
chatting with cricket.

05:34:40.560 --> 05:34:42.900
A pair of snakes was slithering along

05:34:42.900 --> 05:34:45.240
right by his talons, but he barely even

05:34:45.240 --> 05:34:46.380
glanced down at them.

05:34:46.439 --> 05:34:49.500
Getting angry will only make me feel

05:34:49.500 --> 05:34:49.919
worse.

05:34:49.979 --> 05:34:51.659
Willow said firmly.

05:34:51.720 --> 05:34:56.580
But I am upset, and just really, really

05:34:56.580 --> 05:34:57.000
sad.

05:34:57.060 --> 05:34:59.939
She shook herself from head to tail.

05:35:00.000 --> 05:35:01.860
That's what this is.

05:35:01.919 --> 05:35:03.240
I'm sad.

05:35:03.360 --> 05:35:06.779
Well, I am pleased for you that you're

05:35:06.779 --> 05:35:08.520
that good at choose your own emotion

05:35:08.520 --> 05:35:10.139
Sundew said.

05:35:10.200 --> 05:35:11.040
I'm definitely mad.

05:35:11.159 --> 05:35:14.220
And I can't just smush that into feeling

05:35:14.220 --> 05:35:17.520
sad or something else instead, so you can

05:35:17.520 --> 05:35:19.139
go eat chocolate or whatever being sad

05:35:19.139 --> 05:35:19.860
leads to.

05:35:19.919 --> 05:35:21.779
I'm going to yell at the queen.

05:35:21.840 --> 05:35:24.419
Willow shot her a troubled look.

05:35:24.479 --> 05:35:26.759
I hope you won't be too mean.

05:35:26.819 --> 05:35:29.520
We need her on our side for the war

05:35:29.520 --> 05:35:29.880
ahead.

05:35:30.000 --> 05:35:33.240
I mean, I want her to keep listening to

05:35:33.240 --> 05:35:34.619
us to you.

05:35:34.680 --> 05:35:37.319
So I just hope you won't drive her away.

05:35:37.380 --> 05:35:40.860
She still talks to Belladonna after all

05:35:40.860 --> 05:35:43.680
this time, Sundew said, and she's a

05:35:43.680 --> 05:35:44.040
queen.

05:35:44.159 --> 05:35:45.900
She should be tough enough to handle it.

05:35:45.959 --> 05:35:48.540
Their trip back to the village seemed

05:35:48.540 --> 05:35:50.759
faster than their trip out, partly

05:35:50.759 --> 05:35:52.259
because they were able to move much more

05:35:52.259 --> 05:35:54.599
quickly through the den of vipers, and

05:35:54.599 --> 05:35:56.220
partly because this time they went around

05:35:56.220 --> 05:35:58.560
the other edge of the lake, which was

05:35:58.560 --> 05:36:00.540
lined with sharp marsh reeds and cobra

05:36:00.540 --> 05:36:02.639
lilies, but nothing that actually managed

05:36:02.639 --> 05:36:03.900
to catch them.

05:36:03.959 --> 05:36:06.779
They reached Queen Sequoia's tree palace

05:36:06.779 --> 05:36:07.979
shortly after nightfall.

05:36:08.040 --> 05:36:10.860
Sundew's Leafsby kept picking up strange

05:36:10.860 --> 05:36:13.319
murmurs from the jungle around Willows

05:36:13.319 --> 05:36:13.799
Village.

05:36:13.860 --> 05:36:15.180
Trouble.

05:36:15.299 --> 05:36:18.119
They'd whisper one moment, and then the

05:36:18.119 --> 05:36:18.419
next.

05:36:18.599 --> 05:36:19.979
All is well.

05:36:20.040 --> 05:36:22.860
She wound her mind through the roots and

05:36:22.860 --> 05:36:24.959
whispers, but she couldn't pin down what

05:36:24.959 --> 05:36:27.000
they were feeling or worrying about.

05:36:27.060 --> 05:36:29.700
All is well, all is well.

05:36:29.759 --> 05:36:31.500
Dangerous coming.

05:36:31.560 --> 05:36:32.759
All is well.

05:36:32.819 --> 05:36:35.819
She shivered and pulled her mind back.

05:36:35.880 --> 05:36:38.700
It didn't make sense, so she'd have to

05:36:38.700 --> 05:36:40.139
ignore it for a while until it did.

05:36:40.200 --> 05:36:42.840
Trees could be ridiculously maddening

05:36:42.840 --> 05:36:43.139
sometimes.

05:36:43.200 --> 05:36:46.619
Hawthorne had pulled his wings in close

05:36:46.619 --> 05:36:48.840
and gone quiet as they entered the

05:36:48.840 --> 05:36:49.979
perimeter of the village.

05:36:50.040 --> 05:36:53.220
He kept looking up at the trees, perhaps

05:36:53.220 --> 05:36:55.139
sensing the leaf wings had come out to

05:36:55.139 --> 05:36:56.040
watch them pass by.

05:36:56.099 --> 05:36:58.860
Sunday hadn't seen any sign of more

05:36:58.860 --> 05:37:01.560
vipers beyond the 2 at his feet, but she

05:37:01.560 --> 05:37:02.700
wondered if they were out there somewhere

05:37:02.700 --> 05:37:03.180
too.

05:37:03.240 --> 05:37:06.240
A small deadly army trailing along behind

05:37:06.240 --> 05:37:06.840
their leader.

05:37:06.900 --> 05:37:10.139
They flew up to the throne room and found

05:37:10.139 --> 05:37:12.479
Hazel there, pacing in a circle around

05:37:12.479 --> 05:37:14.819
tsunami, who was lying down with her eyes

05:37:14.819 --> 05:37:17.159
closed and her front talons clasped.

05:37:17.220 --> 05:37:19.319
If the sea wing was asleep.

05:37:19.380 --> 05:37:20.880
She didn't look very peaceful.

05:37:20.939 --> 05:37:23.520
Her brow was furrowed, and her tail

05:37:23.520 --> 05:37:25.860
twitched furiously, as though she might

05:37:25.860 --> 05:37:27.180
be lashing it inside her dream.

05:37:27.240 --> 05:37:30.959
They landed as quietly as they could, and

05:37:30.959 --> 05:37:32.040
Willow signaled.

05:37:32.099 --> 05:37:33.119
What in the world?

05:37:33.119 --> 05:37:34.380
to Hazel.

05:37:34.500 --> 05:37:37.439
She said she could communicate with a

05:37:37.439 --> 05:37:40.380
distant kingdom somehow, Hazel whispered

05:37:40.380 --> 05:37:41.520
hurrying over to them.

05:37:41.580 --> 05:37:43.860
I have no idea what she's doing.

05:37:43.979 --> 05:37:46.319
Maybe all the dragons over there are

05:37:46.319 --> 05:37:46.860
delusional.

05:37:46.979 --> 05:37:48.959
Or magic.

05:37:49.020 --> 05:37:50.580
Cricket breathed.

05:37:50.700 --> 05:37:52.799
Where's your great grandmother?

05:37:52.860 --> 05:37:54.000
Sundu asked.

05:37:54.060 --> 05:37:56.880
She left with Belladonna and half the

05:37:56.880 --> 05:37:58.860
village, Hazel said.

05:37:58.860 --> 05:38:01.380
They're at the snarling river by now, I'm

05:38:01.380 --> 05:38:01.560
sure.

05:38:01.680 --> 05:38:04.200
She picked up a book from the throne

05:38:04.200 --> 05:38:06.659
fiddled with it for a moment, then put it

05:38:06.659 --> 05:38:06.900
back.

05:38:06.959 --> 05:38:10.319
I haven't heard anything, hoping for a

05:38:10.319 --> 05:38:10.979
messenger soon.

05:38:11.040 --> 05:38:12.299
What did you find?

05:38:12.360 --> 05:38:16.200
We found Hawthorne, Willow said

05:38:16.200 --> 05:38:18.299
indicating the old dragon.

05:38:18.360 --> 05:38:21.599
And he does have an antidote, but we need

05:38:21.599 --> 05:38:22.919
to test it to make sure it works.

05:38:23.040 --> 05:38:25.380
As quickly as possible.

05:38:25.439 --> 05:38:26.700
Sundu agreed.

05:38:26.759 --> 05:38:29.279
So we need a hive wing?

05:38:29.340 --> 05:38:31.080
Hazel asked sharply.

05:38:31.139 --> 05:38:33.419
She climbed onto the throne and tapped

05:38:33.419 --> 05:38:35.040
the small gong hanging above it.

05:38:35.099 --> 05:38:36.840
Then let's get one.

05:38:36.900 --> 05:38:39.540
Three guards came swooping in from the

05:38:39.540 --> 05:38:40.200
level above them.

05:38:40.259 --> 05:38:43.439
Go to the snarling river, Hazel

05:38:43.439 --> 05:38:43.979
commanded.

05:38:44.040 --> 05:38:46.319
Find the queen and find out whether

05:38:46.319 --> 05:38:47.759
Wasp's army is there yet.

05:38:47.819 --> 05:38:50.880
If so, capture a hive wing on his or her

05:38:50.880 --> 05:38:51.840
own and bring it.

05:38:52.860 --> 05:38:55.080
She hesitated for a moment, her eyes

05:38:55.080 --> 05:38:56.759
scanning the village out the window.

05:38:56.819 --> 05:38:59.400
Bring it to the Hemlock Grove on the

05:38:59.400 --> 05:39:01.560
banks of the Gullet River as fast as you

05:39:01.560 --> 05:39:01.740
can.

05:39:01.799 --> 05:39:05.639
I want to go too, Metal demanded.

05:39:05.700 --> 05:39:08.040
She dropped the chest and flopped herself

05:39:08.040 --> 05:39:09.419
loose from the loops of vines.

05:39:09.479 --> 05:39:12.060
I want to abduct a hive wing.

05:39:12.119 --> 05:39:13.500
I want to be where the fighting is.

05:39:13.560 --> 05:39:17.099
You may go with them, Hazel said.

05:39:17.159 --> 05:39:19.439
You can explain everything to the queen.

05:39:19.500 --> 05:39:21.959
The guards bowed and flew off with

05:39:21.959 --> 05:39:22.500
Nettle.

05:39:22.560 --> 05:39:25.080
Their flashing scales quickly swallowed

05:39:25.080 --> 05:39:26.220
by the darkness outside.

05:39:26.279 --> 05:39:29.340
Hazel hopped down from the throne and

05:39:29.340 --> 05:39:31.740
untied the vines around the chest so she

05:39:31.740 --> 05:39:32.279
could look inside.

05:39:32.340 --> 05:39:34.020
This is it?

05:39:34.080 --> 05:39:36.540
She asked, looking up at Hawthorne.

05:39:36.599 --> 05:39:38.700
Will this be enough?

05:39:38.759 --> 05:39:41.819
It depends on how we give it to them, he

05:39:41.819 --> 05:39:42.060
said.

05:39:42.119 --> 05:39:44.819
Ideally, they would all eat a piece at

05:39:44.819 --> 05:39:45.540
least this big.

05:39:45.599 --> 05:39:48.479
He held up his claws to indicate a small

05:39:48.479 --> 05:39:48.959
cube.

05:39:49.080 --> 05:39:51.479
But it might work if we could get it into

05:39:51.479 --> 05:39:52.259
their water supply.

05:39:52.319 --> 05:39:54.779
Sundu shook her head.

05:39:54.840 --> 05:39:57.360
We need a way to give the whole army the

05:39:57.360 --> 05:40:00.240
antidote at once before a wasp realizes

05:40:00.240 --> 05:40:00.840
what's happening.

05:40:00.959 --> 05:40:03.180
Otherwise, she'll stop them from taking

05:40:03.180 --> 05:40:04.619
it the moment she notices.

05:40:04.680 --> 05:40:06.959
She frowned at the pile of roots.

05:40:07.020 --> 05:40:09.840
She knew the jungle was enormous and

05:40:09.840 --> 05:40:11.939
probably contained 100s of plans she'd

05:40:11.939 --> 05:40:12.540
never encountered.

05:40:12.599 --> 05:40:15.599
But she was still a little surprised that

05:40:15.599 --> 05:40:17.459
the heart of salvation didn't look more

05:40:17.459 --> 05:40:17.819
familiar.

05:40:17.880 --> 05:40:21.360
Oh, Cricket said suddenly.

05:40:21.419 --> 05:40:24.720
What if, would it work if we burn it, and

05:40:24.720 --> 05:40:25.740
they breathe in the smoke?

05:40:25.860 --> 05:40:29.340
Hawthorne scrunched up his snout. thinking

05:40:29.340 --> 05:40:30.720
maybe.

05:40:30.840 --> 05:40:33.419
We could set the whole army free that way

05:40:33.419 --> 05:40:33.900
couldn't we?

05:40:34.020 --> 05:40:36.959
Cricket adjusted her glasses and padded

05:40:36.959 --> 05:40:38.279
bumblebee absentmindedly.

05:40:38.340 --> 05:40:41.220
The dragonette had just woken up and was

05:40:41.220 --> 05:40:42.659
trying to clamber out of the sling

05:40:42.659 --> 05:40:43.919
babbling to herself.

05:40:43.919 --> 05:40:46.860
I would think we'd need more than this.

05:40:46.919 --> 05:40:48.240
Hazel said.

05:40:48.299 --> 05:40:50.759
What if we plant a few of these and get

05:40:50.759 --> 05:40:52.619
our most powerful leaf speakers to grow

05:40:52.619 --> 05:40:54.840
them as quickly as possible, so we'll

05:40:54.840 --> 05:40:55.799
have as much as we need.

05:40:55.860 --> 05:40:58.740
Hawthorne reached past her and gently

05:40:58.740 --> 05:40:59.759
closed the chest.

05:40:59.819 --> 05:41:02.759
I'd wait to see if it works on dragons

05:41:02.759 --> 05:41:03.119
first.

05:41:03.180 --> 05:41:05.819
The heart of salvation is rather a pain

05:41:05.819 --> 05:41:07.380
to uproot once it takes hold.

05:41:07.439 --> 05:41:09.659
You wouldn't want to overrun your village

05:41:09.659 --> 05:41:10.439
with it for nothing.

05:41:10.500 --> 05:41:12.959
Keep a few aside for planting.

05:41:13.020 --> 05:41:15.360
The rest should be enough for the army

05:41:15.360 --> 05:41:17.520
and we can grow more for the rest of the

05:41:17.520 --> 05:41:18.240
hives later.

05:41:18.299 --> 05:41:21.900
Hazel lifted one eyebrow with a wooden

05:41:21.900 --> 05:41:24.000
egg wrapped carefully in its sling across

05:41:24.000 --> 05:41:24.540
his chest.

05:41:24.599 --> 05:41:26.880
She opened her mouth to argue with them

05:41:26.880 --> 05:41:29.580
but just then, an abrupt snort from

05:41:29.580 --> 05:41:30.840
tsunami made them all jump.

05:41:30.900 --> 05:41:33.840
The blue dragon let out a hiss.

05:41:33.900 --> 05:41:38.220
And then grumbled, fine, but I'm still

05:41:38.220 --> 05:41:38.700
head of school.

05:41:38.759 --> 05:41:41.400
Yeah, tell him hugs to him too.

05:41:41.459 --> 05:41:43.979
And no, the cows are not bigger and more

05:41:43.979 --> 05:41:44.700
delicious over here.

05:41:44.759 --> 05:41:45.959
Bye.

05:41:46.020 --> 05:41:49.560
She snorted again, rolled over, and sat

05:41:49.560 --> 05:41:51.299
up, blinking and rubbing her eyes.

05:41:51.360 --> 05:41:53.459
Whew, she said.

05:41:53.520 --> 05:41:54.959
I'll never get used to that.

05:41:55.020 --> 05:41:57.419
What did you just do?

05:41:57.540 --> 05:41:59.340
Cricket asked eagerly.

05:41:59.400 --> 05:42:04.919
It's, I, Sandu noticed tsunami slipping

05:42:04.919 --> 05:42:06.180
something into a pouch behind her front

05:42:06.180 --> 05:42:08.700
leg, something she clearly wasn't

05:42:08.700 --> 05:42:09.659
comfortable telling them about.

05:42:09.720 --> 05:42:13.919
I was sort of talking to a few of my

05:42:13.919 --> 05:42:15.419
friends back on the other continent.

05:42:15.479 --> 05:42:17.819
Oh my goodness, how?

05:42:17.880 --> 05:42:20.400
With distant kingdoms magic?

05:42:20.520 --> 05:42:21.540
Cricket asked.

05:42:21.599 --> 05:42:23.040
Yep.

05:42:23.099 --> 05:42:26.040
Tsunami said, flicking her wings back.

05:42:26.099 --> 05:42:27.720
She looked troubled.

05:42:27.720 --> 05:42:28.979
Hard to explain.

05:42:29.040 --> 05:42:32.040
Anyway, they didn't have any particularly

05:42:32.040 --> 05:42:34.740
helpful ideas, but Moon seems really sure

05:42:34.740 --> 05:42:36.360
that there must be a way for you to get

05:42:36.360 --> 05:42:36.540
there.

05:42:36.599 --> 05:42:38.580
She rubbed her forehead.

05:42:38.639 --> 05:42:40.799
Something about a prophecy?

05:42:40.860 --> 05:42:43.919
Have I mentioned that I hate prophecies?

05:42:43.979 --> 05:42:47.099
She had a prophecy about us?

05:42:47.159 --> 05:42:48.119
Cricket yelped.

05:42:48.180 --> 05:42:49.020
What was it?

05:42:49.080 --> 05:42:49.979
What's going to happen?

05:42:50.040 --> 05:42:54.840
No, tsunami said, pointing a stern claw

05:42:54.840 --> 05:42:55.080
at her.

05:42:55.139 --> 05:42:56.759
Do not get excited.

05:42:56.880 --> 05:42:59.580
Prophecies are terrible and annoying.

05:42:59.639 --> 05:43:02.580
And this one sounds like a pile of wet

05:43:02.580 --> 05:43:04.919
seaweed to me, because there's no way you

05:43:04.919 --> 05:43:05.759
can all get over there.

05:43:05.819 --> 05:43:08.040
Claire's side did it?

05:43:08.159 --> 05:43:09.479
Willow pointed out.

05:43:09.540 --> 05:43:12.659
She wasn't a sea wing, but she crossed

05:43:12.659 --> 05:43:14.220
the ocean safely somehow.

05:43:14.279 --> 05:43:16.860
They all looked back at tsunami.

05:43:16.919 --> 05:43:19.799
I guess that's true, she said

05:43:19.799 --> 05:43:20.340
doubtfully.

05:43:20.400 --> 05:43:22.319
I have no idea how, though.

05:43:22.380 --> 05:43:24.840
Maybe there's a clue in the book.

05:43:24.900 --> 05:43:27.779
Willow said, or lean towards sundew.

05:43:27.840 --> 05:43:29.340
Can we look at it?

05:43:29.400 --> 05:43:31.380
Maybe there's something in there that

05:43:31.380 --> 05:43:32.759
will tell us how she got here?

05:43:32.819 --> 05:43:35.939
I read the whole thing, and did notice

05:43:35.939 --> 05:43:39.119
anything like that, Sundew said, but she

05:43:39.119 --> 05:43:41.040
pulled it out of its pouch and unwrapped

05:43:41.040 --> 05:43:41.340
it anyway.

05:43:41.400 --> 05:43:44.279
The faded blue cover and thin pages

05:43:44.279 --> 05:43:46.380
looked even more ancient in the glow from

05:43:46.380 --> 05:43:47.400
the firefly lamps.

05:43:47.459 --> 05:43:50.700
You can check for yourself, but it

05:43:50.700 --> 05:43:51.840
doesn't matter if you don't find

05:43:51.840 --> 05:43:52.380
anything.

05:43:52.439 --> 05:43:54.599
The leaf wings aren't going anywhere.

05:43:54.659 --> 05:43:57.060
I'm staying right here and fighting for

05:43:57.060 --> 05:43:59.459
our place on this continent, no matter

05:43:59.459 --> 05:44:00.479
what WASP does.

05:44:00.540 --> 05:44:04.139
And the antidote will work, Cricket

05:44:04.139 --> 05:44:06.360
chimed in, so we won't have to run away

05:44:06.360 --> 05:44:09.540
although, I mean, I'd love to see the

05:44:09.540 --> 05:44:12.119
distant kingdom someday, if there is a

05:44:12.119 --> 05:44:13.080
way to get across the ocean.

05:44:13.200 --> 05:44:16.020
Hazel glanced out the window.

05:44:16.080 --> 05:44:19.439
The sky was fully dark by now, and the

05:44:19.439 --> 05:44:21.060
jungle was alive with the sounds of busy

05:44:21.060 --> 05:44:23.639
insects, grumbling frogs and night

05:44:23.639 --> 05:44:24.240
predators.

05:44:24.299 --> 05:44:27.240
Let's get to the gullet river, and hope

05:44:27.240 --> 05:44:29.279
the guards return soon, she said.

05:44:29.340 --> 05:44:31.680
Tsunami, you study the book in the

05:44:31.680 --> 05:44:35.040
meanwhile, Sundu, Cricket, Hawthorne, and

05:44:35.040 --> 05:44:35.880
Willow, come with me.

05:44:35.939 --> 05:44:39.000
She opened the chest and picked out 2

05:44:39.000 --> 05:44:40.799
pieces of the heart of salvation route.

05:44:40.919 --> 05:44:42.659
Not me?

05:44:42.720 --> 05:44:44.040
Mandrake started.

05:44:44.099 --> 05:44:45.299
I'll just...

05:44:45.299 --> 05:44:46.799
Wait here then.

05:44:46.860 --> 05:44:48.959
We'll be back soon.

05:44:49.020 --> 05:44:50.279
Sundew said.

05:44:50.400 --> 05:44:53.040
There was no one at the Hemlock Grove

05:44:53.040 --> 05:44:53.880
when they arrived.

05:44:53.939 --> 05:44:56.819
Hawthorn lay down on the grass, cradling

05:44:56.819 --> 05:44:58.860
his wooden egg between his front talons

05:44:58.860 --> 05:45:01.259
and one of his snakes slithered up to

05:45:01.259 --> 05:45:02.159
coil around his neck.

05:45:02.220 --> 05:45:05.459
Cricket watched Hazel pace between the

05:45:05.459 --> 05:45:07.380
trees for a moment, and then she turned

05:45:07.380 --> 05:45:08.340
to Hawthorn.

05:45:08.400 --> 05:45:12.000
Hey, I was wondering something, she

05:45:12.000 --> 05:45:12.240
said.

05:45:12.299 --> 05:45:15.060
You, Sundew teased.

05:45:15.119 --> 05:45:15.599
Really?

05:45:15.659 --> 05:45:17.939
Cricket ignored her.

05:45:18.000 --> 05:45:21.000
According to the legend of the hive, she

05:45:21.000 --> 05:45:21.299
said.

05:45:21.360 --> 05:45:23.819
The plant originally worked on everything

05:45:23.819 --> 05:45:24.419
right?

05:45:24.599 --> 05:45:28.439
Bees, ants, lions, birds, snakes

05:45:28.439 --> 05:45:28.680
anything.

05:45:28.740 --> 05:45:31.740
But it seems like Queen Wasp can only use

05:45:31.740 --> 05:45:32.819
it on hive wings.

05:45:32.880 --> 05:45:35.580
I mean, she must have tried injecting the

05:45:35.580 --> 05:45:36.900
silk wings too, don't you think?

05:45:36.959 --> 05:45:39.180
Maybe even a leaf wing at some point.

05:45:39.240 --> 05:45:41.880
So why doesn't a mind control work on

05:45:41.880 --> 05:45:42.479
other tribes?

05:45:42.540 --> 05:45:46.080
That is an excellent question.

05:45:46.139 --> 05:45:48.299
Hawthorne said approvingly.

05:45:48.360 --> 05:45:51.479
Thank you, Cricket said with delight

05:45:51.479 --> 05:45:52.500
fluttering her wings.

05:45:52.560 --> 05:45:56.400
When I found the plant, it was barely

05:45:56.400 --> 05:45:59.459
hanging on, he said, there was so little

05:45:59.459 --> 05:46:02.939
left, cut off from sunlight, and slowly

05:46:02.939 --> 05:46:03.540
wasting away.

05:46:03.599 --> 05:46:05.520
I brought it into the sun.

05:46:05.580 --> 05:46:07.799
I nursed it back to health.

05:46:07.860 --> 05:46:11.459
And while I did, I used my leaf speak on

05:46:11.459 --> 05:46:11.639
it.

05:46:11.700 --> 05:46:13.860
I trained it, essentially.

05:46:13.919 --> 05:46:16.680
I altered it so that it would only work

05:46:16.680 --> 05:46:17.700
on hive wings.

05:46:17.700 --> 05:46:20.040
Those would be the minds it was drawn

05:46:20.040 --> 05:46:20.279
to.

05:46:20.340 --> 05:46:23.880
I wasn't sure how well I'd succeeded, but

05:46:23.880 --> 05:46:25.020
it seems I did well enough.

05:46:25.080 --> 05:46:28.200
He looked horribly proud of himself.

05:46:28.259 --> 05:46:30.720
Sunday wanted to scratch his face off.

05:46:30.779 --> 05:46:33.720
How could he still be pleased about what

05:46:33.720 --> 05:46:36.959
he did, after all this time, and all the

05:46:36.959 --> 05:46:38.040
damage he'd caused.

05:46:38.099 --> 05:46:40.680
Oh, Cricket said.

05:46:40.740 --> 05:46:42.720
Her wings sank to the ground.

05:46:42.779 --> 05:46:46.439
I Guess that's very impressive.

05:46:46.500 --> 05:46:48.360
It is.

05:46:48.419 --> 05:46:49.500
He assured her.

05:46:49.560 --> 05:46:51.360
Not many dragons could do it.

05:46:51.479 --> 05:46:54.240
It occurred to Sundoo that they should

05:46:54.240 --> 05:46:55.560
tell Hazel the whole story.

05:46:55.680 --> 05:46:58.200
The future queen had no idea what her

05:46:58.200 --> 05:47:00.540
great grandmother and Hawthorne had done

05:47:00.540 --> 05:47:01.919
but this wasn't the time.

05:47:01.979 --> 05:47:04.619
She could hear muffled yells getting

05:47:04.619 --> 05:47:05.459
closer and closer.

05:47:05.520 --> 05:47:08.639
The leaf wing guards appeared in the

05:47:08.639 --> 05:47:11.159
treetops, carrying a hive wing prisoner

05:47:11.159 --> 05:47:12.900
who was blindfolded and tied up with

05:47:12.900 --> 05:47:15.360
Strangler vines like an insect in a

05:47:15.360 --> 05:47:15.900
cocoon.

05:47:15.959 --> 05:47:18.240
They flew him down to the damp earth by

05:47:18.240 --> 05:47:20.819
the riverside, and Nettle threw him at

05:47:20.819 --> 05:47:22.319
Hazel's feet, grinning.

05:47:22.439 --> 05:47:25.500
That was great, she said.

05:47:25.560 --> 05:47:28.319
Sundu wasn't sure she'd ever seen nettles

05:47:28.319 --> 05:47:28.740
so happy.

05:47:28.799 --> 05:47:31.979
It was, quite frankly, very unsettling.

05:47:32.040 --> 05:47:34.619
I want more missions like that.

05:47:34.680 --> 05:47:36.959
But Hazel wasn't smiling.

05:47:37.020 --> 05:47:39.540
She took a step back and gazed down at

05:47:39.540 --> 05:47:41.580
the hive wing, then up at Nettle.

05:47:41.639 --> 05:47:44.279
I guess this means wasp and the hive

05:47:44.279 --> 05:47:45.360
wings are at the river already.

05:47:45.419 --> 05:47:48.119
Oh, yes, we are.

05:47:48.180 --> 05:47:50.700
The hive wing suddenly snapped.

05:47:50.759 --> 05:47:53.040
His fangs glistened in the moonlight.

05:47:53.099 --> 05:47:56.159
Even without seeing his pale white eyes

05:47:56.159 --> 05:47:59.340
Sundu recognized the creepy extra layer

05:47:59.340 --> 05:48:02.459
to his voice, Wasp was inside his mind

05:48:02.459 --> 05:48:04.319
using his mouth to speak to them.

05:48:04.439 --> 05:48:08.639
We're here, Leaf Wing, and this time

05:48:08.639 --> 05:48:10.080
we'll make sure to finish what we

05:48:10.080 --> 05:48:10.439
started.

05:48:10.500 --> 05:48:12.240
You're all dead.

05:48:12.299 --> 05:48:15.659
The hive wing twisted and writhed, trying

05:48:15.659 --> 05:48:17.400
to drag the blindfold off his eyes.

05:48:17.459 --> 05:48:20.220
Nettle put her front talons on his ears

05:48:20.220 --> 05:48:22.860
and pinned him to the ground, ignoring

05:48:22.860 --> 05:48:23.459
his flailing.

05:48:23.520 --> 05:48:26.099
There were 1000s of hive wings on the

05:48:26.099 --> 05:48:28.500
other side of the river, she said in a

05:48:28.500 --> 05:48:30.900
low voice, and we could see more flying

05:48:30.900 --> 05:48:31.139
in.

05:48:31.200 --> 05:48:34.860
They're just standing there. row after

05:48:34.860 --> 05:48:37.200
row of them, staring at the jungle with

05:48:37.200 --> 05:48:38.159
creepy wide eyes.

05:48:38.220 --> 05:48:40.380
It looks like they're waiting for

05:48:40.380 --> 05:48:40.560
something.

05:48:40.619 --> 05:48:42.959
The rest of the tribe?

05:48:42.959 --> 05:48:44.220
Cricket guest.

05:48:44.279 --> 05:48:46.500
It would take longer for the dragons from

05:48:46.500 --> 05:48:48.599
mantis hive and cicada hive to get here.

05:48:48.659 --> 05:48:51.180
Maybe she wants them all in place before

05:48:51.180 --> 05:48:51.900
attacking.

05:48:51.959 --> 05:48:54.419
Did you see Queen Sequoia?

05:48:54.479 --> 05:48:56.099
Hazel asked softly.

05:48:56.159 --> 05:48:58.200
Is Blue with her?

05:48:58.259 --> 05:48:59.580
Cricket chimed in.

05:48:59.639 --> 05:49:01.860
Yes, said Nettle.

05:49:01.919 --> 05:49:04.319
She has the flame silk and the other

05:49:04.319 --> 05:49:06.240
massively annoying silk wing.

05:49:06.299 --> 05:49:07.619
They're working on...

05:49:07.619 --> 05:49:10.139
Hazel cut her off by putting her talon

05:49:10.139 --> 05:49:11.700
around nettle's snout.

05:49:11.759 --> 05:49:13.500
She indicated the hive wing.

05:49:13.500 --> 05:49:16.259
Even with his ears covered, they couldn't

05:49:16.259 --> 05:49:18.599
risk Wasp overhearing Queen Sequoia's

05:49:18.599 --> 05:49:18.959
plans.

05:49:19.020 --> 05:49:21.779
Nettle scowled down at him and nodded.

05:49:21.900 --> 05:49:25.139
Let's do this quickly, Sundu said.

05:49:25.200 --> 05:49:27.479
She held out one talon for the heart of

05:49:27.479 --> 05:49:28.259
salvation route.

05:49:28.319 --> 05:49:31.200
Hazel used her claws to slice off a piece

05:49:31.200 --> 05:49:34.139
about as big as an eyeball, which was an

05:49:34.139 --> 05:49:35.759
image sundu immediately regretted

05:49:35.759 --> 05:49:37.979
conjuring, and passed it to her.

05:49:38.040 --> 05:49:41.040
Nettle lifted the prisoner's snout and

05:49:41.040 --> 05:49:42.119
pride is jaw open.

05:49:42.180 --> 05:49:45.000
He tried to bite her, but her grip was

05:49:45.000 --> 05:49:45.360
strong.

05:49:45.419 --> 05:49:48.299
Sundew stuffed the root into his mouth

05:49:48.299 --> 05:49:50.880
and Nettle slammed it closed, holding it

05:49:50.880 --> 05:49:52.020
shut until he swallowed.

05:49:52.080 --> 05:49:54.479
Finally, she let go and stepped back.

05:49:54.540 --> 05:49:58.080
That little worm cricket is here, isn't

05:49:58.080 --> 05:49:58.259
she?

05:49:58.319 --> 05:50:01.680
The dragon spat immediately, the one who

05:50:01.680 --> 05:50:04.439
thinks she's so very clever, with her

05:50:04.439 --> 05:50:06.419
pamphlets and graffiti and rumors.

05:50:06.479 --> 05:50:08.700
Guess what, cricket?

05:50:08.759 --> 05:50:09.540
I figured it out.

05:50:09.599 --> 05:50:11.580
I know who your father is.

05:50:11.639 --> 05:50:16.380
And he's mine, all mine, and I could kill

05:50:16.380 --> 05:50:19.139
him in a heartbeat if I wanted to, or I

05:50:19.139 --> 05:50:20.040
could let you meet him.

05:50:20.220 --> 05:50:21.419
Would you like that?

05:50:21.479 --> 05:50:24.299
Wouldn't you like to come back to wasp

05:50:24.299 --> 05:50:26.880
hives, so I...

05:50:27.000 --> 05:50:29.639
The hive wing trailed off.

05:50:29.700 --> 05:50:32.459
His whole body went limp, and his head

05:50:32.459 --> 05:50:33.840
lolled back onto the grass.

05:50:33.900 --> 05:50:36.779
Sunder reached out and took one of

05:50:36.779 --> 05:50:38.220
Willow's talent between hers.

05:50:38.279 --> 05:50:40.979
She could feel Willow's heartbeat in her

05:50:40.979 --> 05:50:41.340
palm.

05:50:41.400 --> 05:50:44.639
For once, it was as fast as sundews.

05:50:44.759 --> 05:50:47.099
Hazel turned to Hawthorn.

05:50:47.159 --> 05:50:48.779
Does that mean it worked?

05:50:48.840 --> 05:50:49.619
She asked.

05:50:49.680 --> 05:50:51.779
I think...

05:50:51.779 --> 05:50:53.340
Maybe?

05:50:53.340 --> 05:50:54.119
he said.

05:50:54.240 --> 05:50:58.439
The hive wing jerked once, twice, like a

05:50:58.439 --> 05:50:59.580
fish pulled up on land.

05:50:59.639 --> 05:51:02.220
He rolled on his side and gasped several

05:51:02.220 --> 05:51:04.740
times, as if there wasn't enough air in

05:51:04.740 --> 05:51:05.759
the world to breathe.

05:51:05.759 --> 05:51:08.340
What is happening?

05:51:08.459 --> 05:51:10.319
He croaked finally.

05:51:10.380 --> 05:51:11.639
Where am I?

05:51:11.700 --> 05:51:14.520
Why does everything smell wet?

05:51:14.639 --> 05:51:17.939
Cricket motioned to the others back

05:51:17.939 --> 05:51:20.459
crouched beside him, and removed his

05:51:20.459 --> 05:51:21.180
blindfold.

05:51:21.180 --> 05:51:23.939
From the shadows behind him, Sundew

05:51:23.939 --> 05:51:25.979
couldn't see his face, but she could hear

05:51:25.979 --> 05:51:26.939
the hitch in his voice.

05:51:27.000 --> 05:51:29.340
What's your name?

05:51:29.400 --> 05:51:30.360
Cricket asked him.

05:51:30.479 --> 05:51:32.639
Inch worm?

05:51:32.700 --> 05:51:33.599
He answered.

05:51:33.659 --> 05:51:35.340
From vinegaroon hive?

05:51:35.400 --> 05:51:36.599
Who are you?

05:51:36.720 --> 05:51:38.939
Cricket, she said.

05:51:39.000 --> 05:51:40.560
Cicada hive.

05:51:40.619 --> 05:51:41.580
How do you feel?

05:51:41.639 --> 05:51:43.799
He hesitated for a moment.

05:51:43.860 --> 05:51:45.540
Weird?

05:51:45.659 --> 05:51:47.040
Empty?

05:51:47.159 --> 05:51:49.740
And I seem to be all tied up.

05:51:49.799 --> 05:51:52.439
Do you know why you're here?

05:51:52.500 --> 05:51:54.659
No, he blurted.

05:51:54.720 --> 05:51:56.520
I don't even know where here is.

05:51:56.580 --> 05:52:00.119
Try to think back, Cricket said.

05:52:00.180 --> 05:52:01.979
You were going about your day in your

05:52:01.979 --> 05:52:04.319
hive when suddenly the queen was in your

05:52:04.319 --> 05:52:04.500
head.

05:52:04.560 --> 05:52:06.360
What did she make you do?

05:52:06.419 --> 05:52:09.900
Oh, he said.

05:52:09.959 --> 05:52:11.099
Right.

05:52:11.159 --> 05:52:12.299
The summons.

05:52:12.360 --> 05:52:14.459
I was getting glow where I'm ready for

05:52:14.459 --> 05:52:15.419
school.

05:52:15.479 --> 05:52:16.200
Glow worm.

05:52:16.259 --> 05:52:19.259
He tried to surge upright, but fell back

05:52:19.259 --> 05:52:20.639
straining against the vines.

05:52:20.759 --> 05:52:23.279
Is that your dragonette?

05:52:23.340 --> 05:52:25.740
Cricket said touching his shoulder with

05:52:25.740 --> 05:52:26.159
her wing.

05:52:26.220 --> 05:52:28.380
We'll make sure she's safe.

05:52:28.439 --> 05:52:29.159
Don't worry.

05:52:29.220 --> 05:52:33.659
She was summoned too, he said, his voice

05:52:33.659 --> 05:52:34.740
racked with worry.

05:52:34.799 --> 05:52:36.060
Everyone was.

05:52:36.119 --> 05:52:38.880
I think Wasp called the whole tribe.

05:52:38.939 --> 05:52:40.200
Are we going to war?

05:52:40.259 --> 05:52:42.299
My dragonette is out there.

05:52:42.360 --> 05:52:43.919
She doesn't know how to fight.

05:52:43.979 --> 05:52:45.119
I have to find her.

05:52:45.180 --> 05:52:46.919
He began struggling again.

05:52:47.040 --> 05:52:49.500
We are not going to war.

05:52:49.560 --> 05:52:50.759
Cricket said.

05:52:50.819 --> 05:52:51.959
We're going to stop it.

05:52:52.020 --> 05:52:54.900
If I untie you, will you help us stop

05:52:54.900 --> 05:52:55.080
it?

05:52:55.200 --> 05:52:57.299
Us?

05:52:57.299 --> 05:52:58.500
he said warily.

05:52:58.560 --> 05:53:01.380
Me, and the leaf wings.

05:53:01.439 --> 05:53:02.099
She said.

05:53:02.159 --> 05:53:04.139
You'd have to promise you wouldn't hurt

05:53:04.139 --> 05:53:05.340
any leaf wings.

05:53:05.400 --> 05:53:07.560
I promise, he said.

05:53:07.680 --> 05:53:10.139
I promise, I don't want to fight anyone.

05:53:10.200 --> 05:53:12.479
I just want to get glow worm and go

05:53:12.479 --> 05:53:12.779
home.

05:53:12.840 --> 05:53:16.560
That's what we want too, Cricket said.

05:53:16.619 --> 05:53:19.500
Sandu felt a jolt of familiar anger.

05:53:19.560 --> 05:53:21.360
Is that what we want?

05:53:21.419 --> 05:53:24.659
All the high wings get to go home and

05:53:24.659 --> 05:53:26.819
keep living their happy lives as though

05:53:26.819 --> 05:53:28.500
they didn't nearly destroy us.

05:53:28.560 --> 05:53:30.119
Where's the punishment?

05:53:30.180 --> 05:53:31.380
The justice.

05:53:31.439 --> 05:53:34.080
She knew what Blue would say.

05:53:34.139 --> 05:53:36.540
These hive wings are not the enemy.

05:53:36.599 --> 05:53:38.819
Queen Wasp is the enemy.

05:53:38.939 --> 05:53:40.380
Focus on her.

05:53:40.439 --> 05:53:43.319
But the hive wings had benefited from

05:53:43.319 --> 05:53:45.779
everything WASP did, and they never

05:53:45.779 --> 05:53:47.159
lifted a claw to stop her.

05:53:47.159 --> 05:53:49.259
They were part of the problem too.

05:53:49.319 --> 05:53:52.380
They needed to learn a lesson and atone

05:53:52.380 --> 05:53:54.360
not carry on as though nothing had

05:53:54.360 --> 05:53:54.900
happened.

05:53:54.900 --> 05:53:57.119
She didn't have a chance to say

05:53:57.119 --> 05:53:57.479
anything.

05:53:57.540 --> 05:54:00.060
Not that she had any idea what she would

05:54:00.060 --> 05:54:02.580
say, before Cricket was standing in front

05:54:02.580 --> 05:54:04.319
of Hazel, spreading her wings.

05:54:04.380 --> 05:54:08.340
I think it worked. she whispered, pushing

05:54:08.340 --> 05:54:08.939
up her glasses.

05:54:09.000 --> 05:54:10.740
WASP is gone.

05:54:10.860 --> 05:54:12.299
Hawthorne, you did it.

05:54:12.360 --> 05:54:13.020
He's free.

05:54:13.080 --> 05:54:17.340
Unless he's faking it, Nettle growled.

05:54:17.459 --> 05:54:20.939
I don't think he could, Willow said.

05:54:21.000 --> 05:54:23.759
And Wasp wouldn't miss a chance to be

05:54:23.759 --> 05:54:24.840
scary to my face.

05:54:24.900 --> 05:54:26.099
Cricket agreed.

05:54:26.159 --> 05:54:28.799
If she was in there, she'd show herself.

05:54:28.860 --> 05:54:30.479
Can we untie him?

05:54:30.540 --> 05:54:33.659
Let's get the antidote on its way first

05:54:33.659 --> 05:54:36.060
Hazel said, in her queenly voice.

05:54:36.119 --> 05:54:38.580
Nettle, I assume you want to go back to

05:54:38.580 --> 05:54:39.299
the front lines?

05:54:39.360 --> 05:54:41.400
Yes.

05:54:41.459 --> 05:54:43.439
Nettle hissed with glee.

05:54:43.500 --> 05:54:46.259
I'll go too, Sundoo said.

05:54:46.319 --> 05:54:48.599
She wanted to see for herself what they

05:54:48.599 --> 05:54:50.639
were facing, and if they were able to use

05:54:50.639 --> 05:54:51.599
the antidote.

05:54:51.659 --> 05:54:52.919
She wanted to see it work.

05:54:52.979 --> 05:54:55.919
She wanted to see Queen Wasp's reaction

05:54:55.919 --> 05:54:57.599
when all her power evaporated.

05:54:57.659 --> 05:54:59.400
Can I come?

05:54:59.459 --> 05:55:00.360
Cricket asked.

05:55:00.419 --> 05:55:01.500
To check on Blue?

05:55:01.560 --> 05:55:04.319
Very well, said Hazel.

05:55:04.439 --> 05:55:05.759
Willow and Hawthorne.

05:55:05.819 --> 05:55:07.560
You can help me figure out how to get

05:55:07.560 --> 05:55:09.360
this hive wing back to his dragonette.

05:55:09.419 --> 05:55:10.560
The 3 of you.

05:55:10.619 --> 05:55:12.959
Go collect the antidote and fly it to the

05:55:12.959 --> 05:55:15.000
queen, as fast as you can.

05:55:15.060 --> 05:55:17.939
We have no idea when WASP will decide

05:55:17.939 --> 05:55:18.779
it's time to attack.

05:55:18.840 --> 05:55:22.619
Sundu found herself starting to bow, and

05:55:22.619 --> 05:55:23.580
felt ridiculous.

05:55:23.639 --> 05:55:26.159
She had barely known Sequoia and Hazel

05:55:26.159 --> 05:55:28.740
for a day, and yet she kept instinctively

05:55:28.740 --> 05:55:30.360
treating them like real queens.

05:55:30.419 --> 05:55:33.360
But then, out of the corner of her eye.

05:55:33.419 --> 05:55:35.340
She caught Nettle doing the same thing.

05:55:35.459 --> 05:55:38.040
Nettle of all dragons.

05:55:38.099 --> 05:55:40.619
So maybe sundew wasn't that ridiculous

05:55:40.619 --> 05:55:41.159
after all.

05:55:41.220 --> 05:55:44.400
Willow grabbed one of her talons as

05:55:44.400 --> 05:55:45.540
Sundude took a step back.

05:55:45.599 --> 05:55:48.599
Please be careful, she said.

05:55:48.659 --> 05:55:51.060
Remember, you promised me you'd never

05:55:51.060 --> 05:55:51.299
die.

05:55:51.360 --> 05:55:54.540
She choked out a half sob, half laugh.

05:55:54.599 --> 05:55:58.919
You be careful too, Sundew said, wrapping

05:55:58.919 --> 05:56:00.599
her wings around Willow and pulling her

05:56:00.599 --> 05:56:00.959
clothes.

05:56:01.020 --> 05:56:02.759
I'll see you really soon.

05:56:02.819 --> 05:56:05.880
Like, immediately after we save the

05:56:05.880 --> 05:56:06.060
world.

05:56:06.180 --> 05:56:09.659
Willow laughed again, and then they let

05:56:09.659 --> 05:56:12.060
go of each other, and Sundu lifted into

05:56:12.060 --> 05:56:13.799
the air to follow Nettle and cricket.

05:56:13.860 --> 05:56:16.200
The war was waiting for them.

05:56:16.259 --> 05:56:19.500
And one small plant might be the only

05:56:19.500 --> 05:56:20.819
thing that could stop it.

05:56:20.880 --> 05:56:25.200
Part three.

05:56:25.319 --> 05:56:27.299
Leaves in a Storm.

05:56:27.360 --> 05:56:29.700
Chapter 18.

05:56:29.880 --> 05:56:34.860
I know something, Crickets sang, nudging

05:56:34.860 --> 05:56:36.419
Sundu's wing as they flew through the

05:56:36.419 --> 05:56:36.720
village.

05:56:36.779 --> 05:56:40.619
You know entirely too many things, Sundu

05:56:40.619 --> 05:56:42.419
observed, but you are very welcome to

05:56:42.419 --> 05:56:43.319
keep them all to yourself.

05:56:43.439 --> 05:56:47.220
I know who your one true love is, Cricket

05:56:47.220 --> 05:56:47.880
whispered.

05:56:47.939 --> 05:56:49.500
It's not mandrake.

05:56:49.560 --> 05:56:50.639
I knew it wasn't.

05:56:50.700 --> 05:56:54.000
Yes, because I told you that, Sundew

05:56:54.000 --> 05:56:54.540
snapped.

05:56:54.599 --> 05:56:55.799
You're very clever.

05:56:55.860 --> 05:56:59.220
Well, I just wanted to say I like her, and

05:56:59.220 --> 05:57:00.659
I like the look on your face when she

05:57:00.659 --> 05:57:01.139
talks to you.

05:57:01.200 --> 05:57:04.619
I am not even remotely interested in what

05:57:04.619 --> 05:57:07.680
you like, Sundu barked, landing on a

05:57:07.680 --> 05:57:08.939
branch behind Nettle.

05:57:09.000 --> 05:57:11.279
Cricket thumped down behind them, and

05:57:11.279 --> 05:57:12.720
they all hurried along in silence for a

05:57:12.720 --> 05:57:12.900
moment.

05:57:13.020 --> 05:57:17.099
But thank you, Sundu finally grumbled.

05:57:17.159 --> 05:57:20.639
I figured it out too, Nettle said

05:57:20.639 --> 05:57:21.540
suddenly from the lead.

05:57:21.599 --> 05:57:23.759
She swung her head around to glare at

05:57:23.759 --> 05:57:25.500
sundew and cricket before moving on.

05:57:25.560 --> 05:57:29.040
I don't understand falling for a sapwing

05:57:29.040 --> 05:57:31.799
at all, or when that could have possibly

05:57:31.799 --> 05:57:33.659
happened, but I also don't care.

05:57:33.720 --> 05:57:36.240
And as far as I'm concerned, not having

05:57:36.240 --> 05:57:37.979
you for a sister-in-law would be a

05:57:37.979 --> 05:57:39.060
stellar development.

05:57:39.119 --> 05:57:42.540
Well, not being related to you is one of

05:57:42.540 --> 05:57:44.819
my favorite things about her, Sundu

05:57:44.819 --> 05:57:45.659
growled back.

05:57:45.720 --> 05:57:48.779
Nettle harumped and hopped to the next

05:57:48.779 --> 05:57:49.560
tree.

05:57:49.619 --> 05:57:52.200
A dewy pine leaned hopefully toward her

05:57:52.200 --> 05:57:53.880
and she hissed fiercely at it.

05:57:53.939 --> 05:57:57.479
Sorry, Cricket whispered to Sundu.

05:57:57.540 --> 05:57:58.979
I didn't think she'd hear me.

05:57:59.040 --> 05:58:03.779
I have very sharp ears, Nettle declared.

05:58:03.840 --> 05:58:07.919
This conversation can be over now, Sundew

05:58:07.919 --> 05:58:08.580
suggested.

05:58:08.700 --> 05:58:10.979
She saw the tree palace up ahead and

05:58:10.979 --> 05:58:13.439
darted out in front, swinging out of the

05:58:13.439 --> 05:58:16.380
tree and flying down to it, inside.

05:58:16.439 --> 05:58:18.360
Tsunami had been joined by the other Sea

05:58:18.360 --> 05:58:21.060
Wing, Turtle, who looked much less queasy

05:58:21.060 --> 05:58:21.659
than he had before.

05:58:21.720 --> 05:58:24.720
They both had their phosphorescent scales

05:58:24.720 --> 05:58:26.880
lit up, and were leaning over the book of

05:58:26.880 --> 05:58:28.860
clear sight, studying each page.

05:58:28.919 --> 05:58:32.580
Mandrake came hurrying over as Sundew

05:58:32.580 --> 05:58:32.939
landed.

05:58:33.060 --> 05:58:34.259
Did it work?

05:58:34.319 --> 05:58:35.159
He asked.

05:58:35.220 --> 05:58:37.799
As far as we can tell, she said.

05:58:37.860 --> 05:58:40.500
She stepped into the loops of vines that

05:58:40.500 --> 05:58:42.299
Nettle had abandoned next to the chest

05:58:42.299 --> 05:58:44.099
and started tightening them around

05:58:44.099 --> 05:58:44.520
herself.

05:58:44.580 --> 05:58:47.279
We're taking this to Queen Sequoia now.

05:58:47.340 --> 05:58:51.000
We should leave a few here, Cricket said

05:58:51.000 --> 05:58:53.099
opening the chest and scooping out a

05:58:53.099 --> 05:58:54.060
talon full of roots.

05:58:54.119 --> 05:58:57.000
She glanced around for a moment, then

05:58:57.000 --> 05:58:58.680
went over to pile them on top of the

05:58:58.680 --> 05:58:58.979
throne.

05:58:59.040 --> 05:59:00.659
What about you?

05:59:00.720 --> 05:59:04.380
Sundu asked tsunami, as Nettle tied the

05:59:04.380 --> 05:59:06.119
other side of the looped vines around her

05:59:06.119 --> 05:59:06.540
shoulders.

05:59:06.599 --> 05:59:07.860
Any luck?

05:59:07.919 --> 05:59:10.439
The blue dragon sugar head.

05:59:10.560 --> 05:59:14.099
Nothing much about Pyria so far, but Moon

05:59:14.099 --> 05:59:16.380
said, a secret hides within their book.

05:59:16.439 --> 05:59:18.240
She did?

05:59:18.299 --> 05:59:19.319
Cricket asked.

05:59:19.380 --> 05:59:20.880
Was that part of the prophecy?

05:59:20.939 --> 05:59:24.419
Part of the gibberish, tsunami muttered.

05:59:24.479 --> 05:59:27.060
The big secret in there is that the hive

05:59:27.060 --> 05:59:28.740
wings have been lying about it for 100s

05:59:28.740 --> 05:59:30.840
of years, Sundew pointed out.

05:59:30.900 --> 05:59:32.819
That's got to be what that means.

05:59:32.880 --> 05:59:35.700
That all the prophecies about uniting

05:59:35.700 --> 05:59:37.380
under Queen Wasp were fake.

05:59:37.439 --> 05:59:41.459
Yeah, probably, tsunami said with a

05:59:41.459 --> 05:59:41.759
sigh.

05:59:41.819 --> 05:59:45.959
Let's go, Nettle said, hopping from foot

05:59:45.959 --> 05:59:46.380
to foot.

05:59:46.439 --> 05:59:48.540
Mandrake, you too.

05:59:48.599 --> 05:59:50.340
Not that you'll be useful, but you can at

05:59:50.340 --> 05:59:51.240
least try to look like it.

05:59:51.299 --> 05:59:53.340
Tsunami?

05:59:53.459 --> 05:59:54.840
Cricket said hesitantly.

05:59:54.900 --> 05:59:58.500
This is a lot to ask, but could I leave

05:59:58.500 --> 05:59:59.819
Bumblebee here with you?

05:59:59.880 --> 06:00:01.560
Uh, no.

06:00:01.680 --> 06:00:04.380
Bumblebee objected. throwing her arms

06:00:04.380 --> 06:00:05.400
around Cricket's neck.

06:00:05.459 --> 06:00:07.860
No be, no be, no.

06:00:07.919 --> 06:00:10.080
That does look like fun.

06:00:10.139 --> 06:00:12.000
Tsunami said wryly.

06:00:12.060 --> 06:00:13.680
Bumblebee.

06:00:13.740 --> 06:00:14.639
Be reasonable.

06:00:14.700 --> 06:00:16.740
Cricket yelled over her wails.

06:00:16.799 --> 06:00:19.259
There might be a war where I'm going.

06:00:19.319 --> 06:00:21.299
Dragons all stabbing each other.

06:00:21.360 --> 06:00:23.099
Very bad things.

06:00:23.159 --> 06:00:24.240
I don't want you near that.

06:00:24.299 --> 06:00:25.919
I want you here and safe.

06:00:25.979 --> 06:00:29.819
Stay be bad, Bumblebee argued.

06:00:29.880 --> 06:00:31.200
You save.

06:00:31.259 --> 06:00:33.779
I will be careful and I'll come back

06:00:33.779 --> 06:00:34.619
soon.

06:00:34.680 --> 06:00:35.400
I promise.

06:00:35.459 --> 06:00:38.700
She disentangled Bumblebee and the sling

06:00:38.700 --> 06:00:40.619
and handed them over to an extremely

06:00:40.619 --> 06:00:42.299
skeptical looking tsunami.

06:00:42.360 --> 06:00:44.099
Growl face.

06:00:44.159 --> 06:00:45.779
The dragonette shouted.

06:00:45.840 --> 06:00:47.939
Agna rah, rum, fum.

06:00:48.000 --> 06:00:49.860
I'm actually very cool.

06:00:49.919 --> 06:00:51.479
Tsunami pointed out to her.

06:00:51.540 --> 06:00:53.819
I run a school for dragonettes on my

06:00:53.819 --> 06:00:54.240
continent.

06:00:54.299 --> 06:00:56.520
Bigger, less noisy ones though.

06:00:56.639 --> 06:00:59.759
Bumblebee glowered at her, as though she

06:00:59.759 --> 06:01:01.619
did not find this information endearing

06:01:01.619 --> 06:01:02.040
whatsoever.

06:01:02.099 --> 06:01:04.139
Bye, little bug.

06:01:04.200 --> 06:01:06.000
Sendu called as they lifted off.

06:01:06.060 --> 06:01:06.900
Be good.

06:01:07.020 --> 06:01:12.000
Bumblebee shouted after her, which boded

06:01:12.000 --> 06:01:13.860
ill for the rest of tsunami's night.

06:01:13.919 --> 06:01:16.919
It turned out to be extremely annoying

06:01:16.919 --> 06:01:19.740
and unwieldy, and exhausting, and

06:01:19.740 --> 06:01:22.500
aggravating, to carry the antidote chest

06:01:22.500 --> 06:01:24.540
with nettle on the other side of it.

06:01:24.599 --> 06:01:27.180
Every time Sundew tried to go down, she

06:01:27.180 --> 06:01:28.380
went up.

06:01:28.439 --> 06:01:30.360
Every time sundew tried to hop over a

06:01:30.360 --> 06:01:32.759
stream, Nettle would hop the other way at

06:01:32.759 --> 06:01:35.159
the exact same time, and they'd both end

06:01:35.159 --> 06:01:36.060
up in the water.

06:01:36.119 --> 06:01:38.520
It was lucky that the chest was so sturdy

06:01:38.520 --> 06:01:40.500
and thick, or it would have been covered

06:01:40.500 --> 06:01:43.139
in dents and scratches in no time, or

06:01:43.139 --> 06:01:44.220
possibly collapsed.

06:01:44.279 --> 06:01:46.919
But it was also unlucky, because its

06:01:46.919 --> 06:01:49.619
sturdiness made it really stupidly

06:01:49.619 --> 06:01:49.919
heavy.

06:01:50.040 --> 06:01:53.880
But finally, sometime close to midnight

06:01:53.880 --> 06:01:56.459
sundew guest, they reached the border of

06:01:56.459 --> 06:01:58.919
the jungle and Queen Sequoia's makeshift

06:01:58.919 --> 06:02:00.840
camp, which took them a little while to

06:02:00.840 --> 06:02:01.139
find.

06:02:01.259 --> 06:02:04.080
Sundew had to use her leaf speak to track

06:02:04.080 --> 06:02:05.700
down the area where the plants were

06:02:05.700 --> 06:02:07.560
complaining the most about activity and

06:02:07.560 --> 06:02:08.099
disruption.

06:02:08.159 --> 06:02:11.580
A platform had been hastily set up high

06:02:11.580 --> 06:02:13.860
in the canopy, balanced between a few

06:02:13.860 --> 06:02:15.720
trees and lashed to their branches.

06:02:15.779 --> 06:02:18.599
It was close enough to the thin uppermost

06:02:18.599 --> 06:02:21.000
branches that the 3 moons could shine

06:02:21.000 --> 06:02:23.099
through, illuminating most of the

06:02:23.099 --> 06:02:23.580
encampment.

06:02:23.639 --> 06:02:26.459
Sequoia stood in the middle of it, with

06:02:26.459 --> 06:02:29.159
Belladonna, issuing orders and consulting

06:02:29.159 --> 06:02:31.139
with a flow of incoming and outgoing

06:02:31.139 --> 06:02:31.680
dragons.

06:02:31.799 --> 06:02:34.500
As Sundew and Nettle struggled toward

06:02:34.500 --> 06:02:37.020
them, Sundew saw a few warriors she knew

06:02:37.020 --> 06:02:38.580
receive an order from Sequoia.

06:02:38.639 --> 06:02:40.860
They looked at one another as though they

06:02:40.860 --> 06:02:43.259
might not obey, but then Belladonna

06:02:43.259 --> 06:02:45.360
barked something furiously, and they

06:02:45.360 --> 06:02:46.680
backed away, nodding.

06:02:46.740 --> 06:02:49.740
She also noticed the activity in the

06:02:49.740 --> 06:02:52.139
trees around them, and sensed it down on

06:02:52.139 --> 06:02:53.159
the jungle floor as well.

06:02:53.220 --> 06:02:55.919
Her leaf speak told her that several

06:02:55.919 --> 06:02:58.680
dragons were gathering plants that could

06:02:58.680 --> 06:03:01.619
be used as offensive weapons, blister

06:03:01.619 --> 06:03:04.439
bush seeds, and sandbox tree fruit in

06:03:04.439 --> 06:03:04.619
particular.

06:03:04.740 --> 06:03:07.979
She could hear dragons sending whispered

06:03:07.979 --> 06:03:09.060
messages through the trees.

06:03:09.180 --> 06:03:12.360
They lowered the chest to the platform

06:03:12.360 --> 06:03:13.439
and landed beside it.

06:03:13.500 --> 06:03:16.439
Sender realized that Blue and Sordail

06:03:16.439 --> 06:03:18.779
were there too, huddled in a corner that

06:03:18.779 --> 06:03:21.299
was nearly hidden by leaves, arguing in

06:03:21.299 --> 06:03:22.020
hushed voices.

06:03:22.080 --> 06:03:25.439
I'm not sure I've ever seen Blue argue

06:03:25.439 --> 06:03:27.360
before, Sundew thought.

06:03:27.419 --> 06:03:29.939
She wondered if he felt betrayed by her.

06:03:30.000 --> 06:03:32.400
Would he still help them fight the hive

06:03:32.400 --> 06:03:32.880
wings?

06:03:32.939 --> 06:03:34.979
They'd need his help to burn the

06:03:34.979 --> 06:03:35.580
antidote.

06:03:35.639 --> 06:03:38.220
Sundu realized that she'd been taking his

06:03:38.220 --> 06:03:40.380
flame silk for granted as a weapon they

06:03:40.380 --> 06:03:40.799
could use.

06:03:40.860 --> 06:03:43.380
But it's not our flame silk.

06:03:43.439 --> 06:03:44.400
It's his.

06:03:44.459 --> 06:03:48.000
As she watched, Cricket landed and ran

06:03:48.000 --> 06:03:50.759
over to him, and his face lit with joy at

06:03:50.759 --> 06:03:51.299
the side of her.

06:03:51.360 --> 06:03:53.279
What is this?

06:03:53.340 --> 06:03:55.979
Belladonna demanded, stalking up to the

06:03:55.979 --> 06:03:56.220
chest.

06:03:56.279 --> 06:03:59.939
Sundu waited until Queen Sequoia had

06:03:59.939 --> 06:04:01.380
dismissed the dragon she was speaking

06:04:01.380 --> 06:04:01.979
to.

06:04:02.040 --> 06:04:04.080
The Queen turned toward her with a

06:04:04.080 --> 06:04:06.540
slightly anxious, slightly disbelieving

06:04:06.540 --> 06:04:07.200
look on her face.

06:04:07.259 --> 06:04:11.939
This, sundew said, is the antidote to the

06:04:11.939 --> 06:04:13.500
breath of evil.

06:04:13.560 --> 06:04:15.479
She rested one talon on the lid.

06:04:15.540 --> 06:04:17.400
Hawthorne was still alive.

06:04:17.459 --> 06:04:19.919
He told us a very interesting version of

06:04:19.919 --> 06:04:22.020
the events that led up to the tree wars

06:04:22.020 --> 06:04:22.919
Your Majesty.

06:04:22.979 --> 06:04:26.159
Queen Sequoia flicked her tail from side

06:04:26.159 --> 06:04:28.860
to side, studying Sunday's face.

06:04:28.919 --> 06:04:31.799
He really found an antidote.

06:04:31.860 --> 06:04:33.240
She said quietly.

06:04:33.299 --> 06:04:36.840
We think so, Sundu said, at the same time

06:04:36.840 --> 06:04:38.700
as cricket blurted, yes.

06:04:38.759 --> 06:04:42.180
It's called heart of salvation, Mandrake

06:04:42.180 --> 06:04:42.540
added.

06:04:42.599 --> 06:04:44.580
The queen let out a long breath.

06:04:44.639 --> 06:04:48.119
Then we can finally atone for what we did

06:04:48.119 --> 06:04:49.139
she said.

06:04:49.200 --> 06:04:52.680
Sandu heard the echo of her own thoughts

06:04:52.680 --> 06:04:54.240
like a stab in the heart.

06:04:54.299 --> 06:04:56.819
She'd wanted the hive wings to atone.

06:04:56.880 --> 06:04:59.220
She still wanted them to.

06:04:59.279 --> 06:05:01.740
They were much worse than the leaf

06:05:01.740 --> 06:05:02.040
wings.

06:05:02.099 --> 06:05:05.279
But Hawthorne and Sequoia did terrible

06:05:05.279 --> 06:05:05.759
things too.

06:05:05.819 --> 06:05:08.159
The hive wings would be right to want

06:05:08.159 --> 06:05:10.439
them to be punished, but they would be

06:05:10.439 --> 06:05:12.240
wrong to want the same for the whole leaf

06:05:12.240 --> 06:05:12.840
wing tribe.

06:05:12.900 --> 06:05:16.860
So maybe, maybe I need to think about

06:05:16.860 --> 06:05:17.279
that too.

06:05:17.400 --> 06:05:21.240
Hawthorne, Sequoia, and Wasp.

06:05:21.299 --> 06:05:23.220
I should be angry at them.

06:05:23.279 --> 06:05:25.380
I can be furious at them.

06:05:25.439 --> 06:05:28.139
I can fight wasp without hating the

06:05:28.139 --> 06:05:29.459
entire hive wing tribe.

06:05:29.520 --> 06:05:32.520
I can free the hive wings and spare their

06:05:32.520 --> 06:05:35.099
lives without betraying my quest, because

06:05:35.099 --> 06:05:36.599
WASP is the real enemy.

06:05:36.659 --> 06:05:38.939
Wasp and her mind control.

06:05:39.000 --> 06:05:42.479
She dragged the vines off her wings and

06:05:42.479 --> 06:05:44.279
off the chest so she could throw it

06:05:44.279 --> 06:05:44.520
open.

06:05:44.639 --> 06:05:47.520
Here's what we need to do, she said.

06:05:47.580 --> 06:05:49.919
We take these roots down to the snarling

06:05:49.919 --> 06:05:52.919
river and build a bonfire with them, as

06:05:52.919 --> 06:05:54.540
close to the hive wing army as we can

06:05:54.540 --> 06:05:55.080
safely get.

06:05:55.139 --> 06:05:58.680
Then we set it on fire, they breathe in

06:05:58.680 --> 06:06:01.439
the smoke, and we cross all our claws

06:06:01.439 --> 06:06:02.040
that this works.

06:06:02.099 --> 06:06:05.939
She hesitated, then turned to Blue, who

06:06:05.939 --> 06:06:06.959
had stepped forward to listen.

06:06:07.020 --> 06:06:10.619
Which means we need flame silk, she said

06:06:10.619 --> 06:06:13.439
if blue is willing to give us some.

06:06:13.560 --> 06:06:17.880
If he's willing, Belladonis bat, who's

06:06:17.880 --> 06:06:18.599
giving him a choice?

06:06:18.659 --> 06:06:22.799
I am, Sundu said, frowning at her.

06:06:22.860 --> 06:06:24.360
It's his choice.

06:06:24.419 --> 06:06:26.220
He doesn't belong to us.

06:06:26.220 --> 06:06:28.860
Any more than all the other flame silks

06:06:28.860 --> 06:06:30.060
belong to Queen Wasp.

06:06:30.119 --> 06:06:33.240
If we force him to do what we want, we'll

06:06:33.240 --> 06:06:33.959
be just like her.

06:06:33.959 --> 06:06:36.000
She turned back to Blue.

06:06:36.060 --> 06:06:38.580
But I'm hoping you'll choose to help us

06:06:38.580 --> 06:06:39.599
she said.

06:06:39.659 --> 06:06:41.819
This isn't like burning a hive.

06:06:41.880 --> 06:06:44.639
This should free the hive wings, like we

06:06:44.639 --> 06:06:45.000
hoped.

06:06:45.060 --> 06:06:48.119
Cricket leaned into his shoulder and

06:06:48.119 --> 06:06:49.560
twined her tail around his.

06:06:49.619 --> 06:06:51.000
Please?

06:06:51.119 --> 06:06:51.959
She whispered.

06:06:52.020 --> 06:06:54.000
Of course I will.

06:06:54.060 --> 06:06:55.259
Blue said.

06:06:55.319 --> 06:06:57.479
I'll fly down there and light it myself.

06:06:57.540 --> 06:07:00.119
He looked up at Queen Sequoia.

06:07:00.180 --> 06:07:02.220
But I want you to promise me.

06:07:02.340 --> 06:07:04.500
You won't take any part of my fire to

06:07:04.500 --> 06:07:05.459
hurt any dragons.

06:07:05.580 --> 06:07:09.000
I don't want to find out in 3 days that

06:07:09.000 --> 06:07:11.459
some piece of my flame soak was saved, and

06:07:11.459 --> 06:07:13.020
then used to burn any more hives.

06:07:13.139 --> 06:07:16.619
Belladonna hissed and lashed her tail

06:07:16.619 --> 06:07:18.959
which a sundue guest meant that she'd

06:07:18.959 --> 06:07:20.639
been planning on doing that exact thing.

06:07:20.700 --> 06:07:24.360
I promise, said Queen Sequoia.

06:07:24.419 --> 06:07:25.919
Belladonna?

06:07:25.979 --> 06:07:28.380
The way she looked at Belladonna made it

06:07:28.380 --> 06:07:29.939
clear that wasn't actually a question.

06:07:30.000 --> 06:07:32.279
I promise too.

06:07:32.340 --> 06:07:34.740
Belladonna said sulkily.

06:07:34.799 --> 06:07:38.040
Then let's get to work, said the queen.

06:07:38.099 --> 06:07:40.619
I'll have my soldiers build a pyre

06:07:40.619 --> 06:07:43.319
tonight, under cover of darkness, while

06:07:43.319 --> 06:07:45.060
the hive wings are still frozen out

06:07:45.060 --> 06:07:45.299
there.

06:07:45.360 --> 06:07:48.000
As soon as the sun rises blue.

06:07:48.060 --> 06:07:50.520
I want you to fly down to set it aflame.

06:07:50.580 --> 06:07:52.740
Why not right now?

06:07:52.799 --> 06:07:53.880
Nettle asked.

06:07:53.939 --> 06:07:55.139
Why wait for the sun?

06:07:55.200 --> 06:07:59.099
Because I want to see their eyes, Sequoia

06:07:59.099 --> 06:07:59.340
said.

06:07:59.400 --> 06:08:01.139
I want to be sure it works.

06:08:01.139 --> 06:08:02.639
With luck.

06:08:02.700 --> 06:08:04.500
The queen will wait to make her move

06:08:04.500 --> 06:08:06.959
until morning as well, although we should

06:08:06.959 --> 06:08:09.479
be prepared to fire it at once if she

06:08:09.479 --> 06:08:10.619
starts to do anything tonight.

06:08:10.740 --> 06:08:13.860
Blue nodded, looking terrified.

06:08:13.919 --> 06:08:16.979
I'll help build the bonfire, Sandy

06:08:16.979 --> 06:08:17.400
offered.

06:08:17.459 --> 06:08:18.540
No.

06:08:18.599 --> 06:08:21.360
The queen reached one of her wings out to

06:08:21.360 --> 06:08:22.319
sundew's shoulder.

06:08:22.380 --> 06:08:24.000
I want you to rest.

06:08:24.060 --> 06:08:25.680
Rest?

06:08:25.740 --> 06:08:27.000
Sundu protested.

06:08:27.060 --> 06:08:30.240
The night before war, or a not war

06:08:30.240 --> 06:08:33.000
whatever happens, she amended, glancing

06:08:33.000 --> 06:08:33.959
at cricket's face.

06:08:34.020 --> 06:08:37.560
Yes, absolutely, said the Queen.

06:08:37.619 --> 06:08:40.380
You've been traveling all day, and for

06:08:40.380 --> 06:08:41.580
many days before this one.

06:08:41.639 --> 06:08:44.520
You need to sleep, because 1st thing in

06:08:44.520 --> 06:08:46.500
the morning, I want you to take some of

06:08:46.500 --> 06:08:48.180
these roots and grow more heart of

06:08:48.180 --> 06:08:48.659
salvation.

06:08:48.720 --> 06:08:51.119
We need as much as we can get.

06:08:51.180 --> 06:08:53.880
There are 1000s of hive wings out there.

06:08:53.939 --> 06:08:58.319
Sandu hesitated, tempted to argue, but

06:08:58.319 --> 06:09:00.659
exhaustion was beginning to set in, as

06:09:00.659 --> 06:09:02.159
though her eyelids were stuck together

06:09:02.159 --> 06:09:03.419
with sundew goop.

06:09:03.540 --> 06:09:06.540
It had been a long day, along several

06:09:06.540 --> 06:09:06.959
days.

06:09:07.020 --> 06:09:10.680
It was also kind of a weird, nice feeling

06:09:10.680 --> 06:09:13.020
to have someone notice and care.

06:09:13.080 --> 06:09:15.119
She couldn't remember Belladonna ever

06:09:15.119 --> 06:09:16.860
telling her she needed to sleep.

06:09:16.919 --> 06:09:19.860
All right, but only for a little while.

06:09:19.919 --> 06:09:20.880
She said.

06:09:20.939 --> 06:09:23.939
She took a few roots from the chest and

06:09:23.939 --> 06:09:25.439
tucked them into one of her pouches.

06:09:25.500 --> 06:09:28.080
The rest were carried off by Sequoia's

06:09:28.080 --> 06:09:30.360
soldiers, out through the canopy and down

06:09:30.360 --> 06:09:31.139
to the battlefield.

06:09:31.200 --> 06:09:34.020
Sundew felt strangely apprehensive

06:09:34.020 --> 06:09:35.279
watching them fly away.

06:09:35.340 --> 06:09:38.220
The trees were troubled, but they

06:09:38.220 --> 06:09:40.560
couldn't tell her why, and it tangled up

06:09:40.560 --> 06:09:42.959
her leaf speak, adding tendrils of worry

06:09:42.959 --> 06:09:43.860
to every thought.

06:09:43.919 --> 06:09:46.200
Is this really going to work?

06:09:46.259 --> 06:09:48.479
What if something happens to the

06:09:48.479 --> 06:09:49.080
antidote?

06:09:49.200 --> 06:09:51.900
What if WASP figures out what we're up to

06:09:51.900 --> 06:09:53.340
and manages to destroy it?

06:09:53.400 --> 06:09:56.459
Or what if we free the hive wings from

06:09:56.459 --> 06:09:58.740
her mind control, but they decide to

06:09:58.740 --> 06:09:59.520
fight for her anyway?

06:09:59.580 --> 06:10:03.479
Then there really would be war tomorrow, a

06:10:03.479 --> 06:10:05.639
war where the dragons sundew grew up with

06:10:05.639 --> 06:10:08.279
would all be out in front, with hive wing

06:10:08.279 --> 06:10:09.240
weapons pointed at them.

06:10:09.299 --> 06:10:12.419
Sundew had spent her whole life being

06:10:12.419 --> 06:10:14.279
furious with the hive wings for trying to

06:10:14.279 --> 06:10:17.040
wipe out her tribe, but she hadn't ever

06:10:17.040 --> 06:10:18.779
quite felt the danger of what would

06:10:18.779 --> 06:10:20.099
happen if they tried to do it again.

06:10:20.159 --> 06:10:23.099
She'd been mad about dragons who died

06:10:23.099 --> 06:10:25.740
half a century ago, but now she had to

06:10:25.740 --> 06:10:28.740
picture her friends, her tribe mates, her

06:10:28.740 --> 06:10:31.860
parents, as the targets, and suddenly she

06:10:31.860 --> 06:10:35.520
understood, painfully and forcefully, what

06:10:35.520 --> 06:10:38.159
Sequoia and Willow had felt, and why they

06:10:38.159 --> 06:10:39.659
hadn't wanted to restart the war.

06:10:39.720 --> 06:10:43.979
But we can still stop it, she hoped.

06:10:44.040 --> 06:10:46.619
She prayed, as she climbed up to a

06:10:46.619 --> 06:10:49.020
sheltered curve in the branches, and lay

06:10:49.020 --> 06:10:50.520
down next to cricket and blue.

06:10:50.639 --> 06:10:54.299
If the antidote works, please let it

06:10:54.299 --> 06:10:54.540
work.

06:10:54.599 --> 06:10:58.380
She closed her eyes and drifted into an

06:10:58.380 --> 06:10:59.279
uneasy sleep.

06:10:59.340 --> 06:11:03.840
Chapter 19.

06:11:04.020 --> 06:11:07.740
Sundew woke before dawn, her heart

06:11:07.740 --> 06:11:08.400
pounding.

06:11:08.459 --> 06:11:10.740
She couldn't remember her dreams exactly

06:11:10.740 --> 06:11:13.259
but she felt as though insects had been

06:11:13.259 --> 06:11:16.500
crawling all over her, wasps, perhaps

06:11:16.500 --> 06:11:20.099
1000s and 1000s of wasps with eyes

06:11:20.099 --> 06:11:20.939
bathoms deep.

06:11:21.000 --> 06:11:24.180
She slipped away from cricket and blue

06:11:24.180 --> 06:11:26.700
who were still asleep, curled together

06:11:26.700 --> 06:11:28.319
like intertwining vines.

06:11:28.380 --> 06:11:30.900
Swordtail was sprawled on Blue's other

06:11:30.900 --> 06:11:32.459
side, snoring lightly.

06:11:32.580 --> 06:11:35.880
The tree branches shook as she climbed to

06:11:35.880 --> 06:11:37.799
the top, swaying in the breeze.

06:11:37.860 --> 06:11:40.259
Up here, she could smell the ocean.

06:11:40.319 --> 06:11:43.020
She could hear the cries of seagulls and

06:11:43.020 --> 06:11:44.639
birds of prey as they swooped by

06:11:44.639 --> 06:11:45.180
overhead.

06:11:45.240 --> 06:11:47.759
Away from the jostling noise of the

06:11:47.759 --> 06:11:50.099
jungle plants, her leaf speak could

06:11:50.099 --> 06:11:52.020
discern the faraway murmurs of Savannah

06:11:52.020 --> 06:11:52.619
grasses.

06:11:52.680 --> 06:11:56.159
But this morning there were other smells

06:11:56.159 --> 06:11:57.119
other sounds.

06:11:57.180 --> 06:11:59.700
This morning she could smell dragons.

06:11:59.759 --> 06:12:02.340
She could hear 100s of talons shuffling.

06:12:02.400 --> 06:12:04.200
She could sense the plants under their

06:12:04.200 --> 06:12:06.360
feet being smothered struggling to

06:12:06.360 --> 06:12:06.659
survive.

06:12:06.720 --> 06:12:10.500
And from the very top of the tree, she

06:12:10.500 --> 06:12:13.319
could see them, columns of hive wings

06:12:13.319 --> 06:12:15.599
lined the plain on either side of the

06:12:15.599 --> 06:12:18.240
snarling river, stretching to the horizon

06:12:18.240 --> 06:12:21.299
orange and gold and black scales

06:12:21.299 --> 06:12:25.080
diaphanous wings flickering, 8 dragon in

06:12:25.080 --> 06:12:27.479
its place, an exact distance from every

06:12:27.479 --> 06:12:30.540
other dragon, they looked too precisely

06:12:30.540 --> 06:12:33.180
placed to be real, but they were real.

06:12:33.240 --> 06:12:35.580
The hive wing prisoner had been right.

06:12:35.639 --> 06:12:38.040
It seemed as though Wasp had summoned

06:12:38.040 --> 06:12:39.659
every hive wing in the tribe for this.

06:12:39.720 --> 06:12:43.259
She's hoping to wipe us out with one fell

06:12:43.259 --> 06:12:43.860
swoop.

06:12:43.919 --> 06:12:47.040
Sundu realized, she's going to throw

06:12:47.040 --> 06:12:48.119
everything at us.

06:12:48.180 --> 06:12:50.099
She wants to finish this today.

06:12:50.159 --> 06:12:52.439
Finish us.

06:12:52.500 --> 06:12:54.659
It's terrifying, isn't it?

06:12:54.720 --> 06:12:58.439
Sundew turned to find mandrake perched on

06:12:58.439 --> 06:12:59.880
another high branch nearby.

06:12:59.939 --> 06:13:02.880
His eyes were tired, and she wondered

06:13:02.880 --> 06:13:04.799
whether he'd slept as poorly as she had

06:13:04.799 --> 06:13:06.599
or maybe not at all.

06:13:06.659 --> 06:13:09.180
We'll stop them, she said.

06:13:09.240 --> 06:13:10.380
We have to.

06:13:10.439 --> 06:13:13.919
The sky was shading toward pale gray

06:13:13.919 --> 06:13:15.180
streaked with pink.

06:13:15.240 --> 06:13:17.520
The sun would slip over the horizon

06:13:17.520 --> 06:13:19.080
behind sundew very soon.

06:13:19.139 --> 06:13:22.259
If there's a chance we're all going to

06:13:22.259 --> 06:13:22.919
die today.

06:13:22.979 --> 06:13:25.259
Mandrake, she said.

06:13:25.319 --> 06:13:27.240
I'm not going to marry you.

06:13:27.299 --> 06:13:31.380
I know, he said. giving her a real smile

06:13:31.380 --> 06:13:31.799
for once.

06:13:31.919 --> 06:13:33.779
I've always known that.

06:13:33.840 --> 06:13:35.520
Really?

06:13:35.580 --> 06:13:38.279
she said, because it's not about you.

06:13:38.340 --> 06:13:40.619
You're one of the few dragons I actually

06:13:40.619 --> 06:13:44.099
like, but you're not Willow, and she's

06:13:44.099 --> 06:13:45.659
the only dragon I want to marry.

06:13:45.720 --> 06:13:48.779
I hope you do, he said.

06:13:48.840 --> 06:13:50.700
I hope the antidote works.

06:13:50.759 --> 06:13:53.400
I hope this whole horrible thing ends and

06:13:53.400 --> 06:13:54.900
we all get to live happily ever after.

06:13:54.959 --> 06:13:58.619
His smile faded as he returned his gaze

06:13:58.619 --> 06:14:00.180
to the vast army below them.

06:14:00.240 --> 06:14:02.939
Sundew squinted down at the river

06:14:02.939 --> 06:14:04.979
searching for the bonfire pile.

06:14:05.040 --> 06:14:07.200
It looked pitifully small from up here

06:14:07.200 --> 06:14:09.720
especially next to all those 1000s of

06:14:09.720 --> 06:14:10.380
hive wings.

06:14:10.439 --> 06:14:13.139
Does that look like enough antidote to

06:14:13.139 --> 06:14:13.319
you?

06:14:13.380 --> 06:14:14.580
She asked him.

06:14:14.639 --> 06:14:17.220
He shook his head, looking grim.

06:14:17.279 --> 06:14:20.220
No, not even close.

06:14:20.279 --> 06:14:22.380
It's not going to be enough.

06:14:22.439 --> 06:14:25.560
The smoke might reach the 1st few rows of

06:14:25.560 --> 06:14:27.959
dragons, but that will leave 1000s more

06:14:27.959 --> 06:14:30.540
still behind them, still under wasps

06:14:30.540 --> 06:14:30.959
control.

06:14:31.020 --> 06:14:34.259
Thousands more, still coming for us.

06:14:34.319 --> 06:14:37.619
Panic surged through her like a jolt of

06:14:37.619 --> 06:14:38.099
toxin.

06:14:38.159 --> 06:14:40.919
I'm going to make more, she said.

06:14:40.979 --> 06:14:42.180
Come with me and help.

06:14:42.240 --> 06:14:44.759
He nodded and followed her.

06:14:44.819 --> 06:14:47.159
She scrambled down the tree until she

06:14:47.159 --> 06:14:49.439
found an open gap in the branches, where

06:14:49.439 --> 06:14:51.240
she could spread her wings and drop down

06:14:51.240 --> 06:14:52.080
to the jungle floor.

06:14:52.139 --> 06:14:55.799
It was still very dark down here, but

06:14:55.799 --> 06:14:57.840
Sundu let her leaf speak reach down into

06:14:57.840 --> 06:15:00.299
the soil and out through the root systems

06:15:00.299 --> 06:15:02.700
tracing them along until she found water

06:15:02.700 --> 06:15:05.939
a stream, a tributary of the snarling

06:15:05.939 --> 06:15:06.360
river.

06:15:06.479 --> 06:15:08.819
That would be the best place to grow more

06:15:08.819 --> 06:15:11.279
heart of salvation, in the mud along the

06:15:11.279 --> 06:15:13.500
banks, where the damp earth could help it

06:15:13.500 --> 06:15:13.979
along.

06:15:14.040 --> 06:15:17.520
She heard cracking branches overhead, and

06:15:17.520 --> 06:15:19.380
looked up to see Cricket flailing her way

06:15:19.380 --> 06:15:22.380
down, catching on every vine and cobweb

06:15:22.380 --> 06:15:22.860
as she did.

06:15:22.919 --> 06:15:25.680
Mandrake ducked out of the way as the

06:15:25.680 --> 06:15:27.479
hive wing landed in an ungraceful

06:15:27.479 --> 06:15:28.080
sprawl.

06:15:28.139 --> 06:15:30.659
She hopped to her feet, shaking herself

06:15:30.659 --> 06:15:30.900
off.

06:15:30.959 --> 06:15:34.139
You don't have to come with us, Sundew

06:15:34.139 --> 06:15:34.619
pointed out.

06:15:34.680 --> 06:15:37.200
Sure I do, Cricket said.

06:15:37.259 --> 06:15:38.700
I can help carry roots.

06:15:38.819 --> 06:15:40.799
I can harvest them while you make more

06:15:40.799 --> 06:15:41.220
grow.

06:15:41.279 --> 06:15:43.319
Also, I really want to watch.

06:15:43.380 --> 06:15:45.959
I didn't get nearly enough of a chance to

06:15:45.959 --> 06:15:48.360
watch that choke cherry grow, and I

06:15:48.360 --> 06:15:49.740
imagine it'll be really awesome.

06:15:49.799 --> 06:15:53.580
I mean, scientifically speaking, I wish I

06:15:53.580 --> 06:15:55.139
could make plants grow just by thinking

06:15:55.139 --> 06:15:55.619
at them.

06:15:55.680 --> 06:15:59.759
Well, it's slightly more complicated than

06:15:59.759 --> 06:16:01.259
that, Sundu said.

06:16:01.319 --> 06:16:02.819
But all right, come along.

06:16:02.880 --> 06:16:05.759
They hurried through the jungle until

06:16:05.759 --> 06:16:07.979
they reached the stream, which wound

06:16:07.979 --> 06:16:10.319
between small pitcher plants and gurgled

06:16:10.319 --> 06:16:11.700
over smooth stones.

06:16:11.759 --> 06:16:14.400
Long, feathery ferns leaned over the

06:16:14.400 --> 06:16:17.040
water, as if plotting how to steal it all

06:16:17.040 --> 06:16:17.520
for themselves.

06:16:17.580 --> 06:16:21.959
Sundew found a patch of dirt, dug a hole

06:16:21.959 --> 06:16:23.639
and planted a piece of root in it.

06:16:23.700 --> 06:16:26.459
It looked pale and ghostly against the

06:16:26.459 --> 06:16:29.520
dark wet earth, like a grub that had

06:16:29.520 --> 06:16:31.319
wiggled its way up from the depths of the

06:16:31.319 --> 06:16:34.139
underground, or the haunted spirit of a

06:16:34.139 --> 06:16:34.740
real plant.

06:16:34.799 --> 06:16:37.380
She could still see patches of its white

06:16:37.380 --> 06:16:39.240
skin winking through the dirt as she

06:16:39.240 --> 06:16:41.880
covered it up, until finally, it was

06:16:41.880 --> 06:16:42.540
completely buried.

06:16:42.659 --> 06:16:46.200
Mandrake took another piece, and moved

06:16:46.200 --> 06:16:47.880
farther upstream to do the same thing.

06:16:47.939 --> 06:16:51.299
Cricket stayed beside Sundew, with her

06:16:51.299 --> 06:16:53.580
tail wrapped around her talons, watching

06:16:53.580 --> 06:16:54.240
curiously.

06:16:54.299 --> 06:16:58.380
She wisely, and, surprisingly, kept quiet

06:16:58.380 --> 06:17:00.840
as sundew dug her claws into the earth

06:17:00.840 --> 06:17:03.599
and closed her eyes, summoning all the

06:17:03.599 --> 06:17:05.159
power of her leaf speak.

06:17:05.400 --> 06:17:07.319
Hello, little plant.

06:17:07.380 --> 06:17:09.240
We need your help.

06:17:09.299 --> 06:17:10.740
Hmm.

06:17:10.860 --> 06:17:13.259
The plant murmured back softly.

06:17:13.319 --> 06:17:16.740
You want to grow, Sundu told it.

06:17:16.799 --> 06:17:18.299
Let me help you grow.

06:17:18.419 --> 06:17:21.779
You can grow big and grand and wild.

06:17:21.900 --> 06:17:23.759
With so many roots.

06:17:23.819 --> 06:17:25.020
You won't need them all.

06:17:25.080 --> 06:17:27.119
Grow wild.

06:17:27.180 --> 06:17:28.560
Spread far.

06:17:28.680 --> 06:17:31.200
The plant echoed, more or less.

06:17:31.259 --> 06:17:33.900
Stretching its tendrils like a centipede

06:17:33.900 --> 06:17:34.560
unwinding.

06:17:34.619 --> 06:17:38.099
Grow far, spread wild.

06:17:38.159 --> 06:17:41.159
There was some kind of block between

06:17:41.159 --> 06:17:42.479
sundew and the plant.

06:17:42.540 --> 06:17:45.119
She could reach it, but she couldn't wrap

06:17:45.119 --> 06:17:46.080
herself all around it.

06:17:46.139 --> 06:17:49.080
She could feel it growing, but she

06:17:49.080 --> 06:17:51.000
couldn't latch on to its exact voice.

06:17:51.000 --> 06:17:53.279
She felt as if she was hearing it

06:17:53.279 --> 06:17:55.259
reflected off another surface.

06:17:55.319 --> 06:17:56.819
It was hard to describe.

06:17:56.880 --> 06:18:00.419
Like a sound just out of range that she

06:18:00.419 --> 06:18:02.279
knew she'd recognize if she got a bit

06:18:02.279 --> 06:18:03.060
closer.

06:18:03.119 --> 06:18:06.240
Come forth, Sundu called.

06:18:06.299 --> 06:18:07.500
Be here.

06:18:07.560 --> 06:18:08.880
Let me see you.

06:18:09.000 --> 06:18:12.540
The plant's response felt like rustling

06:18:12.540 --> 06:18:13.500
in the back of her brain.

06:18:13.560 --> 06:18:16.200
Yes, it whispered.

06:18:16.259 --> 06:18:20.819
Coming, growing, spreading, taking.

06:18:20.880 --> 06:18:24.599
And then suddenly, it was as loud as a

06:18:24.599 --> 06:18:25.259
waterfall.

06:18:25.319 --> 06:18:30.599
Yes, here and now it roared, as vines

06:18:30.599 --> 06:18:32.459
shot from the earth and blasted across

06:18:32.459 --> 06:18:33.840
the ground all around them.

06:18:33.900 --> 06:18:35.639
Sundew recoiled.

06:18:35.700 --> 06:18:38.279
Her leaf speak recognizing them before

06:18:38.279 --> 06:18:39.000
her eyes did.

06:18:39.119 --> 06:18:42.720
She stared in disbelief as the vines kept

06:18:42.720 --> 06:18:46.259
growing, spreading, laughing, inside her

06:18:46.259 --> 06:18:49.560
mind, red and green leaves unfurling

06:18:49.560 --> 06:18:52.259
white flowers and evil eyed seeds

06:18:52.259 --> 06:18:52.919
everywhere.

06:18:53.040 --> 06:18:55.740
The antidote wasn't a new plant.

06:18:55.799 --> 06:18:58.259
There was no heart of salvation.

06:18:58.319 --> 06:19:02.159
She was looking at the breath of evil.

06:19:02.220 --> 06:19:06.479
Chapter 20.

06:19:06.779 --> 06:19:10.380
Mandrake, stop, she cried.

06:19:10.439 --> 06:19:12.959
Too late, too late.

06:19:13.080 --> 06:19:17.099
The plant hummed, spread, grow, far, wild

06:19:17.099 --> 06:19:19.740
conquer, consume all mine.

06:19:19.799 --> 06:19:22.020
The vines had stopped growing outward as

06:19:22.020 --> 06:19:24.360
soon as sundew pulled back, but they were

06:19:24.360 --> 06:19:26.639
already huge and covered the bank of the

06:19:26.639 --> 06:19:27.299
stream.

06:19:27.419 --> 06:19:29.700
Cricket was nearly caught in a tangle of

06:19:29.700 --> 06:19:31.979
them, but she'd jumped into the air and

06:19:31.979 --> 06:19:34.619
hovered above, her talons pressed to her

06:19:34.619 --> 06:19:36.419
mouth and her eyes wide with shock.

06:19:36.479 --> 06:19:39.720
Mandrake came stumbling back towards

06:19:39.720 --> 06:19:40.319
sundew.

06:19:40.380 --> 06:19:42.779
She could see that his root had grown as

06:19:42.779 --> 06:19:45.840
well, not as vigorously as hers, but

06:19:45.840 --> 06:19:47.700
enough vines had sprouted to show him

06:19:47.700 --> 06:19:48.959
unmistakably what it was.

06:19:49.080 --> 06:19:51.119
What is this?

06:19:51.240 --> 06:19:53.459
Mandrake asked plaintively.

06:19:53.520 --> 06:19:56.040
It looks just like the breath of evil.

06:19:56.099 --> 06:19:58.259
Sundu, what is happening?

06:19:58.319 --> 06:20:00.720
We were tricked, she said.

06:20:00.779 --> 06:20:02.400
I think, I don't know.

06:20:02.459 --> 06:20:03.840
Why would anyone?

06:20:04.439 --> 06:20:05.099
But look at it.

06:20:05.159 --> 06:20:07.139
The antidote is a lie.

06:20:07.259 --> 06:20:11.819
Maybe not, Cricket stammered from above

06:20:11.819 --> 06:20:12.119
them.

06:20:12.180 --> 06:20:14.939
Maybe another piece of the plant could be

06:20:14.939 --> 06:20:16.200
an antidote for the rest of.

06:20:17.400 --> 06:20:19.020
No, it doesn't make sense.

06:20:19.080 --> 06:20:21.779
Maybe Hawthorne got mixed up and gave us

06:20:21.779 --> 06:20:22.200
the wrong thing?

06:20:22.259 --> 06:20:25.500
No, said Sundew.

06:20:25.619 --> 06:20:28.560
She felt frozen in place, as though the

06:20:28.560 --> 06:20:29.759
plant had hypnotized her.

06:20:29.880 --> 06:20:31.619
He knew what he was doing.

06:20:31.680 --> 06:20:33.959
But I don't understand why.

06:20:34.020 --> 06:20:37.979
She tried, tentatively, to reach out to

06:20:37.979 --> 06:20:39.720
the plant again with her leaf speak.

06:20:39.779 --> 06:20:41.580
Maybe if she understood it.

06:20:41.580 --> 06:20:44.880
Maybe if she spoke to it, she could turn

06:20:44.880 --> 06:20:46.319
it into an antidote.

06:20:46.380 --> 06:20:48.419
Perhaps that was what Hawthorne had

06:20:48.419 --> 06:20:48.599
done.

06:20:48.659 --> 06:20:51.900
But she found nothing healing about this

06:20:51.900 --> 06:20:52.080
plant.

06:20:52.139 --> 06:20:55.020
It felt as sinister as the ones in the

06:20:55.020 --> 06:20:58.139
den of vipers, far worse than the ones in

06:20:58.139 --> 06:21:00.720
Wasp's greenhouse, and when she tried to

06:21:00.720 --> 06:21:04.139
investigate it, it reached right back, a

06:21:04.139 --> 06:21:06.240
sensation like freezing tentacles

06:21:06.240 --> 06:21:07.560
plunging into her brain.

06:21:07.619 --> 06:21:09.779
She closed herself off quickly.

06:21:09.840 --> 06:21:13.860
We have to warn Queen Sequoia, she said.

06:21:13.919 --> 06:21:16.020
She needs to know that burning the roots

06:21:16.020 --> 06:21:16.500
won't help.

06:21:16.560 --> 06:21:21.119
But Intworm, Cricket said, he was cured.

06:21:21.180 --> 06:21:22.619
It worked on him.

06:21:22.680 --> 06:21:26.520
I think perhaps it didn't, Sundu said.

06:21:26.580 --> 06:21:30.299
She felt a new cold fear, like her skin

06:21:30.299 --> 06:21:31.259
turning inside out.

06:21:31.319 --> 06:21:34.560
They'd left inch worm with hazel and

06:21:34.560 --> 06:21:34.979
willow.

06:21:35.040 --> 06:21:37.979
If Wasp was still inside him.

06:21:38.040 --> 06:21:41.340
If the antidote doesn't work, Blue is the

06:21:41.340 --> 06:21:43.860
1st dragon they'll come for, Cricket said

06:21:43.860 --> 06:21:45.360
in a panicked voice.

06:21:45.360 --> 06:21:47.580
He'll be out there where everyone can see

06:21:47.580 --> 06:21:47.880
him.

06:21:47.939 --> 06:21:51.900
We'll go stop them, Sundu said, lifting

06:21:51.900 --> 06:21:52.439
into the air.

06:21:52.500 --> 06:21:55.500
Mandrake, stay here and destroy all these

06:21:55.500 --> 06:21:56.040
vines.

06:21:56.159 --> 06:21:58.439
I mean, really destroy them.

06:21:58.500 --> 06:22:03.360
You can try, said a voice from the other

06:22:03.360 --> 06:22:04.380
side of the stream.

06:22:04.439 --> 06:22:06.959
But it won't make much difference.

06:22:07.020 --> 06:22:09.959
We're spreading through the jungle as we

06:22:09.959 --> 06:22:10.380
speak.

06:22:10.500 --> 06:22:14.400
Hawthorne stood on the opposite riverbank

06:22:14.400 --> 06:22:16.680
twitching pitcher plants away from

06:22:16.680 --> 06:22:19.979
himself with his tail, beside him, with a

06:22:19.979 --> 06:22:22.500
dragon bite viper coiled around her neck

06:22:22.500 --> 06:22:23.880
was Willow.

06:22:24.119 --> 06:22:27.180
Its fangs were bared, and Willow's deer

06:22:27.180 --> 06:22:30.119
brown eyes were fixed on sundew, terrified

06:22:30.119 --> 06:22:31.740
and defiant at the same time.

06:22:31.799 --> 06:22:35.340
Sundu hissed and started forward, but

06:22:35.340 --> 06:22:37.680
Hawthorne raised one claw and made a

06:22:37.680 --> 06:22:40.740
patronizing, uh, uh, uh, sound.

06:22:40.860 --> 06:22:43.439
She could kill him for that sound alone

06:22:43.439 --> 06:22:45.840
but she was definitely going to kill him

06:22:45.840 --> 06:22:47.099
for threatening Willow.

06:22:47.159 --> 06:22:50.939
If you hurt her, Sundu growled.

06:22:51.000 --> 06:22:52.619
If you dare.

06:22:52.680 --> 06:22:55.919
I know, I know, he said.

06:22:55.979 --> 06:22:58.259
You'll do something terrible and violent

06:22:58.259 --> 06:23:01.259
to me, but it will be too late because

06:23:01.259 --> 06:23:02.159
she'll be dead.

06:23:02.220 --> 06:23:05.159
So how about you stay on your side of the

06:23:05.159 --> 06:23:05.459
river?

06:23:05.520 --> 06:23:09.000
Well, we have our little talk, and maybe

06:23:09.000 --> 06:23:12.419
she'll survive this, more or less.

06:23:12.479 --> 06:23:14.700
You too, little gnat.

06:23:14.759 --> 06:23:17.819
And you, disposable leaf wing.

06:23:17.880 --> 06:23:19.619
I can still see you.

06:23:19.680 --> 06:23:22.080
Don't even think about sneaking away.

06:23:22.139 --> 06:23:25.500
Sundew sank back down to the ground.

06:23:25.560 --> 06:23:28.139
Cricket and mandrake did the same on

06:23:28.139 --> 06:23:29.159
either side of her.

06:23:29.159 --> 06:23:31.020
The moment they touched the earth.

06:23:31.080 --> 06:23:33.900
The breath of evil vines slithered around

06:23:33.900 --> 06:23:37.139
and around their talons, snarling them in

06:23:37.139 --> 06:23:38.220
place so they couldn't move.

06:23:38.340 --> 06:23:41.939
There, Hawthorne said.

06:23:42.000 --> 06:23:45.000
After all, it would spoil everything if

06:23:45.000 --> 06:23:46.500
you went to Warren Sequoia.

06:23:46.560 --> 06:23:50.099
My whole brilliant plan, ruined by a trio

06:23:50.099 --> 06:23:50.759
of idiots.

06:23:50.819 --> 06:23:52.439
I think not.

06:23:52.500 --> 06:23:56.220
What brilliant plan, Sandu asked.

06:23:56.279 --> 06:23:58.439
So you tricked us into burning a pile of

06:23:58.439 --> 06:23:58.860
roots.

06:23:58.919 --> 06:24:00.060
Great work.

06:24:00.119 --> 06:24:02.340
If you think that means Queen Sequoia

06:24:02.340 --> 06:24:04.560
won't be prepared for wasp's attack

06:24:04.560 --> 06:24:05.520
you're the idiot.

06:24:05.580 --> 06:24:08.099
She'll be ready even when the bonfire

06:24:08.099 --> 06:24:08.580
does nothing.

06:24:08.639 --> 06:24:10.560
We're stronger than you think.

06:24:10.619 --> 06:24:12.240
And so is this jungle.

06:24:12.360 --> 06:24:14.700
Hawthorne chuckled.

06:24:14.759 --> 06:24:18.240
Oh, I know how strong this jungle is.

06:24:18.299 --> 06:24:21.000
It's been my home for 1000s of years

06:24:21.000 --> 06:24:21.659
after all.

06:24:21.720 --> 06:24:24.779
It came so close to killing me at last

06:24:24.779 --> 06:24:27.240
after so many had failed.

06:24:27.299 --> 06:24:30.299
But then Hawthorne came along and rescued

06:24:30.299 --> 06:24:30.779
me.

06:24:30.840 --> 06:24:33.840
Gormless, lovely dragon husk.

06:24:33.840 --> 06:24:35.580
He's been so useful.

06:24:35.639 --> 06:24:37.979
I think I'm going to keep him forever.

06:24:38.040 --> 06:24:41.880
Or at least until his bones rot, and I

06:24:41.880 --> 06:24:42.779
can't move him anymore.

06:24:42.840 --> 06:24:47.939
Silence fell. chilling and horrible, like

06:24:47.939 --> 06:24:50.400
a dragon trap, closing its jaws around

06:24:50.400 --> 06:24:50.639
them.

06:24:50.700 --> 06:24:52.680
Sundu couldn't breathe.

06:24:52.799 --> 06:24:53.880
She couldn't think.

06:24:53.939 --> 06:24:56.040
She could only stare into Willow's

06:24:56.040 --> 06:24:56.700
frightened eyes.

06:24:56.759 --> 06:24:58.139
Her pulse pounding.

06:24:58.200 --> 06:24:59.759
How do I save you?

06:24:59.819 --> 06:25:00.959
How do I save you?

06:25:01.020 --> 06:25:02.939
How do I save you from this?

06:25:03.000 --> 06:25:05.099
What?

06:25:05.159 --> 06:25:06.959
Mandrake said finally.

06:25:07.020 --> 06:25:09.180
Is Hawthorne?

06:25:09.299 --> 06:25:11.580
Aren't you Hawthorne?

06:25:11.639 --> 06:25:12.599
Cricket asked.

06:25:12.659 --> 06:25:16.439
He, he, said the dragon in front of

06:25:16.439 --> 06:25:16.740
them.

06:25:16.799 --> 06:25:18.540
A sneering sort of wheeze.

06:25:18.599 --> 06:25:21.840
The outer bark is Hawthorn, yes.

06:25:21.900 --> 06:25:24.599
All these years, he thought he was in

06:25:24.599 --> 06:25:24.900
control.

06:25:24.959 --> 06:25:27.840
He thought I was merely one of the voices

06:25:27.840 --> 06:25:28.500
in his head.

06:25:28.560 --> 06:25:31.439
His beautifully carved seed just

06:25:31.439 --> 06:25:32.700
whispering back to him.

06:25:32.819 --> 06:25:36.119
He took out the carving that Sandu had

06:25:36.119 --> 06:25:36.659
thought was an egg.

06:25:36.720 --> 06:25:40.020
But of course, it's supposed to be a

06:25:40.020 --> 06:25:40.380
seed.

06:25:40.439 --> 06:25:42.959
The breath of evil's seed.

06:25:43.020 --> 06:25:46.259
Hawthorne cubbed the seed in his talons.

06:25:46.319 --> 06:25:48.900
Such a clever scientist.

06:25:49.020 --> 06:25:52.319
Left to test his experiments on himself

06:25:52.319 --> 06:25:53.159
poor fellow.

06:25:53.220 --> 06:25:56.459
Imagine what he might have figured out if

06:25:56.459 --> 06:25:58.139
he'd had other test subjects.

06:25:58.200 --> 06:26:00.659
Aren't I lucky he didn't?

06:26:00.720 --> 06:26:03.599
The vines tightened around sundew's

06:26:03.599 --> 06:26:04.020
talons.

06:26:04.080 --> 06:26:07.020
WASP, she growled.

06:26:07.139 --> 06:26:09.779
So you've been here, in our jungle this

06:26:09.779 --> 06:26:11.819
whole time, you knew we were still

06:26:11.819 --> 06:26:12.060
alive.

06:26:12.119 --> 06:26:15.240
Hawthorn threw back his head and

06:26:15.240 --> 06:26:15.779
laughed.

06:26:15.840 --> 06:26:18.720
An awful slithering noise that sent cold

06:26:18.720 --> 06:26:21.060
vibrations through sundew's leaf speak.

06:26:21.180 --> 06:26:26.400
Wasp, really, he said, when he finally

06:26:26.400 --> 06:26:27.299
caught his breath.

06:26:27.360 --> 06:26:29.099
No, no, no.

06:26:29.159 --> 06:26:31.380
She's a perfect ally.

06:26:31.439 --> 06:26:34.319
All poison from her core out.

06:26:34.439 --> 06:26:37.619
But in the end, she's my puppet too.

06:26:37.680 --> 06:26:40.319
I let her do all her great evil things

06:26:40.319 --> 06:26:41.759
because it pleases me.

06:26:41.819 --> 06:26:45.599
But one day, she'll realize I've hollowed

06:26:45.599 --> 06:26:47.759
out her brain, and she has no more

06:26:47.759 --> 06:26:50.340
control than her lowliest worm of a

06:26:50.340 --> 06:26:50.639
subject.

06:26:50.700 --> 06:26:54.180
Then, who are you?

06:26:54.240 --> 06:26:55.799
Cricket burst out.

06:26:55.860 --> 06:26:59.340
Hawthorne's face went very still, his

06:26:59.340 --> 06:27:01.860
eyes flickering white, green, white

06:27:01.860 --> 06:27:02.099
green.

06:27:02.159 --> 06:27:06.000
I am the rightful owner of this continent

06:27:06.000 --> 06:27:08.459
he growled in a low voice.

06:27:08.580 --> 06:27:10.200
It was mine.

06:27:10.259 --> 06:27:12.299
All of it mine.

06:27:12.360 --> 06:27:16.139
Every insect and blade of grass and grain

06:27:16.139 --> 06:27:16.799
of sand.

06:27:16.860 --> 06:27:18.779
I ruled it all.

06:27:18.840 --> 06:27:23.340
And then you came, with your outsized

06:27:23.340 --> 06:27:26.939
brains, and your clumsy crushing talons

06:27:26.939 --> 06:27:30.479
and your fire, and you stole it from me.

06:27:30.540 --> 06:27:33.599
All these 1000s of years.

06:27:33.659 --> 06:27:36.479
I've waited to recapture my home and

06:27:36.479 --> 06:27:37.259
destroy you all.

06:27:37.319 --> 06:27:41.040
I abided my time, and planned my

06:27:41.040 --> 06:27:41.580
vengeance.

06:27:41.639 --> 06:27:45.360
Even trapped in the jungle, I knew I'd

06:27:45.360 --> 06:27:46.500
find a way one day.

06:27:46.560 --> 06:27:49.740
I had no idea how easy it would be in the

06:27:49.740 --> 06:27:50.340
end.

06:27:50.459 --> 06:27:53.099
You foolish, short sighted dragons.

06:27:53.159 --> 06:27:54.840
You came looking for me.

06:27:54.900 --> 06:27:57.180
You fed me to your enemies.

06:27:57.240 --> 06:28:00.479
You let me spread and infect you, and

06:28:00.479 --> 06:28:03.419
soon, every one of you will be no more

06:28:03.419 --> 06:28:05.819
trouble than my obedient snakes here.

06:28:05.880 --> 06:28:09.299
I will always be trouble.

06:28:09.360 --> 06:28:10.680
Sandu said.

06:28:10.740 --> 06:28:13.500
You can't control leaf wings, and you'll

06:28:13.500 --> 06:28:14.279
never control me.

06:28:14.340 --> 06:28:16.020
Or you.

06:28:16.080 --> 06:28:18.299
She tried to say to Willow with her

06:28:18.299 --> 06:28:18.540
eyes.

06:28:18.599 --> 06:28:23.279
Yee, hee, Hawthorne said again.

06:28:23.340 --> 06:28:26.520
His grin widening so far, it looked as

06:28:26.520 --> 06:28:28.139
though his face might split in half.

06:28:28.259 --> 06:28:30.959
You are pleasantly stupid.

06:28:31.080 --> 06:28:33.840
You really haven't figured out the next

06:28:33.840 --> 06:28:35.099
stage of my plan.

06:28:35.159 --> 06:28:37.740
Let's see, how did you put it?

06:28:37.799 --> 06:28:40.560
When the bonfire does nothing.

06:28:40.680 --> 06:28:45.060
But of course, the bonfire does something

06:28:45.060 --> 06:28:46.919
you splintery twig.

06:28:47.040 --> 06:28:50.580
Cricket gasped, apparently guessing it

06:28:50.580 --> 06:28:51.779
before Sundew did.

06:28:51.840 --> 06:28:52.799
What?

06:28:52.860 --> 06:28:54.180
What does it do?

06:28:54.240 --> 06:28:55.799
Mandrake asked.

06:28:55.860 --> 06:28:59.759
Well, Hawthorne did have very powerful

06:28:59.759 --> 06:29:02.639
leaf speak, said the thing inside the

06:29:02.639 --> 06:29:03.659
dragon facing them.

06:29:03.720 --> 06:29:07.080
He almost managed to put a cage around

06:29:07.080 --> 06:29:07.380
me.

06:29:07.439 --> 06:29:10.259
He took advantage of one of my weak

06:29:10.259 --> 06:29:12.299
little shoots, who would have done

06:29:12.299 --> 06:29:15.060
anything to survive, and he really did

06:29:15.060 --> 06:29:17.520
adapt to that branch of me to only work

06:29:17.520 --> 06:29:20.459
on hive wings, aggravating monster.

06:29:20.520 --> 06:29:23.520
He abruptly stabbed himself in the neck

06:29:23.520 --> 06:29:26.580
then tortled as blood trickled down from

06:29:26.580 --> 06:29:26.880
the wound.

06:29:27.000 --> 06:29:29.279
I could work with it though.

06:29:29.400 --> 06:29:32.400
It was a good start, but not what I

06:29:32.400 --> 06:29:32.759
needed.

06:29:32.819 --> 06:29:34.380
Not what I wanted.

06:29:34.439 --> 06:29:36.360
I wanted everyone.

06:29:36.479 --> 06:29:41.099
So once I was finally inside him, I had

06:29:41.099 --> 06:29:42.060
him fix me.

06:29:42.119 --> 06:29:44.819
All his little chains are gone.

06:29:44.880 --> 06:29:49.080
And now, I will have what I want.

06:29:49.139 --> 06:29:52.500
He stretched his wings and closed his

06:29:52.500 --> 06:29:54.119
eyes. breathing deeply.

06:29:54.180 --> 06:29:58.560
The fire has been lit, he murmured.

06:29:58.619 --> 06:30:01.259
The smoke is rising.

06:30:01.319 --> 06:30:04.919
They are breathing it in, and me along

06:30:04.919 --> 06:30:05.279
with it.

06:30:05.340 --> 06:30:08.819
All those brave leaf wings ready to

06:30:08.819 --> 06:30:09.119
fight.

06:30:09.180 --> 06:30:12.360
Oh, there's your mother's son do.

06:30:12.419 --> 06:30:14.759
The queen will be mine soon.

06:30:14.819 --> 06:30:17.880
It's too bad the chrysalis didn't make it

06:30:17.880 --> 06:30:18.360
here in time.

06:30:18.419 --> 06:30:21.119
But I will get to them eventually.

06:30:21.180 --> 06:30:22.740
For now.

06:30:22.799 --> 06:30:25.919
At least I have these 2 sweet little silk

06:30:25.919 --> 06:30:26.700
wings to infect.

06:30:26.819 --> 06:30:31.799
Blue, Cricket said softly, tears rolling

06:30:31.799 --> 06:30:34.500
down her snout, and sword tail.

06:30:34.560 --> 06:30:38.880
And Queen Sequoia, Nettle, Belladonna

06:30:38.880 --> 06:30:41.819
Wolf's Bane, those poor dragons.

06:30:41.880 --> 06:30:45.959
Thorn sharp rage surged through sundew.

06:30:46.020 --> 06:30:48.180
She had never been so furious in her

06:30:48.180 --> 06:30:48.479
life.

06:30:48.540 --> 06:30:51.180
She felt like the vines around her should

06:30:51.180 --> 06:30:53.819
erupt into flames, like she was a white

06:30:53.819 --> 06:30:56.639
hot sun about to set the entire jungle on

06:30:56.639 --> 06:30:56.880
fire.

06:30:56.939 --> 06:31:00.779
She sank her claws into her rage, holding

06:31:00.779 --> 06:31:02.700
it close and letting it build.

06:31:02.759 --> 06:31:05.040
Her anger would get them out of this.

06:31:05.099 --> 06:31:08.400
Her fury was a weapon, and she knew where

06:31:08.400 --> 06:31:09.119
to point it now.

06:31:09.240 --> 06:31:13.500
Next important question, said the thing

06:31:13.500 --> 06:31:14.700
inside Hawthorne.

06:31:14.759 --> 06:31:18.060
Which of you 4 should I infect first?

06:31:18.119 --> 06:31:22.860
Chapter 21.

06:31:23.040 --> 06:31:25.680
Calm now.

06:31:25.740 --> 06:31:28.979
Hawthorne purred when nobody answered

06:31:28.979 --> 06:31:29.400
him.

06:31:29.459 --> 06:31:32.099
Make this easy on yourselves.

06:31:32.159 --> 06:31:35.759
He eat a tiny piece over the root or one

06:31:35.759 --> 06:31:38.220
of the seeds, and all your worries will

06:31:38.220 --> 06:31:38.580
be gone.

06:31:38.700 --> 06:31:40.380
Wouldn't you like that?

06:31:40.439 --> 06:31:42.060
Who'll go first?

06:31:42.119 --> 06:31:45.659
Sunday's eyes were locked with willows.

06:31:45.720 --> 06:31:48.599
The viper's fangs were so close to

06:31:48.599 --> 06:31:51.000
Willow's neck, no matter what sundew

06:31:51.000 --> 06:31:53.939
tried, the moment she made a move, those

06:31:53.939 --> 06:31:56.580
fangs would sink in, and Willow would be

06:31:56.580 --> 06:31:56.759
lost.

06:31:56.819 --> 06:31:59.880
Even if she could somehow kill Hawthorne

06:31:59.880 --> 06:32:01.860
in an instant, which wasn't likely.

06:32:01.919 --> 06:32:04.080
She wasn't sure that would stop the

06:32:04.080 --> 06:32:04.500
viper.

06:32:04.560 --> 06:32:06.180
As far as she could tell.

06:32:06.240 --> 06:32:08.939
The thing controlling all the dragons was

06:32:08.939 --> 06:32:10.500
also controlling the snakes.

06:32:10.560 --> 06:32:13.319
So killing Hawthorne.

06:32:13.380 --> 06:32:16.619
Even killing wasp might not be enough to

06:32:16.619 --> 06:32:16.979
stop it.

06:32:17.099 --> 06:32:21.779
Willow blinked once, twice, 3 times.

06:32:21.900 --> 06:32:24.840
She slowly rolled her eyes down into the

06:32:24.840 --> 06:32:27.119
left at the mud between her and

06:32:27.119 --> 06:32:27.720
Hawthorne.

06:32:27.779 --> 06:32:29.880
Then she looked back at sundew

06:32:29.880 --> 06:32:30.599
meaningfully.

06:32:30.599 --> 06:32:34.740
Wait, I have more questions first, Cricket

06:32:34.740 --> 06:32:35.279
babbled.

06:32:35.340 --> 06:32:37.619
Why aren't your eyes white, like the

06:32:37.619 --> 06:32:39.900
dragons who are controlled by WASP, or

06:32:39.900 --> 06:32:42.299
your voice, why isn't it all double

06:32:42.299 --> 06:32:42.779
weird?

06:32:42.840 --> 06:32:44.639
Like when WASP talks through another

06:32:44.639 --> 06:32:45.119
dragon?

06:32:45.240 --> 06:32:49.200
Sundew shifted her gaze to cricket, trying

06:32:49.200 --> 06:32:51.180
to look as though she was listening, when

06:32:51.180 --> 06:32:53.520
really, all her attention was focused on

06:32:53.520 --> 06:32:54.299
her leaf speak.

06:32:54.360 --> 06:32:56.939
She had to weave it past the creepy

06:32:56.939 --> 06:32:59.040
shivering tangle of the breath of evil

06:32:59.040 --> 06:33:01.680
burrowing through the earth around and

06:33:01.680 --> 06:33:02.099
below it.

06:33:02.159 --> 06:33:04.979
Her awareness slipped out of the nest of

06:33:04.979 --> 06:33:07.860
vines and across the stream, tiptoeing

06:33:07.860 --> 06:33:09.000
through the water wheels.

06:33:09.180 --> 06:33:11.939
The earth between Willow and Hawthorne.

06:33:12.000 --> 06:33:13.740
What had Willow seen there?

06:33:13.799 --> 06:33:16.080
What did she think sundew could use?

06:33:16.200 --> 06:33:19.139
The pitcher plants here were too small to

06:33:19.139 --> 06:33:21.479
swallow a dragon, they had to content

06:33:21.479 --> 06:33:24.360
themselves with insects, frogs, and

06:33:24.360 --> 06:33:26.700
occasional small monkeys, but they were

06:33:26.700 --> 06:33:27.720
still very smug about it.

06:33:27.779 --> 06:33:30.060
Do you know what I ate today?

06:33:30.119 --> 06:33:32.580
Well, do you know what I ate?

06:33:32.700 --> 06:33:34.560
Self important?

06:33:34.619 --> 06:33:36.540
Like all pitcher plants everywhere.

06:33:36.659 --> 06:33:39.959
Even if sundew made them enormous, they

06:33:39.959 --> 06:33:41.700
couldn't attack Hawthorne or the snake

06:33:41.700 --> 06:33:42.060
for her.

06:33:42.119 --> 06:33:44.400
They caught their prey by sitting there

06:33:44.400 --> 06:33:45.900
with their gaping mouths open.

06:33:45.959 --> 06:33:48.900
Sundew reached farther and found

06:33:48.900 --> 06:33:52.680
mushrooms, water lilies, and arrowroot.

06:33:52.740 --> 06:33:54.299
None of that would be helpful.

06:33:54.360 --> 06:33:55.740
Wait.

06:33:55.799 --> 06:33:58.500
There was a tiny sprout buried among the

06:33:58.500 --> 06:33:59.279
pitcher plants.

06:33:59.340 --> 06:34:01.500
Normally, it wouldn't survive another

06:34:01.500 --> 06:34:02.400
moon cycle.

06:34:02.459 --> 06:34:05.279
The self satisfied plants around it would

06:34:05.279 --> 06:34:07.799
crowd it out of existence and steal all

06:34:07.799 --> 06:34:09.479
its prey until it wasted away.

06:34:09.540 --> 06:34:13.740
But sundew could save it, and maybe it

06:34:13.740 --> 06:34:14.939
could save them in exchange.

06:34:15.000 --> 06:34:18.599
She had to be precise though, and fast.

06:34:18.659 --> 06:34:21.659
Hawthorne was explaining something about

06:34:21.659 --> 06:34:24.360
cells and fungi to cricket, something

06:34:24.360 --> 06:34:28.020
about the hosts or playthings of hosts

06:34:28.020 --> 06:34:30.900
having the white eyes, but not the hosts

06:34:30.900 --> 06:34:31.319
themselves.

06:34:31.380 --> 06:34:34.439
She asked another, even more scientific

06:34:34.439 --> 06:34:37.500
question, she was stalling, whether she

06:34:37.500 --> 06:34:39.060
guessed what sundew was doing or not.

06:34:39.119 --> 06:34:43.680
Hello, beautiful plant, Sundew whispered

06:34:43.680 --> 06:34:46.080
with barely a shimmer of leaf speak.

06:34:46.139 --> 06:34:48.900
She didn't want the thing to notice what

06:34:48.900 --> 06:34:50.880
she was doing, and she wouldn't be

06:34:50.880 --> 06:34:53.159
surprised if it could overhear leaf speak

06:34:53.159 --> 06:34:53.700
conversations.

06:34:53.759 --> 06:34:58.979
Oh, she realized suddenly, that's what I

06:34:58.979 --> 06:34:59.939
was hearing in the trees.

06:35:00.000 --> 06:35:02.340
They sensed the breath of evil.

06:35:02.400 --> 06:35:04.919
They were warning one another of trouble

06:35:04.919 --> 06:35:07.619
but Hawthorne was talking over them with

06:35:07.619 --> 06:35:10.380
his own leaf speak, telling them all was

06:35:10.380 --> 06:35:10.619
well.

06:35:10.680 --> 06:35:13.259
He was confusing them and me.

06:35:13.319 --> 06:35:17.459
The little plant said in a teeny, tiny

06:35:17.459 --> 06:35:17.700
voice.

06:35:17.759 --> 06:35:20.520
Would you like to be bigger?

06:35:20.639 --> 06:35:24.060
Sundu asked, in the plant's own language

06:35:24.060 --> 06:35:27.060
she sent it visions of sunshine pouring

06:35:27.060 --> 06:35:29.340
through its leaves, all the pitcher

06:35:29.340 --> 06:35:32.220
plants bowing before it. 1st choice of

06:35:32.220 --> 06:35:34.020
all the prey that wandered through.

06:35:34.080 --> 06:35:36.479
All the creatures it could eat.

06:35:36.540 --> 06:35:40.319
Ooh, the plant murmured.

06:35:40.380 --> 06:35:42.299
I can make you strong.

06:35:42.360 --> 06:35:45.779
Sundu whispered, and big and tall.

06:35:45.840 --> 06:35:48.479
If you will eat one thing for me.

06:35:48.599 --> 06:35:51.180
She showed it the viper.

06:35:51.240 --> 06:35:54.779
The slithering feel of it, the flickering

06:35:54.779 --> 06:35:55.500
danger of it.

06:35:55.560 --> 06:35:58.740
Its exact location in space relative to

06:35:58.740 --> 06:35:59.819
where the sprout could be.

06:35:59.880 --> 06:36:04.500
Ooh, would love to eat that, yes, give

06:36:04.500 --> 06:36:04.740
please.

06:36:04.799 --> 06:36:07.020
The plant said, more or less.

06:36:07.080 --> 06:36:08.639
It's yours.

06:36:08.700 --> 06:36:09.900
Take it.

06:36:09.959 --> 06:36:11.099
Take it fast.

06:36:11.159 --> 06:36:12.479
Now.

06:36:12.540 --> 06:36:15.659
Sundew shoved all her power through the

06:36:15.659 --> 06:36:18.000
systems connecting them, flooding the

06:36:18.000 --> 06:36:18.959
little plant with strength.

06:36:19.080 --> 06:36:22.979
A swarm of sundew tentacles erupted from

06:36:22.979 --> 06:36:25.500
the earth near Hawthorne's feet, bright

06:36:25.500 --> 06:36:28.080
red and green, like the daylight version

06:36:28.080 --> 06:36:29.279
of the evil vines.

06:36:29.340 --> 06:36:32.880
The sundew shot up and out, all its arms

06:36:32.880 --> 06:36:34.919
growing as thick as anacondas in the

06:36:34.919 --> 06:36:35.880
space of a heartbeat.

06:36:35.939 --> 06:36:39.119
And one aimed straight and true for the

06:36:39.119 --> 06:36:40.740
viper around Willow's neck.

06:36:40.799 --> 06:36:43.799
The sticky droplets caught the snake's

06:36:43.799 --> 06:36:47.220
tail, body, head, mouth all at once

06:36:47.220 --> 06:36:48.779
yanking it up into the air.

06:36:48.840 --> 06:36:52.500
The viper writhed furiously, snapping at

06:36:52.500 --> 06:36:53.639
the tendrils of goo.

06:36:53.700 --> 06:36:56.159
But the sundew sucked it in and rolled it

06:36:56.159 --> 06:36:59.159
up fast, like a frog catching a fly on

06:36:59.159 --> 06:36:59.880
its tongue.

06:36:59.939 --> 06:37:01.860
Or a grasshopper.

06:37:01.919 --> 06:37:04.380
How dare you?

06:37:04.500 --> 06:37:06.060
Hawthorne roared.

06:37:06.119 --> 06:37:09.119
Several of the tentacles had snared

06:37:09.119 --> 06:37:10.799
around Hawthorne as well as they shot

06:37:10.799 --> 06:37:13.139
from the ground, but Sundew could see

06:37:13.139 --> 06:37:14.459
that he was fighting them off with his

06:37:14.459 --> 06:37:15.360
own leaf speak.

06:37:15.419 --> 06:37:18.119
A few of them were withdrawing, reaching

06:37:18.119 --> 06:37:19.799
toward Willow instead as she backed

06:37:19.799 --> 06:37:19.979
away.

06:37:20.040 --> 06:37:22.919
No, Sundu commanded.

06:37:22.979 --> 06:37:24.360
Eat that big one.

06:37:24.479 --> 06:37:25.799
The infected one.

06:37:25.860 --> 06:37:26.939
Leave the other.

06:37:27.000 --> 06:37:28.200
I helped you.

06:37:28.259 --> 06:37:29.220
Listen to me.

06:37:29.279 --> 06:37:34.259
Loud, strong, loud, whine did the sundo

06:37:34.259 --> 06:37:35.880
so loud hurts.

06:37:36.000 --> 06:37:39.060
Even with her strength behind it, the

06:37:39.060 --> 06:37:40.139
sundew would give up soon.

06:37:40.200 --> 06:37:42.659
It was never meant to be an aggressive

06:37:42.659 --> 06:37:43.139
predator.

06:37:43.200 --> 06:37:45.299
She needed something else to fight

06:37:45.299 --> 06:37:47.400
Hawthorne with, and the vines were

06:37:47.400 --> 06:37:49.500
getting tighter and tighter around her.

06:37:49.560 --> 06:37:53.340
Sundoo looked around frantically, and saw

06:37:53.340 --> 06:37:55.439
with horror that one of the vines had

06:37:55.439 --> 06:37:57.479
crawled up cricket's leg and wound around

06:37:57.479 --> 06:37:59.159
her neck, squeezing.

06:37:59.220 --> 06:38:01.740
Cricket was trying to bat it away with

06:38:01.740 --> 06:38:03.840
her wings, but her breath was already

06:38:03.840 --> 06:38:05.400
coming in choked gasps.

06:38:05.459 --> 06:38:09.419
Maybe I don't need one more hive wing

06:38:09.419 --> 06:38:13.319
Hawthorne growled, especially a deceitful

06:38:13.319 --> 06:38:15.659
inquisitive one who won't shut up.

06:38:15.720 --> 06:38:18.959
Let her go, Sundu shouted.

06:38:19.020 --> 06:38:20.819
I'm the one who's all the trouble.

06:38:20.880 --> 06:38:22.080
Fight me, not her.

06:38:22.200 --> 06:38:27.119
I know you are, the thing said, but you

06:38:27.119 --> 06:38:28.259
will be useful to me.

06:38:28.319 --> 06:38:31.139
I'm going to use your leaf speak to

06:38:31.139 --> 06:38:33.540
retake my continent between you and

06:38:33.540 --> 06:38:36.779
Hawthorne, and I suppose this feeble worm

06:38:36.779 --> 06:38:39.599
over here, he added, indicating

06:38:39.599 --> 06:38:40.259
Mandrake.

06:38:40.319 --> 06:38:43.319
We can spread across all of Pentala in a

06:38:43.319 --> 06:38:43.740
matter of days.

06:38:43.799 --> 06:38:45.779
I don't think so.

06:38:45.840 --> 06:38:47.880
Willow said from above him.

06:38:47.939 --> 06:38:51.360
Hawthorne started to look up, but he was

06:38:51.360 --> 06:38:54.419
too slow to see the thorn, as long as a

06:38:54.419 --> 06:38:58.680
dragon's tail in her talons, too slow, and

06:38:58.680 --> 06:39:00.959
still too tangled in the sun do to escape

06:39:00.959 --> 06:39:02.880
or move, or fight her off.

06:39:02.939 --> 06:39:06.720
The sharp end of the thorn slammed into

06:39:06.720 --> 06:39:07.439
the base of his neck.

06:39:07.560 --> 06:39:12.240
And he fell, killed instantly, as all the

06:39:12.240 --> 06:39:15.000
breath of evil vines screamed with fury.

06:39:15.060 --> 06:39:19.619
Chapter 22.

06:39:19.860 --> 06:39:23.279
Willow let go of the thorn and lifted

06:39:23.279 --> 06:39:25.619
herself up, her wings beating as she

06:39:25.619 --> 06:39:26.819
pressed her talons to her face.

06:39:26.880 --> 06:39:29.880
Willow, Sandu cried.

06:39:29.939 --> 06:39:30.840
Get to cricket.

06:39:30.900 --> 06:39:34.139
The vines were seething with rage and

06:39:34.139 --> 06:39:34.619
confusion.

06:39:34.680 --> 06:39:37.740
As far as sundews leaf speak could gather

06:39:37.740 --> 06:39:39.959
they were bewildered by the sudden loss

06:39:39.959 --> 06:39:42.779
of Hawthorne, like arms that had been cut

06:39:42.779 --> 06:39:44.880
off an octopus, but still grabbed for

06:39:44.880 --> 06:39:45.119
prey.

06:39:45.180 --> 06:39:48.180
They'd lost their brain for a moment, but

06:39:48.180 --> 06:39:50.159
they were still deadly, and she was sure

06:39:50.159 --> 06:39:52.439
the brain was still out there, even with

06:39:52.439 --> 06:39:53.220
Hawthorne dead.

06:39:53.279 --> 06:39:56.220
Willow snatched a branch from the ground

06:39:56.220 --> 06:39:58.619
and flew to cricket, who looked close to

06:39:58.619 --> 06:39:59.099
passing out.

06:39:59.159 --> 06:40:02.939
Don't land, Sundew warned, or it might

06:40:02.939 --> 06:40:03.720
get you too.

06:40:03.779 --> 06:40:06.720
Willow nodded, hovering over the massive

06:40:06.720 --> 06:40:07.319
vines.

06:40:07.380 --> 06:40:09.540
She snapped the branch in half and

06:40:09.540 --> 06:40:12.000
stabbed the sharp splintery end into the

06:40:12.000 --> 06:40:13.319
vine near Cricket's neck.

06:40:13.380 --> 06:40:16.080
Sundu could hear that tendril hissing

06:40:16.080 --> 06:40:18.060
bleating to the others that it was

06:40:18.060 --> 06:40:18.419
wounded.

06:40:18.479 --> 06:40:21.240
But the other vines couldn't help.

06:40:21.360 --> 06:40:24.360
The plant's voice was still loud, but the

06:40:24.360 --> 06:40:26.220
power to hold the dragon's captive was

06:40:26.220 --> 06:40:26.819
fading.

06:40:27.000 --> 06:40:29.400
Sundew felt the bonds around her talons

06:40:29.400 --> 06:40:30.779
slacken and fall.

06:40:30.840 --> 06:40:34.200
Cricket gasped for breath as the one

06:40:34.200 --> 06:40:35.400
around her neck dropped away.

06:40:35.459 --> 06:40:38.459
The moment the vines were loose enough

06:40:38.459 --> 06:40:40.799
the 3 dragons all threw themselves aloft

06:40:40.799 --> 06:40:43.200
out of reach in case they moved again.

06:40:43.259 --> 06:40:46.259
Mandrake took off across the stream and

06:40:46.259 --> 06:40:48.840
into the trees, and the other 3 followed

06:40:48.840 --> 06:40:50.759
him high up into the branches of a giant

06:40:50.759 --> 06:40:51.540
baobab.

06:40:51.599 --> 06:40:54.779
Sundew through her wings around Willow as

06:40:54.779 --> 06:40:55.439
soon as they landed.

06:40:55.500 --> 06:40:57.720
They held each other for a long moment

06:40:57.720 --> 06:41:00.119
without speaking, their necks curved

06:41:00.119 --> 06:41:00.659
around each other.

06:41:00.720 --> 06:41:03.540
Their hearts beating as fast as rain in a

06:41:03.540 --> 06:41:04.139
thunderstorm.

06:41:04.200 --> 06:41:06.779
Why did the vines let go?

06:41:06.840 --> 06:41:09.299
Cricket asked in a shaky voice.

06:41:09.360 --> 06:41:11.580
I thought there was something out there

06:41:11.580 --> 06:41:14.520
controlling Hawthorne, and the snakes, and

06:41:14.520 --> 06:41:15.299
the vines too.

06:41:15.419 --> 06:41:18.959
Maybe it's dead, Mandrake said

06:41:18.959 --> 06:41:19.259
hopefully.

06:41:19.319 --> 06:41:22.200
Sundu let go of Willow reluctantly and

06:41:22.200 --> 06:41:22.799
shook her head.

06:41:22.860 --> 06:41:24.299
No.

06:41:24.360 --> 06:41:27.060
Willow killed one of its heads, but it's

06:41:27.060 --> 06:41:27.779
got more than one.

06:41:27.840 --> 06:41:31.680
It still has WASP, Willow agreed.

06:41:31.740 --> 06:41:34.680
They all fell silent, thinking of the

06:41:34.680 --> 06:41:36.479
other dragons it might have by now.

06:41:36.540 --> 06:41:38.759
The dragons near the smoke.

06:41:38.880 --> 06:41:41.819
Sundew pressed one of Willow's talons

06:41:41.819 --> 06:41:42.419
between hers.

06:41:42.540 --> 06:41:45.360
That was a pretty important head, though.

06:41:45.479 --> 06:41:48.360
I think the thing was using Hawthorne's

06:41:48.360 --> 06:41:50.459
leaf speak to make the vines attack us.

06:41:50.459 --> 06:41:53.040
Without his leaf speak to control them

06:41:53.040 --> 06:41:55.319
the vines can't move any more than

06:41:55.319 --> 06:41:56.279
ordinary plants can.

06:41:56.340 --> 06:41:59.099
What do we do now?

06:41:59.099 --> 06:41:59.639
Cricket asked.

06:41:59.700 --> 06:42:02.400
We fly to the border and try to save our

06:42:02.400 --> 06:42:05.520
tribe, Sundu said, and our friends.

06:42:05.580 --> 06:42:07.500
She lashed her tail.

06:42:07.560 --> 06:42:10.619
We fight that thing, and kill it exactly

06:42:10.619 --> 06:42:11.459
the way Willow did.

06:42:11.520 --> 06:42:14.159
I don't know about you, but I'm ready to

06:42:14.159 --> 06:42:15.060
kill it a lot.

06:42:15.119 --> 06:42:19.500
Wait, Willow said. pulling sundew's

06:42:19.500 --> 06:42:20.220
talons toward her.

06:42:20.279 --> 06:42:23.520
No, that's exactly what we shouldn't do.

06:42:23.580 --> 06:42:25.500
What?

06:42:25.560 --> 06:42:27.540
Sundew flared her wings.

06:42:27.659 --> 06:42:28.740
We have to.

06:42:28.799 --> 06:42:30.060
We have to go now.

06:42:30.180 --> 06:42:32.819
I really want to destroy some things.

06:42:32.939 --> 06:42:37.439
The 4 of us, against the entire hive wing

06:42:37.439 --> 06:42:40.860
tribe, Queen Wasp, all the best leaf wing

06:42:40.860 --> 06:42:43.979
fighters, and our friends, Willow said.

06:42:44.040 --> 06:42:46.259
We don't even know what to destroy.

06:42:46.319 --> 06:42:48.360
She is right.

06:42:48.419 --> 06:42:49.500
Cricket said.

06:42:49.560 --> 06:42:53.159
I'm all for killing Queen Wasp, but if

06:42:53.159 --> 06:42:54.659
that thing can be in any dragon.

06:42:54.720 --> 06:42:56.279
What are we supposed to do?

06:42:56.340 --> 06:42:57.840
Kill everyone?

06:42:57.900 --> 06:43:00.779
We're not doing that, and you know it

06:43:00.779 --> 06:43:01.200
sundo.

06:43:01.319 --> 06:43:03.240
She did know it.

06:43:03.360 --> 06:43:05.880
Even if there was a way to kill all the

06:43:05.880 --> 06:43:07.919
hive wings, she didn't think she could

06:43:07.919 --> 06:43:08.520
after all.

06:43:08.580 --> 06:43:11.279
Not now that she knew hive wings she

06:43:11.279 --> 06:43:13.799
cared about, or now that she'd learned

06:43:13.799 --> 06:43:16.200
the truth behind all of this, and what

06:43:16.200 --> 06:43:17.580
the leaf wings had done to them.

06:43:17.639 --> 06:43:20.099
And especially not now that she'd heard

06:43:20.099 --> 06:43:21.540
the voice of their true enemy.

06:43:21.599 --> 06:43:26.099
And, of course, she could never hurt Blue

06:43:26.099 --> 06:43:29.639
or Queen Sequoia, or Swordtail, or even

06:43:29.639 --> 06:43:32.400
Belladonna, who usually made her madder

06:43:32.400 --> 06:43:32.939
than anyone.

06:43:33.000 --> 06:43:36.540
If they were all lost to the thing, and

06:43:36.540 --> 06:43:39.360
she felt grimly certain they were, there

06:43:39.360 --> 06:43:40.919
would just have to be another way to save

06:43:40.919 --> 06:43:41.220
them.

06:43:41.279 --> 06:43:44.880
Fine, yes, but we still have to go see

06:43:44.880 --> 06:43:45.540
what's happening.

06:43:45.599 --> 06:43:48.119
We have to fight, she argued.

06:43:48.180 --> 06:43:51.360
We will fight, Willow said.

06:43:51.419 --> 06:43:54.060
We'll use this rage, I promise.

06:43:54.119 --> 06:43:56.340
We have to start by using it to save

06:43:56.340 --> 06:43:57.000
everyone else.

06:43:57.060 --> 06:44:00.240
I want to go to Blue more than anyone

06:44:00.240 --> 06:44:01.439
Cricket said.

06:44:01.500 --> 06:44:03.959
But I also need to make sure this doesn't

06:44:03.959 --> 06:44:04.979
happen to bumblebee.

06:44:05.040 --> 06:44:08.159
Or Hazel, Willow agreed.

06:44:08.220 --> 06:44:10.680
We need to protect the dragons who are

06:44:10.680 --> 06:44:12.720
left, so we have someone to fight with

06:44:12.720 --> 06:44:13.500
us.

06:44:13.560 --> 06:44:17.040
Sundew dug her claws into the branch and

06:44:17.040 --> 06:44:18.240
felt the tree wince.

06:44:18.299 --> 06:44:19.319
Sorry.

06:44:19.380 --> 06:44:21.900
She flickered through her leaf beak

06:44:21.900 --> 06:44:24.180
sending a filament of comfort out to

06:44:24.180 --> 06:44:25.860
smooth over the scratched bark.

06:44:25.919 --> 06:44:27.180
All right.

06:44:27.240 --> 06:44:29.400
All right, she said.

06:44:29.459 --> 06:44:30.479
Let's go.

06:44:30.540 --> 06:44:33.840
They sped through the trees as fast as

06:44:33.840 --> 06:44:35.819
they could move, keeping to the higher

06:44:35.819 --> 06:44:37.799
branches, where there was more room to

06:44:37.799 --> 06:44:40.380
fly, at least sometimes.

06:44:40.439 --> 06:44:43.380
Sundew's village was 1st, closer to the

06:44:43.380 --> 06:44:44.279
snarling river.

06:44:44.340 --> 06:44:46.680
Sundir reached out to the dome as they

06:44:46.680 --> 06:44:49.020
arrived, and moved the plants to make a

06:44:49.020 --> 06:44:49.799
hole near the top.

06:44:49.860 --> 06:44:52.979
They hurtled through, startling all the

06:44:52.979 --> 06:44:53.759
dragons below them.

06:44:53.880 --> 06:44:56.400
It took several moments of confusion

06:44:56.400 --> 06:44:59.639
hissing, yelling, and threats before the

06:44:59.639 --> 06:45:02.040
villagers realized that their savior's

06:45:02.040 --> 06:45:04.380
sundew was one of the attacking dragons.

06:45:04.439 --> 06:45:07.319
That cricket was their erstwhile hive

06:45:07.319 --> 06:45:09.240
wing prisoner, and that they weren't an

06:45:09.240 --> 06:45:11.159
advance party of invaders from Queen

06:45:11.159 --> 06:45:11.759
Wasp.

06:45:11.819 --> 06:45:15.419
But they are coming, Sundu said, we have

06:45:15.419 --> 06:45:18.060
to fall back to the other, to the sapwing

06:45:18.060 --> 06:45:19.979
village and regroup with the dragons

06:45:19.979 --> 06:45:20.220
there.

06:45:20.279 --> 06:45:22.680
Fall back?

06:45:22.740 --> 06:45:24.479
Cobra Lily objected.

06:45:24.540 --> 06:45:28.680
Are you saying we lost already?

06:45:28.740 --> 06:45:30.959
Is Belladonna dead?

06:45:31.020 --> 06:45:33.240
Several voices asked in alarm.

06:45:33.299 --> 06:45:36.840
Not exactly, but she's lost to us right

06:45:36.840 --> 06:45:37.200
now.

06:45:37.259 --> 06:45:38.520
Sundu said.

06:45:38.580 --> 06:45:41.159
I can explain everything, but I'd rather

06:45:41.159 --> 06:45:44.099
do it once to everyone, and I'd rather do

06:45:44.099 --> 06:45:46.200
it after we get all our dragonettes out

06:45:46.200 --> 06:45:46.439
of here.

06:45:46.500 --> 06:45:49.799
Leaf wings don't run away. someone

06:45:49.799 --> 06:45:50.400
shouted.

06:45:50.459 --> 06:45:51.840
We stand and fight.

06:45:51.900 --> 06:45:54.840
We bear our fangs and raise our claws and

06:45:54.840 --> 06:45:57.840
and end up as mind controlled zombies

06:45:57.840 --> 06:45:59.040
just like the hive wings.

06:45:59.099 --> 06:46:00.360
Sundew snapped.

06:46:00.419 --> 06:46:01.680
Don't be idiots.

06:46:01.740 --> 06:46:03.419
This isn't a normal threat.

06:46:03.479 --> 06:46:06.419
We have to find an unnormal way to fight

06:46:06.419 --> 06:46:09.119
it, and we need all the dragons we can

06:46:09.119 --> 06:46:11.939
gather, so we get to safety 1st, then

06:46:11.939 --> 06:46:12.599
make a plan.

06:46:12.659 --> 06:46:15.240
I'll round up the dragonettes.

06:46:15.299 --> 06:46:17.520
Cobra Lily said unexpectedly.

06:46:17.580 --> 06:46:20.459
She loped gracefully off to the nursery

06:46:20.459 --> 06:46:22.799
area, and several other dragons followed

06:46:22.799 --> 06:46:22.979
her.

06:46:23.040 --> 06:46:25.860
Several more stayed to keep arguing with

06:46:25.860 --> 06:46:28.680
Sundoo, but she ignored them and flew to

06:46:28.680 --> 06:46:31.200
the outer wall of the dome, the same spot

06:46:31.200 --> 06:46:32.700
where she used to sneak out to meet

06:46:32.700 --> 06:46:33.240
Willow.

06:46:33.299 --> 06:46:35.880
She rested one talon on the woven

06:46:35.880 --> 06:46:39.000
branches and nudged them apart, hoping

06:46:39.000 --> 06:46:40.799
they felt her love for them as she did.

06:46:40.860 --> 06:46:43.500
She loved all the plants that made up

06:46:43.500 --> 06:46:46.080
this dome, which she'd built to protect

06:46:46.080 --> 06:46:47.099
her tribe.

06:46:47.159 --> 06:46:48.360
She hated to leave it.

06:46:48.419 --> 06:46:51.119
She hated to imagine the breath of evil

06:46:51.119 --> 06:46:53.639
slithering over it, stealing its light

06:46:53.639 --> 06:46:55.020
and smothering it.

06:46:55.080 --> 06:46:57.900
Dragons began climbing out through the

06:46:57.900 --> 06:46:58.200
hole.

06:46:58.259 --> 06:47:00.540
She tried to count them all, but lost

06:47:00.540 --> 06:47:01.439
track around 50.

06:47:01.740 --> 06:47:04.020
She guessed about a 3rd of the village

06:47:04.020 --> 06:47:04.500
was here.

06:47:04.560 --> 06:47:06.779
Most of them probably planning to be

06:47:06.779 --> 06:47:08.759
called up as the next wave of soldiers.

06:47:08.819 --> 06:47:11.279
A lot of them were carrying weapons of

06:47:11.279 --> 06:47:11.759
some sort.

06:47:11.819 --> 06:47:15.000
Many of them had pouches like hers slung

06:47:15.000 --> 06:47:17.400
around them, hopefully full of useful

06:47:17.400 --> 06:47:18.119
deadly things.

06:47:18.180 --> 06:47:21.180
She wished she had time to refill her own

06:47:21.180 --> 06:47:23.400
pouches, but she'd have to do that later

06:47:23.400 --> 06:47:25.500
when all the dragons were somewhere

06:47:25.500 --> 06:47:25.860
safer.

06:47:25.919 --> 06:47:29.759
They moved a bit slower now, hampered by

06:47:29.759 --> 06:47:31.860
their numbers, and the slowest among them

06:47:31.860 --> 06:47:34.200
including 2 dragonettes who couldn't fly

06:47:34.200 --> 06:47:36.959
yet, one elder who hadn't left the

06:47:36.959 --> 06:47:39.720
village in years, and 3 limping dragons

06:47:39.720 --> 06:47:41.520
who'd been recently wounded by various

06:47:41.520 --> 06:47:42.360
jungle dangers.

06:47:42.479 --> 06:47:45.900
Do you think WASP in the army are right

06:47:45.900 --> 06:47:46.439
behind us?

06:47:46.500 --> 06:47:49.740
Mandrake worried, pacing beside Sundew?

06:47:49.799 --> 06:47:51.419
How soon could they get here?

06:47:51.479 --> 06:47:54.479
I'm surprised we haven't seen anyone

06:47:54.479 --> 06:47:54.840
yet.

06:47:54.900 --> 06:47:57.060
Willow admitted in a low voice.

06:47:57.180 --> 06:48:00.360
I would have thought the, the other mind

06:48:00.360 --> 06:48:02.759
would have sent something to chase us

06:48:02.759 --> 06:48:04.500
down as soon as Hawthorne died.

06:48:04.560 --> 06:48:07.799
Maybe the smoke didn't reach all the leaf

06:48:07.799 --> 06:48:09.479
wings, and they were giving it a fight.

06:48:09.540 --> 06:48:13.020
Sundew guest, feeling proud of them, and

06:48:13.020 --> 06:48:14.520
horribly worried for them at the same

06:48:14.520 --> 06:48:14.880
time.

06:48:14.939 --> 06:48:18.900
Also, it doesn't know where to go, Cricket

06:48:18.900 --> 06:48:19.319
said.

06:48:19.380 --> 06:48:20.400
What?

06:48:20.459 --> 06:48:22.200
Willow tilted her head.

06:48:22.259 --> 06:48:25.740
When Wasp takes over a dragon, she

06:48:25.740 --> 06:48:27.840
doesn't get his memories and thoughts and

06:48:27.840 --> 06:48:29.459
knowledge, Cricket said.

06:48:29.520 --> 06:48:31.740
The other mind might have stolen our

06:48:31.740 --> 06:48:33.720
friends, but it doesn't know everything

06:48:33.720 --> 06:48:34.619
they know.

06:48:34.680 --> 06:48:36.720
It wouldn't know the way to Sundew's

06:48:36.720 --> 06:48:37.020
village.

06:48:37.080 --> 06:48:40.500
But it will know the way to mine, Willow

06:48:40.500 --> 06:48:43.080
said, because it was there inside

06:48:43.080 --> 06:48:43.919
Hawthorne.

06:48:43.979 --> 06:48:47.639
That's true, Cricket said, although it

06:48:47.639 --> 06:48:49.259
might have trouble remembering the way

06:48:49.259 --> 06:48:50.939
since it didn't come from the border

06:48:50.939 --> 06:48:53.520
before, and without Hawthorne's leaf

06:48:53.520 --> 06:48:55.919
speak, it won't be able to clear sundews

06:48:55.919 --> 06:48:58.439
and dragon traps out of its way, like

06:48:58.439 --> 06:48:59.939
sundew is doing for us right now.

06:49:00.000 --> 06:49:03.659
Sundu was surprised that she'd noticed.

06:49:03.720 --> 06:49:06.000
She was doing it almost automatically

06:49:06.000 --> 06:49:08.340
sending her leaf speak out ahead of the

06:49:08.340 --> 06:49:09.599
group to check for dangers.

06:49:09.659 --> 06:49:13.740
So, when we met Hawthorne in the den of

06:49:13.740 --> 06:49:17.580
vipers, Mandrake said slowly, were we

06:49:17.580 --> 06:49:19.979
talking to the real Hawthorne, or the

06:49:19.979 --> 06:49:20.819
thing inside him?

06:49:20.939 --> 06:49:23.400
It seems like it had all of Hawthorne's

06:49:23.400 --> 06:49:23.759
memories.

06:49:23.819 --> 06:49:27.060
I think it was the real Hawthorne, cricket

06:49:27.060 --> 06:49:27.540
said.

06:49:27.599 --> 06:49:30.659
But he's spent the last 50 years being

06:49:30.659 --> 06:49:32.639
manipulated by that voice in his head.

06:49:32.700 --> 06:49:35.400
He might not have known what it was going

06:49:35.400 --> 06:49:36.060
to do.

06:49:36.119 --> 06:49:38.639
Maybe he didn't even know the antidote

06:49:38.639 --> 06:49:39.119
wasn't real.

06:49:39.180 --> 06:49:41.819
But he was doing what it wanted him to do

06:49:41.819 --> 06:49:44.400
even when it wasn't controlling him.

06:49:44.459 --> 06:49:46.860
Sundew shuddered.

06:49:46.979 --> 06:49:51.119
Imagine spending 50 years alone, with no

06:49:51.119 --> 06:49:53.040
one but an evil voice to talk to.

06:49:53.099 --> 06:49:55.619
Perhaps Hawthorne had been more than

06:49:55.619 --> 06:49:57.060
adequately punished after all.

06:49:57.119 --> 06:50:01.439
Do we need to talk about what it is?

06:50:01.439 --> 06:50:03.180
Mandrake asked.

06:50:03.240 --> 06:50:05.279
What's using the plant to control

06:50:05.279 --> 06:50:05.880
everyone?

06:50:05.939 --> 06:50:09.240
And is it the same dragon who used it all

06:50:09.240 --> 06:50:11.880
those 1000s of years ago in the legend of

06:50:11.880 --> 06:50:12.419
the hive?

06:50:12.419 --> 06:50:13.619
Cricket asked.

06:50:13.680 --> 06:50:15.779
If so, where is he?

06:50:15.840 --> 06:50:17.880
And why hasn't he come out in all these

06:50:17.880 --> 06:50:18.360
years?

06:50:18.419 --> 06:50:21.360
Or is it a group of dragons, and are they

06:50:21.360 --> 06:50:22.200
hiding somewhere?

06:50:22.259 --> 06:50:24.900
Sundew looked over at Willow.

06:50:24.959 --> 06:50:27.779
And she saw from Willow's face that she

06:50:27.779 --> 06:50:29.459
had come to the same conclusion as

06:50:29.459 --> 06:50:30.060
sundew.

06:50:30.119 --> 06:50:32.700
I think it's not a dragon.

06:50:32.819 --> 06:50:34.680
Sundu said slowly.

06:50:34.740 --> 06:50:37.979
I think it's the plant itself.

06:50:38.040 --> 06:50:39.779
Willow nodded.

06:50:39.840 --> 06:50:42.240
Cricket blinked at her.

06:50:42.299 --> 06:50:43.740
The planned?

06:50:43.799 --> 06:50:45.180
But how?

06:50:45.240 --> 06:50:49.020
That's plants don't have a consciousness

06:50:49.020 --> 06:50:51.900
or a voice, or make sinister evil plans?

06:50:51.959 --> 06:50:56.400
Some of them do, actually, Sundew said, I

06:50:56.400 --> 06:50:57.180
can vouch for that.

06:50:57.240 --> 06:51:00.540
They don't usually have voices like ours

06:51:00.540 --> 06:51:02.400
and I'm guessing this one didn't until

06:51:02.400 --> 06:51:04.740
dragons came along and did adapted to use

06:51:04.740 --> 06:51:05.040
us.

06:51:05.099 --> 06:51:07.380
Yeesh.

06:51:07.439 --> 06:51:10.380
Mandrake said, stepping carefully over a

06:51:10.380 --> 06:51:13.139
fallen branch, and eyeing it as though it

06:51:13.139 --> 06:51:14.759
might suddenly leap up to attack him.

06:51:14.819 --> 06:51:18.299
It's just a guess, Willow added.

06:51:18.360 --> 06:51:20.639
We need to find out more so we can stop

06:51:20.639 --> 06:51:20.880
it.

06:51:20.939 --> 06:51:24.060
It was late morning when they reached the

06:51:24.060 --> 06:51:25.200
other leaf wing camp.

06:51:25.259 --> 06:51:27.840
Sundew had seen the guards patrolling in

06:51:27.840 --> 06:51:30.360
the trees, watching them arrive, but

06:51:30.360 --> 06:51:31.500
nobody came out to stop them.

06:51:31.560 --> 06:51:35.220
We'll have to warn them that not all leaf

06:51:35.220 --> 06:51:36.240
wings can be trusted anymore.

06:51:36.299 --> 06:51:39.540
She thought with a shiver, now that

06:51:39.540 --> 06:51:41.340
anyone could have the enemy lurking

06:51:41.340 --> 06:51:41.819
inside them.

06:51:41.880 --> 06:51:44.759
They left the dragons from Sundu's

06:51:44.759 --> 06:51:46.860
village, gathered in a huddle in the

06:51:46.860 --> 06:51:48.959
biggest clearing, glaring up at the

06:51:48.959 --> 06:51:50.340
curious dragons around them.

06:51:50.459 --> 06:51:53.220
Bumblebee came galloping across the

06:51:53.220 --> 06:51:55.020
throne room when cricket and sundew

06:51:55.020 --> 06:51:57.299
landed, her wings flopping to either side

06:51:57.299 --> 06:51:58.139
of her.

06:51:58.200 --> 06:52:01.020
To sundew's surprise, she beelined

06:52:01.020 --> 06:52:02.880
straight for sundew and bonked into her

06:52:02.880 --> 06:52:05.099
feet, bouncing and reaching to be picked

06:52:05.099 --> 06:52:05.819
up.

06:52:05.880 --> 06:52:09.240
Hey, little bug, Sundew said, lifting

06:52:09.240 --> 06:52:09.479
her.

06:52:09.479 --> 06:52:12.000
The dragonette's yellow and black stripes

06:52:12.000 --> 06:52:13.860
seemed cuter than they had the day before

06:52:13.860 --> 06:52:16.560
and her snout was warm as she snuggled

06:52:16.560 --> 06:52:17.700
into Sundew's neck.

06:52:17.759 --> 06:52:21.599
Sundew found herself feeling weirdly glad

06:52:21.599 --> 06:52:23.759
that they'd come back instead of going to

06:52:23.759 --> 06:52:24.119
fight.

06:52:24.240 --> 06:52:26.639
Saving bumblebee from the other mind.

06:52:26.700 --> 06:52:28.860
That would be worth it.

06:52:28.919 --> 06:52:30.779
What has happened to me?

06:52:30.840 --> 06:52:33.959
Tsunami and Turtle were the only other

06:52:33.959 --> 06:52:36.360
ones there, both of them still leaning

06:52:36.360 --> 06:52:37.560
over the book of Clearsight.

06:52:37.619 --> 06:52:39.180
Any luck?

06:52:39.240 --> 06:52:40.500
Willow asked them.

06:52:40.560 --> 06:52:42.119
Tsunami shook her head.

06:52:42.180 --> 06:52:43.259
Not yet.

06:52:43.319 --> 06:52:46.319
I must admit, I like this clear side a

06:52:46.319 --> 06:52:47.520
bit better than I did before, though.

06:52:47.639 --> 06:52:50.520
Why did you ever not like her?

06:52:50.580 --> 06:52:53.220
Cricket asked, obviously shocked.

06:52:53.279 --> 06:52:56.040
Because I thought she was an idiot who

06:52:56.040 --> 06:52:58.020
nearly let her boyfriend destroy the

06:52:58.020 --> 06:52:59.700
world, tsunami said.

06:52:59.759 --> 06:53:02.639
Although, to be fair, I guess so did we.

06:53:02.759 --> 06:53:04.259
What?

06:53:04.380 --> 06:53:05.400
Willow asked.

06:53:05.459 --> 06:53:08.220
Long story. tsunami said.

06:53:08.279 --> 06:53:11.220
They turned as Hazel swept into the room

06:53:11.220 --> 06:53:13.139
with a few leaf wing guards behind her.

06:53:13.200 --> 06:53:15.419
Where's Inchworm?

06:53:15.479 --> 06:53:18.240
Sundu asked, if he was still here, in the

06:53:18.240 --> 06:53:20.159
village, with wasp inside him.

06:53:20.220 --> 06:53:23.220
I had my guards take him back to the

06:53:23.220 --> 06:53:25.080
snarling river, Hazel said.

06:53:25.139 --> 06:53:26.819
Why, what happened?

06:53:26.880 --> 06:53:28.020
Where's the Queen?

06:53:28.080 --> 06:53:29.400
Did the antidote work?

06:53:29.459 --> 06:53:32.459
Willow told her the whole story, as

06:53:32.459 --> 06:53:34.080
quickly and briefly as she could.

06:53:34.139 --> 06:53:37.080
By the end of it, Hazel was looking as

06:53:37.080 --> 06:53:38.459
shattered as Sundew felt.

06:53:38.520 --> 06:53:41.939
So you think this other mind got

06:53:41.939 --> 06:53:43.139
everyone?

06:53:43.139 --> 06:53:44.099
she asked.

06:53:44.159 --> 06:53:47.700
I think we have to assume so, Sundu

06:53:47.700 --> 06:53:48.060
answered.

06:53:48.119 --> 06:53:50.459
Even if the smoke didn't reach all the

06:53:50.459 --> 06:53:52.680
leaf wings, all it needed was Queen

06:53:52.680 --> 06:53:53.520
Sequoia.

06:53:53.580 --> 06:53:55.979
Once it had her, it could convince

06:53:55.979 --> 06:53:58.919
everyone else to take the antidote, and

06:53:58.919 --> 06:54:00.479
no one would know that wasn't a normal

06:54:00.479 --> 06:54:01.560
order from our queen.

06:54:01.680 --> 06:54:05.939
So, we have to get everyone and hide

06:54:05.939 --> 06:54:08.939
somewhere, Hazel said, rubbing her

06:54:08.939 --> 06:54:09.299
forehead.

06:54:09.360 --> 06:54:11.459
She turned to the guards and put on her

06:54:11.459 --> 06:54:12.360
queen voice.

06:54:12.599 --> 06:54:14.340
Gather the entire tribe.

06:54:14.400 --> 06:54:16.799
Tell them we're using the evacuation plan

06:54:16.799 --> 06:54:18.000
and moving out before noon.

06:54:18.060 --> 06:54:20.220
Pack lightly, if at all.

06:54:20.279 --> 06:54:21.360
Bring weapons.

06:54:21.419 --> 06:54:23.700
Try not to panic the dragonettes.

06:54:23.819 --> 06:54:26.520
Tell them, tell them all is not lost.

06:54:26.580 --> 06:54:29.759
If we move swiftly, make sure they know

06:54:29.759 --> 06:54:31.860
we can still save our queen and our

06:54:31.860 --> 06:54:33.900
friends, and that I'll tell them more

06:54:33.900 --> 06:54:35.159
once we reach safety.

06:54:35.159 --> 06:54:37.500
But where is that?

06:54:37.619 --> 06:54:40.439
Willow asked, as the guards nodded and

06:54:40.439 --> 06:54:40.860
flew away.

06:54:40.919 --> 06:54:43.919
We can keep retreating farther into the

06:54:43.919 --> 06:54:46.139
jungle, but eventually we'll hit the

06:54:46.139 --> 06:54:46.680
ocean.

06:54:46.740 --> 06:54:49.919
So then we cross it, Cricket said.

06:54:49.979 --> 06:54:51.779
I still think we have to get to the

06:54:51.779 --> 06:54:52.680
distant kingdoms.

06:54:52.740 --> 06:54:54.659
That's our only hope.

06:54:54.840 --> 06:54:56.040
How?

06:54:56.220 --> 06:54:58.680
tsunami said, slamming the book of clear

06:54:58.680 --> 06:54:59.520
sight shut.

06:54:59.580 --> 06:55:01.080
This thing is no use.

06:55:01.200 --> 06:55:04.080
Turtle and I can't swim 100s of you

06:55:04.080 --> 06:55:04.619
across.

06:55:04.680 --> 06:55:07.979
Let me see that book, Hazel said.

06:55:08.040 --> 06:55:10.979
Turtle brought it over to her, and she

06:55:10.979 --> 06:55:13.200
flipped through it, brushing her claws

06:55:13.200 --> 06:55:14.159
across the pages.

06:55:14.220 --> 06:55:16.439
Sundew tried to think.

06:55:16.500 --> 06:55:19.020
Maybe we could build giant floating

06:55:19.020 --> 06:55:22.080
platforms, she thought, and pile everyone

06:55:22.080 --> 06:55:25.319
onto them, and take turns pulling them

06:55:25.319 --> 06:55:25.979
across the ocean.

06:55:26.040 --> 06:55:29.279
She had a notion, although she wasn't

06:55:29.279 --> 06:55:31.439
sure where it had come from that their

06:55:31.439 --> 06:55:33.540
earliest ancestors had arrived here that

06:55:33.540 --> 06:55:34.799
way, more or less.

06:55:34.860 --> 06:55:37.860
But we don't have time to build platforms

06:55:37.860 --> 06:55:39.959
big enough for all the remaining leaf

06:55:39.959 --> 06:55:40.860
wings.

06:55:40.919 --> 06:55:42.000
Maybe we do.

06:55:42.060 --> 06:55:44.759
Maybe we can buy ourselves time.

06:55:44.880 --> 06:55:48.060
If I go back and fight, with Cobra Lily

06:55:48.060 --> 06:55:50.400
and some of the others, while everyone

06:55:50.400 --> 06:55:51.299
else starts building.

06:55:51.360 --> 06:55:55.439
This book feels weird, Hazel said in her

06:55:55.439 --> 06:55:57.599
regular voice, turning it over and

06:55:57.599 --> 06:55:59.040
running one talon over the back.

06:55:59.159 --> 06:56:01.619
I can't say I approve of whoever

06:56:01.619 --> 06:56:02.040
bounded.

06:56:02.099 --> 06:56:05.099
Willow cracked a smile for the 1st time

06:56:05.099 --> 06:56:05.639
all day.

06:56:05.700 --> 06:56:08.819
Trust you to care about the book binding

06:56:08.819 --> 06:56:11.700
of the ancient magical sacred text, she

06:56:11.700 --> 06:56:11.939
said.

06:56:12.000 --> 06:56:14.939
Well, look at how the bat cover is

06:56:14.939 --> 06:56:16.139
thicker than the front cover.

06:56:16.200 --> 06:56:17.459
That's just messy.

06:56:17.520 --> 06:56:20.040
The end pages are sewn down with these

06:56:20.040 --> 06:56:21.360
perfect little stitches.

06:56:21.419 --> 06:56:25.319
It looks like gold thread, but maybe it's

06:56:25.319 --> 06:56:26.159
flame silk.

06:56:26.220 --> 06:56:27.720
The kind that doesn't burn.

06:56:27.779 --> 06:56:30.180
So someone put all this effort into

06:56:30.180 --> 06:56:32.340
perfectly sewing down the end papers

06:56:32.340 --> 06:56:34.860
around the edges, but left the middle all

06:56:34.860 --> 06:56:35.279
lumpy.

06:56:35.340 --> 06:56:39.119
She stared at the inside back cover for a

06:56:39.119 --> 06:56:39.360
moment.

06:56:39.419 --> 06:56:40.919
Hazel.

06:56:40.979 --> 06:56:42.419
What are you doing?

06:56:42.479 --> 06:56:46.319
Cricket gasped, as the leaf wing sliced a

06:56:46.319 --> 06:56:48.000
long slit around the edges of the last

06:56:48.000 --> 06:56:48.900
end paper?

06:56:48.959 --> 06:56:51.000
You're destroying the book.

06:56:51.119 --> 06:56:53.819
But Hazel wasn't listening.

06:56:53.880 --> 06:56:56.459
She reached 2 claws between the paper and

06:56:56.459 --> 06:56:59.520
the leather, and carefully, delicately

06:56:59.520 --> 06:57:02.040
slid out the folded page that was hidden

06:57:02.040 --> 06:57:02.279
inside.

06:57:02.400 --> 06:57:06.060
It felt as if the whole world was holding

06:57:06.060 --> 06:57:06.479
its breath.

06:57:06.540 --> 06:57:09.599
Sundew wasn't sure why this felt so

06:57:09.599 --> 06:57:10.020
important.

06:57:10.080 --> 06:57:12.599
It would probably be something like the

06:57:12.599 --> 06:57:14.700
rest of the book, a prophecy about

06:57:14.700 --> 06:57:17.340
something that happened centuries ago, or

06:57:17.340 --> 06:57:19.080
another sentimental letter about being

06:57:19.080 --> 06:57:19.979
nice to one another.

06:57:20.040 --> 06:57:24.119
And yet, even her scales prickled with

06:57:24.119 --> 06:57:27.240
anticipation as Hazel carefully unfolded

06:57:27.240 --> 06:57:28.439
the secret note.

06:57:28.500 --> 06:57:31.500
It's a map.

06:57:31.560 --> 06:57:33.299
She said wonderingly.

06:57:33.360 --> 06:57:37.799
Chapter 23.

06:57:38.099 --> 06:57:41.580
Hazel spread out the map on the throne

06:57:41.580 --> 06:57:43.439
and they all crowded around to look at

06:57:43.439 --> 06:57:43.799
it.

06:57:43.860 --> 06:57:46.080
The ink was faded, but still legible.

06:57:46.139 --> 06:57:49.319
Sundew stared at the odd shapes, and

06:57:49.319 --> 06:57:51.659
recognized the peninsulas that jutted

06:57:51.659 --> 06:57:52.740
into Dragonfly Bay.

06:57:52.799 --> 06:57:55.680
Willow leaned against her shoulder, her

06:57:55.680 --> 06:57:56.939
scales warm and smooth.

06:57:57.000 --> 06:58:00.959
That must be the distant kingdoms, Cricket

06:58:00.959 --> 06:58:03.360
said, pointing to the coastline on the

06:58:03.360 --> 06:58:04.979
far right hand edge of the map.

06:58:05.040 --> 06:58:07.740
Yes, tsunami agreed.

06:58:07.799 --> 06:58:10.139
That's the ice kingdom up here, the

06:58:10.139 --> 06:58:11.639
kingdom of sand all along here.

06:58:11.700 --> 06:58:15.419
And this is the eastern coast of Pantala

06:58:15.419 --> 06:58:18.360
Hazel said, pointing to the coastline on

06:58:18.360 --> 06:58:18.599
the left.

06:58:18.720 --> 06:58:22.139
Even in a one page drawing, the distance

06:58:22.139 --> 06:58:24.119
between the 2 continents looked immense

06:58:24.119 --> 06:58:25.979
uncrossable.

06:58:26.040 --> 06:58:27.419
Sundew's heart sank.

06:58:27.540 --> 06:58:31.380
So these dots in between, Turtle said

06:58:31.380 --> 06:58:33.659
could those be islands?

06:58:33.720 --> 06:58:36.720
Yes, Cricket cried, making them all

06:58:36.720 --> 06:58:37.500
jump.

06:58:37.560 --> 06:58:38.279
That's it.

06:58:38.340 --> 06:58:39.540
They're islands.

06:58:39.599 --> 06:58:40.380
Look.

06:58:40.439 --> 06:58:42.720
Clearsight drew little arrows from one to

06:58:42.720 --> 06:58:43.139
the next.

06:58:43.200 --> 06:58:44.279
Start here.

06:58:44.340 --> 06:58:47.759
Then fly here, then here, next.

06:58:47.880 --> 06:58:50.939
Her claw hovered above the map as she

06:58:50.939 --> 06:58:51.599
pointed out the route.

06:58:51.720 --> 06:58:55.680
That's how she got to Penthala, Willow

06:58:55.680 --> 06:58:56.580
said wonderingly.

06:58:56.639 --> 06:58:59.580
She must have used her future site to see

06:58:59.580 --> 06:59:02.580
which direction the nearest island was, so

06:59:02.580 --> 06:59:04.380
she could rest between flights.

06:59:04.439 --> 06:59:05.700
That's amazing.

06:59:05.759 --> 06:59:09.479
And then she wrote it all out, so someone

06:59:09.479 --> 06:59:11.520
could follow the islands back across the

06:59:11.520 --> 06:59:12.360
ocean one day.

06:59:12.419 --> 06:59:16.500
Hazel's face was aglow with excitement, or

06:59:16.500 --> 06:59:19.139
a whole tribe of someone's, this is what

06:59:19.139 --> 06:59:20.880
we need to get to the distant kingdoms.

06:59:21.000 --> 06:59:22.919
Oh, wow.

06:59:22.979 --> 06:59:24.299
Cricket said.

06:59:24.360 --> 06:59:25.500
We are going.

06:59:25.560 --> 06:59:27.779
We're really going?

06:59:27.840 --> 06:59:29.939
She looked out of the trees.

06:59:30.000 --> 06:59:32.040
And Sundu could guess what she was

06:59:32.040 --> 06:59:32.279
feeling.

06:59:32.340 --> 06:59:35.700
On the one talon, the distant kingdoms

06:59:35.700 --> 06:59:38.099
and bumblebee's safety, on the other.

06:59:38.220 --> 06:59:39.360
Blue.

06:59:39.419 --> 06:59:42.540
If that were willow trapped by the other

06:59:42.540 --> 06:59:45.299
mind, Sundu wasn't sure she'd be able to

06:59:45.299 --> 06:59:47.520
fly away, no matter what the stakes

06:59:47.520 --> 06:59:47.759
were.

06:59:47.819 --> 06:59:52.200
Yes, we're going, all of us, right now

06:59:52.200 --> 06:59:53.400
Hazel said.

06:59:53.520 --> 06:59:55.139
Oh.

06:59:55.200 --> 06:59:59.459
Everyone, tsunami said, sounding slightly

06:59:59.459 --> 06:59:59.939
alarmed.

07:00:00.000 --> 07:00:02.700
I mean, right, yes, of course.

07:00:02.759 --> 07:00:06.479
Everyone, I'll just come home with a

07:00:06.479 --> 07:00:08.159
whole other tribe of dragons.

07:00:08.220 --> 07:00:12.060
Make that too, said a voice behind them.

07:00:12.119 --> 07:00:15.119
Sundu's heart nearly flew out of her

07:00:15.119 --> 07:00:17.700
chest before she spun around and saw that

07:00:17.700 --> 07:00:18.959
the speaker was IO.

07:00:19.020 --> 07:00:22.020
The tall purple silk wing glided into the

07:00:22.020 --> 07:00:24.360
throne room with a few other silk wings

07:00:24.360 --> 07:00:25.020
behind her.

07:00:25.080 --> 07:00:28.020
Sundu recognized cinnabar from the jewel

07:00:28.020 --> 07:00:30.180
hive chrysalis, who waved at her and

07:00:30.180 --> 07:00:30.540
cricket.

07:00:30.599 --> 07:00:33.000
Oh, tsunami said.

07:00:33.060 --> 07:00:35.759
I mean, sure, what difference does 7 more

07:00:35.759 --> 07:00:36.720
silk wings make?

07:00:36.779 --> 07:00:39.540
There are about 200 more of us at the

07:00:39.540 --> 07:00:41.639
mouth of the Gullet River, Io said.

07:00:41.700 --> 07:00:43.979
I thought we'd sneak in the back way to

07:00:43.979 --> 07:00:45.959
join you, but it sounds like we're too

07:00:45.959 --> 07:00:52.259
late. 200 tsunami said faintly. 200

07:00:52.259 --> 07:00:54.000
silkwings came to help us?

07:00:54.060 --> 07:00:55.380
Hazel said.

07:00:55.439 --> 07:00:58.799
Sorry, I only made it to Yellow Jacket

07:00:58.799 --> 07:01:02.220
Hive, Wasp Hive, and Jewel Hive, Io

07:01:02.220 --> 07:01:02.580
said.

07:01:02.639 --> 07:01:04.799
I didn't have time to get to the others

07:01:04.799 --> 07:01:06.840
but I can round up more if I go back

07:01:06.840 --> 07:01:07.259
now.

07:01:07.319 --> 07:01:09.419
The chrysalis is bigger than anyone

07:01:09.419 --> 07:01:09.779
thinks.

07:01:09.840 --> 07:01:15.060
200, Willow said to Sundo, her eyes

07:01:15.060 --> 07:01:15.540
shining.

07:01:15.599 --> 07:01:17.759
I told you they were worth saving.

07:01:17.819 --> 07:01:21.060
We found a way to the distant kingdoms

07:01:21.060 --> 07:01:22.799
Hazel said to Io.

07:01:22.860 --> 07:01:25.020
We need to go before Wasp and her army

07:01:25.020 --> 07:01:25.380
get here.

07:01:25.439 --> 07:01:27.659
Are we going to fight them?

07:01:27.720 --> 07:01:30.360
One of the silk wings asked nervously.

07:01:30.419 --> 07:01:34.139
We will, but not today, Hazel said.

07:01:34.200 --> 07:01:35.159
We're not ready.

07:01:35.220 --> 07:01:38.700
Wasp can infect leaf wings and silk wings

07:01:38.700 --> 07:01:38.939
now.

07:01:39.000 --> 07:01:41.819
If we stay to try to fight.

07:01:41.880 --> 07:01:43.619
We could all end up under her control

07:01:43.619 --> 07:01:45.900
with no chance of ever fighting back.

07:01:45.959 --> 07:01:49.080
IO flared her wings and growled.

07:01:49.139 --> 07:01:51.720
She can control silk wings.

07:01:51.779 --> 07:01:53.880
Then I have to go warn the chrysalis.

07:01:53.939 --> 07:01:55.500
We need to get everyone out of the

07:01:55.500 --> 07:01:55.919
hives.

07:01:55.979 --> 07:01:59.759
Hazel hesitated, then looked at Willow, as

07:01:59.759 --> 07:02:01.380
though she was hoping to find a plan in

07:02:01.380 --> 07:02:02.279
Willow's expression.

07:02:02.340 --> 07:02:04.020
What's wrong?

07:02:04.080 --> 07:02:05.220
Cricket asked.

07:02:05.279 --> 07:02:06.360
I was right.

07:02:06.419 --> 07:02:08.939
Someone needs to stay behind to gather

07:02:08.939 --> 07:02:11.220
the rest of the silk wings and bring them

07:02:11.220 --> 07:02:12.240
over the ocean too.

07:02:12.419 --> 07:02:16.560
Sundu realized what Willow and Hazel had

07:02:16.560 --> 07:02:16.979
figured out.

07:02:17.040 --> 07:02:21.060
The problem, she said, is that we'd have

07:02:21.060 --> 07:02:22.439
to leave them a copy of the map.

07:02:22.560 --> 07:02:24.840
And if there's a copy left on this

07:02:24.840 --> 07:02:27.900
continent, It could fall into the other

07:02:27.900 --> 07:02:31.139
mind's talons, Willow finished, or

07:02:31.139 --> 07:02:32.939
tendrils or whatever.

07:02:33.000 --> 07:02:37.319
Oh, Cricket said, her wings starting to

07:02:37.319 --> 07:02:37.619
droop.

07:02:37.680 --> 07:02:41.639
Hey, no, IO said loudly.

07:02:41.700 --> 07:02:44.459
Come on, there's no way we're flying to

07:02:44.459 --> 07:02:46.740
safety and leaving 100s of silk wings to

07:02:46.740 --> 07:02:47.639
be zombified.

07:02:47.700 --> 07:02:49.680
Could you seriously abandon them all like

07:02:49.680 --> 07:02:49.919
that?

07:02:49.979 --> 07:02:52.740
Seriously, when we could save them?

07:02:52.799 --> 07:02:55.919
But it puts our whole escape at risk

07:02:55.919 --> 07:02:57.479
Hazel pointed out.

07:02:57.540 --> 07:03:01.080
If we leave right now with the map, WASP

07:03:01.080 --> 07:03:02.520
and the other mind won't be able to

07:03:02.520 --> 07:03:04.919
follow, we'd be completely safe over

07:03:04.919 --> 07:03:07.680
there, but if we leave a copy of the map

07:03:07.680 --> 07:03:10.560
they could find it and come after us, they

07:03:10.560 --> 07:03:11.819
would come after us.

07:03:11.880 --> 07:03:16.020
Also, by the way, there are some other

07:03:16.020 --> 07:03:18.840
dragons over there, tsunami said in a

07:03:18.840 --> 07:03:21.419
rush, who might not be super excited

07:03:21.419 --> 07:03:24.779
about you all arriving, and PS, also

07:03:24.779 --> 07:03:26.819
would definitely not like you to be

07:03:26.819 --> 07:03:28.979
followed by a creepy hive brain army.

07:03:29.040 --> 07:03:32.580
They won't get the map, Io said

07:03:32.580 --> 07:03:33.180
fiercely.

07:03:33.240 --> 07:03:35.939
I'll hide it somewhere safe, so even if

07:03:35.939 --> 07:03:37.919
they catch me and take over my mind

07:03:37.919 --> 07:03:39.060
they'll never find it.

07:03:39.119 --> 07:03:42.479
You have to let me save the silk wings.

07:03:42.540 --> 07:03:46.500
Look, if WASP gets them, it'll double the

07:03:46.500 --> 07:03:48.599
size of her army, you don't want that

07:03:48.599 --> 07:03:48.779
right?

07:03:48.840 --> 07:03:50.700
So this is practical.

07:03:50.759 --> 07:03:53.700
And also, obviously, the right thing to

07:03:53.700 --> 07:03:53.939
do.

07:03:54.000 --> 07:03:55.619
I mean, really.

07:03:56.279 --> 07:03:58.860
Hazel sighed and rubbed a spot over her

07:03:58.860 --> 07:03:59.279
eyes.

07:03:59.340 --> 07:04:02.220
I wish great grandmother were here to

07:04:02.220 --> 07:04:03.000
tell me what to do.

07:04:03.119 --> 07:04:07.200
She is not, Sundew said, which means

07:04:07.200 --> 07:04:08.459
you're the queen for now.

07:04:08.520 --> 07:04:11.700
Hazel gave her a wry half smile.

07:04:11.759 --> 07:04:14.639
Unless Belladonna is right, and it should

07:04:14.639 --> 07:04:15.119
be you.

07:04:15.180 --> 07:04:16.860
No thanks.

07:04:16.919 --> 07:04:18.540
Sundew shook her head.

07:04:18.599 --> 07:04:20.939
You're the exact right queen for us.

07:04:21.000 --> 07:04:23.099
You have the voice and everything.

07:04:23.159 --> 07:04:24.479
I do.

07:04:24.540 --> 07:04:26.040
I've been practicing it.

07:04:26.099 --> 07:04:27.419
Hazel agreed.

07:04:27.479 --> 07:04:30.119
She lifted her chin and turned to IO.

07:04:30.180 --> 07:04:32.639
Her entire posture becoming majestic and

07:04:32.639 --> 07:04:33.119
imposing.

07:04:33.240 --> 07:04:36.779
Very well, we'll make you a copy, and

07:04:36.779 --> 07:04:38.459
you'll go save the silk wings.

07:04:38.520 --> 07:04:40.500
I can make the copy.

07:04:40.560 --> 07:04:42.180
Total volunteered.

07:04:42.240 --> 07:04:44.340
He fiddled with his claws when everyone

07:04:44.340 --> 07:04:44.939
looked at him.

07:04:45.060 --> 07:04:49.020
I, um, I have excellent penmanship.

07:04:49.139 --> 07:04:53.040
Do that, Hazel said, producing a chief of

07:04:53.040 --> 07:04:54.959
bookmaking paper from a hollow behind the

07:04:54.959 --> 07:04:55.319
throne.

07:04:55.380 --> 07:04:58.680
Just one copy, and make it perfect.

07:04:58.740 --> 07:05:01.500
Io, decide who's going with you.

07:05:01.619 --> 07:05:04.619
Me, Cinnabar said immediately.

07:05:04.680 --> 07:05:07.799
Um, Sundu interjected.

07:05:07.860 --> 07:05:09.299
One small thing.

07:05:09.360 --> 07:05:11.759
If you happen to run into 3 leaf wings

07:05:11.759 --> 07:05:13.560
out there, please bring them with you.

07:05:13.619 --> 07:05:16.380
Their names are Bryony, Pokweed, and

07:05:16.380 --> 07:05:17.040
Hemlock.

07:05:17.099 --> 07:05:19.619
Hemlock, Willow said.

07:05:19.680 --> 07:05:20.819
Your father?

07:05:20.880 --> 07:05:23.040
Sundu nodded.

07:05:23.099 --> 07:05:25.619
They weren't exactly close, she and her

07:05:25.619 --> 07:05:25.860
father.

07:05:25.919 --> 07:05:28.080
He was usually too busy following

07:05:28.080 --> 07:05:30.479
Belladonna's orders, and he was terrible

07:05:30.479 --> 07:05:32.880
with words, but he was still her father

07:05:32.880 --> 07:05:34.380
and she was leaving him here.

07:05:34.439 --> 07:05:37.619
She had no idea where he might be or how

07:05:37.619 --> 07:05:38.400
to get him a message.

07:05:38.459 --> 07:05:41.340
She just had to hope IO found him before

07:05:41.340 --> 07:05:42.419
the other mind did.

07:05:42.479 --> 07:05:45.720
Hazel was about to issue another order

07:05:45.720 --> 07:05:47.880
but stopped as they all heard crashing

07:05:47.880 --> 07:05:48.419
from overhead.

07:05:48.479 --> 07:05:51.840
Sundew felt all her muscles tense as she

07:05:51.840 --> 07:05:52.139
looked up.

07:05:52.200 --> 07:05:54.240
They couldn't have reached us this

07:05:54.240 --> 07:05:55.020
quickly.

07:05:55.020 --> 07:05:56.340
They can't be here already.

07:05:56.400 --> 07:06:00.060
Bumblebee squeaked, and Sundu realized

07:06:00.060 --> 07:06:02.040
she'd tightened her arms around her.

07:06:02.099 --> 07:06:04.500
The dragonette squirmed out of her grasp

07:06:04.500 --> 07:06:06.599
and clambered onto Cricket's back

07:06:06.599 --> 07:06:06.959
instead.

07:06:07.020 --> 07:06:10.080
But it wasn't a hive wing who came

07:06:10.080 --> 07:06:11.759
hurtling pell mell through the trees.

07:06:11.819 --> 07:06:14.759
It was one of Hazel's leaf wing guards.

07:06:14.819 --> 07:06:17.459
He catapulted to a stop in the center of

07:06:17.459 --> 07:06:19.319
the throne room, gasping for air.

07:06:19.380 --> 07:06:21.479
Are they here?

07:06:21.779 --> 07:06:22.799
Hazel asked.

07:06:22.860 --> 07:06:26.099
No, he said, shaking his head.

07:06:26.159 --> 07:06:27.779
But something else is happening.

07:06:27.840 --> 07:06:29.880
They've set the jungle on fire.

07:06:29.939 --> 07:06:32.819
Oh, no, Sandu thought.

07:06:32.939 --> 07:06:36.000
She opened out her leaf speak, and had to

07:06:36.000 --> 07:06:37.919
slam it closed almost immediately.

07:06:37.979 --> 07:06:40.799
The shrieking trees filled her head with

07:06:40.799 --> 07:06:41.819
rage and sorrow.

07:06:41.880 --> 07:06:44.639
She couldn't bear the entire jungle's

07:06:44.639 --> 07:06:45.959
panic in there along with her own.

07:06:46.020 --> 07:06:49.319
She clenched her talons into fists.

07:06:49.380 --> 07:06:51.119
The other mind couldn't win.

07:06:51.180 --> 07:06:53.580
She couldn't run away and let it think it

07:06:53.580 --> 07:06:53.880
won.

07:06:53.939 --> 07:06:56.700
Get everyone to the coast.

07:06:56.759 --> 07:06:58.080
Hazel ordered the guard.

07:06:58.139 --> 07:07:00.479
We'll gather on the north shore of the

07:07:00.479 --> 07:07:01.500
mouth of the Gullet River.

07:07:01.560 --> 07:07:03.779
Use the evacuation plan.

07:07:03.840 --> 07:07:06.959
Everyone was assigned to a trio, and all

07:07:06.959 --> 07:07:08.939
the dragonettes and elders have someone

07:07:08.939 --> 07:07:09.900
responsible for them.

07:07:09.959 --> 07:07:12.119
Tell them to go right now.

07:07:12.180 --> 07:07:15.180
He flew off, and she spun toward turtle.

07:07:15.240 --> 07:07:18.479
Draw faster, dragon from across the sea.

07:07:18.540 --> 07:07:21.479
Our dragons don't have an evacuation

07:07:21.479 --> 07:07:21.959
plan.

07:07:22.080 --> 07:07:23.880
Mandrake interjected.

07:07:23.939 --> 07:07:26.340
He saw the look on Hazel's face and

07:07:26.340 --> 07:07:29.040
stammered, but we can make one right

07:07:29.040 --> 07:07:29.340
now.

07:07:29.400 --> 07:07:32.340
Sundu grabbed his shoulders.

07:07:32.400 --> 07:07:34.139
You can organize them.

07:07:34.200 --> 07:07:36.119
You'll be great at this, mandrake.

07:07:36.180 --> 07:07:37.919
It's just like sorting the insect

07:07:37.919 --> 07:07:38.700
collection.

07:07:38.759 --> 07:07:42.779
Yes, he said, his face brightening.

07:07:42.840 --> 07:07:43.319
I am good at that.

07:07:43.439 --> 07:07:47.040
So go sort leaf wings, she said.

07:07:47.099 --> 07:07:48.779
Make sure they know where they're going

07:07:48.779 --> 07:07:50.340
or have someone to follow.

07:07:50.400 --> 07:07:53.880
He sprang away, leaping from the edge of

07:07:53.880 --> 07:07:54.540
the platform.

07:07:54.599 --> 07:07:57.180
Sundew turned and found Willow watching

07:07:57.180 --> 07:08:00.240
her, standing only a wing length away

07:08:00.240 --> 07:08:01.979
with a worried look on her face.

07:08:02.040 --> 07:08:04.860
Beyond them, the other dragons had all

07:08:04.860 --> 07:08:07.380
leaped into motion, flurrying about as

07:08:07.380 --> 07:08:09.900
turtle bent over the throne, drawing the

07:08:09.900 --> 07:08:10.439
copy of the map.

07:08:10.500 --> 07:08:13.799
Why aren't you going to organize your

07:08:13.799 --> 07:08:14.099
tribe?

07:08:14.220 --> 07:08:15.299
Willow asked.

07:08:15.360 --> 07:08:18.419
Because he'll be better at it, Sundew

07:08:18.419 --> 07:08:18.599
said.

07:08:18.720 --> 07:08:20.759
Willow narrowed her eyes.

07:08:20.819 --> 07:08:22.919
You're their natural leader.

07:08:22.979 --> 07:08:25.740
They should get used to following Queen

07:08:25.740 --> 07:08:28.380
Hazel's orders anyway, Sundu pointed

07:08:28.380 --> 07:08:28.860
out.

07:08:28.919 --> 07:08:30.240
Sundo.

07:08:30.299 --> 07:08:33.419
Willow hesitated, then took a step closer

07:08:33.419 --> 07:08:34.680
spreading her wings.

07:08:34.740 --> 07:08:37.860
Sundew spread hers as well, until the

07:08:37.860 --> 07:08:40.500
edges brushed together, encircling them

07:08:40.500 --> 07:08:42.360
in a small green bubble of quiet.

07:08:42.419 --> 07:08:45.180
Please don't do whatever you're thinking

07:08:45.180 --> 07:08:46.740
Willow whispered.

07:08:46.799 --> 07:08:50.279
I can't run away, Sundu protested.

07:08:50.400 --> 07:08:52.500
I am so angry, Willow.

07:08:52.560 --> 07:08:55.139
I want to go set all of them on fire.

07:08:55.200 --> 07:08:57.840
I want to set everyone in the world on

07:08:57.840 --> 07:09:00.959
fire, and drip poisonous sap on their

07:09:00.959 --> 07:09:03.540
heads, and pull out each of their claws

07:09:03.540 --> 07:09:06.000
and then stab them in their faces, and

07:09:06.000 --> 07:09:07.319
then set them on fire again.

07:09:07.380 --> 07:09:10.020
I know, Willow said.

07:09:10.080 --> 07:09:13.740
So do I. That caught sundew off guard.

07:09:13.799 --> 07:09:15.060
You do?

07:09:15.119 --> 07:09:17.459
Yes, Willow said.

07:09:17.580 --> 07:09:19.680
They said our trees on fire.

07:09:19.740 --> 07:09:22.500
The only trees we have left.

07:09:22.619 --> 07:09:26.459
They stole my queen, and that, that thing

07:09:26.459 --> 07:09:28.979
was going to use your leaf speak to

07:09:28.979 --> 07:09:30.479
devour all of Pentala.

07:09:30.479 --> 07:09:33.180
When it said that, I felt everything

07:09:33.180 --> 07:09:34.740
you're feeling, son do.

07:09:34.799 --> 07:09:37.439
I never let myself get mad like that

07:09:37.439 --> 07:09:37.979
before.

07:09:38.040 --> 07:09:41.880
And your anger helped you save us, Sundew

07:09:41.880 --> 07:09:43.200
said, with the thorn.

07:09:43.259 --> 07:09:45.840
Right, Willow said.

07:09:45.900 --> 07:09:47.340
Yes, fine.

07:09:47.400 --> 07:09:50.400
You can make thee, I told you so, face

07:09:50.400 --> 07:09:52.619
but I'm going to make it right back at

07:09:52.619 --> 07:09:53.340
you.

07:09:53.400 --> 07:09:55.259
You're right that you should be mad.

07:09:55.319 --> 07:09:58.200
But I'm right, that you should focus on

07:09:58.200 --> 07:10:00.240
who deserves your anger and when to

07:10:00.240 --> 07:10:00.659
fight.

07:10:00.720 --> 07:10:04.860
They all deserve my anger, Sundew said

07:10:04.860 --> 07:10:05.939
her voice rising.

07:10:06.000 --> 07:10:08.099
You know they don't.

07:10:08.159 --> 07:10:10.319
There's a monster inside them.

07:10:10.380 --> 07:10:12.659
There's a monster leading them.

07:10:12.720 --> 07:10:15.479
If you scatter your anger around like

07:10:15.479 --> 07:10:16.919
dandelion seeds.

07:10:16.979 --> 07:10:19.740
You'll hurt everyone. tire yourself out

07:10:19.740 --> 07:10:22.139
and end up with a bunch of indignant

07:10:22.139 --> 07:10:23.040
dandelions.

07:10:23.099 --> 07:10:26.099
But if you summon it all together, and

07:10:26.099 --> 07:10:28.560
aim for the monsters, you'll win.

07:10:28.619 --> 07:10:32.819
I know you will, because your sundew, my

07:10:32.819 --> 07:10:33.840
forever dragon.

07:10:33.900 --> 07:10:37.979
Sundew's eyes filled with tears, and she

07:10:37.979 --> 07:10:39.419
covered them with her talons.

07:10:39.479 --> 07:10:41.880
That's not fair.

07:10:41.939 --> 07:10:43.740
You're turning me into you.

07:10:43.799 --> 07:10:46.020
Look at my stupid leaking face.

07:10:46.080 --> 07:10:50.520
I think you mean, ah, you're my forever

07:10:50.520 --> 07:10:53.939
dragon too, Willow, Willow said, in a

07:10:53.939 --> 07:10:55.919
rather terrible imitation of Sundoo's

07:10:55.919 --> 07:10:56.159
voice.

07:10:56.220 --> 07:10:59.279
You know you are, twigs for brains.

07:10:59.340 --> 07:11:03.299
You're like, really good at this romance

07:11:03.299 --> 07:11:05.099
thing, Willow observed.

07:11:05.159 --> 07:11:08.279
Sundu laughed around her tears and

07:11:08.279 --> 07:11:11.639
thought, how can I be this furious and

07:11:11.639 --> 07:11:14.759
this sad, and this terrified, and this

07:11:14.759 --> 07:11:16.799
full of love, all at the same time?

07:11:16.860 --> 07:11:21.119
Wait, I have one more really excellent

07:11:21.119 --> 07:11:22.680
point, Willow said.

07:11:22.740 --> 07:11:25.139
If you go tearing off to fight the thing

07:11:25.139 --> 07:11:27.959
right now, fueled by super rage.

07:11:28.020 --> 07:11:32.340
It will 100% gobble up your brain, and

07:11:32.340 --> 07:11:34.799
then it'll have Pentala's most powerful

07:11:34.799 --> 07:11:35.639
leaf speak.

07:11:35.639 --> 07:11:38.939
Without Hawthorne, that plant can only

07:11:38.939 --> 07:11:41.279
grow at whatever speed it normally grows

07:11:41.279 --> 07:11:41.520
at.

07:11:41.580 --> 07:11:45.959
Probably pretty fast, sundew guest, like

07:11:45.959 --> 07:11:46.439
a weed.

07:11:46.560 --> 07:11:49.680
But nowhere near as fast as it could grow

07:11:49.680 --> 07:11:51.479
if it had Hawthorne.

07:11:51.540 --> 07:11:52.860
Or you.

07:11:52.919 --> 07:11:55.979
So you need to get far away from it more

07:11:55.979 --> 07:11:58.500
than anyone, if we want a chance of

07:11:58.500 --> 07:12:00.360
saving this continent when we come back.

07:12:00.479 --> 07:12:03.240
Sundu sighed and leaned into her.

07:12:03.299 --> 07:12:05.040
All right.

07:12:05.099 --> 07:12:06.479
You're right.

07:12:06.540 --> 07:12:11.040
As usual, Willow, Willow added, in her

07:12:11.040 --> 07:12:13.560
sundew voice, smiling through her tears.

07:12:13.619 --> 07:12:15.599
When we come back.

07:12:15.720 --> 07:12:18.959
Sundew kept those words close to her

07:12:18.959 --> 07:12:21.959
heart, as they flew to the coast, as they

07:12:21.959 --> 07:12:23.880
gathered the bedraggled remnants of their

07:12:23.880 --> 07:12:27.180
tribes, as they looked west, to the line

07:12:27.180 --> 07:12:30.240
of fire that rose toward the sunset, and

07:12:30.240 --> 07:12:32.939
then east, over the Beatle Dark Ocean

07:12:32.939 --> 07:12:34.680
into apparent nothingness.

07:12:34.740 --> 07:12:37.979
She repeated them to herself as they all

07:12:37.979 --> 07:12:40.380
lifted into the sky, following Queen

07:12:40.380 --> 07:12:43.139
Hazel's southeast to the 1st island on

07:12:43.139 --> 07:12:44.099
Clearsight's map.

07:12:44.159 --> 07:12:46.259
We are coming back.

07:12:46.319 --> 07:12:49.560
We'll get everyone to safety. figure out

07:12:49.560 --> 07:12:50.880
how to stop the other mind.

07:12:50.939 --> 07:12:52.380
Gather some allies.

07:12:52.439 --> 07:12:56.400
Sundu looked over her shoulder at the

07:12:56.400 --> 07:12:57.959
continent that was vanishing into the

07:12:57.959 --> 07:12:59.099
distance and the dusk.

07:12:59.220 --> 07:13:02.520
And then, we'll be back to deal with

07:13:02.520 --> 07:13:02.700
you.

07:13:02.819 --> 07:13:07.380
Epilogue.

07:13:07.439 --> 07:13:11.400
The white dragon paced furiously over the

07:13:11.400 --> 07:13:14.400
snow dusted grass, the sound of frozen

07:13:14.400 --> 07:13:17.279
blades cracking under her talons, carried

07:13:17.279 --> 07:13:18.840
across the wide open tundra.

07:13:18.959 --> 07:13:22.439
Draboa sighed and wheeled down toward

07:13:22.439 --> 07:13:22.680
her.

07:13:22.740 --> 07:13:24.959
She couldn't keep hiding in the clouds

07:13:24.959 --> 07:13:25.259
forever.

07:13:25.319 --> 07:13:28.799
Each moment she delayed, would only make

07:13:28.799 --> 07:13:30.720
the young ice wing queen more hostile.

07:13:30.779 --> 07:13:34.020
She landed on claws that were instantly

07:13:34.020 --> 07:13:36.599
freezing, even though she'd been alive

07:13:36.599 --> 07:13:39.180
for so long, she'd never gotten used to

07:13:39.180 --> 07:13:42.119
cold temperatures, her sand winged blood

07:13:42.119 --> 07:13:44.459
wanted to be out in the desert, rolling

07:13:44.459 --> 07:13:45.180
in warm sand.

07:13:45.299 --> 07:13:50.099
Finally, Queen Snowfall shouted, bounding

07:13:50.099 --> 07:13:52.139
over, I don't have time to wait around

07:13:52.139 --> 07:13:52.619
forever.

07:13:52.680 --> 07:13:54.779
I have an entire kingdom to run.

07:13:54.900 --> 07:13:57.540
Sorry, Treboa said.

07:13:57.599 --> 07:14:00.060
She inclined her head as politely as she

07:14:00.060 --> 07:14:01.560
could without actually bowing.

07:14:01.619 --> 07:14:04.740
Queen Glacier usually arrived after I

07:14:04.740 --> 07:14:04.979
did.

07:14:05.040 --> 07:14:08.939
Well, Snowfall dug her claws into the

07:14:08.939 --> 07:14:12.119
ground, scowling, her wings gave a little

07:14:12.119 --> 07:14:12.659
tremor.

07:14:12.720 --> 07:14:15.720
Treboa had noticed that happen before

07:14:15.720 --> 07:14:18.419
whenever she mentioned Snowfall's late

07:14:18.419 --> 07:14:18.659
mother.

07:14:18.720 --> 07:14:21.360
It made her think maybe there was a heart

07:14:21.360 --> 07:14:23.819
under Snowfall's icy exterior after all

07:14:23.819 --> 07:14:27.479
one that mourned for glacier, but there

07:14:27.479 --> 07:14:28.860
weren't many other signs of it.

07:14:28.919 --> 07:14:32.400
I guess I'm more punctual than she is

07:14:32.400 --> 07:14:35.099
snowfall blurted, so you'll have to be

07:14:35.099 --> 07:14:35.400
too.

07:14:35.459 --> 07:14:39.959
I will try, Jerboa said, inclining her

07:14:39.959 --> 07:14:40.380
head again.

07:14:40.439 --> 07:14:42.779
Have you thought about what I asked?

07:14:42.840 --> 07:14:45.840
The ice wing queen began pacing again.

07:14:45.900 --> 07:14:48.240
Before Turboa could answer, she

07:14:48.240 --> 07:14:49.200
interrupted herself.

07:14:49.259 --> 07:14:51.000
Well, I've changed my mind.

07:14:51.060 --> 07:14:53.040
I need something else instead.

07:14:53.099 --> 07:14:55.439
Turboa arched one eyebrow.

07:14:55.500 --> 07:14:57.060
Oh.

07:14:57.119 --> 07:15:01.319
The Great Ice Cliff, Snowfall said, it's

07:15:01.319 --> 07:15:02.040
completely stupid.

07:15:02.099 --> 07:15:05.880
I've always thought so, Treboa agreed.

07:15:05.939 --> 07:15:09.119
It protects our southern border from, I

07:15:09.119 --> 07:15:11.459
don't know, invading sand wings.

07:15:11.520 --> 07:15:13.200
If they were dumb enough to try that

07:15:13.200 --> 07:15:14.819
Snowfall said.

07:15:14.880 --> 07:15:17.340
I've only seen its animus magic work

07:15:17.340 --> 07:15:17.639
once.

07:15:17.700 --> 07:15:21.419
Shooting ice spears at any dragon who

07:15:21.419 --> 07:15:23.880
crosses the border that isn't an ice wing

07:15:23.880 --> 07:15:25.139
Treboa said.

07:15:25.200 --> 07:15:27.720
That's why we meet on this side of it.

07:15:27.779 --> 07:15:30.599
Snowfall rolled our eyes at the

07:15:30.599 --> 07:15:31.919
obviousness of this observation.

07:15:31.979 --> 07:15:33.900
But here's the problem.

07:15:33.959 --> 07:15:36.540
Maybe most dragons would try to attack

07:15:36.540 --> 07:15:39.540
that way overland, and so we'd be

07:15:39.540 --> 07:15:39.959
protected.

07:15:40.020 --> 07:15:43.380
But what if Dark Stalker comes back, or

07:15:43.380 --> 07:15:45.119
another dragon like him comes along.

07:15:45.180 --> 07:15:47.639
And they try coming at us over the water

07:15:47.639 --> 07:15:48.180
instead.

07:15:48.240 --> 07:15:51.000
What if they fly around and come in our

07:15:51.000 --> 07:15:54.360
northern border or east or west?

07:15:54.479 --> 07:15:56.580
Jerboa's side.

07:15:56.639 --> 07:16:00.060
It's too cold for anyone to do that, she

07:16:00.060 --> 07:16:00.360
said.

07:16:00.419 --> 07:16:03.419
The truth is, other tribes are not the

07:16:03.419 --> 07:16:05.340
slightest bit interested in stealing your

07:16:05.340 --> 07:16:05.939
kingdom.

07:16:06.000 --> 07:16:08.880
Maybe not, but they might be interested

07:16:08.880 --> 07:16:11.520
in killing all of us, Snowfall said.

07:16:11.580 --> 07:16:15.299
I can think of a very big, scary, awful

07:16:15.299 --> 07:16:17.819
dragon who was pretty recently interested

07:16:17.819 --> 07:16:18.840
in that exact thing.

07:16:18.900 --> 07:16:23.340
It was very unfortunate that Snowfall's

07:16:23.340 --> 07:16:25.500
rain had begun as a result of the plague

07:16:25.500 --> 07:16:27.659
Dark Stalker had sent to wipe out the ice

07:16:27.659 --> 07:16:28.380
wings.

07:16:28.380 --> 07:16:31.500
He hadn't succeeded, and he was gone now

07:16:31.500 --> 07:16:34.740
but as a result, Snowfall had ended up as

07:16:34.740 --> 07:16:37.259
an incredibly paranoid, perpetually

07:16:37.259 --> 07:16:40.619
anxious queen, which made her exhausting

07:16:40.619 --> 07:16:41.759
for Jaboa to deal with.

07:16:41.819 --> 07:16:45.720
So I want you to expand the great ice

07:16:45.720 --> 07:16:47.819
cliff for me, said the queen.

07:16:47.880 --> 07:16:50.400
She waved one talent at a kingdom behind

07:16:50.400 --> 07:16:50.639
her.

07:16:50.700 --> 07:16:54.240
I wanted to go all the way around, along

07:16:54.240 --> 07:16:55.860
the entire border of the kingdom.

07:16:55.979 --> 07:16:59.639
She paused, then gave Jerboa a narrow

07:16:59.639 --> 07:17:00.240
suspicious look.

07:17:00.299 --> 07:17:03.659
Something has happened, but you can't go

07:17:03.659 --> 07:17:04.799
tell Queen Thorn.

07:17:04.860 --> 07:17:07.979
I have never spoken to Queen Thorn.

07:17:08.099 --> 07:17:10.020
Treboa said truthfully.

07:17:10.080 --> 07:17:12.900
That didn't mean she never would, but

07:17:12.900 --> 07:17:15.000
snowfall seemed satisfied enough with her

07:17:15.000 --> 07:17:15.180
answer.

07:17:15.299 --> 07:17:18.060
I have scouts patrolling around our

07:17:18.060 --> 07:17:19.319
borders day and night.

07:17:19.380 --> 07:17:22.619
Snowfall said in a hushed voice.

07:17:22.680 --> 07:17:24.900
I've told them to fly out into the ocean

07:17:24.900 --> 07:17:27.599
as far as they can, to keep an eye on

07:17:27.599 --> 07:17:29.939
everything for me, just in case someone

07:17:29.939 --> 07:17:31.259
does attack.

07:17:31.319 --> 07:17:34.680
Oh, Jerboa said again.

07:17:34.740 --> 07:17:36.959
She had discovered that this was often

07:17:36.959 --> 07:17:39.000
the only contribution she needed to make

07:17:39.000 --> 07:17:41.639
to a conversation, especially when it was

07:17:41.639 --> 07:17:42.180
with a queen.

07:17:42.240 --> 07:17:45.779
And guess what one of them saw.

07:17:45.840 --> 07:17:47.520
Snowfall whispered.

07:17:47.580 --> 07:17:49.799
Druboa arched her brows again.

07:17:49.860 --> 07:17:51.599
Dragons!

07:17:51.659 --> 07:17:55.319
Snowfall shouted, 100s of dragons, coming

07:17:55.319 --> 07:17:57.299
this way, across the ocean.

07:17:57.360 --> 07:17:59.639
I don't know from where, but they're

07:17:59.639 --> 07:18:01.680
coming from my kingdom, and I won't let

07:18:01.680 --> 07:18:01.979
them.

07:18:02.040 --> 07:18:05.099
Build me more ice cliff right now.

07:18:05.159 --> 07:18:09.060
Maybe they're not coming for your

07:18:09.060 --> 07:18:09.479
kingdom.

07:18:09.599 --> 07:18:11.340
Jerboa pointed out.

07:18:11.400 --> 07:18:13.680
She had a pretty good idea of what

07:18:13.680 --> 07:18:16.139
dragons those were, from what Moon and

07:18:16.139 --> 07:18:17.099
Luna had said.

07:18:17.159 --> 07:18:19.680
She hadn't realized they were so close

07:18:19.680 --> 07:18:20.220
though.

07:18:20.279 --> 07:18:22.740
Maybe instead of shutting them out with

07:18:22.740 --> 07:18:24.659
magic, you should see if they're all

07:18:24.659 --> 07:18:24.900
right.

07:18:24.959 --> 07:18:26.520
Maybe they need help.

07:18:26.580 --> 07:18:31.080
Snowfall screamed.

07:18:31.139 --> 07:18:34.500
No, it's an invasion, and you have to

07:18:34.500 --> 07:18:34.979
stop it.

07:18:35.040 --> 07:18:39.720
Queen Snowfall, Treboa said firmly. trying

07:18:39.720 --> 07:18:41.639
to cut off the tantrum before it got much

07:18:41.639 --> 07:18:41.880
worse.

07:18:42.000 --> 07:18:44.639
Your mother and I had an agreement.

07:18:44.700 --> 07:18:47.459
She never abused my animus powers.

07:18:47.520 --> 07:18:49.799
And look how she ended up.

07:18:49.860 --> 07:18:52.799
Snowfall cried, even more frantic.

07:18:52.919 --> 07:18:55.319
She could have won the war of Sandwing

07:18:55.319 --> 07:18:55.860
succession.

07:18:55.919 --> 07:18:58.020
She could have protected the tribe from

07:18:58.020 --> 07:18:58.799
the plague.

07:18:58.860 --> 07:19:01.200
No, Jerboa interrupted.

07:19:01.259 --> 07:19:04.020
If she had come to me then, if I had

07:19:04.020 --> 07:19:06.060
known, we would have stopped it sooner

07:19:06.060 --> 07:19:06.840
and saved her.

07:19:06.900 --> 07:19:08.700
But she couldn't get to me.

07:19:08.759 --> 07:19:10.439
She was too sick.

07:19:10.500 --> 07:19:12.299
That's why she sent you.

07:19:12.419 --> 07:19:15.599
And I rather wish she hadn't.

07:19:15.659 --> 07:19:18.779
Queen Glacier was a reasonable dragon to

07:19:18.779 --> 07:19:19.139
deal with.

07:19:19.200 --> 07:19:22.139
Queen Snowfall on the other talon.

07:19:22.200 --> 07:19:24.779
She should have told me about you sooner

07:19:24.840 --> 07:19:26.340
snowfall said.

07:19:26.459 --> 07:19:28.979
Our own animus dragon is exactly what we

07:19:28.979 --> 07:19:29.400
need.

07:19:29.459 --> 07:19:34.319
I'm not your animus dragon, Jerbo

07:19:34.319 --> 07:19:36.900
observed, and I have bad news.

07:19:37.020 --> 07:19:39.959
She saw the panic sparking in Snowfall's

07:19:39.959 --> 07:19:41.520
eyes, and hurried on quickly.

07:19:41.580 --> 07:19:44.159
Animus magic isn't working.

07:19:44.220 --> 07:19:46.259
Right now, apparently.

07:19:46.319 --> 07:19:48.840
Queen Snowfall stared at her.

07:19:48.900 --> 07:19:52.439
Confusion and rage and alarm battling in

07:19:52.439 --> 07:19:52.919
her expression.

07:19:52.979 --> 07:19:54.779
Sorry about that.

07:19:54.900 --> 07:19:57.959
Truboa added, What?

07:19:58.020 --> 07:19:59.939
Snowfall roared.

07:20:00.060 --> 07:20:01.919
Jerboa spread her talons.

07:20:01.979 --> 07:20:03.900
It just isn't.

07:20:03.959 --> 07:20:06.240
It's not working for me or any of the

07:20:06.240 --> 07:20:07.740
other animus dragons.

07:20:07.799 --> 07:20:11.040
All previous spells are still working, but

07:20:11.040 --> 07:20:12.419
nothing new can be cast.

07:20:12.479 --> 07:20:15.479
She shrugged, her wings rising and

07:20:15.479 --> 07:20:16.500
falling in the chilly air.

07:20:16.560 --> 07:20:18.900
How is that possible?

07:20:18.959 --> 07:20:20.340
Snowfall shouted.

07:20:20.400 --> 07:20:22.319
Why is this happening now?

07:20:22.380 --> 07:20:24.119
Just when I found you.

07:20:24.180 --> 07:20:26.939
I need that magic.

07:20:27.000 --> 07:20:29.819
Or perhaps, Jerboa said.

07:20:29.880 --> 07:20:31.740
This continent would be better off

07:20:31.740 --> 07:20:33.599
without animus magic for a little while.

07:20:33.659 --> 07:20:36.779
Snowfall jabbed one claw at her.

07:20:36.840 --> 07:20:38.459
Prove it.

07:20:38.520 --> 07:20:39.419
Prove that it doesn't work.

07:20:39.479 --> 07:20:43.139
Jerboa agreeably snapped a frozen twig up

07:20:43.139 --> 07:20:43.560
from the ground.

07:20:43.619 --> 07:20:47.279
I hereby enchant this twig to turn

07:20:47.279 --> 07:20:48.900
anything it touches green.

07:20:48.959 --> 07:20:50.220
She said.

07:20:50.279 --> 07:20:51.959
She held it out to Snowfall.

07:20:52.080 --> 07:20:55.319
Absolutely not, Snowfall snapped.

07:20:55.439 --> 07:20:57.659
With another shrug.

07:20:57.720 --> 07:20:58.919
Jerboa tapped herself with it.

07:20:58.979 --> 07:21:01.979
Shoulder, snout, wings.

07:21:02.040 --> 07:21:03.779
Her colors stayed the same.

07:21:03.840 --> 07:21:07.139
She poked a nearby rock, but it remained

07:21:07.139 --> 07:21:08.220
as gray as ever.

07:21:08.279 --> 07:21:11.040
Snowfall grabbed the twig out of her

07:21:11.040 --> 07:21:14.099
talons and glared at it, then threw it as

07:21:14.099 --> 07:21:14.639
far as she could.

07:21:14.700 --> 07:21:18.659
Treboa kept quiet, resisting the urge to

07:21:18.659 --> 07:21:19.979
say, see?

07:21:20.099 --> 07:21:24.000
If you can't do magic, Queen Snowball

07:21:24.000 --> 07:21:26.099
spat, then what good are you?

07:21:26.159 --> 07:21:28.380
You're completely useless.

07:21:28.439 --> 07:21:31.200
Jerboa watched the queen spin and fly

07:21:31.200 --> 07:21:31.560
away.

07:21:31.619 --> 07:21:34.740
Fury radiating off her like a cloud of

07:21:34.740 --> 07:21:36.060
ice particles.

07:21:36.180 --> 07:21:39.779
Completely useless, Treboa thought

07:21:39.840 --> 07:21:42.599
allowing herself the smallest of smiles.

07:21:42.659 --> 07:21:44.159
Yes.

07:21:44.220 --> 07:21:47.099
Just like I've always wanted.

07:21:47.220 --> 07:21:53.099
A guide to the Dragons of Penthala.

07:21:53.159 --> 07:21:55.619
Hive wings.

07:21:55.680 --> 07:21:57.060
Description.

07:21:57.119 --> 07:22:01.500
Red, yellow. and or orange, but always

07:22:01.500 --> 07:22:06.000
mixed with some black scales, 4 wings

07:22:06.000 --> 07:22:08.159
vary from dragon to dragon.

07:22:08.220 --> 07:22:11.400
Examples include deadly stingers that can

07:22:11.400 --> 07:22:13.740
extend from their wrists to stab their

07:22:13.740 --> 07:22:16.740
enemies, Venom in their teeth or claws.

07:22:16.860 --> 07:22:20.159
A paralyzing toxin that can immobilize

07:22:20.159 --> 07:22:20.700
their prey.

07:22:20.759 --> 07:22:24.060
Others can spray boiling acid from a

07:22:24.060 --> 07:22:27.779
stinger on their tails, Queen, Queen

07:22:27.779 --> 07:22:28.500
Wasp.

07:22:28.560 --> 07:22:31.200
Silk wings.

07:22:31.200 --> 07:22:32.700
Description.

07:22:32.759 --> 07:22:35.819
Silkwing dragonettes are born wingless

07:22:35.819 --> 07:22:38.400
but go through a metamorphosis at age 6

07:22:38.400 --> 07:22:42.000
when they develop 4 huge wings and silk

07:22:42.000 --> 07:22:44.639
spinning abilities, as beautiful and

07:22:44.639 --> 07:22:47.759
gentle as butterflies, with scales in any

07:22:47.759 --> 07:22:50.220
color under the sun, except black.

07:22:50.340 --> 07:22:54.900
Abilities, can spin silk from glands on

07:22:54.900 --> 07:22:57.299
their wrists to create webs or other

07:22:57.299 --> 07:23:00.360
woven articles, can detect vibrations

07:23:00.360 --> 07:23:02.220
with their antennae to assess threats.

07:23:02.279 --> 07:23:05.880
Queen, Queen Wasp.

07:23:05.939 --> 07:23:09.299
The last silk wing queen, before the tree

07:23:09.299 --> 07:23:11.580
wars, was queen monarch.

07:23:11.580 --> 07:23:14.040
Leaf wings.

07:23:14.099 --> 07:23:17.459
Description. wiped out during the tree

07:23:17.459 --> 07:23:20.159
wars with the hive wings, but while they

07:23:20.159 --> 07:23:22.259
lived, this tribe had green and brown

07:23:22.259 --> 07:23:24.840
scales, and wings shaped like leaves.

07:23:24.900 --> 07:23:26.639
Abilities.

07:23:26.700 --> 07:23:29.880
Could absorb energy from sunlight, and

07:23:29.880 --> 07:23:31.319
were accomplished gardeners.

07:23:31.380 --> 07:23:34.619
Some were rumored to have unusual control

07:23:34.619 --> 07:23:35.580
over plants.

07:23:35.639 --> 07:23:37.380
Queen.

07:23:37.439 --> 07:23:40.680
Last known queen of the leaf wings was

07:23:40.680 --> 07:23:44.580
Queen Sequoia, about 50 years ago, at the

07:23:44.580 --> 07:23:45.900
time of the tree wars.

